1.1.1|1.1.1 vRddhiraadaich|vRddhiraadaich|vRddhiraadaich 1.1.1|वृद्धिरादैच्|वृद्धिरादैच् १.१.१|१.१.१|१.१.१ वृद्धिरादैच्
आ, ऐ and औ are called वृद्धि।<br><br>Terms: वृद्धि

1.1.2|1.1.2 adeNG guNaH|adeNG guNaH|adeNG guNaH 1.1.2|अदेङ् गुणः|अदेङ् गुणः १.१.२|१.१.२|१.१.२ अदेङ् गुणः
अ, ए and ओ are called गुण।<br><br>Terms: गुण

1.1.3|1.1.3 iko guNavRddhii|iko guNavRddhii|iko guNavRddhii 1.1.3|इको गुणवृद्धी|इको गुणवृद्धी १.१.३|१.१.३|१.१.३ इको गुणवृद्धी
In the absence of any special role whenever गुण or वृद्धि is enjoined about any expression by using the terms गुण or वृद्धि, it is to be understood to come in the room of the इक् (इ, उ, ऋ, लृ) of that expression.<br><br>Terms: गुण-वृद्धि

1.1.4|1.1.4 na dhaatulopa aardhadhaatuke|na dhaatulopa aardhadhaatuke|na dhaatulopa aardhadhaatuke 1.1.4|न धातुलोप आर्धधातुके|न धातुलोप आर्धधातुके १.१.४|१.१.४|१.१.४ न धातुलोप आर्धधातुके
The गुण and वृद्धि substitutions which otherwise would have presented themselves do not take place, when such an आर्धधातुक ३.४.११४ affix follows, which causes a portion of the root to be elided.<br><br>Terms: गुण-वृद्धि

1.1.5|1.1.5 kkNGiti cha|kkNGiti cha|kkNGiti cha 1.1.5|क्क्ङिति च|क्क्ङिति च १.१.५|१.१.५|१.१.५ क्क्ङिति च
And that, which otherwise would have caused गुण or वृद्धि, does not do so, when it has an indicatory क् , ग् , ङ्।<br><br>Terms: गुण-वृद्धि

1.1.6|1.1.6 diidhiiveviiTaam|diidhiiveviiTaam|diidhiiveviiTaam 1.1.6|दीधीवेवीटाम्|दीधीवेवीटाम् १.१.६|१.१.६|१.१.६ दीधीवेवीटाम्
The गुण and वृद्धि substitutions which otherwise would have presented themselves do not however come, in the place of the vowels of दिधि 'to shine' and वेवि 'to go', and of the augment called इट् ।<br><br>Terms: गुण-वृद्धि

1.1.7|1.1.7 halo.anantaraaH saMyogaH|halo.anantaraaH saMyogaH|halo.anantaraaH saMyogaH 1.1.7|हलोऽनन्तराः संयोगः|हलोऽनन्तराः संयोगः १.१.७|१.१.७|१.१.७ हलोऽनन्तराः संयोगः
Consonants unseparated by a vowel are called conjunct consonants.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.8|1.1.8 mukhanaasikaavachano.anunaasikaH|mukhanaasikaavachano.anunaasikaH|mukhanaasikaavachano.anunaasikaH 1.1.8|मुखनासिकावचनोऽनुनासिकः|मुखनासिकावचनोऽनुनासिकः १.१.८|१.१.८|१.१.८ मुखनासिकावचनोऽनुनासिकः
That which is pronounced by the nose along with the mouth is called अनुनासिक or nasal.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.9|1.1.9 tulyaasyaprayatnaM savarNam|tulyaasyaprayatnaM savarNam|tulyaasyaprayatnaM savarNam 1.1.9|तुल्यास्यप्रयत्नं सवर्णम्|तुल्यास्यप्रयत्नं सवर्णम् १.१.९|१.१.९|१.१.९ तुल्यास्यप्रयत्नं सवर्णम्
Those whose place of utterance and effort are equal are called सवर्ण or homogeneous letters.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.10|1.1.10 naajjhalau|naajjhalau|naajjhalau 1.1.10|नाज्झलौ|नाज्झलौ १.१.१०|१.१.१०|१.१.१० नाज्झलौ
There is however no homogeneity between vowels and consonants, though their place and effort be equal.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.11|1.1.11 iiduudeddvivachanaM pragRhyam|iiduudeddvivachanaM pragRhyam|iiduudeddvivachanaM pragRhyam 1.1.11|ईदूदेद्द्विवचनं प्रगृह्यम्|ईदूदेद्द्विवचनं प्रगृह्यम् १.१.११|१.१.११|१.१.११ ईदूदेद्द्विवचनं प्रगृह्यम्
A dual case affix ending in ई or ऊ or ए is called प्रगृह्य , or excepted vowels which do not admit सन्धि or conjugation.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.12|1.1.12 adaso maat|adaso maat|adaso maat 1.1.12|अदसो मात्|अदसो मात् १.१.१२|१.१.१२|१.१.१२ अदसो मात्
The same letters after the म् of the pronoun अदस् are प्रगृह्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.13|1.1.13 she|she|she 1.1.13|शे|शे १.१.१३|१.१.१३|१.१.१३ शे
The affix शे (the Vedic substitute of the case-affixes) is a प्रगृह्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.14|1.1.14 nipaata ekaajanaaNG|nipaata ekaajanaaNG|nipaata ekaajanaaNG 1.1.14|निपात एकाजनाङ्|निपात एकाजनाङ् १.१.१४|१.१.१४|१.१.१४ निपात एकाजनाङ्
A particle १.४.५६ consisting of a single vowel, with the exception of the particle आङ् is प्रगृह्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.15|1.1.15 ot|ot|ot 1.1.15|ओत्|ओत् १.१.१५|१.१.१५|१.१.१५ ओत्
The final ओ of a particle is a प्रगृह्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.16|1.1.16 sambuddhau shaakalyasyetaavanaarShe|sambuddhau shaakalyasyetaavanaarShe|sambuddhau shaakalyasyetaavanaarShe 1.1.16|सम्बुद्धौ शाकल्यस्येतावनार्षे|सम्बुद्धौ शाकल्यस्येतावनार्षे १.१.१६|१.१.१६|१.१.१६ सम्बुद्धौ शाकल्यस्येतावनार्षे
The final ओ of a vocative singular २.३.४९ before the word इति according to शाकल्य , in a secular or non-vedic literature is a प्रगृह्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.17|1.1.17 uNJaH|uNJaH|uNJaH 1.1.17|उञः|उञः १.१.१७|१.१.१७|१.१.१७ उञः
The particle ऊञ् before इति , according to शाकल्य is a प्रगृह्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.18|1.1.18 Uँ|Uँ|Uँ 1.1.18|ऊँ|ऊँ १.१.१८|१.१.१८|१.१.१८ ऊँ
The particle ऊँ replaces उञ in non-vedic literature and it is a प्रगृह्य in the opinion of शाकल्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.19|1.1.19 iiduutau cha saptamyarthe|iiduutau cha saptamyarthe|iiduutau cha saptamyarthe 1.1.19|ईदूतौ च सप्तम्यर्थे|ईदूतौ च सप्तम्यर्थे १.१.१९|१.१.१९|१.१.१९ ईदूतौ च सप्तम्यर्थे
The final ई and ऊ of words giving the sense of the locative case are प्रगृह्य।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.20|1.1.20 daadhaa ghvadaap|daadhaa ghvadaap|daadhaa ghvadaap 1.1.20|दाधा घ्वदाप्|दाधा घ्वदाप् १.१.२०|१.१.२०|१.१.२० दाधा घ्वदाप्
The words having the form of दा 'to give' and धा 'to place' are called घु।<br><br>Terms: घु-संज्ञा

1.1.21|1.1.21 aadyantavadekasmin|aadyantavadekasmin|aadyantavadekasmin 1.1.21|आद्यन्तवदेकस्मिन्|आद्यन्तवदेकस्मिन् १.१.२१|१.१.२१|१.१.२१ आद्यन्तवदेकस्मिन्
An operation should be performed on a single letter, as upon an initial or upon a final.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.22|1.1.22 taraptamapau ghaH|taraptamapau ghaH|taraptamapau ghaH 1.1.22|तरप्तमपौ घः|तरप्तमपौ घः १.१.२२|१.१.२२|१.१.२२ तरप्तमपौ घः
The affixes तरप् and तमप् ae called घ।<br><br>Terms: घ-संज्ञा

1.1.23|1.1.23 bahugaNavatuDati saMkhyaa|bahugaNavatuDati saMkhyaa|bahugaNavatuDati saMkhyaa 1.1.23|बहुगणवतुडति संख्या|बहुगणवतुडति संख्या १.१.२३|१.१.२३|१.१.२३ बहुगणवतुडति संख्या
The words बहु 'many' , गण 'class' and the words ending in the affix वतु -- यद्तदेतेभ्यः परिमाणे वतुप्‌ ५.२.३९ and डति -- किमः संख्यापरिमाणे डति च ५.२.४१ are called numerals (संख्या).<br><br>Terms: संख्या

1.1.24|1.1.24 ShNaantaa ShaT|ShNaantaa ShaT|ShNaantaa ShaT 1.1.24|ष्णान्ता षट्|ष्णान्ता षट् १.१.२४|१.१.२४|१.१.२४ ष्णान्ता षट्
The संख्या-s having ष or न as their final are called षट्।<br><br>Terms: संख्या

1.1.25|1.1.25 Dati cha|Dati cha|Dati cha 1.1.25|डति च|डति च १.१.२५|१.१.२५|१.१.२५ डति च
And the संख्या-s ending with the affix डति are called षट्।<br><br>Terms: संख्या

1.1.26|1.1.26 ktaktavatuu niShThaa|ktaktavatuu niShThaa|ktaktavatuu niShThaa 1.1.26|क्तक्तवतू निष्ठा|क्तक्तवतू निष्ठा १.१.२६|१.१.२६|१.१.२६ क्तक्तवतू निष्ठा
The affixes क्त and क्तवतु are called निष्ठा।<br><br>Terms: निष्ठा

1.1.27|1.1.27 sarvaadiini sarvanaamaani|sarvaadiini sarvanaamaani|sarvaadiini sarvanaamaani 1.1.27|सर्वादीनि सर्वनामानि|सर्वादीनि सर्वनामानि १.१.२७|१.१.२७|१.१.२७ सर्वादीनि सर्वनामानि
The words सर्व 'all' and the rest are called सर्वनाम or pronouns.<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

1.1.28|1.1.28 vibhaaShaa diksamaase bahuvriihau|vibhaaShaa diksamaase bahuvriihau|vibhaaShaa diksamaase bahuvriihau 1.1.28|विभाषा दिक्समासे बहुव्रीहौ|विभाषा दिक्समासे बहुव्रीहौ १.१.२८|१.१.२८|१.१.२८ विभाषा दिक्समासे बहुव्रीहौ
The above words are optionally सर्वनाम when they occur in a बहुव्रीही compound signifying direction -- दिङ्नामान्यन्तराले २.२.२६.<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही

1.1.29|1.1.29 na bahuvriihau|na bahuvriihau|na bahuvriihau 1.1.29|न बहुव्रीहौ|न बहुव्रीहौ १.१.२९|१.१.२९|१.१.२९ न बहुव्रीहौ
The words सर्व etc. are not सर्वनाम when they occur in a बहुव्रीही compound.<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

1.1.30|1.1.30 tRtiiyaasamaase|tRtiiyaasamaase|tRtiiyaasamaase 1.1.30|तृतीयासमासे|तृतीयासमासे १.१.३०|१.१.३०|१.१.३० तृतीयासमासे
In the Instrumental Determinative Compounds the words सर्व etc. are not सर्वनाम।<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

1.1.31|1.1.31 dvandve cha|dvandve cha|dvandve cha 1.1.31|द्वन्द्वे च|द्वन्द्वे च १.१.३१|१.१.३१|१.१.३१ द्वन्द्वे च
And in Collective Compound -- दिङ्नामान्यन्तराले २.२.२६, the words सर्व etc. are not सर्वनाम।<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

1.1.32|1.1.32 vibhaaShaa jasi|vibhaaShaa jasi|vibhaaShaa jasi 1.1.32|विभाषा जसि|विभाषा जसि १.१.३२|१.१.३२|१.१.३२ विभाषा जसि
Their द्वन्द compounds are optionally सर्वनाम when the nominative plural termination जस् follows.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

1.1.33|1.1.33 prathamacharamatayaalpaardhakatipayanemaashcha|prathamacharamatayaalpaardhakatipayanemaashcha|prathamacharamatayaalpaardhakatipayanemaashcha 1.1.33|प्रथमचरमतयाल्पार्धकतिपयनेमाश्च|प्रथमचरमतयाल्पार्धकतिपयनेमाश्च १.१.३३|१.१.३३|१.१.३३ प्रथमचरमतयाल्पार्धकतिपयनेमाश्च
And also the words प्रथम 'first', चर्म 'last', words with the affix तय -- संख्याया अवयवे तयप्‌ ५.२.४२, अल्प 'few', अर्ध 'half', कतिपय 'some' and नेम 'half' are optionally सर्वनाम , before the Nominative Plural termination.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति

1.1.34|1.1.34 puurvaparaavaradaxiNottaraaparaadharaaNi|puurvaparaavaradaxiNottaraaparaadharaaNi|puurvaparaavaradaxiNottaraaparaadharaaNi 1.1.34|पूर्वपरावरदक्षिणोत्तरापराधराणि|पूर्वपरावरदक्षिणोत्तरापराधराणि १.१.३४|१.१.३४|१.१.३४ पूर्वपरावरदक्षिणोत्तरापराधराणि
The words पूर्व 'prior', पर 'after', अवर 'posterior', दक्षिण 'south', उत्तर 'north', अपर 'other', अधर 'inferior', when they discriminate relative position, not when they are appellatives, are optionally सर्वनाम before the affix जस्।<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

1.1.35|1.1.35 svamaJNaatidhanaakhyaayaam|svamaJNaatidhanaakhyaayaam|svamaJNaatidhanaakhyaayaam 1.1.35|स्वमज्ञातिधनाख्यायाम्|स्वमज्ञातिधनाख्यायाम् १.१.३५|१.१.३५|१.१.३५ स्वमज्ञातिधनाख्यायाम्
The word स्व 'own', when it does not mean a kinsman or property is optionally सर्वनाम before the affix जस्।<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

1.1.36|1.1.36 antaraM bahiryogopasaMvyaanayoH|antaraM bahiryogopasaMvyaanayoH|antaraM bahiryogopasaMvyaanayoH 1.1.36|अन्तरं बहिर्योगोपसंव्यानयोः|अन्तरं बहिर्योगोपसंव्यानयोः १.१.३६|१.१.३६|१.१.३६ अन्तरं बहिर्योगोपसंव्यानयोः
The word अन्तर always being a सर्वनाम , when meaning 'outer' or 'lower garment', is optionally so before the affix जस्।<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

1.1.37|1.1.37 svaraadinipaatamavyayam|svaraadinipaatamavyayam|svaraadinipaatamavyayam 1.1.37|स्वरादिनिपातमव्ययम्|स्वरादिनिपातमव्ययम् १.१.३७|१.१.३७|१.१.३७ स्वरादिनिपातमव्ययम्
The words स्वर् 'heaven' etc. and the particles -- निपात एकाजनाङ् १.४.५६, are called अव्यय or indeclinables.<br><br>Terms: अव्यय

1.1.38|1.1.38 taddhitashchaasarvavibhaktiH|taddhitashchaasarvavibhaktiH|taddhitashchaasarvavibhaktiH 1.1.38|तद्धितश्चासर्वविभक्तिः|तद्धितश्चासर्वविभक्तिः १.१.३८|१.१.३८|१.१.३८ तद्धितश्चासर्वविभक्तिः
And the words ending in तद्धित or secondary affixes -- तद्धिताः ४.१.७६, which are not declined in all the cases are also अव्यय or indeclinables.<br><br>Terms: अव्यय

1.1.39|1.1.39 kRnmejantaH|kRnmejantaH|kRnmejantaH 1.1.39|कृन्मेजन्तः|कृन्मेजन्तः १.१.३९|१.१.३९|१.१.३९ कृन्मेजन्तः
The words formed by those कृत् or primary affixes -- कृदतिङ् ३.१.९३, which end with a म् or in a ए , ओ , ऐ and औ are also अव्यय or indeclinables.<br><br>Terms: अव्यय

1.1.40|1.1.40 ktvaatosunkasunaH|ktvaatosunkasunaH|ktvaatosunkasunaH 1.1.40|क्त्वातोसुन्कसुनः|क्त्वातोसुन्कसुनः १.१.४०|१.१.४०|१.१.४० क्त्वातोसुन्कसुनः
The words ending in क्त्व , तोसुन् -- भावलक्षणे स्थेण्कृञ्वदिचरिहुतमिजनिभ्यस्तोसुन् ३.४.१६, and कसुन् are अव्यय or indeclinables.<br><br>Terms: अव्यय

1.1.41|1.1.41 avyayiibhaavashcha|avyayiibhaavashcha|avyayiibhaavashcha 1.1.41|अव्ययीभावश्च|अव्ययीभावश्च १.१.४१|१.१.४१|१.१.४१ अव्ययीभावश्च
The compound called अव्ययीभाव is also अव्यय or indeclinable.<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

1.1.42|1.1.42 shi sarvanaamasthaanam|shi sarvanaamasthaanam|shi sarvanaamasthaanam 1.1.42|शि सर्वनामस्थानम्|शि सर्वनामस्थानम् १.१.४२|१.१.४२|१.१.४२ शि सर्वनामस्थानम्
The affix शि ७.१.२० is called सर्वनामस्थान।<br><br>Terms: सर्वनामस्थान

1.1.43|1.1.43 suDanapuMsakasya|suDanapuMsakasya|suDanapuMsakasya 1.1.43|सुडनपुंसकस्य|सुडनपुंसकस्य १.१.४३|१.१.४३|१.१.४३ सुडनपुंसकस्य
The first five case affixes comprised in the प्रत्यहार सुट् (i.e. the three case-terminations of the Nominative, and the singular and dual of the Accusative) are also called सर्वनामस्थान , except the case-affixes of the neuter gender.<br><br>Terms: सर्वनामस्थान

1.1.44|1.1.44 na veti vibhaaShaa|na veti vibhaaShaa|na veti vibhaaShaa 1.1.44|न वेति विभाषा|न वेति विभाषा १.१.४४|१.१.४४|१.१.४४ न वेति विभाषा
May or may not' is called विभाषा or option.<br><br>Terms: विभाषा

1.1.45|1.1.45 igyaNaH samprasaaraNam|igyaNaH samprasaaraNam|igyaNaH samprasaaraNam 1.1.45|इग्यणः सम्प्रसारणम्|इग्यणः सम्प्रसारणम् १.१.४५|१.१.४५|१.१.४५ इग्यणः सम्प्रसारणम्
The इक् vowels which replace the semi-vowels यण् are called सम्प्रसारण।<br><br>Terms: सम्प्रसारण

1.1.46|1.1.46 aadyantau Takitau|aadyantau Takitau|aadyantau Takitau 1.1.46|आद्यन्तौ टकितौ|आद्यन्तौ टकितौ १.१.४६|१.१.४६|१.१.४६ आद्यन्तौ टकितौ
Of whatsoever the augments enunciated are distinguished by an indicatory ट् or क् , they precede or follow it accordingly.<br><br>Terms: augment

1.1.47|1.1.47 midacho.antyaatparaH|midacho.antyaatparaH|midacho.antyaatparaH 1.1.47|मिदचोऽन्त्यात्परः|मिदचोऽन्त्यात्परः १.१.४७|१.१.४७|१.१.४७ मिदचोऽन्त्यात्परः
The augment that has an indicatory म् comes after the last among the vowels and becomes the final position of that which it augments.<br><br>Terms: augment

1.1.48|1.1.48 echa igghrasvaadeshe|echa igghrasvaadeshe|echa igghrasvaadeshe 1.1.48|एच इग्घ्रस्वादेशे|एच इग्घ्रस्वादेशे १.१.४८|१.१.४८|१.१.४८ एच इग्घ्रस्वादेशे
Of एच् vowels, इक् is the substitute, when short is to be substituted.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.49|1.1.49 ShaShThii sthaaneyogaa|ShaShThii sthaaneyogaa|ShaShThii sthaaneyogaa 1.1.49|षष्ठी स्थानेयोगा|षष्ठी स्थानेयोगा १.१.४९|१.१.४९|१.१.४९ षष्ठी स्थानेयोगा
The force of the negative case in a sūtra is that of the phrase 'in the place of', when no special rules qualify the sense of Genitive 6th-Case.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.50|1.1.50 sthaane.antaratamaH|sthaane.antaratamaH|sthaane.antaratamaH 1.1.50|स्थानेऽन्तरतमः|स्थानेऽन्तरतमः १.१.५०|१.१.५०|१.१.५० स्थानेऽन्तरतमः
When a common term is obtained as a substitute, the likest of its significates to that in the place of which it comes, is the actual substitute.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.51|1.1.51 uraँN raparaH|uraँN raparaH|uraँN raparaH 1.1.51|उरँण् रपरः|उरँण् रपरः १.१.५१|१.१.५१|१.१.५१ उरँण् रपरः
When a letter of अण् प्रत्यहार comes as a substitute for ऋ it is always followed by र्।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.52|1.1.52 alo.antyasya|alo.antyasya|alo.antyasya 1.1.52|अलोऽन्त्यस्य|अलोऽन्त्यस्य १.१.५२|१.१.५२|१.१.५२ अलोऽन्त्यस्य
The substitute takes the place of only the final letter (of that which is denoted by a term exhibited in the Genitive 6th-Case.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.53|1.1.53 NGichcha|NGichcha|NGichcha 1.1.53|ङिच्च|ङिच्च १.१.५३|१.१.५३|१.१.५३ ङिच्च
And the substitute which hs indicatory ङ् (even though it consists of more than one letter) takes the place of the final letter only of the original expression.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.54|1.1.54 aadeH parasya|aadeH parasya|aadeH parasya 1.1.54|आदेः परस्य|आदेः परस्य १.१.५४|१.१.५४|१.१.५४ आदेः परस्य
That which is enjoined to come in th room of what follows is to be understood as coming in the room only of the first letter thereof.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.55|1.1.55 anekaalshitsarvasya|anekaalshitsarvasya|anekaalshitsarvasya 1.1.55|अनेकाल्शित्सर्वस्य|अनेकाल्शित्सर्वस्य १.१.५५|१.१.५५|१.१.५५ अनेकाल्शित्सर्वस्य
A substitute consisting of more than one letter and a substitute having an indicatory श् take the place of the whole of the original expression exhibited in the Genitive 6th-Case.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.56|1.1.56 sthaanivadaadesho.analvidhau|sthaanivadaadesho.analvidhau|sthaanivadaadesho.analvidhau 1.1.56|स्थानिवदादेशोऽनल्विधौ|स्थानिवदादेशोऽनल्विधौ १.१.५६|१.१.५६|१.१.५६ स्थानिवदादेशोऽनल्विधौ
A substitute (आदेश) is like the former occupant (स्थानी) but not in the case of a rule the occasion for the operation of which is furnished by the letters of the original term.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.57|1.1.57 achaH parasmin puurvavidhau|achaH parasmin puurvavidhau|achaH parasmin puurvavidhau 1.1.57|अचः परस्मिन् पूर्वविधौ|अचः परस्मिन् पूर्वविधौ १.१.५७|१.१.५७|१.१.५७ अचः परस्मिन् पूर्वविधौ
A substitute in the room of a vowel caused by something that follows, should be regarded as that whose place it takes when a rule would else take effect on what stands anterior to the original vowel.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.58|1.1.58 na padaantadvirvachanavareyalopasvarasavarNaanusvaaradiirghajashcharvidhiShu|na padaantadvirvachanavareyalopasvarasavarNaanusvaaradiirghajashcharvidhiShu|na padaantadvirvachanavareyalopasvarasavarNaanusvaaradiirghajashcharvidhiShu 1.1.58|न पदान्तद्विर्वचनवरेयलोपस्वरसवर्णानुस्वारदीर्घजश्चर्विधिषु|न पदान्तद्विर्वचनवरेयलोपस्वरसवर्णानुस्वारदीर्घजश्चर्विधिषु १.१.५८|१.१.५८|१.१.५८ न पदान्तद्विर्वचनवरेयलोपस्वरसवर्णानुस्वारदीर्घजश्चर्विधिषु
Not so, in rules relating to the finals of words, to the doubling of letters, to the affixing of वरच् , to the elision of य , to accent, to homogenous letters, to अनुस्वर , to the lengthening of vowels and to the substitution of जस् and चर् characters.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.59|1.1.59 dvirvachane.achi|dvirvachane.achi|dvirvachane.achi 1.1.59|द्विर्वचनेऽचि|द्विर्वचनेऽचि १.१.५९|१.१.५९|१.१.५९ द्विर्वचनेऽचि
Before an affix having an initial vowel, which causes reduplication, the substitute which takes the place of a vowel is like the original vowel even in form, only for the purpose of reduplication and no further.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.60|1.1.60 adarshanaM lopaH|adarshanaM lopaH|adarshanaM lopaH 1.1.60|अदर्शनं लोपः|अदर्शनं लोपः १.१.६०|१.१.६०|१.१.६० अदर्शनं लोपः
The substitution of a blank (लोप) signifies disappearance.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.61|1.1.61 pratyayasya luk‌shlulupaH|pratyayasya luk‌shlulupaH|pratyayasya luk‌shlulupaH 1.1.61|प्रत्ययस्य लुक्‌श्लुलुपः|प्रत्ययस्य लुक्‌श्लुलुपः १.१.६१|१.१.६१|१.१.६१ प्रत्ययस्य लुक्‌श्लुलुपः
The disappearance of an affix when it is caused by the words लुक् , श्लु or लुप् are designated by those terms respectively.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.62|1.1.62 pratyayalope pratyayalaxaNam|pratyayalope pratyayalaxaNam|pratyayalope pratyayalaxaNam 1.1.62|प्रत्ययलोपे प्रत्ययलक्षणम्|प्रत्ययलोपे प्रत्ययलक्षणम् १.१.६२|१.१.६२|१.१.६२ प्रत्ययलोपे प्रत्ययलक्षणम्
When elision of an affix has taken place (लोप), the affix still exerts its influence and the operations dependant upon it, take place as if it were present.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.63|1.1.63 na lumataa.angasya|na lumataa.angasya|na lumataa.angasya 1.1.63|न लुमताऽङ्गस्य|न लुमताऽङ्गस्य १.१.६३|१.१.६३|१.१.६३ न लुमताऽङ्गस्य
Of the base (अङ्ग), whose affix has been elided by the use of the three words containing लु , the operations dependant on it do not take place, regarding such base.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.64|1.1.64 acho.antyaadi Ti|acho.antyaadi Ti|acho.antyaadi Ti 1.1.64|अचोऽन्त्यादि टि|अचोऽन्त्यादि टि १.१.६४|१.१.६४|१.१.६४ अचोऽन्त्यादि टि
The final portion of a word, beginning with the last among the vowels in the word, is called टि।<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.65|1.1.65 alo.antyaat puurva upadhaa|alo.antyaat puurva upadhaa|alo.antyaat puurva upadhaa 1.1.65|अलोऽन्त्यात् पूर्व उपधा|अलोऽन्त्यात् पूर्व उपधा १.१.६५|१.१.६५|१.१.६५ अलोऽन्त्यात् पूर्व उपधा
The letter immediately preceding the last letter of a word is called penultimate (उपधा).<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.66|1.1.66 tasminniti nirdiShTe puurvasya|tasminniti nirdiShTe puurvasya|tasminniti nirdiShTe puurvasya 1.1.66|तस्मिन्निति निर्दिष्टे पूर्वस्य|तस्मिन्निति निर्दिष्टे पूर्वस्य १.१.६६|१.१.६६|१.१.६६ तस्मिन्निति निर्दिष्टे पूर्वस्य
When a term is exhibited in the seventh case in these sūtras, the operation directed, is to be understood as effecting the state of what immediately precedes the which the term denotes.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.67|1.1.67 tasmaadityuttarasya|tasmaadityuttarasya|tasmaadityuttarasya 1.1.67|तस्मादित्युत्तरस्य|तस्मादित्युत्तरस्य १.१.६७|१.१.६७|१.१.६७ तस्मादित्युत्तरस्य
An operation casused by the exhibition of a term in the Ablative 5th case, is to be understood to enjoin the substitution of something in the room of that which immediately follows the word denoted by the term.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.68|1.1.68 svaM ruupaM shabdasyaashabdasaMJNaa|svaM ruupaM shabdasyaashabdasaMJNaa|svaM ruupaM shabdasyaashabdasaMJNaa 1.1.68|स्वं रूपं शब्दस्याशब्दसंज्ञा|स्वं रूपं शब्दस्याशब्दसंज्ञा १.१.६८|१.१.६८|१.१.६८ स्वं रूपं शब्दस्याशब्दसंज्ञा
In this Grammar, when an operation is directed with regard to a word, the individual form of the word posesssing meaning is to be understood, except with regard to aword which is a definition.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.69|1.1.69 aNudit savarNasya chaapratyayaH|aNudit savarNasya chaapratyayaH|aNudit savarNasya chaapratyayaH 1.1.69|अणुदित् सवर्णस्य चाप्रत्ययः|अणुदित् सवर्णस्य चाप्रत्ययः १.१.६९|१.१.६९|१.१.६९ अणुदित् सवर्णस्य चाप्रत्ययः
The letters of the प्रत्याहार अण् i.e. the vowels and semi-vowels and a term having उ for its indicatory letter, refer to their own form as well as to their homogeneous letters, except when they are used as प्रत्यय-s or affixes.<br><br>Terms: प्रत्यहार

1.1.70|1.1.70 taparastatkaalasya|taparastatkaalasya|taparastatkaalasya 1.1.70|तपरस्तत्कालस्य|तपरस्तत्कालस्य १.१.७०|१.१.७०|१.१.७० तपरस्तत्कालस्य
The letter which has त् after or before it, besides referring to its own form, refers to those homogeneous letters which have the some prosodial length or time.<br><br>Terms: तपर-करणम्

1.1.71|1.1.71 aadirantyena sahetaa|aadirantyena sahetaa|aadirantyena sahetaa 1.1.71|आदिरन्त्येन सहेता|आदिरन्त्येन सहेता १.१.७१|१.१.७१|१.१.७१ आदिरन्त्येन सहेता
An initial letter, with a final इत् letter as a final, is the name of itself and of the intervening letters.<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.1.72|1.1.72 yena vidhistadantasya|yena vidhistadantasya|yena vidhistadantasya 1.1.72|येन विधिस्तदन्तस्य|येन विधिस्तदन्तस्य १.१.७२|१.१.७२|१.१.७२ येन विधिस्तदन्तस्य
An injunction which is made with regard to a particular attribute, applies to words having that attribute at their end as well as to that attribute itself.<br><br>Terms: 

1.1.73|1.1.73 vRddhiryasyaachaamaadistad vRddham|vRddhiryasyaachaamaadistad vRddham|vRddhiryasyaachaamaadistad vRddham 1.1.73|वृद्धिर्यस्याचामादिस्तद् वृद्धम्|वृद्धिर्यस्याचामादिस्तद् वृद्धम् १.१.७३|१.१.७३|१.१.७३ वृद्धिर्यस्याचामादिस्तद् वृद्धम्
That word, among the vowels of which the first is a वृद्धि , is called वृद्धम्। <br><br>Terms: वृद्धम्

1.1.74|1.1.74 tyadaadiini cha|tyadaadiini cha|tyadaadiini cha 1.1.74|त्यदादीनि च|त्यदादीनि च १.१.७४|१.१.७४|१.१.७४ त्यदादीनि च
The words त्यद् etc. are called वृद्धम्।<br><br>Terms: वृद्धम्

1.1.75|1.1.75 eNG praachaaM deshe|eNG praachaaM deshe|eNG praachaaM deshe 1.1.75|एङ् प्राचां देशे|एङ् प्राचां देशे १.१.७५|१.१.७५|१.१.७५ एङ् प्राचां देशे
A word that has the letters ए and ओ as the first among its vowels, gets also the designation of वृद्धम्।<br><br>Terms: वृद्धम्

1.2.1|1.2.1 gaankuTaadibhyo.aNJNinNG it|gaankuTaadibhyo.aNJNinNG it|gaankuTaadibhyo.aNJNinNG it 1.2.1|गाङ्कुटादिभ्योऽञ्णिन्ङ् इत्|गाङ्कुटादिभ्योऽञ्णिन्ङ् इत् १.२.१|१.२.१|१.२.१ गाङ्कुटादिभ्योऽञ्णिन्ङ् इत्
 All affixes after the verb गाङ् 'to study' and the verb कुट् 'to be crooked' and the rest, are as if they had an indicatory ङ् (ङित्), except those affixes which have an indicatory ञ् (ञित्) or ण् (णित्).<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.2|1.2.2 vija iT|vija iT|vija iT 1.2.2|विज इट्|विज इट् १.२.२|१.२.२|१.२.२ विज इट्
 An affix which begins with the augment इट् -- आर्धधातुकस्येड् वलादेः ७.२.३५, is ङित् after the root विज् 'to fear, to move'.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.3|1.2.3 vibhaaShorNoH|vibhaaShorNoH|vibhaaShorNoH 1.2.3|विभाषोर्णोः|विभाषोर्णोः १.२.३|१.२.३|१.२.३ विभाषोर्णोः
 After the verb ऊर्ण 'to cover', the affix beginning with the augment इट् is regarded optionally like ङित्।<br><br>Terms:  augment

1.2.4|1.2.4 saarvadhaatukamapit|saarvadhaatukamapit|saarvadhaatukamapit 1.2.4|सार्वधातुकमपित्|सार्वधातुकमपित् १.२.४|१.२.४|१.२.४ सार्वधातुकमपित्
 A सार्वधातुक -- तिङ्शित्सार्वधातुकम् ३.४.११३, affix not having an indicatory ङित्।<br><br>Terms:  सार्वधातुक

1.2.5|1.2.5 asaMyogaalliT kit|asaMyogaalliT kit|asaMyogaalliT kit 1.2.5|असंयोगाल्लिट् कित्|असंयोगाल्लिट् कित् १.२.५|१.२.५|१.२.५ असंयोगाल्लिट् कित्
 The affixes of लिट् (Perfect Tense) not coming after a conjunct consonant, are as if they had an indicatory क् (कित्).<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.6|1.2.6 iindhibhavatibhyaaM cha|iindhibhavatibhyaaM cha|iindhibhavatibhyaaM cha 1.2.6|ईन्धिभवतिभ्यां च|ईन्धिभवतिभ्यां च १.२.६|१.२.६|१.२.६ ईन्धिभवतिभ्यां च
 The लिट् (Perfect Tense) affixes after the roots इन्धि 'to kindle' and भू 'to become' are also कित्।<br><br>Terms:  लिट्

1.2.7|1.2.7 mRDamRdagudhakuShaklishavadavasaH ktvaa|mRDamRdagudhakuShaklishavadavasaH ktvaa|mRDamRdagudhakuShaklishavadavasaH ktvaa 1.2.7|मृडमृदगुधकुषक्लिशवदवसः क्त्वा|मृडमृदगुधकुषक्लिशवदवसः क्त्वा १.२.७|१.२.७|१.२.७ मृडमृदगुधकुषक्लिशवदवसः क्त्वा
 The affix क्त्वा is कित् after मृड् 'to be gracious', मृद् 'to squeeze', गुध् 'to wrap up', कुष् 'to tear', क्लिश् 'to suffer', वद् 'to speak' and वस् 'to dwell'.<br><br>Terms:  कित्

1.2.8|1.2.8 rudavidamuShagrahisvapiprachChaH saँshcha|rudavidamuShagrahisvapiprachChaH saँshcha|rudavidamuShagrahisvapiprachChaH saँshcha 1.2.8|रुदविदमुषग्रहिस्वपिप्रच्छः सँश्च|रुदविदमुषग्रहिस्वपिप्रच्छः सँश्च १.२.८|१.२.८|१.२.८ रुदविदमुषग्रहिस्वपिप्रच्छः सँश्च
The affixes क्त्वा and सन् ३.१.७ are कित् after रुद् 'to weep', विद् 'to know', मुष् 'to steal', गृह् 'to seize', स्वप् 'to sleep' and प्रच्छ् 'to ask'. <br><br>Terms:  कित्

1.2.9|1.2.9 iko jhal|iko jhal|iko jhal 1.2.9|इको झल्|इको झल् १.२.९|१.२.९|१.२.९ इको झल्
The affix सन् beginning with a letter of the प्रत्यहार झल् is like कित् after the verbs ending in इक् vowels.<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.10|1.2.10 halantaachcha|halantaachcha|halantaachcha 1.2.10|हलन्ताच्च|हलन्ताच्च १.२.१०|१.२.१०|१.२.१० हलन्ताच्च
 And after a root ending in a consonant and preceded by a vowel of the प्रत्यहार इक् , the affix सन् beginning witha झल् consonant, is like कित् ।<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.11|1.2.11 liNGsichaavaatmanepadeShu|liNGsichaavaatmanepadeShu|liNGsichaavaatmanepadeShu 1.2.11|लिङ्सिचावात्मनेपदेषु|लिङ्सिचावात्मनेपदेषु १.२.११|१.२.११|१.२.११ लिङ्सिचावात्मनेपदेषु
 After roots ending in a consonant, that adjoins a vowel of इक् प्रत्यहार , the substitutes of the -- विधिनिमन्त्रणामन्त्रण अधीष्टसम्प्रश्नप्रार्थनेषु लिङ् ३.३.१६१and सिच् -- च्लेः सिच् ३.१.४४, when they begin with a consonant of झल् प्रत्यहार , are कित् when the आत्मनेपद affixes follow.<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.12|1.2.12 ushcha|ushcha|ushcha 1.2.12|उश्च|उश्च १.२.१२|१.२.१२|१.२.१२ उश्च
 And after the verbs ending in ऋ , the substitutes of लिङ् and the affix सिच् , are कित् , when they begin with झल् and the आत्मनेपद affixes follow.<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.13|1.2.13 vaa gamaH|vaa gamaH|vaa gamaH 1.2.13|वा गमः|वा गमः १.२.१३|१.२.१३|१.२.१३ वा गमः
Optionally after the verb गम् , the लिङ् and the सिच् beginning with झल् consonants, in the आत्मनेपद , are कित्।<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.14|1.2.14 hanaH sich|hanaH sich|hanaH sich 1.2.14|हनः सिच्|हनः सिच् १.२.१४|१.२.१४|१.२.१४ हनः सिच्
The सिच् आत्मनेपद affixes are कित् after the root हन् 'to kill'.<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.15|1.2.15 yamo gandhane|yamo gandhane|yamo gandhane 1.2.15|यमो गन्धने|यमो गन्धने १.२.१५|१.२.१५|१.२.१५ यमो गन्धने
The affix सिच् before आत्मनेपद affixes is कित् after the verb यम् when meaning 'to divulge'.<br><br>Terms: कित् 

1.2.16|1.2.16 vibhaaShopayamane|vibhaaShopayamane|vibhaaShopayamane 1.2.16|विभाषोपयमने|विभाषोपयमने १.२.१६|१.२.१६|१.२.१६ विभाषोपयमने
The affix सिच् before आत्मनेपद affixes is कित् optionally when यम् means 'to expose'.<br><br>Terms: कित् 

1.2.17|1.2.17 sthaa ghvorichcha|sthaa ghvorichcha|sthaa ghvorichcha 1.2.17|स्था घ्वोरिच्च|स्था घ्वोरिच्च १.२.१७|१.२.१७|१.२.१७ स्था घ्वोरिच्च
The affix सिच् before आत्मनेपद affixes is कित् after स्था 'to stand' and घु मृषस्तितिक्षायाम् १.२.२० verbs, and these verbs change their आ into इ before these terminations.<br><br>Terms: कित् 

1.2.18|1.2.18 na ktvaa seT|na ktvaa seT|na ktvaa seT 1.2.18|न क्त्वा सेट्|न क्त्वा सेट् १.२.१८|१.२.१८|१.२.१८ न क्त्वा सेट्
 The affix क्त्वा when it takes the augment इट् (i.e. when it is सेट्) is not कित् ।<br><br>Terms: कित् 

1.2.19|1.2.19 niShThaa shiiNGsvidimidixvididhRShaH|niShThaa shiiNGsvidimidixvididhRShaH|niShThaa shiiNGsvidimidixvididhRShaH 1.2.19|निष्ठा शीङ्स्विदिमिदिक्ष्विदिधृषः|निष्ठा शीङ्स्विदिमिदिक्ष्विदिधृषः १.२.१९|१.२.१९|१.२.१९ निष्ठा शीङ्स्विदिमिदिक्ष्विदिधृषः
 The सेट् निष्ठा affixes are not कित् after the verbs शीङ् 'to lie down', स्विद् 'to sweat', मिद् 'to melt', क्ष्विद् 'to be unctuous', and दृश् 'to offend'.<br><br>Terms: कित् 

1.2.20|1.2.20 mRShastitixaayaam|mRShastitixaayaam|mRShastitixaayaam 1.2.20|मृषस्तितिक्षायाम्|मृषस्तितिक्षायाम् १.२.२०|१.२.२०|१.२.२० मृषस्तितिक्षायाम्
 The सेट् निष्ठा affix is not कित् after the verb मृष् 'to forbear'.<br><br>Terms: कित् 

1.2.21|1.2.21 udupadhaadbhaavaadikarmaNoranyatarasyaam|udupadhaadbhaavaadikarmaNoranyatarasyaam|udupadhaadbhaavaadikarmaNoranyatarasyaam 1.2.21|उदुपधाद्भावादिकर्मणोरन्यतरस्याम्|उदुपधाद्भावादिकर्मणोरन्यतरस्याम् १.२.२१|१.२.२१|१.२.२१ उदुपधाद्भावादिकर्मणोरन्यतरस्याम्
 The सेट् निष्ठा affix is optionally not कित् after the verbs with a penultimate उ if used impersonally or denoting the beginning of action.<br><br>Terms: कित् 

1.2.22|1.2.22 puuNGaH ktvaa cha|puuNGaH ktvaa cha|puuNGaH ktvaa cha 1.2.22|पूङः क्त्वा च|पूङः क्त्वा च १.२.२२|१.२.२२|१.२.२२ पूङः क्त्वा च
 The सेट् निष्ठा affix and the सेट् क्त्वा are not कित् after the verb पुङ् 'to purify'.<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.23|1.2.23 nopadhaatthaphaantaadvaa|nopadhaatthaphaantaadvaa|nopadhaatthaphaantaadvaa 1.2.23|नोपधात्थफान्ताद्वा|नोपधात्थफान्ताद्वा १.२.२३|१.२.२३|१.२.२३ नोपधात्थफान्ताद्वा
 The सेट् क्त्वा is optionally कित् after the verbs having a penultimate न् ending in a थ् and फ्।<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.24|1.2.24 vanciluncyRtashcha|vanciluncyRtashcha|vanciluncyRtashcha 1.2.24|वञ्चिलुञ्च्यृतश्च|वञ्चिलुञ्च्यृतश्च १.२.२४|१.२.२४|१.२.२४ वञ्चिलुञ्च्यृतश्च
 The सेट् क्त्वा is optionally कित् after the verbs वञ्च् 'to cheat', लुञ्च् 'to pluck' and ऋत् 'to dare or abhor'.<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.25|1.2.25 tRShimRShikRsheH kaashyapasya|tRShimRShikRsheH kaashyapasya|tRShimRShikRsheH kaashyapasya 1.2.25|तृषिमृषिकृशेः काश्यपस्य|तृषिमृषिकृशेः काश्यपस्य १.२.२५|१.२.२५|१.२.२५ तृषिमृषिकृशेः काश्यपस्य
The सेट् क्त्वा is optionally कित् , according to the opinion of ऋषि काश्यप after the verbs तृष् 'to be thirsty', मृष् 'to sprinkle' and कृश् 'to become lean'.<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.26|1.2.26 ralo vyupadhaaddhalaadeH saMshcha|ralo vyupadhaaddhalaadeH saMshcha|ralo vyupadhaaddhalaadeH saMshcha 1.2.26|रलो व्युपधाद्धलादेः संश्च|रलो व्युपधाद्धलादेः संश्च १.२.२६|१.२.२६|१.२.२६ रलो व्युपधाद्धलादेः संश्च
 After a verb which begins in a consonant and ends in a letter of रल् प्रत्यहार and has as its penultimate इ or ई and उ or ऊ , the क्त्वा and सन् affixes are optionally कित् ।<br><br>Terms: कित्

1.2.27|1.2.27 Ukaalo.ajjhrasvadiirghaplutaH|Ukaalo.ajjhrasvadiirghaplutaH|Ukaalo.ajjhrasvadiirghaplutaH 1.2.27|ऊकालोऽज्झ्रस्वदीर्घप्लुतः|ऊकालोऽज्झ्रस्वदीर्घप्लुतः १.२.२७|१.२.२७|१.२.२७ ऊकालोऽज्झ्रस्वदीर्घप्लुतः
 A vowel whose time is that of short उ , ऊ and the prolated ऊ , is called respectively ह्रस्व short, दीर्घ long and प्लुत prolated.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.28|1.2.28 achashcha|achashcha|achashcha 1.2.28|अचश्च|अचश्च १.२.२८|१.२.२८|१.२.२८ अचश्च
 The short, long and prolated, when enunciated as such, by using these terms, are to be understood to come in the place of vowels only.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.29|1.2.29 uchchairudaattaH|uchchairudaattaH|uchchairudaattaH 1.2.29|उच्चैरुदात्तः|उच्चैरुदात्तः १.२.२९|१.२.२९|१.२.२९ उच्चैरुदात्तः
 The vowel that is perceived as having a high tone is called उदात्त or acutely accented.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.30|1.2.30 niichairanudaattaH|niichairanudaattaH|niichairanudaattaH 1.2.30|नीचैरनुदात्तः|नीचैरनुदात्तः १.२.३०|१.२.३०|१.२.३० नीचैरनुदात्तः
The vowel that is perceived as having a low tone is called अनुदात्तः or gravely accented<br><br>Terms: अनुदात्त

1.2.31|1.2.31 samaahaaraH svaritaH|samaahaaraH svaritaH|samaahaaraH svaritaH 1.2.31|समाहारः स्वरितः|समाहारः स्वरितः १.२.३१|१.२.३१|१.२.३१ समाहारः स्वरितः
The vowel that has the combination of अनुदात्त and उदात्त tones is said to be स्वरित or circumflexly accented.<br><br>Terms: स्वरित

1.2.32|1.2.32 tasyaadita udaattamardhahrasvam|tasyaadita udaattamardhahrasvam|tasyaadita udaattamardhahrasvam 1.2.32|तस्यादित उदात्तमर्धह्रस्वम्|तस्यादित उदात्तमर्धह्रस्वम् १.२.३२|१.२.३२|१.२.३२ तस्यादित उदात्तमर्धह्रस्वम्
Of it (स्वरित-s) the first portion is उदात्त , to the extent of a half measure, or prosodial length.<br><br>Terms: स्वरित

1.2.33|1.2.33 ekashruti duuraat sambuddhau|ekashruti duuraat sambuddhau|ekashruti duuraat sambuddhau 1.2.33|एकश्रुति दूरात् सम्बुद्धौ|एकश्रुति दूरात् सम्बुद्धौ १.२.३३|१.२.३३|१.२.३३ एकश्रुति दूरात् सम्बुद्धौ
In addressing a person from a distance the tone is called एकश्रुति or monotony.<br><br>Terms: एकश्रुति

1.2.34|1.2.34 yaJNakarmaNyajapanyuuNGkhasaamasu|yaJNakarmaNyajapanyuuNGkhasaamasu|yaJNakarmaNyajapanyuuNGkhasaamasu 1.2.34|यज्ञकर्मण्यजपन्यूङ्खसामसु|यज्ञकर्मण्यजपन्यूङ्खसामसु १.२.३४|१.२.३४|१.२.३४ यज्ञकर्मण्यजपन्यूङ्खसामसु
In sacrificial works there is Monotony, except in जप (silent repetition of a formula), न्यूङ्ख vowels (16 sorts of ओम्) and the साम Vedas.<br><br>Terms: एकश्रुति

1.2.35|1.2.35 uchchaistaraaM vaa vaShaTkaaraH|uchchaistaraaM vaa vaShaTkaaraH|uchchaistaraaM vaa vaShaTkaaraH 1.2.35|उच्चैस्तरां वा वषट्कारः|उच्चैस्तरां वा वषट्कारः १.२.३५|१.२.३५|१.२.३५ उच्चैस्तरां वा वषट्कारः
The pronounciation of the word वषट् , may optionally be by raising the voice (accutely accented), or it may be pronounced with monotony.<br><br>Terms: एकश्रुति

1.2.36|1.2.36 vibhaaShaa Chandasi|vibhaaShaa Chandasi|vibhaaShaa Chandasi 1.2.36|विभाषा छन्दसि|विभाषा छन्दसि १.२.३६|१.२.३६|१.२.३६ विभाषा छन्दसि
The monotony is optional in the recitation of the Vedas or they may be recited with accents.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

1.2.37|1.2.37 na subrahmaNyaayaaM svaritasya tuudaattaH|na subrahmaNyaayaaM svaritasya tuudaattaH|na subrahmaNyaayaaM svaritasya tuudaattaH 1.2.37|न सुब्रह्मण्यायां स्वरितस्य तूदात्तः|न सुब्रह्मण्यायां स्वरितस्य तूदात्तः १.२.३७|१.२.३७|१.२.३७ न सुब्रह्मण्यायां स्वरितस्य तूदात्तः
There should be no Monotony in the recitation of the सब्रह्मण्य hymns and in those hymns, the vowels, that would otherwise have taken the स्वरित accent, take the उदात्त accent instead.<br><br>Terms: स्वरित

1.2.38|1.2.38 devabrahmaNoranudaattaH|devabrahmaNoranudaattaH|devabrahmaNoranudaattaH 1.2.38|देवब्रह्मणोरनुदात्तः|देवब्रह्मणोरनुदात्तः १.२.३८|१.२.३८|१.२.३८ देवब्रह्मणोरनुदात्तः
The words देवा and ब्राह्मण in those hymns have अनुदात्त accent.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.39|1.2.39 svaritaat saMhitaayaamanudaattaanaam|svaritaat saMhitaayaamanudaattaanaam|svaritaat saMhitaayaamanudaattaanaam 1.2.39|स्वरितात् संहितायामनुदात्तानाम्|स्वरितात् संहितायामनुदात्तानाम् १.२.३९|१.२.३९|१.२.३९ स्वरितात् संहितायामनुदात्तानाम्
The Monotony takes the place of the अनुदात्त vowels which follow the स्वरित vowels, in close proximity (संहिता).<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.40|1.2.40 udaattasvaritaparasya sannataraH|udaattasvaritaparasya sannataraH|udaattasvaritaparasya sannataraH 1.2.40|उदात्तस्वरितपरस्य सन्नतरः|उदात्तस्वरितपरस्य सन्नतरः १.२.४०|१.२.४०|१.२.४० उदात्तस्वरितपरस्य सन्नतरः
The accent called सन्नतर is substituted in the room of an अनुदात्त vowel, which has an उदात्त or स्वरित vowel following it.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.41|1.2.41 apRkta ekaal pratyayaH|apRkta ekaal pratyayaH|apRkta ekaal pratyayaH 1.2.41|अपृक्त एकाल् प्रत्ययः|अपृक्त एकाल् प्रत्ययः १.२.४१|१.२.४१|१.२.४१ अपृक्त एकाल् प्रत्ययः
An affix consisting of a single letter is called अपृक्त।<br><br>Terms:  अपृक्त

1.2.42|1.2.42 tatpuruShaH samaanaadhikaraNaH karmadhaarayaH|tatpuruShaH samaanaadhikaraNaH karmadhaarayaH|tatpuruShaH samaanaadhikaraNaH karmadhaarayaH 1.2.42|तत्पुरुषः समानाधिकरणः कर्मधारयः|तत्पुरुषः समानाधिकरणः कर्मधारयः १.२.४२|१.२.४२|१.२.४२ तत्पुरुषः समानाधिकरणः कर्मधारयः
A तत्-पुरुष compound, the case of each member is the same, is called कर्मधारय or Appositional Determinative compound.<br><br>Terms:  कर्मधारय

1.2.43|1.2.43 prathamaanirdiShTaM samaasa upasarjanam|prathamaanirdiShTaM samaasa upasarjanam|prathamaanirdiShTaM samaasa upasarjanam 1.2.43|प्रथमानिर्दिष्टं समास उपसर्जनम्|प्रथमानिर्दिष्टं समास उपसर्जनम् १.२.४३|१.२.४३|१.२.४३ प्रथमानिर्दिष्टं समास उपसर्जनम्
In (this book, in the sūtras relating to) compound, the word that is exhibited in the Nominative -1st case, is called उपसर्जन or the secondary word.<br><br>Terms: उपसर्जन

1.2.44|1.2.44 ekavibhakti chaapuurvanipaate|ekavibhakti chaapuurvanipaate|ekavibhakti chaapuurvanipaate 1.2.44|एकविभक्ति चापूर्वनिपाते|एकविभक्ति चापूर्वनिपाते १.२.४४|१.२.४४|१.२.४४ एकविभक्ति चापूर्वनिपाते
A word which hs one fixed case, (while the word compounded with it may vary its case) is also उपसर्जन , except for the purposes of the the rule which requires the उपसर्जन to stand first in a compound.<br><br>Terms:  उपसर्जन

1.2.45|1.2.45 arthavadadhaaturapratyayaH praatipadikam|arthavadadhaaturapratyayaH praatipadikam|arthavadadhaaturapratyayaH praatipadikam 1.2.45|अर्थवदधातुरप्रत्ययः प्रातिपदिकम्|अर्थवदधातुरप्रत्ययः प्रातिपदिकम् १.२.४५|१.२.४५|१.२.४५ अर्थवदधातुरप्रत्ययः प्रातिपदिकम्
A significant form of a word, not being a verbal root (धातु), or an affix (प्रत्यय) is called a प्रातिपदिक or crude-form.<br><br>Terms: प्रातिपदिक

1.2.46|1.2.46 kRttaddhitasamaasaashcha|kRttaddhitasamaasaashcha|kRttaddhitasamaasaashcha 1.2.46|कृत्तद्धितसमासाश्च|कृत्तद्धितसमासाश्च १.२.४६|१.२.४६|१.२.४६ कृत्तद्धितसमासाश्च
The forms ending कृत् affixes or तद्धित affixes, or compound are also called प्रातिपदिक।<br><br>Terms: प्रातिपदिक

1.2.47|1.2.47 hrasvo napuMsake praatipadikasya|hrasvo napuMsake praatipadikasya|hrasvo napuMsake praatipadikasya 1.2.47|ह्रस्वो नपुंसके प्रातिपदिकस्य|ह्रस्वो नपुंसके प्रातिपदिकस्य १.२.४७|१.२.४७|१.२.४७ ह्रस्वो नपुंसके प्रातिपदिकस्य
The short vowel is substituted in the neuter, for the final vowel, of a प्रातिपदिक।<br><br>Terms: प्रातिपदिक

1.2.48|1.2.48 gostriyorupasarjjanasya|gostriyorupasarjjanasya|gostriyorupasarjjanasya 1.2.48|गोस्त्रियोरुपसर्ज्जनस्य|गोस्त्रियोरुपसर्ज्जनस्य १.२.४८|१.२.४८|१.२.४८ गोस्त्रियोरुपसर्ज्जनस्य
A short vowel is the substitute of प्रातिपदिक which ends with the word गो 'a cow' and of that which ends with what has as its termination a feminine affix, when regarded as उपसर्जन।<br><br>Terms: प्रातिपदिक

1.2.49|1.2.49 luk taddhitaluki|luk taddhitaluki|luk taddhitaluki 1.2.49|लुक् तद्धितलुकि|लुक् तद्धितलुकि १.२.४९|१.२.४९|१.२.४९ लुक् तद्धितलुकि
When a तद्धित affix is elided by the word लुक् there takes place the elision by लुक् of feminine affix of the उपसर्जन।<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

1.2.50|1.2.50 idgoNyaaH|idgoNyaaH|idgoNyaaH 1.2.50|इद्गोण्याः|इद्गोण्याः १.२.५०|१.२.५०|१.२.५० इद्गोण्याः
The short is substituted in the place of गोणी , when the तद्धित affix is elided by लुक्।<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

1.2.51|1.2.51 lupi yuktavadvyaktivachane|lupi yuktavadvyaktivachane|lupi yuktavadvyaktivachane 1.2.51|लुपि युक्तवद्व्यक्तिवचने|लुपि युक्तवद्व्यक्तिवचने १.२.५१|१.२.५१|१.२.५१ लुपि युक्तवद्व्यक्तिवचने
When a तद्धित affix is elided by using the word लुप् , then the gender and number (of the derivative word) agree with those of the original word.<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

1.2.52|1.2.52 visheShaNaanaaM chaajaateH|visheShaNaanaaM chaajaateH|visheShaNaanaaM chaajaateH 1.2.52|विशेषणानां चाजातेः|विशेषणानां चाजातेः १.२.५२|१.२.५२|१.२.५२ विशेषणानां चाजातेः
And of adjectives (the gender and number are the same as of the word formed by लुप् elision of the तद्धित and which they qualify) so far as the जाति (or kind of species) is concerned, (or when not expressing जाति).<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

1.2.53|1.2.53 tadashiShyaM saMJNaapramaaNatvaat|tadashiShyaM saMJNaapramaaNatvaat|tadashiShyaM saMJNaapramaaNatvaat 1.2.53|तदशिष्यं संज्ञाप्रमाणत्वात्|तदशिष्यं संज्ञाप्रमाणत्वात् १.२.५३|१.२.५३|१.२.५३ तदशिष्यं संज्ञाप्रमाणत्वात्
This (concord or gender and number, of primitive and derivative nouns, and of attributes and substantives need not be taught (or approved), because it has the authority of संज्ञा (conventional term or idiom).<br><br>Terms: संज्ञा

1.2.54|1.2.54 lubyogaaprakhyaanaat|lubyogaaprakhyaanaat|lubyogaaprakhyaanaat 1.2.54|लुब्योगाप्रख्यानात्|लुब्योगाप्रख्यानात् १.२.५४|१.२.५४|१.२.५४ लुब्योगाप्रख्यानात्
The sūtras declaring लुप् elision need not also be taught, because of the non-currency of the etymological meaning of the words supposed to be formed by लुप् elision.<br><br>Terms:  लुप्

1.2.55|1.2.55 yogapramaaNe cha tadabhaave.adarshanaM syaat|yogapramaaNe cha tadabhaave.adarshanaM syaat|yogapramaaNe cha tadabhaave.adarshanaM syaat 1.2.55|योगप्रमाणे च तदभावेऽदर्शनं स्यात्|योगप्रमाणे च तदभावेऽदर्शनं स्यात् १.२.५५|१.२.५५|१.२.५५ योगप्रमाणे च तदभावेऽदर्शनं स्यात्
And if the etymological meaning 'be held authoritative', then when such meaning is absent, the word also should vanish.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.56|1.2.56 pradhaanapratyayaarthavachanamarthasyaanyapramaaNatvaat|pradhaanapratyayaarthavachanamarthasyaanyapramaaNatvaat|pradhaanapratyayaarthavachanamarthasyaanyapramaaNatvaat 1.2.56|प्रधानप्रत्ययार्थवचनमर्थस्यान्यप्रमाणत्वात्|प्रधानप्रत्ययार्थवचनमर्थस्यान्यप्रमाणत्वात् १.२.५६|१.२.५६|१.२.५६ प्रधानप्रत्ययार्थवचनमर्थस्यान्यप्रमाणत्वात्
(Nor need be taught) the rule relating to the dependance of the meaning of a word on the principal (प्रधान in a compound) or on the affix (प्रत्यय) because the authority of the meaning (of a word, compound or derivative) consists in something else.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.57|1.2.57 kaalopasarjane cha tulyam|kaalopasarjane cha tulyam|kaalopasarjane cha tulyam 1.2.57|कालोपसर्जने च तुल्यम्|कालोपसर्जने च तुल्यम् १.२.५७|१.२.५७|१.२.५७ कालोपसर्जने च तुल्यम्
And a rule fixing the meaning of Tense (काल) and उपसर्जन (sequence) is equally (unnecessary, and need not be taught).<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.58|1.2.58 jaatyaakhyaayaamekasmin bahuvachanamanyatarasyaam|jaatyaakhyaayaamekasmin bahuvachanamanyatarasyaam|jaatyaakhyaayaamekasmin bahuvachanamanyatarasyaam 1.2.58|जात्याख्यायामेकस्मिन् बहुवचनमन्यतरस्याम्|जात्याख्यायामेकस्मिन् बहुवचनमन्यतरस्याम् १.२.५८|१.२.५८|१.२.५८ जात्याख्यायामेकस्मिन् बहुवचनमन्यतरस्याम्
In (a common) name (expressive of) class, in denoting the singular, the plural is optionally used.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.59|1.2.59 asmado dvaayoshcha|asmado dvaayoshcha|asmado dvaayoshcha 1.2.59|अस्मदो द्वायोश्च|अस्मदो द्वायोश्च १.२.५९|१.२.५९|१.२.५९ अस्मदो द्वायोश्च
The plural of the pronoun अस्मद् 'I', is used optionally, though the sense requires a singular or a dual number.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.60|1.2.60 phalguniiproShThapadaanaaM cha naxatre|phalguniiproShThapadaanaaM cha naxatre|phalguniiproShThapadaanaaM cha naxatre 1.2.60|फल्गुनीप्रोष्ठपदानां च नक्षत्रे|फल्गुनीप्रोष्ठपदानां च नक्षत्रे १.२.६०|१.२.६०|१.२.६० फल्गुनीप्रोष्ठपदानां च नक्षत्रे
And the dual of फाल्गुनी and प्रष्ठपदा , when signifying asterisms, (also connotes optionally plural).<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.61|1.2.61 Chandasi punarvasvorekavachanam|Chandasi punarvasvorekavachanam|Chandasi punarvasvorekavachanam 1.2.61|छन्दसि पुनर्वस्वोरेकवचनम्|छन्दसि पुनर्वस्वोरेकवचनम् १.२.६१|१.२.६१|१.२.६१ छन्दसि पुनर्वस्वोरेकवचनम्
In the Vedas, the two stars, पुनर्वासू , may optionally be singular, (and connote a dual).<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.62|1.2.62 vishaakhayoshcha|vishaakhayoshcha|vishaakhayoshcha 1.2.62|विशाखयोश्च|विशाखयोश्च १.२.६२|१.२.६२|१.२.६२ विशाखयोश्च
In the Vedas, the two stars विशाखा may optionally be in the singular number.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.63|1.2.63 tiShyapunarvasvornaxatradvaMdve bahuvachanasya|tiShyapunarvasvornaxatradvaMdve bahuvachanasya|tiShyapunarvasvornaxatradvaMdve bahuvachanasya 1.2.63|तिष्यपुनर्वस्वोर्नक्षत्रद्वंद्वे बहुवचनस्य|तिष्यपुनर्वस्वोर्नक्षत्रद्वंद्वे बहुवचनस्य १.२.६३|१.२.६३|१.२.६३ तिष्यपुनर्वस्वोर्नक्षत्रद्वंद्वे बहुवचनस्य
In the द्वन्द compounds of the stars तिष्व and पुनर्वसू , the dual constantly comes in place of the plural.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

1.2.64|1.2.64 saruupaaNaamekasheSha ekavibhaktau|saruupaaNaamekasheSha ekavibhaktau|saruupaaNaamekasheSha ekavibhaktau 1.2.64|सरूपाणामेकशेष एकविभक्तौ|सरूपाणामेकशेष एकविभक्तौ १.२.६४|१.२.६४|१.२.६४ सरूपाणामेकशेष एकविभक्तौ
Of the words having the same form and all in the same one case-termination, the last one is only retained.<br><br>Terms: 

1.2.65|1.2.65 vRddho yuunaa tallaxaNashchedeva visheShaH|vRddho yuunaa tallaxaNashchedeva visheShaH|vRddho yuunaa tallaxaNashchedeva visheShaH 1.2.65|वृद्धो यूना तल्लक्षणश्चेदेव विशेषः|वृद्धो यूना तल्लक्षणश्चेदेव विशेषः १.२.६५|१.२.६५|१.२.६५ वृद्धो यूना तल्लक्षणश्चेदेव विशेषः
The वृद्ध (or patronymic गोत्र word becomes एकशेष and is retained, when compounded) with a patronymic word युवन् , provided that the specific difference in form between them be in their signs (affix) only.<br><br>Terms:  वृद्ध

1.2.66|1.2.66 strii puMvachcha|strii puMvachcha|strii puMvachcha 1.2.66|स्त्री पुंवच्च|स्त्री पुंवच्च १.२.६६|१.२.६६|१.२.६६ स्त्री पुंवच्च
And so also a feminine word, ending with a वृद्ध affix, when similarly spoken along with the same word but which ends with a युवन् affix, is only retained and it is treated like a masculine.<br><br>Terms:  वृद्ध

1.2.67|1.2.67 pumaan striyaa|pumaan striyaa|pumaan striyaa 1.2.67|पुमान् स्त्रिया|पुमान् स्त्रिया १.२.६७|१.२.६७|१.२.६७ पुमान् स्त्रिया
A word in the masculine gender, similarly spoken along with the same word, but ending with the feminine affix, becomes एकशेष and the latter is dropped.<br><br>Terms:  एकशेष

1.2.68|1.2.68 bhraatRputrau svasRduhitRbhyaam|bhraatRputrau svasRduhitRbhyaam|bhraatRputrau svasRduhitRbhyaam 1.2.68|भ्रातृपुत्रौ स्वसृदुहितृभ्याम्|भ्रातृपुत्रौ स्वसृदुहितृभ्याम् १.२.६८|१.२.६८|१.२.६८ भ्रातृपुत्रौ स्वसृदुहितृभ्याम्
The words भ्रातृ 'brother' and पुत्र 'son', when spoken of along with स्वसृ 'sister' and दुहितृ 'daughter' respectively are only retained and the latter are dropped.<br><br>Terms:  भ्रातृ

1.2.69|1.2.69 napuMsakamanapuMsakenaikavachchaasyaanyatarasyaam|napuMsakamanapuMsakenaikavachchaasyaanyatarasyaam|napuMsakamanapuMsakenaikavachchaasyaanyatarasyaam 1.2.69|नपुंसकमनपुंसकेनैकवच्चास्यान्यतरस्याम्|नपुंसकमनपुंसकेनैकवच्चास्यान्यतरस्याम् १.२.६९|१.२.६९|१.२.६९ नपुंसकमनपुंसकेनैकवच्चास्यान्यतरस्याम्
A neuter noun, which has the same form, only differing in affix, is optionally retained and the other is dropped and it is like a singular number.<br><br>Terms:  neuter

1.2.70|1.2.70 pitaa maatraa|pitaa maatraa|pitaa maatraa 1.2.70|पिता मात्रा|पिता मात्रा १.२.७०|१.२.७०|१.२.७० पिता मात्रा
The word पितृ 'father' is optionally only retained when spoken of along with मातृ 'mother'.<br><br>Terms:  पितृ

1.2.71|1.2.71 shvashuraH shvashrvaa|shvashuraH shvashrvaa|shvashuraH shvashrvaa 1.2.71|श्वशुरः श्वश्र्वा|श्वशुरः श्वश्र्वा १.२.७१|१.२.७१|१.२.७१ श्वशुरः श्वश्र्वा
The word श्वशुर 'father-in-law', is optionally only retained, when spoken of along with श्वशुरू 'mother-in-law'.<br><br>Terms:  श्वशुर

1.2.72|1.2.72 tyadaadiini sarvairnityam|tyadaadiini sarvairnityam|tyadaadiini sarvairnityam 1.2.72|त्यदादीनि सर्वैर्नित्यम्|त्यदादीनि सर्वैर्नित्यम् १.२.७२|१.२.७२|१.२.७२ त्यदादीनि सर्वैर्नित्यम्
The pronouns त्यद् etc. when spoken of along with any other noun, (pronoun other than त्यद् etc.) are always retained as एकशेष (to the exclusion of others).<br><br>Terms:  एकशेष

1.2.73|1.2.73 graamyapashusaMgheShu ataruNeShu strii|graamyapashusaMgheShu ataruNeShu strii|graamyapashusaMgheShu ataruNeShu strii 1.2.73|ग्राम्यपशुसंघेषु अतरुणेषु स्त्री|ग्राम्यपशुसंघेषु अतरुणेषु स्त्री १.२.७३|१.२.७३|१.२.७३ ग्राम्यपशुसंघेषु अतरुणेषु स्त्री
The feminine noun is only retained when denoting a collection of domestic animals, not being young.<br><br>Terms:  feminine

1.3.1|1.3.1 bhuuvaadayo dhaatavaH|bhuuvaadayo dhaatavaH|bhuuvaadayo dhaatavaH 1.3.1|भूवादयो धातवः|भूवादयो धातवः १.३.१|१.३.१|१.३.१ भूवादयो धातवः
The words beginning with भू 'to become' and denoting action, are called धातु or verbal roots.<br><br>Terms: धातु

1.3.2|1.3.2 upadeshe.ajanunaasika it|upadeshe.ajanunaasika it|upadeshe.ajanunaasika it 1.3.2|उपदेशेऽजनुनासिक इत्|उपदेशेऽजनुनासिक इत् १.३.२|१.३.२|१.३.२ उपदेशेऽजनुनासिक इत्
The nasalised vowels are इत् in उपदेश or original enunciation.<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.3|1.3.3 halantyam|halantyam|halantyam 1.3.3|हलन्त्यम्|हलन्त्यम् १.३.३|१.३.३|१.३.३ हलन्त्यम्
In उपदेश , the final consonant of roots etc. is इत्।<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.4|1.3.4 na vibhaktau tusmaaH|na vibhaktau tusmaaH|na vibhaktau tusmaaH 1.3.4|न विभक्तौ तुस्माः|न विभक्तौ तुस्माः १.३.४|१.३.४|१.३.४ न विभक्तौ तुस्माः
The final dental consonants and the final स् and म् are not इत् , in affixes called विभक्ति or inflective affixes.<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.5|1.3.5 aadirNJiTuDavaH|aadirNJiTuDavaH|aadirNJiTuDavaH 1.3.5|आदिर्ञिटुडवः|आदिर्ञिटुडवः १.३.५|१.३.५|१.३.५ आदिर्ञिटुडवः
The initial ञि , टु , डु are इत्।<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.6|1.3.6 ShaH pratyayasya|ShaH pratyayasya|ShaH pratyayasya 1.3.6|षः प्रत्ययस्य|षः प्रत्ययस्य १.३.६|१.३.६|१.३.६ षः प्रत्ययस्य
The initial ष् of an affix is indicatory.<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.7|1.3.7 chuTuu|chuTuu|chuTuu 1.3.7|चुटू|चुटू १.३.७|१.३.७|१.३.७ चुटू
The initial palatals and linguals of an affix are indicatory.<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.8|1.3.8 lashakvataddhite|lashakvataddhite|lashakvataddhite 1.3.8|लशक्वतद्धिते|लशक्वतद्धिते १.३.८|१.३.८|१.३.८ लशक्वतद्धिते
The initial ल् and श् and the gutturals of all affixes, except , तद्धित are indicatory.<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.9|1.3.9 tasya lopaH|tasya lopaH|tasya lopaH 1.3.9|तस्य लोपः|तस्य लोपः १.३.९|१.३.९|१.३.९ तस्य लोपः
Of this, (namely of that which has been called इत् ), there is elision.<br><br>Terms: इत्

1.3.10|1.3.10 yathaasaMkhyamanudeshaH samaanaam|yathaasaMkhyamanudeshaH samaanaam|yathaasaMkhyamanudeshaH samaanaam 1.3.10|यथासंख्यमनुदेशः समानाम्|यथासंख्यमनुदेशः समानाम् १.३.१०|१.३.१०|१.३.१० यथासंख्यमनुदेशः समानाम्
When a rule involves the case of equal numbers of substitutes and of things for which these are to be substituted, their mutual correspondence or assignment of each to each, is according to the order of enumeration.<br><br>Terms: 

1.3.11|1.3.11 svaritenaadhikaaraH|svaritenaadhikaaraH|svaritenaadhikaaraH 1.3.11|स्वरितेनाधिकारः|स्वरितेनाधिकारः १.३.११|१.३.११|१.३.११ स्वरितेनाधिकारः
In these aphorisms, when a word is marked with a स्वरित accent, by that an अधिकार or a governing rule is to be understood.<br><br>Terms: स्वरित

1.3.12|1.3.12 anudaattaNGita aatmanepadam|anudaattaNGita aatmanepadam|anudaattaNGita aatmanepadam 1.3.12|अनुदात्तङित आत्मनेपदम्|अनुदात्तङित आत्मनेपदम् १.३.१२|१.३.१२|१.३.१२ अनुदात्तङित आत्मनेपदम्
After a root which has an indicatory अनुदात्त vowel (अनुदात्तेत्) or an indicatory ङ् (ङित्), the affixes are those of the आत्मनेपद।<br><br>Terms: अनुदात्त-आत्मनेपद

1.3.13|1.3.13 bhaavakarmmaNoH|bhaavakarmmaNoH|bhaavakarmmaNoH 1.3.13|भावकर्म्मणोः|भावकर्म्मणोः १.३.१३|१.३.१३|१.३.१३ भावकर्म्मणोः
An आत्मनेपद affix is the substitute of the affix ल ३.४.६९ when it denotes the action of the verb or the object of the verb.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.14|1.3.14 karttari karmmavyatihaare|karttari karmmavyatihaare|karttari karmmavyatihaare 1.3.14|कर्त्तरि कर्म्मव्यतिहारे|कर्त्तरि कर्म्मव्यतिहारे १.३.१४|१.३.१४|१.३.१४ कर्त्तरि कर्म्मव्यतिहारे
In denoting the agent, when reciprocity of action is to be expressed, the affixes of the आत्मनेपद are employed.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.15|1.3.15 na gatihiMsaarthebhyaH|na gatihiMsaarthebhyaH|na gatihiMsaarthebhyaH 1.3.15|न गतिहिंसार्थेभ्यः|न गतिहिंसार्थेभ्यः १.३.१५|१.३.१५|१.३.१५ न गतिहिंसार्थेभ्यः
After verbs having the sense of 'motion', or 'injury', when expressing interchange of action, the आत्मनेपद affixes are used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.16|1.3.16 itaretaraanyonyopapadaachcha|itaretaraanyonyopapadaachcha|itaretaraanyonyopapadaachcha 1.3.16|इतरेतरान्योन्योपपदाच्च|इतरेतरान्योन्योपपदाच्च १.३.१६|१.३.१६|१.३.१६ इतरेतरान्योन्योपपदाच्च
And after the verbs which take the words इतरेतर 'each other' and अन्योन्य 'one another', as उपपद (or dependant qualifying words), the affixes of आत्मनेपद are not used, though reciprocity of action be denoted.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.17|1.3.17 nervishaH|nervishaH|nervishaH 1.3.17|नेर्विशः|नेर्विशः १.३.१७|१.३.१७|१.३.१७ नेर्विशः
After the verb विश् 'to enter', when preceded by the preposition नि, the आत्मनेपद affixes are employed<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.18|1.3.18 parivyavebhyaH kriyaH|parivyavebhyaH kriyaH|parivyavebhyaH kriyaH 1.3.18|परिव्यवेभ्यः क्रियः|परिव्यवेभ्यः क्रियः १.३.१८|१.३.१८|१.३.१८ परिव्यवेभ्यः क्रियः
After the verb क्री 'to purchase', when preceded by परि , वि or अव , the आत्मनेपद affix is employed, even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.19|1.3.19 viparaabhyaaM jeH|viparaabhyaaM jeH|viparaabhyaaM jeH 1.3.19|विपराभ्यां जेः|विपराभ्यां जेः १.३.१९|१.३.१९|१.३.१९ विपराभ्यां जेः
After the verb जि 'to conquer', preceded by वि or परा , the आत्मनेपद affix is employed.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.20|1.3.20 aaNGo do.anaasyaviharaNe|aaNGo do.anaasyaviharaNe|aaNGo do.anaasyaviharaNe 1.3.20|आङो दोऽनास्यविहरणे|आङो दोऽनास्यविहरणे १.३.२०|१.३.२०|१.३.२० आङो दोऽनास्यविहरणे
After the verb दा 'to give', preceded by अङ् , and when not meaning 'to open the mouth', the आत्मनेपद affix is used, even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.21|1.3.21 kriiDo.anusamparibhyashcha|kriiDo.anusamparibhyashcha|kriiDo.anusamparibhyashcha 1.3.21|क्रीडोऽनुसम्परिभ्यश्च|क्रीडोऽनुसम्परिभ्यश्च १.३.२१|१.३.२१|१.३.२१ क्रीडोऽनुसम्परिभ्यश्च
After the verb क्रीड 'to play', preceded by अनु , सम् , or परि as well as आङ्, the आत्मनेपद affix is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.22|1.3.22 samavapravibhyaH sthaH|samavapravibhyaH sthaH|samavapravibhyaH sthaH 1.3.22|समवप्रविभ्यः स्थः|समवप्रविभ्यः स्थः १.३.२२|१.३.२२|१.३.२२ समवप्रविभ्यः स्थः
After the verb स्था 'to stand', preceded by सम् , अव , प्र , वि , the आत्मनेपद affix is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.23|1.3.23 prakaashanastheyaakhyayoshcha|prakaashanastheyaakhyayoshcha|prakaashanastheyaakhyayoshcha 1.3.23|प्रकाशनस्थेयाख्ययोश्च|प्रकाशनस्थेयाख्ययोश्च १.३.२३|१.३.२३|१.३.२३ प्रकाशनस्थेयाख्ययोश्च
After the verb स्था 'when meaning to indicate one's intentions to another', or 'to make an award as an arbitrator', the आत्मनेपद affix is employed.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.24|1.3.24 udo.anuurddhvakarmaNi|udo.anuurddhvakarmaNi|udo.anuurddhvakarmaNi 1.3.24|उदोऽनूर्द्ध्वकर्मणि|उदोऽनूर्द्ध्वकर्मणि १.३.२४|१.३.२४|१.३.२४ उदोऽनूर्द्ध्वकर्मणि
After the verb स्था 'to stand', preceded by उत् , when not meaning 'to get up or rise', as from a seat; the आत्मनेपद affix is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

