1.3.29|1.3.29 samo gamyRchChiprachChisvaratyartishruvidibhyaH|samo gamyRchChiprachChisvaratyartishruvidibhyaH|samo gamyRchChiprachChisvaratyartishruvidibhyaH 1.3.29|समो गम्यृच्छिप्रच्छिस्वरत्यर्तिश्रुविदिभ्यः|समो गम्यृच्छिप्रच्छिस्वरत्यर्तिश्रुविदिभ्यः १.३.२९|१.३.२९|१.३.२९ समो गम्यृच्छिप्रच्छिस्वरत्यर्तिश्रुविदिभ्यः
After the verbs गम् 'to go', ऋच्छ् 'to become hard', प्रच्छ् 'to ask', स्वर् 'to find fault', ऋ 'to go', श्रु 'to hear' and विद् 'to know', when used intransitively and preceded by सम् , the आत्मनेपद affix is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.30|1.3.30 nisamupavibhyo hvaH|nisamupavibhyo hvaH|nisamupavibhyo hvaH 1.3.30|निसमुपविभ्यो ह्वः|निसमुपविभ्यो ह्वः १.३.३०|१.३.३०|१.३.३० निसमुपविभ्यो ह्वः
After the verbs ह्वे 'to call', preceded by नि , सम् , उप and वि , the आत्मनेपद is used, even, when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.31|1.3.31 sparddhaayaamaaNGaH|sparddhaayaamaaNGaH|sparddhaayaamaaNGaH 1.3.31|स्पर्द्धायामाङः|स्पर्द्धायामाङः १.३.३१|१.३.३१|१.३.३१ स्पर्द्धायामाङः
After the verbs ह्वे 'to call', when meaning 'to challenge' and preceded by अङ् , the आत्मनेपद is used, even, when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.32|1.3.32 gandhanaavaxepaNasevanasaahasikyapratiyatnaprakathanopayogeShu kRNJaH|gandhanaavaxepaNasevanasaahasikyapratiyatnaprakathanopayogeShu kRNJaH|gandhanaavaxepaNasevanasaahasikyapratiyatnaprakathanopayogeShu kRNJaH 1.3.32|गन्धनावक्षेपणसेवनसाहसिक्यप्रतियत्नप्रकथनोपयोगेषु कृञः|गन्धनावक्षेपणसेवनसाहसिक्यप्रतियत्नप्रकथनोपयोगेषु कृञः १.३.३२|१.३.३२|१.३.३२ गन्धनावक्षेपणसेवनसाहसिक्यप्रतियत्नप्रकथनोपयोगेषु कृञः
After the verb कृ when meaning 'to divulge', 'to revile', 'to serve', 'to use violence', 'to cause change', 'to recite' and 'to do an act tending to effect a desired purpose', the आत्मनेपद is used, even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.33|1.3.33 adheH prasahane|adheH prasahane|adheH prasahane 1.3.33|अधेः प्रसहने|अधेः प्रसहने १.३.३३|१.३.३३|१.३.३३ अधेः प्रसहने
After the verb कृ preceded by अधि , when the sense is that of 'overcoming or defeat', the आत्मनेपद is used, even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.34|1.3.34 veH shabdakarmmaNaH|veH shabdakarmmaNaH|veH shabdakarmmaNaH 1.3.34|वेः शब्दकर्म्मणः|वेः शब्दकर्म्मणः १.३.३४|१.३.३४|१.३.३४ वेः शब्दकर्म्मणः
After the verb कृ preceded by वि , even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent, and when the sense is that of 'making sound' (literally having 'sound' for its object), the आत्मनेपद affix is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.35|1.3.35 akarmakaachcha|akarmakaachcha|akarmakaachcha 1.3.35|अकर्मकाच्च|अकर्मकाच्च १.३.३५|१.३.३५|१.३.३५ अकर्मकाच्च
After the verb कृ preceded by वि , when used intransitively, the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.36|1.3.36 sammaananotsanjanaachaaryakaraNaJNaanabhRtivigaNanavyayeShu niyaH|sammaananotsanjanaachaaryakaraNaJNaanabhRtivigaNanavyayeShu niyaH|sammaananotsanjanaachaaryakaraNaJNaanabhRtivigaNanavyayeShu niyaH 1.3.36|सम्माननोत्सञ्जनाचार्यकरणज्ञानभृतिविगणनव्ययेषु नियः|सम्माननोत्सञ्जनाचार्यकरणज्ञानभृतिविगणनव्ययेषु नियः १.३.३६|१.३.३६|१.३.३६ सम्माननोत्सञ्जनाचार्यकरणज्ञानभृतिविगणनव्ययेषु नियः
After the verb नी 'to lead', when used in the sense of 'to guide so as to render the person guided worthy', 'to lift up', 'make one a spiritual guide', 'to determine the true sense', 'to employ on wages', 'to pay debt' and 'to give as in charity', even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent, the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.37|1.3.37 kartRsthe chaashariire karmaNi|kartRsthe chaashariire karmaNi|kartRsthe chaashariire karmaNi 1.3.37|कर्तृस्थे चाशरीरे कर्मणि|कर्तृस्थे चाशरीरे कर्मणि १.३.३७|१.३.३७|१.३.३७ कर्तृस्थे चाशरीरे कर्मणि
After the verb नी , when it governs an incorporeal object in the agent, as its object, the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.38|1.3.38 vRttisargataayaneShu kramaH|vRttisargataayaneShu kramaH|vRttisargataayaneShu kramaH 1.3.38|वृत्तिसर्गतायनेषु क्रमः|वृत्तिसर्गतायनेषु क्रमः १.३.३८|१.३.३८|१.३.३८ वृत्तिसर्गतायनेषु क्रमः
After the verb क्रम् 'to move', when used in the senses of 'continuity', 'energy' and 'development', the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.39|1.3.39 upaparaabhyaam|upaparaabhyaam|upaparaabhyaam 1.3.39|उपपराभ्याम्|उपपराभ्याम् १.३.३९|१.३.३९|१.३.३९ उपपराभ्याम्
After the verb क्रम् , preceded by उप and पर , when used in the senses of 'continuity', 'energy' and 'development', the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.40|1.3.40 aaNGa udgamane|aaNGa udgamane|aaNGa udgamane 1.3.40|आङ उद्गमने|आङ उद्गमने १.३.४०|१.३.४०|१.३.४० आङ उद्गमने
After the verb क्रम् , preceded by an अङ् , the आत्मनेपद is used,when in the sense of 'the rising of a luminary'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.41|1.3.41 veH paadaviharaNe|veH paadaviharaNe|veH paadaviharaNe 1.3.41|वेः पादविहरणे|वेः पादविहरणे १.३.४१|१.३.४१|१.३.४१ वेः पादविहरणे
After the verb क्रम् preceded by वि , the आत्मनेपद is used, when in the sense of 'placing of foot-steps'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.42|1.3.42 propaabhyaaM samarthaabhyaam|propaabhyaaM samarthaabhyaam|propaabhyaaM samarthaabhyaam 1.3.42|प्रोपाभ्यां समर्थाभ्याम्|प्रोपाभ्यां समर्थाभ्याम् १.३.४२|१.३.४२|१.३.४२ प्रोपाभ्यां समर्थाभ्याम्
After the verb क्रम् preceded by वि , the आत्मनेपद is used when it is preceded by प्र and उप , both conveying the same sense; viz. that of 'beginning an action'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.43|1.3.43 anupasargaadvaa|anupasargaadvaa|anupasargaadvaa 1.3.43|अनुपसर्गाद्वा|अनुपसर्गाद्वा १.३.४३|१.३.४३|१.३.४३ अनुपसर्गाद्वा
After the verb क्रम् the आत्मनेपद is optionally used, when it is not preceded by any preposition.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.44|1.3.44 apahnave JNaH|apahnave JNaH|apahnave JNaH 1.3.44|अपह्नवे ज्ञः|अपह्नवे ज्ञः १.३.४४|१.३.४४|१.३.४४ अपह्नवे ज्ञः
After the verb ज्ञ , when used in the sense of 'denying', the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.45|1.3.45 akarmakaachcha|akarmakaachcha|akarmakaachcha 1.3.45|अकर्मकाच्च|अकर्मकाच्च १.३.४५|१.३.४५|१.३.४५ अकर्मकाच्च
And when used intransitively after the verb ज्ञ , the आत्मनेपद is used, when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.46|1.3.46 sampratibhyaamanaadhyaane|sampratibhyaamanaadhyaane|sampratibhyaamanaadhyaane 1.3.46|सम्प्रतिभ्यामनाध्याने|सम्प्रतिभ्यामनाध्याने १.३.४६|१.३.४६|१.३.४६ सम्प्रतिभ्यामनाध्याने
After the verb ज्ञ , preceded by सम् and प्रति , the आत्मनेपद is used, when Not Used in the sense of 'remembering with regret'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.47|1.3.47 bhaasanopasambhaaShaaJNaanayatnavimatyupamantraNeShu vadaH|bhaasanopasambhaaShaaJNaanayatnavimatyupamantraNeShu vadaH|bhaasanopasambhaaShaaJNaanayatnavimatyupamantraNeShu vadaH 1.3.47|भासनोपसम्भाषाज्ञानयत्नविमत्युपमन्त्रणेषु वदः|भासनोपसम्भाषाज्ञानयत्नविमत्युपमन्त्रणेषु वदः १.३.४७|१.३.४७|१.३.४७ भासनोपसम्भाषाज्ञानयत्नविमत्युपमन्त्रणेषु वदः
After the verb वद् , the आत्मनेपद is used, when used in the senses of 'showing brilliance, or proficiency in', pacifying', 'knowledge', 'effort', 'difference of opinion' and 'flattering'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.48|1.3.48 vyaktavaachaaM samuchchaaraNe|vyaktavaachaaM samuchchaaraNe|vyaktavaachaaM samuchchaaraNe 1.3.48|व्यक्तवाचां समुच्चारणे|व्यक्तवाचां समुच्चारणे १.३.४८|१.३.४८|१.३.४८ व्यक्तवाचां समुच्चारणे
After the verb वद् , the आत्मनेपद is used, when used in the sense of 'speaking articulately in a similar manner'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.49|1.3.49 anorakarmakaat|anorakarmakaat|anorakarmakaat 1.3.49|अनोरकर्मकात्|अनोरकर्मकात् १.३.४९|१.३.४९|१.३.४९ अनोरकर्मकात्
After the verb वद् , preceded by अनु when it is intransitively used, the आत्मनेपद is used, when the sense is that of 'speaking articulately in a similar manner'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.50|1.3.50 vibhaaShaa vipralaape|vibhaaShaa vipralaape|vibhaaShaa vipralaape 1.3.50|विभाषा विप्रलापे|विभाषा विप्रलापे १.३.५०|१.३.५०|१.३.५० विभाषा विप्रलापे
After the verb वद् , the आत्मनेपद is used otpionally, when the sense is that of 'contradicting with each other'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.51|1.3.51 avaadgraH|avaadgraH|avaadgraH 1.3.51|अवाद्ग्रः|अवाद्ग्रः १.३.५१|१.३.५१|१.३.५१ अवाद्ग्रः
After the verb गॄ 'to swallow', when preceded by अव, the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.52|1.3.52 samaH pratiJNaane|samaH pratiJNaane|samaH pratiJNaane 1.3.52|समः प्रतिज्ञाने|समः प्रतिज्ञाने १.३.५२|१.३.५२|१.३.५२ समः प्रतिज्ञाने
After the verb गॄ 'to swallow', when preceded by सम् , the आत्मनेपद affix is used in the sense of 'promising'.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.53|1.3.53 udashcharaH sakarmakaat|udashcharaH sakarmakaat|udashcharaH sakarmakaat 1.3.53|उदश्चरः सकर्मकात्|उदश्चरः सकर्मकात् १.३.५३|१.३.५३|१.३.५३ उदश्चरः सकर्मकात्
After the verb चर् 'to walk' preceded by उत् , when used intransitively, the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.54|1.3.54 samastRtiiyaayuktaat|samastRtiiyaayuktaat|samastRtiiyaayuktaat 1.3.54|समस्तृतीयायुक्तात्|समस्तृतीयायुक्तात् १.३.५४|१.३.५४|१.३.५४ समस्तृतीयायुक्तात्
After the verb चर् 'to walk' preceded by सम् , and when connected with a noun in the Instrumental - 3rd Case, the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.55|1.3.55 daaNashcha saa chechchaturthyarthe|daaNashcha saa chechchaturthyarthe|daaNashcha saa chechchaturthyarthe 1.3.55|दाणश्च सा चेच्चतुर्थ्यर्थे|दाणश्च सा चेच्चतुर्थ्यर्थे १.३.५५|१.३.५५|१.३.५५ दाणश्च सा चेच्चतुर्थ्यर्थे
And after the verb दा 'to give', preceded by सम् , and connected with a noun in the Instrumental - 3rd Case, the आत्मनेपद affix is used, provided this Instrumental Case has the sense of the Dative - 4th Case.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.56|1.3.56 upaadyamaH svakaraNe|upaadyamaH svakaraNe|upaadyamaH svakaraNe 1.3.56|उपाद्यमः स्वकरणे|उपाद्यमः स्वकरणे १.३.५६|१.३.५६|१.३.५६ उपाद्यमः स्वकरणे
After the verb यम् 'to give', preceded by उप , when used in the sense of 'espousing', the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.57|1.3.57 JNaashrusmRdRshaaM sanaH|JNaashrusmRdRshaaM sanaH|JNaashrusmRdRshaaM sanaH 1.3.57|ज्ञाश्रुस्मृदृशां सनः|ज्ञाश्रुस्मृदृशां सनः १.३.५७|१.३.५७|१.३.५७ ज्ञाश्रुस्मृदृशां सनः
After the Desideratives formed by the affix सन् , of the verbs ज्ञा 'to know', श्रु 'to hear', स्मृ 'to remember' and दृश् 'to see', the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.58|1.3.58 naanorJNaH|naanorJNaH|naanorJNaH 1.3.58|नानोर्ज्ञः|नानोर्ज्ञः १.३.५८|१.३.५८|१.३.५८ नानोर्ज्ञः
After the Desiderative of ज्ञा 'to know' when preceded by अनु , the आत्मनेपद affix is Not used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.59|1.3.59 pratyaaNGbhyaaM shruvaH|pratyaaNGbhyaaM shruvaH|pratyaaNGbhyaaM shruvaH 1.3.59|प्रत्याङ्भ्यां श्रुवः|प्रत्याङ्भ्यां श्रुवः १.३.५९|१.३.५९|१.३.५९ प्रत्याङ्भ्यां श्रुवः
After the Desideratives of श्रु 'to hear', when preceded by प्रत and आङ् , the आत्मनेपद affix is Not used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.60|1.3.60 shadeH shitaH|shadeH shitaH|shadeH shitaH 1.3.60|शदेः शितः|शदेः शितः १.३.६०|१.३.६०|१.३.६० शदेः शितः
After the verb शद् 'to decay', when it has one of the affixes with an indicatory श् (शित्) the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.61|1.3.61 mriyaterluNG‌liNGoshcha|mriyaterluNG‌liNGoshcha|mriyaterluNG‌liNGoshcha 1.3.61|म्रियतेर्लुङ्‌लिङोश्च|म्रियतेर्लुङ्‌लिङोश्च १.३.६१|१.३.६१|१.३.६१ म्रियतेर्लुङ्‌लिङोश्च
After the verb मृ 'to die', when it has one of the affixes having an indicatory श् , as well as when it takes the affixes लुङ् (Aorist ३.२.११०) and लिङ् (Benedictive ३.३.१५९), the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.62|1.3.62 puurvavat sanaH|puurvavat sanaH|puurvavat sanaH 1.3.62|पूर्ववत् सनः|पूर्ववत् सनः १.३.६२|१.३.६२|१.३.६२ पूर्ववत् सनः
The verb which is आत्मनेपदि in its primitive form before taking of the affix सन् , will also be आत्मनेपदि when it ends in the affix सन्। in other words; after a Desiderative verb, आत्मनेपद is used, if it would have been used after the primitive verb.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.63|1.3.63 aampratyayavat kRNJo.anuprayogasya|aampratyayavat kRNJo.anuprayogasya|aampratyayavat kRNJo.anuprayogasya 1.3.63|आम्प्रत्ययवत् कृञोऽनुप्रयोगस्य|आम्प्रत्ययवत् कृञोऽनुप्रयोगस्य १.३.६३|१.३.६३|१.३.६३ आम्प्रत्ययवत् कृञोऽनुप्रयोगस्य
Like the verb that takes the affix आम् , if the verb be conjugated with the आत्मनेपद terminations, so of the verb कृ when subjoined thereto as an auxiliary, the terminations are of the आत्मनेपद , even when the fruit of the action does not acccrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.64|1.3.64 propaabhyaaM yujerayaJNapaatreShu|propaabhyaaM yujerayaJNapaatreShu|propaabhyaaM yujerayaJNapaatreShu 1.3.64|प्रोपाभ्यां युजेरयज्ञपात्रेषु|प्रोपाभ्यां युजेरयज्ञपात्रेषु १.३.६४|१.३.६४|१.३.६४ प्रोपाभ्यां युजेरयज्ञपात्रेषु
After the verb युज् 'to join', the आत्मनेपद is used, when it is preceded by प्र and उप except with reference to sacrificial vessels even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.65|1.3.65 samaH xNuvaH|samaH xNuvaH|samaH xNuvaH 1.3.65|समः क्ष्णुवः|समः क्ष्णुवः १.३.६५|१.३.६५|१.३.६५ समः क्ष्णुवः
After the verb क्षणु 'to sharpen', preceded by सम् , the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.66|1.3.66 bhujo.anavane|bhujo.anavane|bhujo.anavane 1.3.66|भुजोऽनवने|भुजोऽनवने १.३.६६|१.३.६६|१.३.६६ भुजोऽनवने
After the verb भुज् , the आत्मनेपद is used, except in the sense of protecting.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.67|1.3.67 NeraNau yat karma Nau chet sa kartaa.anaadhyaane|NeraNau yat karma Nau chet sa kartaa.anaadhyaane|NeraNau yat karma Nau chet sa kartaa.anaadhyaane 1.3.67|णेरणौ यत् कर्म णौ चेत् स कर्ताऽनाध्याने|णेरणौ यत् कर्म णौ चेत् स कर्ताऽनाध्याने १.३.६७|१.३.६७|१.३.६७ णेरणौ यत् कर्म णौ चेत् स कर्ताऽनाध्याने
After a verb ending in the affix णि (causal) the आत्मनेपद is used, provided that when the object in the non-णि or non-causal sense becomes the agent in the causal; and when it does not mean 'to remember with regret', even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.68|1.3.68 bhiismyorhetubhaye|bhiismyorhetubhaye|bhiismyorhetubhaye 1.3.68|भीस्म्योर्हेतुभये|भीस्म्योर्हेतुभये १.३.६८|१.३.६८|१.३.६८ भीस्म्योर्हेतुभये
After the causatives of the verbs भी 'to fear' and स्मि 'to wonder' even when the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent the आत्मनेपद is employed, when the fear is produced directly by the causative agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.69|1.3.69 gRdhivancyoH pralambhane|gRdhivancyoH pralambhane|gRdhivancyoH pralambhane 1.3.69|गृधिवञ्च्योः प्रलम्भने|गृधिवञ्च्योः प्रलम्भने १.३.६९|१.३.६९|१.३.६९ गृधिवञ्च्योः प्रलम्भने
After the causatives of the verbs गृध 'to covet' and वञ्च 'to go' the आत्मनेपद is used in the sense of 'deceiving' even though the fruit of the action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.70|1.3.70 liyaH sammaananashaaliniikaraNayoshcha|liyaH sammaananashaaliniikaraNayoshcha|liyaH sammaananashaaliniikaraNayoshcha 1.3.70|लियः सम्माननशालिनीकरणयोश्च|लियः सम्माननशालिनीकरणयोश्च १.३.७०|१.३.७०|१.३.७० लियः सम्माननशालिनीकरणयोश्च
After the causative of the verb लि 'to melt or stick', the आत्मनेपद is employed, when used in the sense of showing respect, subduing and deceiving, even though the fruit of action does not accrue to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.71|1.3.71 mithyopapadaat kRNJo.abhyaase|mithyopapadaat kRNJo.abhyaase|mithyopapadaat kRNJo.abhyaase 1.3.71|मिथ्योपपदात् कृञोऽभ्यासे|मिथ्योपपदात् कृञोऽभ्यासे १.३.७१|१.३.७१|१.३.७१ मिथ्योपपदात् कृञोऽभ्यासे
After the causative of the verb कृ , the आत्मनेपद is used, when it has the word मिथ्या 'incorrect', as an उपपद or dependent word and is used in the sense of 'repeated wrong utterance', even when the fruit of action does not accrue no the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.72|1.3.72 svaritaNJitaH kartrabhipraaye kriyaaphale|svaritaNJitaH kartrabhipraaye kriyaaphale|svaritaNJitaH kartrabhipraaye kriyaaphale 1.3.72|स्वरितञितः कर्त्रभिप्राये क्रियाफले|स्वरितञितः कर्त्रभिप्राये क्रियाफले १.३.७२|१.३.७२|१.३.७२ स्वरितञितः कर्त्रभिप्राये क्रियाफले
After the verb marked with a स्वरित or which has an indicatory ञित् , the terminations of the आत्मनेपद are used, when the fruit of the action accrues to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.73|1.3.73 apaadvadaH|apaadvadaH|apaadvadaH 1.3.73|अपाद्वदः|अपाद्वदः १.३.७३|१.३.७३|१.३.७३ अपाद्वदः
After the verb वद् 'to tell', preceded by अप , when the fruit of the action accrues to the agent, the terminations are of the आत्मनेपद।<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.74|1.3.74 Nichashcha|Nichashcha|Nichashcha 1.3.74|णिचश्च|णिचश्च १.३.७४|१.३.७४|१.३.७४ णिचश्च
After a verb ending in the affix णि (causal) when the fruit of the action accrues to the agent, the आत्मनेपद is used.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.75|1.3.75 samudaaNGbhyo yamo.agranthe|samudaaNGbhyo yamo.agranthe|samudaaNGbhyo yamo.agranthe 1.3.75|समुदाङ्भ्यो यमोऽग्रन्थे|समुदाङ्भ्यो यमोऽग्रन्थे १.३.७५|१.३.७५|१.३.७५ समुदाङ्भ्यो यमोऽग्रन्थे
After the verb यम् 'to strive', preceded by सम् , उत् and आङ् , when it does not refer to a book, the आत्मनेपद is used, when the fruit of the action accrues to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.76|1.3.76 anupasargaajJNaH|anupasargaajJNaH|anupasargaajJNaH 1.3.76|अनुपसर्गाज्ज्ञः|अनुपसर्गाज्ज्ञः १.३.७६|१.३.७६|१.३.७६ अनुपसर्गाज्ज्ञः
After the verb ज्ञा , when not preceded by any उपसर्ग , the terminations are of the आत्मनेपद , when the fruit of the action accrues to the agent.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.77|1.3.77 vibhaaShopapadena pratiiyamaane|vibhaaShopapadena pratiiyamaane|vibhaaShopapadena pratiiyamaane 1.3.77|विभाषोपपदेन प्रतीयमाने|विभाषोपपदेन प्रतीयमाने १.३.७७|१.३.७७|१.३.७७ विभाषोपपदेन प्रतीयमाने
The आत्मनेपद is optionally used, when the fact of the fruit of the action accruing to the agent is indicted by an उपपदग i.e. by a word used along with the verb.<br><br>Terms: आत्मनेपद

1.3.78|1.3.78 sheShaat kartari parasmaipadam|sheShaat kartari parasmaipadam|sheShaat kartari parasmaipadam 1.3.78|शेषात् कर्तरि परस्मैपदम्|शेषात् कर्तरि परस्मैपदम् १.३.७८|१.३.७८|१.३.७८ शेषात् कर्तरि परस्मैपदम्
After the rest i.e. all those verbs not falling under any one of the previous provisions, the terminations of the परस्मैपद are used, in marking the agent i.e. in the active voice.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.79|1.3.79 anuparaabhyaaM kRNJaH|anuparaabhyaaM kRNJaH|anuparaabhyaaM kRNJaH 1.3.79|अनुपराभ्यां कृञः|अनुपराभ्यां कृञः १.३.७९|१.३.७९|१.३.७९ अनुपराभ्यां कृञः
After the verb कृ 'to make' preceded by the अनु and पर , परस्मैपद is used, even the fruit of the action goes to the agent and when the sense is that of 'divulging' etc.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.80|1.3.80 abhipratyatibhyaH xipaH|abhipratyatibhyaH xipaH|abhipratyatibhyaH xipaH 1.3.80|अभिप्रत्यतिभ्यः क्षिपः|अभिप्रत्यतिभ्यः क्षिपः १.३.८०|१.३.८०|१.३.८० अभिप्रत्यतिभ्यः क्षिपः
After the verb क्षिप् 'to throw', coming after अभि , प्रति and अति , परस्मैपद is used, even though the fruit of the action goes to the agent<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.81|1.3.81 praadvahaH|praadvahaH|praadvahaH 1.3.81|प्राद्वहः|प्राद्वहः १.३.८१|१.३.८१|१.३.८१ प्राद्वहः
After the verb वह् 'to bear', coming after प्र , परस्मैपद is used, even though the fruit of the action accrues to the the agent.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.82|1.3.82 parermRShaH|parermRShaH|parermRShaH 1.3.82|परेर्मृषः|परेर्मृषः १.३.८२|१.३.८२|१.३.८२ परेर्मृषः
After the verb मृष् 'to bear', preceded by परि , परस्मैपद is used when the fruit of the action accrues to the agent.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.83|1.3.83 vyaaNGparibhyo ramaH|vyaaNGparibhyo ramaH|vyaaNGparibhyo ramaH 1.3.83|व्याङ्परिभ्यो रमः|व्याङ्परिभ्यो रमः १.३.८३|१.३.८३|१.३.८३ व्याङ्परिभ्यो रमः
After the verb रम् 'to sport', preceded by वि and आङ् , परस्मैपद is used.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.84|1.3.84 upaachcha|upaachcha|upaachcha 1.3.84|उपाच्च|उपाच्च १.३.८४|१.३.८४|१.३.८४ उपाच्च
And also after उप , the verb रम् takes the affixes of the परस्मैपद।<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.85|1.3.85 vibhaaShaa.akarmakaat|vibhaaShaa.akarmakaat|vibhaaShaa.akarmakaat 1.3.85|विभाषाऽकर्मकात्|विभाषाऽकर्मकात् १.३.८५|१.३.८५|१.३.८५ विभाषाऽकर्मकात्
After the verb रम् 'to sport', preceded by उप , परस्मैपद is optionally used, when employed intransitively.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.86|1.3.86 budhayudhanashajaneNGprudrusrubhyo NeH|budhayudhanashajaneNGprudrusrubhyo NeH|budhayudhanashajaneNGprudrusrubhyo NeH 1.3.86|बुधयुधनशजनेङ्प्रुद्रुस्रुभ्यो णेः|बुधयुधनशजनेङ्प्रुद्रुस्रुभ्यो णेः १.३.८६|१.३.८६|१.३.८६ बुधयुधनशजनेङ्प्रुद्रुस्रुभ्यो णेः
After the verbs बुध् 'to know', युध् 'to fight', नश् 'to destroy', जन 'to be born', एङ् 'to go', प्रु 'to move', द्रु 'to run' and स्रु 'to flow', ending in the affix णे (i.e. when used in the causative), परस्मैपद is used, even when the fruit of the action goes to the agent.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.87|1.3.87 nigaraNachalanaarthebhyaH|nigaraNachalanaarthebhyaH|nigaraNachalanaarthebhyaH 1.3.87|निगरणचलनार्थेभ्यः|निगरणचलनार्थेभ्यः १.३.८७|१.३.८७|१.३.८७ निगरणचलनार्थेभ्यः
And after the causatives of verbs which have no sense of the 'eating or swallowing' and 'shaking or moving' परस्मैपद is used, even when the fruit of the action goes to the agent.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.88|1.3.88 aNaavakarmakaachchittavatkartRkaat|aNaavakarmakaachchittavatkartRkaat|aNaavakarmakaachchittavatkartRkaat 1.3.88|अणावकर्मकाच्चित्तवत्कर्तृकात्|अणावकर्मकाच्चित्तवत्कर्तृकात् १.३.८८|१.३.८८|१.३.८८ अणावकर्मकाच्चित्तवत्कर्तृकात्
The affixes of the परस्मैपद are used after the causal of that verb, which in its non-causal state was intransitive and had a being endowed with reason for its agent, even when the fruit of the action accrues to the agent.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.89|1.3.89 na paadamyaaNGyamaaNGyasaparimuharuchinRtivadavasaH|na paadamyaaNGyamaaNGyasaparimuharuchinRtivadavasaH|na paadamyaaNGyamaaNGyasaparimuharuchinRtivadavasaH 1.3.89|न पादम्याङ्यमाङ्यसपरिमुहरुचिनृतिवदवसः|न पादम्याङ्यमाङ्यसपरिमुहरुचिनृतिवदवसः १.३.८९|१.३.८९|१.३.८९ न पादम्याङ्यमाङ्यसपरिमुहरुचिनृतिवदवसः
But the affixes of the परस्मैपद are not used after the causals of the verbs पा 'to drink', दम् 'to tame', आयम् 'to extend', आयस् 'to exert oneself', परिमुह 'to be bewildered', रुच् 'to shine' नृत् 'to dance', वद् 'to speak' and वस् 'to dwell'.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.90|1.3.90 vaa kyaShaH|vaa kyaShaH|vaa kyaShaH 1.3.90|वा क्यषः|वा क्यषः १.३.९०|१.३.९०|१.३.९० वा क्यषः
The affixes of the परस्मैपद are used optionally after the denominative verbs ending in the affix क्यष।<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.91|1.3.91 dyudbhyo luNGi|dyudbhyo luNGi|dyudbhyo luNGi 1.3.91|द्युद्भ्यो लुङि|द्युद्भ्यो लुङि १.३.९१|१.३.९१|१.३.९१ द्युद्भ्यो लुङि
After the verbs द्युत् 'to shine' etc., the terminations of the परस्मैपद are optionally employed, when the affixes of लुण् (Aorist) follow.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.92|1.3.92 vRdbhyaH syasanoH|vRdbhyaH syasanoH|vRdbhyaH syasanoH 1.3.92|वृद्भ्यः स्यसनोः|वृद्भ्यः स्यसनोः १.३.९२|१.३.९२|१.३.९२ वृद्भ्यः स्यसनोः
After the verbs वृत् 'to exist' etc., परस्मैपद is optionally used when the affixes स्य (Future and conditional) and सन् (Desiderative) follow.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.3.93|1.3.93 luTi cha kLLipaH|luTi cha kLLipaH|luTi cha kLLipaH 1.3.93|लुटि च कॢपः|लुटि च कॢपः १.३.९३|१.३.९३|१.३.९३ लुटि च कॢपः
After the verb क्लिप् 'to be fit', परस्मैपद is optionally used, when लुट् (1st Future) is affixed, as well as when स्य and सन् are affixed.<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद

1.4.1|1.4.1 aa kaDaaraadekaa saMJNaa|aa kaDaaraadekaa saMJNaa|aa kaDaaraadekaa saMJNaa 1.4.1|आ कडारादेका संज्ञा|आ कडारादेका संज्ञा १.४.१|१.४.१|१.४.१ आ कडारादेका संज्ञा
From this सूत्र up the the aphorism कडाराः कर्मधराये २.२.३८ only one name of each thing named is to be understood.<br><br>Terms: संज्ञा

1.4.2|1.4.2 vipratiShedhe paraM kaaryam|vipratiShedhe paraM kaaryam|vipratiShedhe paraM kaaryam 1.4.2|विप्रतिषेधे परं कार्यम्|विप्रतिषेधे परं कार्यम् १.४.२|१.४.२|१.४.२ विप्रतिषेधे परं कार्यम्
When rules of equal force prohibit each other then the last in the order herein given is to take effect.<br><br>Terms: कार्यम्

1.4.3|1.4.3 yuu stryaakhyau nadii|yuu stryaakhyau nadii|yuu stryaakhyau nadii 1.4.3|यू स्त्र्याख्यौ नदी|यू स्त्र्याख्यौ नदी १.४.३|१.४.३|१.४.३ यू स्त्र्याख्यौ नदी
Word-forms ending in long ई and ऊ being names of females called नदी।<br><br>Terms: about अष्टाध्यायी

1.4.4|1.4.4 neyaNGuvaNGsthaanaavastrii|neyaNGuvaNGsthaanaavastrii|neyaNGuvaNGsthaanaavastrii 1.4.4|नेयङुवङ्स्थानावस्त्री|नेयङुवङ्स्थानावस्त्री १.४.४|१.४.४|१.४.४ नेयङुवङ्स्थानावस्त्री
Feminine words ending in ई and ऊ which admit the substitute इयङ् and उवङ् ६.१.७७ are not called नदी ; except the word स्त्री (which is called नदी not withstanding its substituting इयङ्).<br><br>Terms: नदी संज्ञा

1.4.5|1.4.5 vaa.a.ami|vaa.a.ami|vaa.a.ami 1.4.5|वाऽऽमि|वाऽऽमि १.४.५|१.४.५|१.४.५ वाऽऽमि
Feminine words ending in ई and ऊ though admiting इयङ् and उवङ् ६.१.७७ substitutes, are optionally termed नदी when the affix अम् (Genitive Plural) follows, but not so the word स्त्री , which is always नदी।<br><br>Terms: नदी स्त्री

1.4.6|1.4.6 NGiti hrasvashcha|NGiti hrasvashcha|NGiti hrasvashcha 1.4.6|ङिति ह्रस्वश्च|ङिति ह्रस्वश्च १.४.६|१.४.६|१.४.६ ङिति ह्रस्वश्च
When a case-affix having an indicatory ङ् (ङित्) follows, then feminine words ending in short इ and उ are optionally termed नदी , as well as feminine nouns in long ई and ऊ which admit इयङ् and उवङ् ; but not so the word स्त्री which is always नदी।<br><br>Terms: नदी स्त्री

1.4.7|1.4.7 sheSho ghyasakhi|sheSho ghyasakhi|sheSho ghyasakhi 1.4.7|शेषो घ्यसखि|शेषो घ्यसखि १.४.७|१.४.७|१.४.७ शेषो घ्यसखि
The rest of the words that end in short इ and उ are घि with the exception of the word सखि।<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.8|1.4.8 patiH samaasa eva|patiH samaasa eva|patiH samaasa eva 1.4.8|पतिः समास एव|पतिः समास एव १.४.८|१.४.८|१.४.८ पतिः समास एव
The word पति is called घि only when it is in a compound.<br><br>Terms: घि संज्ञा

1.4.9|1.4.9 ShaShThiiyuktashChandasi vaa|ShaShThiiyuktashChandasi vaa|ShaShThiiyuktashChandasi vaa 1.4.9|षष्ठीयुक्तश्छन्दसि वा|षष्ठीयुक्तश्छन्दसि वा १.४.९|१.४.९|१.४.९ षष्ठीयुक्तश्छन्दसि वा
The word पति when used in connection with a noun ending in the 6th or genitive case, is घि , optionally, in the छन्दस् (Veda).<br><br>Terms: घि पति

1.4.10|1.4.10 hrasvaM laghu|hrasvaM laghu|hrasvaM laghu 1.4.10|ह्रस्वं लघु|ह्रस्वं लघु १.४.१०|१.४.१०|१.४.१० ह्रस्वं लघु
A short vowel is called लघु 'light'.<br><br>Terms: घि पति

1.4.11|1.4.11 saMyoge guru|saMyoge guru|saMyoge guru 1.4.11|संयोगे गुरु|संयोगे गुरु १.४.११|१.४.११|१.४.११ संयोगे गुरु
When a conjunct consonant followsm a short vowel is termed गुरु 'heavy'.<br><br>Terms: लघु

1.4.12|1.4.12 diirghaM cha|diirghaM cha|diirghaM cha 1.4.12|दीर्घं च|दीर्घं च १.४.१२|१.४.१२|१.४.१२ दीर्घं च
And a long vowel is also called गुरु 'heavy'.<br><br>Terms: गुरु

1.4.13|1.4.13 yasmaat pratyayavidhistadaadi pratyaye.angam|yasmaat pratyayavidhistadaadi pratyaye.angam|yasmaat pratyayavidhistadaadi pratyaye.angam 1.4.13|यस्मात् प्रत्ययविधिस्तदादि प्रत्ययेऽङ्गम्|यस्मात् प्रत्ययविधिस्तदादि प्रत्ययेऽङ्गम् १.४.१३|१.४.१३|१.४.१३ यस्मात् प्रत्ययविधिस्तदादि प्रत्ययेऽङ्गम्
After whatsoever there is an affix enjoined, wether verbal or crude-form, that which begins therewith in the form in which it appears when the affix follows it, is called an अङ्ग 'Inflective base'.<br><br>Terms: गुरु

1.4.14|1.4.14 suptiNGantaM padam|suptiNGantaM padam|suptiNGantaM padam 1.4.14|सुप्तिङन्तं पदम्|सुप्तिङन्तं पदम् १.४.१४|१.४.१४|१.४.१४ सुप्तिङन्तं पदम्
That which ends in सुप् 'case-affix' ४.१.२ or तिङ् ३.४.७८ (tense-affix), is called पद or inflected word.<br><br>Terms: अङ्ग संज्ञा

1.4.15|1.4.15 naH kye|naH kye|naH kye 1.4.15|नः क्ये|नः क्ये १.४.१५|१.४.१५|१.४.१५ नः क्ये
The word-form ending in न् , is called पद when क्य follows (i.e. the affixes क्यच् , क्यङ् and क्यष्।<br><br>Terms: पद संज्ञा

1.4.16|1.4.16 siti cha|siti cha|siti cha 1.4.16|सिति च|सिति च १.४.१६|१.४.१६|१.४.१६ सिति च
When an affix having an indicatory स् follows then that which precedes it is called पद।<br><br>Terms: पद-न् , क्य

1.4.17|1.4.17 svaadiShvasarvanaamasthaane|svaadiShvasarvanaamasthaane|svaadiShvasarvanaamasthaane 1.4.17|स्वादिष्वसर्वनामस्थाने|स्वादिष्वसर्वनामस्थाने १.४.१७|१.४.१७|१.४.१७ स्वादिष्वसर्वनामस्थाने
When the affixes beginning with a सु ४.१.२ and ending in कप् ५.४.१५१ follow, not being सर्वनामस्थान १.१.४३ then that which precedes is called पद।<br><br>Terms: पद संज्ञा

1.4.18|1.4.18 yachi bham|yachi bham|yachi bham 1.4.18|यचि भम्|यचि भम् १.४.१८|१.४.१८|१.४.१८ यचि भम्
And when an affix with an initial य् or an initial vowel, being one of the affixes, beginning with सु and ending in क् , follows, not being सर्वनामस्थान , then what precedes, is called भ।<br><br>Terms: पद संज्ञा

1.4.19|1.4.19 tasau matvarthe|tasau matvarthe|tasau matvarthe 1.4.19|तसौ मत्वर्थे|तसौ मत्वर्थे १.४.१९|१.४.१९|१.४.१९ तसौ मत्वर्थे
The word-form ending in त् or in स् is called भ when an affix with the force of मतुप् 'whose is it' or 'in whom it is' ५.२.९४, follows.<br><br>Terms: भ संज्ञा

1.4.20|1.4.20 ayasmayaadiini chChandasi|ayasmayaadiini chChandasi|ayasmayaadiini chChandasi 1.4.20|अयस्मयादीनि च्छन्दसि|अयस्मयादीनि च्छन्दसि १.४.२०|१.४.२०|१.४.२० अयस्मयादीनि च्छन्दसि
Words like अयस्मय etc. are valid forms in the छन्दस्।<br><br>Terms: भ संज्ञा

1.4.21|1.4.21 bahuShu bahuvachanam|bahuShu bahuvachanam|bahuShu bahuvachanam 1.4.21|बहुषु बहुवचनम्|बहुषु बहुवचनम् १.४.२१|१.४.२१|१.४.२१ बहुषु बहुवचनम्
In expressing multeity, a Plural case affix is employed.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

1.4.22|1.4.22 dvyekayordvivachanaikavachane|dvyekayordvivachanaikavachane|dvyekayordvivachanaikavachane 1.4.22|द्व्येकयोर्द्विवचनैकवचने|द्व्येकयोर्द्विवचनैकवचने १.४.२२|१.४.२२|१.४.२२ द्व्येकयोर्द्विवचनैकवचने
The dual and singular case-affixes are employed severally in the sense of duality and unity.<br><br>Terms: बहुवचन

1.4.23|1.4.23 kaarake|kaarake|kaarake 1.4.23|कारके|कारके १.४.२३|१.४.२३|१.४.२३ कारके
The phrase कारक (meaning 'in the special relation to a word expressing an action') is to be understood in the following aphorisms.<br><br>Terms: एक-द्वि-वचन

1.4.24|1.4.24 dhruvamapaaye.apaadaanam|dhruvamapaaye.apaadaanam|dhruvamapaaye.apaadaanam 1.4.24|ध्रुवमपायेऽपादानम्|ध्रुवमपायेऽपादानम् १.४.२४|१.४.२४|१.४.२४ ध्रुवमपायेऽपादानम्
A noun whose relation to an action is that of a fixed point from which departure takes place is called अपादान or Ablation.<br><br>Terms: कारक

1.4.25|1.4.25 bhiitraarthaanaaM bhayahetuH|bhiitraarthaanaaM bhayahetuH|bhiitraarthaanaaM bhayahetuH 1.4.25|भीत्रार्थानां भयहेतुः|भीत्रार्थानां भयहेतुः १.४.२५|१.४.२५|१.४.२५ भीत्रार्थानां भयहेतुः
In case of words implying 'fear' and 'protection from danger' that from which the danger of fear procedes is called अपादान कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.26|1.4.26 paraajerasoDhaH|paraajerasoDhaH|paraajerasoDhaH 1.4.26|पराजेरसोढः|पराजेरसोढः १.४.२६|१.४.२६|१.४.२६ पराजेरसोढः
In the case of the verb पराजि 'to be tired or weary of', that which becomes unbearable, is called अपादान कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.27|1.4.27 vaaraNaarthaanaaM iipsitaH|vaaraNaarthaanaaM iipsitaH|vaaraNaarthaanaaM iipsitaH 1.4.27|वारणार्थानां ईप्सितः|वारणार्थानां ईप्सितः १.४.२७|१.४.२७|१.४.२७ वारणार्थानां ईप्सितः
In case of verbs having the sense of 'preventing, the desired object from which one is prevented or warded off', is called Ablation or अपदान कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.28|1.4.28 antarddhau yenaadarshanamichChati|antarddhau yenaadarshanamichChati|antarddhau yenaadarshanamichChati 1.4.28|अन्तर्द्धौ येनादर्शनमिच्छति|अन्तर्द्धौ येनादर्शनमिच्छति १.४.२८|१.४.२८|१.४.२८ अन्तर्द्धौ येनादर्शनमिच्छति
When concealment is indicated, the person whose sight one wishes to avoid, is called अपादान कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.29|1.4.29 aakhyaatopayoge|aakhyaatopayoge|aakhyaatopayoge 1.4.29|आख्यातोपयोगे|आख्यातोपयोगे १.४.२९|१.४.२९|१.४.२९ आख्यातोपयोगे
The noun denoting the teacher is called Ablation or अपादान , in relation to the action signifying formal teaching.<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.30|1.4.30 janikartuH prakRtiH|janikartuH prakRtiH|janikartuH prakRtiH 1.4.30|जनिकर्तुः प्रकृतिः|जनिकर्तुः प्रकृतिः १.४.३०|१.४.३०|१.४.३० जनिकर्तुः प्रकृतिः
The prime cause of the agent of the verb जन् 'to be born', is called अपादान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.31|1.4.31 bhuvaH prabhavaH|bhuvaH prabhavaH|bhuvaH prabhavaH 1.4.31|भुवः प्रभवः|भुवः प्रभवः १.४.३१|१.४.३१|१.४.३१ भुवः प्रभवः
The source of the agent of the verb भू 'to become' is called अपादान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.32|1.4.32 karmaNaa yamabhipraiti sa sampradaanam|karmaNaa yamabhipraiti sa sampradaanam|karmaNaa yamabhipraiti sa sampradaanam 1.4.32|कर्मणा यमभिप्रैति स सम्प्रदानम्|कर्मणा यमभिप्रैति स सम्प्रदानम् १.४.३२|१.४.३२|१.४.३२ कर्मणा यमभिप्रैति स सम्प्रदानम्
The person whom one wishes to connect with the object of giving, is called सम्प्रदान or receipient.<br><br>Terms: कारक-अपादान

1.4.33|1.4.33 ruchyarthaanaaM priiyamaaNaH|ruchyarthaanaaM priiyamaaNaH|ruchyarthaanaaM priiyamaaNaH 1.4.33|रुच्यर्थानां प्रीयमाणः|रुच्यर्थानां प्रीयमाणः १.४.३३|१.४.३३|१.४.३३ रुच्यर्थानां प्रीयमाणः
In case of verbs having the signification of the root रुच् 'to like', the person or thing that is pleased or satisfied, is called सम्प्रदान or receipient.<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.34|1.4.34 shlaaghahnuNGsthaashapaaM JNiipsyamaanaH|shlaaghahnuNGsthaashapaaM JNiipsyamaanaH|shlaaghahnuNGsthaashapaaM JNiipsyamaanaH 1.4.34|श्लाघह्नुङ्स्थाशपां ज्ञीप्स्यमानः|श्लाघह्नुङ्स्थाशपां ज्ञीप्स्यमानः १.४.३४|१.४.३४|१.४.३४ श्लाघह्नुङ्स्थाशपां ज्ञीप्स्यमानः
In case of verbs श्लाघ् 'to praise', ह्नु 'to take away', स्था 'to stand', शप् 'to curse', the preson whom it is intended to inform of or persuade by, these actions, is called सम्प्रदान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.35|1.4.35 dhaareruttamarNaH|dhaareruttamarNaH|dhaareruttamarNaH 1.4.35|धारेरुत्तमर्णः|धारेरुत्तमर्णः १.४.३५|१.४.३५|१.४.३५ धारेरुत्तमर्णः
In the case of the verb धारि 'to owe', the creditor is called सम्प्रदान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.36|1.4.36 spRheriipsitaH|spRheriipsitaH|spRheriipsitaH 1.4.36|स्पृहेरीप्सितः|स्पृहेरीप्सितः १.४.३६|१.४.३६|१.४.३६ स्पृहेरीप्सितः
In the case of the verb स्पृह् 'to desire', the thing desired is called सम्प्रदान कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.37|1.4.37 krudhadruherShyaa.asuuyaarthaanaaM yaM prati kopaH|krudhadruherShyaa.asuuyaarthaanaaM yaM prati kopaH|krudhadruherShyaa.asuuyaarthaanaaM yaM prati kopaH 1.4.37|क्रुधद्रुहेर्ष्याऽसूयार्थानां यं प्रति कोपः|क्रुधद्रुहेर्ष्याऽसूयार्थानां यं प्रति कोपः १.४.३७|१.४.३७|१.४.३७ क्रुधद्रुहेर्ष्याऽसूयार्थानां यं प्रति कोपः
In the case of the verbs having the sense of क्रद्ध् 'to be angry', द्रुह् 'to injure', ईर्ष्या 'to envy', असूया 'to detract', the person against whom the feeling of anger etc. is directed is called सम्प्रदान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.38|1.4.38 krudhadruhorupasRShTayoH karma|krudhadruhorupasRShTayoH karma|krudhadruhorupasRShTayoH karma 1.4.38|क्रुधद्रुहोरुपसृष्टयोः कर्म|क्रुधद्रुहोरुपसृष्टयोः कर्म १.४.३८|१.४.३८|१.४.३८ क्रुधद्रुहोरुपसृष्टयोः कर्म
But in the case of the verbs क्रुद्ध् and द्रुह् , when preceded by prepositions, the person against whom the feeling of anger etc. is directed is called कर्म कारक or object.<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.39|1.4.39 raadhiixyoryasya viprashnaH|raadhiixyoryasya viprashnaH|raadhiixyoryasya viprashnaH 1.4.39|राधीक्ष्योर्यस्य विप्रश्नः|राधीक्ष्योर्यस्य विप्रश्नः १.४.३९|१.४.३९|१.४.३९ राधीक्ष्योर्यस्य विप्रश्नः
In the case of the verbs राध् 'to propitiate' and ईक्ष् 'to look to', the person about whose good or bad fortune questions are asked is called सम्प्रदान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म

1.4.40|1.4.40 pratyaaNGbhyaaM shruvaH puurvasya kartaa|pratyaaNGbhyaaM shruvaH puurvasya kartaa|pratyaaNGbhyaaM shruvaH puurvasya kartaa 1.4.40|प्रत्याङ्भ्यां श्रुवः पूर्वस्य कर्ता|प्रत्याङ्भ्यां श्रुवः पूर्वस्य कर्ता १.४.४०|१.४.४०|१.४.४० प्रत्याङ्भ्यां श्रुवः पूर्वस्य कर्ता
In the case of the verb श्रु preceded by the prepositions प्रति and अङ् and meaning 'to promise', the person to whom promise is made (literally: the person who as the agent of the former verb) is called सम्प्रदान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.41|1.4.41 anupratigRNashcha|anupratigRNashcha|anupratigRNashcha 1.4.41|अनुप्रतिगृणश्च|अनुप्रतिगृणश्च १.४.४१|१.४.४१|१.४.४१ अनुप्रतिगृणश्च
In the case of the verb गृ preceded by अनु and प्रति and meaning 'to encourage by repeating', the person who was the agent of the prior action, which is repeated, is called सम्प्रदान।<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.42|1.4.42 saadhakatamaM karaNam|saadhakatamaM karaNam|saadhakatamaM karaNam 1.4.42|साधकतमं करणम्|साधकतमं करणम् १.४.४२|१.४.४२|१.४.४२ साधकतमं करणम्
That which is especially auxiliary in the accomplishment of the action is called Instrument or करण कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.43|1.4.43 divaH karma cha|divaH karma cha|divaH karma cha 1.4.43|दिवः कर्म च|दिवः कर्म च १.४.४३|१.४.४३|१.४.४३ दिवः कर्म च
That which is especially auxiliary in the accomplishment of the action, of the verb दिव् 'to play' is called कर्म - object, as well as करण।<br><br>Terms: कारक-करण

1.4.44|1.4.44 parikrayaNe sampradaanamanyatarasyaam|parikrayaNe sampradaanamanyatarasyaam|parikrayaNe sampradaanamanyatarasyaam 1.4.44|परिक्रयणे सम्प्रदानमन्यतरस्याम्|परिक्रयणे सम्प्रदानमन्यतरस्याम् १.४.४४|१.४.४४|१.४.४४ परिक्रयणे सम्प्रदानमन्यतरस्याम्
In the case of hiring on wages, that which is especially auxiliary in the accomplishment of the action of the verb परिक्री 'employing on stipulated wages', is optionally called सम्प्रदान or receipient.<br><br>Terms: कारक-करण

1.4.45|1.4.45 aadhaaro.adhikaraNam|aadhaaro.adhikaraNam|aadhaaro.adhikaraNam 1.4.45|आधारोऽधिकरणम्|आधारोऽधिकरणम् १.४.४५|१.४.४५|१.४.४५ आधारोऽधिकरणम्
That which is related to the action as the site where the action is performed by reason of the agent or the object being in that place is called अधिकरण or location.<br><br>Terms: कारक-सम्प्रदान

1.4.46|1.4.46 adhishiiNGsthaa.a.asaaM karma|adhishiiNGsthaa.a.asaaM karma|adhishiiNGsthaa.a.asaaM karma 1.4.46|अधिशीङ्स्थाऽऽसां कर्म|अधिशीङ्स्थाऽऽसां कर्म १.४.४६|१.४.४६|१.४.४६ अधिशीङ्स्थाऽऽसां कर्म
That which is the site of the verbs शीङ् 'to lie down', स्था 'to stand', आस् 'to sit', when preceded by the preposition अधि , is however called कर्म कारक or object.<br><br>Terms: कारक-अधिकरण

1.4.47|1.4.47 abhinivishashcha|abhinivishashcha|abhinivishashcha 1.4.47|अभिनिविशश्च|अभिनिविशश्च १.४.४७|१.४.४७|१.४.४७ अभिनिविशश्च
That which is the site of the verb अभिनिविश् 'to enter', is also called कर्म कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म

1.4.48|1.4.48 upaanvadhyaaNGvasaH|upaanvadhyaaNGvasaH|upaanvadhyaaNGvasaH 1.4.48|उपान्वध्याङ्वसः|उपान्वध्याङ्वसः १.४.४८|१.४.४८|१.४.४८ उपान्वध्याङ्वसः
That which is the site of the verb वस् 'to dwell', when preceded by उप , अनु , and आङ् is called कर्म कारक।<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म

1.4.49|1.4.49 karturiipsitatamaM karma|karturiipsitatamaM karma|karturiipsitatamaM karma 1.4.49|कर्तुरीप्सिततमं कर्म|कर्तुरीप्सिततमं कर्म १.४.४९|१.४.४९|१.४.४९ कर्तुरीप्सिततमं कर्म
That which is intended should be most effected by the act of the agent is called the object or कर्म।<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म

1.4.50|1.4.50 tathaayuktaM chaanipsiitam|tathaayuktaM chaanipsiitam|tathaayuktaM chaanipsiitam 1.4.50|तथायुक्तं चानिप्सीतम्|तथायुक्तं चानिप्सीतम् १.४.५०|१.४.५०|१.४.५० तथायुक्तं चानिप्सीतम्
If that which is not intended to be most affected by the act becomes however similarly connected with the action it also is called कर्म।<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म-संज्ञा

1.4.51|1.4.51 akathitaM cha|akathitaM cha|akathitaM cha 1.4.51|अकथितं च|अकथितं च १.४.५१|१.४.५१|१.४.५१ अकथितं च
And if that कारक which is not spoken of as coming under any of the special relations of Ablation etc., is also called कर्म।<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म

1.4.52|1.4.52 gatibuddhipratyavasaanaarthashabdakarmaakarmakaaNaamaNi kartaa|gatibuddhipratyavasaanaarthashabdakarmaakarmakaaNaamaNi kartaa|gatibuddhipratyavasaanaarthashabdakarmaakarmakaaNaamaNi kartaa 1.4.52|गतिबुद्धिप्रत्यवसानार्थशब्दकर्माकर्मकाणामणि कर्ता|गतिबुद्धिप्रत्यवसानार्थशब्दकर्माकर्मकाणामणि कर्ता १.४.५२|१.४.५२|१.४.५२ गतिबुद्धिप्रत्यवसानार्थशब्दकर्माकर्मकाणामणि कर्ता
Of the verbs having the sense of 'motion', 'knowledge or information' and 'eating' and of verbs that have some literary work for their object and of intransitive verbs, that which was the agent of the verb in its primitive (non-णि or non-causal state), is called the कर्म or object, in its causative state (when the verb takes the affix णि).<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म-संज्ञा

1.4.53|1.4.53 hRkroranyatarasyaam|hRkroranyatarasyaam|hRkroranyatarasyaam 1.4.53|हृक्रोरन्यतरस्याम्|हृक्रोरन्यतरस्याम् १.४.५३|१.४.५३|१.४.५३ हृक्रोरन्यतरस्याम्
The agent of the verb in its non-णि (primitive) form in the case of हृ 'to lose' and कृ 'to make', is optionally called कर्म or object when these verbs take the affix.<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म

1.4.54|1.4.54 svatantraH kartaa|svatantraH kartaa|svatantraH kartaa 1.4.54|स्वतन्त्रः कर्ता|स्वतन्त्रः कर्ता १.४.५४|१.४.५४|१.४.५४ स्वतन्त्रः कर्ता
Whatever the speaker chooses as the independent, principal and absolute source of action is called कर्ता or agent.<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्म

1.4.55|1.4.55 tatprayojako hetushcha|tatprayojako hetushcha|tatprayojako hetushcha 1.4.55|तत्प्रयोजको हेतुश्च|तत्प्रयोजको हेतुश्च १.४.५५|१.४.५५|१.४.५५ तत्प्रयोजको हेतुश्च
That which is the mover thereof, i.e. of the independent source of action, is called हेतु or cause, as well as कर्ता or agent.<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्ता-संज्ञा

1.4.56|1.4.56 praagriishvaraannipaataaH|praagriishvaraannipaataaH|praagriishvaraannipaataaH 1.4.56|प्राग्रीश्वरान्निपाताः|प्राग्रीश्वरान्निपाताः १.४.५६|१.४.५६|१.४.५६ प्राग्रीश्वरान्निपाताः
From this point forward up to the aphorism अधिरीश्वरे १.४.९७, all that we shall say is to be understood to have the name of निपात or Particles.<br><br>Terms: कारक-कर्ता-संज्ञा

1.4.57|1.4.57 chaadayo.asattve|chaadayo.asattve|chaadayo.asattve 1.4.57|चादयोऽसत्त्वे|चादयोऽसत्त्वे १.४.५७|१.४.५७|१.४.५७ चादयोऽसत्त्वे
The word च 'and' etc. are called निपात or Particles, when they do not signify susbtances.<br><br>Terms: निपात-संज्ञा

1.4.58|1.4.58 praadayaH|praadayaH|praadayaH 1.4.58|प्रादयः|प्रादयः १.४.५८|१.४.५८|१.४.५८ प्रादयः
The words प्र etc. are called निपात when not signifying susbtances.<br><br>Terms: निपात-शब्दाः

1.4.59|1.4.59 upasargaaH kriyaayoge|upasargaaH kriyaayoge|upasargaaH kriyaayoge 1.4.59|उपसर्गाः क्रियायोगे|उपसर्गाः क्रियायोगे १.४.५९|१.४.५९|१.४.५९ उपसर्गाः क्रियायोगे
The words प्र etc. get the designation of उपसर्ग or prepositions, when in composition with a verb.<br><br>Terms: निपात-संज्ञा

1.4.60|1.4.60 gatishcha|gatishcha|gatishcha 1.4.60|गतिश्च|गतिश्च १.४.६०|१.४.६०|१.४.६० गतिश्च
The words प्र etc. are called also गति when in composition with a verb.<br><br>Terms: उपसर्ग-संज्ञा

1.4.61|1.4.61 UryaadichviDaachashcha|UryaadichviDaachashcha|UryaadichviDaachashcha 1.4.61|ऊर्यादिच्विडाचश्च|ऊर्यादिच्विडाचश्च १.४.६१|१.४.६१|१.४.६१ ऊर्यादिच्विडाचश्च
The words उरी 'assent' etc. and those that end with च्वि ५.४.५० and those that end with डाच् ५.४.५७ (when in composition with the verb भू , कृ or अस् ) are called गति।<br><br>Terms: गति-संज्ञा

1.4.62|1.4.62 anukaraNaM chaanitiparam|anukaraNaM chaanitiparam|anukaraNaM chaanitiparam 1.4.62|अनुकरणं चानितिपरम्|अनुकरणं चानितिपरम् १.४.६२|१.४.६२|१.४.६२ अनुकरणं चानितिपरम्
A word imitative of sounds is also called गति when it is not followed by the word इति।<br><br>Terms: गति-संज्ञा

1.4.63|1.4.63 aadaraanaadarayoH sadasatii|aadaraanaadarayoH sadasatii|aadaraanaadarayoH sadasatii 1.4.63|आदरानादरयोः सदसती|आदरानादरयोः सदसती १.४.६३|१.४.६३|१.४.६३ आदरानादरयोः सदसती
The words सत् and असत् when in composition with a verb ae called गति , when used in the sense of 'respect or love' and 'disrespect or indifference'.<br><br>Terms: गति-संज्ञा

1.4.64|1.4.64 bhuuShaNe.alam|bhuuShaNe.alam|bhuuShaNe.alam 1.4.64|भूषणेऽलम्|भूषणेऽलम् १.४.६४|१.४.६४|१.४.६४ भूषणेऽलम्
The word अलम् when in composition with a verb is called गति , when used in the sense of 'ornament'.<br><br>Terms: गति-संज्ञा

1.4.65|1.4.65 antaraparigrahe|antaraparigrahe|antaraparigrahe 1.4.65|अन्तरपरिग्रहे|अन्तरपरिग्रहे १.४.६५|१.४.६५|१.४.६५ अन्तरपरिग्रहे
The word अन्तर् is called गति , when used in the sense of 'non-accepting', when in composition with a verb.<br><br>Terms: गति-अलम्

1.4.66|1.4.66 kaNemanasii shraddhaapratiighaate|kaNemanasii shraddhaapratiighaate|kaNemanasii shraddhaapratiighaate 1.4.66|कणेमनसी श्रद्धाप्रतीघाते|कणेमनसी श्रद्धाप्रतीघाते १.४.६६|१.४.६६|१.४.६६ कणेमनसी श्रद्धाप्रतीघाते
The words कणे and मनस् are गति when in composition with a verb and used in the sense of 'reaction by satiation'.<br><br>Terms: गति-अन्तर्

1.4.67|1.4.67 puro.avyayam|puro.avyayam|puro.avyayam 1.4.67|पुरोऽव्ययम्|पुरोऽव्ययम् १.४.६७|१.४.६७|१.४.६७ पुरोऽव्ययम्
The word पुरः 'in front of', when indeclinable and in composition with a verb, is called गति।<br><br>Terms: गति-मनस्-कणे

1.4.68|1.4.68 astaM cha|astaM cha|astaM cha 1.4.68|अस्तं च|अस्तं च १.४.६८|१.४.६८|१.४.६८ अस्तं च
And the indeclinable word अस्तम् 'at home' is called गति , when in composition with a verb.<br><br>Terms: गति-पुरः

1.4.69|1.4.69 achCha gatyarthavadeShu|achCha gatyarthavadeShu|achCha gatyarthavadeShu 1.4.69|अच्छ गत्यर्थवदेषु|अच्छ गत्यर्थवदेषु १.४.६९|१.४.६९|१.४.६९ अच्छ गत्यर्थवदेषु
The indeclinable word अच्छ 'before in the presence of' is called गति , when used in the composition with verbs denoting 'motion' or with the verb वद् 'to speak'.<br><br>Terms: गति-अस्तम्

1.4.70|1.4.70 ado.anupadeshe|ado.anupadeshe|ado.anupadeshe 1.4.70|अदोऽनुपदेशे|अदोऽनुपदेशे १.४.७०|१.४.७०|१.४.७० अदोऽनुपदेशे
The word अदस् 'that' is called गति when in composition with a verb and not implying a direction to another.<br><br>Terms: गति-अच्छ

1.4.71|1.4.71 tiro.antarddhau|tiro.antarddhau|tiro.antarddhau 1.4.71|तिरोऽन्तर्द्धौ|तिरोऽन्तर्द्धौ १.४.७१|१.४.७१|१.४.७१ तिरोऽन्तर्द्धौ
The word तिरस् when used in the sense of 'disappearance' is called गति when in composition with a verb.<br><br>Terms: गति-अदस्

1.4.72|1.4.72 vibhaaShaa kRNJi|vibhaaShaa kRNJi|vibhaaShaa kRNJi 1.4.72|विभाषा कृञि|विभाषा कृञि १.४.७२|१.४.७२|१.४.७२ विभाषा कृञि
The word तिरस् 'disappearance' is optionally called गति when the verb कृ follows.<br><br>Terms: गति-तिरस्

1.4.73|1.4.73 upaaje.anvaaje|upaaje.anvaaje|upaaje.anvaaje 1.4.73|उपाजेऽन्वाजे|उपाजेऽन्वाजे १.४.७३|१.४.७३|१.४.७३ उपाजेऽन्वाजे
The words उपाजे and अनवाजे both meaning 'supporting or assisting the weak', are optionally called गति when used along with the verb कृ।<br><br>Terms: गति-तिरस्-कृ

1.4.74|1.4.74 saaxaatprabhRtiini cha|saaxaatprabhRtiini cha|saaxaatprabhRtiini cha 1.4.74|साक्षात्प्रभृतीनि च|साक्षात्प्रभृतीनि च १.४.७४|१.४.७४|१.४.७४ साक्षात्प्रभृतीनि च
The words साक्षात् 'in the presence of' etc. are optionally called गति when used along with the verb कृ।<br><br>Terms: गति-उपाजे-अनवाजे-कृ

1.4.75|1.4.75 anatyaadhaana urasimanasii|anatyaadhaana urasimanasii|anatyaadhaana urasimanasii 1.4.75|अनत्याधान उरसिमनसी|अनत्याधान उरसिमनसी १.४.७५|१.४.७५|१.४.७५ अनत्याधान उरसिमनसी
The word उर्सि 'in the breast' and मनसि 'in the mind' ae optionally called गति when the verb कृ follows, provided that they are not used in the sense of 'placing'.<br><br>Terms: गति-साक्षात्-कृ

1.4.76|1.4.76 madhyepadenivachane cha|madhyepadenivachane cha|madhyepadenivachane cha 1.4.76|मध्येपदेनिवचने च|मध्येपदेनिवचने च १.४.७६|१.४.७६|१.४.७६ मध्येपदेनिवचने च
And the words मध्ये 'in the middle', पदे 'in the foot' and निवचने 'speechless' are optionally called गति , when कृ follows, the sense not being of placing.<br><br>Terms: गति-उर्सि-मनसि

1.4.77|1.4.77 nityaM haste paaNaavupayamane|nityaM haste paaNaavupayamane|nityaM haste paaNaavupayamane 1.4.77|नित्यं हस्ते पाणावुपयमने|नित्यं हस्ते पाणावुपयमने १.४.७७|१.४.७७|१.४.७७ नित्यं हस्ते पाणावुपयमने
The word हस्ते 'in the hand', पाणौ 'in the hand' are always necessarily called गति when used with the verb कृ in the sense of 'marriage'.<br><br>Terms: गति-मध्ये

1.4.78|1.4.78 praadhvaM bandhane|praadhvaM bandhane|praadhvaM bandhane 1.4.78|प्राध्वं बन्धने|प्राध्वं बन्धने १.४.७८|१.४.७८|१.४.७८ प्राध्वं बन्धने
The indeclinable word प्रध्वम् followed by the verb कृ , is always called गति when in used in the sense of 'binding'.<br><br>Terms: गति-हस्ते

1.4.79|1.4.79 jiivikopaniShadaavaupamye|jiivikopaniShadaavaupamye|jiivikopaniShadaavaupamye 1.4.79|जीविकोपनिषदावौपम्ये|जीविकोपनिषदावौपम्ये १.४.७९|१.४.७९|१.४.७९ जीविकोपनिषदावौपम्ये
The words जीविका and उपनिषद् followed by the verb कृ are called गति when used in the sense of 'likeness and resemblance'.<br><br>Terms: गति-प्रध्वम्

1.4.80|1.4.80 te praagdhaatoH|te praagdhaatoH|te praagdhaatoH 1.4.80|ते प्राग्धातोः|ते प्राग्धातोः १.४.८०|१.४.८०|१.४.८० ते प्राग्धातोः
The particles called गति and उपसर्ग are to be employed before the verbal roots (i.e. to say that they are prefixes).<br><br>Terms: गति-जीविका-उपनिषद्

1.4.81|1.4.81 Chandasi pare.api|Chandasi pare.api|Chandasi pare.api 1.4.81|छन्दसि परेऽपि|छन्दसि परेऽपि १.४.८१|१.४.८१|१.४.८१ छन्दसि परेऽपि
In the छन्दस् (Veda) these गति and उपसर्ग are employed indifferently after the verbal root, as well as before it.<br><br>Terms: गति-उपसर्ग

1.4.82|1.4.82 vyavahitaashcha|vyavahitaashcha|vyavahitaashcha 1.4.82|व्यवहिताश्च|व्यवहिताश्च १.४.८२|१.४.८२|१.४.८२ व्यवहिताश्च
In the छन्दस् (Veda) these गति and उपसर्ग are also seen separated from the verb by intervening words.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

1.4.83|1.4.83 karmapravachaniiyaaH|karmapravachaniiyaaH|karmapravachaniiyaaH 1.4.83|कर्मप्रवचनीयाः|कर्मप्रवचनीयाः १.४.८३|१.४.८३|१.४.८३ कर्मप्रवचनीयाः
From this point as far as aphorism १.४.९७ treated of, are to be understood as having the name of कर्म-प्रवचनीय।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

1.4.84|1.4.84 anurlaxaNe|anurlaxaNe|anurlaxaNe 1.4.84|अनुर्लक्षणे|अनुर्लक्षणे १.४.८४|१.४.८४|१.४.८४ अनुर्लक्षणे
The word अनु , when it denotes a sign, is called कर्म-प्रवचनीय।<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय-संज्ञा

1.4.85|1.4.85 tRtiiyaa.arthe|tRtiiyaa.arthe|tRtiiyaa.arthe 1.4.85|तृतीयाऽर्थे|तृतीयाऽर्थे १.४.८५|१.४.८५|१.४.८५ तृतीयाऽर्थे
The word अनु , कर्म-प्रवचनीय when it has the force of the 3rd case.<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय-अनु

1.4.86|1.4.86 hiine|hiine|hiine 1.4.86|हीने|हीने १.४.८६|१.४.८६|१.४.८६ हीने
The word अनु , कर्म-प्रवचनीय when it is used in the sense of 'inferior or subordinate to'.<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय-अनु

1.4.87|1.4.87 upo.adhike cha|upo.adhike cha|upo.adhike cha 1.4.87|उपोऽधिके च|उपोऽधिके च १.४.८७|१.४.८७|१.४.८७ उपोऽधिके च
The word उप when it means 'superior' or 'inferior to' is कर्म-प्रवचनीय।<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय-अनु

1.4.88|1.4.88 apaparii varjane|apaparii varjane|apaparii varjane 1.4.88|अपपरी वर्जने|अपपरी वर्जने १.४.८८|१.४.८८|१.४.८८ अपपरी वर्जने
The words अप and परि are कर्म-प्रवचनीय when meaning 'exclusion'.<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय-उप

1.4.89|1.4.89 aaNG maryaadaavachane|aaNG maryaadaavachane|aaNG maryaadaavachane 1.4.89|आङ् मर्यादावचने|आङ् मर्यादावचने १.४.८९|१.४.८९|१.४.८९ आङ् मर्यादावचने
The word आङ् 'as far as', is कर्म-प्रवचनीय when it expresses limit (e.g. when it means 'as far as inclusive of' or 'as far as exclusive of').<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय-उप

1.4.90|1.4.90 laxaNetthambhuutaakhyaanabhaagaviipsaasu pratiparyanavaH|laxaNetthambhuutaakhyaanabhaagaviipsaasu pratiparyanavaH|laxaNetthambhuutaakhyaanabhaagaviipsaasu pratiparyanavaH 1.4.90|लक्षणेत्थम्भूताख्यानभागवीप्सासु प्रतिपर्यनवः|लक्षणेत्थम्भूताख्यानभागवीप्सासु प्रतिपर्यनवः १.४.९०|१.४.९०|१.४.९० लक्षणेत्थम्भूताख्यानभागवीप्सासु प्रतिपर्यनवः
The words प्रति , परि and अनु are कर्म-प्रवचनीय when used in the sense of 'sign' ('in the direction of') , 'mere statement of circumstances' ('as regards'), 'division', 'share of' and 'pervasion', severally.<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.91|1.4.91 abhirabhaage|abhirabhaage|abhirabhaage 1.4.91|अभिरभागे|अभिरभागे १.४.९१|१.४.९१|१.४.९१ अभिरभागे
The word अभि is कर्म-प्रवचनीय when used in the above senses of 'in the direction of', 'as regards', and 'each severally', but not when it means 'division', 'share of'.<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.92|1.4.92 pratiH pratinidhipratidaanayoH|pratiH pratinidhipratidaanayoH|pratiH pratinidhipratidaanayoH 1.4.92|प्रतिः प्रतिनिधिप्रतिदानयोः|प्रतिः प्रतिनिधिप्रतिदानयोः १.४.९२|१.४.९२|१.४.९२ प्रतिः प्रतिनिधिप्रतिदानयोः
The word प्रति is कर्म -प्रवचनीय when used in the sense of representative ('representative of') or exchange ('in exchange for').<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.93|1.4.93 adhiparii anarthakau|adhiparii anarthakau|adhiparii anarthakau 1.4.93|अधिपरी अनर्थकौ|अधिपरी अनर्थकौ १.४.९३|१.४.९३|१.४.९३ अधिपरी अनर्थकौ
The words अधि and परि are कर्म-प्रवचनीय when used as mere expletives.<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.94|1.4.94 suH puujaayaam|suH puujaayaam|suH puujaayaam 1.4.94|सुः पूजायाम्|सुः पूजायाम् १.४.९४|१.४.९४|१.४.९४ सुः पूजायाम्
The word सु is कर्म-प्रवचनीय when used in the sense of respect, (when it means 'excellently').<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.95|1.4.95 atiratikramaNe cha|atiratikramaNe cha|atiratikramaNe cha 1.4.95|अतिरतिक्रमणे च|अतिरतिक्रमणे च १.४.९५|१.४.९५|१.४.९५ अतिरतिक्रमणे च
The word अति in the sense of super-abundance ('excessively') and 'excellently' is कर्म-प्रवचनीय।<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.96|1.4.96 apiH padaarthasambhaavanaanvavasargagarhaasamuchchayeShu|apiH padaarthasambhaavanaanvavasargagarhaasamuchchayeShu|apiH padaarthasambhaavanaanvavasargagarhaasamuchchayeShu 1.4.96|अपिः पदार्थसम्भावनान्ववसर्गगर्हासमुच्चयेषु|अपिः पदार्थसम्भावनान्ववसर्गगर्हासमुच्चयेषु १.४.९६|१.४.९६|१.४.९६ अपिः पदार्थसम्भावनान्ववसर्गगर्हासमुच्चयेषु
The word अपि is कर्म-प्रवचनीय when it implies, the sense of word 'understood' ('somewhat') or 'possibility' (e.g. 'even' in the sense of such a great person), or permission to do as one likes, ('if you like'), or censure ('even' in the sense of what is disgraceful); or collection ('and').<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.97|1.4.97 adhiriishvare|adhiriishvare|adhiriishvare 1.4.97|अधिरीश्वरे|अधिरीश्वरे १.४.९७|१.४.९७|१.४.९७ अधिरीश्वरे
The words अधि is कर्म-प्रवचनीय when used in the sense of 'lord' ('being as a lord' or 'having as a lord')<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.98|1.4.98 vibhaaShaa kRNJi|vibhaaShaa kRNJi|vibhaaShaa kRNJi 1.4.98|विभाषा कृञि|विभाषा कृञि १.४.९८|१.४.९८|१.४.९८ विभाषा कृञि
The words अधि is optionally कर्म-प्रवचनीय when the verb कृ follows.<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.99|1.4.99 laH parasmaipadam|laH parasmaipadam|laH parasmaipadam 1.4.99|लः परस्मैपदम्|लः परस्मैपदम् १.४.९९|१.४.९९|१.४.९९ लः परस्मैपदम्
The substitutes of ल are called परस्मैपद।<br><br>Terms: कर्मप्रवचनीय

1.4.100|1.4.100 taNGaanaavaatmanepadam|taNGaanaavaatmanepadam|taNGaanaavaatmanepadam 1.4.100|तङानावात्मनेपदम्|तङानावात्मनेपदम् १.४.१००|१.४.१००|१.४.१०० तङानावात्मनेपदम्
The nine affixes comprised under the प्रत्याहार - तङ् and the two ending in आन (शानच् and कानच्), which are susbtitutes of ल are called आत्मनेपद।<br><br>Terms: परस्मैपद-संज्ञा

1.4.101|1.4.101 tiNGastriiNi triiNi prathamamadhyamottamaaH|tiNGastriiNi triiNi prathamamadhyamottamaaH|tiNGastriiNi triiNi prathamamadhyamottamaaH 1.4.101|तिङस्त्रीणि त्रीणि प्रथममध्यमोत्तमाः|तिङस्त्रीणि त्रीणि प्रथममध्यमोत्तमाः १.४.१०१|१.४.१०१|१.४.१०१ तिङस्त्रीणि त्रीणि प्रथममध्यमोत्तमाः
The three triads in both the sets परस्मैपद and आत्मनेपद , of conjugational affixes (comprised under the general name तिङ् , a प्रत्यहार formed of the first and last of them, viz. तिप् and महिङ्) are called, in order, Lowest - 3rd Person of European Grammar, Middle -2nd Person, and Highest -1st Person.<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.102|1.4.102 taanyekavachanadvivachanabahuvachanaanyekashaH|taanyekavachanadvivachanabahuvachanaanyekashaH|taanyekavachanadvivachanabahuvachanaanyekashaH 1.4.102|तान्येकवचनद्विवचनबहुवचनान्येकशः|तान्येकवचनद्विवचनबहुवचनान्येकशः १.४.१०२|१.४.१०२|१.४.१०२ तान्येकवचनद्विवचनबहुवचनान्येकशः
These three triads of conjugational affixes, which have received the name of Lowest etc. are called (as regard the three expressions in each triad) severally 'the expression for one' (singular), 'the expression for two' (dual) and 'the expression for many' (plural).<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.103|1.4.103 supaH|supaH|supaH 1.4.103|सुपः|सुपः १.४.१०३|१.४.१०३|१.४.१०३ सुपः
Of सुप् (which is a प्रत्याहार formed of सु the first of the case affixes and the final प् of the last of them), the expressions in each successive set of the three, are also severally called singular, dual and plural.<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.104|1.4.104 vibhaktishcha|vibhaktishcha|vibhaktishcha 1.4.104|विभक्तिश्च|विभक्तिश्च १.४.१०४|१.४.१०४|१.४.१०४ विभक्तिश्च
The triads of conjugational affixes and case affixes are also called विभक्ति or Inflective affixes.<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.105|1.4.105 yuShmadyupapade samaanaadhikaraNe sthaaninyapi madhyamaH|yuShmadyupapade samaanaadhikaraNe sthaaninyapi madhyamaH|yuShmadyupapade samaanaadhikaraNe sthaaninyapi madhyamaH 1.4.105|युष्मद्युपपदे समानाधिकरणे स्थानिन्यपि मध्यमः|युष्मद्युपपदे समानाधिकरणे स्थानिन्यपि मध्यमः १.४.१०५|१.४.१०५|१.४.१०५ युष्मद्युपपदे समानाधिकरणे स्थानिन्यपि मध्यमः
When the pronoun युष्मद् 'thou' understood, and also when the same expressed, is the attendant word in the agreement with the verb, then there is the verbal termination called the middle (2nd person).<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.106|1.4.106 prahaase cha manyopapade manyateruttama ekavachcha|prahaase cha manyopapade manyateruttama ekavachcha|prahaase cha manyopapade manyateruttama ekavachcha 1.4.106|प्रहासे च मन्योपपदे मन्यतेरुत्तम एकवच्च|प्रहासे च मन्योपपदे मन्यतेरुत्तम एकवच्च १.४.१०६|१.४.१०६|१.४.१०६ प्रहासे च मन्योपपदे मन्यतेरुत्तम एकवच्च
When joke is implied with reference to an action, the verb denoting it is used in the 2nd person; provided that the word मन्य 'to think' is the attendant word (उपपद) of such verb and of the verb मन्य itself, the affix must be of the 1st person and singular number.<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.107|1.4.107 asmadyuttamaH|asmadyuttamaH|asmadyuttamaH 1.4.107|अस्मद्युत्तमः|अस्मद्युत्तमः १.४.१०७|१.४.१०७|१.४.१०७ अस्मद्युत्तमः
When the pronoun अस्मद् 'I', understood and also when expressed, is the attendant word in agreement with the verb, then there is the verbal termination called the Highest or 1st person.<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.108|1.4.108 sheShe prathamaH|sheShe prathamaH|sheShe prathamaH 1.4.108|शेषे प्रथमः|शेषे प्रथमः १.४.१०८|१.४.१०८|१.४.१०८ शेषे प्रथमः
In the other cases, viz. where 'thou' or 'I' are not the attendant words in agreement with the verb, there is the verbal termination called the Lowest (3rd person).<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.109|1.4.109 paraH saMnikarShaH saMhitaa|paraH saMnikarShaH saMhitaa|paraH saMnikarShaH saMhitaa 1.4.109|परः संनिकर्षः संहिता|परः संनिकर्षः संहिता १.४.१०९|१.४.१०९|१.४.१०९ परः संनिकर्षः संहिता
The closest proximity of letters, there being the intervention of half a मात्रा or prosodial length between them, is called contact or संहिता।<br><br>Terms: 

1.4.110|1.4.110 viraamo.avasaanam|viraamo.avasaanam|viraamo.avasaanam 1.4.110|विरामोऽवसानम्|विरामोऽवसानम् १.४.११०|१.४.११०|१.४.११० विरामोऽवसानम्
The cessation or the absence of succeeding letters is called pause or अवसान।<br><br>Terms: सन्धि-संज्ञा

2.1.1|2.1.1 samarthaH padavidhiH|samarthaH padavidhiH|samarthaH padavidhiH 2.1.1|समर्थः पदविधिः|समर्थः पदविधिः २.१.१|२.१.१|२.१.१ समर्थः पदविधिः
A rule which relates to complete words (and not to the roots out of which the words are constructed) is to be understood to apply only to those words the senses of which are connected.<br><br>Terms: पद-परिभाषा

2.1.2|2.1.2 subaamantrite paraangavat‌ svare|subaamantrite paraangavat‌ svare|subaamantrite paraangavat‌ svare 2.1.2|सुबामन्त्रिते पराङ्गवत्‌ स्वरे|सुबामन्त्रिते पराङ्गवत्‌ स्वरे २.१.२|२.१.२|२.१.२ सुबामन्त्रिते पराङ्गवत्‌ स्वरे
A word ending in सुप् or a case-affix, when followed by a word in the Vocative Case, is regarded as if it was the अङ्ग or component part of such subsequent vocative word, when a rule relating to accent is to be applied.<br><br>Terms: 

2.1.3|2.1.3 praak kaDaaraat‌ samaasaH|praak kaDaaraat‌ samaasaH|praak kaDaaraat‌ samaasaH 2.1.3|प्राक् कडारात्‌ समासः|प्राक् कडारात्‌ समासः २.१.३|२.१.३|२.१.३ प्राक् कडारात्‌ समासः
From this point up to the aphorism कडाराः कर्मधराये २.२.३८, all the terms that we shall say, describe will get the designation of समास or compound<br><br>Terms: समास

2.1.4|2.1.4 saha supaa|saha supaa|saha supaa 2.1.4|सह सुपा|सह सुपा २.१.४|२.१.४|२.१.४ सह सुपा
The words सह सुपा meaning 'with a word ending in a case-affix', are to be understood in each of the succeeding aphorisms.<br><br>Terms: समास

2.1.5|2.1.5 avyayiibhaavaH|avyayiibhaavaH|avyayiibhaavaH 2.1.5|अव्ययीभावः|अव्ययीभावः २.१.५|२.१.५|२.१.५ अव्ययीभावः
From this point forward whatever we shall describe will get the name अव्ययीभाव समास or adverbial compound.<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास

2.1.6|2.1.6 avyayaM vibhaktisamiipasamRddhivyRddhyarthaabhaavaatyayaasampratishabdapraadurbhaavapashchaadyathaa.a.anupuurvyayaugapadyasaadRshyasampattisaakalyaantavachaneShu|avyayaM vibhaktisamiipasamRddhivyRddhyarthaabhaavaatyayaasampratishabdapraadurbhaavapashchaadyathaa.a.anupuurvyayaugapadyasaadRshyasampattisaakalyaantavachaneShu|avyayaM vibhaktisamiipasamRddhivyRddhyarthaabhaavaatyayaasampratishabdapraadurbhaavapashchaadyathaa.a.anupuurvyayaugapadyasaadRshyasampattisaakalyaantavachaneShu 2.1.6|अव्ययं विभक्तिसमीपसमृद्धिव्यृद्ध्यर्थाभावात्ययासम्प्रतिशब्दप्रादुर्भावपश्चाद्यथाऽऽनुपूर्व्ययौगपद्यसादृश्यसम्पत्तिसाकल्यान्तवचनेषु|अव्ययं विभक्तिसमीपसमृद्धिव्यृद्ध्यर्थाभावात्ययासम्प्रतिशब्दप्रादुर्भावपश्चाद्यथाऽऽनुपूर्व्ययौगपद्यसादृश्यसम्पत्तिसाकल्यान्तवचनेषु २.१.६|२.१.६|२.१.६ अव्ययं विभक्तिसमीपसमृद्धिव्यृद्ध्यर्थाभावात्ययासम्प्रतिशब्दप्रादुर्भावपश्चाद्यथाऽऽनुपूर्व्ययौगपद्यसादृश्यसम्पत्तिसाकल्यान्तवचनेषु
An अव्यय - indeclinable, used with the sense of an inflective-affix (विभक्ति) or of near to, or prosperity, or diversity, or absence of the thing, or departure, or not now, or the production of some sound, or after, or according to, or order of arrangement, or totality, or termination, is invariably compounded with a word ending in a case-affix which is connected with it in sense and the compound so formed is called अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास

2.1.7|2.1.7 yathaa.asaadRye|yathaa.asaadRye|yathaa.asaadRye 2.1.7|यथाऽसादृये|यथाऽसादृये २.१.७|२.१.७|२.१.७ यथाऽसादृये
The indeclinable word यथा when it does not signify 'likeness' is invariably compounded with a word ending in a case-affix which is in construction with it and the compound is called अव्ययीभाव समास।<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास

2.1.8|2.1.8 yaavadavadhaaraNe|yaavadavadhaaraNe|yaavadavadhaaraNe 2.1.8|यावदवधारणे|यावदवधारणे २.१.८|२.१.८|२.१.८ यावदवधारणे
The indeclinable word यावत् when it signifies limitation, is invariably compounded with a word ending in a case-affix which is in construction with it, and the compound so formed is called अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास

2.1.9|2.1.9 suppratinaa maatraa.arthe|suppratinaa maatraa.arthe|suppratinaa maatraa.arthe 2.1.9|सुप्प्रतिना मात्राऽर्थे|सुप्प्रतिना मात्राऽर्थे २.१.९|२.१.९|२.१.९ सुप्प्रतिना मात्राऽर्थे
A word ending in a case-affix is compounded with the indeclinable word प्रति , when meaning 'a little' and the compound so formed is called अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास

2.1.10|2.1.10 axashalaakaasaMkhyaaH pariNaa|axashalaakaasaMkhyaaH pariNaa|axashalaakaasaMkhyaaH pariNaa 2.1.10|अक्षशलाकासंख्याः परिणा|अक्षशलाकासंख्याः परिणा २.१.१०|२.१.१०|२.१.१० अक्षशलाकासंख्याः परिणा
The words अक्ष 'a die for playing with', शलाका 'an ivory piece used in gambling' and सङ्खया 'numerals' are compounded with the word परि and the compound so formed is called अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास

2.1.11|2.1.11 vibhaaShaa|vibhaaShaa|vibhaaShaa 2.1.11|विभाषा|विभाषा २.१.११|२.१.११|२.१.११ विभाषा
The word विभाषा or option governs all succeeding sūtras.<br><br>Terms: विभाषा

2.1.12|2.1.12 apaparibahirancavaH pancamyaa|apaparibahirancavaH pancamyaa|apaparibahirancavaH pancamyaa 2.1.12|अपपरिबहिरञ्चवः पञ्चम्या|अपपरिबहिरञ्चवः पञ्चम्या २.१.१२|२.१.१२|२.१.१२ अपपरिबहिरञ्चवः पञ्चम्या
The words अप , परि , बहिल् and indeclinables ending in अञ्चु may optionally be compounded with a word ending in the 5th case affix and the compound so formed will be अव्ययीभाव ।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.13|2.1.13 aaNG maryaadaa.abhividhyoH|aaNG maryaadaa.abhividhyoH|aaNG maryaadaa.abhividhyoH 2.1.13|आङ् मर्यादाऽभिविध्योः|आङ् मर्यादाऽभिविध्योः २.१.१३|२.१.१३|२.१.१३ आङ् मर्यादाऽभिविध्योः
The word आङ् when signifying limit exclusive or limit inclusive, may optionally be compounded with a word ending in the 5th case and the compound so formed is called अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.14|2.1.14 laxaNenaabhipratii aabhimukhye|laxaNenaabhipratii aabhimukhye|laxaNenaabhipratii aabhimukhye 2.1.14|लक्षणेनाभिप्रती आभिमुख्ये|लक्षणेनाभिप्रती आभिमुख्ये २.१.१४|२.१.१४|२.१.१४ लक्षणेनाभिप्रती आभिमुख्ये
The words अभि and प्रति when implying direction (towards), are optionally compounded with a word ending in a case-affix denoting the limit, or the goal which regulates or marks the direction and the resulting compound is अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.15|2.1.15 anuryatsamayaa|anuryatsamayaa|anuryatsamayaa 2.1.15|अनुर्यत्समया|अनुर्यत्समया २.१.१५|२.१.१५|२.१.१५ अनुर्यत्समया
The word अनु 'near to' is optionally compounded with that word, nearness to which is indicated by the particle and the resulting compound is अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.16|2.1.16 yasya chaayaamaH|yasya chaayaamaH|yasya chaayaamaH 2.1.16|यस्य चायामः|यस्य चायामः २.१.१६|२.१.१६|२.१.१६ यस्य चायामः
The word अनु 'alongside of' is optionally compounded with the word indicative of that whose length the particle expresses and compound so formed is called अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.17|2.1.17 tiShThadguprabhRtiini cha|tiShThadguprabhRtiini cha|tiShThadguprabhRtiini cha 2.1.17|तिष्ठद्गुप्रभृतीनि च|तिष्ठद्गुप्रभृतीनि च २.१.१७|२.१.१७|२.१.१७ तिष्ठद्गुप्रभृतीनि च
And the words तिष्ठद्गु 'at the time when the cows stand to be milked', etc. are अव्ययीभाव compounds.<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.18|2.1.18 paare madhye ShaShThyaa vaa|paare madhye ShaShThyaa vaa|paare madhye ShaShThyaa vaa 2.1.18|पारे मध्ये षष्ठ्या वा|पारे मध्ये षष्ठ्या वा २.१.१८|२.१.१८|२.१.१८ पारे मध्ये षष्ठ्या वा
The words पार 'across' and मध्य 'middle' may optionally be compounded with a word ending in the 6th-Case-affix, when they take forms परे and मध्ये and the compound so formed is अव्ययीभाव।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.19|2.1.19 saMkhyaa vaMshyena|saMkhyaa vaMshyena|saMkhyaa vaMshyena 2.1.19|संख्या वंश्येन|संख्या वंश्येन २.१.१९|२.१.१९|२.१.१९ संख्या वंश्येन
A numeral (संख्या) may be compounded with a word denoting 'one belonging toa family' and the resulting compound is अव्ययीभाव ।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.20|2.1.20 nadiibhishcha|nadiibhishcha|nadiibhishcha 2.1.20|नदीभिश्च|नदीभिश्च २.१.२०|२.१.२०|२.१.२० नदीभिश्च
A numeral (संख्या) may be compounded with the names of 'rivers' and the resulting compound is अव्ययीभाव denoting an aggregate.<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.21|2.1.21 anyapadaarthe cha saMJNaayaam‌|anyapadaarthe cha saMJNaayaam‌|anyapadaarthe cha saMJNaayaam‌ 2.1.21|अन्यपदार्थे च संज्ञायाम्‌|अन्यपदार्थे च संज्ञायाम्‌ २.१.२१|२.१.२१|२.१.२१ अन्यपदार्थे च संज्ञायाम्‌
A word ending in a case-affix is compounded with words denoting the names of rivers, when the compound word denotes a thing other than that expressed by the terms of the compound and is an appelllative, the compound so formed being an अव्ययीभाव ।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.1.22|2.1.22 tatpuruShaH|tatpuruShaH|tatpuruShaH 2.1.22|तत्पुरुषः|तत्पुरुषः २.१.२२|२.१.२२|२.१.२२ तत्पुरुषः
From this sūtra as far as sūtra २.२.२३, the word तत्-पुरुष is governing word, and is understood in all the following sūtras.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.23|2.1.23 dvigushcha|dvigushcha|dvigushcha 2.1.23|द्विगुश्च|द्विगुश्च २.१.२३|२.१.२३|२.१.२३ द्विगुश्च
And the compound called द्विगु (Numeral Determinative Compound) is all called तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.24|2.1.24 dvitiiyaa shritaatiitapatitagataatyastapraaptaapannaiH|dvitiiyaa shritaatiitapatitagataatyastapraaptaapannaiH|dvitiiyaa shritaatiitapatitagataatyastapraaptaapannaiH 2.1.24|द्वितीया श्रितातीतपतितगतात्यस्तप्राप्तापन्नैः|द्वितीया श्रितातीतपतितगतात्यस्तप्राप्तापन्नैः २.१.२४|२.१.२४|२.१.२४ द्वितीया श्रितातीतपतितगतात्यस्तप्राप्तापन्नैः
A word ending in a 2nd case-affix is compounded with the words श्रित 'who had recourse to', अतीत 'gone by', पतित 'who has fallen upon', गत 'who has gone to', अत्यस्त 'who has passed', प्राप्त 'who has obtained' and अपान्न 'who has reached' and the resulting compound is called तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.25|2.1.25 svayaM ktena|svayaM ktena|svayaM ktena 2.1.25|स्वयं क्तेन|स्वयं क्तेन २.१.२५|२.१.२५|२.१.२५ स्वयं क्तेन
The indeclinable word स्वयम् 'oneself' is compounded with a word ending in the affix क्त and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.26|2.1.26 khaTvaa xepe|khaTvaa xepe|khaTvaa xepe 2.1.26|खट्वा क्षेपे|खट्वा क्षेपे २.१.२६|२.१.२६|२.१.२६ खट्वा क्षेपे
The word खट्वा in the Accusative -2nd case is compounded with a word ending in the affix क्त , when censure is implied and the compound so formed is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.27|2.1.27 saami|saami|saami 2.1.27|सामि|सामि २.१.२७|२.१.२७|२.१.२७ सामि
The indeclinable word सामि 'half' is compounded with a word ending in the affix क्त and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.28|2.1.28 kaalaaH|kaalaaH|kaalaaH 2.1.28|कालाः|कालाः २.१.२८|२.१.२८|२.१.२८ कालाः
The words denoting time, being in the Accusative -2nd case, are optionally compounded with a word ending in the affix क्त and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.29|2.1.29 atyantasaMyoge cha|atyantasaMyoge cha|atyantasaMyoge cha 2.1.29|अत्यन्तसंयोगे च|अत्यन्तसंयोगे च २.१.२९|२.१.२९|२.१.२९ अत्यन्तसंयोगे च
Words denoting time being in the Accusative -2nd case, are optionally compounded with a word ending in a case-affix, when used in the sense of complete connection throughout with the time (i.e. duration of time) and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.30|2.1.30 tRtiiyaa tatkRtaarthena guNavachanena|tRtiiyaa tatkRtaarthena guNavachanena|tRtiiyaa tatkRtaarthena guNavachanena 2.1.30|तृतीया तत्कृतार्थेन गुणवचनेन|तृतीया तत्कृतार्थेन गुणवचनेन २.१.३०|२.१.३०|२.१.३० तृतीया तत्कृतार्थेन गुणवचनेन
A word ending with the Instrumental -3rd case-affix is optionally compounded with what denotes quality, the quality being that which is instrumentally caused by the thing signified by what ends with the 3rd case-affix and with the word अर्थ 'wealth' and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.31|2.1.31 puurvasadRshasamonaarthakalahanipuNamishrashlaxNaiH|puurvasadRshasamonaarthakalahanipuNamishrashlaxNaiH|puurvasadRshasamonaarthakalahanipuNamishrashlaxNaiH 2.1.31|पूर्वसदृशसमोनार्थकलहनिपुणमिश्रश्लक्ष्णैः|पूर्वसदृशसमोनार्थकलहनिपुणमिश्रश्लक्ष्णैः २.१.३१|२.१.३१|२.१.३१ पूर्वसदृशसमोनार्थकलहनिपुणमिश्रश्लक्ष्णैः
A word ending in Instrumental -3rd case-affix is compounded with the words पूर्व 'prior', सदृश 'like', सम 'similar', अनर्थ 'words having the sense of less', कलह 'quarrel', निपुण 'proficient', मिश्र 'mixed' and श्लक्षण 'polished sleek', and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.32|2.1.32 kartRkaraNe kRtaa bahulam‌|kartRkaraNe kRtaa bahulam‌|kartRkaraNe kRtaa bahulam‌ 2.1.32|कर्तृकरणे कृता बहुलम्‌|कर्तृकरणे कृता बहुलम्‌ २.१.३२|२.१.३२|२.१.३२ कर्तृकरणे कृता बहुलम्‌
A word ending with the Instrumental -3rd case-affix, when it denotes the agent or instrument -- २.३.१८, is compounded diversely with what ends with a कृत् affix and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.33|2.1.33 kRtyairadhikaarthavachane|kRtyairadhikaarthavachane|kRtyairadhikaarthavachane 2.1.33|कृत्यैरधिकार्थवचने|कृत्यैरधिकार्थवचने २.१.३३|२.१.३३|२.१.३३ कृत्यैरधिकार्थवचने
A word ending with the Instrumental -3rd case-affix when it denotes the agent or the Instrument, is compounded optionally with a word ending in a कृत्य affix, when exaggerated statement (wether of praise or of censure) is implied and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.34|2.1.34 annena vyanjanam‌|annena vyanjanam‌|annena vyanjanam‌ 2.1.34|अन्नेन व्यञ्जनम्‌|अन्नेन व्यञ्जनम्‌ २.१.३४|२.१.३४|२.१.३४ अन्नेन व्यञ्जनम्‌
A word ending with the Instrumental -3rd case-affix and denoting a condiment, is optionally compounded with a word ending in a case-affix, signifying food and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.35|2.1.35 bhaxyeNa mishriikaraNam‌|bhaxyeNa mishriikaraNam‌|bhaxyeNa mishriikaraNam‌ 2.1.35|भक्ष्येण मिश्रीकरणम्‌|भक्ष्येण मिश्रीकरणम्‌ २.१.३५|२.१.३५|२.१.३५ भक्ष्येण मिश्रीकरणम्‌
A word ending with the Instrumental -3rd case-affix and denoting a relish giving or refining ingredient, is compounded with a word meaning, victuals and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.36|2.1.36 chaturthii tadarthaarthabalihitasukharaxitaiH|chaturthii tadarthaarthabalihitasukharaxitaiH|chaturthii tadarthaarthabalihitasukharaxitaiH 2.1.36|चतुर्थी तदर्थार्थबलिहितसुखरक्षितैः|चतुर्थी तदर्थार्थबलिहितसुखरक्षितैः २.१.३६|२.१.३६|२.१.३६ चतुर्थी तदर्थार्थबलिहितसुखरक्षितैः
A word ending with the Dative -4th case is compounded with what denotes that which is for the purpose of what ends with the Dative -4th case and so too with the words अर्थ 'on account of', बलि 'a sacrifice', हित 'salutary', सुख 'pleasure' and रक्षित 'kept' and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.37|2.1.37 pancamii bhayena|pancamii bhayena|pancamii bhayena 2.1.37|पञ्चमी भयेन|पञ्चमी भयेन २.१.३७|२.१.३७|२.१.३७ पञ्चमी भयेन
A word ending with the Ablative -5th case-affix is optionally compounded with the word भय 'fear' and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.38|2.1.38 apetaapoDhamuktapatitaapatrastairalpashaH|apetaapoDhamuktapatitaapatrastairalpashaH|apetaapoDhamuktapatitaapatrastairalpashaH 2.1.38|अपेतापोढमुक्तपतितापत्रस्तैरल्पशः|अपेतापोढमुक्तपतितापत्रस्तैरल्पशः २.१.३८|२.१.३८|२.१.३८ अपेतापोढमुक्तपतितापत्रस्तैरल्पशः
A word ending with the Ablative -5th case-affix is compounded with the words अपेत 'gone away', अपोध 'carried away', मुक्त 'freed', पतित 'fallen', अपत्रस्त 'afraid of', when the event takes place in a gradual manner and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.39|2.1.39 stokaantikaduuraarthakRchChraaNi ktena|stokaantikaduuraarthakRchChraaNi ktena|stokaantikaduuraarthakRchChraaNi ktena 2.1.39|स्तोकान्तिकदूरार्थकृच्छ्राणि क्तेन|स्तोकान्तिकदूरार्थकृच्छ्राणि क्तेन २.१.३९|२.१.३९|२.१.३९ स्तोकान्तिकदूरार्थकृच्छ्राणि क्तेन
Words with a sense of स्तोक 'aa little', अन्तिक 'near', दूर 'far' and कृच्छ्र 'penance', ending in the Ablative -5th case are compounded with what ends in क्त and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.40|2.1.40 saptamii shauNDaiH|saptamii shauNDaiH|saptamii shauNDaiH 2.1.40|सप्तमी शौण्डैः|सप्तमी शौण्डैः २.१.४०|२.१.४०|२.१.४० सप्तमी शौण्डैः
A word ending in the Locative -7th-case-affix is compounded with the words शौण्ड 'skilled' etc. and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.41|2.1.41 siddhashuShkapakvabandhaishcha|siddhashuShkapakvabandhaishcha|siddhashuShkapakvabandhaishcha 2.1.41|सिद्धशुष्कपक्वबन्धैश्च|सिद्धशुष्कपक्वबन्धैश्च २.१.४१|२.१.४१|२.१.४१ सिद्धशुष्कपक्वबन्धैश्च
A word ending with the Locative -7th-case-affix is compounded with the words सिद्ध 'perfected', शुष्क 'dried', पक्व 'cooked', and बन्ध 'bound' and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष । <br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.42|2.1.42 dhvaankSheNa xepe|dhvaankSheNa xepe|dhvaankSheNa xepe 2.1.42|ध्वाङ्क्षेण क्षेपे|ध्वाङ्क्षेण क्षेपे २.१.४२|२.१.४२|२.१.४२ ध्वाङ्क्षेण क्षेपे
A word ending in the Locative -7th-case-affix is compounded with the words ध्वाङ्क्ष 'a crow' and synonyms of crow when contempt is implied and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.43|2.1.43 kRtyairRNe|kRtyairRNe|kRtyairRNe 2.1.43|कृत्यैर्ऋणे|कृत्यैर्ऋणे २.१.४३|२.१.४३|२.१.४३ कृत्यैर्ऋणे
A word ending with the Locative -7th-case-affix is compounded with words ending with कृत्य-affix (a Future Passive Participle) and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.44|2.1.44 saMJNaayaam‌|saMJNaayaam‌|saMJNaayaam‌ 2.1.44|संज्ञायाम्‌|संज्ञायाम्‌ २.१.४४|२.१.४४|२.१.४४ संज्ञायाम्‌
A word ending with the Locative -7th-case-affix is invariably compounded with a word ending in a case-affix, when the compound thus formed is used as an appellative and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.45|2.1.45 ktenaahoraatraavayavaaH|ktenaahoraatraavayavaaH|ktenaahoraatraavayavaaH 2.1.45|क्तेनाहोरात्रावयवाः|क्तेनाहोरात्रावयवाः २.१.४५|२.१.४५|२.१.४५ क्तेनाहोरात्रावयवाः
The names of divisions of day or night ending with Locative -7th-case-affix are compounded with words ending with affix क्त and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.46|2.1.46 tatra|tatra|tatra 2.1.46|तत्र|तत्र २.१.४६|२.१.४६|२.१.४६ तत्र
The word तत्र 'there' which is a word ending with Locative -7th-case-affix सप्तम्यास्त्रल् ५.३.१०, is compounded with a word ending in क्त and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.47|2.1.47 xepe|xepe|xepe 2.1.47|क्षेपे|क्षेपे २.१.४७|२.१.४७|२.१.४७ क्षेपे
The word ending in Locative -7th-case-affix is compounded with a word ending with the affix क्त when 'censure' is implied and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.48|2.1.48 paatresamitaadayashcha|paatresamitaadayashcha|paatresamitaadayashcha 2.1.48|पात्रेसमितादयश्च|पात्रेसमितादयश्च २.१.४८|२.१.४८|२.१.४८ पात्रेसमितादयश्च
The words like पात्रे-सम्मित 'a dish-companion' (a parasite) etc. are तत्-पुरुष compounds when contempt is implied.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.49|2.1.49 puurvakaalaikasarvajaratpuraaNanavakevalaaH samaanaadhikaraNena|puurvakaalaikasarvajaratpuraaNanavakevalaaH samaanaadhikaraNena|puurvakaalaikasarvajaratpuraaNanavakevalaaH samaanaadhikaraNena 2.1.49|पूर्वकालैकसर्वजरत्पुराणनवकेवलाः समानाधिकरणेन|पूर्वकालैकसर्वजरत्पुराणनवकेवलाः समानाधिकरणेन २.१.४९|२.१.४९|२.१.४९ पूर्वकालैकसर्वजरत्पुराणनवकेवलाः समानाधिकरणेन
A case-inflected word denoting an action which naturally precedes in time (पूर्वकाल) and the words एक 'one', सर्व 'all' जरत 'old', पुराण 'ancient', नव 'new', and केवल 'only' are compounded with their co-relative case-inflected words which are in the same case with them and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.50|2.1.50 diksaMkhye saMJNaayaam‌|diksaMkhye saMJNaayaam‌|diksaMkhye saMJNaayaam‌ 2.1.50|दिक्संख्ये संज्ञायाम्‌|दिक्संख्ये संज्ञायाम्‌ २.१.५०|२.१.५०|२.१.५० दिक्संख्ये संज्ञायाम्‌
The words expressing a point of the compass or a number (संख्या ) enter into compostion with the word correlated to them by being in the same case, when the sense of the compound is that of an appellative and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.51|2.1.51 taddhitaarthottarapadasamaahaare cha|taddhitaarthottarapadasamaahaare cha|taddhitaarthottarapadasamaahaare cha 2.1.51|तद्धितार्थोत्तरपदसमाहारे च|तद्धितार्थोत्तरपदसमाहारे च २.१.५१|२.१.५१|२.१.५१ तद्धितार्थोत्तरपदसमाहारे च
In a case where the sense is that of a तद्धित-affix or when an additional member comes after the compound or when an aggregate is to be expressed, then a word signifying a point of the compass or a number, enters into composition with a case-inflected word which is in agreement with it by being in the same case and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.52|2.1.52 saMkhyaapuurvo dviguH|saMkhyaapuurvo dviguH|saMkhyaapuurvo dviguH 2.1.52|संख्यापूर्वो द्विगुः|संख्यापूर्वो द्विगुः २.१.५२|२.१.५२|२.१.५२ संख्यापूर्वो द्विगुः
In a case where the sense is that of a तद्धित-affix or when an additional member comes after the compound or when an aggregate is to be expressed, the compound, the first member of which is numeral, is called द्विगु (Numeral Determinative Compound).<br><br>Terms: समास-द्विगु

2.1.53|2.1.53 kutsitaani kutsanaiH|kutsitaani kutsanaiH|kutsitaani kutsanaiH 2.1.53|कुत्सितानि कुत्सनैः|कुत्सितानि कुत्सनैः २.१.५३|२.१.५३|२.१.५३ कुत्सितानि कुत्सनैः
Case-inflected words expressing vileness are compounded with case-inflected words, expressing contempt and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.54|2.1.54 paapaaNake kutsitaiH|paapaaNake kutsitaiH|paapaaNake kutsitaiH 2.1.54|पापाणके कुत्सितैः|पापाणके कुत्सितैः २.१.५४|२.१.५४|२.१.५४ पापाणके कुत्सितैः
The case-inflected words पाप 'sin' and अणक 'insignificant' are compounded with words expressive of vileness and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.55|2.1.55 upamaanaani saamaanyavachanaiH|upamaanaani saamaanyavachanaiH|upamaanaani saamaanyavachanaiH 2.1.55|उपमानानि सामान्यवचनैः|उपमानानि सामान्यवचनैः २.१.५५|२.१.५५|२.१.५५ उपमानानि सामान्यवचनैः
Case-inflected words denoting objects of comparison are compounded with words denoting what is likened to them, by reason of the latter possessing qualities in common with the former and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.56|2.1.56 upamitaM vyaaghraadibhiH saamaanyaaprayoge|upamitaM vyaaghraadibhiH saamaanyaaprayoge|upamitaM vyaaghraadibhiH saamaanyaaprayoge 2.1.56|उपमितं व्याघ्रादिभिः सामान्याप्रयोगे|उपमितं व्याघ्रादिभिः सामान्याप्रयोगे २.१.५६|२.१.५६|२.१.५६ उपमितं व्याघ्रादिभिः सामान्याप्रयोगे
A case-inflected word denoting subject of comparison is compounded with the words व्याघ्र 'tiger' etc., the latter being the standard of comparison and in construction with the former and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ; provided that any word expressing the common characteristic (सामान्य) as explained above, is not used.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.57|2.1.57 visheShaNaM visheShyeNa bahulam‌|visheShaNaM visheShyeNa bahulam‌|visheShaNaM visheShyeNa bahulam‌ 2.1.57|विशेषणं विशेष्येण बहुलम्‌|विशेषणं विशेष्येण बहुलम्‌ २.१.५७|२.१.५७|२.१.५७ विशेषणं विशेष्येण बहुलम्‌
A case-inflected word denoting the qualifier (the Adjective), is compounded diversely with a case-inflected word denoting the thing thereby qualified, (the Substantive), the latter being in agreement (same case) with the former and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.58|2.1.58 puurvaaparaprathamacharamajaghanyasamaanamadhyamadhyamaviiraashcha|puurvaaparaprathamacharamajaghanyasamaanamadhyamadhyamaviiraashcha|puurvaaparaprathamacharamajaghanyasamaanamadhyamadhyamaviiraashcha 2.1.58|पूर्वापरप्रथमचरमजघन्यसमानमध्यमध्यमवीराश्च|पूर्वापरप्रथमचरमजघन्यसमानमध्यमध्यमवीराश्च २.१.५८|२.१.५८|२.१.५८ पूर्वापरप्रथमचरमजघन्यसमानमध्यमध्यमवीराश्च
A case-inflected words पूर्व 'prior', अपर 'other', प्रथम 'first', चरम 'last', जघन्य 'hindmost', समान 'equal', मध्य 'middle', मध्यम 'middle', and वीर 'hero' are compounded with words ending with a case-affix and which are in agreement (same case) with them and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.59|2.1.59 shreNyaadayaH kRtaadibhiH|shreNyaadayaH kRtaadibhiH|shreNyaadayaH kRtaadibhiH 2.1.59|श्रेण्यादयः कृतादिभिः|श्रेण्यादयः कृतादिभिः २.१.५९|२.१.५९|२.१.५९ श्रेण्यादयः कृतादिभिः
The case-inflected words श्रेणी 'class' etc. are compounded with words कृत् 'made' etc. which are in agreement (same case), with them and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.60|2.1.60 ktena naNJvishiShTenaanaNJ|ktena naNJvishiShTenaanaNJ|ktena naNJvishiShTenaanaNJ 2.1.60|क्तेन नञ्विशिष्टेनानञ्|क्तेन नञ्विशिष्टेनानञ् २.१.६०|२.१.६०|२.१.६० क्तेन नञ्विशिष्टेनानञ्
A word ending with the affix क्त and not having the negative augment नञ् is compounded with the same word ending with the affix क्त but which is distinguished from the former, by having the augment नञ् and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.61|2.1.61 sanmahatparamottamotkRShTaaH puujyamaanaiH|sanmahatparamottamotkRShTaaH puujyamaanaiH|sanmahatparamottamotkRShTaaH puujyamaanaiH 2.1.61|सन्महत्परमोत्तमोत्कृष्टाः पूज्यमानैः|सन्महत्परमोत्तमोत्कृष्टाः पूज्यमानैः २.१.६१|२.१.६१|२.१.६१ सन्महत्परमोत्तमोत्कृष्टाः पूज्यमानैः
The words सत् 'good, महत् 'great', परम 'highest', उत्तम 'best' and उत्कृष्ट 'excellent' are compounded with the words denoting the person deserving the respect and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.62|2.1.62 vRndaarakanaagakunjaraiH puujyamaanam‌|vRndaarakanaagakunjaraiH puujyamaanam‌|vRndaarakanaagakunjaraiH puujyamaanam‌ 2.1.62|वृन्दारकनागकुञ्जरैः पूज्यमानम्‌|वृन्दारकनागकुञ्जरैः पूज्यमानम्‌ २.१.६२|२.१.६२|२.१.६२ वृन्दारकनागकुञ्जरैः पूज्यमानम्‌
A case-inflected word denoting object deserving of respect is compounded with the words वृन्दारक 'eminent', नाग 'serpent or elephant', कुञ्जर 'elephant' and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.63|2.1.63 katarakatamau jaatipariprashne|katarakatamau jaatipariprashne|katarakatamau jaatipariprashne 2.1.63|कतरकतमौ जातिपरिप्रश्ने|कतरकतमौ जातिपरिप्रश्ने २.१.६३|२.१.६३|२.१.६३ कतरकतमौ जातिपरिप्रश्ने
The words कतर 'which or who of two', and कतम 'which or who of many', when used in asking questions about the genus or class, are compounded with the other case-inflected words with which they are in construction and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.64|2.1.64 kiM xepe|kiM xepe|kiM xepe 2.1.64|किं क्षेपे|किं क्षेपे २.१.६४|२.१.६४|२.१.६४ किं क्षेपे
The word किम् 'what', when implying 'contempt' is compounded with a word ending in case-affix and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.65|2.1.65 poTaayuvatistokakatipayagRShTidhenuvashaavehatbaShkayaNiipravaktRRshrotriyaadhyaapakadhuurtairjaatiH|poTaayuvatistokakatipayagRShTidhenuvashaavehatbaShkayaNiipravaktRRshrotriyaadhyaapakadhuurtairjaatiH|poTaayuvatistokakatipayagRShTidhenuvashaavehatbaShkayaNiipravaktRRshrotriyaadhyaapakadhuurtairjaatiH 2.1.65|पोटायुवतिस्तोककतिपयगृष्टिधेनुवशावेहत्बष्कयणीप्रवक्तॄश्रोत्रियाध्यापकधूर्तैर्जातिः|पोटायुवतिस्तोककतिपयगृष्टिधेनुवशावेहत्बष्कयणीप्रवक्तॄश्रोत्रियाध्यापकधूर्तैर्जातिः २.१.६५|२.१.६५|२.१.६५ पोटायुवतिस्तोककतिपयगृष्टिधेनुवशावेहत्बष्कयणीप्रवक्तॄश्रोत्रियाध्यापकधूर्तैर्जातिः
A case-inflected word denoting a genus (जाति) is compounded with the words पोटा 'a hermaphrodite', युवति 'a young female', स्तोक 'a little', कतिपय 'a few', गृष्टि 'a cow which has had only one calf', धेनु 'milch cow', वशा 'a barren female', वेहद् 'a cow that miscarries', बष्कयणी 'a cow that has a full-grown calf', प्रवक्तृ 'an expounder', श्रोत्रिय 'a learned ब्राह्मण ', अध्यापक 'a teacher' and धूर्त 'a cunning fellow' and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.66|2.1.66 prashaMsaavachanaishcha|prashaMsaavachanaishcha|prashaMsaavachanaishcha 2.1.66|प्रशंसावचनैश्च|प्रशंसावचनैश्च २.१.६६|२.१.६६|२.१.६६ प्रशंसावचनैश्च
A case-inflected word denoting a genus (जाति) is compounded with a word denoting praise and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.67|2.1.67 yuvaa khalatipalitavalinajaratiibhiH|yuvaa khalatipalitavalinajaratiibhiH|yuvaa khalatipalitavalinajaratiibhiH 2.1.67|युवा खलतिपलितवलिनजरतीभिः|युवा खलतिपलितवलिनजरतीभिः २.१.६७|२.१.६७|२.१.६७ युवा खलतिपलितवलिनजरतीभिः
The word युवा 'young' is compounded with the words खलति 'bald headed', पलित 'grey-haired', वलिन 'wrinkled', जरति 'decayed', when they are in agreement (same case) and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.68|2.1.68 kRtyatulyaakhyaa ajaatyaa|kRtyatulyaakhyaa ajaatyaa|kRtyatulyaakhyaa ajaatyaa 2.1.68|कृत्यतुल्याख्या अजात्या|कृत्यतुल्याख्या अजात्या २.१.६८|२.१.६८|२.१.६८ कृत्यतुल्याख्या अजात्या
Words ending with कृत् -affix and the word तुल्य 'equal' and its synonyms are compounded with words which do not denote genus (जाति) being in the same case with them and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.69|2.1.69 varNo varNena|varNo varNena|varNo varNena 2.1.69|वर्णो वर्णेन|वर्णो वर्णेन २.१.६९|२.१.६९|२.१.६९ वर्णो वर्णेन
A case-inflected word denoting 'colour' is compounded with another case-inflected word which is in agreement with the former and also denotes colour and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.70|2.1.70 kumaaraH shramaNaa.a.adibhiH|kumaaraH shramaNaa.a.adibhiH|kumaaraH shramaNaa.a.adibhiH 2.1.70|कुमारः श्रमणाऽऽदिभिः|कुमारः श्रमणाऽऽदिभिः २.१.७०|२.१.७०|२.१.७० कुमारः श्रमणाऽऽदिभिः
The word कुमार 'a boy' is compounded with co-ordinate words श्रमण 'an ascetic' etc. and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.71|2.1.71 chatuShpaado garbhiNyaa|chatuShpaado garbhiNyaa|chatuShpaado garbhiNyaa 2.1.71|चतुष्पादो गर्भिण्या|चतुष्पादो गर्भिण्या २.१.७१|२.१.७१|२.१.७१ चतुष्पादो गर्भिण्या
A case-inflected word denoting a quadraped is compounded with the co-ordinate word गर्भिणी and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष ।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.1.72|2.1.72 mayuuravyaMsakaadayashcha|mayuuravyaMsakaadayashcha|mayuuravyaMsakaadayashcha 2.1.72|मयूरव्यंसकादयश्च|मयूरव्यंसकादयश्च २.१.७२|२.१.७२|२.१.७२ मयूरव्यंसकादयश्च
And the words मयूर-व्यंसका 'cunning like a peacock' etc. are तत्-पुरुष compounds.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.1|2.2.1 puurvaaparaadharottaramekadeshinaikaadhikaraNe|puurvaaparaadharottaramekadeshinaikaadhikaraNe|puurvaaparaadharottaramekadeshinaikaadhikaraNe 2.2.1|पूर्वापराधरोत्तरमेकदेशिनैकाधिकरणे|पूर्वापराधरोत्तरमेकदेशिनैकाधिकरणे २.२.१|२.२.१|२.२.१ पूर्वापराधरोत्तरमेकदेशिनैकाधिकरणे
The words पूर्व 'front', अपर 'near', अधर 'lower', उत्तर 'upper', are compounded when in construction with a word signifying a thing that has parts, provided that the thing having parts is distinguished numerically by unity; and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास

2.2.2|2.2.2 ardhaM napuMsakam‌|ardhaM napuMsakam‌|ardhaM napuMsakam‌ 2.2.2|अर्धं नपुंसकम्‌|अर्धं नपुंसकम्‌ २.२.२|२.२.२|२.२.२ अर्धं नपुंसकम्‌
The word अर्द्ध when it signifies exactly equal parts i.e. halves, is always neuter and is compounded with a word signifying a thing that has parts, provided that the thing halved is numerically one; and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.3|2.2.3 dvitiiyatRtiiyachaturthaturyaaNyanyatarasyaam‌|dvitiiyatRtiiyachaturthaturyaaNyanyatarasyaam‌|dvitiiyatRtiiyachaturthaturyaaNyanyatarasyaam‌ 2.2.3|द्वितीयतृतीयचतुर्थतुर्याण्यन्यतरस्याम्‌|द्वितीयतृतीयचतुर्थतुर्याण्यन्यतरस्याम्‌ २.२.३|२.२.३|२.२.३ द्वितीयतृतीयचतुर्थतुर्याण्यन्यतरस्याम्‌
The words द्वितीय 'second', तृतीय 'third', चतुर्थ 'fourth', तुर्य 'fourth', are optionally compounded with that word which signifies a thing that has parts, provided that the thing having parts is distinguished numerically by unity. The compound so formed is called तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.4|2.2.4 praaptaapanne cha dvitiiyayaa|praaptaapanne cha dvitiiyayaa|praaptaapanne cha dvitiiyayaa 2.2.4|प्राप्तापन्ने च द्वितीयया|प्राप्तापन्ने च द्वितीयया २.२.४|२.२.४|२.२.४ प्राप्तापन्ने च द्वितीयया
The words प्राप्त 'obtained', and आपन्न 'obtained' are optionally compounded with words ending in a Second Case-affix and form तत्-पुरुष compound.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.5|2.2.5 kaalaaH parimaaNinaa|kaalaaH parimaaNinaa|kaalaaH parimaaNinaa 2.2.5|कालाः परिमाणिना|कालाः परिमाणिना २.२.५|२.२.५|२.२.५ कालाः परिमाणिना
Words denoting time are compounded when in construction, with words denoting the object whose duration is measured by the time, and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.6|2.2.6 naNJ‌|naNJ‌|naNJ‌ 2.2.6|नञ्‌|नञ्‌ २.२.६|२.२.६|२.२.६ नञ्‌
The negative word नञ् is compounded with a case-inflected word with which it is in construction, and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.7|2.2.7 iiShadakRtaa|iiShadakRtaa|iiShadakRtaa 2.2.7|ईषदकृता|ईषदकृता २.२.७|२.२.७|२.२.७ ईषदकृता
The word ईषत् 'a little' is compounded with a case-inflected word which does not end with a कृत् affix and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.8|2.2.8 ShaShThii|ShaShThii|ShaShThii 2.2.8|षष्ठी|षष्ठी २.२.८|२.२.८|२.२.८ षष्ठी
A word ending with a sixth case-affix is compounded with a case-inflected word with which it is in construction and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.9|2.2.9 yaajakaadibhishcha|yaajakaadibhishcha|yaajakaadibhishcha 2.2.9|याजकादिभिश्च|याजकादिभिश्च २.२.९|२.२.९|२.२.९ याजकादिभिश्च
A word ending with a sixth case-affix is compounded with the word याजक 'sacrificer' etc. and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.10|2.2.10 na nirdhaaraNe|na nirdhaaraNe|na nirdhaaraNe 2.2.10|न निर्धारणे|न निर्धारणे २.२.१०|२.२.१०|२.२.१० न निर्धारणे
A word in the genitive case is not compounded with another, when the force of the sixth case-affix is that of specification (निर्धारण).<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.11|2.2.11 puuraNaguNasuhitaarthasadavyayatavyasamaanaadhikaraNena|puuraNaguNasuhitaarthasadavyayatavyasamaanaadhikaraNena|puuraNaguNasuhitaarthasadavyayatavyasamaanaadhikaraNena 2.2.11|पूरणगुणसुहितार्थसदव्ययतव्यसमानाधिकरणेन|पूरणगुणसुहितार्थसदव्ययतव्यसमानाधिकरणेन २.२.११|२.२.११|२.२.११ पूरणगुणसुहितार्थसदव्ययतव्यसमानाधिकरणेन
A word ending in a sixth case-affix is not compounded with a word having the sense of an ordinal, an attribute, or satisfaction, or with a participle ending in the suffix सत् 3.2127, or an indeclinable, or ending with the affix तव्य , or with a word denoting the same object (i.e. when they are in apposition).<br><br>Terms: समास-निर्धारण

2.2.12|2.2.12 ktena cha puujaayaam‌|ktena cha puujaayaam‌|ktena cha puujaayaam‌ 2.2.12|क्तेन च पूजायाम्‌|क्तेन च पूजायाम्‌ २.२.१२|२.२.१२|२.२.१२ क्तेन च पूजायाम्‌
A word ending with sixth case-affix is not compounded with a word ending with the affix क्त , when the force of क्त is to denote 'respect' etc.<br><br>Terms: समास-विभक्ति-6

2.2.13|2.2.13 adhikaraNavaachinaa cha|adhikaraNavaachinaa cha|adhikaraNavaachinaa cha 2.2.13|अधिकरणवाचिना च|अधिकरणवाचिना च २.२.१३|२.२.१३|२.२.१३ अधिकरणवाचिना च
A word ending with a sixth case-affix is not compounded with a word ending with the affix क्त , when the force of the latter is to denote 'locality' in which something happened<br><br>Terms: समास-विभक्ति-6

2.2.14|2.2.14 karmmaNi cha|karmmaNi cha|karmmaNi cha 2.2.14|कर्म्मणि च|कर्म्मणि च २.२.१४|२.२.१४|२.२.१४ कर्म्मणि च
A word ending with a sixth case-affix is not compounded with another, when the force of the genitive is that of the accusative.<br><br>Terms: समास-विभक्ति-6

2.2.15|2.2.15 tRjakaabhyaaM kartari|tRjakaabhyaaM kartari|tRjakaabhyaaM kartari 2.2.15|तृजकाभ्यां कर्तरि|तृजकाभ्यां कर्तरि २.२.१५|२.२.१५|२.२.१५ तृजकाभ्यां कर्तरि
A word ending with a sixth case-affix is not compounded with a word ending with त्रिच् or अक , when the force of the genitive case is that of an agent.<br><br>Terms: समास-विभक्ति-6

2.2.16|2.2.16 karttari cha|karttari cha|karttari cha 2.2.16|कर्त्तरि च|कर्त्तरि च २.२.१६|२.२.१६|२.२.१६ कर्त्तरि च
A word ending with a sixth case-affix is not compounded with a word ending with त्रिच् or अक affix when the force of these latter affixes is that of an agent.<br><br>Terms: समास-विभक्ति-6

2.2.17|2.2.17 nityaM kriiDaajiivikayoH|nityaM kriiDaajiivikayoH|nityaM kriiDaajiivikayoH 2.2.17|नित्यं क्रीडाजीविकयोः|नित्यं क्रीडाजीविकयोः २.२.१७|२.२.१७|२.२.१७ नित्यं क्रीडाजीविकयोः
A word ending with a sixth case-affix is invariably compounded with a word ending with अक , when these affixes denote a sport or livelihood; and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-विभक्ति-6

2.2.18|2.2.18 kugatipraadayaH|kugatipraadayaH|kugatipraadayaH 2.2.18|कुगतिप्रादयः|कुगतिप्रादयः २.२.१८|२.२.१८|२.२.१८ कुगतिप्रादयः
The indeclinable word कु 'bad' , the particles called गति and the prepositions प्र etc. are invariably compounded with other words with which they are in construction and the resulting compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-विभक्ति-6-तत्-पुरुष

2.2.19|2.2.19 upapadamatiNG|upapadamatiNG|upapadamatiNG 2.2.19|उपपदमतिङ्|उपपदमतिङ् २.२.१९|२.२.१९|२.२.१९ उपपदमतिङ्
An उपपद of attendant word तत्रोपपदं सप्तमीस्थम्‌ ३.१.९२ which does not end with a tense-affix ३.४.७८ is invariably compounded with that with which it is in construction. The compound thus formed is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-उपसर्ग-अव्यय

2.2.20|2.2.20 amaivaavyayena|amaivaavyayena|amaivaavyayena 2.2.20|अमैवाव्ययेन|अमैवाव्ययेन २.२.२०|२.२.२०|२.२.२० अमैवाव्ययेन
When an उपपद is compounded with an indeclinable, then it is compounded only with those अव्ययs which end in the affix अम्।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-तिङ्

2.2.21|2.2.21 tRtiiyaaprabhRtiinyanyatarasyaam‌|tRtiiyaaprabhRtiinyanyatarasyaam‌|tRtiiyaaprabhRtiinyanyatarasyaam‌ 2.2.21|तृतीयाप्रभृतीन्यन्यतरस्याम्‌|तृतीयाप्रभृतीन्यन्यतरस्याम्‌ २.२.२१|२.२.२१|२.२.२१ तृतीयाप्रभृतीन्यन्यतरस्याम्‌
An उपपद ending in third case-affix ३.४.४७ etc. is compounded optionally with an indeclinable formed by the affix अम् and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-अव्यय

2.2.22|2.2.22 ktvaa cha|ktvaa cha|ktvaa cha 2.2.22|क्त्वा च|क्त्वा च २.२.२२|२.२.२२|२.२.२२ क्त्वा च
An उपपद ending in third case-affix or any other of the remaining four cases, is optionally compounded with a word ending with the affix क्तवा and the compound is तत्-पुरुष।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-विभक्ति-3

2.2.23|2.2.23 sheSho bahuvriihiH|sheSho bahuvriihiH|sheSho bahuvriihiH 2.2.23|शेषो बहुव्रीहिः|शेषो बहुव्रीहिः २.२.२३|२.२.२३|२.२.२३ शेषो बहुव्रीहिः
The remaining compound is called बहुव्रीही।<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-विभक्ति-3-7

2.2.24|2.2.24 anekamanyapadaarthe|anekamanyapadaarthe|anekamanyapadaarthe 2.2.24|अनेकमन्यपदार्थे|अनेकमन्यपदार्थे २.२.२४|२.२.२४|२.२.२४ अनेकमन्यपदार्थे
Two or more words, ending in any case-affix, form compound, denoting another new thing, not connoted by those words individually and the compound is called बहुव्रीही।<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही

2.2.25|2.2.25 saMkhyayaa.avyayaasannaaduuraadhikasaMkhyaaH saMkhyeye|saMkhyayaa.avyayaasannaaduuraadhikasaMkhyaaH saMkhyeye|saMkhyayaa.avyayaasannaaduuraadhikasaMkhyaaH saMkhyeye 2.2.25|संख्ययाऽव्ययासन्नादूराधिकसंख्याः संख्येये|संख्ययाऽव्ययासन्नादूराधिकसंख्याः संख्येये २.२.२५|२.२.२५|२.२.२५ संख्ययाऽव्ययासन्नादूराधिकसंख्याः संख्येये
indeclinable words and the words आसन्न 'near', अदूर 'near', अधिक 'more' and the words called संख्या (Numerals) are compounded with another संख्या word, when the sense is that of a numeral or संख्या। The compound is बहुव्रीही।<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही-definition

2.2.26|2.2.26 diNGnaamaanyantaraale|diNGnaamaanyantaraale|diNGnaamaanyantaraale 2.2.26|दिङ्नामान्यन्तराले|दिङ्नामान्यन्तराले २.२.२६|२.२.२६|२.२.२६ दिङ्नामान्यन्तराले
Words which are the names of the points of the compass are compounded, when the compound signifies the intermediate point and the compound so formed is बहुव्रीही।<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही-संख्या

2.2.27|2.2.27 tatra tenedamiti saruupe|tatra tenedamiti saruupe|tatra tenedamiti saruupe 2.2.27|तत्र तेनेदमिति सरूपे|तत्र तेनेदमिति सरूपे २.२.२७|२.२.२७|२.२.२७ तत्र तेनेदमिति सरूपे
Two homonymous words (both being in the locative case or both being in the instrumental case) are compounded, the sense being 'this happens therein or with that'. The compound so formed is बहुव्रीही।<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही

2.2.28|2.2.28 tena saheti tulyayoge|tena saheti tulyayoge|tena saheti tulyayoge 2.2.28|तेन सहेति तुल्ययोगे|तेन सहेति तुल्ययोगे २.२.२८|२.२.२८|२.२.२८ तेन सहेति तुल्ययोगे
The word सह 'together' is compounded with a word ending with the third case-affix and the compound is बहुव्रीही ; provided that, the companion and the person accompanied are equally effected by any action or thing, in the same manner.<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही-विभक्ति

2.2.29|2.2.29 chaarthe dvaMdvaH|chaarthe dvaMdvaH|chaarthe dvaMdvaH 2.2.29|चार्थे द्वंद्वः|चार्थे द्वंद्वः २.२.२९|२.२.२९|२.२.२९ चार्थे द्वंद्वः
When a set of several words ending with case-affixes stands in a relation expressable by 'and' the set is made into a compound and the compound so formed is called द्वन्द्व।<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही-विभक्ति-wo

2.2.30|2.2.30 upasarjanaM puurvam‌|upasarjanaM puurvam‌|upasarjanaM puurvam‌ 2.2.30|उपसर्जनं पूर्वम्‌|उपसर्जनं पूर्वम्‌ २.२.३०|२.२.३०|२.२.३० उपसर्जनं पूर्वम्‌
The उपसर्जन १.२.४३ is to be placed first in a compound.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द्व-definition

2.2.31|2.2.31 raajadantaadiShu param‌|raajadantaadiShu param‌|raajadantaadiShu param‌ 2.2.31|राजदन्तादिषु परम्‌|राजदन्तादिषु परम्‌ २.२.३१|२.२.३१|२.२.३१ राजदन्तादिषु परम्‌
The उपसर्जन is to be put last in the words राजदन्त etc.<br><br>Terms: समास-rule-उपसर्जन

2.2.32|2.2.32 dvaMdve ghi|dvaMdve ghi|dvaMdve ghi 2.2.32|द्वंद्वे घि|द्वंद्वे घि २.२.३२|२.२.३२|२.२.३२ द्वंद्वे घि
In a द्वन्द्व compound, let a word called घि १.४.७, stand first.<br><br>Terms: समास-rule-उपसर्जन

2.2.33|2.2.33 ajaadyadantam‌|ajaadyadantam‌|ajaadyadantam‌ 2.2.33|अजाद्यदन्तम्‌|अजाद्यदन्तम्‌ २.२.३३|२.२.३३|२.२.३३ अजाद्यदन्तम्‌
In a द्वन्द्व compound, let a what begins with a vowel and ends with a short अ be placed first.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द्व-घि

2.2.34|2.2.34 alpaachtaram‌|alpaachtaram‌|alpaachtaram‌ 2.2.34|अल्पाच्तरम्‌|अल्पाच्तरम्‌ २.२.३४|२.२.३४|२.२.३४ अल्पाच्तरम्‌
In a द्वन्द्व compound, that word-form which has fewer vowels, is to be placed first.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द्व-अच्

2.2.35|2.2.35 saptamiivisheShaNe bahuvriihau|saptamiivisheShaNe bahuvriihau|saptamiivisheShaNe bahuvriihau 2.2.35|सप्तमीविशेषणे बहुव्रीहौ|सप्तमीविशेषणे बहुव्रीहौ २.२.३५|२.२.३५|२.२.३५ सप्तमीविशेषणे बहुव्रीहौ
A word with the seventh case-affix and an epithet are to be placed first in the बहुव्रीही compound.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द्व-अच्

2.2.36|2.2.36 niShThaa|niShThaa|niShThaa 2.2.36|निष्ठा|निष्ठा २.२.३६|२.२.३६|२.२.३६ निष्ठा
What ends with a निष्ठा १.१.२६ shall stand first in a बहुव्रीही compound.<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही

2.2.37|2.2.37 vaa.a.ahitaagnyaadiShu|vaa.a.ahitaagnyaadiShu|vaa.a.ahitaagnyaadiShu 2.2.37|वाऽऽहिताग्न्यादिषु|वाऽऽहिताग्न्यादिषु २.२.३७|२.२.३७|२.२.३७ वाऽऽहिताग्न्यादिषु
In the compounds अहिताग्नि and the like, the निष्ठा-formed word may optionally be placed first.<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही-निष्ठा

2.2.38|2.2.38 kaDaaraaH karmadharaaye|kaDaaraaH karmadharaaye|kaDaaraaH karmadharaaye 2.2.38|कडाराः कर्मधराये|कडाराः कर्मधराये २.२.३८|२.२.३८|२.२.३८ कडाराः कर्मधराये
The words कडाराः and the like, are optionally placed first in the कर्मधार्य।<br><br>Terms: समास-बहुव्रीही-निष्ठा

2.3.1|2.3.1 anabhihite|anabhihite|anabhihite 2.3.1|अनभिहिते|अनभिहिते २.३.१|२.३.१|२.३.१ अनभिहिते
The word अनभिहिते meaning 'not being specified' is to be understood as the governing word.<br><br>Terms: अनभिहिते-संज्ञा

2.3.2|2.3.2 karmaNi dvitiiyaa|karmaNi dvitiiyaa|karmaNi dvitiiyaa 2.3.2|कर्मणि द्वितीया|कर्मणि द्वितीया २.३.२|२.३.२|२.३.२ कर्मणि द्वितीया
When the object is not denoted by the termination of the verb i.e. when the verb does not agree with it, the 2nd case-affix is attached to the word.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2

2.3.3|2.3.3 tRtiiyaa cha hoshChandasi|tRtiiyaa cha hoshChandasi|tRtiiyaa cha hoshChandasi 2.3.3|तृतीया च होश्छन्दसि|तृतीया च होश्छन्दसि २.३.३|२.३.३|२.३.३ तृतीया च होश्छन्दसि
In the छन्दस् (Veda), the object of the verb हु 'to sacrifice' takes the affix of the 3rd case and of the 2nd case as well.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

2.3.4|2.3.4 antaraa.antareNa yukte|antaraa.antareNa yukte|antaraa.antareNa yukte 2.3.4|अन्तराऽन्तरेण युक्ते|अन्तराऽन्तरेण युक्ते २.३.४|२.३.४|२.३.४ अन्तराऽन्तरेण युक्ते
A word joined with (or governed by) the word अन्तरा or अन्तरेण takes the second case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-कर्मणि

2.3.5|2.3.5 kaalaadhvanoratyantasaMyoge|kaalaadhvanoratyantasaMyoge|kaalaadhvanoratyantasaMyoge 2.3.5|कालाध्वनोरत्यन्तसंयोगे|कालाध्वनोरत्यन्तसंयोगे २.३.५|२.३.५|२.३.५ कालाध्वनोरत्यन्तसंयोगे
After a word denoting time, or length, the affix of the 2nd case is used, when denoting a full duration.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2

2.3.6|2.3.6 apavarge tRtiiyaa|apavarge tRtiiyaa|apavarge tRtiiyaa 2.3.6|अपवर्गे तृतीया|अपवर्गे तृतीया २.३.६|२.३.६|२.३.६ अपवर्गे तृतीया
The 3rd case-affix is used after the words denoting the duration of time or place, when the accomplishment of the desired object is meant to be expressed.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

2.3.7|2.3.7 saptamiipancamyau kaarakamadhye|saptamiipancamyau kaarakamadhye|saptamiipancamyau kaarakamadhye 2.3.7|सप्तमीपञ्चम्यौ कारकमध्ये|सप्तमीपञ्चम्यौ कारकमध्ये २.३.७|२.३.७|२.३.७ सप्तमीपञ्चम्यौ कारकमध्ये
A noun denoting time or place gets the affix of the 7th or the 5th case when the sense applied is that the time or space is the interval between one action and another (or implies an interval of time and space between कारक-s.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5, 7

2.3.8|2.3.8 karmapravachaniiyayukte dvitiiyaa|karmapravachaniiyayukte dvitiiyaa|karmapravachaniiyayukte dvitiiyaa 2.3.8|कर्मप्रवचनीययुक्ते द्वितीया|कर्मप्रवचनीययुक्ते द्वितीया २.३.८|२.३.८|२.३.८ कर्मप्रवचनीययुक्ते द्वितीया
The 2nd case-affix is employed after a word which is joined with a कर्मप्रवचनीयाः १.४.८३.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2

2.3.9|2.3.9 yasmaadadhikaM yasya cheshvaravachanaM tatra saptamii|yasmaadadhikaM yasya cheshvaravachanaM tatra saptamii|yasmaadadhikaM yasya cheshvaravachanaM tatra saptamii 2.3.9|यस्मादधिकं यस्य चेश्वरवचनं तत्र सप्तमी|यस्मादधिकं यस्य चेश्वरवचनं तत्र सप्तमी २.३.९|२.३.९|२.३.९ यस्मादधिकं यस्य चेश्वरवचनं तत्र सप्तमी
Where a word is governed by a कर्मप्रवचनीयाः १.४.८३ in the sense of 'more than' उपोऽधिके च १.४.८७ or 'lord of' अधिरीश्वरे १.४.९७ there the 7th case-affix (locative) is used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

2.3.10|2.3.10 pancamii apaaNGparibhiH|pancamii apaaNGparibhiH|pancamii apaaNGparibhiH 2.3.10|पञ्चमी अपाङ्परिभिः|पञ्चमी अपाङ्परिभिः २.३.१०|२.३.१०|२.३.१० पञ्चमी अपाङ्परिभिः
The 5th case-affix (Ablative) is used when a word is governed by the following कर्मप्रवचनीयाः १.४.८३ i.e. अप , आङ् and परि।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.11|2.3.11 pratinidhipratidaane cha yasmaat‌|pratinidhipratidaane cha yasmaat‌|pratinidhipratidaane cha yasmaat‌ 2.3.11|प्रतिनिधिप्रतिदाने च यस्मात्‌|प्रतिनिधिप्रतिदाने च यस्मात्‌ २.३.११|२.३.११|२.३.११ प्रतिनिधिप्रतिदाने च यस्मात्‌
The 5th case-affix (Ablative) is used after whatsoever is governed by a कर्मप्रवचनीयाः १.४.८३ in the sense of 'susbtitute' or 'exchange' -- प्रतिः प्रतिनिधिप्रतिदानयोः १.४.९२.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.12|2.3.12 gatyarthakarmaNi dvitiiyaachaturthyau cheShTaayaamanadhvani|gatyarthakarmaNi dvitiiyaachaturthyau cheShTaayaamanadhvani|gatyarthakarmaNi dvitiiyaachaturthyau cheShTaayaamanadhvani 2.3.12|गत्यर्थकर्मणि द्वितीयाचतुर्थ्यौ चेष्टायामनध्वनि|गत्यर्थकर्मणि द्वितीयाचतुर्थ्यौ चेष्टायामनध्वनि २.३.१२|२.३.१२|२.३.१२ गत्यर्थकर्मणि द्वितीयाचतुर्थ्यौ चेष्टायामनध्वनि
In the case of roots implying motion, the place which the motion is directed takes the affix of the 2nd (Accusative) or the 4th (Dative) case in denoting the 'object', when physical motion is meant and the object is not a word expressing 'road'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2, 4

2.3.13|2.3.13 chaturthii sampradaane|chaturthii sampradaane|chaturthii sampradaane 2.3.13|चतुर्थी सम्प्रदाने|चतुर्थी सम्प्रदाने २.३.१३|२.३.१३|२.३.१३ चतुर्थी सम्प्रदाने
In denoting the सम्प्रदान-कारक -- कर्मणा यमभिप्रैति स सम्प्रदानम् १.४.३२, the 4th case-affix of the Dative is used after the noun.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-4

2.3.14|2.3.14 kriyaarthopapadasya cha karmaNi sthaaninaH|kriyaarthopapadasya cha karmaNi sthaaninaH|kriyaarthopapadasya cha karmaNi sthaaninaH 2.3.14|क्रियार्थोपपदस्य च कर्मणि स्थानिनः|क्रियार्थोपपदस्य च कर्मणि स्थानिनः २.३.१४|२.३.१४|२.३.१४ क्रियार्थोपपदस्य च कर्मणि स्थानिनः
The 4th case-affix is employed in denoting the object (कर्म) of that verb, which is suppressed (स्थानी) in a sentence and which has in construction (उपपद) there-with another verb, denoting an action, performed for the sake of the future action -- तुमुन्ण्वुलौ क्रियायां क्रियार्थायाम्‌३.३.१०. In other words, when the sense of an infinitive of purpose formed by तुमुन् and ण्वुल् -- ३.३.१०, is suppressed in a sentence, the object of this infinitive is put in the Dative -- 4th case.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-4

2.3.15|2.3.15 tumarthaachcha bhaavavachanaat‌|tumarthaachcha bhaavavachanaat‌|tumarthaachcha bhaavavachanaat‌ 2.3.15|तुमर्थाच्च भाववचनात्‌|तुमर्थाच्च भाववचनात्‌ २.३.१५|२.३.१५|२.३.१५ तुमर्थाच्च भाववचनात्‌
The 4th case-affix is used after a crude-form which ends in an affix denoting 'condition' (abstract noun -- भाववचनाश्च ३.३.११) and having the force of the affix तुम् (or Infinitive or purpose).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-4

2.3.16|2.3.16 namaHsvastisvaahaasvadhaalaMvaShaDyogaachcha|namaHsvastisvaahaasvadhaalaMvaShaDyogaachcha|namaHsvastisvaahaasvadhaalaMvaShaDyogaachcha 2.3.16|नमःस्वस्तिस्वाहास्वधालंवषड्योगाच्च|नमःस्वस्तिस्वाहास्वधालंवषड्योगाच्च २.३.१६|२.३.१६|२.३.१६ नमःस्वस्तिस्वाहास्वधालंवषड्योगाच्च
The 4th case-affix is used in conjuction with the words नमः 'salutation', स्वस्ति 'peace', स्वाहा , स्वधा (terms used in offering oblations to Gods and पित्रि-s, respectively), अलम् , 'a match for', 'sufficient for' and वषट् , a term for oblation.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-4

2.3.17|2.3.17 manyakarmaNyanaadare vibhaaShaa.apraaNiShu|manyakarmaNyanaadare vibhaaShaa.apraaNiShu|manyakarmaNyanaadare vibhaaShaa.apraaNiShu 2.3.17|मन्यकर्मण्यनादरे विभाषाऽप्राणिषु|मन्यकर्मण्यनादरे विभाषाऽप्राणिषु २.३.१७|२.३.१७|२.३.१७ मन्यकर्मण्यनादरे विभाषाऽप्राणिषु
In denoting the indirect object, which is not an animal, of the verb मन्य 'to think', the Dative -- 4th case is optionally used, when contempt is to be shown.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-4

2.3.18|2.3.18 kartRkaraNayostRtiiyaa|kartRkaraNayostRtiiyaa|kartRkaraNayostRtiiyaa 2.3.18|कर्तृकरणयोस्तृतीया|कर्तृकरणयोस्तृतीया २.३.१८|२.३.१८|२.३.१८ कर्तृकरणयोस्तृतीया
In denoting the agent -- स्वतन्त्रः कर्ता १.४.५४, or the instrument -- साधकतमं करणम् १.४.४२, the 3rd case is used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

2.3.19|2.3.19 sahayukte.apradhaane|sahayukte.apradhaane|sahayukte.apradhaane 2.3.19|सहयुक्तेऽप्रधाने|सहयुक्तेऽप्रधाने २.३.१९|२.३.१९|२.३.१९ सहयुक्तेऽप्रधाने
When the word सह 'with', is joined to a word the latter takes the 3rd case, when the sense is that the word in the 3rd case is not the principal but the accompaniment of the principal thing.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

2.3.20|2.3.20 yenaangavikaaraH|yenaangavikaaraH|yenaangavikaaraH 2.3.20|येनाङ्गविकारः|येनाङ्गविकारः २.३.२०|२.३.२०|२.३.२० येनाङ्गविकारः
By whatsoever limb, being defective, is pointed out the defect of the person after that the 3rd case-affix is used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

2.3.21|2.3.21 itthaMbhuutalaxaNe|itthaMbhuutalaxaNe|itthaMbhuutalaxaNe 2.3.21|इत्थंभूतलक्षणे|इत्थंभूतलक्षणे २.३.२१|२.३.२१|२.३.२१ इत्थंभूतलक्षणे
Any mark or attribute, by which is indicated the existence of a particular state or condition, is put in the 3rd case to express this relation.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

2.3.22|2.3.22 saMJNo.anyatarasyaaM karmaNi|saMJNo.anyatarasyaaM karmaNi|saMJNo.anyatarasyaaM karmaNi 2.3.22|संज्ञोऽन्यतरस्यां कर्मणि|संज्ञोऽन्यतरस्यां कर्मणि २.३.२२|२.३.२२|२.३.२२ संज्ञोऽन्यतरस्यां कर्मणि
After the verb सम्-ज्ञः , the 3rd case-affix is optionally used in denoting the object.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

2.3.23|2.3.23 hetau|hetau|hetau 2.3.23|हेतौ|हेतौ २.३.२३|२.३.२३|२.३.२३ हेतौ
When the word denotes 'cause' it takes the 3rd case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

2.3.24|2.3.24 akartaryRNe pancamii|akartaryRNe pancamii|akartaryRNe pancamii 2.3.24|अकर्तर्यृणे पञ्चमी|अकर्तर्यृणे पञ्चमी २.३.२४|२.३.२४|२.३.२४ अकर्तर्यृणे पञ्चमी
A word implying 'debt', considered as a 'cause' but not as कर्तृ or agent, takes the 5th case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.25|2.3.25 vibhaaShaa guNe.astriyaam‌|vibhaaShaa guNe.astriyaam‌|vibhaaShaa guNe.astriyaam‌ 2.3.25|विभाषा गुणेऽस्त्रियाम्‌|विभाषा गुणेऽस्त्रियाम्‌ २.३.२५|२.३.२५|२.३.२५ विभाषा गुणेऽस्त्रियाम्‌
The 5th case-affix is used optionally when the noun expresses an attribute, being the cause of an action and not being of the feminine gender.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.26|2.3.26 ShaShThii hetuprayoge|ShaShThii hetuprayoge|ShaShThii hetuprayoge 2.3.26|षष्ठी हेतुप्रयोगे|षष्ठी हेतुप्रयोगे २.३.२६|२.३.२६|२.३.२६ षष्ठी हेतुप्रयोगे
The 6th-Case-affix is used after a noun implying the cause of an action, when the word हेतु is used along with such a word.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.27|2.3.27 sarvanaamnastRtiiyaa cha|sarvanaamnastRtiiyaa cha|sarvanaamnastRtiiyaa cha 2.3.27|सर्वनाम्नस्तृतीया च|सर्वनाम्नस्तृतीया च २.३.२७|२.३.२७|२.३.२७ सर्वनाम्नस्तृतीया च
After a सर्वनामस्थान -- सर्वादीनि सर्वनामानि १.१.२७, when it signifies the cause of an action and the word हेतु is used with it, the 3rd case-affix is used, as well as the 6th.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3, 6

2.3.28|2.3.28 apaadaane pancamii|apaadaane pancamii|apaadaane pancamii 2.3.28|अपादाने पञ्चमी|अपादाने पञ्चमी २.३.२८|२.३.२८|२.३.२८ अपादाने पञ्चमी
When the अपादान कारक -- ध्रुवमपायेऽपादानम् १.४.२४, is denoted, the 5th case-affix is used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.29|2.3.29 anyaaraaditararttedik‌shabdaancuuttarapadaajaahiyukte|anyaaraaditararttedik‌shabdaancuuttarapadaajaahiyukte|anyaaraaditararttedik‌shabdaancuuttarapadaajaahiyukte 2.3.29|अन्यारादितरर्त्तेदिक्‌शब्दाञ्चूत्तरपदाजाहियुक्ते|अन्यारादितरर्त्तेदिक्‌शब्दाञ्चूत्तरपदाजाहियुक्ते २.३.२९|२.३.२९|२.३.२९ अन्यारादितरर्त्तेदिक्‌शब्दाञ्चूत्तरपदाजाहियुक्ते
When a noun is joined with words meaning 'other than' or with आरात् 'near or remote', or इतर 'different from' or ऋते 'without', or words indicative of 'directions' (used also with reference to the time corresponding to them) or with words having अञ्चु 'to bend' as the last member of the compound and expressive of direction, or with words ending with the affix आच् -- दक्षिणादाच् ५.३.३६ or आहि -- आहि च दूरे ५.३.३७, the 5th case-affix is used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.30|2.3.30 ShaShThyatasarthapratyayena|ShaShThyatasarthapratyayena|ShaShThyatasarthapratyayena 2.3.30|षष्ठ्यतसर्थप्रत्ययेन|षष्ठ्यतसर्थप्रत्ययेन २.३.३०|२.३.३०|२.३.३० षष्ठ्यतसर्थप्रत्ययेन
The 6th-Case-affix is used when used in connection with words ending with affixes having the sense of the affix अतसुच -- दक्षिणोत्तराभ्यामतसुच् ५.३.२८.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.31|2.3.31 enapaa dvitiiyaa|enapaa dvitiiyaa|enapaa dvitiiyaa 2.3.31|एनपा द्वितीया|एनपा द्वितीया २.३.३१|२.३.३१|२.३.३१ एनपा द्वितीया
With a word ending with the affix एनाप् -- एनबन्यतरस्यामदूरेऽपञ्चम्याः ५.३.३५, the 2nd case-affix is used, as well as the 6th.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2, 6

2.3.32|2.3.32 pRthagvinaanaanaabhistRtiiyaa.anyatarasyaam‌|pRthagvinaanaanaabhistRtiiyaa.anyatarasyaam‌|pRthagvinaanaanaabhistRtiiyaa.anyatarasyaam‌ 2.3.32|पृथग्विनानानाभिस्तृतीयाऽन्यतरस्याम्‌|पृथग्विनानानाभिस्तृतीयाऽन्यतरस्याम्‌ २.३.३२|२.३.३२|२.३.३२ पृथग्विनानानाभिस्तृतीयाऽन्यतरस्याम्‌
When joined with the words पृथक् 'without', विना 'without' and नाना 'without', the 3rd case-affix is used, optionally (as well as the 5th and the 2nd).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2, 3, 5

2.3.33|2.3.33 karaNe cha stokaalpakRchChrakatipayasyaasattvavachanasya|karaNe cha stokaalpakRchChrakatipayasyaasattvavachanasya|karaNe cha stokaalpakRchChrakatipayasyaasattvavachanasya 2.3.33|करणे च स्तोकाल्पकृच्छ्रकतिपयस्यासत्त्ववचनस्य|करणे च स्तोकाल्पकृच्छ्रकतिपयस्यासत्त्ववचनस्य २.३.३३|२.३.३३|२.३.३३ करणे च स्तोकाल्पकृच्छ्रकतिपयस्यासत्त्ववचनस्य
When expressing an instrument-कारक, optionally after the words स्तोक 'little', अल्प 'little', कृच्छ्र 'difficulty' and कतिपय 'some', the 5th case-affix is used, when they do not denote material objects.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.34|2.3.34 duuraantikaarthaiH ShaShThyanyatarasyaam‌|duuraantikaarthaiH ShaShThyanyatarasyaam‌|duuraantikaarthaiH ShaShThyanyatarasyaam‌ 2.3.34|दूरान्तिकार्थैः षष्ठ्यन्यतरस्याम्‌|दूरान्तिकार्थैः षष्ठ्यन्यतरस्याम्‌ २.३.३४|२.३.३४|२.३.३४ दूरान्तिकार्थैः षष्ठ्यन्यतरस्याम्‌
When in conjunction with words having the sense of दूर 'distant' and अन्तिक 'near', the 6th-Case-affix is optionally used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.35|2.3.35 duuraantikaarthebhyo dvitiiyaa cha|duuraantikaarthebhyo dvitiiyaa cha|duuraantikaarthebhyo dvitiiyaa cha 2.3.35|दूरान्तिकार्थेभ्यो द्वितीया च|दूरान्तिकार्थेभ्यो द्वितीया च २.३.३५|२.३.३५|२.३.३५ दूरान्तिकार्थेभ्यो द्वितीया च
After the words दूर 'distant' and अन्तिक 'near', the 2nd case-affix is used as well as the 5th and the 3rd.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2, 3, 5

2.3.36|2.3.36 saptamyadhikaraNe cha|saptamyadhikaraNe cha|saptamyadhikaraNe cha 2.3.36|सप्तम्यधिकरणे च|सप्तम्यधिकरणे च २.३.३६|२.३.३६|२.३.३६ सप्तम्यधिकरणे च
The 7th case-affix is used when the sense is that of location -- आधारोऽधिकरणम् १.४.४५, as well as after the words meaning 'distant' and 'near'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

2.3.37|2.3.37 yasya cha bhaavena bhaavalaxaNam‌|yasya cha bhaavena bhaavalaxaNam‌|yasya cha bhaavena bhaavalaxaNam‌ 2.3.37|यस्य च भावेन भावलक्षणम्‌|यस्य च भावेन भावलक्षणम्‌ २.३.३७|२.३.३७|२.३.३७ यस्य च भावेन भावलक्षणम्‌
By the action (भाव) of whatsoever, the time of another action is indicated, that takes the 7th case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

2.3.38|2.3.38 ShaShThii chaanaadare|ShaShThii chaanaadare|ShaShThii chaanaadare 2.3.38|षष्ठी चानादरे|षष्ठी चानादरे २.३.३८|२.३.३८|२.३.३८ षष्ठी चानादरे
The 6th-Case-affix is used (as well as the 7th), when disregard is to be shown after that by whose action the time of another action is indicated.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6, 7

2.3.39|2.3.39 svaamiishvaraadhipatidaayaadasaaxipratibhuuprasuutaishcha|svaamiishvaraadhipatidaayaadasaaxipratibhuuprasuutaishcha|svaamiishvaraadhipatidaayaadasaaxipratibhuuprasuutaishcha 2.3.39|स्वामीश्वराधिपतिदायादसाक्षिप्रतिभूप्रसूतैश्च|स्वामीश्वराधिपतिदायादसाक्षिप्रतिभूप्रसूतैश्च २.३.३९|२.३.३९|२.३.३९ स्वामीश्वराधिपतिदायादसाक्षिप्रतिभूप्रसूतैश्च
The 6th and the 7th case-affixes are used after words when they are joined with स्वामिन् 'master', ईश्वर 'lord', अधिपति 'ruler', दायाद 'an heir', साक्षिन् 'witness', प्रतिभू 'a surety' and प्रसूत 'begotten'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6, 7

2.3.40|2.3.40 aayuktakushalaabhyaaM chaasevaayaam‌|aayuktakushalaabhyaaM chaasevaayaam‌|aayuktakushalaabhyaaM chaasevaayaam‌ 2.3.40|आयुक्तकुशलाभ्यां चासेवायाम्‌|आयुक्तकुशलाभ्यां चासेवायाम्‌ २.३.४०|२.३.४०|२.३.४० आयुक्तकुशलाभ्यां चासेवायाम्‌
In conjunction with the words आयुक्त 'engaged', and कुशल 'skilful', when meaning entire absorption in an engagement, the 6th and the 7th case-affixes are used after a word.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6, 7

2.3.41|2.3.41 yatashcha nirdhaaraNam‌|yatashcha nirdhaaraNam‌|yatashcha nirdhaaraNam‌ 2.3.41|यतश्च निर्धारणम्‌|यतश्च निर्धारणम्‌ २.३.४१|२.३.४१|२.३.४१ यतश्च निर्धारणम्‌
The 6th and the 7th case-affixes are used after those words from which specification is made, (as of an individual from the whole class).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6, 7

2.3.42|2.3.42 pancamii vibhakte|pancamii vibhakte|pancamii vibhakte 2.3.42|पञ्चमी विभक्ते|पञ्चमी विभक्ते २.३.४२|२.३.४२|२.३.४२ पञ्चमी विभक्ते
The 5th case-affix is used when the thing specified is different or divided from (and not included in) that from which specification is intended.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-5

2.3.43|2.3.43 saadhunipuNaabhyaam archaayaaM saptamyaprateH|saadhunipuNaabhyaam archaayaaM saptamyaprateH|saadhunipuNaabhyaam archaayaaM saptamyaprateH 2.3.43|साधुनिपुणाभ्याम् अर्चायां सप्तम्यप्रतेः|साधुनिपुणाभ्याम् अर्चायां सप्तम्यप्रतेः २.३.४३|२.३.४३|२.३.४३ साधुनिपुणाभ्याम् अर्चायां सप्तम्यप्रतेः
In conjunction with the words साधु 'good' and निपुण 'skilfull' when they denote respect, the 7th case-affix is used, provided that the word प्रति is not used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

2.3.44|2.3.44 prasitotsukaabhyaaM tRtiiyaa cha|prasitotsukaabhyaaM tRtiiyaa cha|prasitotsukaabhyaaM tRtiiyaa cha 2.3.44|प्रसितोत्सुकाभ्यां तृतीया च|प्रसितोत्सुकाभ्यां तृतीया च २.३.४४|२.३.४४|२.३.४४ प्रसितोत्सुकाभ्यां तृतीया च
In conjunction with the words प्रसिक्त and उत्सुक 'greatly desirous of', the 3rd case-affix is used after the word, as well as the 7th.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3, 7

2.3.45|2.3.45 naxatre cha lupi|naxatre cha lupi|naxatre cha lupi 2.3.45|नक्षत्रे च लुपि|नक्षत्रे च लुपि २.३.४५|२.३.४५|२.३.४५ नक्षत्रे च लुपि
When an affix declaring the time of an Asterism is elided by लुप् -- लुबविशेषे ४.२.४, the 7th and the 3rd case-affixes are used after the word, whose affix is also elided.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3, 7

2.3.46|2.3.46 praatipadikaarthalingaparimaaNavachanamaatre prathamaa|praatipadikaarthalingaparimaaNavachanamaatre prathamaa|praatipadikaarthalingaparimaaNavachanamaatre prathamaa 2.3.46|प्रातिपदिकार्थलिङ्गपरिमाणवचनमात्रे प्रथमा|प्रातिपदिकार्थलिङ्गपरिमाणवचनमात्रे प्रथमा २.३.४६|२.३.४६|२.३.४६ प्रातिपदिकार्थलिङ्गपरिमाणवचनमात्रे प्रथमा
Where the sense is that of the Nominal-stem -- अर्थवदधातुरप्रत्ययः प्रातिपदिकम् १.२.४५, or of gender only, or measure only or number only, the 1st case-affix is used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-1

2.3.47|2.3.47 sambodhane cha|sambodhane cha|sambodhane cha 2.3.47|सम्बोधने च|सम्बोधने च २.३.४७|२.३.४७|२.३.४७ सम्बोधने च
And when the sense is that of addressing, the 1st case-affix is used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-1

2.3.48|2.3.48 saa.a.amantritam‌|saa.a.amantritam‌|saa.a.amantritam‌ 2.3.48|साऽऽमन्त्रितम्‌|साऽऽमन्त्रितम्‌ २.३.४८|२.३.४८|२.३.४८ साऽऽमन्त्रितम्‌
The word ending with the 1st case-affix, in the sense of addressing, is called आमन्त्रित or Vocative.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-8

2.3.49|2.3.49 ekavachanaM saMbuddhiH|ekavachanaM saMbuddhiH|ekavachanaM saMbuddhiH 2.3.49|एकवचनं संबुद्धिः|एकवचनं संबुद्धिः २.३.४९|२.३.४९|२.३.४९ एकवचनं संबुद्धिः
In the case of Vocative, the singular number of the 1st case-affix is called स्मबुद्धि।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-8

2.3.50|2.3.50 ShaShThii sheShe|ShaShThii sheShe|ShaShThii sheShe 2.3.50|षष्ठी शेषे|षष्ठी शेषे २.३.५०|२.३.५०|२.३.५० षष्ठी शेषे
The 6th-Case-affix is used in the remaining cases, that is to say, where there is a sense, such as the relation between property and its owner etc. different from that of a word related to a verb and from that of a Nominal-stem.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.51|2.3.51 JNo.avidarthasya karaNe|JNo.avidarthasya karaNe|JNo.avidarthasya karaNe 2.3.51|ज्ञोऽविदर्थस्य करणे|ज्ञोऽविदर्थस्य करणे २.३.५१|२.३.५१|२.३.५१ ज्ञोऽविदर्थस्य करणे
Of the verb ज्ञा , when not used in the sense 'to know', the instrument takes the 6th-Case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.52|2.3.52 adhiigarthadayeshaaM karmaNi|adhiigarthadayeshaaM karmaNi|adhiigarthadayeshaaM karmaNi 2.3.52|अधीगर्थदयेशां कर्मणि|अधीगर्थदयेशां कर्मणि २.३.५२|२.३.५२|२.३.५२ अधीगर्थदयेशां कर्मणि
Of the verbs having the sense of 'remembering', (अधिक्), and of दय 'to give', 'to pity', 'to protect', 'to move' and of ईश 'to rule or be master of', the object takes the 6th-Case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.53|2.3.53 kRNJaH pratiyatne|kRNJaH pratiyatne|kRNJaH pratiyatne 2.3.53|कृञः प्रतियत्ने|कृञः प्रतियत्ने २.३.५३|२.३.५३|२.३.५३ कृञः प्रतियत्ने
The object of the verb कृ takes the 6th-Case-affix, when it means 'to impart a new quality or virtue' -- गन्धनावक्षेपणसेवनसाहसिक्यप्रतियत्नप्रकथनोपयोगेषु कृञः १.३.३२.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.54|2.3.54 rujaarthaanaaM bhaavavachanaanaamajvareH|rujaarthaanaaM bhaavavachanaanaamajvareH|rujaarthaanaaM bhaavavachanaanaamajvareH 2.3.54|रुजार्थानां भाववचनानामज्वरेः|रुजार्थानां भाववचनानामज्वरेः २.३.५४|२.३.५४|२.३.५४ रुजार्थानां भाववचनानामज्वरेः
The object of verbs having the sense of रुज् 'to afflict', with the exception of the Causative verb ज्वरय 'to be feverish', takes the 6th-Case-affix, when the verb expresses a condition (i.e. when the subject is an Abstract noun).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.55|2.3.55 aashiShi naathaH|aashiShi naathaH|aashiShi naathaH 2.3.55|आशिषि नाथः|आशिषि नाथः २.३.५५|२.३.५५|२.३.५५ आशिषि नाथः
Of the verb नाथ् when meaning 'to bless', the object takes the 6th-Case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.56|2.3.56 jaasiniprahaNanaaTakraathapiShaaM hiMsaayaam‌|jaasiniprahaNanaaTakraathapiShaaM hiMsaayaam‌|jaasiniprahaNanaaTakraathapiShaaM hiMsaayaam‌ 2.3.56|जासिनिप्रहणनाटक्राथपिषां हिंसायाम्‌|जासिनिप्रहणनाटक्राथपिषां हिंसायाम्‌ २.३.५६|२.३.५६|२.३.५६ जासिनिप्रहणनाटक्राथपिषां हिंसायाम्‌
The object of the verbs जासि 'to strike', 'to hurt', हन् 'to strike' preceded by नि and ग्र , नाट् 'to injure', क्राथ and पिष when they mean 'to injure', takes the 6th-Case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.57|2.3.57 vyavahRpaNoH samarthayoH|vyavahRpaNoH samarthayoH|vyavahRpaNoH samarthayoH 2.3.57|व्यवहृपणोः समर्थयोः|व्यवहृपणोः समर्थयोः २.३.५७|२.३.५७|२.३.५७ व्यवहृपणोः समर्थयोः
The object of the verbs व्यवहृ and पण् when they ae synonymous, that is when they mean 'dealing in sale and purchase transactions' or 'staking in gambling' takes the 6th-Case-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.58|2.3.58 divastadarthasya|divastadarthasya|divastadarthasya 2.3.58|दिवस्तदर्थस्य|दिवस्तदर्थस्य २.३.५८|२.३.५८|२.३.५८ दिवस्तदर्थस्य
The object of the verb दिव् when having the above-mentioned sense of 'dealing' or 'stalking', takes the 6th-Case.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.59|2.3.59 vibhaaShopasarge|vibhaaShopasarge|vibhaaShopasarge 2.3.59|विभाषोपसर्गे|विभाषोपसर्गे २.३.५९|२.३.५९|२.३.५९ विभाषोपसर्गे
The object of the verb दिव् when having the above-mentioned sense of 'dealing' or 'stalking', optionally takes the 6th-Case, when preceded by an उपसर्ग (preposition).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.60|2.3.60 dvitiiyaa braahmaNe|dvitiiyaa braahmaNe|dvitiiyaa braahmaNe 2.3.60|द्वितीया ब्राह्मणे|द्वितीया ब्राह्मणे २.३.६०|२.३.६०|२.३.६० द्वितीया ब्राह्मणे
The object of the verb दिव् when having the above-mentioned sense of 'dealing' or 'stalking', takes the 2nd case, in the ब्राह्मण literature.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2

2.3.61|2.3.61 preShyabruvorhaviSho devataasampradaane|preShyabruvorhaviSho devataasampradaane|preShyabruvorhaviSho devataasampradaane 2.3.61|प्रेष्यब्रुवोर्हविषो देवतासम्प्रदाने|प्रेष्यब्रुवोर्हविषो देवतासम्प्रदाने २.३.६१|२.३.६१|२.३.६१ प्रेष्यब्रुवोर्हविषो देवतासम्प्रदाने
The object of the verb प्रेष्य and ब्रूहि (imperative singular of दिवादि verb, meaning 'send' and 'utter') denoting sacrificial food, takes the 6th-Case-affix, when making offerings to deity is meant or when deity is the recepient.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.62|2.3.62 chaturthyarthe bahulaM Chandasi|chaturthyarthe bahulaM Chandasi|chaturthyarthe bahulaM Chandasi 2.3.62|चतुर्थ्यर्थे बहुलं छन्दसि|चतुर्थ्यर्थे बहुलं छन्दसि २.३.६२|२.३.६२|२.३.६२ चतुर्थ्यर्थे बहुलं छन्दसि
In the छन्दस् the 6th-Case-affix is used diversely with the force of the 4th case-affix.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

2.3.63|2.3.63 yajeshcha karaNe|yajeshcha karaNe|yajeshcha karaNe 2.3.63|यजेश्च करणे|यजेश्च करणे २.३.६३|२.३.६३|२.३.६३ यजेश्च करणे
The 6th-Case-affix is diversely used in the छन्दस् in denoting the instrument of the verb यज् 'to sacrifice'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.64|2.3.64 kRtvo.arthaprayoge kaale.adhikaraNe|kRtvo.arthaprayoge kaale.adhikaraNe|kRtvo.arthaprayoge kaale.adhikaraNe 2.3.64|कृत्वोऽर्थप्रयोगे कालेऽधिकरणे|कृत्वोऽर्थप्रयोगे कालेऽधिकरणे २.३.६४|२.३.६४|२.३.६४ कृत्वोऽर्थप्रयोगे कालेऽधिकरणे
The 6th-Case-affix is used in denoting location (अधिकरण) after a word denoting time (काल) when used along with a word ending with an affix having the sense of कृत्वसुच् -- संख्यायाः क्रियाऽभ्यावृत्तिगणने कृत्वसुच् ५.४.१७ 'so many times'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.65|2.3.65 kartRkarmaNoH kRti|kartRkarmaNoH kRti|kartRkarmaNoH kRti 2.3.65|कर्तृकर्मणोः कृति|कर्तृकर्मणोः कृति २.३.६५|२.३.६५|२.३.६५ कर्तृकर्मणोः कृति
The 6th-Case-affix is used after a word, in denoting the agent and the object, when used along with a word ending with a कृत्-affix --कृदतिङ् ३.१.९३.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.66|2.3.66 ubhayapraaptau karmaNi|ubhayapraaptau karmaNi|ubhayapraaptau karmaNi 2.3.66|उभयप्राप्तौ कर्मणि|उभयप्राप्तौ कर्मणि २.३.६६|२.३.६६|२.३.६६ उभयप्राप्तौ कर्मणि
When the agent and the object of the action denoted by the words formed by कृत्-affixes, are both used in a sentence, in the object only, the 6th-Case-affix is employed and not in the agent (the object is put in the Genitive 6th-Case and not the Agent).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.67|2.3.67 ktasya cha vartamaane|ktasya cha vartamaane|ktasya cha vartamaane 2.3.67|क्तस्य च वर्तमाने|क्तस्य च वर्तमाने २.३.६७|२.३.६७|२.३.६७ क्तस्य च वर्तमाने
The past participle ending in क्त when used in the sense of the present tense, -- ञीतः क्तः ३.२.१८७ and -- मतिबुद्धिपूजार्थेभ्यश्च ३.२.१८८ , is used with the Genitive 6th-Case.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.68|2.3.68 adhikaraNavaachinashcha|adhikaraNavaachinashcha|adhikaraNavaachinashcha 2.3.68|अधिकरणवाचिनश्च|अधिकरणवाचिनश्च २.३.६८|२.३.६८|२.३.६८ अधिकरणवाचिनश्च
The past participle ending in क्त is used with the Genitive 6th-Case, when the former expresses location -- क्तोऽधिकरणे च ध्रौव्यगतिप्रत्यवसानार्थेभ्यः ३.४.७६.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.69|2.3.69 na lokaavyayaniShThaakhalarthatRnaam‌|na lokaavyayaniShThaakhalarthatRnaam‌|na lokaavyayaniShThaakhalarthatRnaam‌ 2.3.69|न लोकाव्ययनिष्ठाखलर्थतृनाम्‌|न लोकाव्ययनिष्ठाखलर्थतृनाम्‌ २.३.६९|२.३.६९|२.३.६९ न लोकाव्ययनिष्ठाखलर्थतृनाम्‌
The 6th-Case-affix is not used the express the agent or the object, when the word is governed by an Active Participle ending in the affix ल , or उ , or उक or an indeclinable, or by a Past Participle in the क्त and क्तवतु or by a word ending in an affix having the sense of खल् or by a Noun of agency formed by तृन्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.70|2.3.70 akenorbhaviShyadaadhamarNyayoH|akenorbhaviShyadaadhamarNyayoH|akenorbhaviShyadaadhamarNyayoH 2.3.70|अकेनोर्भविष्यदाधमर्ण्ययोः|अकेनोर्भविष्यदाधमर्ण्ययोः २.३.७०|२.३.७०|२.३.७० अकेनोर्भविष्यदाधमर्ण्ययोः
The 6th-Case-affix is not used when the word is governed by a verbal nounin अक denoting futurity, or in a इन् denoting 'futurity and indebtness'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.71|2.3.71 kRtyaanaaM kartari vaa|kRtyaanaaM kartari vaa|kRtyaanaaM kartari vaa 2.3.71|कृत्यानां कर्तरि वा|कृत्यानां कर्तरि वा २.३.७१|२.३.७१|२.३.७१ कृत्यानां कर्तरि वा
The 6th-Case-affix is optionally used in denoting the agent, (but not the object), when the word is governed by a Future Passive Participle (कृत्य).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.72|2.3.72 tulyaarthairatulopamaabhyaaM tRtiiyaa.anyatarasyaam‌|tulyaarthairatulopamaabhyaaM tRtiiyaa.anyatarasyaam‌|tulyaarthairatulopamaabhyaaM tRtiiyaa.anyatarasyaam‌ 2.3.72|तुल्यार्थैरतुलोपमाभ्यां तृतीयाऽन्यतरस्याम्‌|तुल्यार्थैरतुलोपमाभ्यां तृतीयाऽन्यतरस्याम्‌ २.३.७२|२.३.७२|२.३.७२ तुल्यार्थैरतुलोपमाभ्यां तृतीयाऽन्यतरस्याम्‌
The 3rd or the 6th-Case-affix may optionally be employed, when the word is joined with another word meaning 'like to or resemblance', excepting तुला and उपना।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

2.3.73|2.3.73 chaturthii chaashiShyaayuShyamadrabhadrakushalasukhaarthahitaiH|chaturthii chaashiShyaayuShyamadrabhadrakushalasukhaarthahitaiH|chaturthii chaashiShyaayuShyamadrabhadrakushalasukhaarthahitaiH 2.3.73|चतुर्थी चाशिष्यायुष्यमद्रभद्रकुशलसुखार्थहितैः|चतुर्थी चाशिष्यायुष्यमद्रभद्रकुशलसुखार्थहितैः २.३.७३|२.३.७३|२.३.७३ चतुर्थी चाशिष्यायुष्यमद्रभद्रकुशलसुखार्थहितैः
The 4th as well as the 6th-Case-affix may be used, when blessing is intended in connection with the words आयुष 'long life', मद्र 'joy', भद्र 'good fortune', कुशल 'welfare', सुख 'happiness', अर्थ 'prosperity' and हित 'good'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-4, 6

2.4.1|2.4.1 dvigurekavachanam‌|dvigurekavachanam‌|dvigurekavachanam‌ 2.4.1|द्विगुरेकवचनम्‌|द्विगुरेकवचनम्‌ २.४.१|२.४.१|२.४.१ द्विगुरेकवचनम्‌
 All affixes after the verb गाङ् 'to study' and the verb कुट् 'to be crooked' and the rest, are as if they had an indicatory ङ् (ङित्), except those affixes which have an indicatory ञ् (ञित्) or ण् (णित्).<br><br>Terms: 

2.4.2|2.4.2 dvaMdvashcha praaNituuryasenaangaanaam‌|dvaMdvashcha praaNituuryasenaangaanaam‌|dvaMdvashcha praaNituuryasenaangaanaam‌ 2.4.2|द्वंद्वश्च प्राणितूर्यसेनाङ्गानाम्‌|द्वंद्वश्च प्राणितूर्यसेनाङ्गानाम्‌ २.४.२|२.४.२|२.४.२ द्वंद्वश्च प्राणितूर्यसेनाङ्गानाम्‌
 An affix which begins with the augment इट् -- आर्धधातुकस्येड् वलादेः ७.२.३५, is ङित् after the root विज् 'to fear, to move'.<br><br>Terms: 

2.4.3|2.4.3 anuvaade charaNaanaam‌|anuvaade charaNaanaam‌|anuvaade charaNaanaam‌ 2.4.3|अनुवादे चरणानाम्‌|अनुवादे चरणानाम्‌ २.४.३|२.४.३|२.४.३ अनुवादे चरणानाम्‌
A द्वन्द compound or words signifying persons belonging to the different Vedic-schools, when the sense is that of repition is singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.4|2.4.4 adhvaryukraturanapuMsakam.|adhvaryukraturanapuMsakam.|adhvaryukraturanapuMsakam. 2.4.4|अध्वर्युक्रतुरनपुंसकम्.|अध्वर्युक्रतुरनपुंसकम्. २.४.४|२.४.४|२.४.४ अध्वर्युक्रतुरनपुंसकम्.
A द्वन्द compound of words denoting क्रतु (sacrifices) ordained by यजुर् (अध्वर्यु) Veda, is singular, provided they are never used in the neuter gender<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.5|2.4.5 adhyayanato.aviprakRShTaakhyaanaam‌|adhyayanato.aviprakRShTaakhyaanaam‌|adhyayanato.aviprakRShTaakhyaanaam‌ 2.4.5|अध्ययनतोऽविप्रकृष्टाख्यानाम्‌|अध्ययनतोऽविप्रकृष्टाख्यानाम्‌ २.४.५|२.४.५|२.४.५ अध्ययनतोऽविप्रकृष्टाख्यानाम्‌
A द्वन्द compound of words denoting (persons who have studied) subjects, which in their order of study are not remote from each other, is singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.6|2.4.6 jaatirapraaNinaam‌|jaatirapraaNinaam‌|jaatirapraaNinaam‌ 2.4.6|जातिरप्राणिनाम्‌|जातिरप्राणिनाम्‌ २.४.६|२.४.६|२.४.६ जातिरप्राणिनाम्‌
A द्वन्द compound of words signifying जाति (genus) which are not the names of living beings, is singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.7|2.4.7 vishiShTalingo nadii desho.agraamaaH|vishiShTalingo nadii desho.agraamaaH|vishiShTalingo nadii desho.agraamaaH 2.4.7|विशिष्टलिङ्गो नदी देशोऽग्रामाः|विशिष्टलिङ्गो नदी देशोऽग्रामाः २.४.७|२.४.७|२.४.७ विशिष्टलिङ्गो नदी देशोऽग्रामाः
A द्वन्द compound of words of different genders, denoting names of rivers and countries, but not of towns, is singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.8|2.4.8 xudrajantavaH|xudrajantavaH|xudrajantavaH 2.4.8|क्षुद्रजन्तवः|क्षुद्रजन्तवः २.४.८|२.४.८|२.४.८ क्षुद्रजन्तवः
A द्वन्द compound of words signifying small animals, is singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.9|2.4.9 yeShaaM cha virodhaH shaashvatikaH|yeShaaM cha virodhaH shaashvatikaH|yeShaaM cha virodhaH shaashvatikaH 2.4.9|येषां च विरोधः शाश्वतिकः|येषां च विरोधः शाश्वतिकः २.४.९|२.४.९|२.४.९ येषां च विरोधः शाश्वतिकः
A द्वन्द compound of words signifying those animals only among whom there is permanent enimity i.e. natural and eternal antipathy or quarrel, is singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.10|2.4.10 shuudraaNaamaniravasitaanaam‌|shuudraaNaamaniravasitaanaam‌|shuudraaNaamaniravasitaanaam‌ 2.4.10|शूद्राणामनिरवसितानाम्‌|शूद्राणामनिरवसितानाम्‌ २.४.१०|२.४.१०|२.४.१० शूद्राणामनिरवसितानाम्‌
A द्वन्द compound of words denoting those classes of शुद्रा-s who have not been expelled from the communion of higher classes, is singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.11|2.4.11 gavaashvaprabhRtiini cha|gavaashvaprabhRtiini cha|gavaashvaprabhRtiini cha 2.4.11|गवाश्वप्रभृतीनि च|गवाश्वप्रभृतीनि च २.४.११|२.४.११|२.४.११ गवाश्वप्रभृतीनि च
The word गवाश and others are also द्वन्द compounds which take the singular number.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.12|2.4.12 vibhaaShaa vRxamRgatRNadhaanyavyanjanapashushakunyashvavaDavapuurvaaparaadharottaraaNaam‌|vibhaaShaa vRxamRgatRNadhaanyavyanjanapashushakunyashvavaDavapuurvaaparaadharottaraaNaam‌|vibhaaShaa vRxamRgatRNadhaanyavyanjanapashushakunyashvavaDavapuurvaaparaadharottaraaNaam‌ 2.4.12|विभाषा वृक्षमृगतृणधान्यव्यञ्जनपशुशकुन्यश्ववडवपूर्वापराधरोत्तराणाम्‌|विभाषा वृक्षमृगतृणधान्यव्यञ्जनपशुशकुन्यश्ववडवपूर्वापराधरोत्तराणाम्‌ २.४.१२|२.४.१२|२.४.१२ विभाषा वृक्षमृगतृणधान्यव्यञ्जनपशुशकुन्यश्ववडवपूर्वापराधरोत्तराणाम्‌
A द्वन्द compound of words being the names of trees, wild animals, grass, corn, condiment, domestic beasts and birds and the compounds अश्व-वडव , पूर्व-पर and अधरोत्तर , are optionally singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.13|2.4.13 vipratiShiddhaM chaanadhikaraNavaachi|vipratiShiddhaM chaanadhikaraNavaachi|vipratiShiddhaM chaanadhikaraNavaachi 2.4.13|विप्रतिषिद्धं चानधिकरणवाचि|विप्रतिषिद्धं चानधिकरणवाचि २.४.१३|२.४.१३|२.४.१३ विप्रतिषिद्धं चानधिकरणवाचि
A द्वन्द compound of words of contrary significations, but not being the names of concrete substances.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.14|2.4.14 na dadhipayaaadiini|na dadhipayaaadiini|na dadhipayaaadiini 2.4.14|न दधिपयआदीनि|न दधिपयआदीनि २.४.१४|२.४.१४|२.४.१४ न दधिपयआदीनि
The द्वन्द compounds like दधिपय etc. are not singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.15|2.4.15 adhikaraNaitaavattve cha|adhikaraNaitaavattve cha|adhikaraNaitaavattve cha 2.4.15|अधिकरणैतावत्त्वे च|अधिकरणैतावत्त्वे च २.४.१५|२.४.१५|२.४.१५ अधिकरणैतावत्त्वे च
A द्वन्द compound denoting a fixed number (एकत्व) of concrete things (अधिकरण) is not singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.16|2.4.16 vibhaaShaa samiipe|vibhaaShaa samiipe|vibhaaShaa samiipe 2.4.16|विभाषा समीपे|विभाषा समीपे २.४.१६|२.४.१६|२.४.१६ विभाषा समीपे
A द्वन्द compound denoting an approximate number of concrete substances, is optionally singular.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.17|2.4.17 sa napuMsakam‌|sa napuMsakam‌|sa napuMsakam‌ 2.4.17|स नपुंसकम्‌|स नपुंसकम्‌ २.४.१७|२.४.१७|२.४.१७ स नपुंसकम्‌
It, namely the द्विगु or द्वन्द compound, with regard to which singular number has been ordained by the above rules, is always neuter gender.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द

2.4.18|2.4.18 avyayiibhaavashcha|avyayiibhaavashcha|avyayiibhaavashcha 2.4.18|अव्ययीभावश्च|अव्ययीभावश्च २.४.१८|२.४.१८|२.४.१८ अव्ययीभावश्च
An अव्ययीभाव -- अव्ययं विभक्तिसमीपसमृद्धिव्यृद्ध्यर्थाभावात्ययासम्प्रतिशब्दप्रादुर्भावपश्चाद्यथाऽऽनुपूर्व्ययौगपद्यसादृश्यसम्पत्तिसाकल्यान्तवचनेषु २.१.६, compound is also neuter gender. <br><br>Terms: समास-अव्ययीभाव

2.4.19|2.4.19 tatpuruSho.anaNJ‌ karmadhaarayaH|tatpuruSho.anaNJ‌ karmadhaarayaH|tatpuruSho.anaNJ‌ karmadhaarayaH 2.4.19|तत्पुरुषोऽनञ्‌ कर्मधारयः|तत्पुरुषोऽनञ्‌ कर्मधारयः २.४.१९|२.४.१९|२.४.१९ तत्पुरुषोऽनञ्‌ कर्मधारयः
A तत्-पुरुष compound, with the exception of that which is formed by the particle नञ् , and or the कर्मधारय compound, becomes neuter gender, in the cases explained in the following sūtras.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.4.20|2.4.20 saMJNaayaaM kanthoshiinareShu|saMJNaayaaM kanthoshiinareShu|saMJNaayaaM kanthoshiinareShu 2.4.20|संज्ञायां कन्थोशीनरेषु|संज्ञायां कन्थोशीनरेषु २.४.२०|२.४.२०|२.४.२० संज्ञायां कन्थोशीनरेषु
When denoting an appellative, a तत्-पुरुष compound ending with the word कन्था 'town', is neuter in gender, provided that it is the name of a town situtated in a country of the उशीनर-s.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.4.21|2.4.21 upaJNopakramaM tadaadyaachikhyaasaayaam‌|upaJNopakramaM tadaadyaachikhyaasaayaam‌|upaJNopakramaM tadaadyaachikhyaasaayaam‌ 2.4.21|उपज्ञोपक्रमं तदाद्याचिख्यासायाम्‌|उपज्ञोपक्रमं तदाद्याचिख्यासायाम्‌ २.४.२१|२.४.२१|२.४.२१ उपज्ञोपक्रमं तदाद्याचिख्यासायाम्‌
A तत्-पुरुष compound ending with the words उपज्ञा 'invention' and उपक्रम 'commencement' is neuter in gender, when it is intended to express the starting point of a work which is first invented or commenced.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष

2.4.22|2.4.22 Chaayaa baahulye|Chaayaa baahulye|Chaayaa baahulye 2.4.22|छाया बाहुल्ये|छाया बाहुल्ये २.४.२२|२.४.२२|२.४.२२ छाया बाहुल्ये
A तत्-पुरुष compound ending with the word छाया 'shadow' in neuter in gender when the sense is that of profusenss of the thing indicated by the first term.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-gender

2.4.23|2.4.23 sabhaa raajaa.amanuShyapuurvaa|sabhaa raajaa.amanuShyapuurvaa|sabhaa raajaa.amanuShyapuurvaa 2.4.23|सभा राजाऽमनुष्यपूर्वा|सभा राजाऽमनुष्यपूर्वा २.४.२३|२.४.२३|२.४.२३ सभा राजाऽमनुष्यपूर्वा
A तत्-पुरुष compound ending with the word सभा 'court' is neuter, provided that it is preceded by (a word synonymous with) the word राजा or by a word denoting a non-human-being. <br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-gender

2.4.24|2.4.24 ashaalaa cha|ashaalaa cha|ashaalaa cha 2.4.24|अशाला च|अशाला च २.४.२४|२.४.२४|२.४.२४ अशाला च
A तत्-पुरुष compound ending with the word सभा 'court', when it does not mean a house but means concourse, is neuter.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-gender

2.4.25|2.4.25 vibhaaShaa senaasuraaChaayaashaalaanishaanaam‌|vibhaaShaa senaasuraaChaayaashaalaanishaanaam‌|vibhaaShaa senaasuraaChaayaashaalaanishaanaam‌ 2.4.25|विभाषा सेनासुराछायाशालानिशानाम्‌|विभाषा सेनासुराछायाशालानिशानाम्‌ २.४.२५|२.४.२५|२.४.२५ विभाषा सेनासुराछायाशालानिशानाम्‌
A तत्-पुरुष compound ending with the words सेना 'army', सुरा 'wine', छाया 'shadow', शाला 'house' and निशा 'night', is optionally neuter, with the exception of that which is formed by the particle नञ् -- नञ्‌ २.२.६, and the कर्मधारय compound.<br><br>Terms: समास-तत्-पुरुष-कर्मधारय

2.4.26|2.4.26 paravallingaM dvandvatatpuruShayoH|paravallingaM dvandvatatpuruShayoH|paravallingaM dvandvatatpuruShayoH 2.4.26|परवल्लिङ्गं द्वन्द्वतत्पुरुषयोः|परवल्लिङ्गं द्वन्द्वतत्पुरुषयोः २.४.२६|२.४.२६|२.४.२६ परवल्लिङ्गं द्वन्द्वतत्पुरुषयोः
The gender of द्वन्द compound or तत्-पुरुष compound is like that of the last word in it.<br><br>Terms: समास-द्वन्द-gender

2.4.27|2.4.27 puurvavadashvavaDavau|puurvavadashvavaDavau|puurvavadashvavaDavau 2.4.27|पूर्ववदश्ववडवौ|पूर्ववदश्ववडवौ २.४.२७|२.४.२७|२.४.२७ पूर्ववदश्ववडवौ
The gender of the compound of the word अश्व 'horse' and वडव 'a mare', is like that of the first word in it.<br><br>Terms: समास-gender

2.4.28|2.4.28 hemantashishiraavahoraatre cha chChandasi|hemantashishiraavahoraatre cha chChandasi|hemantashishiraavahoraatre cha chChandasi 2.4.28|हेमन्तशिशिरावहोरात्रे च च्छन्दसि|हेमन्तशिशिरावहोरात्रे च च्छन्दसि २.४.२८|२.४.२८|२.४.२८ हेमन्तशिशिरावहोरात्रे च च्छन्दसि
Of the compounds हेमन्त-शिशिरौ and अहोरात्रे , the gender is like that of the first word, in the छन्दस् ।<br><br>Terms: समास-gender

2.4.29|2.4.29 raatraahnaahaaH puMsi|raatraahnaahaaH puMsi|raatraahnaahaaH puMsi 2.4.29|रात्राह्नाहाः पुंसि|रात्राह्नाहाः पुंसि २.४.२९|२.४.२९|२.४.२९ रात्राह्नाहाः पुंसि
The द्वन्द and तत्-पुरुष compound ending with the words रात्र and अह्न are spoken of in masculine.<br><br>Terms: समास-gender

2.4.30|2.4.30 apathaM napuMsakam‌|apathaM napuMsakam‌|apathaM napuMsakam‌ 2.4.30|अपथं नपुंसकम्‌|अपथं नपुंसकम्‌ २.४.३०|२.४.३०|२.४.३० अपथं नपुंसकम्‌
The तत्-पुरुष word अपथम् 'a bad road', is neuter.<br><br>Terms: समास-gender

2.4.31|2.4.31 ardharchaaH puMsi cha|ardharchaaH puMsi cha|ardharchaaH puMsi cha 2.4.31|अर्धर्चाः पुंसि च|अर्धर्चाः पुंसि च २.४.३१|२.४.३१|२.४.३१ अर्धर्चाः पुंसि च
The words अर्धर्च etc. are spoken of in masculine and neuter.<br><br>Terms: समास-gender

2.4.32|2.4.32 idamo.anvaadeshe.ashanudaattastRtiiyaa.a.adau|idamo.anvaadeshe.ashanudaattastRtiiyaa.a.adau|idamo.anvaadeshe.ashanudaattastRtiiyaa.a.adau 2.4.32|इदमोऽन्वादेशेऽशनुदात्तस्तृतीयाऽऽदौ|इदमोऽन्वादेशेऽशनुदात्तस्तृतीयाऽऽदौ २.४.३२|२.४.३२|२.४.३२ इदमोऽन्वादेशेऽशनुदात्तस्तृतीयाऽऽदौ
In the room of इदम् 'this', in the case of its re-employment in a subsequent member of the same sentence and referring to the same thing (अन्वादेश) there is the substitution of अश् which is अनुदात्त (gravely accented), when the Instrumental -3rd case-affix and the rest follow.<br><br>Terms: इदम्

2.4.33|2.4.33 etadastratasostratasau chaanudaattau|etadastratasostratasau chaanudaattau|etadastratasostratasau chaanudaattau 2.4.33|एतदस्त्रतसोस्त्रतसौ चानुदात्तौ|एतदस्त्रतसोस्त्रतसौ चानुदात्तौ २.४.३३|२.४.३३|२.४.३३ एतदस्त्रतसोस्त्रतसौ चानुदात्तौ
In the room of एतद् in the case of re-employment there is the substitution of the gravely accented अश् when the affixes त्र -- सप्तम्यास्त्रल् ५.३.१० and तस् -- पञ्चम्यास्तसिल् ५.३.७ follow, and the affixes त्र and तद् are अनुदात्त (gravely accented) also.<br><br>Terms: समास

2.4.34|2.4.34 dvitiiyaaTaussvenaH|dvitiiyaaTaussvenaH|dvitiiyaaTaussvenaH 2.4.34|द्वितीयाटौस्स्वेनः|द्वितीयाटौस्स्वेनः २.४.३४|२.४.३४|२.४.३४ द्वितीयाटौस्स्वेनः
When an affix of the Accusative -2nd case or टा - Instrumental -3rd case singular or ओश् Locative -7th-case dual follows, एन् which is अनुदात्त is the substitute of इदम् and its re-employment.<br><br>Terms: समास

2.4.35|2.4.35 aarddhadhaatuke|aarddhadhaatuke|aarddhadhaatuke 2.4.35|आर्द्धधातुके|आर्द्धधातुके २.४.३५|२.४.३५|२.४.३५ आर्द्धधातुके
The clause 'when the affix is आर्धधातुक is understood in the following sūtras up to sūtra २.४.५८.<br><br>Terms: आर्धधातुक-substitutes

