And the affix खच् comes after the verb गम् 'to go' when in composition with the verbs - 1. अन्त 'end' 2. अत्यन्त 'extreme' 3. अध्वम् 'road' 4. दूर 'far' 5. पार 'across' 6. सर्व 'all' 7. अनन्त 'endless'.<br><br>Terms: खच्

3.2.49|3.2.49 aashiShi hanaH|aashiShi hanaH|aashiShi hanaH 3.2.49|आशिषि हनः|आशिषि हनः ३.२.४९|३.२.४९|३.२.४९ आशिषि हनः
The affix ड comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when the object is in composition with it and when benediction is intended.<br><br>Terms: ड

3.2.50|3.2.50 ape kleshatamasoH|ape kleshatamasoH|ape kleshatamasoH 3.2.50|अपे क्लेशतमसोः|अपे क्लेशतमसोः ३.२.५०|३.२.५०|३.२.५० अपे क्लेशतमसोः
The affix ड comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when it is compounded with the preposition अप् and when the object in composition with it, is the word क्लेश 'pain' or तमस् 'darkness'.<br><br>Terms: ड

3.2.51|3.2.51 kumaarashiirShayorNiniH|kumaarashiirShayorNiniH|kumaarashiirShayorNiniH 3.2.51|कुमारशीर्षयोर्णिनिः|कुमारशीर्षयोर्णिनिः ३.२.५१|३.२.५१|३.२.५१ कुमारशीर्षयोर्णिनिः
The affix णिनि comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when the word in composition with it is कुमार 'a child' or शीर्ष 'head'.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.52|3.2.52 laxaNe jaayaapatyoShTak|laxaNe jaayaapatyoShTak|laxaNe jaayaapatyoShTak 3.2.52|लक्षणे जायापत्योष्टक्|लक्षणे जायापत्योष्टक् ३.२.५२|३.२.५२|३.२.५२ लक्षणे जायापत्योष्टक्
The affix टक् comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when it is in composition with the word जाया 'wife' or पति 'huband' as object and when the word so formed denotes the agent possessed of that attribute (or when the word so formed denotes a mark).<br><br>Terms: टक्

3.2.53|3.2.53 amanuShyakartRke cha|amanuShyakartRke cha|amanuShyakartRke cha 3.2.53|अमनुष्यकर्तृके च|अमनुष्यकर्तृके च ३.२.५३|३.२.५३|३.२.५३ अमनुष्यकर्तृके च
The affix टक् comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when the object is in composition with it and when the word to be formed denotes an agent other than a human being.<br><br>Terms: टक्

3.2.54|3.2.54 shaktau hastikapaaTayoH|shaktau hastikapaaTayoH|shaktau hastikapaaTayoH 3.2.54|शक्तौ हस्तिकपाटयोः|शक्तौ हस्तिकपाटयोः ३.२.५४|३.२.५४|३.२.५४ शक्तौ हस्तिकपाटयोः
The affix टक् comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when the object is in composition with it as its object is हस्ति 'elephant' or कपाट 'gate' and when the sense indicated is that of power.<br><br>Terms: टक्

3.2.55|3.2.55 paaNighataaDaghau shilpini|paaNighataaDaghau shilpini|paaNighataaDaghau shilpini 3.2.55|पाणिघताडघौ शिल्पिनि|पाणिघताडघौ शिल्पिनि ३.२.५५|३.२.५५|३.२.५५ पाणिघताडघौ शिल्पिनि
The word पाणिघ and ताडघ are irregularly formed when denoting an artificier.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.2.56|3.2.56 aaDhyasubhagasthuulapalitanagnaandhapriyeShu chvyrtheShvachvau kRNJaH karaNe khyun|aaDhyasubhagasthuulapalitanagnaandhapriyeShu chvyrtheShvachvau kRNJaH karaNe khyun|aaDhyasubhagasthuulapalitanagnaandhapriyeShu chvyrtheShvachvau kRNJaH karaNe khyun 3.2.56|आढ्यसुभगस्थूलपलितनग्नान्धप्रियेषु च्व्य्र्थेष्वच्वौ कृञः करणे ख्युन्|आढ्यसुभगस्थूलपलितनग्नान्धप्रियेषु च्व्य्र्थेष्वच्वौ कृञः करणे ख्युन् ३.२.५६|३.२.५६|३.२.५६ आढ्यसुभगस्थूलपलितनग्नान्धप्रियेषु च्व्य्र्थेष्वच्वौ कृञः करणे ख्युन्
The affix ख्युन् , when in the sense of the word to be formed is that of an instrumental agent, comes after the verb कृ 'to make', when the following words are in composition with it - 1. आढ्य 'rich' 2. सुभग 'fortunate' 3. स्थूल 'big' 4. पलित 'grey' 5. नग्न 'naked' 6. अन्ध 'blind' 7. प्रिय 'pleasant', provided these words formed by the affix च्वि though not actually ending in the affix च्वि।<br><br>Terms: ख्युन्

3.2.57|3.2.57 kartari bhuvaH khiShNuchkhukaNJau|kartari bhuvaH khiShNuchkhukaNJau|kartari bhuvaH khiShNuchkhukaNJau 3.2.57|कर्तरि भुवः खिष्णुच्खुकञौ|कर्तरि भुवः खिष्णुच्खुकञौ ३.२.५७|३.२.५७|३.२.५७ कर्तरि भुवः खिष्णुच्खुकञौ
The affixes खिष्णुच् and खकञ् , when the word to be formed denotes an agent comes after the verb भू 'to become', when it is in composition with the words formed by the affix च्वि though not actually ending in the affix च्वि।<br><br>Terms: खिष्णुच् and खकञ्

3.2.58|3.2.58 spRsho.anudake kvin|spRsho.anudake kvin|spRsho.anudake kvin 3.2.58|स्पृशोऽनुदके क्विन्|स्पृशोऽनुदके क्विन् ३.२.५८|३.२.५८|३.२.५८ स्पृशोऽनुदके क्विन्
The affix क्विन् comes after the verb स्पृश् 'to touch' when it is in composition with a case-inflected word other than उदक 'water'.<br><br>Terms: क्विन्

3.2.59|3.2.59 RtvigdadhRksragdiguShNigancuyujikruncaaM cha|RtvigdadhRksragdiguShNigancuyujikruncaaM cha|RtvigdadhRksragdiguShNigancuyujikruncaaM cha 3.2.59|ऋत्विग्दधृक्स्रग्दिगुष्णिगञ्चुयुजिक्रुञ्चां च|ऋत्विग्दधृक्स्रग्दिगुष्णिगञ्चुयुजिक्रुञ्चां च ३.२.५९|३.२.५९|३.२.५९ ऋत्विग्दधृक्स्रग्दिगुष्णिगञ्चुयुजिक्रुञ्चां च
The words - 1. ऋत्विक् 'a domestic priest' 2. दधृक् 'impudent' 3. स्रक् 'a garland' 4. दिक् 'direction' and 5. उष्णिक् 'a quatrain', are irregularly formed by adding the affix क्विन् and also after the verbs 6. अञ्चु 'to worship' 7. युजि 'to join' 8. क्रुञ्चु 'to approach', the affix क्विन् is used.<br><br>Terms: क्विन्

3.2.60|3.2.60 tyadaadiShu dRsho.anaalochane kaNJ cha|tyadaadiShu dRsho.anaalochane kaNJ cha|tyadaadiShu dRsho.anaalochane kaNJ cha 3.2.60|त्यदादिषु दृशोऽनालोचने कञ् च|त्यदादिषु दृशोऽनालोचने कञ् च ३.२.६०|३.२.६०|३.२.६० त्यदादिषु दृशोऽनालोचने कञ् च
And the affix कञ् comes after the verb दृश् 'to see' when it is in composition with त्यद् etc. and does not signify perception.<br><br>Terms: कञ्

3.2.61|3.2.61 satsuudviShadruhaduhayujavidabhidachChidajiniiraajaamupasarge.api kvip‌|satsuudviShadruhaduhayujavidabhidachChidajiniiraajaamupasarge.api kvip‌|satsuudviShadruhaduhayujavidabhidachChidajiniiraajaamupasarge.api kvip‌ 3.2.61|सत्सूद्विषद्रुहदुहयुजविदभिदच्छिदजिनीराजामुपसर्गेऽपि क्विप्‌|सत्सूद्विषद्रुहदुहयुजविदभिदच्छिदजिनीराजामुपसर्गेऽपि क्विप्‌ ३.२.६१|३.२.६१|३.२.६१ सत्सूद्विषद्रुहदुहयुजविदभिदच्छिदजिनीराजामुपसर्गेऽपि क्विप्‌
The affix क्विप्‌ comes after the following verbs when in composition with a word ending in a case-affix, though it may be an उपसर्ग viz. 1. सत् 'to sit' 2. सू 'to bring forth' 3. द्विष् 'to hate' 4. द्रुह् 'to bear malice' 5. दुह् 'to milk' 6. युज् 'to join' , 'to concentrate the mind' 7. विद् 'to know', 'to consider' 8. भिद् 'to divide' 9. च्छिद् 'to cut' 10. जि 'to conquer' 11. नी 'to lead 12. राज् 'to shine'.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्‌

3.2.62|3.2.62 bhajo NviH|bhajo NviH|bhajo NviH 3.2.62|भजो ण्विः|भजो ण्विः ३.२.६२|३.२.६२|३.२.६२ भजो ण्विः
The affix ण्वि comes after the verb भज् 'to share' when in composition with a word ending in a case-affix whether it be an उपसर्ग or not.<br><br>Terms: ण्वि

3.2.63|3.2.63 Chandasi sahaH|Chandasi sahaH|Chandasi sahaH 3.2.63|छन्दसि सहः|छन्दसि सहः ३.२.६३|३.२.६३|३.२.६३ छन्दसि सहः
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the affix णिव comes after the verb सह् 'to bear' when in composition with a word ending in a case-affix.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.64|3.2.64 vahashcha|vahashcha|vahashcha 3.2.64|वहश्च|वहश्च ३.२.६४|३.२.६४|३.२.६४ वहश्च
The affix णिव after the verb वह् 'to carry' in the छन्दस् (Vedas), when the word ending in case-affix is in composition with it.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.65|3.2.65 kavyapuriiShapuriiShyeShu NJyuT|kavyapuriiShapuriiShyeShu NJyuT|kavyapuriiShapuriiShyeShu NJyuT 3.2.65|कव्यपुरीषपुरीष्येषु ञ्युट्|कव्यपुरीषपुरीष्येषु ञ्युट् ३.२.६५|३.२.६५|३.२.६५ कव्यपुरीषपुरीष्येषु ञ्युट्
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the affix ञ्युट् comes after the verb वह् 'to carry' when it is in composition with the words कव्य 'oblation of food to deceased ancesters', पुरीष 'faeces' and पुरीष्य 'water'.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.66|3.2.66 havye.anantaH paadam|havye.anantaH paadam|havye.anantaH paadam 3.2.66|हव्येऽनन्तः पादम्|हव्येऽनन्तः पादम् ३.२.६६|३.२.६६|३.२.६६ हव्येऽनन्तः पादम्
The affix ञ्युट् comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the verb वह् 'to carry' when it is in composition with the word हव्य 'an oblation to gods', provided that the word so formed does not occur in the middle of a पाद (4th part of a stanza).<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.67|3.2.67 janasanakhanakramagamo viT|janasanakhanakramagamo viT|janasanakhanakramagamo viT 3.2.67|जनसनखनक्रमगमो विट्|जनसनखनक्रमगमो विट् ३.२.६७|३.२.६७|३.२.६७ जनसनखनक्रमगमो विट्
The affix विट् (the whole of which is elided) comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the verbs 1. जन् 'to be born' 2. सन् 'to bestow' 3. खन् 'to dig' 4. क्रम् 'to pace' 5. गम् 'to go' when a word ending in case-affix is in composition and the final nasals are changed into long आ।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.68|3.2.68 ado.ananne|ado.ananne|ado.ananne 3.2.68|अदोऽनन्ने|अदोऽनन्ने ३.२.६८|३.२.६८|३.२.६८ अदोऽनन्ने
The affix विट् comes after the verb अद् 'to eat' when in composition with a case-inflected word other than अन्न 'food'.<br><br>Terms: विट्

3.2.69|3.2.69 kravye cha|kravye cha|kravye cha 3.2.69|क्रव्ये च|क्रव्ये च ३.२.६९|३.२.६९|३.२.६९ क्रव्ये च
The affix विट् comes after the verb अद् 'to eat' when the word क्रव्य is in composition with it.<br><br>Terms: विट्

3.2.70|3.2.70 duhaH kab ghashcha|duhaH kab ghashcha|duhaH kab ghashcha 3.2.70|दुहः कब् घश्च|दुहः कब् घश्च ३.२.७०|३.२.७०|३.२.७० दुहः कब् घश्च
The affix कप् comes after the verb दुह् 'to milk' when in composition with a word ending in a case-affix and the letter घ replaces the final.<br><br>Terms: कप्

3.2.71|3.2.71 mantre shvetavahaukthashaspuroDaasho Nvin|mantre shvetavahaukthashaspuroDaasho Nvin|mantre shvetavahaukthashaspuroDaasho Nvin 3.2.71|मन्त्रे श्वेतवहौक्थशस्पुरोडाशो ण्विन्|मन्त्रे श्वेतवहौक्थशस्पुरोडाशो ण्विन् ३.२.७१|३.२.७१|३.२.७१ मन्त्रे श्वेतवहौक्थशस्पुरोडाशो ण्विन्
In the मन्त्र literature,the affix णिवन् comes after the words 1. श्वेतवह 2.उक्थश 3. पुरोडाश् ।<br><br>Terms: णिवन्

3.2.72|3.2.72 ave yajaH|ave yajaH|ave yajaH 3.2.72|अवे यजः|अवे यजः ३.२.७२|३.२.७२|३.२.७२ अवे यजः
In the मन्त्र literature,the affix णिवन् comes after the verb यज् 'to sacrifice' when in composition the word अव्।<br><br>Terms: णिवन्

3.2.73|3.2.73 vijupe Chandasi|vijupe Chandasi|vijupe Chandasi 3.2.73|विजुपे छन्दसि|विजुपे छन्दसि ३.२.७३|३.२.७३|३.२.७३ विजुपे छन्दसि
The affix विच् comes after the verb यज् 'to sacrifice' when उप precedes it, in the छन्दस् (Vedas).<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.74|3.2.74 aato maninkvanipvanipashcha|aato maninkvanipvanipashcha|aato maninkvanipvanipashcha 3.2.74|आतो मनिन्क्वनिप्वनिपश्च|आतो मनिन्क्वनिप्वनिपश्च ३.२.७४|३.२.७४|३.२.७४ आतो मनिन्क्वनिप्वनिपश्च
The affixes मनिन् (मन्), वनिप् (वन्), विनय (वन्) and विच् come in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the verbs which end in long आ , when used in a case-inflected word or उपसर्ग in in composition. <br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.75|3.2.75 anyebhyo.api dRshyante|anyebhyo.api dRshyante|anyebhyo.api dRshyante 3.2.75|अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यन्ते|अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यन्ते ३.२.७५|३.२.७५|३.२.७५ अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यन्ते
These affixes i.e. - मनिन् (मन्), वनिप् (वन्), विनय (वन्) and विच् are seen after other verbs also besides those ending in long आ।<br><br>Terms: मनिन् , वनिप् , विनय and विच्

3.2.76|3.2.76 kvip cha|kvip cha|kvip cha 3.2.76|क्विप् च|क्विप् च ३.२.७६|३.२.७६|३.२.७६ क्विप् च
And the affix क्विप् is also seen after all verbs, whether having an उपपद or not in the Vedic as well as in the modern Sanskṛt.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्

3.2.77|3.2.77 sthaH ka cha|sthaH ka cha|sthaH ka cha 3.2.77|स्थः क च|स्थः क च ३.२.७७|३.२.७७|३.२.७७ स्थः क च
The affixes क and क्विप् come after the verb स्था when in composition with a word ending in a case-affix or an उपसर्ग ।<br><br>Terms: क andक्विप्

3.2.78|3.2.78 supyajaatau NinistaachChilye|supyajaatau NinistaachChilye|supyajaatau NinistaachChilye 3.2.78|सुप्यजातौ णिनिस्ताच्छिल्ये|सुप्यजातौ णिनिस्ताच्छिल्ये ३.२.७८|३.२.७८|३.२.७८ सुप्यजातौ णिनिस्ताच्छिल्ये
When habit is to be expressed, the affix णिनि comes after a verb, provided the word with a case-affix in composition with it does not mean a genus.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.79|3.2.79 kartaryupamaane|kartaryupamaane|kartaryupamaane 3.2.79|कर्तर्युपमाने|कर्तर्युपमाने ३.२.७९|३.२.७९|३.२.७९ कर्तर्युपमाने
The affix णिनि comes after a verb when in composition with a word denoting an object of comparison, expressing the agent, the sense of the affix being 'doing something like that', that is to say, when the उपपद agent is the standard of comparison of the agent denoted by the word to which the sense of the affix refers.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.80|3.2.80 vrate|vrate|vrate 3.2.80|व्रते|व्रते ३.२.८०|३.२.८०|३.२.८० व्रते
The affix णिनि comes after a verb, in composition with a word ending in a case-affix.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.81|3.2.81 bahulamaabhiixNye|bahulamaabhiixNye|bahulamaabhiixNye 3.2.81|बहुलमाभीक्ष्ण्ये|बहुलमाभीक्ष्ण्ये ३.२.८१|३.२.८१|३.२.८१ बहुलमाभीक्ष्ण्ये
The affix णिनि comes after a verb diversely when continued repitition of an action is to be expressed.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.82|3.2.82 manaH|manaH|manaH 3.2.82|मनः|मनः ३.२.८२|३.२.८२|३.२.८२ मनः
The affix णिनि comes after the verb मन् 'to think' when there is a word with a case-affix in composition with it.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.83|3.2.83 aatmamaane khashcha|aatmamaane khashcha|aatmamaane khashcha 3.2.83|आत्ममाने खश्च|आत्ममाने खश्च ३.२.८३|३.२.८३|३.२.८३ आत्ममाने खश्च
And the affix णिनि comes after the verb मन् 'to think' when the word in composition with it is a word with a case-affix and when it is used to signify thought, whereof the object is self (the sense of the affix being 'thinking himself as such').<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.84|3.2.84 bhuute|bhuute|bhuute 3.2.84|भूते|भूते ३.२.८४|३.२.८४|३.२.८४ भूते
All the affixes to be treated of hereafter should be understood to come in the sense of past time.<br><br>Terms: भूत

3.2.85|3.2.85 karaNe yajaH|karaNe yajaH|karaNe yajaH 3.2.85|करणे यजः|करणे यजः ३.२.८५|३.२.८५|३.२.८५ करणे यजः
The affix णिनि comes after the verb यज् 'to sacrifice' with the sense of past time, when the word in composition is the Instrumental -3rd case.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.86|3.2.86 karmaNi hanaH|karmaNi hanaH|karmaNi hanaH 3.2.86|कर्मणि हनः|कर्मणि हनः ३.२.८६|३.२.८६|३.२.८६ कर्मणि हनः
The affix णिनि comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' with the sense of past time, when the word in composition is in the Accusative -2nd case.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.2.87|3.2.87 brahmabhruuNavRtreShu kvip‌|brahmabhruuNavRtreShu kvip‌|brahmabhruuNavRtreShu kvip‌ 3.2.87|ब्रह्मभ्रूणवृत्रेषु क्विप्‌|ब्रह्मभ्रूणवृत्रेषु क्विप्‌ ३.२.८७|३.२.८७|३.२.८७ ब्रह्मभ्रूणवृत्रेषु क्विप्‌
The affix क्विप्‌ comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' with the sense of past time when the following words in the Accusative -2nd case ae in composition - 1. भ्रूण 'a foetus' 2. वृत्र ।<br><br>Terms: क्विप्‌

3.2.88|3.2.88 bahulaM Chandasi|bahulaM Chandasi|bahulaM Chandasi 3.2.88|बहुलं छन्दसि|बहुलं छन्दसि ३.२.८८|३.२.८८|३.२.८८ बहुलं छन्दसि
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the affix क्विप्‌ diversely comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' with the sense of past time,ending with the word even when the word in composition with it is other than those mentioned in the last sūtra.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्‌

3.2.89|3.2.89 sukarmapaapamantrapuNyeShu kRNJaH|sukarmapaapamantrapuNyeShu kRNJaH|sukarmapaapamantrapuNyeShu kRNJaH 3.2.89|सुकर्मपापमन्त्रपुण्येषु कृञः|सुकर्मपापमन्त्रपुण्येषु कृञः ३.२.८९|३.२.८९|३.२.८९ सुकर्मपापमन्त्रपुण्येषु कृञः
The affix क्विप्‌ comes after the verb कृ 'to make' with the sense of past time, when the following words in the Accusative -2nd case are in composition - 1. सु 'action' 2. कर्म 'action' 3. पाप 'sin' 4. मन्त्र 'hymn' 5. पुण्य 'virtue'.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्‌

3.2.90|3.2.90 some suNJaH|some suNJaH|some suNJaH 3.2.90|सोमे सुञः|सोमे सुञः ३.२.९०|३.२.९०|३.२.९० सोमे सुञः
The affix क्विप्‌ comes after the verb सु 'to press out juice' with the sense of past time, when the word सोम , in the Accusative -2nd case, is in composition.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्‌

3.2.91|3.2.91 agnau cheH|agnau cheH|agnau cheH 3.2.91|अग्नौ चेः|अग्नौ चेः ३.२.९१|३.२.९१|३.२.९१ अग्नौ चेः
The affix क्विप्‌ comes after the verb चि 'to collect' with the sense of past time, when the word अग्नि , in the Accusative -2nd case, is in composition.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्‌

3.2.92|3.2.92 karmaNyagnyaakhyaayaam|karmaNyagnyaakhyaayaam|karmaNyagnyaakhyaayaam 3.2.92|कर्मण्यग्न्याख्यायाम्|कर्मण्यग्न्याख्यायाम् ३.२.९२|३.२.९२|३.२.९२ कर्मण्यग्न्याख्यायाम्
In expressing an object the affix क्विप्‌ comes after the verb चि 'to collect' with the sense of past time when in composition with a word in the Accusative -2nd case, provided the word so formed is the name of fire.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्‌

3.2.93|3.2.93 karmaNiinirvikriyaH|karmaNiinirvikriyaH|karmaNiinirvikriyaH 3.2.93|कर्मणीनिर्विक्रियः|कर्मणीनिर्विक्रियः ३.२.९३|३.२.९३|३.२.९३ कर्मणीनिर्विक्रियः
The affix इनि comes after the compound verb विकृ 'to sell' in the sense of past time, when in composition with a word in the Accusative -2nd case.<br><br>Terms: इनि

3.2.94|3.2.94 dRsheH kvanip‌|dRsheH kvanip‌|dRsheH kvanip‌ 3.2.94|दृशेः क्वनिप्‌|दृशेः क्वनिप्‌ ३.२.९४|३.२.९४|३.२.९४ दृशेः क्वनिप्‌
The affix क्वनिप्‌ comes after the verb दृश् 'to see' in the sense of past time, when in composition with a word in the Accusative -2nd case.<br><br>Terms: क्वनिप्‌

3.2.95|3.2.95 raajani yudhikRNJaH|raajani yudhikRNJaH|raajani yudhikRNJaH 3.2.95|राजनि युधिकृञः|राजनि युधिकृञः ३.२.९५|३.२.९५|३.२.९५ राजनि युधिकृञः
The affix क्वनिप्‌ comes after the verbs युध 'to fight' and कृ 'to make' with a past signification when the word राजन् 'king' is in composition, in the Accusative -2nd case.<br><br>Terms: क्वनिप्‌

3.2.96|3.2.96 sahe cha|sahe cha|sahe cha 3.2.96|सहे च|सहे च ३.२.९६|३.२.९६|३.२.९६ सहे च
The affix क्वनिप्‌ comes after the verbs युध 'to fight' and कृ 'to make' with a past signification when the word सह 'with', is in composition.<br><br>Terms: क्वनिप्‌

3.2.97|3.2.97 saptamyaaM janerDaH|saptamyaaM janerDaH|saptamyaaM janerDaH 3.2.97|सप्तम्यां जनेर्डः|सप्तम्यां जनेर्डः ३.२.९७|३.२.९७|३.२.९७ सप्तम्यां जनेर्डः
The affix ड comes after the verb जन् 'to be produced', with a past signification, when the word, in composition with it is in the Locative -7th-case.<br><br>Terms: ड

3.2.98|3.2.98 pancamyaamajaatau|pancamyaamajaatau|pancamyaamajaatau 3.2.98|पञ्चम्यामजातौ|पञ्चम्यामजातौ ३.२.९८|३.२.९८|३.२.९८ पञ्चम्यामजातौ
The affix ड comes after the verb जन् 'to be produced', with a past signification, when the word, in composition with it is in the Ablative -5th case, which does not denote a genus.<br><br>Terms: ड

3.2.99|3.2.99 upasarge cha saMJNaayaam|upasarge cha saMJNaayaam|upasarge cha saMJNaayaam 3.2.99|उपसर्गे च संज्ञायाम्|उपसर्गे च संज्ञायाम् ३.२.९९|३.२.९९|३.२.९९ उपसर्गे च संज्ञायाम्
The affix ड comes after the verb जन् 'to be produced', with a past signification, when an उपसर्ग is in composition and when the sense is simply appellative.<br><br>Terms: ड

3.2.100|3.2.100 anau karmaNi|anau karmaNi|anau karmaNi 3.2.100|अनौ कर्मणि|अनौ कर्मणि ३.२.१००|३.२.१००|३.२.१०० अनौ कर्मणि
The affix ड comes after the verb जन् 'to be produced', with a past signification, when the root takes the preposition अनु and is compounded with a word in the Accusative -2nd case.<br><br>Terms: ड

3.2.101|3.2.101 anyeShvapi dRshyate|anyeShvapi dRshyate|anyeShvapi dRshyate 3.2.101|अन्येष्वपि दृश्यते|अन्येष्वपि दृश्यते ३.२.१०१|३.२.१०१|३.२.१०१ अन्येष्वपि दृश्यते
The affix ड is seen to come after the verb जन् 'to be produced', with a past signification,though it be in composition with other nouns, having cases other than those mentioned in the previous sūtras.<br><br>Terms: ड

3.2.102|3.2.102 niShThaa|niShThaa|niShThaa 3.2.102|निष्ठा|निष्ठा ३.२.१०२|३.२.१०२|३.२.१०२ निष्ठा
The affixes called निष्ठा come after a verbal root used in the sense of past time.<br><br>Terms: निष्ठा

3.2.103|3.2.103 suyajorNGvanip‌|suyajorNGvanip‌|suyajorNGvanip‌ 3.2.103|सुयजोर्ङ्वनिप्‌|सुयजोर्ङ्वनिप्‌ ३.२.१०३|३.२.१०३|३.२.१०३ सुयजोर्ङ्वनिप्‌
The affix ङ्वनिप् comes after the verbs सु 'to press out or extract juice' and यज् 'to sacrifice', with a past signification.<br><br>Terms: ङ्वनिप्

3.2.104|3.2.104 jiiryateratRn|jiiryateratRn|jiiryateratRn 3.2.104|जीर्यतेरतृन्|जीर्यतेरतृन् ३.२.१०४|३.२.१०४|३.२.१०४ जीर्यतेरतृन्
The affix अतृन् comes after the verb जृ 'to grow old' with the sense of past time.<br><br>Terms: अतृन्

3.2.105|3.2.105 Chandasi liT|Chandasi liT|Chandasi liT 3.2.105|छन्दसि लिट्|छन्दसि लिट् ३.२.१०५|३.२.१०५|३.२.१०५ छन्दसि लिट्
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the affix लिट् (Perfect Tense) comes after a verb with a past signification.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.106|3.2.106 liTaH kaanajvaa|liTaH kaanajvaa|liTaH kaanajvaa 3.2.106|लिटः कानज्वा|लिटः कानज्वा ३.२.१०६|३.२.१०६|३.२.१०६ लिटः कानज्वा
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the affix लिट् (Perfect Tense) is optionally replaced by the affix कानच्।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.107|3.2.107 kvasushcha|kvasushcha|kvasushcha 3.2.107|क्वसुश्च|क्वसुश्च ३.२.१०७|३.२.१०७|३.२.१०७ क्वसुश्च
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the affix क्वसु is optionally the substitute for लिट् ।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.108|3.2.108 bhaaShaayaaM sadavasashruvaH|bhaaShaayaaM sadavasashruvaH|bhaaShaayaaM sadavasashruvaH 3.2.108|भाषायां सदवसश्रुवः|भाषायां सदवसश्रुवः ३.२.१०८|३.२.१०८|३.२.१०८ भाषायां सदवसश्रुवः
In modern Sanskṛt the affix क्वसु optionally replaces लिट् (Perfect Tense) aafter the verbs सद् , वस् and श्रु with a past signification.<br><br>Terms: क्वसु

3.2.109|3.2.109 upeyivaananaashvaananuuchaanashcha|upeyivaananaashvaananuuchaanashcha|upeyivaananaashvaananuuchaanashcha 3.2.109|उपेयिवाननाश्वाननूचानश्च|उपेयिवाननाश्वाननूचानश्च ३.२.१०९|३.२.१०९|३.२.१०९ उपेयिवाननाश्वाननूचानश्च
The forms उपेयिवान् , नाश्वान् , नूचान् are irregularly formed.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.2.110|3.2.110 luNG|luNG|luNG 3.2.110|लुङ्|लुङ् ३.२.११०|३.२.११०|३.२.११० लुङ्
The affix लुङ् (Aorist) comes after the verb in the sense of past time.<br><br>Terms: लुङ्

3.2.111|3.2.111 anadyatane laNG|anadyatane laNG|anadyatane laNG 3.2.111|अनद्यतने लङ्|अनद्यतने लङ् ३.२.१११|३.२.१११|३.२.१११ अनद्यतने लङ्
The affix लुङ् (Aorist) comes after a verbal root used in the sense of past before the commencement of the current day.<br><br>Terms: लुङ्

3.2.112|3.2.112 abhiJNaavachane lRT|abhiJNaavachane lRT|abhiJNaavachane lRT 3.2.112|अभिज्ञावचने लृट्|अभिज्ञावचने लृट् ३.२.११२|३.२.११२|३.२.११२ अभिज्ञावचने लृट्
When a word implying 'recollection' is in connection with it, a verb takes the affix लृट् (2nd Future) in the sense of the past before the commencement of the present day.<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.2.113|3.2.113 na yadi|na yadi|na yadi 3.2.113|न यदि|न यदि ३.२.११३|३.२.११३|३.२.११३ न यदि
The affix लृट् (2nd Future) is not applied in the sense of the past when the उपपद denoting recollection has in connection with it the particle यत्।<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.2.114|3.2.114 vibhaaShaa saakaankShe|vibhaaShaa saakaankShe|vibhaaShaa saakaankShe 3.2.114|विभाषा साकाङ्क्षे|विभाषा साकाङ्क्षे ३.२.११४|३.२.११४|३.२.११४ विभाषा साकाङ्क्षे
The affix लृट् (2nd Future) is optionally applied in the sense of the past, when a word implying 'recollection' is in connection with it and whether such a word has the particle यत् or is used simply; provided that the two verbs, occuring in the same complex sentence, are also connected together, that each is necessary to the other , to complete the sense of the speaker.<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.2.115|3.2.115 paroxe liT|paroxe liT|paroxe liT 3.2.115|परोक्षे लिट्|परोक्षे लिट् ३.२.११५|३.२.११५|३.२.११५ परोक्षे लिट्
The affix लिट् (Perfect Tense) comes after the verb in the sense of the past before the commencement of the current dayand unperceived by the narrator.<br><br>Terms: लिट्

3.2.116|3.2.116 hashashvatorlaNG cha|hashashvatorlaNG cha|hashashvatorlaNG cha 3.2.116|हशश्वतोर्लङ् च|हशश्वतोर्लङ् च ३.२.११६|३.२.११६|३.२.११६ हशश्वतोर्लङ् च
And the affix लङ् (Imperfect Tense) comes after the verb when the particles ह and शश्वत are in connection with it and when the verb denotes past action unperceived by the speaker and before the commencement of the current day.<br><br>Terms: लङ्

3.2.117|3.2.117 prashne chaasannakaale|prashne chaasannakaale|prashne chaasannakaale 3.2.117|प्रश्ने चासन्नकाले|प्रश्ने चासन्नकाले ३.२.११७|३.२.११७|३.२.११७ प्रश्ने चासन्नकाले
The affixes लङ् (Imperfect Tense) and लिट् (Perfect Tense) come after a verb (in expressing a past time not belonging to the current day and unperceived by the speaker) when the past referred to is recent and the sentence is interrogative.<br><br>Terms: लङ् and लिट्

3.2.118|3.2.118 laT sme|laT sme|laT sme 3.2.118|लट् स्मे|लट् स्मे ३.२.११८|३.२.११८|३.२.११८ लट् स्मे
The affix लट् (Present Tense) comes after a verb when the particle स्म is in connection with it (and denotes a past time not belonging to the current day and unperceived by the speaker). Note : This debars लिट् (Perfect Tense) .<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.119|3.2.119 aparoxe cha|aparoxe cha|aparoxe cha 3.2.119|अपरोक्षे च|अपरोक्षे च ३.२.११९|३.२.११९|३.२.११९ अपरोक्षे च
The affix लट् (Present Tense) comes after a verb when the particle स्म is in connection with it and denotes a past action not belonging to the current day and when the action is perceived by the agent.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.120|3.2.120 nanau pRShTaprativachane|nanau pRShTaprativachane|nanau pRShTaprativachane 3.2.120|ननौ पृष्टप्रतिवचने|ननौ पृष्टप्रतिवचने ३.२.१२०|३.२.१२०|३.२.१२० ननौ पृष्टप्रतिवचने
The affix लट् (Present Tense) is used after a verb in denoting a past action when the word ननु is in connection with it and an answer is givento the question.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.121|3.2.121 nanvorvibhaaShaa|nanvorvibhaaShaa|nanvorvibhaaShaa 3.2.121|नन्वोर्विभाषा|नन्वोर्विभाषा ३.२.१२१|३.२.१२१|३.२.१२१ नन्वोर्विभाषा
The affix लट् (Present Tense) comes optionally after a verb in denoting past time, in reply to an interrogation, when the words न 'not' and नु 'what of that' are in connection with it.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.122|3.2.122 puri luNG chaasme|puri luNG chaasme|puri luNG chaasme 3.2.122|पुरि लुङ् चास्मे|पुरि लुङ् चास्मे ३.२.१२२|३.२.१२२|३.२.१२२ पुरि लुङ् चास्मे
Optionally the affixes लुङ् (Aorist) and लट् (Present Tense) come after a verb in denoting past time not belonging to the current day, when the word पुरा is used in the sentence, provided that the word स्म is not used.<br><br>Terms: लुङ् and लट्

3.2.123|3.2.123 vartamaane laँT|vartamaane laँT|vartamaane laँT 3.2.123|वर्तमाने लँट्|वर्तमाने लँट् ३.२.१२३|३.२.१२३|३.२.१२३ वर्तमाने लँट्
The affix लट् (Present Tense) comes after a verb when denoting a present action.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.124|3.2.124 laTaH shatRshaanachaavaprathamaasamaanaadhikaraNe|laTaH shatRshaanachaavaprathamaasamaanaadhikaraNe|laTaH shatRshaanachaavaprathamaasamaanaadhikaraNe 3.2.124|लटः शतृशानचावप्रथमासमानाधिकरणे|लटः शतृशानचावप्रथमासमानाधिकरणे ३.२.१२४|३.२.१२४|३.२.१२४ लटः शतृशानचावप्रथमासमानाधिकरणे
The affixes शतृ and शानच् are substitutes of लट् (Present Tense) when agreeing with what does not end with the 1st (Nominative Case) case-affix.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.125|3.2.125 sambodhane cha|sambodhane cha|sambodhane cha 3.2.125|सम्बोधने च|सम्बोधने च ३.२.१२५|३.२.१२५|३.२.१२५ सम्बोधने च
The affixes शतृ and शानच् are substitutes of लट् (Present Tense) even when agreeing with what ends with a 1st (Nominative Case) case-affix, provided that it is in the Vocative Case.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.126|3.2.126 laxaNahetvoH kriyaayaaH|laxaNahetvoH kriyaayaaH|laxaNahetvoH kriyaayaaH 3.2.126|लक्षणहेत्वोः क्रियायाः|लक्षणहेत्वोः क्रियायाः ३.२.१२६|३.२.१२६|३.२.१२६ लक्षणहेत्वोः क्रियायाः
The affixes शतृ and शानच् are substitutes of लट् (Present Tense) and come after a verb in expressing an attendent circumstance or characteristic and the cause of an action.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.2.127|3.2.127 tau sat‌|tau sat‌|tau sat‌ 3.2.127|तौ सत्‌|तौ सत्‌ ३.२.१२७|३.२.१२७|३.२.१२७ तौ सत्‌
These two - शतृ and शानच् are called सत्‌।<br><br>Terms: शतृ and शानच्

3.2.128|3.2.128 puuNGyajoH shaanan|puuNGyajoH shaanan|puuNGyajoH shaanan 3.2.128|पूङ्यजोः शानन्|पूङ्यजोः शानन् ३.२.१२८|३.२.१२८|३.२.१२८ पूङ्यजोः शानन्
The affix शानन् comes after the verbs पू 'to purify' and यज् 'to sacrifice'.<br><br>Terms: शानन्

3.2.129|3.2.129 taachChiilyavayovachanashaktiShu chaanash|taachChiilyavayovachanashaktiShu chaanash|taachChiilyavayovachanashaktiShu chaanash 3.2.129|ताच्छील्यवयोवचनशक्तिषु चानश्|ताच्छील्यवयोवचनशक्तिषु चानश् ३.२.१२९|३.२.१२९|३.२.१२९ ताच्छील्यवयोवचनशक्तिषु चानश्
The affix चानश् comes after a verb in expressing 'habit', standard of age' and 'inability'.<br><br>Terms: चानश्

3.2.130|3.2.130 iNGdhaaryoH shatrakRchChriNi|iNGdhaaryoH shatrakRchChriNi|iNGdhaaryoH shatrakRchChriNi 3.2.130|इङ्धार्योः शत्रकृच्छ्रिणि|इङ्धार्योः शत्रकृच्छ्रिणि ३.२.१३०|३.२.१३०|३.२.१३० इङ्धार्योः शत्रकृच्छ्रिणि
The affix शतृ comes after the verb इङ् 'to go' and धारि 'to hold' in denoting that the agent does the action without trouble.<br><br>Terms: शतृ

3.2.131|3.2.131 dviSho.amitre|dviSho.amitre|dviSho.amitre 3.2.131|द्विषोऽमित्रे|द्विषोऽमित्रे ३.२.१३१|३.२.१३१|३.२.१३१ द्विषोऽमित्रे
The affix शतृ comes after the verb द्विष् when the agent indicated means 'an enemy'.<br><br>Terms: शतृ

3.2.132|3.2.132 suNJo yaJNasaMyoge|suNJo yaJNasaMyoge|suNJo yaJNasaMyoge 3.2.132|सुञो यज्ञसंयोगे|सुञो यज्ञसंयोगे ३.२.१३२|३.२.१३२|३.२.१३२ सुञो यज्ञसंयोगे
The affix शतृ comes after the verb सु 'to press out or extract juice' when the sense is that of association with sacrifice.<br><br>Terms: शतृ

3.2.133|3.2.133 arhaH puujaayaam|arhaH puujaayaam|arhaH puujaayaam 3.2.133|अर्हः पूजायाम्|अर्हः पूजायाम् ३.२.१३३|३.२.१३३|३.२.१३३ अर्हः पूजायाम्
The affix शतृ comes after the verb अर्ह in expressing praise.<br><br>Terms: शतृ

3.2.134|3.2.134 aakvestachChiilataddharmatatsaadhukaariShu|aakvestachChiilataddharmatatsaadhukaariShu|aakvestachChiilataddharmatatsaadhukaariShu 3.2.134|आक्वेस्तच्छीलतद्धर्मतत्साधुकारिषु|आक्वेस्तच्छीलतद्धर्मतत्साधुकारिषु ३.२.१३४|३.२.१३४|३.२.१३४ आक्वेस्तच्छीलतद्धर्मतत्साधुकारिषु
From this sūtra as far as क्विप् in sūtra ३.४.१७७ (inclusive), the affixes that we shall treat of, are to be understood in the sense of agents having such a habit or nature or having skill in such and such action.<br><br>Terms: अधिकार

3.2.135|3.2.135 tRn|tRn|tRn 3.2.135|तृन्|तृन् ३.२.१३५|३.२.१३५|३.२.१३५ तृन्
The affix तृन् comes after all verbs in the sense of 'agents having such a habit etc.'.<br><br>Terms: तृन्

3.2.136|3.2.136 alaMkRNJniraakRNJprajanotpachotpatonmadaruchyapatrapavRtuvRdhusahachara iShNuch|alaMkRNJniraakRNJprajanotpachotpatonmadaruchyapatrapavRtuvRdhusahachara iShNuch|alaMkRNJniraakRNJprajanotpachotpatonmadaruchyapatrapavRtuvRdhusahachara iShNuch 3.2.136|अलंकृञ्निराकृञ्प्रजनोत्पचोत्पतोन्मदरुच्यपत्रपवृतुवृधुसहचर इष्णुच्|अलंकृञ्निराकृञ्प्रजनोत्पचोत्पतोन्मदरुच्यपत्रपवृतुवृधुसहचर इष्णुच् ३.२.१३६|३.२.१३६|३.२.१३६ अलंकृञ्निराकृञ्प्रजनोत्पचोत्पतोन्मदरुच्यपत्रपवृतुवृधुसहचर इष्णुच्
The affix इष्णुच् comes after following verbs in the sense of 'agents having such a habit etc.' - 1. अलंकृ 'to adorn' 2. ञ्निराकृ 'to expell' 3. प्रजन् 'to be born' 4. उत्पच् 'to be ripe' 5. उत्पत् 'to fly' 6. उन्मद् 'to be mad' 7. रुच् 'to shine' 8. अपत्रप् 'to be ashamed' 9. वृत् 'to move' 10. वृध् 'to grow 12. सह 'to bear' 13. चर् 'to walk'.<br><br>Terms: इष्णुच्

3.2.137|3.2.137 NeshChandasi|NeshChandasi|NeshChandasi 3.2.137|णेश्छन्दसि|णेश्छन्दसि ३.२.१३७|३.२.१३७|३.२.१३७ णेश्छन्दसि
The affix इष्णुच् in the sense of 'the agent having such a habit etc.' comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the verb that ends in the causative णि।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस् इष्णुच्

3.2.138|3.2.138 bhuvashcha|bhuvashcha|bhuvashcha 3.2.138|भुवश्च|भुवश्च ३.२.१३८|३.२.१३८|३.२.१३८ भुवश्च
The affix इष्णुच् in the sense of 'the agent having such a habit etc.' comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the verb भू 'to be' etc.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस् इष्णुच्

3.2.139|3.2.139 glaajisthashcha gsnuH|glaajisthashcha gsnuH|glaajisthashcha gsnuH 3.2.139|ग्लाजिस्थश्च ग्स्नुः|ग्लाजिस्थश्च ग्स्नुः ३.२.१३९|३.२.१३९|३.२.१३९ ग्लाजिस्थश्च ग्स्नुः
The affix क्स्नु comes after the following verbs in the sense of 'the agent having such a habit etc.' viz. - 1. ग्ला 'to be weary' 2. जि 'to conquer' 3. स्था 'to stand', as well as after भू 'to be'.<br><br>Terms: क्स्नु

3.2.140|3.2.140 trasigRdhidhRShixipeH knuH|trasigRdhidhRShixipeH knuH|trasigRdhidhRShixipeH knuH 3.2.140|त्रसिगृधिधृषिक्षिपेः क्नुः|त्रसिगृधिधृषिक्षिपेः क्नुः ३.२.१४०|३.२.१४०|३.२.१४० त्रसिगृधिधृषिक्षिपेः क्नुः
The affix क्नु comes after the verbs - 1. त्रस् 'to tremble' 2. गृध् 'to be greedy' 3. धृष् 'to be bold' 4. क्षिप् 'to throw' in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.'.<br><br>Terms: क्नुः

3.2.141|3.2.141 shamityaShTaabhyo ghinuN|shamityaShTaabhyo ghinuN|shamityaShTaabhyo ghinuN 3.2.141|शमित्यष्टाभ्यो घिनुण्|शमित्यष्टाभ्यो घिनुण् ३.२.१४१|३.२.१४१|३.२.१४१ शमित्यष्टाभ्यो घिनुण्
The affix घिनुण् comes after the 8 verbs beginning with शम् 'to be calm' in the sense of 'the agent having such a habit etc.'.<br><br>Terms: घिनुण्

