3.2.168|3.2.168 sanaashaMsabhixa uH|sanaashaMsabhixa uH|sanaashaMsabhixa uH 3.2.168|सनाशंसभिक्ष उः|सनाशंसभिक्ष उः ३.२.१६८|३.२.१६८|३.२.१६८ सनाशंसभिक्ष उः
The affix उ comes after the roots that have taken the affix सन् and after all the verbs आशंस् 'to wish' and भिक्ष 'to beg' in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.'.<br><br>Terms: उ

3.2.169|3.2.169 vindurichChuH|vindurichChuH|vindurichChuH 3.2.169|विन्दुरिच्छुः|विन्दुरिच्छुः ३.२.१६९|३.२.१६९|३.२.१६९ विन्दुरिच्छुः
The words विन्दु and इच्छु are irregularly formed by the addition of the affix उ , in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular उ

3.2.170|3.2.170 kyaachChandasi|kyaachChandasi|kyaachChandasi 3.2.170|क्याच्छन्दसि|क्याच्छन्दसि ३.२.१७०|३.२.१७०|३.२.१७० क्याच्छन्दसि
The affix उ comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the roots that have taken the Denominative affix क्य in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.'.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.171|3.2.171 aadRgamahanajanaH kikinau liT cha|aadRgamahanajanaH kikinau liT cha|aadRgamahanajanaH kikinau liT cha 3.2.171|आदृगमहनजनः किकिनौ लिट् च|आदृगमहनजनः किकिनौ लिट् च ३.२.१७१|३.२.१७१|३.२.१७१ आदृगमहनजनः किकिनौ लिट् च
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the affixes कि and किन् in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' come after the verbs that end in long आ or long or short ऋ and after the verbs 1. गम् 'to go' 2. हन् 'to kill' 3. जन् 'to be produced' and these affixes operate likek लिट् (Perfect Tense) causing reduplication of the root.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.2.172|3.2.172 svapitRShornajiNG|svapitRShornajiNG|svapitRShornajiNG 3.2.172|स्वपितृषोर्नजिङ्|स्वपितृषोर्नजिङ् ३.२.१७२|३.२.१७२|३.२.१७२ स्वपितृषोर्नजिङ्
The affix नजिङ् comes, in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' after the verbs स्वप् 'to sleep' and तृष् 'to be thirsty'.<br><br>Terms: नजिङ्

3.2.173|3.2.173 shRRvandyoraaruH|shRRvandyoraaruH|shRRvandyoraaruH 3.2.173|शॄवन्द्योरारुः|शॄवन्द्योरारुः ३.२.१७३|३.२.१७३|३.२.१७३ शॄवन्द्योरारुः
The affix आरु comes, in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' after the verbs शॄ 'to to injure' and वन्द् 'to praise, to salute'.<br><br>Terms: आरु

3.2.174|3.2.174 bhiyaH kruklukanau|bhiyaH kruklukanau|bhiyaH kruklukanau 3.2.174|भियः क्रुक्लुकनौ|भियः क्रुक्लुकनौ ३.२.१७४|३.२.१७४|३.२.१७४ भियः क्रुक्लुकनौ
The affixes क्रु and क्लुकन come in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' after the verb भी 'to fear'.<br><br>Terms: क्रु and क्लुकन

3.2.175|3.2.175 stheshabhaasapisakaso varach|stheshabhaasapisakaso varach|stheshabhaasapisakaso varach 3.2.175|स्थेशभासपिसकसो वरच्|स्थेशभासपिसकसो वरच् ३.२.१७५|३.२.१७५|३.२.१७५ स्थेशभासपिसकसो वरच्
The affix वरच् comes, in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' after the verbs 1. स्था 'to stand' 2. ईश 'to rule' 3. भास् 'to shine' 4. पिस् 'to go' 5. कस् 'to go'.<br><br>Terms: वरच्

3.2.176|3.2.176 yashcha yaNGaH|yashcha yaNGaH|yashcha yaNGaH 3.2.176|यश्च यङः|यश्च यङः ३.२.१७६|३.२.१७६|३.२.१७६ यश्च यङः
The affix वरच् in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' comes after the verb या when it ends with the affix यङ्।<br><br>Terms: वरच्

3.2.177|3.2.177 bhraajabhaasadhurvidyutorjipRRjugraavastuvaH kvip‌|bhraajabhaasadhurvidyutorjipRRjugraavastuvaH kvip‌|bhraajabhaasadhurvidyutorjipRRjugraavastuvaH kvip‌ 3.2.177|भ्राजभासधुर्विद्युतोर्जिपॄजुग्रावस्तुवः क्विप्‌|भ्राजभासधुर्विद्युतोर्जिपॄजुग्रावस्तुवः क्विप्‌ ३.२.१७७|३.२.१७७|३.२.१७७ भ्राजभासधुर्विद्युतोर्जिपॄजुग्रावस्तुवः क्विप्‌
The affix क्विप् comes in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' after the verbs 1. भ्राज 'to shine' 2. भास् 'to shine' 3. धुर्व 'to injure' 4. द्युत् 'to shine' 5. ऊर्ज 'to be strong' 6. पॄ 'to fill' 7. जु 'to move rapdily' 8. स्तु 'to praise', when preceded by the word ग्रवन् 'a stone'.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्

3.2.178|3.2.178 anyebhyo.api dRshyate|anyebhyo.api dRshyate|anyebhyo.api dRshyate 3.2.178|अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यते|अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यते ३.२.१७८|३.२.१७८|३.२.१७८ अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यते
The affix क्विप् comes in the sense of 'agent having such a habit etc.' after the verbs other than those seen above.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्

3.2.179|3.2.179 bhuvaH saMJNaa.antarayoH|bhuvaH saMJNaa.antarayoH|bhuvaH saMJNaa.antarayoH 3.2.179|भुवः संज्ञाऽन्तरयोः|भुवः संज्ञाऽन्तरयोः ३.२.१७९|३.२.१७९|३.२.१७९ भुवः संज्ञाऽन्तरयोः
The affix क्विप् comes after the verb भू 'to be' when the word so formed denotes a name or surety.<br><br>Terms: क्विप्

3.2.180|3.2.180 viprasambhyo DvasaMJNaayaam|viprasambhyo DvasaMJNaayaam|viprasambhyo DvasaMJNaayaam 3.2.180|विप्रसम्भ्यो ड्वसंज्ञायाम्|विप्रसम्भ्यो ड्वसंज्ञायाम् ३.२.१८०|३.२.१८०|३.२.१८० विप्रसम्भ्यो ड्वसंज्ञायाम्
The affix डु comes after the verb भू 'to be' when it is preceded by the उपसर्ग वि , प्र and सम् provided that the word to be formed does not mean an appellative.<br><br>Terms: डु

3.2.181|3.2.181 dhaH karmaNi ShTran|dhaH karmaNi ShTran|dhaH karmaNi ShTran 3.2.181|धः कर्मणि ष्ट्रन्|धः कर्मणि ष्ट्रन् ३.२.१८१|३.२.१८१|३.२.१८१ धः कर्मणि ष्ट्रन्
The affix ष्ट्रन् comes, in denoting the object after the verb धा 'to feed'.<br><br>Terms: ष्ट्रन्

3.2.182|3.2.182 daamniishasayuyujastutudasisichamihapatadashanahaH karaNe|daamniishasayuyujastutudasisichamihapatadashanahaH karaNe|daamniishasayuyujastutudasisichamihapatadashanahaH karaNe 3.2.182|दाम्नीशसयुयुजस्तुतुदसिसिचमिहपतदशनहः करणे|दाम्नीशसयुयुजस्तुतुदसिसिचमिहपतदशनहः करणे ३.२.१८२|३.२.१८२|३.२.१८२ दाम्नीशसयुयुजस्तुतुदसिसिचमिहपतदशनहः करणे
The affix ष्ट्रन् with in the sense of instrument, comes after the verbs 1. दाप 'to cut' 2. नी 'to lead' 3. शस् 'to hurt' 4. यु 'to join' 5. युज् 'to join' 6. स्तु 'to praise' 7. तुद् 'to inflict pain' 8. सि 'to bind' 9. सिच् 'to sprinkle' 10. मिह् 'to urine' 11. पत् 'to fall' 12. दश् 'to bite' 13. नह् 'to bind'<br><br>Terms: ष्ट्रन्

3.2.183|3.2.183 halasuukarayoH puvaH|halasuukarayoH puvaH|halasuukarayoH puvaH 3.2.183|हलसूकरयोः पुवः|हलसूकरयोः पुवः ३.२.१८३|३.२.१८३|३.२.१८३ हलसूकरयोः पुवः
The affix ष्ट्रन् is used after the verb पू 'to purify' with the sense of instrument when denoting a member of the body of a plough or of a hog.<br><br>Terms: ष्ट्रन्

3.2.184|3.2.184 artiluudhuusuukhanasahachara itraH|artiluudhuusuukhanasahachara itraH|artiluudhuusuukhanasahachara itraH 3.2.184|अर्तिलूधूसूखनसहचर इत्रः|अर्तिलूधूसूखनसहचर इत्रः ३.२.१८४|३.२.१८४|३.२.१८४ अर्तिलूधूसूखनसहचर इत्रः
The affix इत्र comes after the verbs 1. ऋ 'to go' 2. लू 'to cut' 3. धू 'to shake' 4. सू 'to bring forth' 5. खन् 'to dig' 6. सह् 'to bear' 7. चर् 'to go' , with the sense of instrument.<br><br>Terms: इत्र

3.2.185|3.2.185 puvaH saMJNaayaam|puvaH saMJNaayaam|puvaH saMJNaayaam 3.2.185|पुवः संज्ञायाम्|पुवः संज्ञायाम् ३.२.१८५|३.२.१८५|३.२.१८५ पुवः संज्ञायाम्
The affix इत्र comes after the verb पू 'to purify' with the sense of the agent so expressed being the instrument when the sense of the complete word is simply appellative and not descriptive.<br><br>Terms: इत्र

3.2.186|3.2.186 kartari charShidevatayoH|kartari charShidevatayoH|kartari charShidevatayoH 3.2.186|कर्तरि चर्षिदेवतयोः|कर्तरि चर्षिदेवतयोः ३.२.१८६|३.२.१८६|३.२.१८६ कर्तरि चर्षिदेवतयोः
The affix इत्र comes after the verb पू 'to purify' with the sense of the agent or instrument when it is respectively used in connection with a sage or a deity.<br><br>Terms: इत्र

3.2.187|3.2.187 NJiitaH ktaH|NJiitaH ktaH|NJiitaH ktaH 3.2.187|ञीतः क्तः|ञीतः क्तः ३.२.१८७|३.२.१८७|३.२.१८७ ञीतः क्तः
The verbal roots marked with an indicatory ञि , take the affix क्त , in denoting the present time.<br><br>Terms: क्त

3.2.188|3.2.188 matibuddhipuujaarthebhyashcha|matibuddhipuujaarthebhyashcha|matibuddhipuujaarthebhyashcha 3.2.188|मतिबुद्धिपूजार्थेभ्यश्च|मतिबुद्धिपूजार्थेभ्यश्च ३.२.१८८|३.२.१८८|३.२.१८८ मतिबुद्धिपूजार्थेभ्यश्च
And after the roots denoting inclination, understanding, or respect, the affix क्त is used with the force of the present<br><br>Terms: क्त

3.3.1|3.3.1 uNaadayo bahulam|uNaadayo bahulam|uNaadayo bahulam 3.3.1|उणादयो बहुलम्|उणादयो बहुलम् ३.३.१|३.३.१|३.३.१ उणादयो बहुलम्
The affixes उण् and the rest with the force of the present and with a sense simply appellative are attached diversely.<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.2|3.3.2 bhuute.api dRshyante|bhuute.api dRshyante|bhuute.api dRshyante 3.3.2|भूतेऽपि दृश्यन्ते|भूतेऽपि दृश्यन्ते ३.३.२|३.३.२|३.३.२ भूतेऽपि दृश्यन्ते
The उणादि affixes are seen also attached with the force of the past time.<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.3|3.3.3 bhaviShyati gamyaadayaH|bhaviShyati gamyaadayaH|bhaviShyati gamyaadayaH 3.3.3|भविष्यति गम्यादयः|भविष्यति गम्यादयः ३.३.३|३.३.३|३.३.३ भविष्यति गम्यादयः
The words गामि etc. are valid forms having the sense of the future time.<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.4|3.3.4 yaavatpuraanipaatayorlaT|yaavatpuraanipaatayorlaT|yaavatpuraanipaatayorlaT 3.3.4|यावत्पुरानिपातयोर्लट्|यावत्पुरानिपातयोर्लट् ३.३.४|३.३.४|३.३.४ यावत्पुरानिपातयोर्लट्
The affix लट् (Present Tense) comes after a root with the force of futurity when it has in construction with it the particles यावत् and पुरा।<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.5|3.3.5 vibhaaShaa kadaakarhyoH|vibhaaShaa kadaakarhyoH|vibhaaShaa kadaakarhyoH 3.3.5|विभाषा कदाकर्ह्योः|विभाषा कदाकर्ह्योः ३.३.५|३.३.५|३.३.५ विभाषा कदाकर्ह्योः
The affix लट् (Present Tense) is optionally used after a root with the force of the futurity when it has in construction with it the adverbs कदा and कर्हि।<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.6|3.3.6 kiMvRtte lipsaayaam|kiMvRtte lipsaayaam|kiMvRtte lipsaayaam 3.3.6|किंवृत्ते लिप्सायाम्|किंवृत्ते लिप्सायाम् ३.३.६|३.३.६|३.३.६ किंवृत्ते लिप्सायाम्
When the word किम् or its derivatives are in construction with a verb, the affix लट् (Present Tense) is used optionally after a root, in denoting future time, provided that the sentences expresses a desire of gaining on the part of the speaker.<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.7|3.3.7 lipsyamaanasiddhau cha|lipsyamaanasiddhau cha|lipsyamaanasiddhau cha 3.3.7|लिप्स्यमानसिद्धौ च|लिप्स्यमानसिद्धौ च ३.३.७|३.३.७|३.३.७ लिप्स्यमानसिद्धौ च
And when the success, that would accrue to another by fulfilling the desire of the speaker, is indicated in a sentence, the present tense may optionally be used with the force of the futurity.<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.8|3.3.8 loDarthalaxaNe cha|loDarthalaxaNe cha|loDarthalaxaNe cha 3.3.8|लोडर्थलक्षणे च|लोडर्थलक्षणे च ३.३.८|३.३.८|३.३.८ लोडर्थलक्षणे च
The affix लट् (Present Tense) is optionally used with the force of futurity after that root, which is in a conditional sentence, is the condition precedent for the action indicated by another verb having the sense of the imperative mood.<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.9|3.3.9 liNG chordhvamauhuurtike|liNG chordhvamauhuurtike|liNG chordhvamauhuurtike 3.3.9|लिङ् चोर्ध्वमौहूर्तिके|लिङ् चोर्ध्वमौहूर्तिके ३.३.९|३.३.९|३.३.९ लिङ् चोर्ध्वमौहूर्तिके
The लट् (Present Tense) or the लिङ् (Potential) is used under similar conditions in denoting futurity, when the future time is future by a मूहूर्त (= 48 minutes).<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.3.10|3.3.10 tumunNvulau kriyaayaaM kriyaarthaayaam‌|tumunNvulau kriyaayaaM kriyaarthaayaam‌|tumunNvulau kriyaayaaM kriyaarthaayaam‌ 3.3.10|तुमुन्ण्वुलौ क्रियायां क्रियार्थायाम्‌|तुमुन्ण्वुलौ क्रियायां क्रियार्थायाम्‌ ३.३.१०|३.३.१०|३.३.१० तुमुन्ण्वुलौ क्रियायां क्रियार्थायाम्‌
The affixes तुमुन् and ण्वुल् are placed after a verbal root with the force of the future when the word in construction therewith is another verb, denoting an action performed for the sake of the (future) action.<br><br>Terms: तुमुन् and ण्वुल्

3.3.11|3.3.11 bhaavavachanaashcha|bhaavavachanaashcha|bhaavavachanaashcha 3.3.11|भाववचनाश्च|भाववचनाश्च ३.३.११|३.३.११|३.३.११ भाववचनाश्च
And the affixes that are ordained to come after a root with the force of denoting the mere action of the verb, such as धञ् etc. -- लोहितादिडाज्भ्यः क्यष् ३.१.३, have also the force of the future, when the word in construction therewith is another verb denoting an action performed for the sake of the future action.<br><br>Terms: धञ्

3.3.12|3.3.12 aN karmaNi cha|aN karmaNi cha|aN karmaNi cha 3.3.12|अण् कर्मणि च|अण् कर्मणि च ३.३.१२|३.३.१२|३.३.१२ अण् कर्मणि च
The affix अण् comes after a root with the force of the future when the word in construction with it is in the Accusative -2nd case and when the action is performed for the sake of another action.<br><br>Terms: अण्

3.3.13|3.3.13 lRT sheShe cha|lRT sheShe cha|lRT sheShe cha 3.3.13|लृट् शेषे च|लृट् शेषे च ३.३.१३|३.३.१३|३.३.१३ लृट् शेषे च
The affix लृट् (2nd Future) is used after a verb in the remaining cases where futurity pure and simple is indicated and also where there is construction with it another verb denoting an action performed for the sake of the future action.<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.3.14|3.3.14 lRTaH sad vaa|lRTaH sad vaa|lRTaH sad vaa 3.3.14|लृटः सद् वा|लृटः सद् वा ३.३.१४|३.३.१४|३.३.१४ लृटः सद् वा
The affixes called सत् i.e. शतृ and शानच् are optionally the substitutes of लृट् (2nd Future).<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.3.15|3.3.15 anadyatane luT|anadyatane luT|anadyatane luT 3.3.15|अनद्यतने लुट्|अनद्यतने लुट् ३.३.१५|३.३.१५|३.३.१५ अनद्यतने लुट्
The affix लुट् (1st Future) comes after a verbal root in the sense of what will happen but not in the course of the current day.<br><br>Terms: लुट्

3.3.16|3.3.16 padarujavishaspRsho ghaNJ|padarujavishaspRsho ghaNJ|padarujavishaspRsho ghaNJ 3.3.16|पदरुजविशस्पृशो घञ्|पदरुजविशस्पृशो घञ् ३.३.१६|३.३.१६|३.३.१६ पदरुजविशस्पृशो घञ्
The affix घञ् comes after the roots 1. पद् 'to pace' 2. रुज् 'to pain 3. विश् 'to enter' 4. स्पृश् 'to touch'.<br><br>Terms: घञ्

3.3.17|3.3.17 sR sthire|sR sthire|sR sthire 3.3.17|सृ स्थिरे|सृ स्थिरे ३.३.१७|३.३.१७|३.३.१७ सृ स्थिरे
