3.3.56|3.3.56 erach|erach|erach 3.3.56|एरच्|एरच् ३.३.५६|३.३.५६|३.३.५६ एरच्
The affix अच् comes after a root ending in इ or ई (when mere action is denoted or when the sense is that of an appellative, the word being related to the verb from which its name is deduced, but not as an agent).<br><br>Terms: अच्

3.3.57|3.3.57 Rdorap‌|Rdorap‌|Rdorap‌ 3.3.57|ऋदोरप्‌|ऋदोरप्‌ ३.३.५७|३.३.५७|३.३.५७ ऋदोरप्‌
After a root ending in long ॠ , short उ or long ऊ , there is the affix अप्।<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.58|3.3.58 grahavRdRnishchigamashcha|grahavRdRnishchigamashcha|grahavRdRnishchigamashcha 3.3.58|ग्रहवृदृनिश्चिगमश्च|ग्रहवृदृनिश्चिगमश्च ३.३.५८|३.३.५८|३.३.५८ ग्रहवृदृनिश्चिगमश्च
The affix अप् comes after the verbs 1. ग्रह् 'to seize' 2. वृ 'to choose' 3. दृ 4. निश्चि 5. गम् 'to go'.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.59|3.3.59 upasarge.adaH|upasarge.adaH|upasarge.adaH 3.3.59|उपसर्गेऽदः|उपसर्गेऽदः ३.३.५९|३.३.५९|३.३.५९ उपसर्गेऽदः
The affix अप् comes after the verb अद् 'to eat' when an उपसर्ग is in composition.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.60|3.3.60 nau Na cha|nau Na cha|nau Na cha 3.3.60|नौ ण च|नौ ण च ३.३.६०|३.३.६०|३.३.६० नौ ण च
And The affix ण as well as अप् come after the verb अद् 'to eat' when the उपसर्ग नि is in composition.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.61|3.3.61 vyadhajaporanupasarge|vyadhajaporanupasarge|vyadhajaporanupasarge 3.3.61|व्यधजपोरनुपसर्गे|व्यधजपोरनुपसर्गे ३.३.६१|३.३.६१|३.३.६१ व्यधजपोरनुपसर्गे
The affix अप् comes after the verbs 1. व्यध् 'to hurt or to pierce' 2. जप् 'to mutter' when no उपसर्ग is in composition with them.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.62|3.3.62 svanahasorvaa|svanahasorvaa|svanahasorvaa 3.3.62|स्वनहसोर्वा|स्वनहसोर्वा ३.३.६२|३.३.६२|३.३.६२ स्वनहसोर्वा
The affix अप् comes optionally after the verbs 1. स्वन् 2. हस् when no उपसर्ग is in composition with them.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.63|3.3.63 yamaH samupaniviShu|yamaH samupaniviShu|yamaH samupaniviShu 3.3.63|यमः समुपनिविषु|यमः समुपनिविषु ३.३.६३|३.३.६३|३.३.६३ यमः समुपनिविषु
And The affix अप् comes optionally after the verb यम् 'to surround' when the उपसर्ग -s सम् , उप , नि and वि are in composition ; or even when it is without उपसर्ग -less.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.64|3.3.64 nau gadanadapaThasvanaH|nau gadanadapaThasvanaH|nau gadanadapaThasvanaH 3.3.64|नौ गदनदपठस्वनः|नौ गदनदपठस्वनः ३.३.६४|३.३.६४|३.३.६४ नौ गदनदपठस्वनः
The affix अप् comes optionally after the verbs 1. गद् 'to speak' 2. नद् 'to sound' 3. पठ् 'to read' 4. स्वन् 'to sound' when the उपसर्ग नि is in composition with them.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.65|3.3.65 kvaNo viiNaayaaM cha|kvaNo viiNaayaaM cha|kvaNo viiNaayaaM cha 3.3.65|क्वणो वीणायां च|क्वणो वीणायां च ३.३.६५|३.३.६५|३.३.६५ क्वणो वीणायां च
The affix अप् comes optionally after the verb क्वन् 'to jingle' when नि is in composition with it, as well as when it is without any उपसर्ग or when 'flute' is meant.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.66|3.3.66 nityaM paNaH parimaaNe|nityaM paNaH parimaaNe|nityaM paNaH parimaaNe 3.3.66|नित्यं पणः परिमाणे|नित्यं पणः परिमाणे ३.३.६६|३.३.६६|३.३.६६ नित्यं पणः परिमाणे
The affix अप् comes Invariably after the verb पण् 'to barter' when the sense is that of 'measure'.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.67|3.3.67 mado.anupasarge|mado.anupasarge|mado.anupasarge 3.3.67|मदोऽनुपसर्गे|मदोऽनुपसर्गे ३.३.६७|३.३.६७|३.३.६७ मदोऽनुपसर्गे
The affix अप् comes after the verb मद् when not in composition with an उपसर्ग ।<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.68|3.3.68 pramadasammadau harShe|pramadasammadau harShe|pramadasammadau harShe 3.3.68|प्रमदसम्मदौ हर्षे|प्रमदसम्मदौ हर्षे ३.३.६८|३.३.६८|३.३.६८ प्रमदसम्मदौ हर्षे
The words प्रमद and सम्मद are irregularly formed, meaning 'joy'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.69|3.3.69 samudorajaH pashuShu|samudorajaH pashuShu|samudorajaH pashuShu 3.3.69|समुदोरजः पशुषु|समुदोरजः पशुषु ३.३.६९|३.३.६९|३.३.६९ समुदोरजः पशुषु
The affix अप् comes after the verb अज् 'to go' when the preposition सम् and उत् are in composition and the word so formed refers to beasts.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.70|3.3.70 axeShu glahaH|axeShu glahaH|axeShu glahaH 3.3.70|अक्षेषु ग्लहः|अक्षेषु ग्लहः ३.३.७०|३.३.७०|३.३.७० अक्षेषु ग्लहः
The word ग्लह is irregularly formed when the sense of the root refers to gambling.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.71|3.3.71 prajane sarteH|prajane sarteH|prajane sarteH 3.3.71|प्रजने सर्तेः|प्रजने सर्तेः ३.३.७१|३.३.७१|३.३.७१ प्रजने सर्तेः
The affix अप् comes after the verb श्रि 'to flow' in the sense of impregnating (the covering of cows etc.).<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.72|3.3.72 hvaH samprasaaraNaM cha nyabhyupaviShu|hvaH samprasaaraNaM cha nyabhyupaviShu|hvaH samprasaaraNaM cha nyabhyupaviShu 3.3.72|ह्वः सम्प्रसारणं च न्यभ्युपविषु|ह्वः सम्प्रसारणं च न्यभ्युपविषु ३.३.७२|३.३.७२|३.३.७२ ह्वः सम्प्रसारणं च न्यभ्युपविषु
The affix अप् comes after the verb ह्वे 'to call' when the preposition नि , अभि , उप and वि are in composition with it and its semi-vowel is changed into the corresponding vowel.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.73|3.3.73 aaNGi yuddhe|aaNGi yuddhe|aaNGi yuddhe 3.3.73|आङि युद्धे|आङि युद्धे ३.३.७३|३.३.७३|३.३.७३ आङि युद्धे
The affix अप् comes after the verb ह्वे 'to call' when the word in composition is the उपसर्ग आण् and the semi-vowel of the root is changed into its corresponding vowel, when the word so formed means 'battle'.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.74|3.3.74 nipaanamaahaavaH|nipaanamaahaavaH|nipaanamaahaavaH 3.3.74|निपानमाहावः|निपानमाहावः ३.३.७४|३.३.७४|३.३.७४ निपानमाहावः
The word आहाव is irregularly formed when meaning 'a trough'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.75|3.3.75 bhaave.anupasargasya|bhaave.anupasargasya|bhaave.anupasargasya 3.3.75|भावेऽनुपसर्गस्य|भावेऽनुपसर्गस्य ३.३.७५|३.३.७५|३.३.७५ भावेऽनुपसर्गस्य
The affix अप् comes after the verb ह्वे 'to call' and there is the change of the semi-vowel to its corresponding vowel, when the root is without an उपसर्ग and mere action is denoted.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.76|3.3.76 hanashcha vadhaH|hanashcha vadhaH|hanashcha vadhaH 3.3.76|हनश्च वधः|हनश्च वधः ३.३.७६|३.३.७६|३.३.७६ हनश्च वधः
The affix अप् comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when without an उपसर्ग , in the sense of mere action and वध is the substitute of हन् 'to kill' before this affix.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.77|3.3.77 muurtau ghanaH|muurtau ghanaH|muurtau ghanaH 3.3.77|मूर्तौ घनः|मूर्तौ घनः ३.३.७७|३.३.७७|३.३.७७ मूर्तौ घनः
The affix अप् comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when the word so formed means 'solidity' and घन् is the substitute.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.78|3.3.78 antarghano deshe|antarghano deshe|antarghano deshe 3.3.78|अन्तर्घनो देशे|अन्तर्घनो देशे ३.३.७८|३.३.७८|३.३.७८ अन्तर्घनो देशे
The verb हन् preceded by the word अन्तर् takes the affix अप् and घन् is the substitute of the word हन् when the word so formed means 'a country'.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.79|3.3.79 agaaraikadeshe praghaNaH praghaaNashcha|agaaraikadeshe praghaNaH praghaaNashcha|agaaraikadeshe praghaNaH praghaaNashcha 3.3.79|अगारैकदेशे प्रघणः प्रघाणश्च|अगारैकदेशे प्रघणः प्रघाणश्च ३.३.७९|३.३.७९|३.३.७९ अगारैकदेशे प्रघणः प्रघाणश्च
The words प्रघणः and प्रघाण are irregularly formed meaning 'a portion of a dwelling house'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.80|3.3.80 udghano.atyaadhaanam|udghano.atyaadhaanam|udghano.atyaadhaanam 3.3.80|उद्घनोऽत्याधानम्|उद्घनोऽत्याधानम् ३.३.८०|३.३.८०|३.३.८० उद्घनोऽत्याधानम्
The word उद्घन is irregularly formed in the sense of 'bench'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.81|3.3.81 apaghano.angam|apaghano.angam|apaghano.angam 3.3.81|अपघनोऽङ्गम्|अपघनोऽङ्गम् ३.३.८१|३.३.८१|३.३.८१ अपघनोऽङ्गम्
The word अपघन is irregularly formed meaning 'a member of the body'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.82|3.3.82 karaNe.ayovidruShu|karaNe.ayovidruShu|karaNe.ayovidruShu 3.3.82|करणेऽयोविद्रुषु|करणेऽयोविद्रुषु ३.३.८२|३.३.८२|३.३.८२ करणेऽयोविद्रुषु
The affix अप् comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when the words अयस् , वि or द्रु are in composition with it, when the word so formed is related to the verb as an instrument and घन् is the substitute.<br><br>Terms: अप्

3.3.83|3.3.83 stambe ka cha|stambe ka cha|stambe ka cha 3.3.83|स्तम्बे क च|स्तम्बे क च ३.३.८३|३.३.८३|३.३.८३ स्तम्बे क च
The affix क also comes after a root हन् 'to kill' when स्तम्ब 'a clump' is the word in composition and the relation of the word so formed to the verb is that of the intrument.<br><br>Terms: क

3.3.84|3.3.84 parau ghaH|parau ghaH|parau ghaH 3.3.84|परौ घः|परौ घः ३.३.८४|३.३.८४|३.३.८४ परौ घः
The affix क also comes after a root हन् 'to kill' when the उपसर्ग परि is in composition and the relation between the word so formed and the verb is that of an instrument and घ replaces हन् ।<br><br>Terms: क

3.3.85|3.3.85 upaghna aashraye|upaghna aashraye|upaghna aashraye 3.3.85|उपघ्न आश्रये|उपघ्न आश्रये ३.३.८५|३.३.८५|३.३.८५ उपघ्न आश्रये
The word उपघ्न is irregularly formed meaning 'an inclined place for leaning or support'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.86|3.3.86 saMghodghau gaNaprashaMsayoH|saMghodghau gaNaprashaMsayoH|saMghodghau gaNaprashaMsayoH 3.3.86|संघोद्घौ गणप्रशंसयोः|संघोद्घौ गणप्रशंसयोः ३.३.८६|३.३.८६|३.३.८६ संघोद्घौ गणप्रशंसयोः
The words संघ and उद्घ are irregularly formed in the sense of 'a collection' and 'a praise' respectively.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.87|3.3.87 nigho nimitam|nigho nimitam|nigho nimitam 3.3.87|निघो निमितम्|निघो निमितम् ३.३.८७|३.३.८७|३.३.८७ निघो निमितम्
The word निघ is irregularly formed in the sense of 'as high as broad'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.88|3.3.88 DvitaH ktriH|DvitaH ktriH|DvitaH ktriH 3.3.88|ड्वितः क्त्रिः|ड्वितः क्त्रिः ३.३.८८|३.३.८८|३.३.८८ ड्वितः क्त्रिः
The affix क्त्रि comes after the verb which has an indicatory डु when denoting mere action etc.<br><br>Terms: क्त्रि

3.3.89|3.3.89 Tvito.athuch|Tvito.athuch|Tvito.athuch 3.3.89|ट्वितोऽथुच्|ट्वितोऽथुच् ३.३.८९|३.३.८९|३.३.८९ ट्वितोऽथुच्
After that verb that has an indicatory टु , the affix अथुच् comes with the force of denoting mere action etc.<br><br>Terms: अथुच्

3.3.90|3.3.90 yajayaachayatavichChaprachCharaxo naNG|yajayaachayatavichChaprachCharaxo naNG|yajayaachayatavichChaprachCharaxo naNG 3.3.90|यजयाचयतविच्छप्रच्छरक्षो नङ्|यजयाचयतविच्छप्रच्छरक्षो नङ् ३.३.९०|३.३.९०|३.३.९० यजयाचयतविच्छप्रच्छरक्षो नङ्
After the verbs 1. यज् 'to worship' 2. याच् 'to ask for' 3. यत् 'to strive' 4. विच्छ् 'to shine' 5. प्रच्छ् 'to ask' 6. रक्ष् 'to preserve', comes the affix नङ् with the force of denoting mere action etc.<br><br>Terms: नङ्

3.3.91|3.3.91 svapo nan|svapo nan|svapo nan 3.3.91|स्वपो नन्|स्वपो नन् ३.३.९१|३.३.९१|३.३.९१ स्वपो नन्
The affix नन् comes under similar circumstances after the verb स्वप् 'to sleep'.<br><br>Terms: नन्

3.3.92|3.3.92 upasarge ghoH kiH|upasarge ghoH kiH|upasarge ghoH kiH 3.3.92|उपसर्गे घोः किः|उपसर्गे घोः किः ३.३.९२|३.३.९२|३.३.९२ उपसर्गे घोः किः
The affix कि comes under similar circumstances after a घु verb -- दाधा घ्वदाप् १.१.२० when an उपसर्ग is in composition with it.<br><br>Terms: कि

3.3.93|3.3.93 karmaNyadhikaraNe cha|karmaNyadhikaraNe cha|karmaNyadhikaraNe cha 3.3.93|कर्मण्यधिकरणे च|कर्मण्यधिकरणे च ३.३.९३|३.३.९३|३.३.९३ कर्मण्यधिकरणे च
The affix कि comes after a घु verb -- दाधा घ्वदाप् १.१.२० when a word in the Accusative -2nd case is in composition with it and when the relation of the word so formed to its verb, is that of 'location.<br><br>Terms: कि

3.3.94|3.3.94 striyaaM ktin|striyaaM ktin|striyaaM ktin 3.3.94|स्त्रियां क्तिन्|स्त्रियां क्तिन् ३.३.९४|३.३.९४|३.३.९४ स्त्रियां क्तिन्
To express an action etc. by a word in the feminine gender, the affix क्तिन् is added to the root.<br><br>Terms: क्तिन्

3.3.95|3.3.95 sthaagaapaapachaaM bhaave|sthaagaapaapachaaM bhaave|sthaagaapaapachaaM bhaave 3.3.95|स्थागापापचां भावे|स्थागापापचां भावे ३.३.९५|३.३.९५|३.३.९५ स्थागापापचां भावे
After the roots 1. स्था 'to stand' 2. गा 'to sing' 3. पा 'to drink' 4. पच् 'to cook', the affix क्तिन् is used when a word in the feminine gender denoting a 'mere action' is to be expressed.<br><br>Terms: क्तिन्

3.3.96|3.3.96 mantre vRSheShapachamanavidabhuuviiraa udaattaH|mantre vRSheShapachamanavidabhuuviiraa udaattaH|mantre vRSheShapachamanavidabhuuviiraa udaattaH 3.3.96|मन्त्रे वृषेषपचमनविदभूवीरा उदात्तः|मन्त्रे वृषेषपचमनविदभूवीरा उदात्तः ३.३.९६|३.३.९६|३.३.९६ मन्त्रे वृषेषपचमनविदभूवीरा उदात्तः
In the मन्त्र literature, क्तिन् acutely accented comes after the following roots, forming words in feminine gender, denoting a 'mere action' 1. वृष् 'to rain' 2. इष् 'to wish 3. पच् 'to cook' 4. मन् 'to think' 5. विद् 'to know' 6. भू 'to be' 7. वि 'to go, to consume' 8. रा 'to give'.<br><br>Terms: क्तिन्

3.3.97|3.3.97 Utiyuutijuutisaatihetikiirtayashcha|Utiyuutijuutisaatihetikiirtayashcha|Utiyuutijuutisaatihetikiirtayashcha 3.3.97|ऊतियूतिजूतिसातिहेतिकीर्तयश्च|ऊतियूतिजूतिसातिहेतिकीर्तयश्च ३.३.९७|३.३.९७|३.३.९७ ऊतियूतिजूतिसातिहेतिकीर्तयश्च
And these words viz. 1. ऊति 'preserving sport' 2. यूति 'joining' 3. जूति 'velocity' 4. साति 'destruction' 5. हेति 'a weapon' 6. कीर्ति 'fame', are anomalous forms, acutely accented (उदात्त).<br><br>Terms: उदात्त

3.3.98|3.3.98 vrajayajorbhaave kyap‌|vrajayajorbhaave kyap‌|vrajayajorbhaave kyap‌ 3.3.98|व्रजयजोर्भावे क्यप्‌|व्रजयजोर्भावे क्यप्‌ ३.३.९८|३.३.९८|३.३.९८ व्रजयजोर्भावे क्यप्‌
The affix क्यप्‌ comes after a roots 1. व्रज 'to go' 2. यज् 'to worship' acutely accented (उदात्त) in forming a word in the feminine denoting action.<br><br>Terms: क्यप्‌

3.3.99|3.3.99 saMJNaayaaM samajaniShadanipatamanavidaShuNJshiiNGbhRNJiNaH|saMJNaayaaM samajaniShadanipatamanavidaShuNJshiiNGbhRNJiNaH|saMJNaayaaM samajaniShadanipatamanavidaShuNJshiiNGbhRNJiNaH 3.3.99|संज्ञायां समजनिषदनिपतमनविदषुञ्शीङ्भृञिणः|संज्ञायां समजनिषदनिपतमनविदषुञ्शीङ्भृञिणः ३.३.९९|३.३.९९|३.३.९९ संज्ञायां समजनिषदनिपतमनविदषुञ्शीङ्भृञिणः
The affix क्यप्‌ comes after the following verbs in forming a word in the feminine denoting an 'appellative 'and is acutely accented (उदात्त) viz. 1. समज 2. निषद 3. निपत 4. मन 5. विद 6. षुञ् 7. शीङ् 8. भृञ् 9. इण्<br><br>Terms: क्यप्‌

3.3.100|3.3.100 kRNJaH sha cha|kRNJaH sha cha|kRNJaH sha cha 3.3.100|कृञः श च|कृञः श च ३.३.१००|३.३.१००|३.३.१०० कृञः श च
And after the root कृ comes the affix श in forming a feminine as well as the affix क्यप्‌।<br><br>Terms: क्यप्‌

3.3.101|3.3.101 ichChaa|ichChaa|ichChaa 3.3.101|इच्छा|इच्छा ३.३.१०१|३.३.१०१|३.३.१०१ इच्छा
The form इच्छा 'desire' is irregular.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.102|3.3.102 a pratyayaat‌|a pratyayaat‌|a pratyayaat‌ 3.3.102|अ प्रत्ययात्‌|अ प्रत्ययात्‌ ३.३.१०२|३.३.१०२|३.३.१०२ अ प्रत्ययात्‌
After the verbs that end in an affix, there is the affix अ, the word being feminine.<br><br>Terms: अ

3.3.103|3.3.103 guroshcha halaH|guroshcha halaH|guroshcha halaH 3.3.103|गुरोश्च हलः|गुरोश्च हलः ३.३.१०३|३.३.१०३|३.३.१०३ गुरोश्च हलः
The affix अ comes after a verb which has a prosodially heavy vowel and ends in a consonant when the word to be formed is feminine.<br><br>Terms: अ

3.3.104|3.3.104 Shidbhidaadibhyo.aNG|Shidbhidaadibhyo.aNG|Shidbhidaadibhyo.aNG 3.3.104|षिद्भिदादिभ्योऽङ्|षिद्भिदादिभ्योऽङ् ३.३.१०४|३.३.१०४|३.३.१०४ षिद्भिदादिभ्योऽङ्
The affix अण् comes after those verbs that have an indicatory षि and after भिद् when the word to be formed is feminine.<br><br>Terms: अण्

3.3.105|3.3.105 chintipuujikathikumbicharchashcha|chintipuujikathikumbicharchashcha|chintipuujikathikumbicharchashcha 3.3.105|चिन्तिपूजिकथिकुम्बिचर्चश्च|चिन्तिपूजिकथिकुम्बिचर्चश्च ३.३.१०५|३.३.१०५|३.३.१०५ चिन्तिपूजिकथिकुम्बिचर्चश्च
The affix अण् as well as the affix युच् come after the following verbs, forming feminine words - 1. चिन्त् 'to think' 2. पूज् 'to worship' 3. कथ् 'to narrate' 4. कुम्ब् 'to cover' 5. चर्च् 'to learn'<br><br>Terms: अण्

3.3.106|3.3.106 aatashchopasarge|aatashchopasarge|aatashchopasarge 3.3.106|आतश्चोपसर्गे|आतश्चोपसर्गे ३.३.१०६|३.३.१०६|३.३.१०६ आतश्चोपसर्गे
The affix अण् comes after those verbs which end in long आ when an उपसर्ग is in composition and when the word to be formed is feminine.<br><br>Terms: अण्

3.3.107|3.3.107 Nyaasashrantho yuch|Nyaasashrantho yuch|Nyaasashrantho yuch 3.3.107|ण्यासश्रन्थो युच्|ण्यासश्रन्थो युच् ३.३.१०७|३.३.१०७|३.३.१०७ ण्यासश्रन्थो युच्
After verbs ending in णि and after आस् 'to sit' and श्रन्थ् 'to loose', there is the affix युच् when the word to be formed is feminine.<br><br>Terms: युच्

3.3.108|3.3.108 rogaakhyaayaaM Nvul bahulam|rogaakhyaayaaM Nvul bahulam|rogaakhyaayaaM Nvul bahulam 3.3.108|रोगाख्यायां ण्वुल् बहुलम्|रोगाख्यायां ण्वुल् बहुलम् ३.३.१०८|३.३.१०८|३.३.१०८ रोगाख्यायां ण्वुल् बहुलम्
The affix ण्वुल् comes diversely after verbs when the word to be formed is feminine noun, being the name of 'diseases'.<br><br>Terms: ण्वुल्

3.3.109|3.3.109 saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam 3.3.109|संज्ञायाम्|संज्ञायाम् ३.३.१०९|३.३.१०९|३.३.१०९ संज्ञायाम्
The affix ण्वुल् comes after the verbal roots, when the word to be formed is an appellative.<br><br>Terms: ण्वुल्

3.3.110|3.3.110 vibhaaShaa.a.akhyaanapariprashnayoriNJ cha|vibhaaShaa.a.akhyaanapariprashnayoriNJ cha|vibhaaShaa.a.akhyaanapariprashnayoriNJ cha 3.3.110|विभाषाऽऽख्यानपरिप्रश्नयोरिञ् च|विभाषाऽऽख्यानपरिप्रश्नयोरिञ् च ३.३.११०|३.३.११०|३.३.११० विभाषाऽऽख्यानपरिप्रश्नयोरिञ् च
And the affix इञ् comes optionally after a root when a question and answer is expressed (as well as ण्वुल् and other affixes ordained by other rules).<br><br>Terms: इञ्

3.3.111|3.3.111 paryaayaarharNotpattiShu Nvuch|paryaayaarharNotpattiShu Nvuch|paryaayaarharNotpattiShu Nvuch 3.3.111|पर्यायार्हर्णोत्पत्तिषु ण्वुच्|पर्यायार्हर्णोत्पत्तिषु ण्वुच् ३.३.१११|३.३.१११|३.३.१११ पर्यायार्हर्णोत्पत्तिषु ण्वुच्
The affix ण्वुच् comes optionally after a root in the sense of succession, merit, debt or production.<br><br>Terms: ण्वुच्

3.3.112|3.3.112 aakroshe naNJyaniH|aakroshe naNJyaniH|aakroshe naNJyaniH 3.3.112|आक्रोशे नञ्यनिः|आक्रोशे नञ्यनिः ३.३.११२|३.३.११२|३.३.११२ आक्रोशे नञ्यनिः
The affix अनि comes after a verb when the particle नञ् is in composition with it and the sense implied is that of 'cursing'.<br><br>Terms: अनि

3.3.113|3.3.113 kRtyalyuTo bahulam|kRtyalyuTo bahulam|kRtyalyuTo bahulam 3.3.113|कृत्यल्युटो बहुलम्|कृत्यल्युटो बहुलम् ३.३.११३|३.३.११३|३.३.११३ कृत्यल्युटो बहुलम्
The affixes called कृत्य -- कृत्याः प्राङ् ण्वुलः ३.१.९५, and the affix ल्युट् , are diversely applicable and have other senses than those taught before.<br><br>Terms: कृत्य

3.3.114|3.3.114 napuMsake bhaave ktaH|napuMsake bhaave ktaH|napuMsake bhaave ktaH 3.3.114|नपुंसके भावे क्तः|नपुंसके भावे क्तः ३.३.११४|३.३.११४|३.३.११४ नपुंसके भावे क्तः
The affix क्त is added to the root when action is expressed, the word being in the neuter gender.<br><br>Terms: क्त

3.3.115|3.3.115 lyuT cha|lyuT cha|lyuT cha 3.3.115|ल्युट् च|ल्युट् च ३.३.११५|३.३.११५|३.३.११५ ल्युट् च
The affix ल्युट् is added to the root when the name of an action is expressed, in the neuter gender.<br><br>Terms: ल्युट्

3.3.116|3.3.116 karmaNi cha yena saMsparshaat‌ kartuH shariirasukham|karmaNi cha yena saMsparshaat‌ kartuH shariirasukham|karmaNi cha yena saMsparshaat‌ kartuH shariirasukham 3.3.116|कर्मणि च येन संस्पर्शात्‌ कर्तुः शरीरसुखम्|कर्मणि च येन संस्पर्शात्‌ कर्तुः शरीरसुखम् ३.३.११६|३.३.११६|३.३.११६ कर्मणि च येन संस्पर्शात्‌ कर्तुः शरीरसुखम्
The affix ल्युट् is added to a root when the name of an action is expressed, in the neuter gender provided that the verb has in construction with it, such a word in the Accusative -2nd case, as indicates the thing, from the contact with which, there arises a pleaasant sensation corporally to the agent.<br><br>Terms: ल्युट्

3.3.117|3.3.117 karaNaadhikaraNayoshcha|karaNaadhikaraNayoshcha|karaNaadhikaraNayoshcha 3.3.117|करणाधिकरणयोश्च|करणाधिकरणयोश्च ३.३.११७|३.३.११७|३.३.११७ करणाधिकरणयोश्च
The affix ल्युट् is added to a root when the relation of the word so formed to the verb is that of an instrument or location.<br><br>Terms: ल्युट्

3.3.118|3.3.118 puMsi saMJNaayaaM ghaH praayeNa|puMsi saMJNaayaaM ghaH praayeNa|puMsi saMJNaayaaM ghaH praayeNa 3.3.118|पुंसि संज्ञायां घः प्रायेण|पुंसि संज्ञायां घः प्रायेण ३.३.११८|३.३.११८|३.३.११८ पुंसि संज्ञायां घः प्रायेण
The affix घ generally comes in the sense of an instrument or location after a root, when the word to be formed is a name and is in the masculine gender.<br><br>Terms: घ

3.3.119|3.3.119 gocharasaMcharavahavrajavyajaapaNanigamaashcha|gocharasaMcharavahavrajavyajaapaNanigamaashcha|gocharasaMcharavahavrajavyajaapaNanigamaashcha 3.3.119|गोचरसंचरवहव्रजव्यजापणनिगमाश्च|गोचरसंचरवहव्रजव्यजापणनिगमाश्च ३.३.११९|३.३.११९|३.३.११९ गोचरसंचरवहव्रजव्यजापणनिगमाश्च
And the words 1. गोचर 2. संचर 3. वह 4. व्रज 5. व्यज 6. आपण 7. निगम are anomalous.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.120|3.3.120 ave tRRstrorghaNJ|ave tRRstrorghaNJ|ave tRRstrorghaNJ 3.3.120|अवे तॄस्त्रोर्घञ्|अवे तॄस्त्रोर्घञ् ३.३.१२०|३.३.१२०|३.३.१२० अवे तॄस्त्रोर्घञ्
The affix घञ् comes after the roots 1. तॄ 'to cross' 2. स्तॄ 'to spread, to cover', when the उपसर्ग अव is in composition with them and when the word so formed is an appellative related to the verb either as an instrument or as a location.<br><br>Terms: घञ्

3.3.121|3.3.121 halashcha|halashcha|halashcha 3.3.121|हलश्च|हलश्च ३.३.१२१|३.३.१२१|३.३.१२१ हलश्च
And after a verb ending in a consonant, comes the affix घञ् (when the word to be formed is masculine and related to the verb as an instrument or a location and thereby the palatal is changed into guttural).<br><br>Terms: घञ्

3.3.122|3.3.122 adhyaayanyaayodyaavasaMhaaraadhaaraavayaashcha|adhyaayanyaayodyaavasaMhaaraadhaaraavayaashcha|adhyaayanyaayodyaavasaMhaaraadhaaraavayaashcha 3.3.122|अध्यायन्यायोद्यावसंहाराधारावयाश्च|अध्यायन्यायोद्यावसंहाराधारावयाश्च ३.३.१२२|३.३.१२२|३.३.१२२ अध्यायन्यायोद्यावसंहाराधारावयाश्च
And the words 1. अध्याय 2. न्याय 3. उद्याव 4. संहार 5. आधारा 6. आवयाः are anomalous.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.123|3.3.123 udanko.anudake|udanko.anudake|udanko.anudake 3.3.123|उदङ्कोऽनुदके|उदङ्कोऽनुदके ३.३.१२३|३.३.१२३|३.३.१२३ उदङ्कोऽनुदके
The word उदङ्क is anomalous when the sense of the root refers to subjects other than 'water'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.124|3.3.124 jaalamaanaayaH|jaalamaanaayaH|jaalamaanaayaH 3.3.124|जालमानायः|जालमानायः ३.३.१२४|३.३.१२४|३.३.१२४ जालमानायः
The word आनाय is irregularly formed when the meaning is 'a net'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.3.125|3.3.125 khano gha cha|khano gha cha|khano gha cha 3.3.125|खनो घ च|खनो घ च ३.३.१२५|३.३.१२५|३.३.१२५ खनो घ च
The affix घ as well as घञ् come after the verb खन् 'to dig' when the word to be formed is an appellative related to the verb as an instrument or location.<br><br>Terms: घ and घञ्

3.3.126|3.3.126 iiShadduHsuShu kRchChraakRchChraartheShu khal|iiShadduHsuShu kRchChraakRchChraartheShu khal|iiShadduHsuShu kRchChraakRchChraartheShu khal 3.3.126|ईषद्दुःसुषु कृच्छ्राकृच्छ्रार्थेषु खल्|ईषद्दुःसुषु कृच्छ्राकृच्छ्रार्थेषु खल् ३.३.१२६|३.३.१२६|३.३.१२६ ईषद्दुःसुषु कृच्छ्राकृच्छ्रार्थेषु खल्
In the sense of 'hard and difficult' or 'light and easy' the affix खल् is added to a verb when ईषद् and दुर् and सु are combined with it as उपपद-s.<br><br>Terms: खल्

3.3.127|3.3.127 kartRkarmaNoshcha bhuukRNJoH|kartRkarmaNoshcha bhuukRNJoH|kartRkarmaNoshcha bhuukRNJoH 3.3.127|कर्तृकर्मणोश्च भूकृञोः|कर्तृकर्मणोश्च भूकृञोः ३.३.१२७|३.३.१२७|३.३.१२७ कर्तृकर्मणोश्च भूकृञोः
The affix खल् comes after the verbs भू 'to be' and कृ when the उपपद-s in composition with them are 'agent' and 'object' respectively, preceded by the words ईषद् etc. in combination with them, meaning 'hard or light'.<br><br>Terms: खल्

3.3.128|3.3.128 aato yuch|aato yuch|aato yuch 3.3.128|आतो युच्|आतो युच् ३.३.१२८|३.३.१२८|३.३.१२८ आतो युच्
The affix युच् comes after the roots ending in long आ (when ईषद् and दुर् and सु are combined as उपपद-sūtras, in the sense of easily or with difficulty).<br><br>Terms: युच्

3.3.129|3.3.129 Chandasi gatyarthebhyaH|Chandasi gatyarthebhyaH|Chandasi gatyarthebhyaH 3.3.129|छन्दसि गत्यर्थेभ्यः|छन्दसि गत्यर्थेभ्यः ३.३.१२९|३.३.१२९|३.३.१२९ छन्दसि गत्यर्थेभ्यः
The affix युच् comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the roots having the sense of 'to go' when the word ईषद् etc. meaning 'lightly' or 'with difficulty' are in composition with such verbs.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस् युच्

3.3.130|3.3.130 anyebhyo.api dRshyate|anyebhyo.api dRshyate|anyebhyo.api dRshyate 3.3.130|अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यते|अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यते ३.३.१३०|३.३.१३०|३.३.१३० अन्येभ्योऽपि दृश्यते
The affix युच् is seen to come number the छन्दस् (Vedas) after other verbs also, than those meaning 'to go'<br><br>Terms: छन्दस् युच्

3.3.131|3.3.131 vartamaanasaamiipye vartamaanavadvaa|vartamaanasaamiipye vartamaanavadvaa|vartamaanasaamiipye vartamaanavadvaa 3.3.131|वर्तमानसामीप्ये वर्तमानवद्वा|वर्तमानसामीप्ये वर्तमानवद्वा ३.३.१३१|३.३.१३१|३.३.१३१ वर्तमानसामीप्ये वर्तमानवद्वा
The affixes which are used when the sense is that of present time, may, optionally in like manner, be used when the sense is that of past or future time not remote from the present.<br><br>Terms: 

3.3.132|3.3.132 aashaMsaayaaM bhuutavachcha|aashaMsaayaaM bhuutavachcha|aashaMsaayaaM bhuutavachcha 3.3.132|आशंसायां भूतवच्च|आशंसायां भूतवच्च ३.३.१३२|३.३.१३२|३.३.१३२ आशंसायां भूतवच्च
The affixes which are used when the sense is that of past time or of the present time, may, optionally, in like manner, be used after a root in denoting future time when hope is expressed.<br><br>Terms: 

3.3.133|3.3.133 xipravachane lRT|xipravachane lRT|xipravachane lRT 3.3.133|क्षिप्रवचने लृट्|क्षिप्रवचने लृट् ३.३.१३३|३.३.१३३|३.३.१३३ क्षिप्रवचने लृट्
When the word क्षिप्र 'quickly' or its synonym is in construction with the verb, the future affix लृट् (2nd Future) is used after the root when 'hope' is expressed in a conditional form.<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.3.134|3.3.134 aashaMsaavachane liNG|aashaMsaavachane liNG|aashaMsaavachane liNG 3.3.134|आशंसावचने लिङ्|आशंसावचने लिङ् ३.३.१३४|३.३.१३४|३.३.१३४ आशंसावचने लिङ्
The affix of the Potential is used in denoting Futurity after a root, when the उपपद in composition with it is a word expressing 'hope'.<br><br>Terms: 

3.3.135|3.3.135 naanadyatanavat‌ kriyaaprabandhasaamiipyayoH|naanadyatanavat‌ kriyaaprabandhasaamiipyayoH|naanadyatanavat‌ kriyaaprabandhasaamiipyayoH 3.3.135|नानद्यतनवत्‌ क्रियाप्रबन्धसामीप्ययोः|नानद्यतनवत्‌ क्रियाप्रबन्धसामीप्ययोः ३.३.१३५|३.३.१३५|३.३.१३५ नानद्यतनवत्‌ क्रियाप्रबन्धसामीप्ययोः
When constant continuance of action or a near Past or Future is meant, the Past and Future are not denoted as taught in अनद्यतने लङ् ३.२.१११ and अनद्यतने लुट् ३.३.१५, through the Imperfect and the II Future, but through the Aorist and the First Future.<br><br>Terms: 

3.3.136|3.3.136 bhaviShyati maryaadaavachane.avarasmin|bhaviShyati maryaadaavachane.avarasmin|bhaviShyati maryaadaavachane.avarasmin 3.3.136|भविष्यति मर्यादावचनेऽवरस्मिन्|भविष्यति मर्यादावचनेऽवरस्मिन् ३.३.१३६|३.३.१३६|३.३.१३६ भविष्यति मर्यादावचनेऽवरस्मिन्
The Futurity is not expressed, as taught in अनद्यतने लुट् ३.३.१५ throught the II Future, but through the I Future, when a statement is made of a limit on this (अवर) side of another place.<br><br>Terms: II Future

3.3.137|3.3.137 kaalavibhaage chaanahoraatraaNaam|kaalavibhaage chaanahoraatraaNaam|kaalavibhaage chaanahoraatraaNaam 3.3.137|कालविभागे चानहोरात्राणाम्|कालविभागे चानहोरात्राणाम् ३.३.१३७|३.३.१३७|३.३.१३७ कालविभागे चानहोरात्राणाम्
The II Future is used instead of the I Future in denoting Future time not belonging to the current day when the word अवर is used together with a word expressing division of time, but not when it is a word giving the sense of 'day' or 'night'.<br><br>Terms: II Future

3.3.138|3.3.138 parasmin vibhaaShaa|parasmin vibhaaShaa|parasmin vibhaaShaa 3.3.138|परस्मिन् विभाषा|परस्मिन् विभाषा ३.३.१३८|३.३.१३८|३.३.१३८ परस्मिन् विभाषा
Optionally so, when a declaration is made with regard to that side of a limit of time.<br><br>Terms: II Future

3.3.139|3.3.139 liNG‌nimitte lRNG kriyaa.atipattau|liNG‌nimitte lRNG kriyaa.atipattau|liNG‌nimitte lRNG kriyaa.atipattau 3.3.139|लिङ्‌निमित्ते लृङ् क्रियाऽतिपत्तौ|लिङ्‌निमित्ते लृङ् क्रियाऽतिपत्तौ ३.३.१३९|३.३.१३९|३.३.१३९ लिङ्‌निमित्ते लृङ् क्रियाऽतिपत्तौ
Where there is a reason for affixing लिङ् (Benedictive) the affix ऌङ् (Conditional Future) is used in the Future tense when the non-completion of the action is to be understood.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.140|3.3.140 bhuute cha|bhuute cha|bhuute cha 3.3.140|भूते च|भूते च ३.३.१४०|३.३.१४०|३.३.१४० भूते च
And (where there is a reason for affixing लिङ् (Benedictive) , the affix ऌङ् (Conditional Future) is to be used, when the non-completion of the action is to be understood) if the sense is that of past time.<br><br>Terms: ऌङ्

3.3.141|3.3.141 votaapyoH|votaapyoH|votaapyoH 3.3.141|वोताप्योः|वोताप्योः ३.३.१४१|३.३.१४१|३.३.१४१ वोताप्योः
From this point up to sūtra उताप्योः समर्थयोर्लिङ् ३.३.१५२ (the whole of the following sentence is to be taken as exerting a governing the influence on the sūtras that follow; where there is a reason for affix लिङ् (Benedictive) , the ऌङ् (Conditional Future) may be) optionally (used in denoting the past time, when the non-completion of the action is to be understood).<br><br>Terms: लिङ् and लृट्

3.3.142|3.3.142 garhaayaaM laDapijaatvoH|garhaayaaM laDapijaatvoH|garhaayaaM laDapijaatvoH 3.3.142|गर्हायां लडपिजात्वोः|गर्हायां लडपिजात्वोः ३.३.१४२|३.३.१४२|३.३.१४२ गर्हायां लडपिजात्वोः
The affix लट् (Present Tense) is used after a root when it has in composition with it the wordsअपि or जातु , the sense implied by the sentence being that of 'censure'.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.3.143|3.3.143 vibhaaShaa kathami liNG cha|vibhaaShaa kathami liNG cha|vibhaaShaa kathami liNG cha 3.3.143|विभाषा कथमि लिङ् च|विभाषा कथमि लिङ् च ३.३.१४३|३.३.१४३|३.३.१४३ विभाषा कथमि लिङ् च
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) as well as लट् (Present Tense) is optionally used after a root when the word कथम् is in construction with it and censure is implied.<br><br>Terms: लिङ् and लृट्

3.3.144|3.3.144 kiMvRtte liNGlRTau|kiMvRtte liNGlRTau|kiMvRtte liNGlRTau 3.3.144|किंवृत्ते लिङ्लृटौ|किंवृत्ते लिङ्लृटौ ३.३.१४४|३.३.१४४|३.३.१४४ किंवृत्ते लिङ्लृटौ
The affixes लिङ् (Benedictive) and लृट् (I Future) come after a verb when the interrogative words like किम् etc. aer in composition with it and censure is implied.<br><br>Terms: लिङ् and लृट्

3.3.145|3.3.145 anavakLLiptyamarShayorakiMvRtte api|anavakLLiptyamarShayorakiMvRtte api|anavakLLiptyamarShayorakiMvRtte api 3.3.145|अनवकॢप्त्यमर्षयोरकिंवृत्ते अपि|अनवकॢप्त्यमर्षयोरकिंवृत्ते अपि ३.३.१४५|३.३.१४५|३.३.१४५ अनवकॢप्त्यमर्षयोरकिंवृत्ते अपि
When it is to be expressed that somebody hold that something is not likely to take place or is not to be tolerated, the Potential and the I Future are used, even without the Interrogative Pronoun.<br><br>Terms: लिङ् and लृट्

3.3.146|3.3.146 kiMkilaastyartheShu lRT|kiMkilaastyartheShu lRT|kiMkilaastyartheShu lRT 3.3.146|किंकिलास्त्यर्थेषु लृट्|किंकिलास्त्यर्थेषु लृट् ३.३.१४६|३.३.१४६|३.३.१४६ किंकिलास्त्यर्थेषु लृट्
The affix लृट् (I Future) is used after a root when the words किंकिल or those having the sense of अस्ति 'he is' are in construction with it (when the action is not likely to occur, or is not to be tolerated).<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.3.147|3.3.147 jaatuyadorliNG|jaatuyadorliNG|jaatuyadorliNG 3.3.147|जातुयदोर्लिङ्|जातुयदोर्लिङ् ३.३.१४७|३.३.१४७|३.३.१४७ जातुयदोर्लिङ्
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes after a root, the words जातु and यत् being in construction with it, when the sense is that the action is not believed to be likely or is not to be tolerated.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.148|3.3.148 yachchayatrayoH|yachchayatrayoH|yachchayatrayoH 3.3.148|यच्चयत्रयोः|यच्चयत्रयोः ३.३.१४८|३.३.१४८|३.३.१४८ यच्चयत्रयोः
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes after a root in all tenses when the words यच्च and यत्र are in composition with it, provided that censure is implied.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.149|3.3.149 garhaayaaM cha|garhaayaaM cha|garhaayaaM cha 3.3.149|गर्हायां च|गर्हायां च ३.३.१४९|३.३.१४९|३.३.१४९ गर्हायां च
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes in all tenses when the words यच्च and यत्र are in composition with it, provided that censure is implied.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.150|3.3.150 chitriikaraNe cha|chitriikaraNe cha|chitriikaraNe cha 3.3.150|चित्रीकरणे च|चित्रीकरणे च ३.३.१५०|३.३.१५०|३.३.१५० चित्रीकरणे च
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes in all tenses when used with the words यच्च and यत्र and the sense implied is that of 'wonder'.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.151|3.3.151 sheShe lRDayadau|sheShe lRDayadau|sheShe lRDayadau 3.3.151|शेषे लृडयदौ|शेषे लृडयदौ ३.३.१५१|३.३.१५१|३.३.१५१ शेषे लृडयदौ
In all the cases when 'wonder' is implied by word other than यच्च and यत्र , the affix लृट् (I Future) is used after a root, except when the word यदि is used.<br><br>Terms: लृट्

3.3.152|3.3.152 utaapyoH samarthayorliNG|utaapyoH samarthayorliNG|utaapyoH samarthayorliNG 3.3.152|उताप्योः समर्थयोर्लिङ्|उताप्योः समर्थयोर्लिङ् ३.३.१५२|३.३.१५२|३.३.१५२ उताप्योः समर्थयोर्लिङ्
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes after a verb in all tenses when the words उत and अपि , both having the same meaning, are in composition. <br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.153|3.3.153 kaamapravedane.akachchiti|kaamapravedane.akachchiti|kaamapravedane.akachchiti 3.3.153|कामप्रवेदनेऽकच्चिति|कामप्रवेदनेऽकच्चिति ३.३.१५३|३.३.१५३|३.३.१५३ कामप्रवेदनेऽकच्चिति
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes after a root, in expressing or making known of a wish, except when the word कच्चित् is in composition with it.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.154|3.3.154 sambhavaane.alamiti chet‌ siddhaaprayoge|sambhavaane.alamiti chet‌ siddhaaprayoge|sambhavaane.alamiti chet‌ siddhaaprayoge 3.3.154|सम्भवानेऽलमिति चेत्‌ सिद्धाप्रयोगे|सम्भवानेऽलमिति चेत्‌ सिद्धाप्रयोगे ३.३.१५४|३.३.१५४|३.३.१५४ सम्भवानेऽलमिति चेत्‌ सिद्धाप्रयोगे
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) is used after a root, when the expectation (of a person or thing being able or competent to do or suffer the action denoted by the verb is implied (or expressed by any other word used along with them) than 'alarm'.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.155|3.3.155 vibhaaShaa dhaatau sambhaavanavachane.ayadi|vibhaaShaa dhaatau sambhaavanavachane.ayadi|vibhaaShaa dhaatau sambhaavanavachane.ayadi 3.3.155|विभाषा धातौ सम्भावनवचनेऽयदि|विभाषा धातौ सम्भावनवचनेऽयदि ३.३.१५५|३.३.१५५|३.३.१५५ विभाषा धातौ सम्भावनवचनेऽयदि
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) is optionally used after a verb when it has another verb which expresses 'expectation' in construction with it, but not so when the word यत् is used.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.156|3.3.156 hetuhetumatorliNG|hetuhetumatorliNG|hetuhetumatorliNG 3.3.156|हेतुहेतुमतोर्लिङ्|हेतुहेतुमतोर्लिङ् ३.३.१५६|३.३.१५६|३.३.१५६ हेतुहेतुमतोर्लिङ्
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) is optionally used after those verbs which express the condition and its consequence.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.157|3.3.157 ichChaartheShu liNGloTau|ichChaartheShu liNGloTau|ichChaartheShu liNGloTau 3.3.157|इच्छार्थेषु लिङ्लोटौ|इच्छार्थेषु लिङ्लोटौ ३.३.१५७|३.३.१५७|३.३.१५७ इच्छार्थेषु लिङ्लोटौ
The affixes लिङ् (Benedictive) and लोट् (Imperative) are used after a root when another verb having the same sense of 'wishing' is in construction with it.<br><br>Terms: लिङ् and लोट्

3.3.158|3.3.158 samaanakartRkeShu tumun|samaanakartRkeShu tumun|samaanakartRkeShu tumun 3.3.158|समानकर्तृकेषु तुमुन्|समानकर्तृकेषु तुमुन् ३.३.१५८|३.३.१५८|३.३.१५८ समानकर्तृकेषु तुमुन्
The affix तुमुन् comes after a verb when another verb meaning 'to wish' is in construction, provided that the agent of both the verbs is the same.<br><br>Terms: तुमुन्

3.3.159|3.3.159 liNG cha|liNG cha|liNG cha 3.3.159|लिङ् च|लिङ् च ३.३.१५९|३.३.१५९|३.३.१५९ लिङ् च
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) is used after a verb when the verbs meaning 'to wish' are in construction with it and the agent of both the verbs is the same.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.160|3.3.160 ichChaarthebhyo vibhaaShaa vartamaane|ichChaarthebhyo vibhaaShaa vartamaane|ichChaarthebhyo vibhaaShaa vartamaane 3.3.160|इच्छार्थेभ्यो विभाषा वर्तमाने|इच्छार्थेभ्यो विभाषा वर्तमाने ३.३.१६०|३.३.१६०|३.३.१६० इच्छार्थेभ्यो विभाषा वर्तमाने
After roots meaning 'to wish' the लिङ् (Benedictive) is optionally used denoting the present time.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.161|3.3.161 vidhiniman‍traNaaman‍traNaadhiiSh‍TasaMprash‍napraarthaneShu liNG|vidhiniman‍traNaaman‍traNaadhiiSh‍TasaMprash‍napraarthaneShu liNG|vidhiniman‍traNaaman‍traNaadhiiSh‍TasaMprash‍napraarthaneShu liNG 3.3.161|विधिनिमन्‍त्रणामन्‍त्रणाधीष्‍टसंप्रश्‍नप्रार्थनेषु लिङ्|विधिनिमन्‍त्रणामन्‍त्रणाधीष्‍टसंप्रश्‍नप्रार्थनेषु लिङ् ३.३.१६१|३.३.१६१|३.३.१६१ विधिनिमन्‍त्रणामन्‍त्रणाधीष्‍टसंप्रश्‍नप्रार्थनेषु लिङ्
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes after a verb when the agent either 1. commands 2. invites 3. permits 4. politely expresses a wish 6. asks questions or 7. prays.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.162|3.3.162 loT cha|loT cha|loT cha 3.3.162|लोट् च|लोट् च ३.३.१६२|३.३.१६२|३.३.१६२ लोट् च
The affix लोट् (Imperative) is used after a root in the sense of commanding etc.<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.3.163|3.3.163 praiShaatisargapraaptakaaleShu kRtyaashcha|praiShaatisargapraaptakaaleShu kRtyaashcha|praiShaatisargapraaptakaaleShu kRtyaashcha 3.3.163|प्रैषातिसर्गप्राप्तकालेषु कृत्याश्च|प्रैषातिसर्गप्राप्तकालेषु कृत्याश्च ३.३.१६३|३.३.१६३|३.३.१६३ प्रैषातिसर्गप्राप्तकालेषु कृत्याश्च
The affixes called कृत्य and the affix लोट् (Imperative) come also after verbs, in the sense of direction, granting permission and proper (particular) time.<br><br>Terms: कृत्य and लोट्

3.3.164|3.3.164 liNG chordhvamauhuurtike|liNG chordhvamauhuurtike|liNG chordhvamauhuurtike 3.3.164|लिङ् चोर्ध्वमौहूर्तिके|लिङ् चोर्ध्वमौहूर्तिके ३.३.१६४|३.३.१६४|३.३.१६४ लिङ् चोर्ध्वमौहूर्तिके
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) (as well as कृत्य and लोट् (Imperative) ) is used (under similar circumstances in the sense of 1. direction 2. permission etc.) when the time is future by a मुहूर्त (48 minutes or an Indian hour); (or the Potential may be used as well when it signifies 'at this very moment').<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.165|3.3.165 sme loT|sme loT|sme loT 3.3.165|स्मे लोट्|स्मे लोट् ३.३.१६५|३.३.१६५|३.३.१६५ स्मे लोट्
The affix लोट् (Imperative) comes after a verb when the word स्म is in composition (when the sense is that of 'direction', permission etc.) and referring to time by a मुहूर्त (48 minutes or an Indian hour).<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.3.166|3.3.166 adhiiShTe cha|adhiiShTe cha|adhiiShTe cha 3.3.166|अधीष्टे च|अधीष्टे च ३.३.१६६|३.३.१६६|३.३.१६६ अधीष्टे च
And when 'wish' is meant ( the लोट् (Imperative) may be used when the word स्म is in composition with the verb.<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.3.167|3.3.167 kaalasamayavelaasu tumun|kaalasamayavelaasu tumun|kaalasamayavelaasu tumun 3.3.167|कालसमयवेलासु तुमुन्|कालसमयवेलासु तुमुन् ३.३.१६७|३.३.१६७|३.३.१६७ कालसमयवेलासु तुमुन्
The affix तुमुन् comes after a root wehnt he words 1. काल 2. समय 3. वेला (all meaning time) are in composition.<br><br>Terms: तुमुन्

3.3.168|3.3.168 liNG yadi|liNG yadi|liNG yadi 3.3.168|लिङ् यदि|लिङ् यदि ३.३.१६८|३.३.१६८|३.३.१६८ लिङ् यदि
The affix लिङ् (Benedictive) comes after a root when the word यद् is in composition and the words 1. काल 2. समय 3. वेला occur in construction.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.169|3.3.169 arhe kRtyatRchashcha|arhe kRtyatRchashcha|arhe kRtyatRchashcha 3.3.169|अर्हे कृत्यतृचश्च|अर्हे कृत्यतृचश्च ३.३.१६९|३.३.१६९|३.३.१६९ अर्हे कृत्यतृचश्च
The affixes कृत्य and the affix तृच are added to a root when fitness as regards the agent is implied (as well as in the affix लिङ् (Benedictive) ).<br><br>Terms: कृत्य and तृच

3.3.170|3.3.170 aavashyakaadhamarNyayorNiniH|aavashyakaadhamarNyayorNiniH|aavashyakaadhamarNyayorNiniH 3.3.170|आवश्यकाधमर्ण्ययोर्णिनिः|आवश्यकाधमर्ण्ययोर्णिनिः ३.३.१७०|३.३.१७०|३.३.१७० आवश्यकाधमर्ण्ययोर्णिनिः
The affix णिनि is added to the root in denoting agent, showing that there is some 'necessity' or 'indebtedness' or 'obligation' on the part of the agent in connection with the action denoted by the verb.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

3.3.171|3.3.171 kRtyaashcha|kRtyaashcha|kRtyaashcha 3.3.171|कृत्याश्च|कृत्याश्च ३.३.१७१|३.३.१७१|३.३.१७१ कृत्याश्च
The affixes called कृत्य also come after a root when the sense to be indicated is that of 'necessity' or 'obligation'.<br><br>Terms: कृत्य

3.3.172|3.3.172 shaki liNG cha|shaki liNG cha|shaki liNG cha 3.3.172|शकि लिङ् च|शकि लिङ् च ३.३.१७२|३.३.१७२|३.३.१७२ शकि लिङ् च
And the affix लिङ् (Benedictive) as well as the कृत्य affixes come after a verb when the sense is that of 'capability'.<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.3.173|3.3.173 aashiShi liNGloTau|aashiShi liNGloTau|aashiShi liNGloTau 3.3.173|आशिषि लिङ्लोटौ|आशिषि लिङ्लोटौ ३.३.१७३|३.३.१७३|३.३.१७३ आशिषि लिङ्लोटौ
The affixes लिङ् (Benedictive) and लोट् (Imperative) come after a verb by which 'benediction' is intended.<br><br>Terms: लिङ् and लोट्

3.3.174|3.3.174 ktichktau cha saMJNaayaam|ktichktau cha saMJNaayaam|ktichktau cha saMJNaayaam 3.3.174|क्तिच्क्तौ च संज्ञायाम्|क्तिच्क्तौ च संज्ञायाम् ३.३.१७४|३.३.१७४|३.३.१७४ क्तिच्क्तौ च संज्ञायाम्
The affixes क्तिच् and क्त are used after a root when benediction is intende, provided that the whole word so formed is an appellative.<br><br>Terms: क्तिच् and क्त

3.3.175|3.3.175 maaNGi luNG|maaNGi luNG|maaNGi luNG 3.3.175|माङि लुङ्|माङि लुङ् ३.३.१७५|३.३.१७५|३.३.१७५ माङि लुङ्
The affixes लुङ् (Aorist) comes after a verb when the word माण् is used in connection with it.<br><br>Terms: लुङ्

3.3.176|3.3.176 smottare laNG cha|smottare laNG cha|smottare laNG cha 3.3.176|स्मोत्तरे लङ् च|स्मोत्तरे लङ् च ३.३.१७६|३.३.१७६|३.३.१७६ स्मोत्तरे लङ् च
When the word मान is followed by स्म the affix लङ् (Imperfect Tense) as well as लुङ् (Aorist) may be used after a verbal root.<br><br>Terms: लङ्

3.4.1|3.4.1 dhaatusambandhe pratyayaaH|dhaatusambandhe pratyayaaH|dhaatusambandhe pratyayaaH 3.4.1|धातुसम्बन्धे प्रत्ययाः|धातुसम्बन्धे प्रत्ययाः ३.४.१|३.४.१|३.४.१ धातुसम्बन्धे प्रत्ययाः
When there is a syntactical relation between the senses of the verbs, the affixes are valid, even in denoting time other than that for which they have been specifically enjoined.<br><br>Terms: 

3.4.2|3.4.2 kriyaasamabhihaare loT|kriyaasamabhihaare loT|kriyaasamabhihaare loT 3.4.2|क्रियासमभिहारे लोट्|क्रियासमभिहारे लोट् ३.४.२|३.४.२|३.४.२ क्रियासमभिहारे लोट्
When the (frequency of) repetition of an action is indicated, the affix लोट् (Imperative) is added to the root and the verb is repeated. And the affixes हि and स्व or the affixes त and ध्वम् are the substitutes of लोट् (Imperative).<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.3|3.4.3 samuchchaye.anyatarasyaam|samuchchaye.anyatarasyaam|samuchchaye.anyatarasyaam 3.4.3|समुच्चयेऽन्यतरस्याम्|समुच्चयेऽन्यतरस्याम् ३.४.३|३.४.३|३.४.३ समुच्चयेऽन्यतरस्याम्
The affix लोट् (Imperative) is similarly added to the root optionally when several themes follow one after another.<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.4|3.4.4 yathaavidhyanuprayogaH puurvasmin|yathaavidhyanuprayogaH puurvasmin|yathaavidhyanuprayogaH puurvasmin 3.4.4|यथाविध्यनुप्रयोगः पूर्वस्मिन्|यथाविध्यनुप्रयोगः पूर्वस्मिन् ३.४.४|३.४.४|३.४.४ यथाविध्यनुप्रयोगः पूर्वस्मिन्
In the first case -- क्रियासमभिहारे लोट्, लोटो हिस्वौ, वा च तध्वमोः ३.४.२ the same verb must be used in the subsequent clause, as the verb which was put in the लोट् (Imperative Mood) .<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.5|3.4.5 samuchchaye saamaanyavachanasya|samuchchaye saamaanyavachanasya|samuchchaye saamaanyavachanasya 3.4.5|समुच्चये सामान्यवचनस्य|समुच्चये सामान्यवचनस्य ३.४.५|३.४.५|३.४.५ समुच्चये सामान्यवचनस्य
In the second case -- समुच्चयेऽन्यतरस्याम् ३.४.३, where many actions are spoken of together, the verb that is made to follow, should be such as has the sense common to all those verbs.<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.6|3.4.6 Chandasi luNGlaNGliTaH|Chandasi luNGlaNGliTaH|Chandasi luNGlaNGliTaH 3.4.6|छन्दसि लुङ्लङ्लिटः|छन्दसि लुङ्लङ्लिटः ३.४.६|३.४.६|३.४.६ छन्दसि लुङ्लङ्लिटः
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the लुङ् (Aorist), लङ् (Imperfect Tense) and लिट् (Perfect Tense) are optionally used in all tenses, in relation to verbs.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-लुङ्, लङ् and लिट्

3.4.7|3.4.7 liNGarthe leT|liNGarthe leT|liNGarthe leT 3.4.7|लिङर्थे लेट्|लिङर्थे लेट् ३.४.७|३.४.७|३.४.७ लिङर्थे लेट्
The affix लेट् (Vedic Subjunctive) is optionally used the छन्दस् (Vedas) wherever the लिङ् (Benedictive) can be used.<br><br>Terms: लेट्

3.4.8|3.4.8 upasaMvaadaashankayoshcha|upasaMvaadaashankayoshcha|upasaMvaadaashankayoshcha 3.4.8|उपसंवादाशङ्कयोश्च|उपसंवादाशङ्कयोश्च ३.४.८|३.४.८|३.४.८ उपसंवादाशङ्कयोश्च
Where a contingent promise (a reciprocal agreement) or apprehension is implied, the affix लेट् (Vedic Subjunctive) is used after a root in the छन्दस् (Vedas) Literature.<br><br>Terms: लेट्

3.4.9|3.4.9 tumarthe sesenaseasenksekasenadhyaiadhyainkadhyaikadhyainshadhyaishadhyaintavaitaveNGtavenaH|tumarthe sesenaseasenksekasenadhyaiadhyainkadhyaikadhyainshadhyaishadhyaintavaitaveNGtavenaH|tumarthe sesenaseasenksekasenadhyaiadhyainkadhyaikadhyainshadhyaishadhyaintavaitaveNGtavenaH 3.4.9|तुमर्थे सेसेनसेअसेन्क्सेकसेनध्यैअध्यैन्कध्यैकध्यैन्शध्यैशध्यैन्तवैतवेङ्तवेनः|तुमर्थे सेसेनसेअसेन्क्सेकसेनध्यैअध्यैन्कध्यैकध्यैन्शध्यैशध्यैन्तवैतवेङ्तवेनः ३.४.९|३.४.९|३.४.९ तुमर्थे सेसेनसेअसेन्क्सेकसेनध्यैअध्यैन्कध्यैकध्यैन्शध्यैशध्यैन्तवैतवेङ्तवेनः
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the following affixes come after the roots with the force of the affix तुमुन् , viz. 1. से 2. सेन् 3. असे 4. असेन् 5. क्से 6. क्सेन् 7. अध्यै 8. अध्यैन् 9. कध्यै 10. कध्यैन् 11. शाध्यै 12. शाध्यैन् 13. तवै 14. तवै 15. तवैन् ।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.4.10|3.4.10 prayai rohiShyai avyathiShyai|prayai rohiShyai avyathiShyai|prayai rohiShyai avyathiShyai 3.4.10|प्रयै रोहिष्यै अव्यथिष्यै|प्रयै रोहिष्यै अव्यथिष्यै ३.४.१०|३.४.१०|३.४.१० प्रयै रोहिष्यै अव्यथिष्यै
The words 1. प्रयै 2. रोहिष्यै 3. अव्यथिष्यै are irregularly formed Vedic Infinitives.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.4.11|3.4.11 dRshe vikhye cha|dRshe vikhye cha|dRshe vikhye cha 3.4.11|दृशे विख्ये च|दृशे विख्ये च ३.४.११|३.४.११|३.४.११ दृशे विख्ये च
The words 1. दृशे 2. विख्ये are anomalous Vedic Infinitives.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.4.12|3.4.12 shaki Namulkamulau|shaki Namulkamulau|shaki Namulkamulau 3.4.12|शकि णमुल्कमुलौ|शकि णमुल्कमुलौ ३.४.१२|३.४.१२|३.४.१२ शकि णमुल्कमुलौ
The affixes णमुल् and कमुल् are added to roots in the छन्दस् (Vedas) to form Infinitives, when they are governed by the verb शक् 'to be able'.<br><br>Terms: णमुल् and कमुल्

3.4.13|3.4.13 iishvare tosunkasunau|iishvare tosunkasunau|iishvare tosunkasunau 3.4.13|ईश्वरे तोसुन्कसुनौ|ईश्वरे तोसुन्कसुनौ ३.४.१३|३.४.१३|३.४.१३ ईश्वरे तोसुन्कसुनौ
The affixes तोसुन् and कसुन् are added to roots in the छन्दस् (Vedas) to form Infinitives, when the word ईश्वर is in composition.<br><br>Terms: तोसुन् and कसुन्

3.4.14|3.4.14 kRtyaarthe tavaikenkenyatvanaH|kRtyaarthe tavaikenkenyatvanaH|kRtyaarthe tavaikenkenyatvanaH 3.4.14|कृत्यार्थे तवैकेन्केन्यत्वनः|कृत्यार्थे तवैकेन्केन्यत्वनः ३.४.१४|३.४.१४|३.४.१४ कृत्यार्थे तवैकेन्केन्यत्वनः
The affixes 1. तवै 2. केन् 3. केन्य 4. त्वन् are added to roots in the छन्दस् (Vedas), in the sense of कृत्य-affixes.<br><br>Terms: तवै-केन्-केन्य-त्वन्

3.4.15|3.4.15 avachaxe cha|avachaxe cha|avachaxe cha 3.4.15|अवचक्षे च|अवचक्षे च ३.४.१५|३.४.१५|३.४.१५ अवचक्षे च
The word of अवचक्षे is an anomalous passive participle in the छन्दस् (Vedas).<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-अवचक्षे

3.4.16|3.4.16 bhaavalaxaNe stheNkRNJvadicharihutamijanibhyastosun|bhaavalaxaNe stheNkRNJvadicharihutamijanibhyastosun|bhaavalaxaNe stheNkRNJvadicharihutamijanibhyastosun 3.4.16|भावलक्षणे स्थेण्कृञ्वदिचरिहुतमिजनिभ्यस्तोसुन्|भावलक्षणे स्थेण्कृञ्वदिचरिहुतमिजनिभ्यस्तोसुन् ३.४.१६|३.४.१६|३.४.१६ भावलक्षणे स्थेण्कृञ्वदिचरिहुतमिजनिभ्यस्तोसुन्
The affix तोसुन् comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the following verbs, when mere name of the action is indicated viz. 1. स्था 'to stand' 2. इण् 'to go' 3. कृञ् 'to make' 4. वद् 'to speak' 5. चर् 'to go, to walk' 6. हु 'to sacrifice' 7. तम् 'to grow tired' 8. जन् 'to produce' ।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-तोसुन्

3.4.17|3.4.17 sRpitRdoH kasun|sRpitRdoH kasun|sRpitRdoH kasun 3.4.17|सृपितृदोः कसुन्|सृपितृदोः कसुन् ३.४.१७|३.४.१७|३.४.१७ सृपितृदोः कसुन्
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the affix कसुन् comes after the verbs 1. सृप् 'to creep' 2. तृद् 'to injure' , in the sense of Infinitives indicating name of action.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-कसुन्

3.4.18|3.4.18 alaNGkhalvoH pratiShedhayoH praachaaM ktvaa|alaNGkhalvoH pratiShedhayoH praachaaM ktvaa|alaNGkhalvoH pratiShedhayoH praachaaM ktvaa 3.4.18|अलङ्खल्वोः प्रतिषेधयोः प्राचां क्त्वा|अलङ्खल्वोः प्रतिषेधयोः प्राचां क्त्वा ३.४.१८|३.४.१८|३.४.१८ अलङ्खल्वोः प्रतिषेधयोः प्राचां क्त्वा
According to the opinion of the Eastern Grammarians, the affix क्त्वा comes after the verb, when there are in combination with it, the words अलम् and खलु expressing the sense of prohibition.<br><br>Terms: क्त्वा

3.4.19|3.4.19 udiichaaM maaNGo vyatiihaare|udiichaaM maaNGo vyatiihaare|udiichaaM maaNGo vyatiihaare 3.4.19|उदीचां माङो व्यतीहारे|उदीचां माङो व्यतीहारे ३.४.१९|३.४.१९|३.४.१९ उदीचां माङो व्यतीहारे
According to the opinion of the Eastern Grammarians, the affix क्त्वा is added to the root मेन् 'to exchange' when the sense is that of interchange, (though the action denoted by the former word is not prior to the action denoted by the latter word).<br><br>Terms: क्त्वा

3.4.20|3.4.20 paraavarayoge cha|paraavarayoge cha|paraavarayoge cha 3.4.20|परावरयोगे च|परावरयोगे च ३.४.२०|३.४.२०|३.४.२० परावरयोगे च
The affix क्त्वा is added to a root, to denote what is situated on the side - पर or on this side of something - अवर।<br><br>Terms: क्त्वा

3.4.21|3.4.21 samaanakartRkayoH puurvakaale|samaanakartRkayoH puurvakaale|samaanakartRkayoH puurvakaale 3.4.21|समानकर्तृकयोः पूर्वकाले|समानकर्तृकयोः पूर्वकाले ३.४.२१|३.४.२१|३.४.२१ समानकर्तृकयोः पूर्वकाले
When two actions have the same agent, the affix क्त्वा comes after that verb which takes place in time anterior to that of the other (i.e. Absolutive in त्व refers to that action which precedes in time).<br><br>Terms: क्त्वा

3.4.22|3.4.22 aabhiixNye Namul cha|aabhiixNye Namul cha|aabhiixNye Namul cha 3.4.22|आभीक्ष्ण्ये णमुल् च|आभीक्ष्ण्ये णमुल् च ३.४.२२|३.४.२२|३.४.२२ आभीक्ष्ण्ये णमुल् च
The affixes णमुल् and क्त्वा come after a root when reiteration is to be expressed.<br><br>Terms: णमुल् and क्त्वा

3.4.23|3.4.23 na yadyanaakaankShe|na yadyanaakaankShe|na yadyanaakaankShe 3.4.23|न यद्यनाकाङ्क्षे|न यद्यनाकाङ्क्षे ३.४.२३|३.४.२३|३.४.२३ न यद्यनाकाङ्क्षे
The affixes णमुल् and क्त्वा are not added to a root when the word यद् is used in a simple sentence which does not depend upon another to complete the sense.<br><br>Terms: णमुल् and क्त्वा

3.4.24|3.4.24 vibhaaShaa.agreprathamapuurveShu|vibhaaShaa.agreprathamapuurveShu|vibhaaShaa.agreprathamapuurveShu 3.4.24|विभाषाऽग्रेप्रथमपूर्वेषु|विभाषाऽग्रेप्रथमपूर्वेषु ३.४.२४|३.४.२४|३.४.२४ विभाषाऽग्रेप्रथमपूर्वेषु
The affixes णमुल् and क्त्वा come optionally after that verb which denotes the prior action, when both verbs have the same agent, provided that the following words are in composition - 1. अग्रे 2. प्रथम 3. पूर्व।<br><br>Terms: णमुल् and क्त्वा

3.4.25|3.4.25 karmaNyaakroshe kRNJaH khamuNJ|karmaNyaakroshe kRNJaH khamuNJ|karmaNyaakroshe kRNJaH khamuNJ 3.4.25|कर्मण्याक्रोशे कृञः खमुञ्|कर्मण्याक्रोशे कृञः खमुञ् ३.४.२५|३.४.२५|३.४.२५ कर्मण्याक्रोशे कृञः खमुञ्
The affix खमुञ् is added to the verb कृ 'to make', when a word in the Accusative -2nd case is in construction with it, if the sense intended implies 'abuse'.<br><br>Terms: खमुञ्

3.4.26|3.4.26 svaadumi Namul|svaadumi Namul|svaadumi Namul 3.4.26|स्वादुमि णमुल्|स्वादुमि णमुल् ३.४.२६|३.४.२६|३.४.२६ स्वादुमि णमुल्
(When the actions signified by the verbs कृ 'to make' and another have the same agent), the affix णमुल् is added to the verb कृ 'to make' which is concerned about a time anterior to that of the other), provided that a word signifying 'sweet' is in composition.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.27|3.4.27 anyathaivaMkathamitthaMsu siddhaaprayogashchet‌|anyathaivaMkathamitthaMsu siddhaaprayogashchet‌|anyathaivaMkathamitthaMsu siddhaaprayogashchet‌ 3.4.27|अन्यथैवंकथमित्थंसु सिद्धाप्रयोगश्चेत्‌|अन्यथैवंकथमित्थंसु सिद्धाप्रयोगश्चेत्‌ ३.४.२७|३.४.२७|३.४.२७ अन्यथैवंकथमित्थंसु सिद्धाप्रयोगश्चेत्‌
When the words 1. अन्यथा 'otherwise' 2. एवम् 'so' 3. कथम् 'how' 4. इत्थम् 'thus' are compounded with the verb, the णमुल् comes after कृ 'to make', if it be such that its omission would be unobjectionable.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.28|3.4.28 yathaatathayorasuuyaaprativachane|yathaatathayorasuuyaaprativachane|yathaatathayorasuuyaaprativachane 3.4.28|यथातथयोरसूयाप्रतिवचने|यथातथयोरसूयाप्रतिवचने ३.४.२८|३.४.२८|३.४.२८ यथातथयोरसूयाप्रतिवचने
The affix णमुल् is added to the root कृ 'to make', the words 1. यथा 2. तथा being compounded with it when an angry reply is made (if the omission of कृञ् is unobjectionable).<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.29|3.4.29 karmaNi dRshividoH saakalye|karmaNi dRshividoH saakalye|karmaNi dRshividoH saakalye 3.4.29|कर्मणि दृशिविदोः साकल्ये|कर्मणि दृशिविदोः साकल्ये ३.४.२९|३.४.२९|३.४.२९ कर्मणि दृशिविदोः साकल्ये
When the object is compounded with it, the verb दृश् 'to see' or विद् 'to know' takes the affix णमुल् to denote the total number of such objects.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.30|3.4.30 yaavati vindajiivoH|yaavati vindajiivoH|yaavati vindajiivoH 3.4.30|यावति विन्दजीवोः|यावति विन्दजीवोः ३.४.३०|३.४.३०|३.४.३० यावति विन्दजीवोः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb विद् 'to know' and जीव् 'to live' when the word यावत् is combined with them.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.31|3.4.31 charmodarayoH puureH|charmodarayoH puureH|charmodarayoH puureH 3.4.31|चर्मोदरयोः पूरेः|चर्मोदरयोः पूरेः ३.४.३१|३.४.३१|३.४.३१ चर्मोदरयोः पूरेः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb पुर् 'to fill' when the word चर्मन् and उदर् are compounded with it.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.32|3.4.32 varShapramaaNa Ulopashchaasyaanyatarasyaam|varShapramaaNa Ulopashchaasyaanyatarasyaam|varShapramaaNa Ulopashchaasyaanyatarasyaam 3.4.32|वर्षप्रमाण ऊलोपश्चास्यान्यतरस्याम्|वर्षप्रमाण ऊलोपश्चास्यान्यतरस्याम् ३.४.३२|३.४.३२|३.४.३२ वर्षप्रमाण ऊलोपश्चास्यान्यतरस्याम्
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb पुर् 'to fill' when the word so formed expresses a measure of rainfall and optionally the long ऊ of this पुर् is elided.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.33|3.4.33 chele knopeH|chele knopeH|chele knopeH 3.4.33|चेले क्नोपेः|चेले क्नोपेः ३.४.३३|३.४.३३|३.४.३३ चेले क्नोपेः
The affix णमुल् comes after the causative of the root क्नूय् 'to wet', when there is compounded with a noun denoting 'clothing', in the Accusative -2nd case, as an उपपद , if the whole word so formed expresses a measure of the rainfall.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.34|3.4.34 nimuulasamuulayoH kaShaH|nimuulasamuulayoH kaShaH|nimuulasamuulayoH kaShaH 3.4.34|निमूलसमूलयोः कषः|निमूलसमूलयोः कषः ३.४.३४|३.४.३४|३.४.३४ निमूलसमूलयोः कषः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb कष् 'to rub' when the words निमूल and समूल are compounded with it in the Accusative -2nd case.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.35|3.4.35 shuShkachuurNaruuxeShu piShaH|shuShkachuurNaruuxeShu piShaH|shuShkachuurNaruuxeShu piShaH 3.4.35|शुष्कचूर्णरूक्षेषु पिषः|शुष्कचूर्णरूक्षेषु पिषः ३.४.३५|३.४.३५|३.४.३५ शुष्कचूर्णरूक्षेषु पिषः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb पिष् 'to grind', when the words 1. शुष्क 'dry' 2. चूर्ण 'powder' 3. रूक्षे 'dry', in the Accusative -2nd case are compounded with it.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.36|3.4.36 samuulaakRtajiiveShu hankRNJgrahaH|samuulaakRtajiiveShu hankRNJgrahaH|samuulaakRtajiiveShu hankRNJgrahaH 3.4.36|समूलाकृतजीवेषु हन्कृञ्ग्रहः|समूलाकृतजीवेषु हन्कृञ्ग्रहः ३.४.३६|३.४.३६|३.४.३६ समूलाकृतजीवेषु हन्कृञ्ग्रहः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verbs 1. हन् 'to kill' 2. कृ 'to make' 3. ग्रह् 'to seize', when the words 1. समूल 2. आकृत 3. जीव in the Accusative -2nd case are respectively compounded with them.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.37|3.4.37 karaNe hanaH|karaNe hanaH|karaNe hanaH 3.4.37|करणे हनः|करणे हनः ३.४.३७|३.४.३७|३.४.३७ करणे हनः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb हन् 'to kill' when a word in the Instrumental -3rd case is in composition with it.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.38|3.4.38 snehane piShaH|snehane piShaH|snehane piShaH 3.4.38|स्नेहने पिषः|स्नेहने पिषः ३.४.३८|३.४.३८|३.४.३८ स्नेहने पिषः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb पिष् 'to grind' when a word in the Instrumental -3rd case denoting 'liquid' is in composition.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.39|3.4.39 haste varttigrahoH|haste varttigrahoH|haste varttigrahoH 3.4.39|हस्ते वर्त्तिग्रहोः|हस्ते वर्त्तिग्रहोः ३.४.३९|३.४.३९|३.४.३९ हस्ते वर्त्तिग्रहोः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verbs वर्त्ति (the causative of वृत्) and ग्रह् 'to seize' when a word denoting 'hand' in the Instrumental -3rd case, is in composition.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.40|3.4.40 sve puShaH|sve puShaH|sve puShaH 3.4.40|स्वे पुषः|स्वे पुषः ३.४.४०|३.४.४०|३.४.४० स्वे पुषः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verb पुष् 'to feed' when a word in the Instrumental -3rd case having the sense of स्व is in composition.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.41|3.4.41 adhikaraNe bandhaH|adhikaraNe bandhaH|adhikaraNe bandhaH 3.4.41|अधिकरणे बन्धः|अधिकरणे बन्धः ३.४.४१|३.४.४१|३.४.४१ अधिकरणे बन्धः
The affix णमुल् comes after the बन्ध् 'to bind' when a word expressing location is in construction with it.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.42|3.4.42 saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam 3.4.42|संज्ञायाम्|संज्ञायाम् ३.४.४२|३.४.४२|३.४.४२ संज्ञायाम्
The affix णमुल् comes after the बन्ध् 'to bind' when a word so formed denotes an appellative.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.43|3.4.43 kartrorjiivapuruShayornashivahoH|kartrorjiivapuruShayornashivahoH|kartrorjiivapuruShayornashivahoH 3.4.43|कर्त्रोर्जीवपुरुषयोर्नशिवहोः|कर्त्रोर्जीवपुरुषयोर्नशिवहोः ३.४.४३|३.४.४३|३.४.४३ कर्त्रोर्जीवपुरुषयोर्नशिवहोः
The affix णमुल् comes after the roots नश् 'to destroy' and वह् 'to carry' when the words जीव 'life' and पुरुष 'person' expressing the agent of these verbs, are respectively in construction with them.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.44|3.4.44 Urdhve shuShipuuroH|Urdhve shuShipuuroH|Urdhve shuShipuuroH 3.4.44|ऊर्ध्वे शुषिपूरोः|ऊर्ध्वे शुषिपूरोः ३.४.४४|३.४.४४|३.४.४४ ऊर्ध्वे शुषिपूरोः
The affix णमुल् comes after the roots शुष् 'to dry' and पूर् 'to fill' when the word ऊर्ध्व denoting an agent is in composition with them.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.45|3.4.45 upamaane karmaNi cha|upamaane karmaNi cha|upamaane karmaNi cha 3.4.45|उपमाने कर्मणि च|उपमाने कर्मणि च ३.४.४५|३.४.४५|३.४.४५ उपमाने कर्मणि च
The affix णमुल् comes after a root when an object or an agent denoting similitude is in composition with it.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.46|3.4.46 kaShaadiShu yathaavidhyanuprayogaH|kaShaadiShu yathaavidhyanuprayogaH|kaShaadiShu yathaavidhyanuprayogaH 3.4.46|कषादिषु यथाविध्यनुप्रयोगः|कषादिषु यथाविध्यनुप्रयोगः ३.४.४६|३.४.४६|३.४.४६ कषादिषु यथाविध्यनुप्रयोगः
The same verb should be used after the gerunds formed from the verbs कष् 'to rub' etc. as the verb from which the gerund is derived.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.47|3.4.47 upadaMshastRtiiyaayaam|upadaMshastRtiiyaayaam|upadaMshastRtiiyaayaam 3.4.47|उपदंशस्तृतीयायाम्|उपदंशस्तृतीयायाम् ३.४.४७|३.४.४७|३.४.४७ उपदंशस्तृतीयायाम्
The affix णमुल् comes after a root दंश् 'to bite' preceded by the preposition उप when a word ending with the Instrumental -3rd case is in composition with it..<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.48|3.4.48 hiMsaarthaanaaM cha samaanakarmakaaNaam|hiMsaarthaanaaM cha samaanakarmakaaNaam|hiMsaarthaanaaM cha samaanakarmakaaNaam 3.4.48|हिंसार्थानां च समानकर्मकाणाम्|हिंसार्थानां च समानकर्मकाणाम् ३.४.४८|३.४.४८|३.४.४८ हिंसार्थानां च समानकर्मकाणाम्
The affix णमुल् comes after the roots having the sense of हिंस 'to injure, to strike' when the object of this gerund is the same as the object of the main verb and when the noun with which it is compounded ends with the Instrumental -3rd case-affix.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.49|3.4.49 saptamyaaM chopapiiDarudhakarShaH|saptamyaaM chopapiiDarudhakarShaH|saptamyaaM chopapiiDarudhakarShaH 3.4.49|सप्तम्यां चोपपीडरुधकर्षः|सप्तम्यां चोपपीडरुधकर्षः ३.४.४९|३.४.४९|३.४.४९ सप्तम्यां चोपपीडरुधकर्षः
The affix णमुल् comes after the roots 1. पीड् 'to press' 2. रुद्ध् 'to obstruct' 3. कृष् 'to draw' when they are preceded by the preposition उप and when they are compounded with nouns ending with the Locative -7th case-affix.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.50|3.4.50 samaasattau|samaasattau|samaasattau 3.4.50|समासत्तौ|समासत्तौ ३.४.५०|३.४.५०|३.४.५० समासत्तौ
(The affix णमुल् comes after a root when a word in the Locative -7th case or Instrumental -3rd case is in composition with it) and when immediate contiguity is intended i.e. 'to fall together by the ears'.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.51|3.4.51 pramaaNe cha|pramaaNe cha|pramaaNe cha 3.4.51|प्रमाणे च|प्रमाणे च ३.४.५१|३.४.५१|३.४.५१ प्रमाणे च
The affix णमुल् comes after a root when a noun in the Instrumental -3rd case or Locative -7th case is in composition with it and when measure of length is intended.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.52|3.4.52 apaadaane pariipsaayaam|apaadaane pariipsaayaam|apaadaane pariipsaayaam 3.4.52|अपादाने परीप्सायाम्|अपादाने परीप्सायाम् ३.४.५२|३.४.५२|३.४.५२ अपादाने परीप्सायाम्
The affix णमुल् is added to the root when a noun in the Ablative -5th case is in composition and when 'haste' is intended.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.53|3.4.53 dvitiiyaayaaM cha|dvitiiyaayaaM cha|dvitiiyaayaaM cha 3.4.53|द्वितीयायां च|द्वितीयायां च ३.४.५३|३.४.५३|३.४.५३ द्वितीयायां च
The affix णमुल् is added to the root when a word in the Accusative -2nd case is in composition and when 'haste' is intended.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.54|3.4.54 svaange.adhruve|svaange.adhruve|svaange.adhruve 3.4.54|स्वाङ्गेऽध्रुवे|स्वाङ्गेऽध्रुवे ३.४.५४|३.४.५४|३.४.५४ स्वाङ्गेऽध्रुवे
The affix णमुल् comes after a verb when a word in the Accusative -2nd case is in composition, signifying the limbs of one's own body, when the limb is such that its loss will not destroy life.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.55|3.4.55 pariklishyamaane cha|pariklishyamaane cha|pariklishyamaane cha 3.4.55|परिक्लिश्यमाने च|परिक्लिश्यमाने च ३.४.५५|३.४.५५|३.४.५५ परिक्लिश्यमाने च
The affix णमुल् comes after a root when a word in the Accusative -2nd case denoting a limb of one's own body, which is completely afflicted by the action, is in composition.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.56|3.4.56 vishipatipadiskandaaM vyaapyamaanaasevyamaanayoH|vishipatipadiskandaaM vyaapyamaanaasevyamaanayoH|vishipatipadiskandaaM vyaapyamaanaasevyamaanayoH 3.4.56|विशिपतिपदिस्कन्दां व्याप्यमानासेव्यमानयोः|विशिपतिपदिस्कन्दां व्याप्यमानासेव्यमानयोः ३.४.५६|३.४.५६|३.४.५६ विशिपतिपदिस्कन्दां व्याप्यमानासेव्यमानयोः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verbs 1. विश् 'to enter' 2. पत् 'to fall' 3. पद् 'to pace, to go' 4. स्कन्द् 'to leap', when a word in Accusative -2nd case is in composition and when the sense denoted is that of complete pervasion and total abosrption.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.57|3.4.57 asyatitRShoH kriyaa.antare kaaleShu|asyatitRShoH kriyaa.antare kaaleShu|asyatitRShoH kriyaa.antare kaaleShu 3.4.57|अस्यतितृषोः क्रियाऽन्तरे कालेषु|अस्यतितृषोः क्रियाऽन्तरे कालेषु ३.४.५७|३.४.५७|३.४.५७ अस्यतितृषोः क्रियाऽन्तरे कालेषु
The affix णमुल् comes after the verbs 1. अस् 'to throw' 2. तृष् 'to be thirsty' when it is intended to express an intermission of the action denoted by the root, provided that a word in the Accusative -2nd case denoting time is in composition.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.58|3.4.58 naamnyaadishigrahoH|naamnyaadishigrahoH|naamnyaadishigrahoH 3.4.58|नाम्न्यादिशिग्रहोः|नाम्न्यादिशिग्रहोः ३.४.५८|३.४.५८|३.४.५८ नाम्न्यादिशिग्रहोः
The affix णमुल् comes after the verbs 1. आदिश् 2. ग्रह् 'to seize' when the word नामन् 'name' in the Accusative -2nd case is in composition.<br><br>Terms: णमुल्

3.4.59|3.4.59 avyaye.ayathaabhipretaakhyaane kRNJaH ktvaaNamulau|avyaye.ayathaabhipretaakhyaane kRNJaH ktvaaNamulau|avyaye.ayathaabhipretaakhyaane kRNJaH ktvaaNamulau 3.4.59|अव्ययेऽयथाभिप्रेताख्याने कृञः क्त्वाणमुलौ|अव्ययेऽयथाभिप्रेताख्याने कृञः क्त्वाणमुलौ ३.४.५९|३.४.५९|३.४.५९ अव्ययेऽयथाभिप्रेताख्याने कृञः क्त्वाणमुलौ
The affixes क्तवा and णमुल् come after the root कृ 'to make' when an indeclinable word in composition with it and the meaning is the communication of anything in a disagreeable or undesired way.<br><br>Terms: क्तवा and णमुल्

3.4.60|3.4.60 tiryachyapavarge|tiryachyapavarge|tiryachyapavarge 3.4.60|तिर्यच्यपवर्गे|तिर्यच्यपवर्गे ३.४.६०|३.४.६०|३.४.६० तिर्यच्यपवर्गे
The affixes क्तवा and णमुल् come after the root कृ 'to make' when the word त्रियक् is in composition in the sense of 'carrying to the end'.<br><br>Terms: क्तवा and णमुल्

3.4.61|3.4.61 svaange taspratyaye kRbhvoH|svaange taspratyaye kRbhvoH|svaange taspratyaye kRbhvoH 3.4.61|स्वाङ्गे तस्प्रत्यये कृभ्वोः|स्वाङ्गे तस्प्रत्यये कृभ्वोः ३.४.६१|३.४.६१|३.४.६१ स्वाङ्गे तस्प्रत्यये कृभ्वोः
The affixes क्तवा and णमुल् are added to the roots कृ 'to make' and भू 'to be', in composition with a word denoting a member of one's own body when the affix तस् is joined thereto.<br><br>Terms: क्तवा and णमुल्

3.4.62|3.4.62 naadhaa.arthapratyaye chvyarthe|naadhaa.arthapratyaye chvyarthe|naadhaa.arthapratyaye chvyarthe 3.4.62|नाधाऽर्थप्रत्यये च्व्यर्थे|नाधाऽर्थप्रत्यये च्व्यर्थे ३.४.६२|३.४.६२|३.४.६२ नाधाऽर्थप्रत्यये च्व्यर्थे
The affixes क्तवा and णमुल् are added to the roots कृ 'to make' and भू 'to be', when a word ending in the affix ना -- विनञ्भ्यां नानाञौ नसह ५.२.२७, or in an affix having the force of धा -- संख्याया विधाऽर्थे धा ५.३.४२, or having the sense of the affix च्वि 'to make or to become something with it had not been before' -- अभूततद्भावे कृभ्वस्तियोगे सम्पद्यकर्तरि च्विः ५.४.५०, is in composition.<br><br>Terms: क्तवा and णमुल्

3.4.63|3.4.63 tuuShNiimi bhuvaH|tuuShNiimi bhuvaH|tuuShNiimi bhuvaH 3.4.63|तूष्णीमि भुवः|तूष्णीमि भुवः ३.४.६३|३.४.६३|३.४.६३ तूष्णीमि भुवः
The affixes क्तवा and णमुल् are added to the roots भू 'to be', when the word तूष्णीम् 'silently' is in composition.<br><br>Terms: क्तवा and णमुल्

3.4.64|3.4.64 anvachyaanulomye|anvachyaanulomye|anvachyaanulomye 3.4.64|अन्वच्यानुलोम्ये|अन्वच्यानुलोम्ये ३.४.६४|३.४.६४|३.४.६४ अन्वच्यानुलोम्ये
The affixes क्तवा and णमुल् come after the root भू 'to be' when the word अन्वक् in the sense of being favourably disposed, is in composition.<br><br>Terms: क्तवा and णमुल्

3.4.65|3.4.65 shakadhRShaJNaaglaaghaTarabhalabhakramasahaarhaastyartheShu tumun|shakadhRShaJNaaglaaghaTarabhalabhakramasahaarhaastyartheShu tumun|shakadhRShaJNaaglaaghaTarabhalabhakramasahaarhaastyartheShu tumun 3.4.65|शकधृषज्ञाग्लाघटरभलभक्रमसहार्हास्त्यर्थेषु तुमुन्|शकधृषज्ञाग्लाघटरभलभक्रमसहार्हास्त्यर्थेषु तुमुन् ३.४.६५|३.४.६५|३.४.६५ शकधृषज्ञाग्लाघटरभलभक्रमसहार्हास्त्यर्थेषु तुमुन्
The affix तुमुन् is added to every verb when another verb having the sense of 1. शक् 'to be able' 2. धृष् 'to make bold' 3. ज्ञा 'to know' 4. ग्लै 'to be weary' 5. घट् 'to strive' 6. रभ् 'to begin' 7. लभ् 'to get' 8. क्रम् 'to set about' 9. सह् 'to bear' 10. अर्ह् 'to be pleased or to condescend' 11. अस् 'to be'.<br><br>Terms: तुमुन्

3.4.66|3.4.66 paryaaptivachaneShvalamartheShu|paryaaptivachaneShvalamartheShu|paryaaptivachaneShvalamartheShu 3.4.66|पर्याप्तिवचनेष्वलमर्थेषु|पर्याप्तिवचनेष्वलमर्थेषु ३.४.६६|३.४.६६|३.४.६६ पर्याप्तिवचनेष्वलमर्थेषु
The affix तुमुन् comes after a verb haivng in composition with it अलम् and its synonyms when these words express to be capable of something.<br><br>Terms: तुमुन्

3.4.67|3.4.67 kartari kRt‌|kartari kRt‌|kartari kRt‌ 3.4.67|कर्तरि कृत्‌|कर्तरि कृत्‌ ३.४.६७|३.४.६७|३.४.६७ कर्तरि कृत्‌
The affixes calle कृत् are used in the sense of an agent.<br><br>Terms: कृत्

3.4.68|3.4.68 bhavyageyapravachaniiyopasthaaniiyajanyaaplaavyaapaatyaa vaa|bhavyageyapravachaniiyopasthaaniiyajanyaaplaavyaapaatyaa vaa|bhavyageyapravachaniiyopasthaaniiyajanyaaplaavyaapaatyaa vaa 3.4.68|भव्यगेयप्रवचनीयोपस्थानीयजन्याप्लाव्यापात्या वा|भव्यगेयप्रवचनीयोपस्थानीयजन्याप्लाव्यापात्या वा ३.४.६८|३.४.६८|३.४.६८ भव्यगेयप्रवचनीयोपस्थानीयजन्याप्लाव्यापात्या वा
The words 1. भव्य 2. गेय 3. प्रवचनीय 3. उपस्थानीय 4. जन्य 5. आप्लाव्य 6. आपात्य may be optionally be used to denote the agent.<br><br>Terms: कृत्

3.4.69|3.4.69 laH karmaNi cha bhaave chaakarmakebhyaH.|laH karmaNi cha bhaave chaakarmakebhyaH.|laH karmaNi cha bhaave chaakarmakebhyaH. 3.4.69|लः कर्मणि च भावे चाकर्मकेभ्यः.|लः कर्मणि च भावे चाकर्मकेभ्यः. ३.४.६९|३.४.६९|३.४.६९ लः कर्मणि च भावे चाकर्मकेभ्यः.
The tense affixes called ल are used in denoting the object and the agent and after intransitive verbs, they denote the action as well as the agent.<br><br>Terms: ल

3.4.70|3.4.70 tayoreva kRtyaktakhalarthaaH|tayoreva kRtyaktakhalarthaaH|tayoreva kRtyaktakhalarthaaH 3.4.70|तयोरेव कृत्यक्तखलर्थाः|तयोरेव कृत्यक्तखलर्थाः ३.४.७०|३.४.७०|३.४.७० तयोरेव कृत्यक्तखलर्थाः
The affixes called कृत्य and the affix called क्त and those that have the sense of खल् have only these last two senses, viz. an action and an object (भाव and कर्म).<br><br>Terms: कृत्य and क्त

3.4.71|3.4.71 adikarmaNi ktaH kartari cha|adikarmaNi ktaH kartari cha|adikarmaNi ktaH kartari cha 3.4.71|अदिकर्मणि क्तः कर्तरि च|अदिकर्मणि क्तः कर्तरि च ३.४.७१|३.४.७१|३.४.७१ अदिकर्मणि क्तः कर्तरि च
The affix क्त also denotes the agent when it expresses a beginning of an action.<br><br>Terms: क्त

3.4.72|3.4.72 gatyarthaakarmakashliShashiiNGsthaa.a.asavasajanaruhajiiryatibhyashcha|gatyarthaakarmakashliShashiiNGsthaa.a.asavasajanaruhajiiryatibhyashcha|gatyarthaakarmakashliShashiiNGsthaa.a.asavasajanaruhajiiryatibhyashcha 3.4.72|गत्यर्थाकर्मकश्लिषशीङ्स्थाऽऽसवसजनरुहजीर्यतिभ्यश्च|गत्यर्थाकर्मकश्लिषशीङ्स्थाऽऽसवसजनरुहजीर्यतिभ्यश्च ३.४.७२|३.४.७२|३.४.७२ गत्यर्थाकर्मकश्लिषशीङ्स्थाऽऽसवसजनरुहजीर्यतिभ्यश्च
The affix क्त is used in denoting the agent as well as the act and the object after verbs implying motion after intransitive roots and after the verbs 1. श्लिष् 'to embrace' 2. शि 'to lie down' 3. स्था 'to stand' 4. आस् 'to sit' 5. वस् 'to dwell' 6. जन् 'to produce' 7. रुह् 'to mount' 8. जृ 'to grow old'.<br><br>Terms: क्त

3.4.73|3.4.73 daashagoghnau sampradaane|daashagoghnau sampradaane|daashagoghnau sampradaane 3.4.73|दाशगोघ्नौ सम्प्रदाने|दाशगोघ्नौ सम्प्रदाने ३.४.७३|३.४.७३|३.४.७३ दाशगोघ्नौ सम्प्रदाने
The word दाश and गोघ्न are irregularly formed and the affix in these denotes the idea of the Dative or Receipient.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.4.74|3.4.74 bhiimaadayo.apaadaane|bhiimaadayo.apaadaane|bhiimaadayo.apaadaane 3.4.74|भीमादयोऽपादाने|भीमादयोऽपादाने ३.४.७४|३.४.७४|३.४.७४ भीमादयोऽपादाने
The words भीम etc. are irregularly formed and denote ablation.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

3.4.75|3.4.75 taabhyaamanyatroNaadayaH|taabhyaamanyatroNaadayaH|taabhyaamanyatroNaadayaH 3.4.75|ताभ्यामन्यत्रोणादयः|ताभ्यामन्यत्रोणादयः ३.४.७५|३.४.७५|३.४.७५ ताभ्यामन्यत्रोणादयः
The words formed by उणादि affixes denote other ideas other than these two - 1. Reciepient 2. Ablation.<br><br>Terms: उणादि

3.4.76|3.4.76 kto.adhikaraNe cha dhrauvyagatipratyavasaanaarthebhyaH|kto.adhikaraNe cha dhrauvyagatipratyavasaanaarthebhyaH|kto.adhikaraNe cha dhrauvyagatipratyavasaanaarthebhyaH 3.4.76|क्तोऽधिकरणे च ध्रौव्यगतिप्रत्यवसानार्थेभ्यः|क्तोऽधिकरणे च ध्रौव्यगतिप्रत्यवसानार्थेभ्यः ३.४.७६|३.४.७६|३.४.७६ क्तोऽधिकरणे च ध्रौव्यगतिप्रत्यवसानार्थेभ्यः
The affix क्त which is ordained after roots denoting fixedness (to cling to a place), motion and taking gives the sense of location as well.<br><br>Terms: क्त

3.4.77|3.4.77 lasya|lasya|lasya 3.4.77|लस्य|लस्य ३.४.७७|३.४.७७|३.४.७७ लस्य
In the place of ल will be substituted the affixes we shall announce hereafter.<br><br>Terms: ल

3.4.78|3.4.78 tiptasjhisipthasthamibvasmas taataaMjhathaasaathaaMdhvamiDvahimahiNG|tiptasjhisipthasthamibvasmas taataaMjhathaasaathaaMdhvamiDvahimahiNG|tiptasjhisipthasthamibvasmas taataaMjhathaasaathaaMdhvamiDvahimahiNG 3.4.78|तिप्तस्झिसिप्थस्थमिब्वस्मस् तातांझथासाथांध्वमिड्वहिमहिङ्|तिप्तस्झिसिप्थस्थमिब्वस्मस् तातांझथासाथांध्वमिड्वहिमहिङ् ३.४.७८|३.४.७८|३.४.७८ तिप्तस्झिसिप्थस्थमिब्वस्मस् तातांझथासाथांध्वमिड्वहिमहिङ्
The following are the substitutes of ल - तिप् - तस् - झि - सिप् - थस् - थ - मिप् - वस् - मस् - त - आताम् - झ - थास् - आथाम् - ध्वम् - इट् - वहि - महिङ् ।<br><br>Terms: ल

3.4.79|3.4.79 Tita aatmanepadaanaaM Tere|Tita aatmanepadaanaaM Tere|Tita aatmanepadaanaaM Tere 3.4.79|टित आत्मनेपदानां टेरे|टित आत्मनेपदानां टेरे ३.४.७९|३.४.७९|३.४.७९ टित आत्मनेपदानां टेरे
The substitute ए replaces he last vowel, with the consonant that follows it, of the आत्मनेपद substitutes of that ल which has an indicatory ट्।<br><br>Terms: ल

3.4.80|3.4.80 thaasasse|thaasasse|thaasasse 3.4.80|थासस्से|थासस्से ३.४.८०|३.४.८०|३.४.८० थासस्से
The word से is the substitute of थास् in those tenses that have an indicatory ट्।<br><br>Terms: ल-टित्

3.4.81|3.4.81 liTastajhayoreshirech|liTastajhayoreshirech|liTastajhayoreshirech 3.4.81|लिटस्तझयोरेशिरेच्|लिटस्तझयोरेशिरेच् ३.४.८१|३.४.८१|३.४.८१ लिटस्तझयोरेशिरेच्
The words एश् and इरेच् are the substitutes of ट and झ respectively in the लिट् (Perfect Tense).<br><br>Terms: ल-टित्

3.4.82|3.4.82 parasmaipadaanaaM NalatususthalathusaNalvamaaH|parasmaipadaanaaM NalatususthalathusaNalvamaaH|parasmaipadaanaaM NalatususthalathusaNalvamaaH 3.4.82|परस्मैपदानां णलतुसुस्थलथुसणल्वमाः|परस्मैपदानां णलतुसुस्थलथुसणल्वमाः ३.४.८२|३.४.८२|३.४.८२ परस्मैपदानां णलतुसुस्थलथुसणल्वमाः
In the room of the परस्मैपद affixes, the following are substituted in the लिट् (Perfect Tense). Singular - णल् (अ), थल् (थ), णल् (अ). Dual - अतुस् (अतुः), अथुस् (अथुः), व (व). Plural - उस् (उः) , अ (अ), म (म).<br><br>Terms: लिट्

3.4.83|3.4.83 vido laTo vaa|vido laTo vaa|vido laTo vaa 3.4.83|विदो लटो वा|विदो लटो वा ३.४.८३|३.४.८३|३.४.८३ विदो लटो वा
The above nine affixes of the लिट् (Perfect Tense) are optionally added in the लट् (Present Tense) also after the verb विद् 'to know'.<br><br>Terms: लिट् and लट्

3.4.84|3.4.84 bruvaH pancaanaamaadita aaho bruvaH|bruvaH pancaanaamaadita aaho bruvaH|bruvaH pancaanaamaadita aaho bruvaH 3.4.84|ब्रुवः पञ्चानामादित आहो ब्रुवः|ब्रुवः पञ्चानामादित आहो ब्रुवः ३.४.८४|३.४.८४|३.४.८४ ब्रुवः पञ्चानामादित आहो ब्रुवः
Instead of the first 5 tense-affixes in the लट् (Present Tense) coming after the verb ब्रु 'to speak' there may optionally be the affixes of the लिट् (Perfect Tense) ; आह being at the same time the substitute in the room of ब्रु 'to speak'.<br><br>Terms: लट्

3.4.85|3.4.85 loTo laNGvat‌|loTo laNGvat‌|loTo laNGvat‌ 3.4.85|लोटो लङ्वत्‌|लोटो लङ्वत्‌ ३.४.८५|३.४.८५|३.४.८५ लोटो लङ्वत्‌
The personal endings of the लोट् (Imperative Mood) are as those of the लङ् (Imperfect Tense).<br><br>Terms: लोट् and लङ्

3.4.86|3.4.86 eruH|eruH|eruH 3.4.86|एरुः|एरुः ३.४.८६|३.४.८६|३.४.८६ एरुः
In the लोट् (Imperative Mood) उ is the substitute of इ।<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.87|3.4.87 serhyapichcha|serhyapichcha|serhyapichcha 3.4.87|सेर्ह्यपिच्च|सेर्ह्यपिच्च ३.४.८७|३.४.८७|३.४.८७ सेर्ह्यपिच्च
In the लोट् (Imperative Mood) , हि is substituted for सि and this has not the indicatory प् of सिप् , i.e. it is acutely accented.<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.88|3.4.88 vaa Chandasi|vaa Chandasi|vaa Chandasi 3.4.88|वा छन्दसि|वा छन्दसि ३.४.८८|३.४.८८|३.४.८८ वा छन्दसि
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the substitute of हि is optionally treated as not having an indicatory प्।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

3.4.89|3.4.89 merniH|merniH|merniH 3.4.89|मेर्निः|मेर्निः ३.४.८९|३.४.८९|३.४.८९ मेर्निः
In the लोट् (Imperative Mood) नि is substituted for the affix मि।<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.90|3.4.90 aametaH|aametaH|aametaH 3.4.90|आमेतः|आमेतः ३.४.९०|३.४.९०|३.४.९० आमेतः
In the लोट् (Imperative Mood) आम् is substituted for what would have substituted otherwise ए by टित आत्मनेपदानां टेरे ३.४.७९.<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.91|3.4.91 savaabhyaaM vaamau|savaabhyaaM vaamau|savaabhyaaM vaamau 3.4.91|सवाभ्यां वामौ|सवाभ्यां वामौ ३.४.९१|३.४.९१|३.४.९१ सवाभ्यां वामौ
For such an ए coming after स् , is substituted व् and for that coming after व् , is substituted अम् , in the (Imperative Mood).<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.92|3.4.92 aaDuttamasya pichcha|aaDuttamasya pichcha|aaDuttamasya pichcha 3.4.92|आडुत्तमस्य पिच्च|आडुत्तमस्य पिच्च ३.४.९२|३.४.९२|३.४.९२ आडुत्तमस्य पिच्च
In the लोट् (Imperative Mood) आट् is the augment of the affixes the first person and the termination is as if it had an indicatory प्।<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.93|3.4.93 eta ai|eta ai|eta ai 3.4.93|एत ऐ|एत ऐ ३.४.९३|३.४.९३|३.४.९३ एत ऐ
The ऐ is substituted for ए forming part of the affixes of the first person of the लोट् (Imperative Mood).<br><br>Terms: लोट्

3.4.94|3.4.94 leTo.aDaaTau|leTo.aDaaTau|leTo.aDaaTau 3.4.94|लेटोऽडाटौ|लेटोऽडाटौ ३.४.९४|३.४.९४|३.४.९४ लेटोऽडाटौ
The augments अट् and आट् are added to the तिङ् (Personal Endings) of the लेट् (Vedic Subjunctive).<br><br>Terms: लेट्

3.4.95|3.4.95 aata ai|aata ai|aata ai 3.4.95|आत ऐ|आत ऐ ३.४.९५|३.४.९५|३.४.९५ आत ऐ
In the लेट् (Vedic Subjunctive) ऐ is the substitute of आ in the first and second person dual of the आत्मनेपद ।<br><br>Terms: लेट्

3.4.96|3.4.96 vaito.anyatra|vaito.anyatra|vaito.anyatra 3.4.96|वैतोऽन्यत्र|वैतोऽन्यत्र ३.४.९६|३.४.९६|३.४.९६ वैतोऽन्यत्र
In the लेट् (Vedic Subjunctive) ऐ is optionally the substitute of ए in other places then those mentioned in the last sūtra.<br><br>Terms: लेट्

3.4.97|3.4.97 itashcha lopaH parasmaipadeShu|itashcha lopaH parasmaipadeShu|itashcha lopaH parasmaipadeShu 3.4.97|इतश्च लोपः परस्मैपदेषु|इतश्च लोपः परस्मैपदेषु ३.४.९७|३.४.९७|३.४.९७ इतश्च लोपः परस्मैपदेषु
In the परस्मैपद affixes the इ is optionally elided in the लेट् (Vedic Subjunctive).<br><br>Terms: लेट्

3.4.98|3.4.98 sa uttamasya|sa uttamasya|sa uttamasya 3.4.98|स उत्तमस्य|स उत्तमस्य ३.४.९८|३.४.९८|३.४.९८ स उत्तमस्य
The स् of the first person is optionally elided in the लेट् (Vedic Subjunctive).<br><br>Terms: लेट्

3.4.99|3.4.99 nityaM NGitaH|nityaM NGitaH|nityaM NGitaH 3.4.99|नित्यं ङितः|नित्यं ङितः ३.४.९९|३.४.९९|३.४.९९ नित्यं ङितः
There is always elision of the स् of the first person of the affixes that come in the room of that ल which has an indicatory ङ्।<br><br>Terms: ल

3.4.100|3.4.100 itashcha|itashcha|itashcha 3.4.100|इतश्च|इतश्च ३.४.१००|३.४.१००|३.४.१०० इतश्च
And there is elision of the इ of that परस्मैपद affix which is the substitute of a ल having an indicatory ङ्।<br><br>Terms: ल

3.4.101|3.4.101 tasthasthamipaaM taaMtaMtaamaH|tasthasthamipaaM taaMtaMtaamaH|tasthasthamipaaM taaMtaMtaamaH 3.4.101|तस्थस्थमिपां तांतंतामः|तस्थस्थमिपां तांतंतामः ३.४.१०१|३.४.१०१|३.४.१०१ तस्थस्थमिपां तांतंतामः
The affixes 1. ताम् 2. तम् 3. त 4. आम् are the substitutes of the four affixes तस् , थस् , थ and मिप् respectively of any ल which has an indicatory ङ् ।<br><br>Terms: ल

3.4.102|3.4.102 liNGassiiyuT|liNGassiiyuT|liNGassiiyuT 3.4.102|लिङस्सीयुट्|लिङस्सीयुट् ३.४.१०२|३.४.१०२|३.४.१०२ लिङस्सीयुट्
The तिङ् (Personal Endings) of the लिङ् (Benedictive) and the Potential take the augment स्युत् ।<br><br>Terms: लिङ्

3.4.103|3.4.103 yaasuT parasmaipadeShuudaatto NGichcha|yaasuT parasmaipadeShuudaatto NGichcha|yaasuT parasmaipadeShuudaatto NGichcha 3.4.103|यासुट् परस्मैपदेषूदात्तो ङिच्च|यासुट् परस्मैपदेषूदात्तो ङिच्च ३.४.१०३|३.४.१०३|३.४.१०३ यासुट् परस्मैपदेषूदात्तो ङिच्च
When the परस्मैपद affixes of the Potential follow, then यासुट् acutely accented, is their augment and the termination is regarded as having an indicatory ङ्।<br><br>Terms: यासुट्

3.4.104|3.4.104 kidaashiShi|kidaashiShi|kidaashiShi 3.4.104|किदाशिषि|किदाशिषि ३.४.१०४|३.४.१०४|३.४.१०४ किदाशिषि
The augment यासुट् comes after that लिङ् (Benedictive) also which denotes benediction and it is acutely accented and the substitutes of this लिङ् (Benedictive) are as they had an indicatory क्।<br><br>Terms: यासुट्

3.4.105|3.4.105 jhasya ran|jhasya ran|jhasya ran 3.4.105|झस्य रन्|झस्य रन् ३.४.१०५|३.४.१०५|३.४.१०५ झस्य रन्
The affix रन् is the substitute of झ in the लिङ् (Potential and Benedictive).<br><br>Terms: रन्

3.4.106|3.4.106 iTo.at‌|iTo.at‌|iTo.at‌ 3.4.106|इटोऽत्‌|इटोऽत्‌ ३.४.१०६|३.४.१०६|३.४.१०६ इटोऽत्‌
The short अ is the substitute of इ of the आत्मनेपद first person singular in the Potential and Benedictive.<br><br>Terms: अ

3.4.107|3.4.107 suT tithoH|suT tithoH|suT tithoH 3.4.107|सुट् तिथोः|सुट् तिथोः ३.४.१०७|३.४.१०७|३.४.१०७ सुट् तिथोः
The augment सुट् is added to the following affixes त and थ when part of the affixes of the Potential and Benedictive.<br><br>Terms: सुट्

3.4.108|3.4.108 jherjus|jherjus|jherjus 3.4.108|झेर्जुस्|झेर्जुस् ३.४.१०८|३.४.१०८|३.४.१०८ झेर्जुस्
In the Potential and Benedictive जुस् is the substitute of झि , the ending of the first person plural परस्मैपद ।<br><br>Terms: झि

3.4.109|3.4.109 sijabhyastavidibhyaH cha|sijabhyastavidibhyaH cha|sijabhyastavidibhyaH cha 3.4.109|सिजभ्यस्तविदिभ्यः च|सिजभ्यस्तविदिभ्यः च ३.४.१०९|३.४.१०९|३.४.१०९ सिजभ्यस्तविदिभ्यः च
(In those tenses which are marked with an indicatory ङ् ) जुस् is the substitute of झि when it comes after an लुङ् (Aorist) in सिच् or the लङ् (Imperfect Tense) of a reduplicated verb or the root विद् 'to know'.<br><br>Terms: झि

3.4.110|3.4.110 aataH|aataH|aataH 3.4.110|आतः|आतः ३.४.११०|३.४.११०|३.४.११० आतः
When सिच् is elided जुस् is the substitute of झि after a लुङ् (Aorist) stem which ends in long आ।<br><br>Terms: झि

3.4.111|3.4.111 laNGaH shaakaTaayanasyaiva|laNGaH shaakaTaayanasyaiva|laNGaH shaakaTaayanasyaiva 3.4.111|लङः शाकटायनस्यैव|लङः शाकटायनस्यैव ३.४.१११|३.४.१११|३.४.१११ लङः शाकटायनस्यैव
In the opinion of शाकटायन only जुस् is the substitute of झि , in the लङ् (Imperfect Tense) of the roots which end in a long आ।<br><br>Terms: झि

3.4.112|3.4.112 dviShashcha|dviShashcha|dviShashcha 3.4.112|द्विषश्च|द्विषश्च ३.४.११२|३.४.११२|३.४.११२ द्विषश्च
In the opinion of शाकटायन only जुस् is the substitute of झि , in the लङ् (Imperfect Tense) after the verb द्विष् 'to hate'.<br><br>Terms: झि

3.4.113|3.4.113 tiNGshitsaarvadhaatukam|tiNGshitsaarvadhaatukam|tiNGshitsaarvadhaatukam 3.4.113|तिङ्शित्सार्वधातुकम्|तिङ्शित्सार्वधातुकम् ३.४.११३|३.४.११३|३.४.११३ तिङ्शित्सार्वधातुकम्
All the personal endings -- तिप्तस्झिसिप्थस्थमिब्वस्मस्तातांझथासाथांध्वमिड्वहिमहिङ् ३.४.७८, and all affixes with an indicatory श् are called सार्वधातुक ।<br><br>Terms: सार्वधातुक

3.4.114|3.4.114 aarddhadhaatukaM sheShaH|aarddhadhaatukaM sheShaH|aarddhadhaatukaM sheShaH 3.4.114|आर्द्धधातुकं शेषः|आर्द्धधातुकं शेषः ३.४.११४|३.४.११४|३.४.११४ आर्द्धधातुकं शेषः
The remainder i.e. the affixes other than तिङ् (Personal Endings) and those with an indicatory श् sub-joined to a verbal root are called आर्द्धधातुक।<br><br>Terms: आर्द्धधातुक

3.4.115|3.4.115 liT cha|liT cha|liT cha 3.4.115|लिट् च|लिट् च ३.४.११५|३.४.११५|३.४.११५ लिट् च
The तिङ् (Personal Endings) of the लिट् (Perfect Tense) are also called आर्द्धधातुक ।<br><br>Terms: आर्द्धधातुक

3.4.116|3.4.116 liNGaashiShi|liNGaashiShi|liNGaashiShi 3.4.116|लिङाशिषि|लिङाशिषि ३.४.११६|३.४.११६|३.४.११६ लिङाशिषि
When the sense is that of Benediction, the substitutes of लिङ् (Benedictive) are called आर्द्धधातुक i.e. the तिङ् (Personal Endings) of the लिङ् (Benedictive) are आर्द्धधातुक ।<br><br>Terms: आर्द्धधातुक

3.4.117|3.4.117 Chandasyubhayathaa|Chandasyubhayathaa|Chandasyubhayathaa 3.4.117|छन्दस्युभयथा|छन्दस्युभयथा ३.४.११७|३.४.११७|३.४.११७ छन्दस्युभयथा
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) this distinction of सार्वधातुक and आर्द्धधातुक is not always maintained and the affixes are promiscuously used.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

4.1.1|4.1.1 NGyaappraatipadikaat‌|NGyaappraatipadikaat‌|NGyaappraatipadikaat‌ 4.1.1|ङ्याप्प्रातिपदिकात्‌|ङ्याप्प्रातिपदिकात्‌ ४.१.१|४.१.१|४.१.१ ङ्याप्प्रातिपदिकात्‌
(From this point forward up to the end of the Fifth Chapter, whatever we shall treat of, should be understood to come) after what ends with the feminine affixes ङी or आप् or after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति

4.1.2|4.1.2 svaujasamauTChaShTaabhyaambhisNGebhyaambhyasNGasibhyaambhyasNGasosaamNGyossup‌|svaujasamauTChaShTaabhyaambhisNGebhyaambhyasNGasibhyaambhyasNGasosaamNGyossup‌|svaujasamauTChaShTaabhyaambhisNGebhyaambhyasNGasibhyaambhyasNGasosaamNGyossup‌ 4.1.2|स्वौजसमौट्छष्टाभ्याम्भिस्ङेभ्याम्भ्यस्ङसिभ्याम्भ्यस्ङसोसाम्ङ्योस्सुप्‌|स्वौजसमौट्छष्टाभ्याम्भिस्ङेभ्याम्भ्यस्ङसिभ्याम्भ्यस्ङसोसाम्ङ्योस्सुप्‌ ४.१.२|४.१.२|४.१.२ स्वौजसमौट्छष्टाभ्याम्भिस्ङेभ्याम्भ्यस्ङसिभ्याम्भ्यस्ङसोसाम्ङ्योस्सुप्‌
(After what ends with the feminine teminations ङी or आप् or after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem), the following case-affixes ae used for declension) - 1st - सु (स), औ , जस् (अस्)। 2nd - अम् , औट् (औ), शस् (अस्)। 3rd - टा (आ), भ्याम् , भिस् । 4th - ङे (ए), भ्याम् , भ्यस्। 5th - ङसि (अस्), भ्याम् , भ्यस्। 6th - ङस् (अस्), ओस् , आम्। 7th - ङि (इ), ओस् , सुप् (सु)।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति

4.1.3|4.1.3 striyaam|striyaam|striyaam 4.1.3|स्त्रियाम्|स्त्रियाम् ४.१.३|४.१.३|४.१.३ स्त्रियाम्
When the feminine nature is to be indicated the affixes which we shall treat of hereinafter must be used.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति

4.1.4|4.1.4 ajaadyataShTaap‌|ajaadyataShTaap‌|ajaadyataShTaap‌ 4.1.4|अजाद्यतष्टाप्‌|अजाद्यतष्टाप्‌ ४.१.४|४.१.४|४.१.४ अजाद्यतष्टाप्‌
The affix टाप् is used to indicate feminine nature after the प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) अज etc. and after the stems ending in short अ।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-F

4.1.5|4.1.5 Rnnebhyo NGiip‌|Rnnebhyo NGiip‌|Rnnebhyo NGiip‌ 4.1.5|ऋन्नेभ्यो ङीप्‌|ऋन्नेभ्यो ङीप्‌ ४.१.५|४.१.५|४.१.५ ऋन्नेभ्यो ङीप्‌
The affix ङीप् is used in forming the feminine after प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in ऋ or न्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-F

4.1.6|4.1.6 ugitashcha|ugitashcha|ugitashcha 4.1.6|उगितश्च|उगितश्च ४.१.६|४.१.६|४.१.६ उगितश्च
And after what has an indicatory उक् (उ , ऋ or ऌ) the affix ङीप् is used denoting a feminine.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-F

4.1.7|4.1.7 vano ra cha|vano ra cha|vano ra cha 4.1.7|वनो र च|वनो र च ४.१.७|४.१.७|४.१.७ वनो र च
The affix ङीप् is added, in forming the feminine to the stems that end in the syllable वन् , and र् is the substitute of the final such syllable.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.8|4.1.8 paado.anyatarasyaam|paado.anyatarasyaam|paado.anyatarasyaam 4.1.8|पादोऽन्यतरस्याम्|पादोऽन्यतरस्याम् ४.१.८|४.१.८|४.१.८ पादोऽन्यतरस्याम्
The affix ङीप् is optionally used in the feminine after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending with the word पाद्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.9|4.1.9 TaabRchi|TaabRchi|TaabRchi 4.1.9|टाबृचि|टाबृचि ४.१.९|४.१.९|४.१.९ टाबृचि
The affix ङीप् is used in the feminine after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending with the word पाद् when the word denotes a verse of the ऋग्वेद।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.10|4.1.10 na ShaTsvasraadibhyaH|na ShaTsvasraadibhyaH|na ShaTsvasraadibhyaH 4.1.10|न षट्स्वस्रादिभ्यः|न षट्स्वस्रादिभ्यः ४.१.१०|४.१.१०|४.१.१० न षट्स्वस्रादिभ्यः
The feminine affixes are not used after the stems called षद् -- ष्णान्ता षट् १.१.२४ and after स्वस्र etc.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-F

4.1.11|4.1.11 manaH|manaH|manaH 4.1.11|मनः|मनः ४.१.११|४.१.११|४.१.११ मनः
The affix ङीप् is not used after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in the syllable मन्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.12|4.1.12 ano bahuvriiheH|ano bahuvriiheH|ano bahuvriiheH 4.1.12|अनो बहुव्रीहेः|अनो बहुव्रीहेः ४.१.१२|४.१.१२|४.१.१२ अनो बहुव्रीहेः
The affix ङीप् is not used to denote the feminine after a बहुव्रीहि समास ending in अन्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.13|4.1.13 Daabubhaabhyaamanyatarasyaam‌|Daabubhaabhyaamanyatarasyaam‌|Daabubhaabhyaamanyatarasyaam‌ 4.1.13|डाबुभाभ्यामन्यतरस्याम्‌|डाबुभाभ्यामन्यतरस्याम्‌ ४.१.१३|४.१.१३|४.१.१३ डाबुभाभ्यामन्यतरस्याम्‌
The affix डाप् comes optionally after both - 1. प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in अन् 2. बहुव्रीहि समास ।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.14|4.1.14 anupasarjanaat‌|anupasarjanaat‌|anupasarjanaat‌ 4.1.14|अनुपसर्जनात्‌|अनुपसर्जनात्‌ ४.१.१४|४.१.१४|४.१.१४ अनुपसर्जनात्‌
The following rules apply to a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) which is not a subordinate term in a compound.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.15|4.1.15 TiDDhaaNaNJdvayasajdaghnaNJmaatrachtayapThakThaNJkaNJkvarapaH|TiDDhaaNaNJdvayasajdaghnaNJmaatrachtayapThakThaNJkaNJkvarapaH|TiDDhaaNaNJdvayasajdaghnaNJmaatrachtayapThakThaNJkaNJkvarapaH 4.1.15|टिड्ढाणञ्द्वयसज्दघ्नञ्मात्रच्तयप्ठक्ठञ्कञ्क्वरपः|टिड्ढाणञ्द्वयसज्दघ्नञ्मात्रच्तयप्ठक्ठञ्कञ्क्वरपः ४.१.१५|४.१.१५|४.१.१५ टिड्ढाणञ्द्वयसज्दघ्नञ्मात्रच्तयप्ठक्ठञ्कञ्क्वरपः
The affix ङीप् is added in the feminine after the प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stems) ending in short अ , if the affix with which it ends has an indicatory ट् or if the affix be ढ or अण् or अञ् or द्वयसच् or दघ्नच् or मात्रच् or तयप् or ठक् or ठञ् or कञ् or क्वरप्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.16|4.1.16 yaNJashcha|yaNJashcha|yaNJashcha 4.1.16|यञश्च|यञश्च ४.१.१६|४.१.१६|४.१.१६ यञश्च
The affix ङीप् is used in denoting the feminine after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in यञ् -- गर्गादिभ्यो यञ् ४.१.१०५.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.17|4.1.17 praachaaM Shpha taddhitaH|praachaaM Shpha taddhitaH|praachaaM Shpha taddhitaH 4.1.17|प्राचां ष्फ तद्धितः|प्राचां ष्फ तद्धितः ४.१.१७|४.१.१७|४.१.१७ प्राचां ष्फ तद्धितः
In the opinion of the Eastern Grammarians, the affix ष्फ is used after what ends with the affix यञ् and it is to be regarded as a तद्धित-affix.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.18|4.1.18 sarvatra lohitaadikataantebhyaH|sarvatra lohitaadikataantebhyaH|sarvatra lohitaadikataantebhyaH 4.1.18|सर्वत्र लोहितादिकतान्तेभ्यः|सर्वत्र लोहितादिकतान्तेभ्यः ४.१.१८|४.१.१८|४.१.१८ सर्वत्र लोहितादिकतान्तेभ्यः
The affix ष्फ is invariably added in the feminine after the words beginning with लोहित and ending with क्त when they take the affix यञ्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.19|4.1.19 kauravyamaaNDuukaabhyaaM cha|kauravyamaaNDuukaabhyaaM cha|kauravyamaaNDuukaabhyaaM cha 4.1.19|कौरव्यमाण्डूकाभ्यां च|कौरव्यमाण्डूकाभ्यां च ४.१.१९|४.१.१९|४.१.१९ कौरव्यमाण्डूकाभ्यां च
The affix ष्फ is added in the feminine after the words 1. कौरव्य and 2. माण्डूक।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.20|4.1.20 vayasi prathame|vayasi prathame|vayasi prathame 4.1.20|वयसि प्रथमे|वयसि प्रथमे ४.१.२०|४.१.२०|४.१.२० वयसि प्रथमे
The affix ङीप् is used in the feminine after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in अ and denoting early age.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.21|4.1.21 dvigoH|dvigoH|dvigoH 4.1.21|द्विगोः|द्विगोः ४.१.२१|४.१.२१|४.१.२१ द्विगोः
The affix ङीप् come in the feminine after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in अ , which is द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound). <br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.22|4.1.22 aparimaaNabistaachitakambalyebhyo na taddhitaluki|aparimaaNabistaachitakambalyebhyo na taddhitaluki|aparimaaNabistaachitakambalyebhyo na taddhitaluki 4.1.22|अपरिमाणबिस्ताचितकम्बल्येभ्यो न तद्धितलुकि|अपरिमाणबिस्ताचितकम्बल्येभ्यो न तद्धितलुकि ४.१.२२|४.१.२२|४.१.२२ अपरिमाणबिस्ताचितकम्बल्येभ्यो न तद्धितलुकि
The affix ङीप् is not used when a तद्धित affix is elided after a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) ending in a word not denoting a mass or measure; or in 1. बिस्त 2. आचित or 3. कम्बल्य।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.23|4.1.23 kaaNDaantaat‌ xetre|kaaNDaantaat‌ xetre|kaaNDaantaat‌ xetre 4.1.23|काण्डान्तात्‌ क्षेत्रे|काण्डान्तात्‌ क्षेत्रे ४.१.२३|४.१.२३|४.१.२३ काण्डान्तात्‌ क्षेत्रे
The affix ङीप् is not used after an adjectival द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) ending with the word काण्ड where the तद्धित affix is elided when the compound means field.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.24|4.1.24 puruShaat‌ pramaaNe.anyatarasyaam|puruShaat‌ pramaaNe.anyatarasyaam|puruShaat‌ pramaaNe.anyatarasyaam 4.1.24|पुरुषात्‌ प्रमाणेऽन्यतरस्याम्|पुरुषात्‌ प्रमाणेऽन्यतरस्याम् ४.१.२४|४.१.२४|४.१.२४ पुरुषात्‌ प्रमाणेऽन्यतरस्याम्
The affix ङीप् is not optionally used after a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) where the तद्धित affix is elided when the compound ends in the word पुरुष , referring to 'measure'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.25|4.1.25 bahuvriiheruudhaso NGiiSh.|bahuvriiheruudhaso NGiiSh.|bahuvriiheruudhaso NGiiSh. 4.1.25|बहुव्रीहेरूधसो ङीष्।|बहुव्रीहेरूधसो ङीष्। ४.१.२५|४.१.२५|४.१.२५ बहुव्रीहेरूधसो ङीष्।
The affix ङीप् is used in the feminine after a बहुव्रीहि समास ending in the word ऊधस् 'an udder'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.26|4.1.26 saMkhyaa.avyayaaderNGiip‌|saMkhyaa.avyayaaderNGiip‌|saMkhyaa.avyayaaderNGiip‌ 4.1.26|संख्याऽव्ययादेर्ङीप्‌|संख्याऽव्ययादेर्ङीप्‌ ४.१.२६|४.१.२६|४.१.२६ संख्याऽव्ययादेर्ङीप्‌
The affix ङीप् comes in the feminine after a बहुव्रीहि समास ending in the word ऊधस् 'an udder', beginning with a Numeral or indeclinable.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.27|4.1.27 daamahaayanaantaachcha|daamahaayanaantaachcha|daamahaayanaantaachcha 4.1.27|दामहायनान्ताच्च|दामहायनान्ताच्च ४.१.२७|४.१.२७|४.१.२७ दामहायनान्ताच्च
The affix ङीप् comes in the feminine after a बहुव्रीहि समास beginning with a Numeral and ending with the words 1. दामन् 'a rope' and 2. हायन 'a year'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.28|4.1.28 ana upadhaalopinonyatarasyaam|ana upadhaalopinonyatarasyaam|ana upadhaalopinonyatarasyaam 4.1.28|अन उपधालोपिनोन्यतरस्याम्|अन उपधालोपिनोन्यतरस्याम् ४.१.२८|४.१.२८|४.१.२८ अन उपधालोपिनोन्यतरस्याम्
The affix ङीप् comes after that बहुव्रीहि समास which ending in the syllable अन् loses its penultimate अ।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.29|4.1.29 nityaM saMJNaaChandasoH|nityaM saMJNaaChandasoH|nityaM saMJNaaChandasoH 4.1.29|नित्यं संज्ञाछन्दसोः|नित्यं संज्ञाछन्दसोः ४.१.२९|४.१.२९|४.१.२९ नित्यं संज्ञाछन्दसोः
The affix ङीप् necessarily comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) and in forming Names after that बहुव्रीहि समास which ending in the syllable अन् loses its penultimate अ।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.30|4.1.30 kevalamaamakabhaagadheyapaapaaparasamaanaaryakRta-sumangalabheShajaachcha|kevalamaamakabhaagadheyapaapaaparasamaanaaryakRta-sumangalabheShajaachcha|kevalamaamakabhaagadheyapaapaaparasamaanaaryakRta-sumangalabheShajaachcha 4.1.30|केवलमामकभागधेयपापापरसमानार्यकृत-सुमङ्गलभेषजाच्च|केवलमामकभागधेयपापापरसमानार्यकृत-सुमङ्गलभेषजाच्च ४.१.३०|४.१.३०|४.१.३० केवलमामकभागधेयपापापरसमानार्यकृत-सुमङ्गलभेषजाच्च
The affix ङीप् necessarily comes denoting the feminine after the following प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stems) when used to express a Name or in the छन्दस् (Vedas).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.31|4.1.31 raatreshchaajasau|raatreshchaajasau|raatreshchaajasau 4.1.31|रात्रेश्चाजसौ|रात्रेश्चाजसौ ४.१.३१|४.१.३१|४.१.३१ रात्रेश्चाजसौ
The affix ङीप् comes after the word रात्रि in the छन्दस् (Vedas) and in denoting a Name except the affix जस् (1st - Nominative Case Plural) is added.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.32|4.1.32 antarvatpativatornuk|antarvatpativatornuk|antarvatpativatornuk 4.1.32|अन्तर्वत्पतिवतोर्नुक्|अन्तर्वत्पतिवतोर्नुक् ४.१.३२|४.१.३२|४.१.३२ अन्तर्वत्पतिवतोर्नुक्
The augment नुक् is added to the words अन्तर्वत् and पतिवत् when the affix ङीप् is added to form the feminine.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.33|4.1.33 patyurno yaJNasaMyoge|patyurno yaJNasaMyoge|patyurno yaJNasaMyoge 4.1.33|पत्युर्नो यज्ञसंयोगे|पत्युर्नो यज्ञसंयोगे ४.१.३३|४.१.३३|४.१.३३ पत्युर्नो यज्ञसंयोगे
The substitute न् replaces the final इ of पति before the feminine affix ङीप् when the word so formed means 'a wife' who takes part in the sacrifices of her husband.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.34|4.1.34 vibhaaShaa sapuurvasya|vibhaaShaa sapuurvasya|vibhaaShaa sapuurvasya 4.1.34|विभाषा सपूर्वस्य|विभाषा सपूर्वस्य ४.१.३४|४.१.३४|४.१.३४ विभाषा सपूर्वस्य
In forming the feminine with the affix ङीप् , न् is optionally the substitute of the final इ of पति when the latter is preceded by another vowel.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.35|4.1.35 nityaM sapatnyaadiShu|nityaM sapatnyaadiShu|nityaM sapatnyaadiShu 4.1.35|नित्यं सपत्न्य्आदिषु|नित्यं सपत्न्य्आदिषु ४.१.३५|४.१.३५|४.१.३५ नित्यं सपत्न्य्आदिषु
In forming the feminine with the affix ङीप् the word पति always takes the substitute न् in the words like सपत्नि etc.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.36|4.1.36 puutakratorai cha|puutakratorai cha|puutakratorai cha 4.1.36|पूतक्रतोरै च|पूतक्रतोरै च ४.१.३६|४.१.३६|४.१.३६ पूतक्रतोरै च
In forming the feminine, the letter ऐ is the substitute of the final word पूतक्तु when the affix ङीप् is added.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.37|4.1.37 vRShaakapyagnikusitakusiidaanaamudaattaH|vRShaakapyagnikusitakusiidaanaamudaattaH|vRShaakapyagnikusitakusiidaanaamudaattaH 4.1.37|वृषाकप्यग्निकुसितकुसीदानामुदात्तः|वृषाकप्यग्निकुसितकुसीदानामुदात्तः ४.१.३७|४.१.३७|४.१.३७ वृषाकप्यग्निकुसितकुसीदानामुदात्तः
In forming the feminine with the affix ङीप् the letter ऐ having उदात्त accent is the substitute of the finals 1. वृषाकपि 2. अग्नि 3. कुसति and 3. कुसीद ।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.38|4.1.38 manorau vaa|manorau vaa|manorau vaa 4.1.38|मनोरौ वा|मनोरौ वा ४.१.३८|४.१.३८|४.१.३८ मनोरौ वा
In forming the feminine with the affix ङीप् , औ is optionally the substitute of the final मनु (as well as the उदात्त ऐ).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.39|4.1.39 varNaadanudaattaattopadhaatto naH|varNaadanudaattaattopadhaatto naH|varNaadanudaattaattopadhaatto naH 4.1.39|वर्णादनुदात्तात्तोपधात्तो नः|वर्णादनुदात्तात्तोपधात्तो नः ४.१.३९|४.१.३९|४.१.३९ वर्णादनुदात्तात्तोपधात्तो नः
The affix ङीप् is optionally used after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) expressive of colour ending with a gravely accented vowel and having the letter त् as its penultimate letter and the letter न् is substituted in the room of त्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

4.1.40|4.1.40 anyato NGiiSh.|anyato NGiiSh.|anyato NGiiSh. 4.1.40|अन्यतो ङीष्।|अन्यतो ङीष्। ४.१.४०|४.१.४०|४.१.४० अन्यतो ङीष्।
The affix ङीष् is used in the feminine after every other word expressive of colour and ending with an अनुदात्त accent.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.41|4.1.41 Shidgauraadibhyashcha|Shidgauraadibhyashcha|Shidgauraadibhyashcha 4.1.41|षिद्गौरादिभ्यश्च|षिद्गौरादिभ्यश्च ४.१.४१|४.१.४१|४.१.४१ षिद्गौरादिभ्यश्च
The affix ङीष् is used in forming the feminine after the words ending with affixes which have an indicatory ष् and after the words गौर etc.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.42|4.1.42 jaanapadakuNDagoNasthalabhaajanaagakaalaniilakushakaamukakabaraadvRttyamatraavapanaakRtrimaashraaNaasthaulyavarNaanaachChaadanaayovikaaramaithunechChaakeshavesheShu|jaanapadakuNDagoNasthalabhaajanaagakaalaniilakushakaamukakabaraadvRttyamatraavapanaakRtrimaashraaNaasthaulyavarNaanaachChaadanaayovikaaramaithunechChaakeshavesheShu|jaanapadakuNDagoNasthalabhaajanaagakaalaniilakushakaamukakabaraadvRttyamatraavapanaakRtrimaashraaNaasthaulyavarNaanaachChaadanaayovikaaramaithunechChaakeshavesheShu 4.1.42|जानपदकुण्डगोणस्थलभाजनागकालनीलकुशकामुककबराद्वृत्त्यमत्रावपनाकृत्रिमाश्राणास्थौल्यवर्णानाच्छादनायोविकारमैथुनेच्छाकेशवेशेषु|जानपदकुण्डगोणस्थलभाजनागकालनीलकुशकामुककबराद्वृत्त्यमत्रावपनाकृत्रिमाश्राणास्थौल्यवर्णानाच्छादनायोविकारमैथुनेच्छाकेशवेशेषु ४.१.४२|४.१.४२|४.१.४२ जानपदकुण्डगोणस्थलभाजनागकालनीलकुशकामुककबराद्वृत्त्यमत्रावपनाकृत्रिमाश्राणास्थौल्यवर्णानाच्छादनायोविकारमैथुनेच्छाकेशवेशेषु
The affix ङीष् is used after the 11 words जानपद etc. in the sense of 'profession' etc. 1. जानप् 2. कुण्ड 3. गोण 4. स्थल 5. भाज 6. नाग 7. काल 8. नील 9. कुश् 10. कामुक and 11 कबर ; the affix ङीष् is employed when the sense is that of 1. 'profession or living' 2. 'a bowl' 3. 'a sack or vessel for keeping grain' 4. 'a natural spot of ground' 5. 'a cooked food or rice-gruel' 6. 'stout' 7. 'black-coloured' 8. 'blue-coloured other than cloth' 9. 'a plough-share' 10. 'a libidinous female' 11. 'a fellet or braid of hair', respectively.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.43|4.1.43 shoNaat‌ praachaam|shoNaat‌ praachaam|shoNaat‌ praachaam 4.1.43|शोणात्‌ प्राचाम्|शोणात्‌ प्राचाम् ४.१.४३|४.१.४३|४.१.४३ शोणात्‌ प्राचाम्
The affix ङीष् is used in the feminine according to the opinion of the Eastern Grammarians after the word शोण।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.44|4.1.44 voto guNavachanaat‌|voto guNavachanaat‌|voto guNavachanaat‌ 4.1.44|वोतो गुणवचनात्‌|वोतो गुणवचनात्‌ ४.१.४४|४.१.४४|४.१.४४ वोतो गुणवचनात्‌
The affix ङीष् is optionally used in the feminine after a word ending in short अ and being expressive of quality.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.45|4.1.45 bahvaadibhyashcha|bahvaadibhyashcha|bahvaadibhyashcha 4.1.45|बह्वादिभ्यश्च|बह्वादिभ्यश्च ४.१.४५|४.१.४५|४.१.४५ बह्वादिभ्यश्च
And the affix ङीष् is optionally used in the feminine after the words बहु etc.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.46|4.1.46 nityaM Chandasi|nityaM Chandasi|nityaM Chandasi 4.1.46|नित्यं छन्दसि|नित्यं छन्दसि ४.१.४६|४.१.४६|४.१.४६ नित्यं छन्दसि
The affix ङीष् is always used in the छन्दस् (Vedas) in forming the feminine of the words बहु etc.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.47|4.1.47 bhuvashcha|bhuvashcha|bhuvashcha 4.1.47|भुवश्च|भुवश्च ४.१.४७|४.१.४७|४.१.४७ भुवश्च
The affix ङीष् is always used in the छन्दस् (Vedas) in forming the feminine after the word भु।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.48|4.1.48 puMyogaadaakhyaayaam|puMyogaadaakhyaayaam|puMyogaadaakhyaayaam 4.1.48|पुंयोगादाख्यायाम्|पुंयोगादाख्यायाम् ४.१.४८|४.१.४८|४.१.४८ पुंयोगादाख्यायाम्
The feminine affix ङीष् comes after a word when it expresses the name of a wife in relation to her husband.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.49|4.1.49 indravaruNabhavasharvarudramRDahimaaraNyayavayavanamaatulaachaaryaaNaamaanuk|indravaruNabhavasharvarudramRDahimaaraNyayavayavanamaatulaachaaryaaNaamaanuk|indravaruNabhavasharvarudramRDahimaaraNyayavayavanamaatulaachaaryaaNaamaanuk 4.1.49|इन्द्रवरुणभवशर्वरुद्रमृडहिमारण्ययवयवनमातुलाचार्याणामानुक्|इन्द्रवरुणभवशर्वरुद्रमृडहिमारण्ययवयवनमातुलाचार्याणामानुक् ४.१.४९|४.१.४९|४.१.४९ इन्द्रवरुणभवशर्वरुद्रमृडहिमारण्ययवयवनमातुलाचार्याणामानुक्
The augment आनुक् is added to the Proper Nouns 1. इन्द्र 2. वरुण 3. भव 4. शर्व 5. रुद्र and 6. मृड and to the words 1. हिम 'snow' 3. अरण्य 'forest' 4. यव 'barely' 5. यवन 'a Yavana' 6. मातुल 'a maternal uncle' and 7. आचार्य 'a perceptor', before the feminine affix ङीष्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.50|4.1.50 kriitaat‌ karaNapuurvaat‌|kriitaat‌ karaNapuurvaat‌|kriitaat‌ karaNapuurvaat‌ 4.1.50|क्रीतात्‌ करणपूर्वात्‌|क्रीतात्‌ करणपूर्वात्‌ ४.१.५०|४.१.५०|४.१.५० क्रीतात्‌ करणपूर्वात्‌
The affix ङीष् is used in the feminine after a compound word ending in क्रीत , the first member of the compound being the name of the means wherewith the thing is bought.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.51|4.1.51 ktaadalpaakhyaayaam|ktaadalpaakhyaayaam|ktaadalpaakhyaayaam 4.1.51|क्तादल्पाख्यायाम्|क्तादल्पाख्यायाम् ४.१.५१|४.१.५१|४.१.५१ क्तादल्पाख्यायाम्
The affix ङीष् is used after a compound प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) in which a name denoting the means herewith, is the first member and the second member is a word formed by the Particle क्त when the sense is that of 'a small quantity'. <br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.52|4.1.52 bahuvriiheshchaantodaattaat‌|bahuvriiheshchaantodaattaat‌|bahuvriiheshchaantodaattaat‌ 4.1.52|बहुव्रीहेश्चान्तोदात्तात्‌|बहुव्रीहेश्चान्तोदात्तात्‌ ४.१.५२|४.१.५२|४.१.५२ बहुव्रीहेश्चान्तोदात्तात्‌
The affix ङीष् is used in the feminine after that बहुव्रीहि समास which ending with a word formed by the affix क्त has an acute accent on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.53|4.1.53 asvaangapuurvapadaadvaa|asvaangapuurvapadaadvaa|asvaangapuurvapadaadvaa 4.1.53|अस्वाङ्गपूर्वपदाद्वा|अस्वाङ्गपूर्वपदाद्वा ४.१.५३|४.१.५३|४.१.५३ अस्वाङ्गपूर्वपदाद्वा
The affix ङीष् is optionally used in the feminine after a बहुव्रीहि समास ending with the word in क्त having acute accent on the final, the antecedent word not being a word denoting a part of the body.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.54|4.1.54 svaangaachchopasarjanaadasaMyogopadhaat‌|svaangaachchopasarjanaadasaMyogopadhaat‌|svaangaachchopasarjanaadasaMyogopadhaat‌ 4.1.54|स्वाङ्गाच्चोपसर्जनादसंयोगोपधात्‌|स्वाङ्गाच्चोपसर्जनादसंयोगोपधात्‌ ४.१.५४|४.१.५४|४.१.५४ स्वाङ्गाच्चोपसर्जनादसंयोगोपधात्‌
And the feminine affix ङीष् comes optionally after what ends with the name of a part of the body when the word is a subordinate member in compound and has not a conjunct for its penultimate letter (i.e. the final अ is not preceded by a double consonant).<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.55|4.1.55 naasikodarauShThajaNGghaadantakarNashRngaachcha|naasikodarauShThajaNGghaadantakarNashRngaachcha|naasikodarauShThajaNGghaadantakarNashRngaachcha 4.1.55|नासिकोदरौष्ठजङ्घादन्तकर्णशृङ्गाच्च|नासिकोदरौष्ठजङ्घादन्तकर्णशृङ्गाच्च ४.१.५५|४.१.५५|४.१.५५ नासिकोदरौष्ठजङ्घादन्तकर्णशृङ्गाच्च
And the feminine ङीष् comes optionally after compounds ending with 1. नासिका 'a nose' 2. उदर 'belly' 3. ओष्ठ 'lip' 4. जंघा 'leg' 5. दन्त 'tooth' 6. कर्ण 'ear' and 7. शृङ्ग 'horn'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.56|4.1.56 na kroDaadibahvachaH|na kroDaadibahvachaH|na kroDaadibahvachaH 4.1.56|न क्रोडादिबह्वचः|न क्रोडादिबह्वचः ४.१.५६|४.१.५६|४.१.५६ न क्रोडादिबह्वचः
The feminine affix ङीष् does not come after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) which denoting a part of the body, belongs to the class क्रोडा 'the flank' etc., of a horse', nor when the word is a stem of more than two syllables.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.57|4.1.57 sahanaNJvidyamaanapuurvaachcha|sahanaNJvidyamaanapuurvaachcha|sahanaNJvidyamaanapuurvaachcha 4.1.57|सहनञ्विद्यमानपूर्वाच्च|सहनञ्विद्यमानपूर्वाच्च ४.१.५७|४.१.५७|४.१.५७ सहनञ्विद्यमानपूर्वाच्च
The affix ङीष् does not come in the feminine after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) denoting a part of the body when the word is subordinate in a compound, preceded by the word 1. सह 'with' 2. नञ् 'not' or 3. विद्यमान 'having'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.58|4.1.58 nakhamukhaat‌ saMJNaayaam|nakhamukhaat‌ saMJNaayaam|nakhamukhaat‌ saMJNaayaam 4.1.58|नखमुखात्‌ संज्ञायाम्|नखमुखात्‌ संज्ञायाम् ४.१.५८|४.१.५८|४.१.५८ नखमुखात्‌ संज्ञायाम्
The feminine affix ङीष् is not used after 1. नख 2. मुख when (the word at the end of which they stand) is a Name.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीष्

4.1.59|4.1.59 diirghajihvii cha chChandasi|diirghajihvii cha chChandasi|diirghajihvii cha chChandasi 4.1.59|दीर्घजिह्वी च च्छन्दसि|दीर्घजिह्वी च च्छन्दसि ४.१.५९|४.१.५९|४.१.५९ दीर्घजिह्वी च च्छन्दसि
The form दीर्घजिह्वी 'long-tongued' is irregularly formed in the छन्दस् (Vedas).<br><br>Terms: Irregular

4.1.60|4.1.60 dikpuurvapadaanNGiip‌|dikpuurvapadaanNGiip‌|dikpuurvapadaanNGiip‌ 4.1.60|दिक्पूर्वपदान्ङीप्‌|दिक्पूर्वपदान्ङीप्‌ ४.१.६०|४.१.६०|४.१.६० दिक्पूर्वपदान्ङीप्‌
The feminine affix ङीप् comes after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) which is preceded by a word signifying direction.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-ङीप्

