4.1.74|4.1.74 yaNGashchaap‌|yaNGashchaap‌|yaNGashchaap‌ 4.1.74|यङश्चाप्‌|यङश्चाप्‌ ४.१.७४|४.१.७४|४.१.७४ यङश्चाप्‌
The feminine affix चाप् comes after a stem which is formed by the affix ञ्यङ् or ष्यङ्।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-चाप्

4.1.75|4.1.75 aavaTyaachcha|aavaTyaachcha|aavaTyaachcha 4.1.75|आवट्याच्च|आवट्याच्च ४.१.७५|४.१.७५|४.१.७५ आवट्याच्च
And the feminine affix चाप् comes after the word आवट्य।<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-चाप्

4.1.76|4.1.76 taddhitaaH|taddhitaaH|taddhitaaH 4.1.76|तद्धिताः|तद्धिताः ४.१.७६|४.१.७६|४.१.७६ तद्धिताः
The तद्धित-affixes are treated of here after.<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

4.1.77|4.1.77 yuunastiH|yuunastiH|yuunastiH 4.1.77|यूनस्तिः|यूनस्तिः ४.१.७७|४.१.७७|४.१.७७ यूनस्तिः
The feminine affix ति comes after the प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) युवन् and this affix gets the name तद्धित।<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

4.1.78|4.1.78 aNiNJoranaarShayorguruupottamayoH ShyaNG gotre|aNiNJoranaarShayorguruupottamayoH ShyaNG gotre|aNiNJoranaarShayorguruupottamayoH ShyaNG gotre 4.1.78|अणिञोरनार्षयोर्गुरूपोत्तमयोः ष्यङ् गोत्रे|अणिञोरनार्षयोर्गुरूपोत्तमयोः ष्यङ् गोत्रे ४.१.७८|४.१.७८|४.१.७८ अणिञोरनार्षयोर्गुरूपोत्तमयोः ष्यङ् गोत्रे
In Patronymics used in narrower sense (counting first from the grand-child), which are formed the affixes अण् and इञ् , the feminine is formed by substituting य (ष्यङ्) for the अ and इ of those affixes and adding the long आ under -- यङश्चाप्‌ ४.१.७४, provided that they do not denote ऋषि clans and have prosodially long syllable preceding the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: ष्यङ्

4.1.79|4.1.79 gotraavayavaat‌|gotraavayavaat‌|gotraavayavaat‌ 4.1.79|गोत्रावयवात्‌|गोत्रावयवात्‌ ४.१.७९|४.१.७९|४.१.७९ गोत्रावयवात्‌
After a word denoting a non-principal गोत्र , ष्यङ् is the substitute of अण् and इञ् , the feminine, even though the syllable preceding the final be not prosodially long.<br><br>Terms: ष्यङ्

4.1.80|4.1.80 krauDyaadibhyashcha|krauDyaadibhyashcha|krauDyaadibhyashcha 4.1.80|क्रौड्यादिभ्यश्च|क्रौड्यादिभ्यश्च ४.१.८०|४.१.८०|४.१.८० क्रौड्यादिभ्यश्च
The affix ष्यङ् comes in the feminine after the words क्रौडि etc.<br><br>Terms: ष्यङ्

4.1.81|4.1.81 daivayaJNishauchivRxisaatyamugrikaaNTheviddhibhyo.anyatarasyaam|daivayaJNishauchivRxisaatyamugrikaaNTheviddhibhyo.anyatarasyaam|daivayaJNishauchivRxisaatyamugrikaaNTheviddhibhyo.anyatarasyaam 4.1.81|दैवयज्ञिशौचिवृक्षिसात्यमुग्रिकाण्ठेविद्धिभ्योऽन्यतरस्याम्|दैवयज्ञिशौचिवृक्षिसात्यमुग्रिकाण्ठेविद्धिभ्योऽन्यतरस्याम् ४.१.८१|४.१.८१|४.१.८१ दैवयज्ञिशौचिवृक्षिसात्यमुग्रिकाण्ठेविद्धिभ्योऽन्यतरस्याम्
The affix ष्यङ् optionally comes after the words 1. दैवयज्ञि 2. शौचिवृक्षि 3. सात्यमुग्रि and 4. काण्ठेविद्धि ।<br><br>Terms: ष्यङ्

4.1.82|4.1.82 samarthaanaaM prathamaadvaa|samarthaanaaM prathamaadvaa|samarthaanaaM prathamaadvaa 4.1.82|समर्थानां प्रथमाद्वा|समर्थानां प्रथमाद्वा ४.१.८२|४.१.८२|४.१.८२ समर्थानां प्रथमाद्वा
The तद्धित affixes, on the alternative of their being used at all, comes after the word that is signified by the first of the words in construction in a sūtra.<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

4.1.83|4.1.83 praagdiivyato.aN|praagdiivyato.aN|praagdiivyato.aN 4.1.83|प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण्|प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३|४.१.८३|४.१.८३ प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण्
The affix अण् should be understood to come after whatever we shall teach hereafter up to sūtra तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम् ४.४.२ etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.84|4.1.84 ashvapatyaadibhyashcha|ashvapatyaadibhyashcha|ashvapatyaadibhyashcha 4.1.84|अश्वपत्यादिभ्यश्च|अश्वपत्यादिभ्यश्च ४.१.८४|४.१.८४|४.१.८४ अश्वपत्यादिभ्यश्च
The affix अण् comes after the प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) अश्वपति etc., in the various mentioned senses antedcedently up to तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम् ४.४.२.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.85|4.1.85 dityadityaadityapatyuttarapadaaNNyaH|dityadityaadityapatyuttarapadaaNNyaH|dityadityaadityapatyuttarapadaaNNyaH 4.1.85|दित्यदित्यादित्यपत्युत्तरपदाण्ण्यः|दित्यदित्यादित्यपत्युत्तरपदाण्ण्यः ४.१.८५|४.१.८५|४.१.८५ दित्यदित्यादित्यपत्युत्तरपदाण्ण्यः
The affix ण्य comes, in the various senses taught here-in-after antecedently to तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम् ४.४.२ etc. after the Proper Names - 1. दिति 2. अदिति 3. आदित्य and that which has the word पति as its final member.<br><br>Terms: ण्य

4.1.86|4.1.86 utsaadibhyo.aNJ|utsaadibhyo.aNJ|utsaadibhyo.aNJ 4.1.86|उत्सादिभ्योऽञ्|उत्सादिभ्योऽञ् ४.१.८६|४.१.८६|४.१.८६ उत्सादिभ्योऽञ्
The affix अञ् comes after the word उत्स etc. in the various senses taught antecedently to तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम् ४.४.२.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.1.87|4.1.87 striipuMsaabhyaaM naNJsnaNJau bhavanaat‌|striipuMsaabhyaaM naNJsnaNJau bhavanaat‌|striipuMsaabhyaaM naNJsnaNJau bhavanaat‌ 4.1.87|स्त्रीपुंसाभ्यां नञ्स्नञौ भवनात्‌|स्त्रीपुंसाभ्यां नञ्स्नञौ भवनात्‌ ४.१.८७|४.१.८७|४.१.८७ स्त्रीपुंसाभ्यां नञ्स्नञौ भवनात्‌
The affixes नञ् and स्नञ् come after the words स्त्री and पुंस respectively, in the senses specified in the sūtra reckoning from this one as far as sūtra धान्यानां भवने क्षेत्रे खञ् ५.२.१.<br><br>Terms: नञ् and स्नञ्

4.1.88|4.1.88 dvigorluganapatye|dvigorluganapatye|dvigorluganapatye 4.1.88|द्विगोर्लुगनपत्ये|द्विगोर्लुगनपत्ये ४.१.८८|४.१.८८|४.१.८८ द्विगोर्लुगनपत्ये
A तद्धित affix ordained to come on account of the relation of the words being that of a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) is elided by लुक् when it has the sense of the various affixes taught antecedent to तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम् ४.४.२ etc., but not so, the affix having the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic).<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

4.1.89|4.1.89 gotre.alugachi|gotre.alugachi|gotre.alugachi 4.1.89|गोत्रेऽलुगचि|गोत्रेऽलुगचि ४.१.८९|४.१.८९|४.१.८९ गोत्रेऽलुगचि
The लुक् elision of गोत्र (Patronymic) affixes in plural, which have been enjoined by sūtras यस्कादिभ्यो गोत्रे २.४.६३ etc. and the rest is prohibited, when the affix has an initial vowel and it has the sense of the various affixes taught antecedent to तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम् ४.४.२.<br><br>Terms: लुक्-गोत्र

4.1.90|4.1.90 yuuni luk|yuuni luk|yuuni luk 4.1.90|यूनि लुक्|यूनि लुक् ४.१.९०|४.१.९०|४.१.९० यूनि लुक्
There is लुक् elision of the युवन् गोत्र (Patronymic) forming affix -- जीवति तु वंश्ये युवा ४.१.१६३, when a प्राग्दीव्यतीय affix beginning with a vowel is to be added.<br><br>Terms: लुक्-गोत्र

4.1.91|4.1.91 phakphiNJoranyatarasyaam|phakphiNJoranyatarasyaam|phakphiNJoranyatarasyaam 4.1.91|फक्फिञोरन्यतरस्याम्|फक्फिञोरन्यतरस्याम् ४.१.९१|४.१.९१|४.१.९१ फक्फिञोरन्यतरस्याम्
There is optionally लुक् elision of the युवन् affixes फक् and फिञ् when a प्राग्दीव्यतीय affix beginning with a vowel is to be added.<br><br>Terms: लुक्-गोत्र

4.1.92|4.1.92 tasyaapatyam|tasyaapatyam|tasyaapatyam 4.1.92|तस्यापत्यम्|तस्यापत्यम् ४.१.९२|४.१.९२|४.१.९२ तस्यापत्यम्
The affix अण् mentioned in प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ and those which follow it denote 'theh descendant of someone'.<br><br>Terms: अण् 

4.1.93|4.1.93 eko gotre|eko gotre|eko gotre 4.1.93|एको गोत्रे|एको गोत्रे ४.१.९३|४.१.९३|४.१.९३ एको गोत्रे
The one and the same affix is used when a more distant descendant, how low-so-ever, is to be denoted.<br><br>Terms: गोत्र

4.1.94|4.1.94 gotraadyuunyastriyaam|gotraadyuunyastriyaam|gotraadyuunyastriyaam 4.1.94|गोत्राद्यून्यस्त्रियाम्|गोत्राद्यून्यस्त्रियाम् ४.१.९४|४.१.९४|४.१.९४ गोत्राद्यून्यस्त्रियाम्
When a descendant of the description denoted by युवन् -- जीवति तु वंश्ये युवा ४.१.१६३, is intended to be expressed, a new affix is attached, only after that what already ends with an affix marking a descendant as low at least as a grandson (गोत्र): but in the feminine the word is not termed युवन् and no new affix is added.<br><br>Terms: गोत्र

4.1.95|4.1.95 ata iNJ|ata iNJ|ata iNJ 4.1.95|अत इञ्|अत इञ् ४.१.९५|४.१.९५|४.१.९५ अत इञ्
The affix affix इञ् after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) which ends in short अ , in denoting a descendant.<br><br>Terms: इञ्

4.1.96|4.1.96 baahvaadibhyashcha|baahvaadibhyashcha|baahvaadibhyashcha 4.1.96|बाह्वादिभ्यश्च|बाह्वादिभ्यश्च ४.१.९६|४.१.९६|४.१.९६ बाह्वादिभ्यश्च
The affix इञ् is added in the sense of a descendant after the words बहु etc.<br><br>Terms: इञ्

4.1.97|4.1.97 sudhaaturakaNG cha|sudhaaturakaNG cha|sudhaaturakaNG cha 4.1.97|सुधातुरकङ् च|सुधातुरकङ् च ४.१.९७|४.१.९७|४.१.९७ सुधातुरकङ् च
The affix इञ् is placed after the word सुधातृ in denoting the descendant and the ऋ of सुधातृ is replaced by the substitute अकङ् before this affix.<br><br>Terms: इञ्

4.1.98|4.1.98 gotre kunjaadibhyashchphaNJ|gotre kunjaadibhyashchphaNJ|gotre kunjaadibhyashchphaNJ 4.1.98|गोत्रे कुञ्जादिभ्यश्च्फञ्|गोत्रे कुञ्जादिभ्यश्च्फञ् ४.१.९८|४.१.९८|४.१.९८ गोत्रे कुञ्जादिभ्यश्च्फञ्
The affix च्फञ् comes after the words कुञ्च etc. when a remoter descendant (called गोत्र) is to be denoted.<br><br>Terms: च्फञ्

4.1.99|4.1.99 naDaadibhyaH phak|naDaadibhyaH phak|naDaadibhyaH phak 4.1.99|नडादिभ्यः फक्|नडादिभ्यः फक् ४.१.९९|४.१.९९|४.१.९९ नडादिभ्यः फक्
The affix फक् comes, in denoting a गोत्र descendant after the प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stems) नड etc.<br><br>Terms: फक्

4.1.100|4.1.100 haritaadibhyo.aNJaH|haritaadibhyo.aNJaH|haritaadibhyo.aNJaH 4.1.100|हरितादिभ्योऽञः|हरितादिभ्योऽञः ४.१.१००|४.१.१००|४.१.१०० हरितादिभ्योऽञः
The affix फक् comes after the words हरित etc. when they end in the affix अञ् -- अनृष्यानन्तर्ये बिदादिभ्योऽञ् ४.१.१०४<br><br>Terms: फक्

4.1.101|4.1.101 yaNJiNJoshcha|yaNJiNJoshcha|yaNJiNJoshcha 4.1.101|यञिञोश्च|यञिञोश्च ४.१.१०१|४.१.१०१|४.१.१०१ यञिञोश्च
The affix फक् is added in denoting a descendent after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in the affixes यञ् or इञ्।<br><br>Terms: फक्

4.1.102|4.1.102 sharadvachChunakadarbhaadbhRguvatsaagraayaNeShu|sharadvachChunakadarbhaadbhRguvatsaagraayaNeShu|sharadvachChunakadarbhaadbhRguvatsaagraayaNeShu 4.1.102|शरद्वच्छुनकदर्भाद्भृगुवत्साग्रायणेषु|शरद्वच्छुनकदर्भाद्भृगुवत्साग्रायणेषु ४.१.१०२|४.१.१०२|४.१.१०२ शरद्वच्छुनकदर्भाद्भृगुवत्साग्रायणेषु
The affix फक् comes in denoting a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant after the words 1. शरद्वत् 2. शुनक 3. दर्भा when they denote the descendants of भृगु , वत्स and अग्रायण , respectively. <br><br>Terms: फक्

4.1.103|4.1.103 droNaparvatajiivantaadanyatarayaam|droNaparvatajiivantaadanyatarayaam|droNaparvatajiivantaadanyatarayaam 4.1.103|द्रोणपर्वतजीवन्तादन्यतरयाम्|द्रोणपर्वतजीवन्तादन्यतरयाम् ४.१.१०३|४.१.१०३|४.१.१०३ द्रोणपर्वतजीवन्तादन्यतरयाम्
The affix फक् comes in the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant, optionally after the words 1. द्रोण 2. पर्वत and 3. जीवन्त।<br><br>Terms: फक्

4.1.104|4.1.104 anRShyaanantarye bidaadibhyo.aNJ|anRShyaanantarye bidaadibhyo.aNJ|anRShyaanantarye bidaadibhyo.aNJ 4.1.104|अनृष्यानन्तर्ये बिदादिभ्योऽञ्|अनृष्यानन्तर्ये बिदादिभ्योऽञ् ४.१.१०४|४.१.१०४|४.१.१०४ अनृष्यानन्तर्ये बिदादिभ्योऽञ्
The affix अञ् comes after the words बिद etc. in denoting a remote (गोत्र) descendant, but after those words of this class which are not the names of ancient sages, the affix अञ् has the force of denoting immediate descendant.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.1.105|4.1.105 gargaadibhyo yaNJ|gargaadibhyo yaNJ|gargaadibhyo yaNJ 4.1.105|गर्गादिभ्यो यञ्|गर्गादिभ्यो यञ् ४.१.१०५|४.१.१०५|४.१.१०५ गर्गादिभ्यो यञ्
The affix यञ् comes in the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant after the words गर्ग etc.<br><br>Terms: यञ्

4.1.106|4.1.106 madhubabhrvorbraahmaNakaushikayoH|madhubabhrvorbraahmaNakaushikayoH|madhubabhrvorbraahmaNakaushikayoH 4.1.106|मधुबभ्र्वोर्ब्राह्मणकौशिकयोः|मधुबभ्र्वोर्ब्राह्मणकौशिकयोः ४.१.१०६|४.१.१०६|४.१.१०६ मधुबभ्र्वोर्ब्राह्मणकौशिकयोः
The affix यञ् comes, in the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant after the words 1. मधु and 2. बभ्रु when the words so formed mean ब्राह्मण and कौशिक respectively.<br><br>Terms: यञ्

4.1.107|4.1.107 kapibodhaadaangirase|kapibodhaadaangirase|kapibodhaadaangirase 4.1.107|कपिबोधादाङ्गिरसे|कपिबोधादाङ्गिरसे ४.१.१०७|४.१.१०७|४.१.१०७ कपिबोधादाङ्गिरसे
The affix यञ् comes in the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant after the words 1. कपिand 2. बोध when the special descendants of the family of अङ्गिरस are meant.<br><br>Terms: यञ्

4.1.108|4.1.108 vataNDaachcha|vataNDaachcha|vataNDaachcha 4.1.108|वतण्डाच्च|वतण्डाच्च ४.१.१०८|४.१.१०८|४.१.१०८ वतण्डाच्च
The affix यञ् comes in the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant after the word वतण्ड when meaning a descendant of अङ्गिरस।<br><br>Terms: 

4.1.109|4.1.109 luk striyaam|luk striyaam|luk striyaam 4.1.109|लुक् स्त्रियाम्|लुक् स्त्रियाम् ४.१.१०९|४.१.१०९|४.१.१०९ लुक् स्त्रियाम्
The affix यञ् is लुक् elided in the feminine after the word वतण्डी when meaning a female descendant of अङ्गिरस।<br><br>Terms: यञ्

4.1.110|4.1.110 ashvaadibhyaH phaNJ|ashvaadibhyaH phaNJ|ashvaadibhyaH phaNJ 4.1.110|अश्वादिभ्यः फञ्|अश्वादिभ्यः फञ् ४.१.११०|४.१.११०|४.१.११० अश्वादिभ्यः फञ्
The affix फञ् comes in the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant after the words अश्व etc.<br><br>Terms: फञ्

4.1.111|4.1.111 bhargaat‌ traigarte|bhargaat‌ traigarte|bhargaat‌ traigarte 4.1.111|भर्गात्‌ त्रैगर्ते|भर्गात्‌ त्रैगर्ते ४.१.१११|४.१.१११|४.१.१११ भर्गात्‌ त्रैगर्ते
The affix फञ् comes in the sense of a गोत्र (Patronymic) descendant after the word भर्ग when the meaning is a त्रैगर्ते।<br><br>Terms: फञ्

4.1.112|4.1.112 shivaadibhyo.aN|shivaadibhyo.aN|shivaadibhyo.aN 4.1.112|शिवादिभ्योऽण्|शिवादिभ्योऽण् ४.१.११२|४.१.११२|४.१.११२ शिवादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of a descendant after the words शिव etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.113|4.1.113 avRddhaabhyo nadiimaanuShiibhyastannaamikaabhyaH|avRddhaabhyo nadiimaanuShiibhyastannaamikaabhyaH|avRddhaabhyo nadiimaanuShiibhyastannaamikaabhyaH 4.1.113|अवृद्धाभ्यो नदीमानुषीभ्यस्तन्नामिकाभ्यः|अवृद्धाभ्यो नदीमानुषीभ्यस्तन्नामिकाभ्यः ४.१.११३|४.१.११३|४.१.११३ अवृद्धाभ्यो नदीमानुषीभ्यस्तन्नामिकाभ्यः
The affix अण् comes in the sense of descendant after the words are the names of rivers or women when such words are not वृद्धम् words and when they are used as names and not as adjectives.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.114|4.1.114 RShyandhakavRShNikurubhyashcha|RShyandhakavRShNikurubhyashcha|RShyandhakavRShNikurubhyashcha 4.1.114|ऋष्यन्धकवृष्णिकुरुभ्यश्च|ऋष्यन्धकवृष्णिकुरुभ्यश्च ४.१.११४|४.१.११४|४.१.११४ ऋष्यन्धकवृष्णिकुरुभ्यश्च
The affix अण् comes in the sense of descendant after प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) denoting the name of a ऋषि or the name of a person of the family of 1. अन्धक 2. वृष्णि 3. कुरु।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.115|4.1.115 maaturut‌ saMkhyaasambhadrapuurvaayaaH|maaturut‌ saMkhyaasambhadrapuurvaayaaH|maaturut‌ saMkhyaasambhadrapuurvaayaaH 4.1.115|मातुरुत्‌ संख्यासम्भद्रपूर्वायाः|मातुरुत्‌ संख्यासम्भद्रपूर्वायाः ४.१.११५|४.१.११५|४.१.११५ मातुरुत्‌ संख्यासम्भद्रपूर्वायाः
The affix अण् comes in the sense of descendant after the word मातृ when it is preceded by a Numeral or by the words सम् or भद्र and the letter उ is substituted for the final ऋ of मातृ।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.116|4.1.116 kanyaayaaH kaniina cha|kanyaayaaH kaniina cha|kanyaayaaH kaniina cha 4.1.116|कन्यायाः कनीन च|कन्यायाः कनीन च ४.१.११६|४.१.११६|४.१.११६ कन्यायाः कनीन च
The affix अण् comes in the sense of descendant after the word कन्या and when this affix is added, कनीन is the substitute of कन्या।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.117|4.1.117 vikarNashungachChagalaadvatsabharadvaajaatriShu|vikarNashungachChagalaadvatsabharadvaajaatriShu|vikarNashungachChagalaadvatsabharadvaajaatriShu 4.1.117|विकर्णशुङ्गच्छगलाद्वत्सभरद्वाजात्रिषु|विकर्णशुङ्गच्छगलाद्वत्सभरद्वाजात्रिषु ४.१.११७|४.१.११७|४.१.११७ विकर्णशुङ्गच्छगलाद्वत्सभरद्वाजात्रिषु
The affix अण् comes after the words 1. विकर्ण 2. शुङ्ग and 3. छगल when the sense is a descendant of the family of वत्स , भारद्वाज and अत्रि , respectively.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.118|4.1.118 piilaayaa vaa|piilaayaa vaa|piilaayaa vaa 4.1.118|पीलाया वा|पीलाया वा ४.१.११८|४.१.११८|४.१.११८ पीलाया वा
The affix अण् comes optionally after the word पीला in denoting a descendant.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.119|4.1.119 Dhak cha maNDuukaat‌|Dhak cha maNDuukaat‌|Dhak cha maNDuukaat‌ 4.1.119|ढक् च मण्डूकात्‌|ढक् च मण्डूकात्‌ ४.१.११९|४.१.११९|४.१.११९ ढक् च मण्डूकात्‌
The affix ढक् comes optionally in the sense of a descendant after the word मण्डूक as well as the affix अण्।<br><br>Terms: अण् and ढक्

4.1.120|4.1.120 striibhyo Dhak|striibhyo Dhak|striibhyo Dhak 4.1.120|स्त्रीभ्यो ढक्|स्त्रीभ्यो ढक् ४.१.१२०|४.१.१२०|४.१.१२० स्त्रीभ्यो ढक्
Words ending in the feminine affixes take the affix ढक् in forming their गोत्र (Patronymic).<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.121|4.1.121 dvyachaH|dvyachaH|dvyachaH 4.1.121|द्व्यचः|द्व्यचः ४.१.१२१|४.१.१२१|४.१.१२१ द्व्यचः
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of a descendant after a word ending in a feminine affix and consisting of two vowels.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.122|4.1.122 itashchaaniNJaH|itashchaaniNJaH|itashchaaniNJaH 4.1.122|इतश्चानिञः|इतश्चानिञः ४.१.१२२|४.१.१२२|४.१.१२२ इतश्चानिञः
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of a descendant after a dissyallabic प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in short इ , but not, however after a word ending in the Patronymic affix इञ्।<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.123|4.1.123 shubhraadibhyashcha|shubhraadibhyashcha|shubhraadibhyashcha 4.1.123|शुभ्रादिभ्यश्च|शुभ्रादिभ्यश्च ४.१.१२३|४.१.१२३|४.१.१२३ शुभ्रादिभ्यश्च
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of a descendant after the stems शुभ्र etc.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.124|4.1.124 vikarNakuShiitakaat‌ kaashyape|vikarNakuShiitakaat‌ kaashyape|vikarNakuShiitakaat‌ kaashyape 4.1.124|विकर्णकुषीतकात्‌ काश्यपे|विकर्णकुषीतकात्‌ काश्यपे ४.१.१२४|४.१.१२४|४.१.१२४ विकर्णकुषीतकात्‌ काश्यपे
The affix ढक् comes after the words 1. विकर्ण and 2. कुषीत when they mean the descendants of काश्यप।<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.125|4.1.125 bhruvo vuk cha|bhruvo vuk cha|bhruvo vuk cha 4.1.125|भ्रुवो वुक् च|भ्रुवो वुक् च ४.१.१२५|४.१.१२५|४.१.१२५ भ्रुवो वुक् च
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of a descendant after the word भ्रू and the augment वुक् is added when this affix is to be applied.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.126|4.1.126 kalyaaNyaadiinaaminaNG|kalyaaNyaadiinaaminaNG|kalyaaNyaadiinaaminaNG 4.1.126|कल्याण्यादीनामिनङ्|कल्याण्यादीनामिनङ् ४.१.१२६|४.१.१२६|४.१.१२६ कल्याण्यादीनामिनङ्
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of a descendant after the words कल्याणी etc. and the substitute इनङ् takes the place of the final of these words before this affix.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.127|4.1.127 kulaTaayaa vaa|kulaTaayaa vaa|kulaTaayaa vaa 4.1.127|कुलटाया वा|कुलटाया वा ४.१.१२७|४.१.१२७|४.१.१२७ कुलटाया वा
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of a descendant after the word कुल्टा and इनङ् is optionally the substitute of the final before this affix.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.128|4.1.128 chaTakaayaa airak|chaTakaayaa airak|chaTakaayaa airak 4.1.128|चटकाया ऐरक्|चटकाया ऐरक् ४.१.१२८|४.१.१२८|४.१.१२८ चटकाया ऐरक्
The word चटका takes the affix ऐरक् in forming the Patronymic.<br><br>Terms: ऐरक्

4.1.129|4.1.129 godhaayaa Dhrak|godhaayaa Dhrak|godhaayaa Dhrak 4.1.129|गोधाया ढ्रक्|गोधाया ढ्रक् ४.१.१२९|४.१.१२९|४.१.१२९ गोधाया ढ्रक्
The affix ढ्रक् comes in the sense of a descendant after the word गोधा।<br><br>Terms: ढ्रक्

4.1.130|4.1.130 aaragudiichaam|aaragudiichaam|aaragudiichaam 4.1.130|आरगुदीचाम्|आरगुदीचाम् ४.१.१३०|४.१.१३०|४.१.१३० आरगुदीचाम्
The affix आरक् comes in the sense of a descendant after the word गोधा according to the opinion of Northern Grammarians.<br><br>Terms: आरक्

4.1.131|4.1.131 xudraabhyo vaa|xudraabhyo vaa|xudraabhyo vaa 4.1.131|क्षुद्राभ्यो वा|क्षुद्राभ्यो वा ४.१.१३१|४.१.१३१|४.१.१३१ क्षुद्राभ्यो वा
The affix ढ्रक् comes optionally in the sense of descendant after the feminine words denoting mean objects.<br><br>Terms: ढ्रक्

4.1.132|4.1.132 pitRShvasushChaN|pitRShvasushChaN|pitRShvasushChaN 4.1.132|पितृष्वसुश्छण्|पितृष्वसुश्छण् ४.१.१३२|४.१.१३२|४.१.१३२ पितृष्वसुश्छण्
The affix छण् comes in the senes of a descendant after the word पितृष्वसृ।<br><br>Terms: छण्

4.1.133|4.1.133 Dhaki lopaH|Dhaki lopaH|Dhaki lopaH 4.1.133|ढकि लोपः|ढकि लोपः ४.१.१३३|४.१.१३३|४.१.१३३ ढकि लोपः
The final vowel of पितृष्वसृ is elided when the affix ढक् , in the sense of a descendant, is added.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.134|4.1.134 maatRShvasushcha|maatRShvasushcha|maatRShvasushcha 4.1.134|मातृष्वसुश्च|मातृष्वसुश्च ४.१.१३४|४.१.१३४|४.१.१३४ मातृष्वसुश्च
So also after the word मातृष्वसृ the affix छण् is added and the final is elided when ढक् follows in forming Patronymic.<br><br>Terms: छण्

4.1.135|4.1.135 chatuShpaadbhyo DhaNJ|chatuShpaadbhyo DhaNJ|chatuShpaadbhyo DhaNJ 4.1.135|चतुष्पाद्भ्यो ढञ्|चतुष्पाद्भ्यो ढञ् ४.१.१३५|४.१.१३५|४.१.१३५ चतुष्पाद्भ्यो ढञ्
The affix ढञ् comes in the sense of a descendant after the bases denoting quadrupeds.<br><br>Terms: ढञ्

4.1.136|4.1.136 gRShTyaadibhyashcha|gRShTyaadibhyashcha|gRShTyaadibhyashcha 4.1.136|गृष्ट्यादिभ्यश्च|गृष्ट्यादिभ्यश्च ४.१.१३६|४.१.१३६|४.१.१३६ गृष्ट्यादिभ्यश्च
The affix ढञ् comes in the sense of a descendant after the word गृष्टि etc.<br><br>Terms: ढञ्

4.1.137|4.1.137 raajashvashuraadyat‌|raajashvashuraadyat‌|raajashvashuraadyat‌ 4.1.137|राजश्वशुराद्यत्‌|राजश्वशुराद्यत्‌ ४.१.१३७|४.१.१३७|४.१.१३७ राजश्वशुराद्यत्‌
The affix यत् comes in the sense of the descendant after the words राजन् and श्वसुर।<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.1.138|4.1.138 xatraadghaH|xatraadghaH|xatraadghaH 4.1.138|क्षत्राद्घः|क्षत्राद्घः ४.१.१३८|४.१.१३८|४.१.१३८ क्षत्राद्घः
The affix घ comes in the sense of a descendant after the word क्षत्र।<br><br>Terms: घ

4.1.139|4.1.139 kulaat‌ khaH|kulaat‌ khaH|kulaat‌ khaH 4.1.139|कुलात्‌ खः|कुलात्‌ खः ४.१.१३९|४.१.१३९|४.१.१३९ कुलात्‌ खः
The affix ख comes in the sense of a descendant after the प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) कुल and a compound word that ends in कुल।<br><br>Terms: ख

4.1.140|4.1.140 apuurvapadaadanyatarasyaaM yaDDhakaNJau|apuurvapadaadanyatarasyaaM yaDDhakaNJau|apuurvapadaadanyatarasyaaM yaDDhakaNJau 4.1.140|अपूर्वपदादन्यतरस्यां यड्ढकञौ|अपूर्वपदादन्यतरस्यां यड्ढकञौ ४.१.१४०|४.१.१४०|४.१.१४० अपूर्वपदादन्यतरस्यां यड्ढकञौ
The affixes यत् and ढकञ् come optionally after the word कुल when it is not preceded by any other word which gets the designation of पद -- सुप्तिङन्तं पदम् १.४.१४.<br><br>Terms: यत् and ढकञ्

4.1.141|4.1.141 mahaakulaadaNJkhaNJau|mahaakulaadaNJkhaNJau|mahaakulaadaNJkhaNJau 4.1.141|महाकुलादञ्खञौ|महाकुलादञ्खञौ ४.१.१४१|४.१.१४१|४.१.१४१ महाकुलादञ्खञौ
The affixes अञ् and खञ् come optionally after the word महाकुल।<br><br>Terms: अञ् and खञ्

4.1.142|4.1.142 duShkulaaDDhak|duShkulaaDDhak|duShkulaaDDhak 4.1.142|दुष्कुलाड्ढक्|दुष्कुलाड्ढक् ४.१.१४२|४.१.१४२|४.१.१४२ दुष्कुलाड्ढक्
The affix ढक् comes optionally in the sense of descendant after the word दुष्कुल।<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.1.143|4.1.143 svasushChaH|svasushChaH|svasushChaH 4.1.143|स्वसुश्छः|स्वसुश्छः ४.१.१४३|४.१.१४३|४.१.१४३ स्वसुश्छः
The affix छ comes in the sense of descendant after the word स्वसृ।<br><br>Terms: छ

4.1.144|4.1.144 bhraaturvyachcha|bhraaturvyachcha|bhraaturvyachcha 4.1.144|भ्रातुर्व्यच्च|भ्रातुर्व्यच्च ४.१.१४४|४.१.१४४|४.१.१४४ भ्रातुर्व्यच्च
The affix व्यत् also comes in the sense of descendant after the word भ्रातृ।<br><br>Terms: व्यत्

4.1.145|4.1.145 vyan sapatne|vyan sapatne|vyan sapatne 4.1.145|व्यन् सपत्ने|व्यन् सपत्ने ४.१.१४५|४.१.१४५|४.१.१४५ व्यन् सपत्ने
The affix व्यत् comes after the word भ्रातृ when the sense is that of 'an enemy'.<br><br>Terms: व्यत्

4.1.146|4.1.146 revatyaadibhyaShThak|revatyaadibhyaShThak|revatyaadibhyaShThak 4.1.146|रेवत्यादिभ्यष्ठक्|रेवत्यादिभ्यष्ठक् ४.१.१४६|४.१.१४६|४.१.१४६ रेवत्यादिभ्यष्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes in the sense of descendant after the word रेवती etc.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.1.147|4.1.147 gotrastriyaaH kutsane Na cha|gotrastriyaaH kutsane Na cha|gotrastriyaaH kutsane Na cha 4.1.147|गोत्रस्त्रियाः कुत्सने ण च|गोत्रस्त्रियाः कुत्सने ण च ४.१.१४७|४.१.१४७|४.१.१४७ गोत्रस्त्रियाः कुत्सने ण च
And when contempt is to be expressed, the affix ण comes in the sense of descendant after a feminine word denoting a गोत्र-descendant.<br><br>Terms: ण

4.1.148|4.1.148 vRddhaaTThak sauviireShu bahulam|vRddhaaTThak sauviireShu bahulam|vRddhaaTThak sauviireShu bahulam 4.1.148|वृद्धाट्ठक् सौवीरेषु बहुलम्|वृद्धाट्ठक् सौवीरेषु बहुलम् ४.१.१४८|४.१.१४८|४.१.१४८ वृद्धाट्ठक् सौवीरेषु बहुलम्
When contempt is to be expressed, the affix ठक् is diversely added in the senses of a descendant after a वृद्ध word denoting सौवीर गोत्र-s.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.1.149|4.1.149 pheshCha cha|pheshCha cha|pheshCha cha 4.1.149|फेश्छ च|फेश्छ च ४.१.१४९|४.१.१४९|४.१.१४९ फेश्छ च
When contempt is to be expressed, the affix छ (as well as the affix ठक्) comes in the sense of descendant after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in the affix फिञ् and denoting a सौवीर गोत्र।<br><br>Terms: ठक् and छ

4.1.150|4.1.150 phaaNTaahRtimimataabhyaaM NaphiNJau|phaaNTaahRtimimataabhyaaM NaphiNJau|phaaNTaahRtimimataabhyaaM NaphiNJau 4.1.150|फाण्टाहृतिमिमताभ्यां णफिञौ|फाण्टाहृतिमिमताभ्यां णफिञौ ४.१.१५०|४.१.१५०|४.१.१५० फाण्टाहृतिमिमताभ्यां णफिञौ
The affixes ण and फिञ् comes in the sense of descendant of a person belonging to सुविर country after the word फाण्टाहृति and मिमता।<br><br>Terms: ण and फिञ्

4.1.151|4.1.151 kurvaadibhyo NyaH|kurvaadibhyo NyaH|kurvaadibhyo NyaH 4.1.151|कुर्वादिभ्यो ण्यः|कुर्वादिभ्यो ण्यः ४.१.१५१|४.१.१५१|४.१.१५१ कुर्वादिभ्यो ण्यः
The affix ण्य comes in the sense of descendant after the words कुरु etc.<br><br>Terms: ण्य

4.1.152|4.1.152 senaantalaxaNakaaribhyashcha|senaantalaxaNakaaribhyashcha|senaantalaxaNakaaribhyashcha 4.1.152|सेनान्तलक्षणकारिभ्यश्च|सेनान्तलक्षणकारिभ्यश्च ४.१.१५२|४.१.१५२|४.१.१५२ सेनान्तलक्षणकारिभ्यश्च
The affix ण्य comes in the sense of descendant after प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) ending in सेना after the word लक्षण and after words denoting artisans.<br><br>Terms: ण्य

4.1.153|4.1.153 udiichaamiNJ|udiichaamiNJ|udiichaamiNJ 4.1.153|उदीचामिञ्|उदीचामिञ् ४.१.१५३|४.१.१५३|४.१.१५३ उदीचामिञ्
According to the opinion of Northern Grammarians, the affix इञ् comes in the sense of descendant after the words ending in सेना , the word लक्षण and words expressing artisans.<br><br>Terms: इञ्

4.1.154|4.1.154 tikaadibhyaH phiNJ|tikaadibhyaH phiNJ|tikaadibhyaH phiNJ 4.1.154|तिकादिभ्यः फिञ्|तिकादिभ्यः फिञ् ४.१.१५४|४.१.१५४|४.१.१५४ तिकादिभ्यः फिञ्
The affix फिञ् comes in the sense of descendant after the words तिक etc.<br><br>Terms: फिञ्

4.1.155|4.1.155 kausalyakaarmaaryaabhyaaM cha|kausalyakaarmaaryaabhyaaM cha|kausalyakaarmaaryaabhyaaM cha 4.1.155|कौसल्यकार्मार्याभ्यां च|कौसल्यकार्मार्याभ्यां च ४.१.१५५|४.१.१५५|४.१.१५५ कौसल्यकार्मार्याभ्यां च
The affix फिञ् comes in the sense of descendant after the words कौसल्य and कार्मार्या।<br><br>Terms: फिञ्

4.1.156|4.1.156 aNo dvyachaH|aNo dvyachaH|aNo dvyachaH 4.1.156|अणो द्व्यचः|अणो द्व्यचः ४.१.१५६|४.१.१५६|४.१.१५६ अणो द्व्यचः
The affix फिञ् comes in the sense of descendant after a dissyllabic word ending in the affix अण्।<br><br>Terms: फिञ्

4.1.157|4.1.157 udiichaaM vRddhaadagotraat‌|udiichaaM vRddhaadagotraat‌|udiichaaM vRddhaadagotraat‌ 4.1.157|उदीचां वृद्धादगोत्रात्‌|उदीचां वृद्धादगोत्रात्‌ ४.१.१५७|४.१.१५७|४.१.१५७ उदीचां वृद्धादगोत्रात्‌
According to the opinion of Northern Grammarians after the words with वृद्धि in the first syllable when it is not a गोत्र -name, the affix फिञ् is used in the sense of a descendant.<br><br>Terms: फिञ्

4.1.158|4.1.158 vaakinaadiinaaM kuk cha|vaakinaadiinaaM kuk cha|vaakinaadiinaaM kuk cha 4.1.158|वाकिनादीनां कुक् च|वाकिनादीनां कुक् च ४.१.१५८|४.१.१५८|४.१.१५८ वाकिनादीनां कुक् च
The augment क् (कुक्) is added to the words वाकिन etc. when the Patronymic affix फिन् follows.<br><br>Terms: फिन्

4.1.159|4.1.159 putraantaadanyatarasyaam|putraantaadanyatarasyaam|putraantaadanyatarasyaam 4.1.159|पुत्रान्तादन्यतरस्याम्|पुत्रान्तादन्यतरस्याम् ४.१.१५९|४.१.१५९|४.१.१५९ पुत्रान्तादन्यतरस्याम्
The augment कुक् optionally comes after a stem ending with the word पुत्र when the Patronymic affix फिन् follows.<br><br>Terms: फिन्

4.1.160|4.1.160 praachaamavRddhaat‌ phin bahulam‌|praachaamavRddhaat‌ phin bahulam‌|praachaamavRddhaat‌ phin bahulam‌ 4.1.160|प्राचामवृद्धात्‌ फिन् बहुलम्‌|प्राचामवृद्धात्‌ फिन् बहुलम्‌ ४.१.१६०|४.१.१६०|४.१.१६० प्राचामवृद्धात्‌ फिन् बहुलम्‌
According to the opinion of Eastern Grammarians after a stem not having वृद्धि vowel in the first syllable, the affix फिन् is diversely used in the sense of a descendant.<br><br>Terms: फिन्

4.1.161|4.1.161 manorjaataavaNJyatau Shuk cha|manorjaataavaNJyatau Shuk cha|manorjaataavaNJyatau Shuk cha 4.1.161|मनोर्जातावञ्यतौ षुक् च|मनोर्जातावञ्यतौ षुक् च ४.१.१६१|४.१.१६१|४.१.१६१ मनोर्जातावञ्यतौ षुक् च
The affixes अञ् and यत् come after the word मनु and the augment षुक् is added when these affixes follow provided that the whole word so formed denotes a जाति (class name).<br><br>Terms: अञ् and यत्

4.1.162|4.1.162 apatyaM pautraprabhRti gotram‌|apatyaM pautraprabhRti gotram‌|apatyaM pautraprabhRti gotram‌ 4.1.162|अपत्यं पौत्रप्रभृति गोत्रम्‌|अपत्यं पौत्रप्रभृति गोत्रम्‌ ४.१.१६२|४.१.१६२|४.१.१६२ अपत्यं पौत्रप्रभृति गोत्रम्‌
A descendant being a grandson or a still lower offspring is called गोत्र।<br><br>Terms: गोत्र

4.1.163|4.1.163 jiivati tu vaMshye yuvaa|jiivati tu vaMshye yuvaa|jiivati tu vaMshye yuvaa 4.1.163|जीवति तु वंश्ये युवा|जीवति तु वंश्ये युवा ४.१.१६३|४.१.१६३|४.१.१६३ जीवति तु वंश्ये युवा
But when one in a line of descent beginning with a father (and reckoning upwards) is alive, the descendant of a grandson or still lower descendant is called युवन् only.<br><br>Terms: युवन्

4.1.164|4.1.164 bhraatari cha jyaayasi|bhraatari cha jyaayasi|bhraatari cha jyaayasi 4.1.164|भ्रातरि च ज्यायसि|भ्रातरि च ज्यायसि ४.१.१६४|४.१.१६४|४.१.१६४ भ्रातरि च ज्यायसि
When an elder brother is alive, the younger brother gets the title of युवन् , being the descendant of a grandson etc.<br><br>Terms: युवन्

4.1.165|4.1.165 vaa.anyasmin sapiNDe sthaviratare jiivati|vaa.anyasmin sapiNDe sthaviratare jiivati|vaa.anyasmin sapiNDe sthaviratare jiivati 4.1.165|वाऽन्यस्मिन् सपिण्डे स्थविरतरे जीवति|वाऽन्यस्मिन् सपिण्डे स्थविरतरे जीवति ४.१.१६५|४.१.१६५|४.१.१६५ वाऽन्यस्मिन् सपिण्डे स्थविरतरे जीवति
The living descendant of a grandson etc. is called optionally a युवन् when a more superior सपिण्ड other than a brother is alive.<br><br>Terms: युवन्

4.1.166|4.1.166 vRddhasya cha puujaayaam|vRddhasya cha puujaayaam|vRddhasya cha puujaayaam 4.1.166|वृद्धस्य च पूजायाम्|वृद्धस्य च पूजायाम् ४.१.१६६|४.१.१६६|४.१.१६६ वृद्धस्य च पूजायाम्
The गोत्र is sometimes optionally regarded as युवन् when respectful reference to him is intended.<br><br>Terms: युवन्

4.1.167|4.1.167 yuunashcha kutsaayaam|yuunashcha kutsaayaam|yuunashcha kutsaayaam 4.1.167|यूनश्च कुत्सायाम्|यूनश्च कुत्सायाम् ४.१.१६७|४.१.१६७|४.१.१६७ यूनश्च कुत्सायाम्
The युवन् is optionally spoken of as गोत्र when contemptuous reference to him is intended.<br><br>Terms: युवन्

4.1.168|4.1.168 janapadashabdaat‌ xatriyaadaNJ|janapadashabdaat‌ xatriyaadaNJ|janapadashabdaat‌ xatriyaadaNJ 4.1.168|जनपदशब्दात्‌ क्षत्रियादञ्|जनपदशब्दात्‌ क्षत्रियादञ् ४.१.१६८|४.१.१६८|४.१.१६८ जनपदशब्दात्‌ क्षत्रियादञ्
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of descendant after a word which while denoting a country, expresses also a tribe of क्षत्रिय-s.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.1.169|4.1.169 saalveyagaandhaaribhyaaM cha|saalveyagaandhaaribhyaaM cha|saalveyagaandhaaribhyaaM cha 4.1.169|साल्वेयगान्धारिभ्यां च|साल्वेयगान्धारिभ्यां च ४.१.१६९|४.१.१६९|४.१.१६९ साल्वेयगान्धारिभ्यां च
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of descendant after the words 1. साल्वेय and 2. गान्धारि ।<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.1.170|4.1.170 dvyaNJmagadhakalingasuuramasaadaN|dvyaNJmagadhakalingasuuramasaadaN|dvyaNJmagadhakalingasuuramasaadaN 4.1.170|द्व्यञ्मगधकलिङ्गसूरमसादण्|द्व्यञ्मगधकलिङ्गसूरमसादण् ४.१.१७०|४.१.१७०|४.१.१७० द्व्यञ्मगधकलिङ्गसूरमसादण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of descendant after dissyllabic words and the words 1. मगध 2. कलिङ्ग and 3. सूरमस when they are the names of countries as well as क्षत्रिय-s.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.1.171|4.1.171 vRddhetkosalaajaadaaNJNJyaNG|vRddhetkosalaajaadaaNJNJyaNG|vRddhetkosalaajaadaaNJNJyaNG 4.1.171|वृद्धेत्कोसलाजादाञ्ञ्यङ्|वृद्धेत्कोसलाजादाञ्ञ्यङ् ४.१.१७१|४.१.१७१|४.१.१७१ वृद्धेत्कोसलाजादाञ्ञ्यङ्
The affix ञ्यङ् comes in the sense of descendant after a word having वृद्धि in the first syllable and after a word ending in short इ and after the words 1. कोसल and 2. अजाद when they are the names of countries and क्षत्रिय-s.<br><br>Terms: ञ्यङ्

4.1.172|4.1.172 kuruNaadibhyo NyaH|kuruNaadibhyo NyaH|kuruNaadibhyo NyaH 4.1.172|कुरुणादिभ्यो ण्यः|कुरुणादिभ्यो ण्यः ४.१.१७२|४.१.१७२|४.१.१७२ कुरुणादिभ्यो ण्यः
The affix ण्य comes after the word कुरु and a word beginning with न when these words denote a country being the name of a क्षत्रिय tribe also.<br><br>Terms: ण्य

4.1.173|4.1.173 saalvaavayavapratyagrathakalakuuTaashmakaadiNJ|saalvaavayavapratyagrathakalakuuTaashmakaadiNJ|saalvaavayavapratyagrathakalakuuTaashmakaadiNJ 4.1.173|साल्वावयवप्रत्यग्रथकलकूटाश्मकादिञ्|साल्वावयवप्रत्यग्रथकलकूटाश्मकादिञ् ४.१.१७३|४.१.१७३|४.१.१७३ साल्वावयवप्रत्यग्रथकलकूटाश्मकादिञ्
The affix इञ् comes in the sense of descendant after a word which denotes any sub-division of the country साल्व and after the words 1. प्रत्यग्रथ 2. कलकूट and 3. अश्मक, when these are names of countries and of tribes.<br><br>Terms: इञ्

4.1.174|4.1.174 te tadraajaaH|te tadraajaaH|te tadraajaaH 4.1.174|ते तद्राजाः|ते तद्राजाः ४.१.१७४|४.१.१७४|४.१.१७४ ते तद्राजाः
These (viz. the affixes अञ् -- जनपदशब्दात्‌ क्षत्रियादञ् ४.१.१६८ etc.) are called तद्राजा 'the king thereof' affixes.<br><br>Terms: तद्राजा

4.1.175|4.1.175 kambojaalluk|kambojaalluk|kambojaalluk 4.1.175|कम्बोजाल्लुक्|कम्बोजाल्लुक् ४.१.१७५|४.१.१७५|४.१.१७५ कम्बोजाल्लुक्
After the word कम्बोज there is elision by लुक् of the तद्राजा affix.<br><br>Terms: तद्राजा

4.1.176|4.1.176 striyaamavantikuntikurubhyashcha|striyaamavantikuntikurubhyashcha|striyaamavantikuntikurubhyashcha 4.1.176|स्त्रियामवन्तिकुन्तिकुरुभ्यश्च|स्त्रियामवन्तिकुन्तिकुरुभ्यश्च ४.१.१७६|४.१.१७६|४.१.१७६ स्त्रियामवन्तिकुन्तिकुरुभ्यश्च
In denoting a feminine name, the तद्राजा is elided after the words 1. अवन्ति 2. कुन्ति and 3. कुरु ।<br><br>Terms: तद्राजा

4.1.177|4.1.177 atashcha|atashcha|atashcha 4.1.177|अतश्च|अतश्च ४.१.१७७|४.१.१७७|४.१.१७७ अतश्च
In forming the feminine of a word which ends in the masculine in the तद्राजा affix अ , the affix is लुक् elided.<br><br>Terms: तद्राजा

4.1.178|4.1.178 na praachyabhargaadiyaudheyaadibhyaH|na praachyabhargaadiyaudheyaadibhyaH|na praachyabhargaadiyaudheyaadibhyaH 4.1.178|न प्राच्यभर्गादियौधेयादिभ्यः|न प्राच्यभर्गादियौधेयादिभ्यः ४.१.१७८|४.१.१७८|४.१.१७८ न प्राच्यभर्गादियौधेयादिभ्यः
The तद्राजा affix is not elided in the feminine, if it forms the names of the क्षत्रिय-sūtras of the East or it comes after the word भर्ग etc. and यौधेय etc.<br><br>Terms: तद्राजा

4.2.1|4.2.1 tena raktaM raagaat‌|tena raktaM raagaat‌|tena raktaM raagaat‌ 4.2.1|तेन रक्तं रागात्‌|तेन रक्तं रागात्‌ ४.२.१|४.२.१|४.२.१ तेन रक्तं रागात्‌
The affix अण् already ordained -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३, comes after the name of a colour in the sense of 'coloured thereby'.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.2|4.2.2 laaxaarochanaa(shakalakardamaa)TThak|laaxaarochanaa(shakalakardamaa)TThak|laaxaarochanaa(shakalakardamaa)TThak 4.2.2|लाक्षारोचना(शकलकर्दमा)ट्ठक्|लाक्षारोचना(शकलकर्दमा)ट्ठक् ४.२.२|४.२.२|४.२.२ लाक्षारोचना(शकलकर्दमा)ट्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes, in the sense of coloured thereby after the words 1. लाक्षा 2. रोचना 3. शकल 4. कर्दमा (which being names of colours, are in the Instrumental -3rd case in a sentence).<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.2.3|4.2.3 naxatreNa yuktaH kaalaH|naxatreNa yuktaH kaalaH|naxatreNa yuktaH kaalaH 4.2.3|नक्षत्रेण युक्तः कालः|नक्षत्रेण युक्तः कालः ४.२.३|४.२.३|४.२.३ नक्षत्रेण युक्तः कालः
The affix अण् already ordained -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३, comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction which is the name of a lunar mansion, to signify a time connected with the asterism.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.4|4.2.4 lubavisheShe|lubavisheShe|lubavisheShe 4.2.4|लुबविशेषे|लुबविशेषे ४.२.४|४.२.४|४.२.४ लुबविशेषे
The affix above ordained is elided by लुप् when there is no specification.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.5|4.2.5 saMJNaayaaM shravaNaashvatthaabhyaam‌|saMJNaayaaM shravaNaashvatthaabhyaam‌|saMJNaayaaM shravaNaashvatthaabhyaam‌ 4.2.5|संज्ञायां श्रवणाश्वत्थाभ्याम्‌|संज्ञायां श्रवणाश्वत्थाभ्याम्‌ ४.२.५|४.२.५|४.२.५ संज्ञायां श्रवणाश्वत्थाभ्याम्‌
The affix above ordained is elided by लुप् after the words 1. श्रवण and 2. अश्वथ when the whole word so formed is an appellation and there is specification of time.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.6|4.2.6 dvaMdvaachChaH|dvaMdvaachChaH|dvaMdvaachChaH 4.2.6|द्वंद्वाच्छः|द्वंद्वाच्छः ४.२.६|४.२.६|४.२.६ द्वंद्वाच्छः
The affix छ comes after the द्वन्द compound of the names of lunar mansions, when it is in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction, to signify time connected with the asterism whether there be a specification or not.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.7|4.2.7 dRShTaM saama|dRShTaM saama|dRShTaM saama 4.2.7|दृष्ट्अं साम|दृष्ट्अं साम ४.२.७|४.२.७|४.२.७ दृष्ट्अं साम
The affix अण् -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ comes after a word in construction in the Instrumental -3rd case, in the sense of seen - the thing seen by the one whose name is in the Instrumental -3rd case, being the साम वेद।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.8|4.2.8 kalerDhak|kalerDhak|kalerDhak 4.2.8|कलेर्ढक्|कलेर्ढक् ४.२.८|४.२.८|४.२.८ कलेर्ढक्
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of साम वेद seen after the word कलि being in the Instrumental -3rd case.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.2.9|4.2.9 vaamadevaaDDyaDDyau|vaamadevaaDDyaDDyau|vaamadevaaDDyaDDyau 4.2.9|वामदेवाड्ड्यड्ड्यौ|वामदेवाड्ड्यड्ड्यौ ४.२.९|४.२.९|४.२.९ वामदेवाड्ड्यड्ड्यौ
The affixes ड्यत् and ड्य come in the sense of the साम वेद seen after the word वामदेव , being in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction.<br><br>Terms: ड्यत् and ड्य

4.2.10|4.2.10 parivRto rathaH|parivRto rathaH|parivRto rathaH 4.2.10|परिवृतो रथः|परिवृतो रथः ४.२.१०|४.२.१०|४.२.१० परिवृतो रथः
The affix अण् comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense of 'surrounded' the thing so surrounded being 'a chariot'.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.11|4.2.11 paaNDukambalaadiniH|paaNDukambalaadiniH|paaNDukambalaadiniH 4.2.11|पाण्डुकम्बलादिनिः|पाण्डुकम्बलादिनिः ४.२.११|४.२.११|४.२.११ पाण्डुकम्बलादिनिः
The affix इनि comes after the word पाण्डुकम्बल etc. being in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense of 'surrounded' the thing so surrounded being 'a chariot'.<br><br>Terms: इनि

4.2.12|4.2.12 dvaipavaiyaaghraadaNJ|dvaipavaiyaaghraadaNJ|dvaipavaiyaaghraadaNJ 4.2.12|द्वैपवैयाघ्रादञ्|द्वैपवैयाघ्रादञ् ४.२.१२|४.२.१२|४.२.१२ द्वैपवैयाघ्रादञ्
