The affixes यञ् and वुञ् come after the word केदार in the sense of 'collection thereof'.<br><br>Terms: यञ् and वुञ्

4.2.41|4.2.41 ThaNJ kavachinashcha|ThaNJ kavachinashcha|ThaNJ kavachinashcha 4.2.41|ठञ् कवचिनश्च|ठञ् कवचिनश्च ४.२.४१|४.२.४१|४.२.४१ ठञ् कवचिनश्च
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the word केदार and also after the word कवचिन ।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.2.42|4.2.42 braahmaNamaaNavavaaDavaadyan|braahmaNamaaNavavaaDavaadyan|braahmaNamaaNavavaaDavaadyan 4.2.42|ब्राह्मणमाणववाडवाद्यन्|ब्राह्मणमाणववाडवाद्यन् ४.२.४२|४.२.४२|४.२.४२ ब्राह्मणमाणववाडवाद्यन्
The affix यन् is added in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the words 1. ब्राह्मण 2. माणव and वाडव ।<br><br>Terms: यन्

4.2.43|4.2.43 graamajanabandhusahaayebhyaH tal|graamajanabandhusahaayebhyaH tal|graamajanabandhusahaayebhyaH tal 4.2.43|ग्रामजनबन्धुसहायेभ्यः तल्|ग्रामजनबन्धुसहायेभ्यः तल् ४.२.४३|४.२.४३|४.२.४३ ग्रामजनबन्धुसहायेभ्यः तल्
The affix तल् comes in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the words 1. ग्राम 2. जन 3. बन्धु and 4. सहाय।<br><br>Terms: तल्

4.2.44|4.2.44 anudaattaaderaNJ|anudaattaaderaNJ|anudaattaaderaNJ 4.2.44|अनुदात्तादेरञ्|अनुदात्तादेरञ् ४.२.४४|४.२.४४|४.२.४४ अनुदात्तादेरञ्
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the words having अनुदात्त on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.2.45|4.2.45 khaNDikaadibhyashcha|khaNDikaadibhyashcha|khaNDikaadibhyashcha 4.2.45|खण्डिकादिभ्यश्च|खण्डिकादिभ्यश्च ४.२.४५|४.२.४५|४.२.४५ खण्डिकादिभ्यश्च
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the words खण्डिक etc.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.2.46|4.2.46 charaNebhyo dharmavat‌|charaNebhyo dharmavat‌|charaNebhyo dharmavat‌ 4.2.46|चरणेभ्यो धर्मवत्‌|चरणेभ्यो धर्मवत्‌ ४.२.४६|४.२.४६|४.२.४६ चरणेभ्यो धर्मवत्‌
After the name of a Vedic School, the affixes which denote the rule of that school, also come in the sense of 'collection thereof'.<br><br>Terms: तस्य समूहः

4.2.47|4.2.47 achittahastidhenoShThak|achittahastidhenoShThak|achittahastidhenoShThak 4.2.47|अचित्तहस्तिधेनोष्ठक्|अचित्तहस्तिधेनोष्ठक् ४.२.४७|४.२.४७|४.२.४७ अचित्तहस्तिधेनोष्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the names of things without consciousness and after 1. हस्ति and 2. धेनु।<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.2.48|4.2.48 keshaashvaabhyaaM yanChaavanyatarasyaam|keshaashvaabhyaaM yanChaavanyatarasyaam|keshaashvaabhyaaM yanChaavanyatarasyaam 4.2.48|केशाश्वाभ्यां यञ्छावन्यतरस्याम्|केशाश्वाभ्यां यञ्छावन्यतरस्याम् ४.२.४८|४.२.४८|४.२.४८ केशाश्वाभ्यां यञ्छावन्यतरस्याम्
The affixes यञ् and छ come optionally in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the words 1. केश and 2. अश्व , respectively.<br><br>Terms: यञ् and छ

4.2.49|4.2.49 paashaadibhyo yaH|paashaadibhyo yaH|paashaadibhyo yaH 4.2.49|पाशादिभ्यो यः|पाशादिभ्यो यः ४.२.४९|४.२.४९|४.२.४९ पाशादिभ्यो यः
The affix य comes in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the words पाश etc.<br><br>Terms: य

4.2.50|4.2.50 khalagorathaat‌|khalagorathaat‌|khalagorathaat‌ 4.2.50|खलगोरथात्‌|खलगोरथात्‌ ४.२.५०|४.२.५०|४.२.५० खलगोरथात्‌
The affix य comes in the sense of 'collection thereof' after the words 1. खल 2 गो and 3. रथ।<br><br>Terms: य

4.2.51|4.2.51 initrakaTyachashcha|initrakaTyachashcha|initrakaTyachashcha 4.2.51|इनित्रकट्यचश्च|इनित्रकट्यचश्च ४.२.५१|४.२.५१|४.२.५१ इनित्रकट्यचश्च
The affixes इनि , त्र and कट्यष्यच् come in the sense of 'collection thereof', respectively after the words 1. खल 2 गो and 3. रथ।<br><br>Terms: इनि , त्र and कट्यष्यच्

4.2.52|4.2.52 viShayo deshe|viShayo deshe|viShayo deshe 4.2.52|विषयो देशे|विषयो देशे ४.२.५२|४.२.५२|४.२.५२ विषयो देशे
The affix अण् -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३, comes after a word in the Genitive -6th-Case in construction in the sense of 'any body'sūtras sphere', if a country is indicated by such sphere.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.53|4.2.53 raajanyaadibhyo vuNJ|raajanyaadibhyo vuNJ|raajanyaadibhyo vuNJ 4.2.53|राजन्यादिभ्यो वुञ्|राजन्यादिभ्यो वुञ् ४.२.५३|४.२.५३|४.२.५३ राजन्यादिभ्यो वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes after the words राजन्य etc. in the same sense.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.54|4.2.54 bhaurikyaadyaiShukaaryaadibhyo vidhalbhaktalau|bhaurikyaadyaiShukaaryaadibhyo vidhalbhaktalau|bhaurikyaadyaiShukaaryaadibhyo vidhalbhaktalau 4.2.54|भौरिक्याद्यैषुकार्यादिभ्यो विधल्भक्तलौ|भौरिक्याद्यैषुकार्यादिभ्यो विधल्भक्तलौ ४.२.५४|४.२.५४|४.२.५४ भौरिक्याद्यैषुकार्यादिभ्यो विधल्भक्तलौ
The affixes विधल् and भक्तल् come respectively after the words बहौरिकि and ऐषुकारि etc. in the sense of 'sphere of country'.<br><br>Terms: विधल् and भक्तल्

4.2.55|4.2.55 so.asyaadiriti chChandasaH pragaatheShu|so.asyaadiriti chChandasaH pragaatheShu|so.asyaadiriti chChandasaH pragaatheShu 4.2.55|सोऽस्यादिरिति च्छन्दसः प्रगाथेषु|सोऽस्यादिरिति च्छन्दसः प्रगाथेषु ४.२.५५|४.२.५५|४.२.५५ सोऽस्यादिरिति च्छन्दसः प्रगाथेषु
The affix अण् is added to the names of Meters, indicates a प्रगाथ beginning therewith.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.56|4.2.56 saMgraame prayojanayoddhRbhyaH|saMgraame prayojanayoddhRbhyaH|saMgraame prayojanayoddhRbhyaH 4.2.56|संग्रामे प्रयोजनयोद्धृभ्यः|संग्रामे प्रयोजनयोद्धृभ्यः ४.२.५६|४.२.५६|४.२.५६ संग्रामे प्रयोजनयोद्धृभ्यः
The affix अण् -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ when it is added to a word which denotes either the object of a battle or the warrior of a battle fought for that object or by that warrior as a leader.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.57|4.2.57 tadasyaaM praharaNamiti kriiDaayaam NaH|tadasyaaM praharaNamiti kriiDaayaam NaH|tadasyaaM praharaNamiti kriiDaayaam NaH 4.2.57|तदस्यां प्रहरणमिति क्रीडायाम् णः|तदस्यां प्रहरणमिति क्रीडायाम् णः ४.२.५७|४.२.५७|४.२.५७ तदस्यां प्रहरणमिति क्रीडायाम् णः
The affix ण to the name of a weapon indicates a game played with that weapon.<br><br>Terms: ण

4.2.58|4.2.58 ghaNJaH saa.asyaaM kriyeti NJaH|ghaNJaH saa.asyaaM kriyeti NJaH|ghaNJaH saa.asyaaM kriyeti NJaH 4.2.58|घञः साऽस्यां क्रियेति ञः|घञः साऽस्यां क्रियेति ञः ४.२.५८|४.२.५८|४.२.५८ घञः साऽस्यां क्रियेति ञः
The affix ञ added to a noun of action ending in the affix घञ् denotes an action occurring in that.<br><br>Terms: ञ

4.2.59|4.2.59 tadadhiite tadveda|tadadhiite tadveda|tadadhiite tadveda 4.2.59|तदधीते तद्वेद|तदधीते तद्वेद ४.२.५९|४.२.५९|४.२.५९ तदधीते तद्वेद
The affix अण् -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ comes after a word denoting 'some subject of study' in the sense of 'who has studied that or who understands that'.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.60|4.2.60 kratuukthaadisuutraantaaTThak|kratuukthaadisuutraantaaTThak|kratuukthaadisuutraantaaTThak 4.2.60|क्रतूक्थादिसूत्रान्ताट्ठक्|क्रतूक्थादिसूत्रान्ताट्ठक् ४.२.६०|४.२.६०|४.२.६० क्रतूक्थादिसूत्रान्ताट्ठक्
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'one who studies or one who understands' after the name of a sacrifice after उक्थ etc. and after a stem ending with the word सूत्र।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.2.61|4.2.61 kramaadibhyo vun|kramaadibhyo vun|kramaadibhyo vun 4.2.61|क्रमादिभ्यो वुन्|क्रमादिभ्यो वुन् ४.२.६१|४.२.६१|४.२.६१ क्रमादिभ्यो वुन्
The affix वुन् comes in the sense of 'who studies or who knows' after the words क्रम etc.<br><br>Terms: वुन्

4.2.62|4.2.62 anubraahmaNaadiniH|anubraahmaNaadiniH|anubraahmaNaadiniH 4.2.62|अनुब्राह्मणादिनिः|अनुब्राह्मणादिनिः ४.२.६२|४.२.६२|४.२.६२ अनुब्राह्मणादिनिः
The affix इनि comes in the sense of 'who studies or who knows' after the word अनुब्राह्मण।<br><br>Terms: इनि

4.2.63|4.2.63 vasantaadibhyaShThak|vasantaadibhyaShThak|vasantaadibhyaShThak 4.2.63|वसन्तादिभ्यष्ठक्|वसन्तादिभ्यष्ठक् ४.२.६३|४.२.६३|४.२.६३ वसन्तादिभ्यष्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes in the sense of 'who studies or who knows' after the words वसन्त etc.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.2.64|4.2.64 proktaalluk|proktaalluk|proktaalluk 4.2.64|प्रोक्ताल्लुक्|प्रोक्ताल्लुक् ४.२.६४|४.२.६४|४.२.६४ प्रोक्ताल्लुक्
After the title of a work which is named after the Announcer thereof the affixes denoting 'who studies or who knows that' are elided by लुक् ।<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.2.65|4.2.65 suutraachcha kopadhaat‌|suutraachcha kopadhaat‌|suutraachcha kopadhaat‌ 4.2.65|सूत्राच्च कोपधात्‌|सूत्राच्च कोपधात्‌ ४.२.६५|४.२.६५|४.२.६५ सूत्राच्च कोपधात्‌
The affix denoting denoting 'who studies or who knows that' is elided by लुक् after the title of a sūtra work having क् as penultimate.<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.2.66|4.2.66 ChandobraahmaNaani cha tadviShayaaNi|ChandobraahmaNaani cha tadviShayaaNi|ChandobraahmaNaani cha tadviShayaaNi 4.2.66|छन्दोब्राह्मणानि च तद्विषयाणि|छन्दोब्राह्मणानि च तद्विषयाणि ४.२.६६|४.२.६६|४.२.६६ छन्दोब्राह्मणानि च तद्विषयाणि
The affixes denoting the Announcer when added to छन्दस् (Vedas) and the ब्राह्मण-sūtras express this relation only.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्

4.2.67|4.2.67 tadasminnastiiti deshe tannaamni|tadasminnastiiti deshe tannaamni|tadasminnastiiti deshe tannaamni 4.2.67|तदस्मिन्नस्तीति देशे तन्नाम्नि|तदस्मिन्नस्तीति देशे तन्नाम्नि ४.२.६७|४.२.६७|४.२.६७ तदस्मिन्नस्तीति देशे तन्नाम्नि
(An affix is placed after a word expressive of anything) in the sense of '- that thing is in this' - the place takeing a name therefrom.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.68|4.2.68 tena nirvRttam|tena nirvRttam|tena nirvRttam 4.2.68|तेन निर्वृत्तम्|तेन निर्वृत्तम् ४.२.६८|४.२.६८|४.२.६८ तेन निर्वृत्तम्
After a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction an affix is added in the sense of 'completed by him' when the whole word so formed is the name of a country.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.69|4.2.69 tasya nivaasaH|tasya nivaasaH|tasya nivaasaH 4.2.69|तस्य निवासः|तस्य निवासः ४.२.६९|४.२.६९|४.२.६९ तस्य निवासः
After a word in the Genitive -6th-Case in construction an affix is added in the sense of 'his dwelling-place' the whole word expressing the name of a country.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.70|4.2.70 aduurabhavashcha|aduurabhavashcha|aduurabhavashcha 4.2.70|अदूरभवश्च|अदूरभवश्च ४.२.७०|४.२.७०|४.२.७० अदूरभवश्च
And lastly a place is named after whatever is found near it.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.71|4.2.71 oraNJ|oraNJ|oraNJ 4.2.71|ओरञ्|ओरञ् ४.२.७१|४.२.७१|४.२.७१ ओरञ्
The affix अञ् comes after a stem ending in a उ or ऊ (in the four-fold senses given above).<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.72|4.2.72 matoshcha bahvajangaat‌|matoshcha bahvajangaat‌|matoshcha bahvajangaat‌ 4.2.72|मतोश्च बह्वजङ्गात्‌|मतोश्च बह्वजङ्गात्‌ ४.२.७२|४.२.७२|४.२.७२ मतोश्च बह्वजङ्गात्‌
The affix अञ् comes in the quadruple sense after a word which ends in the affix मतुप् and whose stem is polysyllabic.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.73|4.2.73 bahvachaH kuupeShu|bahvachaH kuupeShu|bahvachaH kuupeShu 4.2.73|बह्वचः कूपेषु|बह्वचः कूपेषु ४.२.७३|४.२.७३|४.२.७३ बह्वचः कूपेषु
The affix अञ् comes in the quadruple sense after a polysyllabic प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) when 'a well' is to be designated.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.74|4.2.74 udak cha vipaashaH|udak cha vipaashaH|udak cha vipaashaH 4.2.74|उदक् च विपाशः|उदक् च विपाशः ४.२.७४|४.२.७४|४.२.७४ उदक् च विपाशः
The affix अञ् comes in the quadruple sense after any polysyllabic प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) in denoting 'a well' situated on the Northern bank of the river विपाश।<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.75|4.2.75 saMkalaadibhyashcha|saMkalaadibhyashcha|saMkalaadibhyashcha 4.2.75|संकलादिभ्यश्च|संकलादिभ्यश्च ४.२.७५|४.२.७५|४.२.७५ संकलादिभ्यश्च
The affix अण् comes after the words संकल etc. in the above 4-fold sense.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.76|4.2.76 striiShu sauviirasaalvapraaxu|striiShu sauviirasaalvapraaxu|striiShu sauviirasaalvapraaxu 4.2.76|स्त्रीषु सौवीरसाल्वप्राक्षु|स्त्रीषु सौवीरसाल्वप्राक्षु ४.२.७६|४.२.७६|४.२.७६ स्त्रीषु सौवीरसाल्वप्राक्षु
So also when the palce is situated in the lands of the सौवीर or साल्व or of the Eatern People and the word in these cases is always feminine.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.77|4.2.77 suvaastvaadibhyo.aN|suvaastvaadibhyo.aN|suvaastvaadibhyo.aN 4.2.77|सुवास्त्वादिभ्योऽण्|सुवास्त्वादिभ्योऽण् ४.२.७७|४.२.७७|४.२.७७ सुवास्त्वादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अञ् comes after the words सुवास्तु etc. in the 4-fold sense.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.78|4.2.78 roNii|roNii|roNii 4.2.78|रोणी|रोणी ४.२.७८|४.२.७८|४.२.७८ रोणी
The affix अण् comes after राणो in the 4-fold sense.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.79|4.2.79 kopadhaachcha|kopadhaachcha|kopadhaachcha 4.2.79|कोपधाच्च|कोपधाच्च ४.२.७९|४.२.७९|४.२.७९ कोपधाच्च
The affix अण् comes in the 4-fold sense after a stem having क् for its penultimate.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.80|4.2.80 vunChaNkaThajilasheniraDhaNJNyayaphakphiNJiNJNJyakakThako.ariihaNakRshaashvarshyakumudakaashatRNaprexaa.ashmasakhisaMkaashabalapaxakarNasutaMgamapragadinvaraahakumudaadibhyaH|vunChaNkaThajilasheniraDhaNJNyayaphakphiNJiNJNJyakakThako.ariihaNakRshaashvarshyakumudakaashatRNaprexaa.ashmasakhisaMkaashabalapaxakarNasutaMgamapragadinvaraahakumudaadibhyaH|vunChaNkaThajilasheniraDhaNJNyayaphakphiNJiNJNJyakakThako.ariihaNakRshaashvarshyakumudakaashatRNaprexaa.ashmasakhisaMkaashabalapaxakarNasutaMgamapragadinvaraahakumudaadibhyaH 4.2.80|वुञ्छण्कठजिलशेनिरढञ्ण्ययफक्फिञिञ्ञ्यकक्ठकोऽरीहणकृशाश्वर्श्यकुमुदकाशतृणप्रेक्षाऽश्मसखिसंकाशबलपक्षकर्णसुतंगमप्रगदिन्वराहकुमुदादिभ्यः|वुञ्छण्कठजिलशेनिरढञ्ण्ययफक्फिञिञ्ञ्यकक्ठकोऽरीहणकृशाश्वर्श्यकुमुदकाशतृणप्रेक्षाऽश्मसखिसंकाशबलपक्षकर्णसुतंगमप्रगदिन्वराहकुमुदादिभ्यः ४.२.८०|४.२.८०|४.२.८० वुञ्छण्कठजिलशेनिरढञ्ण्ययफक्फिञिञ्ञ्यकक्ठकोऽरीहणकृशाश्वर्श्यकुमुदकाशतृणप्रेक्षाऽश्मसखिसंकाशबलपक्षकर्णसुतंगमप्रगदिन्वराहकुमुदादिभ्यः
In the above 4-senses are added the following 17-affixes after the following 17 classes of words respectively - ……………………………………………….<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.81|4.2.81 janapade lup‌|janapade lup‌|janapade lup‌ 4.2.81|जनपदे लुप्‌|जनपदे लुप्‌ ४.२.८१|४.२.८१|४.२.८१ जनपदे लुप्‌
The name of a kingdom is formed by the लुप् elision of these affixes (when the name of the people without the change of number and gender, is at the same time the name of the kingdom).<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.82|4.2.82 varaNaadibhyashcha|varaNaadibhyashcha|varaNaadibhyashcha 4.2.82|वरणादिभ्यश्च|वरणादिभ्यश्च ४.२.८२|४.२.८२|४.२.८२ वरणादिभ्यश्च
Also after the owrd वरण etc. the affix denoting locality becomes elided but the number and gender ar not changed.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.83|4.2.83 sharkaraayaa vaa|sharkaraayaa vaa|sharkaraayaa vaa 4.2.83|शर्कराया वा|शर्कराया वा ४.२.८३|४.२.८३|४.२.८३ शर्कराया वा
Optionally after the word शर्करा the 4-fold significant affix is elided by लुप् ।<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.84|4.2.84 ThakChau cha|ThakChau cha|ThakChau cha 4.2.84|ठक्छौ च|ठक्छौ च ४.२.८४|४.२.८४|४.२.८४ ठक्छौ च
The affixes ठक् and छ come after the word शर्करा in the 4-fold sense.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-अञ्

4.2.85|4.2.85 nadyaaM matup‌|nadyaaM matup‌|nadyaaM matup‌ 4.2.85|नद्यां मतुप्‌|नद्यां मतुप्‌ ४.२.८५|४.२.८५|४.२.८५ नद्यां मतुप्‌
The affix मतुप्‌ is added denoting a river.<br><br>Terms: मतुप्‌

4.2.86|4.2.86 madhvaadibhyashcha|madhvaadibhyashcha|madhvaadibhyashcha 4.2.86|मध्वादिभ्यश्च|मध्वादिभ्यश्च ४.२.८६|४.२.८६|४.२.८६ मध्वादिभ्यश्च
The affix मतुप्‌ is added to the words मधु etc. in the four senses given above.<br><br>Terms: मतुप्‌

4.2.87|4.2.87 kumudanaDavetasebhyo Dmatup‌|kumudanaDavetasebhyo Dmatup‌|kumudanaDavetasebhyo Dmatup‌ 4.2.87|कुमुदनडवेतसेभ्यो ड्मतुप्‌|कुमुदनडवेतसेभ्यो ड्मतुप्‌ ४.२.८७|४.२.८७|४.२.८७ कुमुदनडवेतसेभ्यो ड्मतुप्‌
The affix ड्मतुप्‌ comes after the words 1. कुमुद 2. नड and 3. वेतस in the above four senses and the final of these words is elided before this affix.<br><br>Terms: ड्मतुप्‌

4.2.88|4.2.88 naDashaadaaDDvalach|naDashaadaaDDvalach|naDashaadaaDDvalach 4.2.88|नडशादाड्ड्वलच्|नडशादाड्ड्वलच् ४.२.८८|४.२.८८|४.२.८८ नडशादाड्ड्वलच्
The affix ड्वलच् comes after 1. नड and 2. शाद in the four senses given above, the final of the words being elided.<br><br>Terms: ड्वलच्

4.2.89|4.2.89 shikhaayaa valach|shikhaayaa valach|shikhaayaa valach 4.2.89|शिखाया वलच्|शिखाया वलच् ४.२.८९|४.२.८९|४.२.८९ शिखाया वलच्
The affix वलच् comes after the word शिखा in the above four senses.<br><br>Terms: वलच्

4.2.90|4.2.90 utkaraadibhyashChaH|utkaraadibhyashChaH|utkaraadibhyashChaH 4.2.90|उत्करादिभ्यश्छः|उत्करादिभ्यश्छः ४.२.९०|४.२.९०|४.२.९० उत्करादिभ्यश्छः
The affix छ comes after the words उत्कर etc. in the four senses.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.91|4.2.91 naDaadiinaaM kuk cha|naDaadiinaaM kuk cha|naDaadiinaaM kuk cha 4.2.91|नडादीनां कुक् च|नडादीनां कुक् च ४.२.९१|४.२.९१|४.२.९१ नडादीनां कुक् च
The augment कुक् comes aftere the words नड etc. when the affix छ follows in the above four senses.<br><br>Terms: चातुर्थिक-कुक्

4.2.92|4.2.92 sheShe|sheShe|sheShe 4.2.92|शेषे|शेषे ४.२.९२|४.२.९२|४.२.९२ शेषे
The affixes taught hereafter have senses other than those mentioned above.<br><br>Terms: शेष

4.2.93|4.2.93 raaShTraavaarapaaraadghakhau|raaShTraavaarapaaraadghakhau|raaShTraavaarapaaraadghakhau 4.2.93|राष्ट्रावारपाराद्घखौ|राष्ट्रावारपाराद्घखौ ४.२.९३|४.२.९३|४.२.९३ राष्ट्रावारपाराद्घखौ
The affixes घ and ख are respectively added after the words 1. राष्ट् and 2. अवारपार।<br><br>Terms: घ and ख

4.2.94|4.2.94 graamaadyakhaNJau|graamaadyakhaNJau|graamaadyakhaNJau 4.2.94|ग्रामाद्यखञौ|ग्रामाद्यखञौ ४.२.९४|४.२.९४|४.२.९४ ग्रामाद्यखञौ
The affixes व and खञ् (ईन) come after the word ग्राम।<br><br>Terms: व and खञ्

4.2.95|4.2.95 kattryaadibhyo DhakaNJ|kattryaadibhyo DhakaNJ|kattryaadibhyo DhakaNJ 4.2.95|कत्त्र्यादिभ्यो ढकञ्|कत्त्र्यादिभ्यो ढकञ् ४.२.९५|४.२.९५|४.२.९५ कत्त्र्यादिभ्यो ढकञ्
The affix ढकञ् (एयक) comes after the words कत्रि etc.<br><br>Terms: ढकञ्

4.2.96|4.2.96 kulakuxigriivaabhyaH shvaasyalaMkaareShu|kulakuxigriivaabhyaH shvaasyalaMkaareShu|kulakuxigriivaabhyaH shvaasyalaMkaareShu 4.2.96|कुलकुक्षिग्रीवाभ्यः श्वास्यलंकारेषु|कुलकुक्षिग्रीवाभ्यः श्वास्यलंकारेषु ४.२.९६|४.२.९६|४.२.९६ कुलकुक्षिग्रीवाभ्यः श्वास्यलंकारेषु
The affix ढकञ् is added to the words 1. कुल 2. कुक्षि and 3. ग्रीवा when the whole words so formed mean respectively 'a dog', 'a sword' and 'an ornament'.<br><br>Terms: ढकञ्

4.2.97|4.2.97 nadyaadibhyo Dhak|nadyaadibhyo Dhak|nadyaadibhyo Dhak 4.2.97|नद्यादिभ्यो ढक्|नद्यादिभ्यो ढक् ४.२.९७|४.२.९७|४.२.९७ नद्यादिभ्यो ढक्
The affix ढक् comes after the words नदी etc. in the remaining senses i.e. तत्र जातः ४.३.२५ etc.<br><br>Terms: ढक्

4.2.98|4.2.98 daxiNaapashchaatpurasastyak|daxiNaapashchaatpurasastyak|daxiNaapashchaatpurasastyak 4.2.98|दक्षिणापश्चात्पुरसस्त्यक्|दक्षिणापश्चात्पुरसस्त्यक् ४.२.९८|४.२.९८|४.२.९८ दक्षिणापश्चात्पुरसस्त्यक्
The words 1. दक्षिणा 2. पश्चात् and 3. पुरस् the affix त्यक् (त्य) is added in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: शेष

4.2.99|4.2.99 kaapishyaaH Shphak|kaapishyaaH Shphak|kaapishyaaH Shphak 4.2.99|कापिश्याः ष्फक्|कापिश्याः ष्फक् ४.२.९९|४.२.९९|४.२.९९ कापिश्याः ष्फक्
After the word कापिशी , the affix ष्फक् is added in the remaining senses (the feminine being formed by ङीष् -- षिद्गौरादिभ्यश्च ४.१.४१).<br><br>Terms: ष्फक्

4.2.100|4.2.100 raMkoramanuShye.aN cha|raMkoramanuShye.aN cha|raMkoramanuShye.aN cha 4.2.100|रंकोरमनुष्येऽण् च|रंकोरमनुष्येऽण् च ४.२.१००|४.२.१००|४.२.१०० रंकोरमनुष्येऽण् च
After the word रंकु the affixes ष्फक् and अण् are added in the remaining senses when the meaning is a non-human being.<br><br>Terms: ष्फक्

4.2.101|4.2.101 dyupraagapaagudakpratiicho yat‌|dyupraagapaagudakpratiicho yat‌|dyupraagapaagudakpratiicho yat‌ 4.2.101|द्युप्रागपागुदक्प्रतीचो यत्‌|द्युप्रागपागुदक्प्रतीचो यत्‌ ४.२.१०१|४.२.१०१|४.२.१०१ द्युप्रागपागुदक्प्रतीचो यत्‌
After the words 1. दिव् 2. प्राच् 3. अपाच् 4. उदच् and 5. प्रत्यच् , the affix यत् is added in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.2.102|4.2.102 kanthaayaaShThak|kanthaayaaShThak|kanthaayaaShThak 4.2.102|कन्थायाष्ठक्|कन्थायाष्ठक् ४.२.१०२|४.२.१०२|४.२.१०२ कन्थायाष्ठक्
After the word कन्था the affix is ठक् is added in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.2.103|4.2.103 varNau vuk|varNau vuk|varNau vuk 4.2.103|वर्णौ वुक्|वर्णौ वुक् ४.२.१०३|४.२.१०३|४.२.१०३ वर्णौ वुक्
To the same stem is added the affix वुक् when it treats about something which is to be found in the land of वर्णु (name of a river and also the country near it).<br><br>Terms: वुक्

4.2.104|4.2.104 avyayaattyap‌|avyayaattyap‌|avyayaattyap‌ 4.2.104|अव्ययात्त्यप्‌|अव्ययात्त्यप्‌ ४.२.१०४|४.२.१०४|४.२.१०४ अव्ययात्त्यप्‌
The affix त्यप्‌ comes after an indeclinable in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: त्यप्‌

4.2.105|4.2.105 aiShamohyaHshvaso.anyatarasyaam|aiShamohyaHshvaso.anyatarasyaam|aiShamohyaHshvaso.anyatarasyaam 4.2.105|ऐषमोह्यःश्वसोऽन्यतरस्याम्|ऐषमोह्यःश्वसोऽन्यतरस्याम् ४.२.१०५|४.२.१०५|४.२.१०५ ऐषमोह्यःश्वसोऽन्यतरस्याम्
The affix त्यप्‌ is added optionally after the words 1. ऐषमस् 2. ह्यस् and 3. श्वस् , in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: त्यप्‌

4.2.106|4.2.106 tiiraruupyottarapadaadaNJNJau|tiiraruupyottarapadaadaNJNJau|tiiraruupyottarapadaadaNJNJau 4.2.106|तीररूप्योत्तरपदादञ्ञौ|तीररूप्योत्तरपदादञ्ञौ ४.२.१०६|४.२.१०६|४.२.१०६ तीररूप्योत्तरपदादञ्ञौ
The affix अञ् comes after a word ending with तीर and the ञ् comes after a word ending with कप्य , in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.2.107|4.2.107 dikpuurvapadaadasaMJNaayaaM NJaH|dikpuurvapadaadasaMJNaayaaM NJaH|dikpuurvapadaadasaMJNaayaaM NJaH 4.2.107|दिक्पूर्वपदादसंज्ञायां ञः|दिक्पूर्वपदादसंज्ञायां ञः ४.२.१०७|४.२.१०७|४.२.१०७ दिक्पूर्वपदादसंज्ञायां ञः
The affix ञ comes in the remaining senses after a word preceded by another that signifies 'direction' provided the compound is not a name.<br><br>Terms: ञ

4.2.108|4.2.108 madrebhyo.aNJ|madrebhyo.aNJ|madrebhyo.aNJ 4.2.108|मद्रेभ्योऽञ्|मद्रेभ्योऽञ् ४.२.१०८|४.२.१०८|४.२.१०८ मद्रेभ्योऽञ्
The affix अञ् is added to the word मद्र , preceded by a word denoting 'direction', in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.2.109|4.2.109 udiichyagraamaachcha bahvacho.antodaattaat‌|udiichyagraamaachcha bahvacho.antodaattaat‌|udiichyagraamaachcha bahvacho.antodaattaat‌ 4.2.109|उदीच्यग्रामाच्च बह्वचोऽन्तोदात्तात्‌|उदीच्यग्रामाच्च बह्वचोऽन्तोदात्तात्‌ ४.२.१०९|४.२.१०९|४.२.१०९ उदीच्यग्रामाच्च बह्वचोऽन्तोदात्तात्‌
The affix अञ् comes in the remaining senses after a word consisting of more than two syllables having उदात्त accent on the final, being the name of a village of the people of the North.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.2.110|4.2.110 prasthottarapadapaladyaadikopadhaadaN|prasthottarapadapaladyaadikopadhaadaN|prasthottarapadapaladyaadikopadhaadaN 4.2.110|प्रस्थोत्तरपदपलद्यादिकोपधादण्|प्रस्थोत्तरपदपलद्यादिकोपधादण् ४.२.११०|४.२.११०|४.२.११० प्रस्थोत्तरपदपलद्यादिकोपधादण्
The affix अण् comes in the remaining senses after a word ending with प्रस्थ after the words पलदी etc. and after a word having a penultimate क , whether these words express villages of North folk or not.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.111|4.2.111 kaNvaadibhyo gotre|kaNvaadibhyo gotre|kaNvaadibhyo gotre 4.2.111|कण्वादिभ्यो गोत्रे|कण्वादिभ्यो गोत्रे ४.२.१११|४.२.१११|४.२.१११ कण्वादिभ्यो गोत्रे
The affix अण् comes after the Patronymics formed from कण्व etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.112|4.2.112 iNJashcha|iNJashcha|iNJashcha 4.2.112|इञश्च|इञश्च ४.२.११२|४.२.११२|४.२.११२ इञश्च
After a family-name formed by इञ् the affix अण् is added in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.113|4.2.113 na dvyachaH praachyabharateShu|na dvyachaH praachyabharateShu|na dvyachaH praachyabharateShu 4.2.113|न द्व्यचः प्राच्यभरतेषु|न द्व्यचः प्राच्यभरतेषु ४.२.११३|४.२.११३|४.२.११३ न द्व्यचः प्राच्यभरतेषु
The affix अण् is however not added to a word which though ending in the Patronymic affix इञ् consists of two syllables when it is the family name of Eastern People or of भरत।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.114|4.2.114 vRddhaachChaH|vRddhaachChaH|vRddhaachChaH 4.2.114|वृद्धाच्छः|वृद्धाच्छः ४.२.११४|४.२.११४|४.२.११४ वृद्धाच्छः
After the word वृद्ध , the affix छ is added in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.115|4.2.115 bhavataShThakChasau|bhavataShThakChasau|bhavataShThakChasau 4.2.115|भवतष्ठक्छसौ|भवतष्ठक्छसौ ४.२.११५|४.२.११५|४.२.११५ भवतष्ठक्छसौ
The affixes ठक् and छस् come after वृद्ध word भवत् , in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: ठक् and छस्

4.2.116|4.2.116 kaashyaadibhyaShThaNJNJiThau|kaashyaadibhyaShThaNJNJiThau|kaashyaadibhyaShThaNJNJiThau 4.2.116|काश्यादिभ्यष्ठञ्ञिठौ|काश्यादिभ्यष्ठञ्ञिठौ ४.२.११६|४.२.११६|४.२.११६ काश्यादिभ्यष्ठञ्ञिठौ
The affixes ठञ् and ञिठ् come in the remaining senses after the words काशि etc.<br><br>Terms: ठञ् and ञिठ्

4.2.117|4.2.117 vaahiikagraamebhyashcha|vaahiikagraamebhyashcha|vaahiikagraamebhyashcha 4.2.117|वाहीकग्रामेभ्यश्च|वाहीकग्रामेभ्यश्च ४.२.११७|४.२.११७|४.२.११७ वाहीकग्रामेभ्यश्च
The affixes ठञ् and ञिठ् come in the remaining senses after the वृद्ध words denoting the villages of वाहीक।<br><br>Terms: ठञ् and ञिठ्

4.2.118|4.2.118 vibhaaShoshiinareShu|vibhaaShoshiinareShu|vibhaaShoshiinareShu 4.2.118|विभाषोशीनरेषु|विभाषोशीनरेषु ४.२.११८|४.२.११८|४.२.११८ विभाषोशीनरेषु
The affixes ठञ् and ञिठ् come optionally in the remaining senses after the वृद्ध words denoting वाहीक villages situated in उशीनर।<br><br>Terms: ठञ् and ञिठ्

4.2.119|4.2.119 ordeshe ThaNJ|ordeshe ThaNJ|ordeshe ThaNJ 4.2.119|ओर्देशे ठञ्|ओर्देशे ठञ् ४.२.११९|४.२.११९|४.२.११९ ओर्देशे ठञ्
The affixes ठञ् comes in the remaining senses after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) denoting a locality and ending in उ।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.2.120|4.2.120 vRddhaat‌ praachaam|vRddhaat‌ praachaam|vRddhaat‌ praachaam 4.2.120|वृद्धात्‌ प्राचाम्|वृद्धात्‌ प्राचाम् ४.२.१२०|४.२.१२०|४.२.१२० वृद्धात्‌ प्राचाम्
The affixes ठञ् comes in the remaining senses after a वृद्ध word ending in उ and denoting a locality of East-folks.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.2.121|4.2.121 dhanvayopadhaadvuNJ|dhanvayopadhaadvuNJ|dhanvayopadhaadvuNJ 4.2.121|धन्वयोपधाद्वुञ्|धन्वयोपधाद्वुञ् ४.२.१२१|४.२.१२१|४.२.१२१ धन्वयोपधाद्वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses after a वृद्ध word denoting a locality which has the letter य as its penultimate and after a वृद्ध place name denoting a waste or desert place.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.122|4.2.122 prasthapuravahaantaachcha|prasthapuravahaantaachcha|prasthapuravahaantaachcha 4.2.122|प्रस्थपुरवहान्ताच्च|प्रस्थपुरवहान्ताच्च ४.२.१२२|४.२.१२२|४.२.१२२ प्रस्थपुरवहान्ताच्च
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses after a वृद्ध word denoting a locality and ending with 1. प्रस्थ 2. पुर or वह।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.123|4.2.123 ropadhetoH praachaam|ropadhetoH praachaam|ropadhetoH praachaam 4.2.123|रोपधेतोः प्राचाम्|रोपधेतोः प्राचाम् ४.२.१२३|४.२.१२३|४.२.१२३ रोपधेतोः प्राचाम्
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses after a वृद्ध word denoting a locality of the East-folk, the word having penultimate र or ending in ई।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.124|4.2.124 janapadatadavadhyoshcha|janapadatadavadhyoshcha|janapadatadavadhyoshcha 4.2.124|जनपदतदवध्योश्च|जनपदतदवध्योश्च ४.२.१२४|४.२.१२४|४.२.१२४ जनपदतदवध्योश्च
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses after a वृद्ध word denoting an inhabited kingdom or a limit of such kingdom<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.125|4.2.125 avRddhaadapi bahuvachanaviShayaat‌|avRddhaadapi bahuvachanaviShayaat‌|avRddhaadapi bahuvachanaviShayaat‌ 4.2.125|अवृद्धादपि बहुवचनविषयात्‌|अवृद्धादपि बहुवचनविषयात्‌ ४.२.१२५|४.२.१२५|४.२.१२५ अवृद्धादपि बहुवचनविषयात्‌
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses, even after a word which is not a वृद्ध which is always plural, when it denotes an inhabited country or a limit of such country, as well as after such वृद्ध words.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.126|4.2.126 kachChaagnivaktragarttottarapadaat‌|kachChaagnivaktragarttottarapadaat‌|kachChaagnivaktragarttottarapadaat‌ 4.2.126|क्अच्छाग्निवक्त्रगर्त्तोत्तरपदात्‌|क्अच्छाग्निवक्त्रगर्त्तोत्तरपदात्‌ ४.२.१२६|४.२.१२६|४.२.१२६ क्अच्छाग्निवक्त्रगर्त्तोत्तरपदात्‌
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses after a word whether a वृद्ध or not, denoting a locality and having its second term the words 1. कच्छ 2. अग्नि 3. वक्त्र and 4. गर्त।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.127|4.2.127 dhuumaadibhyashcha|dhuumaadibhyashcha|dhuumaadibhyashcha 4.2.127|धूमादिभ्यश्च|धूमादिभ्यश्च ४.२.१२७|४.२.१२७|४.२.१२७ धूमादिभ्यश्च
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses after the words धूम etc. denoting country.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.128|4.2.128 nagaraat‌ kutsanapraaviiNyayoH|nagaraat‌ kutsanapraaviiNyayoH|nagaraat‌ kutsanapraaviiNyayoH 4.2.128|नगरात्‌ कुत्सनप्रावीण्ययोः|नगरात्‌ कुत्सनप्रावीण्ययोः ४.२.१२८|४.२.१२८|४.२.१२८ नगरात्‌ कुत्सनप्रावीण्ययोः
The affix वुञ् comes after the word नगर in the remaining senses, when censure or praise is implied.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.129|4.2.129 araNyaanmanuShye|araNyaanmanuShye|araNyaanmanuShye 4.2.129|अरण्यान्मनुष्ये|अरण्यान्मनुष्ये ४.२.१२९|४.२.१२९|४.२.१२९ अरण्यान्मनुष्ये
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses after the word अरण्य , in the sense of 'a man'.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.130|4.2.130 vibhaaShaa kuruyugandharaabhyaam|vibhaaShaa kuruyugandharaabhyaam|vibhaaShaa kuruyugandharaabhyaam 4.2.130|विभाषा कुरुयुगन्धराभ्याम्|विभाषा कुरुयुगन्धराभ्याम् ४.२.१३०|४.२.१३०|४.२.१३० विभाषा कुरुयुगन्धराभ्याम्
The affix वुञ् comes optionally in the remaining senses after the words 1. कुरु and 2. युगन्धर।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.131|4.2.131 madravRjyoH kan|madravRjyoH kan|madravRjyoH kan 4.2.131|मद्रवृज्योः कन्|मद्रवृज्योः कन् ४.२.१३१|४.२.१३१|४.२.१३१ मद्रवृज्योः कन्
The affix कन् comes in the remaining senses after the words 1. मद्र and 2. वृजि।<br><br>Terms: कन्

4.2.132|4.2.132 kopadhaadaN|kopadhaadaN|kopadhaadaN 4.2.132|कोपधादण्|कोपधादण् ४.२.१३२|४.२.१३२|४.२.१३२ कोपधादण्
The affix अण् comes in the remaining senses after a word denoting a place and having the letter क as its penultimate.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.133|4.2.133 kachChaadibhyashcha|kachChaadibhyashcha|kachChaadibhyashcha 4.2.133|कच्छादिभ्यश्च|कच्छादिभ्यश्च ४.२.१३३|४.२.१३३|४.२.१३३ कच्छादिभ्यश्च
The affix अण् comes in the remaining senses after the words कच्छ etc. denoting places.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.2.134|4.2.134 manuShyatatsthayorvuNJ|manuShyatatsthayorvuNJ|manuShyatatsthayorvuNJ 4.2.134|मनुष्यतत्स्थयोर्वुञ्|मनुष्यतत्स्थयोर्वुञ् ४.२.१३४|४.२.१३४|४.२.१३४ मनुष्यतत्स्थयोर्वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes after the words कच्छ etc. in the senses of born etc. when the meaning is 'a man' or 'what exists in a man'.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.135|4.2.135 apadaatau saalvaat‌|apadaatau saalvaat‌|apadaatau saalvaat‌ 4.2.135|अपदातौ साल्वात्‌|अपदातौ साल्वात्‌ ४.२.१३५|४.२.१३५|४.२.१३५ अपदातौ साल्वात्‌
The affix वुञ् comes after the word साल्व in the senses of being born etc. when denoting 'a man 'or 'what exists in a man', provided that it does not mean a foot-soldier.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.136|4.2.136 goyavaagvoshcha|goyavaagvoshcha|goyavaagvoshcha 4.2.136|गोयवाग्वोश्च|गोयवाग्वोश्च ४.२.१३६|४.२.१३६|४.२.१३६ गोयवाग्वोश्च
The affix वुञ् comes in the remaining senses of being born etc. after the words साल्व etc. when the word signifies 'a cow' or 'a barley gruel'.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.2.137|4.2.137 gartottarapadaachChaH|gartottarapadaachChaH|gartottarapadaachChaH 4.2.137|गर्तोत्तरपदाच्छः|गर्तोत्तरपदाच्छः ४.२.१३७|४.२.१३७|४.२.१३७ गर्तोत्तरपदाच्छः
The affix छ comes in the remaining senses after a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) denoting a place and having the word गर्त as its second term.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.138|4.2.138 gahaadibhyashcha|gahaadibhyashcha|gahaadibhyashcha 4.2.138|गहादिभ्यश्च|गहादिभ्यश्च ४.२.१३८|४.२.१३८|४.२.१३८ गहादिभ्यश्च
The affix छ comes in the remaining senses after the words गह etc.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.139|4.2.139 praachaaM kaTaadeH|praachaaM kaTaadeH|praachaaM kaTaadeH 4.2.139|प्राचां कटादेः|प्राचां कटादेः ४.२.१३९|४.२.१३९|४.२.१३९ प्राचां कटादेः
The affix छ comes in the remaining senses after the words beginning with कद denoting the places of the East-folk.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.140|4.2.140 raaJNaH ka cha|raaJNaH ka cha|raaJNaH ka cha 4.2.140|राज्ञः क च|राज्ञः क च ४.२.१४०|४.२.१४०|४.२.१४० राज्ञः क च
The letter क is the substitute of the final of the word राजन् , when छ is added.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.141|4.2.141 vRddhaadakekaantakhopadhaat‌|vRddhaadakekaantakhopadhaat‌|vRddhaadakekaantakhopadhaat‌ 4.2.141|वृद्धादकेकान्तखोपधात्‌|वृद्धादकेकान्तखोपधात्‌ ४.२.१४१|४.२.१४१|४.२.१४१ वृद्धादकेकान्तखोपधात्‌
The affix छ comes in the remaining senses after a वृद्ध word denoting a place and ending with अक् or इक् or having ख as its penultimate.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.142|4.2.142 kanthaapaladanagaragraamahradottarapadaat‌|kanthaapaladanagaragraamahradottarapadaat‌|kanthaapaladanagaragraamahradottarapadaat‌ 4.2.142|कन्थापलदनगरग्रामह्रदोत्तरपदात्‌|कन्थापलदनगरग्रामह्रदोत्तरपदात्‌ ४.२.१४२|४.२.१४२|४.२.१४२ कन्थापलदनगरग्रामह्रदोत्तरपदात्‌
The affix छ comes in the remaining senses after a वृद्ध words, having the words 1. कन्था 2. पलद 3. नगर 4. ग्राम and 5. हृद , as second terms.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.143|4.2.143 parvataachcha|parvataachcha|parvataachcha 4.2.143|पर्वताच्च|पर्वताच्च ४.२.१४३|४.२.१४३|४.२.१४३ पर्वताच्च
The affix छ comes after the word पर्वत in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.144|4.2.144 vibhaaShaa.amanuShye|vibhaaShaa.amanuShye|vibhaaShaa.amanuShye 4.2.144|विभाषाऽमनुष्ये|विभाषाऽमनुष्ये ४.२.१४४|४.२.१४४|४.२.१४४ विभाषाऽमनुष्ये
The affix छ optionally comes in the remaining senses after the word पर्वत when it does not denote 'a man'.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.2.145|4.2.145 kRkaNaparNaadbhaaradvaaje|kRkaNaparNaadbhaaradvaaje|kRkaNaparNaadbhaaradvaaje 4.2.145|कृकणपर्णाद्भारद्वाजे|कृकणपर्णाद्भारद्वाजे ४.२.१४५|४.२.१४५|४.२.१४५ कृकणपर्णाद्भारद्वाजे
The affix छ comes in the remaining senses after कृकण and पर्ण when denoting the country भारद्वाच।<br><br>Terms: छ

4.3.1|4.3.1 yuShmadasmadoranyatarasyaaM khaNJ cha|yuShmadasmadoranyatarasyaaM khaNJ cha|yuShmadasmadoranyatarasyaaM khaNJ cha 4.3.1|युष्मदस्मदोरन्यतरस्यां खञ् च|युष्मदस्मदोरन्यतरस्यां खञ् च ४.३.१|४.३.१|४.३.१ युष्मदस्मदोरन्यतरस्यां खञ् च
The affix खञ् also comes optionally in the remaining senses after the words 1. युष्मद् and 2. अस्मद्।<br><br>Terms: खञ्

4.3.2|4.3.2 tasmin naNi cha yuShmaakaasmaakau|tasmin naNi cha yuShmaakaasmaakau|tasmin naNi cha yuShmaakaasmaakau 4.3.2|तस्मिन् नणि च युष्माकास्माकौ|तस्मिन् नणि च युष्माकास्माकौ ४.३.२|४.३.२|४.३.२ तस्मिन् नणि च युष्माकास्माकौ
When the affix खञ् is added and when अण् is added then 1. युष्माक and 2. अस्माक are the substitutes of युष्मद् and अस्मद्।<br><br>Terms: खञ्

4.3.3|4.3.3 tavakamamakaavekavachane|tavakamamakaavekavachane|tavakamamakaavekavachane 4.3.3|तवकममकावेकवचने|तवकममकावेकवचने ४.३.३|४.३.३|४.३.३ तवकममकावेकवचने
In expressing one individual, तबक and ममक are the substitutes of युष्मद् and अस्मद् respectively when खञ् and अण् follow.<br><br>Terms: खञ् and अण्

4.3.4|4.3.4 ardhaadyat‌|ardhaadyat‌|ardhaadyat‌ 4.3.4|अर्धाद्यत्‌|अर्धाद्यत्‌ ४.३.४|४.३.४|४.३.४ अर्धाद्यत्‌
The affix यत् comes after the word अर्द्ध in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.3.5|4.3.5 paraavaraadhamottamapuurvaachcha|paraavaraadhamottamapuurvaachcha|paraavaraadhamottamapuurvaachcha 4.3.5|परावराधमोत्तमपूर्वाच्च|परावराधमोत्तमपूर्वाच्च ४.३.५|४.३.५|४.३.५ परावराधमोत्तमपूर्वाच्च
The affix यत् comes in the remaining senses after the word अर्द्ध when preceded by 1. पर 2. अवर 3. अधम and 4. उत्तम।<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.3.6|4.3.6 dikpuurvapadaaTThaNJ cha|dikpuurvapadaaTThaNJ cha|dikpuurvapadaaTThaNJ cha 4.3.6|दिक्पूर्वपदाट्ठञ् च|दिक्पूर्वपदाट्ठञ् च ४.३.६|४.३.६|४.३.६ दिक्पूर्वपदाट्ठञ् च
And the affix ठञ् also (as well as यत्) comes in the remaining senses after the word अर्द्ध when the prior term denotes a direction.<br><br>Terms: ठञ् and यत्

4.3.7|4.3.7 graamajanapadaikadeshaadaNJThaNJau|graamajanapadaikadeshaadaNJThaNJau|graamajanapadaikadeshaadaNJThaNJau 4.3.7|ग्रामजनपदैकदेशादञ्ठञौ|ग्रामजनपदैकदेशादञ्ठञौ ४.३.७|४.३.७|४.३.७ ग्रामजनपदैकदेशादञ्ठञौ
The affixes अञ् and ठञ् come in the remaining senses after the word अर्द्ध preceded by a word denoting direction when a particular portion of a village or an inhabited country.<br><br>Terms: अञ् and ठञ्

4.3.8|4.3.8 madhyaanmaH|madhyaanmaH|madhyaanmaH 4.3.8|मध्यान्मः|मध्यान्मः ४.३.८|४.३.८|४.३.८ मध्यान्मः
After the word मध्य there is the affix म in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: म

4.3.9|4.3.9 a saampratike|a saampratike|a saampratike 4.3.9|अ साम्प्रतिके|अ साम्प्रतिके ४.३.९|४.३.९|४.३.९ अ साम्प्रतिके
The affix अ comes in the remaining senses after the word मध्य , the meaning being 'fit' or 'proper'.<br><br>Terms: अ

4.3.10|4.3.10 dviipaadanusamudraM yaNJ|dviipaadanusamudraM yaNJ|dviipaadanusamudraM yaNJ 4.3.10|द्वीपादनुसमुद्रं यञ्|द्वीपादनुसमुद्रं यञ् ४.३.१०|४.३.१०|४.३.१० द्वीपादनुसमुद्रं यञ्
The affix यञ् comes in the remaining senses after the word द्वीप , which is near the sea.<br><br>Terms: यञ्

4.3.11|4.3.11 kaalaaTThaNJ|kaalaaTThaNJ|kaalaaTThaNJ 4.3.11|कालाट्ठञ्|कालाट्ठञ् ४.३.११|४.३.११|४.३.११ कालाट्ठञ्
The affix ठञ् comes in the remaining senses after the words denoting time.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.12|4.3.12 shraaddhe sharadaH|shraaddhe sharadaH|shraaddhe sharadaH 4.3.12|श्राद्धे शरदः|श्राद्धे शरदः ४.३.१२|४.३.१२|४.३.१२ श्राद्धे शरदः
The affix ठञ् comes in the remaining senses after the word शरद् when expressing श्राद्ध।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.13|4.3.13 vibhaaShaa rogaatapayoH|vibhaaShaa rogaatapayoH|vibhaaShaa rogaatapayoH 4.3.13|विभाषा रोगातपयोः|विभाषा रोगातपयोः ४.३.१३|४.३.१३|४.३.१३ विभाषा रोगातपयोः
The affix ठञ् comes optionally comes in the remaining senses after the word शरद् when expressing illness or heat.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.14|4.3.14 nishaapradoShaabhyaaM cha|nishaapradoShaabhyaaM cha|nishaapradoShaabhyaaM cha 4.3.14|निशाप्रदोषाभ्यां च|निशाप्रदोषाभ्यां च ४.३.१४|४.३.१४|४.३.१४ निशाप्रदोषाभ्यां च
The affix ठञ् comes optionally comes in the remaining senses after the words 1. निशा and 2. प्रदोष ।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.15|4.3.15 shvasastuT cha|shvasastuT cha|shvasastuT cha 4.3.15|श्वसस्तुट् च|श्वसस्तुट् च ४.३.१५|४.३.१५|४.३.१५ श्वसस्तुट् च
The affix ठञ् comes optionally comes in the remaining senses after the word श्वस् and it takes the augment तुट्।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.16|4.3.16 saMdhivelaa.a.adyRtunaxatrebhyo.aN|saMdhivelaa.a.adyRtunaxatrebhyo.aN|saMdhivelaa.a.adyRtunaxatrebhyo.aN 4.3.16|संधिवेलाऽऽद्यृतुनक्षत्रेभ्योऽण्|संधिवेलाऽऽद्यृतुनक्षत्रेभ्योऽण् ४.३.१६|४.३.१६|४.३.१६ संधिवेलाऽऽद्यृतुनक्षत्रेभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the remaining senses after the words संधिवेला etc. and the words expressing 'season' and 'asterism'.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.17|4.3.17 praavRSha eNyaH|praavRSha eNyaH|praavRSha eNyaH 4.3.17|प्रावृष एण्यः|प्रावृष एण्यः ४.३.१७|४.३.१७|४.३.१७ प्रावृष एण्यः
The affix एण्य comes in the remaining senses after the word प्रावृष।<br><br>Terms: एण्य

4.3.18|4.3.18 varShaabhyaShThak|varShaabhyaShThak|varShaabhyaShThak 4.3.18|वर्षाभ्यष्ठक्|वर्षाभ्यष्ठक् ४.३.१८|४.३.१८|४.३.१८ वर्षाभ्यष्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes in the remaining senses after the word वर्षा।<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.3.19|4.3.19 Chandasi ThaNJ|Chandasi ThaNJ|Chandasi ThaNJ 4.3.19|छन्दसि ठञ्|छन्दसि ठञ् ४.३.१९|४.३.१९|४.३.१९ छन्दसि ठञ्
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the word वर्षा takes the affix ठञ् , in the remaining senses.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-ठञ्

4.3.20|4.3.20 vasantaachcha|vasantaachcha|vasantaachcha 4.3.20|वसन्ताच्च|वसन्ताच्च ४.३.२०|४.३.२०|४.३.२० वसन्ताच्च
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the affix ठञ् comes in the remaining senses after the word वसन्त।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-ठञ्

4.3.21|4.3.21 hemantaachcha|hemantaachcha|hemantaachcha 4.3.21|हेमन्ताच्च|हेमन्ताच्च ४.३.२१|४.३.२१|४.३.२१ हेमन्ताच्च
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the affix ठञ् comes in the remaining senses after the word हेमन्त।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-ठञ्

4.3.22|4.3.22 sarvatraaN cha talopashcha|sarvatraaN cha talopashcha|sarvatraaN cha talopashcha 4.3.22|सर्वत्राण् च तलोपश्च|सर्वत्राण् च तलोपश्च ४.३.२२|४.३.२२|४.३.२२ सर्वत्राण् च तलोपश्च
The affix अण् comes always after the word हेमन्त and (before this affix) the letter त of हेमन्त is elided.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-अण्

4.3.23|4.3.23 saayaMchirampraahNeprage.avyayebhyaShTyuTyulau tuT cha|saayaMchirampraahNeprage.avyayebhyaShTyuTyulau tuT cha|saayaMchirampraahNeprage.avyayebhyaShTyuTyulau tuT cha 4.3.23|सायंचिरम्प्राह्णेप्रगेऽव्ययेभ्यष्ट्युट्युलौ तुट् च|सायंचिरम्प्राह्णेप्रगेऽव्ययेभ्यष्ट्युट्युलौ तुट् च ४.३.२३|४.३.२३|४.३.२३ सायंचिरम्प्राह्णेप्रगेऽव्ययेभ्यष्ट्युट्युलौ तुट् च
After the words 1. सायं 'at eve' 2. चिरम् 'for a long time' 3. प्राह्णे 'in the forenoon' 4. प्रगे 'at dawn' and after indeclinables expressing time, there are the affixes ट्यु and ट्युल् and their augment is तुट्।<br><br>Terms: ट्यु and ट्युल्

4.3.24|4.3.24 vibhaaShaa puurvaahNaaparaahNaabhyaam|vibhaaShaa puurvaahNaaparaahNaabhyaam|vibhaaShaa puurvaahNaaparaahNaabhyaam 4.3.24|विभाषा पूर्वाह्णापराह्णाभ्याम्|विभाषा पूर्वाह्णापराह्णाभ्याम् ४.३.२४|४.३.२४|४.३.२४ विभाषा पूर्वाह्णापराह्णाभ्याम्
Optionally after the words 1. पूर्वाह्ण and 2. अपराह्ण there are the affixes ट्यु and ट्युल् and their augment is तुट्।<br><br>Terms: ट्यु and ट्युल्

4.3.25|4.3.25 tatra jaataH|tatra jaataH|tatra jaataH 4.3.25|तत्र जातः|तत्र जातः ४.३.२५|४.३.२५|४.३.२५ तत्र जातः
The affixes ordained above or hereafter come after a word in the Locative -7th case in construction in the sense of 'born or grown or originated there or then'.<br><br>Terms: ट्यु and ट्युल्

4.3.26|4.3.26 praavRShaShThap‌|praavRShaShThap‌|praavRShaShThap‌ 4.3.26|प्रावृषष्ठप्‌|प्रावृषष्ठप्‌ ४.३.२६|४.३.२६|४.३.२६ प्रावृषष्ठप्‌
After the word प्रावृट् being in the Locative -7th case-affix, there is the affix ठप् in the sense of 'produced therein'.<br><br>Terms: ठप्

4.3.27|4.3.27 saMJNaayaaM sharado vuNJ|saMJNaayaaM sharado vuNJ|saMJNaayaaM sharado vuNJ 4.3.27|संज्ञायां शरदो वुञ्|संज्ञायां शरदो वुञ् ४.३.२७|४.३.२७|४.३.२७ संज्ञायां शरदो वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes after the word शरद in the Locative -7th case-affix in the sense of 'born therein', the whole word being a name.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.28|4.3.28 puurvaahNaaparaahNaardraamuulapradoShaavaskaraadvun|puurvaahNaaparaahNaardraamuulapradoShaavaskaraadvun|puurvaahNaaparaahNaardraamuulapradoShaavaskaraadvun 4.3.28|पूर्वाह्णापराह्णार्द्रामूलप्रदोषावस्कराद्वुन्|पूर्वाह्णापराह्णार्द्रामूलप्रदोषावस्कराद्वुन् ४.३.२८|४.३.२८|४.३.२८ पूर्वाह्णापराह्णार्द्रामूलप्रदोषावस्कराद्वुन्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'born therein' after the words 1. पूर्वाह्ण 2. अपराह्ण 3. आर्द्रा 4. मूला 5. प्रदोष and 6. अवस्कर , the whole being a name.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.29|4.3.29 pathaH pantha cha|pathaH pantha cha|pathaH pantha cha 4.3.29|पथः पन्थ च|पथः पन्थ च ४.३.२९|४.३.२९|४.३.२९ पथः पन्थ च
The affix वुञ् comes after the word पथ , in the sense of 'produced therein' and thereby in the room of पथ , the substitute is पन्थ।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.30|4.3.30 amaavaasyaayaa vaa|amaavaasyaayaa vaa|amaavaasyaayaa vaa 4.3.30|अमावास्याया वा|अमावास्याया वा ४.३.३०|४.३.३०|४.३.३० अमावास्याया वा
The affix वुञ् comes optionally after the word अमावास्या in the sense of 'born therein'.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.31|4.3.31 a cha|a cha|a cha 4.3.31|अ च|अ च ४.३.३१|४.३.३१|४.३.३१ अ च
The affix अ is also added to the word अमावास्या in the sense of 'born therein'.<br><br>Terms: अ

4.3.32|4.3.32 sindhvapakaraabhyaaM kan|sindhvapakaraabhyaaM kan|sindhvapakaraabhyaaM kan 4.3.32|सिन्ध्वपकराभ्यां कन्|सिन्ध्वपकराभ्यां कन् ४.३.३२|४.३.३२|४.३.३२ सिन्ध्वपकराभ्यां कन्
After the words 1. सिन्धु and 2. अपकर there is the affix कन् in the sense of 'born therein'.<br><br>Terms: कन्

4.3.33|4.3.33 aNaNJau cha|aNaNJau cha|aNaNJau cha 4.3.33|अणञौ च|अणञौ च ४.३.३३|४.३.३३|४.३.३३ अणञौ च
And the affixes अण् and अञ् come respectively after the words 1. सिन्धु and 2. अपकर।<br><br>Terms: अण् and अञ्

4.3.34|4.3.34 shraviShThaaphalgunyanuraadhaasvaatitiShyapunarvasuhastavishaakhaa.aShaaDhaabahulaalluk|shraviShThaaphalgunyanuraadhaasvaatitiShyapunarvasuhastavishaakhaa.aShaaDhaabahulaalluk|shraviShThaaphalgunyanuraadhaasvaatitiShyapunarvasuhastavishaakhaa.aShaaDhaabahulaalluk 4.3.34|श्रविष्ठाफल्गुन्यनुराधास्वातितिष्यपुनर्वसुहस्तविशाखाऽषाढाबहुलाल्लुक्|श्रविष्ठाफल्गुन्यनुराधास्वातितिष्यपुनर्वसुहस्तविशाखाऽषाढाबहुलाल्लुक् ४.३.३४|४.३.३४|४.३.३४ श्रविष्ठाफल्गुन्यनुराधास्वातितिष्यपुनर्वसुहस्तविशाखाऽषाढाबहुलाल्लुक्
The affix denoting 'born therein' is elided by लुक् after the words 1. श्रविष्ठ 2. फाल्गुनी 3. अनुराधा 4. स्वाति 5. तिष्य 6. पुनर्वसु 7. हस्त 8. विशाखा 9. अषाढा and 10. बहुला , all denoting asterisms.<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.3.35|4.3.35 sthaanaantagoshaalakharashaalaachcha|sthaanaantagoshaalakharashaalaachcha|sthaanaantagoshaalakharashaalaachcha 4.3.35|स्थानान्तगोशालखरशालाच्च|स्थानान्तगोशालखरशालाच्च ४.३.३५|४.३.३५|४.३.३५ स्थानान्तगोशालखरशालाच्च
There is लुक् elision of the affix denoting 'born therin' after a word ending in स्थान and after the words 1. गोशाल and 2. खरशाल।<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.3.36|4.3.36 vatsashaalaa.abhijidashvayukChatabhiShajo vaa|vatsashaalaa.abhijidashvayukChatabhiShajo vaa|vatsashaalaa.abhijidashvayukChatabhiShajo vaa 4.3.36|वत्सशालाऽभिजिदश्वयुक्छतभिषजो वा|वत्सशालाऽभिजिदश्वयुक्छतभिषजो वा ४.३.३६|४.३.३६|४.३.३६ वत्सशालाऽभिजिदश्वयुक्छतभिषजो वा
There is optionally लुक् elision of the affix denoting 'born therin' after the words 1. वत्सशाला 2. अभिजित् 3. अश्वयुक् and 4. शतभित्।<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.3.37|4.3.37 naxatrebhyo bahulam|naxatrebhyo bahulam|naxatrebhyo bahulam 4.3.37|नक्षत्रेभ्यो बहुलम्|नक्षत्रेभ्यो बहुलम् ४.३.३७|४.३.३७|४.३.३७ नक्षत्रेभ्यो बहुलम्
There is diversely लुक् elision of the affix denoting 'born therein' after an asterism.<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.3.38|4.3.38 kRtalabdhakriitakushalaaH|kRtalabdhakriitakushalaaH|kRtalabdhakriitakushalaaH 4.3.38|कृतलब्धक्रीतकुशलाः|कृतलब्धक्रीतकुशलाः ४.३.३८|४.३.३८|४.३.३८ कृतलब्धक्रीतकुशलाः
An affix (one of those already taught) comes after a word in the Locative -7th case, in the sense of 'done there', 'obtained there', 'bought there' and 'dexterous therein'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.39|4.3.39 praayabhavaH|praayabhavaH|praayabhavaH 4.3.39|प्रायभवः|प्रायभवः ४.३.३९|४.३.३९|४.३.३९ प्रायभवः
After a word being in construction in the Locative -7th case, an affix (one of those ordained already) comes in the sense of 'generally found therein'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.40|4.3.40 upajaanuupakarNopaniiveShThak|upajaanuupakarNopaniiveShThak|upajaanuupakarNopaniiveShThak 4.3.40|उपजानूपकर्णोपनीवेष्ठक्|उपजानूपकर्णोपनीवेष्ठक् ४.३.४०|४.३.४०|४.३.४० उपजानूपकर्णोपनीवेष्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes in the sense of 'mostly to be found there' after the words 1. उपजानु 2. उपकरण and 3. उपोनीवि , being in the Locative -7th case.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.41|4.3.41 saMbhuute|saMbhuute|saMbhuute 4.3.41|संभूते|संभूते ४.३.४१|४.३.४१|४.३.४१ संभूते
After a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) or a word ending in the feminine affix ङि and आप् , being in the Locative -7th case in construction, an affix comes in the sense of 'adapted therein'. <br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.42|4.3.42 koshaaDDhaNJ|koshaaDDhaNJ|koshaaDDhaNJ 4.3.42|कोशाड्ढञ्|कोशाड्ढञ् ४.३.४२|४.३.४२|४.३.४२ कोशाड्ढञ्
The affix ढञ् comes after the words कोश etc. in the sense of 'adapted to that'.<br><br>Terms: ढञ्

4.3.43|4.3.43 kaalaat‌ saadhupuShpyatpachyamaaneShu|kaalaat‌ saadhupuShpyatpachyamaaneShu|kaalaat‌ saadhupuShpyatpachyamaaneShu 4.3.43|कालात्‌ साधुपुष्प्यत्पच्यमानेषु|कालात्‌ साधुपुष्प्यत्पच्यमानेषु ४.३.४३|४.३.४३|४.३.४३ कालात्‌ साधुपुष्प्यत्पच्यमानेषु
An affix comes after a word denoting time being in the Locative -7th case in construction, in the sense of 'being good', 'flowering' or 'ripening therein.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति- 7

4.3.44|4.3.44 upte cha|upte cha|upte cha 4.3.44|उप्ते च|उप्ते च ४.३.४४|४.३.४४|४.३.४४ उप्ते च
An affix comes after a word denoting 'time' being in the Locative -7th case in construction meaning 'sown therein'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.45|4.3.45 aashvayujyaa vuNJ|aashvayujyaa vuNJ|aashvayujyaa vuNJ 4.3.45|आश्वयुज्या वुञ्|आश्वयुज्या वुञ् ४.३.४५|४.३.४५|४.३.४५ आश्वयुज्या वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'sown' after the word आश्वयुजी।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.46|4.3.46 griiShmavasantaadanyatarasyaam|griiShmavasantaadanyatarasyaam|griiShmavasantaadanyatarasyaam 4.3.46|ग्रीष्मवसन्तादन्यतरस्याम्|ग्रीष्मवसन्तादन्यतरस्याम् ४.३.४६|४.३.४६|४.३.४६ ग्रीष्मवसन्तादन्यतरस्याम्
The affix वुञ् comes optionally after the words 1. ग्रीष्म and 2. वसन्त in the sense of 'sown'.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.47|4.3.47 deyamRNe|deyamRNe|deyamRNe 4.3.47|देयमृणे|देयमृणे ४.३.४७|४.३.४७|४.३.४७ देयमृणे
After a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) being in the Locative -7th case in construction denoting time, an affix comes in the sense of 'being then due'; provided that the thing due be 'debt'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.48|4.3.48 kalaapyashvatthayavabusaadvun|kalaapyashvatthayavabusaadvun|kalaapyashvatthayavabusaadvun 4.3.48|कलाप्यश्वत्थयवबुसाद्वुन्|कलाप्यश्वत्थयवबुसाद्वुन् ४.३.४८|४.३.४८|४.३.४८ कलाप्यश्वत्थयवबुसाद्वुन्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'debt then due' after the words 1. कलापिन् 2. अश्वत्थ and 3. यवबुस् , denoting time and being in the Locative -7th case.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.49|4.3.49 griiShmaavarasamaadvuNJ|griiShmaavarasamaadvuNJ|griiShmaavarasamaadvuNJ 4.3.49|ग्रीष्मावरसमाद्वुञ्|ग्रीष्मावरसमाद्वुञ् ४.३.४९|४.३.४९|४.३.४९ ग्रीष्मावरसमाद्वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'debt due' after the words 1. ग्रीष्म and 2. अवरसम।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.50|4.3.50 saMvatsaraagrahaayaNiibhyaaM ThaNJ cha|saMvatsaraagrahaayaNiibhyaaM ThaNJ cha|saMvatsaraagrahaayaNiibhyaaM ThaNJ cha 4.3.50|संवत्सराग्रहायणीभ्यां ठञ् च|संवत्सराग्रहायणीभ्यां ठञ् च ४.३.५०|४.३.५०|४.३.५० संवत्सराग्रहायणीभ्यां ठञ् च
The affix ठञ् also (as well as वुञ् ) comes after the words 1. संवत्सरा 2. अग्राहायणी in the sense of 'debt due'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.51|4.3.51 vyaaharati mRgaH|vyaaharati mRgaH|vyaaharati mRgaH 4.3.51|व्याहरति मृगः|व्याहरति मृगः ४.३.५१|४.३.५१|४.३.५१ व्याहरति मृगः
An affix comes after a word in the Locative -7th case in construction denoting time, in the sense of 'who then wanders' and the word so formed refers to a wild beast.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.52|4.3.52 tadasya soDham|tadasya soDham|tadasya soDham 4.3.52|तदस्य सोढम्|तदस्य सोढम् ४.३.५२|४.३.५२|४.३.५२ तदस्य सोढम्
An affix comes after a word in the Nominative 1st-Case in construction denoting time in the sense of 'this is his habit or endurance'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-1

4.3.53|4.3.53 tatra bhavaH|tatra bhavaH|tatra bhavaH 4.3.53|तत्र भवः|तत्र भवः ४.३.५३|४.३.५३|४.३.५३ तत्र भवः
An affix comes after a word in the Locative -7th case in construction in the sense of 'who stays there'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-7

4.3.54|4.3.54 digaadibhyo yat‌|digaadibhyo yat‌|digaadibhyo yat‌ 4.3.54|दिगादिभ्यो यत्‌|दिगादिभ्यो यत्‌ ४.३.५४|४.३.५४|४.३.५४ दिगादिभ्यो यत्‌
The affix यत् comes in the sense of 'who stays there' after the प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stems) दिक् etc.<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.3.55|4.3.55 shariiraavayavaachcha|shariiraavayavaachcha|shariiraavayavaachcha 4.3.55|शरीरावयवाच्च|शरीरावयवाच्च ४.३.५५|४.३.५५|४.३.५५ शरीरावयवाच्च
The affix यत् comes in the sense of 'what stays there' after a word denoting a part of the body.<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.3.56|4.3.56 dRtikuxikalashivastyastyaherDhaNJ|dRtikuxikalashivastyastyaherDhaNJ|dRtikuxikalashivastyastyaherDhaNJ 4.3.56|दृतिकुक्षिकलशिवस्त्यस्त्यहेर्ढञ्|दृतिकुक्षिकलशिवस्त्यस्त्यहेर्ढञ् ४.३.५६|४.३.५६|४.३.५६ दृतिकुक्षिकलशिवस्त्यस्त्यहेर्ढञ्
The affix ढञ् comes in the sense of 'what stays there' after the words 1. दृति 2. कुक्षि 3. कलशि 4. वस्ति 5. अस्ति and 6. अहि।<br><br>Terms: ढञ्

4.3.57|4.3.57 griivaabhyo.aN cha|griivaabhyo.aN cha|griivaabhyo.aN cha 4.3.57|ग्रीवाभ्योऽण् च|ग्रीवाभ्योऽण् च ४.३.५७|४.३.५७|४.३.५७ ग्रीवाभ्योऽण् च
The affix अण् also (as well as ढञ् ) comes after the word ग्रीवा in the sense of 'what stays there'.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.58|4.3.58 gambhiiraaNJNJyaH|gambhiiraaNJNJyaH|gambhiiraaNJNJyaH 4.3.58|गम्भीराञ्ञ्यः|गम्भीराञ्ञ्यः ४.३.५८|४.३.५८|४.३.५८ गम्भीराञ्ञ्यः
The affix ञ्य comes in the sense of 'who stays there' after the word गम्भीर।<br><br>Terms: ञ्य

4.3.59|4.3.59 avyayiibhaavaachcha|avyayiibhaavaachcha|avyayiibhaavaachcha 4.3.59|अव्ययीभावाच्च|अव्ययीभावाच्च ४.३.५९|४.३.५९|४.३.५९ अव्ययीभावाच्च
After an अव्ययीभाव समास the affix ञ्य is used in the sense of 'who stays there'.<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास-ञ्य

4.3.60|4.3.60 antaHpuurvapadaaTThaNJ|antaHpuurvapadaaTThaNJ|antaHpuurvapadaaTThaNJ 4.3.60|अन्तःपूर्वपदाट्ठञ्|अन्तःपूर्वपदाट्ठञ् ४.३.६०|४.३.६०|४.३.६० अन्तःपूर्वपदाट्ठञ्
After an अव्ययीभाव समास having the word अन्तर as prior term, the affix ठञ् is used in the sense of 'who stays there'.<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास-ठञ्

4.3.61|4.3.61 graamaat‌ paryanupuurvaat‌|graamaat‌ paryanupuurvaat‌|graamaat‌ paryanupuurvaat‌ 4.3.61|ग्रामात्‌ पर्यनुपूर्वात्‌|ग्रामात्‌ पर्यनुपूर्वात्‌ ४.३.६१|४.३.६१|४.३.६१ ग्रामात्‌ पर्यनुपूर्वात्‌
After the word ग्राम preceded by परि or अनु (the whole being अव्ययीभाव समास ) there is the affix ठञ् in the sense of 'who stays there'.<br><br>Terms: अव्ययीभाव समास

4.3.62|4.3.62 jihvaamuulaanguleshChaH|jihvaamuulaanguleshChaH|jihvaamuulaanguleshChaH 4.3.62|जिह्वामूलाङ्गुलेश्छः|जिह्वामूलाङ्गुलेश्छः ४.३.६२|४.३.६२|४.३.६२ जिह्वामूलाङ्गुलेश्छः
After the words 1. जिह्वामूल and 2. अङ्गुलि there is the affix छ in the sense of 'who stays there'.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.3.63|4.3.63 vargaantaachcha|vargaantaachcha|vargaantaachcha 4.3.63|वर्गान्ताच्च|वर्गान्ताच्च ४.३.६३|४.३.६३|४.३.६३ वर्गान्ताच्च
After a word ending with वर्ग the affix छ is used in the sense of 'who ocurs there'.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.3.64|4.3.64 ashabde yatkhaavanyatarasyaam|ashabde yatkhaavanyatarasyaam|ashabde yatkhaavanyatarasyaam 4.3.64|अशब्दे यत्खावन्यतरस्याम्|अशब्दे यत्खावन्यतरस्याम् ४.३.६४|४.३.६४|४.३.६४ अशब्दे यत्खावन्यतरस्याम्
After a word ending with वर्ग but not meaning a 'letter or word' the affixes यत् and ख are optionally used in the sense of 'who stays there'.<br><br>Terms: यत् and ख

4.3.65|4.3.65 karNalalaaTaat‌ kanalaMkaare|karNalalaaTaat‌ kanalaMkaare|karNalalaaTaat‌ kanalaMkaare 4.3.65|कर्णललाटात्‌ कनलंकारे|कर्णललाटात्‌ कनलंकारे ४.३.६५|४.३.६५|४.३.६५ कर्णललाटात्‌ कनलंकारे
The affix कन् comes in the sense of 'what occurs there' after कर्ण and ललाट , the word denoting 'an ornament'. <br><br>Terms: कन्

4.3.66|4.3.66 tasya vyaakhyaana iti cha vyaakhyaatavyanaamnaH|tasya vyaakhyaana iti cha vyaakhyaatavyanaamnaH|tasya vyaakhyaana iti cha vyaakhyaatavyanaamnaH 4.3.66|तस्य व्याख्यान इति च व्याख्यातव्यनाम्नः|तस्य व्याख्यान इति च व्याख्यातव्यनाम्नः ४.३.६६|४.३.६६|४.३.६६ तस्य व्याख्यान इति च व्याख्यातव्यनाम्नः
After the name of a subject of commentary an affix comes in the sense of 'its commentary', as well as in the sense of 'what occurs there'.<br><br>Terms: तत्रभव-अण्

4.3.67|4.3.67 bahvacho.antodaattaaTThaNJ|bahvacho.antodaattaaTThaNJ|bahvacho.antodaattaaTThaNJ 4.3.67|बह्वचोऽन्तोदात्ताट्ठञ्|बह्वचोऽन्तोदात्ताट्ठञ् ४.३.६७|४.३.६७|४.३.६७ बह्वचोऽन्तोदात्ताट्ठञ्
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'staying' and 'a commentary' after a polysyllabic word having उदात्त on the final (the word being the name of a thing to be explained).<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.68|4.3.68 kratuyaJNebhyashcha|kratuyaJNebhyashcha|kratuyaJNebhyashcha 4.3.68|क्रतुयज्ञेभ्यश्च|क्रतुयज्ञेभ्यश्च ४.३.६८|४.३.६८|४.३.६८ क्रतुयज्ञेभ्यश्च
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'occurring' and 'a commentary' after the name of a work to be explained provided that such work relates to a क्रतु or a यज्ञ।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.69|4.3.69 adhyaayeShvevarSheH|adhyaayeShvevarSheH|adhyaayeShvevarSheH 4.3.69|अध्यायेष्वेवर्षेः|अध्यायेष्वेवर्षेः ४.३.६९|४.३.६९|४.३.६९ अध्यायेष्वेवर्षेः
The affix ठञ् comes after the name of an explainable work called after a ऋषि in the senses of 'occurring therein' or 'commentary thereon' when it referes to an अध्याय only.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.70|4.3.70 pauroDaashapuroDaashaat ShThan|pauroDaashapuroDaashaat ShThan|pauroDaashapuroDaashaat ShThan 4.3.70|पौरोडाशपुरोडाशात् ष्ठन्|पौरोडाशपुरोडाशात् ष्ठन् ४.३.७०|४.३.७०|४.३.७० पौरोडाशपुरोडाशात् ष्ठन्
The affix ष्ठन् comes in the sense of 'occurring therein' and 'commentary thereon' after the words 1. पौरोडाश and 2. पुरोडाश।<br><br>Terms: ष्ठन्

4.3.71|4.3.71 Chandaso yadaNau|Chandaso yadaNau|Chandaso yadaNau 4.3.71|छन्दसो यदणौ|छन्दसो यदणौ ४.३.७१|४.३.७१|४.३.७१ छन्दसो यदणौ
The affixes यत् and अण् comes in the sense of 'occurring therein' or 'commentary thereon'after the word छन्दस्।<br><br>Terms: यत् and अण्

4.3.72|4.3.72 dvyajRdbraahmaNarkprathamaadhvarapurashcharaNanaamaakhyaataaTThak|dvyajRdbraahmaNarkprathamaadhvarapurashcharaNanaamaakhyaataaTThak|dvyajRdbraahmaNarkprathamaadhvarapurashcharaNanaamaakhyaataaTThak 4.3.72|द्व्यजृद्ब्राह्मणर्क्प्रथमाध्वरपुरश्चरणनामाख्याताट्ठक्|द्व्यजृद्ब्राह्मणर्क्प्रथमाध्वरपुरश्चरणनामाख्याताट्ठक् ४.३.७२|४.३.७२|४.३.७२ द्व्यजृद्ब्राह्मणर्क्प्रथमाध्वरपुरश्चरणनामाख्याताट्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes in the sense of 'occurring therein' or 'commentary thereon'after a word of two syllables and a word ending in short ऋ and the words 1. ब्राह्मण 2. ऋक् 3. प्रथम 4. पुरश्चरण 5. नाम 6. आख्यात and 7. नामाख्यात being the names of explainable works.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.3.73|4.3.73 aNRgayanaadibhyaH|aNRgayanaadibhyaH|aNRgayanaadibhyaH 4.3.73|अणृगयनादिभ्यः|अणृगयनादिभ्यः ४.३.७३|४.३.७३|४.३.७३ अणृगयनादिभ्यः
The affix अण् comes in the senses of 'occurring therein' and 'commentary thereon' after the words ऋगयन etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.74|4.3.74 tata aagataH|tata aagataH|tata aagataH 4.3.74|तत आगतः|तत आगतः ४.३.७४|४.३.७४|४.३.७४ तत आगतः
The affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ etc. comes in the sense of 'what has come thence'.<br><br>Terms: 

4.3.75|4.3.75 ThagaayasthaanebhyaH|ThagaayasthaanebhyaH|ThagaayasthaanebhyaH 4.3.75|ठगायस्थानेभ्यः|ठगायस्थानेभ्यः ४.३.७५|४.३.७५|४.३.७५ ठगायस्थानेभ्यः
After a word denoting sources of revenue there is the affix ठक् in the sense of 'come thence'.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.3.76|4.3.76 shuNDikaadibhyo.aN|shuNDikaadibhyo.aN|shuNDikaadibhyo.aN 4.3.76|शुण्डिकादिभ्योऽण्|शुण्डिकादिभ्योऽण् ४.३.७६|४.३.७६|४.३.७६ शुण्डिकादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'thence come' after the words शुण्डिक etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.77|4.3.77 vidyaayonisaMbandhebhyo vuNJ|vidyaayonisaMbandhebhyo vuNJ|vidyaayonisaMbandhebhyo vuNJ 4.3.77|विद्यायोनिसंबन्धेभ्यो वुञ्|विद्यायोनिसंबन्धेभ्यो वुञ् ४.३.७७|४.३.७७|४.३.७७ विद्यायोनिसंबन्धेभ्यो वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'thence come' after a word denoting a person connected through the relationship or family origin.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.78|4.3.78 RtaShThaNJ|RtaShThaNJ|RtaShThaNJ 4.3.78|ऋतष्ठञ्|ऋतष्ठञ् ४.३.७८|४.३.७८|४.३.७८ ऋतष्ठञ्
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'come thence' after a word ending in short ऋ and denoting a person related through learning or blood.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.79|4.3.79 pituryachcha|pituryachcha|pituryachcha 4.3.79|पितुर्यच्च|पितुर्यच्च ४.३.७९|४.३.७९|४.३.७९ पितुर्यच्च
The affix यत् and ठञ् comes in the sense of 'come thence' after the word पितृ।<br><br>Terms: यत् and ठञ्

4.3.80|4.3.80 gotraadankavat‌|gotraadankavat‌|gotraadankavat‌ 4.3.80|गोत्रादङ्कवत्‌|गोत्रादङ्कवत्‌ ४.३.८०|४.३.८०|४.३.८० गोत्रादङ्कवत्‌
After a word ending with a Patronymic affix the rule of affix in the sense of 'thence come' is like that relating to the affix denoting its mark.<br><br>Terms: 

4.3.81|4.3.81 hetumanuShyebhyo.anyatarasyaaM ruupyaH|hetumanuShyebhyo.anyatarasyaaM ruupyaH|hetumanuShyebhyo.anyatarasyaaM ruupyaH 4.3.81|हेतुमनुष्येभ्योऽन्यतरस्यां रूप्यः|हेतुमनुष्येभ्योऽन्यतरस्यां रूप्यः ४.३.८१|४.३.८१|४.३.८१ हेतुमनुष्येभ्योऽन्यतरस्यां रूप्यः
The affix रूप्य denotes that which from something has originated when it is added to a word denoting 'cause' or to the name of a man viewed as a cause.<br><br>Terms: रूप्य

4.3.82|4.3.82 mayaT cha|mayaT cha|mayaT cha 4.3.82|मयट् च|मयट् च ४.३.८२|४.३.८२|४.३.८२ मयट् च
After a word denoting a cause or a man viewed as a cause, there is the affix मयट् in the sense of 'come thence'.<br><br>Terms: मयट्

4.3.83|4.3.83 prabhavati|prabhavati|prabhavati 4.3.83|प्रभवति|प्रभवति ४.३.८३|४.३.८३|४.३.८३ प्रभवति
After a प्रातिपदिक (Nominal Stem) which is the Ablative -5th case in construction, an affix (one of those already taught) comes in the sense of 'what appears for the first time'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्त-5

4.3.84|4.3.84 viduuraaNJNJyaH|viduuraaNJNJyaH|viduuraaNJNJyaH 4.3.84|विदूराञ्ञ्यः|विदूराञ्ञ्यः ४.३.८४|४.३.८४|४.३.८४ विदूराञ्ञ्यः
The affix य comes in the sense of 'what manifests itself there' after the word विदुर।<br><br>Terms: य

4.3.85|4.3.85 tadgachChati pathiduutayoH|tadgachChati pathiduutayoH|tadgachChati pathiduutayoH 4.3.85|तद्गच्छति पथिदूतयोः|तद्गच्छति पथिदूतयोः ४.३.८५|४.३.८५|४.३.८५ तद्गच्छति पथिदूतयोः
An affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ etc. comes after a word in the Accusative -2nd case in construction in the sense of 'what goes thereto', provided that, which goes, is a road or a messenger.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2

4.3.86|4.3.86 abhiniShkraamati dvaaram|abhiniShkraamati dvaaram|abhiniShkraamati dvaaram 4.3.86|अभिनिष्क्रामति द्वारम्|अभिनिष्क्रामति द्वारम् ४.३.८६|४.३.८६|४.३.८६ अभिनिष्क्रामति द्वारम्
An affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ etc. comes after a word in the Accusative -2nd case in construction in the sense of 'a door which looks towards that'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2

4.3.87|4.3.87 adhikRtya kRte granthe|adhikRtya kRte granthe|adhikRtya kRte granthe 4.3.87|अधिकृत्य कृते ग्रन्थे|अधिकृत्य कृते ग्रन्थे ४.३.८७|४.३.८७|४.३.८७ अधिकृत्य कृते ग्रन्थे
An affix comes after a word in the Accusative -2nd case in construction in the sense of 'made in relation to any subject' when the thing made is a 'book'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-2

4.3.88|4.3.88 shishukrandayamasabhadvaMdvendrajananaadibhyashChaH|shishukrandayamasabhadvaMdvendrajananaadibhyashChaH|shishukrandayamasabhadvaMdvendrajananaadibhyashChaH 4.3.88|शिशुक्रन्दयमसभद्वंद्वेन्द्रजननादिभ्यश्छः|शिशुक्रन्दयमसभद्वंद्वेन्द्रजननादिभ्यश्छः ४.३.८८|४.३.८८|४.३.८८ शिशुक्रन्दयमसभद्वंद्वेन्द्रजननादिभ्यश्छः
The affix छ comes in the sense of 'a book made relating to a subject' after the following words in the Accusative -2nd case in construction viz. 1. शिशुक्रन्द 2. यमसभ , the द्वन्द समास and the words इन्द्रजनन etc.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.3.89|4.3.89 so.asya nivaasaH|so.asya nivaasaH|so.asya nivaasaH 4.3.89|सोऽस्य निवासः|सोऽस्य निवासः ४.३.८९|४.३.८९|४.३.८९ सोऽस्य निवासः
After a word in the Nominative 1st-Case in construction, an affix comes in the sense of 'this is his dwelling place'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-1

4.3.90|4.3.90 abhijanashcha|abhijanashcha|abhijanashcha 4.3.90|अभिजनश्च|अभिजनश्च ४.३.९०|४.३.९०|४.३.९० अभिजनश्च
After a word in the Nominative 1st-Case in construction, an affix comes in the sense of 'this is his mother-land'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-1

4.3.91|4.3.91 aayudhajiivibhyashChaH parvate|aayudhajiivibhyashChaH parvate|aayudhajiivibhyashChaH parvate 4.3.91|आयुधजीविभ्यश्छः पर्वते|आयुधजीविभ्यश्छः पर्वते ४.३.९१|४.३.९१|४.३.९१ आयुधजीविभ्यश्छः पर्वते
The affix छ comes after a word denoting 'mountain' in the sense of 'this is his mother-land', when it is a person who lives by arms.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.3.92|4.3.92 shaNDikaadibhyo NJyaH|shaNDikaadibhyo NJyaH|shaNDikaadibhyo NJyaH 4.3.92|शण्डिकादिभ्यो ञ्यः|शण्डिकादिभ्यो ञ्यः ४.३.९२|४.३.९२|४.३.९२ शण्डिकादिभ्यो ञ्यः
The affix ञ्य comes in the sense of 'this is his native-land' after the words शण्डिक etc.<br><br>Terms: ञ्य

4.3.93|4.3.93 sindhutaxashilaa.a.adibhyo.aNaNJau|sindhutaxashilaa.a.adibhyo.aNaNJau|sindhutaxashilaa.a.adibhyo.aNaNJau 4.3.93|सिन्धुतक्षशिलाऽऽदिभ्योऽणञौ|सिन्धुतक्षशिलाऽऽदिभ्योऽणञौ ४.३.९३|४.३.९३|४.३.९३ सिन्धुतक्षशिलाऽऽदिभ्योऽणञौ
The affixes अण् and अञ् come respectively after the words सिन्धु etc. and तक्षशिला etc. in the sense of 'this is his native land'.<br><br>Terms: अण् and अञ्

4.3.94|4.3.94 tuudiishalaaturavarmatiikuuchavaaraaDDhakChaNDhaNJyakaH|tuudiishalaaturavarmatiikuuchavaaraaDDhakChaNDhaNJyakaH|tuudiishalaaturavarmatiikuuchavaaraaDDhakChaNDhaNJyakaH 4.3.94|तूदीशलातुरवर्मतीकूचवाराड्ढक्छण्ढञ्यकः|तूदीशलातुरवर्मतीकूचवाराड्ढक्छण्ढञ्यकः ४.३.९४|४.३.९४|४.३.९४ तूदीशलातुरवर्मतीकूचवाराड्ढक्छण्ढञ्यकः
After the words 1. तूदी 2. शलातुर 3. वर्मती and 4. कूचवार come respectively the affixes 1. ढक् 2. छण् 3. ढञ् and 4. यक् in the sense of 'this is his native land'.<br><br>Terms: ढक् , छण् , ढञ् and यक्

4.3.95|4.3.95 bhaktiH|bhaktiH|bhaktiH 4.3.95|भक्तिः|भक्तिः ४.३.९५|४.३.९५|४.३.९५ भक्तिः
An affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३, comes after a word in the Nominative 1st-Case in construction in the sense of 'this is his object of veneration or love'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-1

4.3.96|4.3.96 achittaadadeshakaalaaTThak|achittaadadeshakaalaaTThak|achittaadadeshakaalaaTThak 4.3.96|अचित्ताददेशकालाट्ठक्|अचित्ताददेशकालाट्ठक् ४.३.९६|४.३.९६|४.३.९६ अचित्ताददेशकालाट्ठक्
After a word denoting a thing not having consciousness, but not being the name of a country or time, the affix ठक् is used in the sense of 'this is his object of devotion or love'.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.3.97|4.3.97 mahaaraajaaTThaNJ|mahaaraajaaTThaNJ|mahaaraajaaTThaNJ 4.3.97|महाराजाट्ठञ्|महाराजाट्ठञ् ४.३.९७|४.३.९७|४.३.९७ महाराजाट्ठञ्
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'this is his object of veneration' after the word महाराज।<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.3.98|4.3.98 vaasudevaarjunaabhyaaM vun|vaasudevaarjunaabhyaaM vun|vaasudevaarjunaabhyaaM vun 4.3.98|वासुदेवार्जुनाभ्यां वुन्|वासुदेवार्जुनाभ्यां वुन् ४.३.९८|४.३.९८|४.३.९८ वासुदेवार्जुनाभ्यां वुन्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'this is his object of veneration' after the words 1. वासुदेव and अर्जुना।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.99|4.3.99 gotraxatriyaakhyebhyo bahulaM vuNJ|gotraxatriyaakhyebhyo bahulaM vuNJ|gotraxatriyaakhyebhyo bahulaM vuNJ 4.3.99|गोत्रक्षत्रियाख्येभ्यो बहुलं वुञ्|गोत्रक्षत्रियाख्येभ्यो बहुलं वुञ् ४.३.९९|४.३.९९|४.३.९९ गोत्रक्षत्रियाख्येभ्यो बहुलं वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes diversely in the sense of 'this is his object of veneration' after a word denoting गोत्र (Patronymic) or a क्षत्रिय।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.100|4.3.100 janapadinaaM janapadavat‌ sarvaM janapadena samaanashabdaanaaM bahuvachane|janapadinaaM janapadavat‌ sarvaM janapadena samaanashabdaanaaM bahuvachane|janapadinaaM janapadavat‌ sarvaM janapadena samaanashabdaanaaM bahuvachane 4.3.100|जनपदिनां जनपदवत्‌ सर्वं जनपदेन समानशब्दानां बहुवचने|जनपदिनां जनपदवत्‌ सर्वं जनपदेन समानशब्दानां बहुवचने ४.३.१००|४.३.१००|४.३.१०० जनपदिनां जनपदवत्‌ सर्वं जनपदेन समानशब्दानां बहुवचने
Of words denoting Princes (literally - who are Lords of जनपद) the base and affix meaning 'this is his object of veneration' are the same, in every respect, like those of a word denoting kingdom, provided that, the Prince-denoting words have, in the plural, the same form as the Kingdom-denoting words.<br><br>Terms: 

4.3.101|4.3.101 tena proktam|tena proktam|tena proktam 4.3.101|तेन प्रोक्तम्|तेन प्रोक्तम् ४.३.१०१|४.३.१०१|४.३.१०१ तेन प्रोक्तम्
After a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction, an affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ etc., comes in the sense of 'enounced by him'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

4.3.102|4.3.102 tittirivaratantukhaNDikokhaachChaN|tittirivaratantukhaNDikokhaachChaN|tittirivaratantukhaNDikokhaachChaN 4.3.102|तित्तिरिवरतन्तुखण्डिकोखाच्छण्|तित्तिरिवरतन्तुखण्डिकोखाच्छण् ४.३.१०२|४.३.१०२|४.३.१०२ तित्तिरिवरतन्तुखण्डिकोखाच्छण्
The affix छण् comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' after the words 1. तित्तिरि 2. वरतन्तु 3. खण्डिक and 4. उख।<br><br>Terms: छण्

4.3.103|4.3.103 kaashyapakaushikaabhyaamRShibhyaaM NiniH|kaashyapakaushikaabhyaamRShibhyaaM NiniH|kaashyapakaushikaabhyaamRShibhyaaM NiniH 4.3.103|काश्यपकौशिकाभ्यामृषिभ्यां णिनिः|काश्यपकौशिकाभ्यामृषिभ्यां णिनिः ४.३.१०३|४.३.१०३|४.३.१०३ काश्यपकौशिकाभ्यामृषिभ्यां णिनिः
The affix णिनि comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' after the words 1. काश्यप and 2. कौशिक denoting ऋषि-s (Vedic Seers).<br><br>Terms: णिनि

4.3.104|4.3.104 kalaapivaishampaayanaantevaasibhyashcha|kalaapivaishampaayanaantevaasibhyashcha|kalaapivaishampaayanaantevaasibhyashcha 4.3.104|कलापिवैशम्पायनान्तेवासिभ्यश्च|कलापिवैशम्पायनान्तेवासिभ्यश्च ४.३.१०४|४.३.१०४|४.३.१०४ कलापिवैशम्पायनान्तेवासिभ्यश्च
After the words denoting the pupils of कलापि and वैशम्पायन , the affix णिनि is used in the sense of 'enounced by him'.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

4.3.105|4.3.105 puraaNaprokteShu braahmaNakalpeShu|puraaNaprokteShu braahmaNakalpeShu|puraaNaprokteShu braahmaNakalpeShu 4.3.105|पुराणप्रोक्तेषु ब्राह्मणकल्पेषु|पुराणप्रोक्तेषु ब्राह्मणकल्पेषु ४.३.१०५|४.३.१०५|४.३.१०५ पुराणप्रोक्तेषु ब्राह्मणकल्पेषु
The affix णिनि comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction when it denotes a ब्राह्मण or a कल्प-work enounced by ancient sages.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

4.3.106|4.3.106 shaunakaadibhyashChandasi|shaunakaadibhyashChandasi|shaunakaadibhyashChandasi 4.3.106|शौनकादिभ्यश्छन्दसि|शौनकादिभ्यश्छन्दसि ४.३.१०६|४.३.१०६|४.३.१०६ शौनकादिभ्यश्छन्दसि
The affix णिनि comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' after the words शौनक etc. in denoting छन्दस् (Vedas).<br><br>Terms: णिनि

4.3.107|4.3.107 kaThacharakaalluk|kaThacharakaalluk|kaThacharakaalluk 4.3.107|कठचरकाल्लुक्|कठचरकाल्लुक् ४.३.१०७|४.३.१०७|४.३.१०७ कठचरकाल्लुक्
The affix denoting 'enounced by him' is elided by लुक्-substitution after the words कठ and चरक।<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.3.108|4.3.108 kalaapino.aN|kalaapino.aN|kalaapino.aN 4.3.108|कलापिनोऽण्|कलापिनोऽण् ४.३.१०८|४.३.१०८|४.३.१०८ कलापिनोऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' after the word कलापि।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.109|4.3.109 Chagalino Dhinuk|Chagalino Dhinuk|Chagalino Dhinuk 4.3.109|छगलिनो ढिनुक्|छगलिनो ढिनुक् ४.३.१०९|४.३.१०९|४.३.१०९ छगलिनो ढिनुक्
The affix ढिनुक् comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' after the word छगलिन।<br><br>Terms: ढिनुक्

4.3.110|4.3.110 paaraasharyashilaalibhyaaM bhixunaTasuutrayoH|paaraasharyashilaalibhyaaM bhixunaTasuutrayoH|paaraasharyashilaalibhyaaM bhixunaTasuutrayoH 4.3.110|पाराशर्यशिलालिभ्यां भिक्षुनटसूत्रयोः|पाराशर्यशिलालिभ्यां भिक्षुनटसूत्रयोः ४.३.११०|४.३.११०|४.३.११० पाराशर्यशिलालिभ्यां भिक्षुनटसूत्रयोः
The affix णिनि comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' after the words 1. पाराशर्य and 2. शिलालिन् , the works enounced being भिक्षु-sūtra and नट-sūtra respectively.<br><br>Terms: णिनि

4.3.111|4.3.111 karmandakRshaashvaadiniH|karmandakRshaashvaadiniH|karmandakRshaashvaadiniH 4.3.111|कर्मन्दकृशाश्वादिनिः|कर्मन्दकृशाश्वादिनिः ४.३.१११|४.३.१११|४.३.१११ कर्मन्दकृशाश्वादिनिः
The affix इनि comes in the sense of 'enounced by him' the thing enounced being भिक्षु-sūtra and नट-sūtra after the words 1. कर्मन्द 2. कृशाश्व।<br><br>Terms: इनि

4.3.112|4.3.112 tenaikadik|tenaikadik|tenaikadik 4.3.112|तेनैकदिक्|तेनैकदिक् ४.३.११२|४.३.११२|४.३.११२ तेनैकदिक्
An affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ etc. comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense of 'in the same direction with that'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

4.3.113|4.3.113 tasishcha|tasishcha|tasishcha 4.3.113|तसिश्च|तसिश्च ४.३.११३|४.३.११३|४.३.११३ तसिश्च
The affix तसि comes in the sense of 'in the same direction with that'.<br><br>Terms: तसि

4.3.114|4.3.114 uraso yachcha|uraso yachcha|uraso yachcha 4.3.114|उरसो यच्च|उरसो यच्च ४.३.११४|४.३.११४|४.३.११४ उरसो यच्च
The affixes यत् and तसि come in the sense of 'in the same direction with that' after the word उरस।<br><br>Terms: यत् and तसि

4.3.115|4.3.115 upaJNaate|upaJNaate|upaJNaate 4.3.115|उपज्ञाते|उपज्ञाते ४.३.११५|४.३.११५|४.३.११५ उपज्ञाते
After a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction an affix is used in the sense 'discovered by him'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

4.3.116|4.3.116 kRte granthe|kRte granthe|kRte granthe 4.3.116|कृते ग्रन्थे|कृते ग्रन्थे ४.३.११६|४.३.११६|४.३.११६ कृते ग्रन्थे
An affix comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense of 'made', the thing made being 'a book'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

4.3.117|4.3.117 saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam 4.3.117|संज्ञायाम्|संज्ञायाम् ४.३.११७|४.३.११७|४.३.११७ संज्ञायाम्
An affix comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense of 'made by him' when the whole word is a Name.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-3

4.3.118|4.3.118 kulaalaadibhyo vuNJ|kulaalaadibhyo vuNJ|kulaalaadibhyo vuNJ 4.3.118|कुलालादिभ्यो वुञ्|कुलालादिभ्यो वुञ् ४.३.११८|४.३.११८|४.३.११८ कुलालादिभ्यो वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'made by him' after the words कुलाल etc. the whole word so formed being a Name.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.119|4.3.119 xudraabhramaravaTarapaadapaadaNJ|xudraabhramaravaTarapaadapaadaNJ|xudraabhramaravaTarapaadapaadaNJ 4.3.119|क्षुद्राभ्रमरवटरपादपादञ्|क्षुद्राभ्रमरवटरपादपादञ् ४.३.११९|४.३.११९|४.३.११९ क्षुद्राभ्रमरवटरपादपादञ्
The affix अञ् comes after the words 1. क्षुद्रा 2. भ्रमर 3. वटर and 4. पादप in the sense of 'made by him', the whole word being a Name.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.120|4.3.120 tasyedam|tasyedam|tasyedam 4.3.120|तस्येदम्|तस्येदम् ४.३.१२०|४.३.१२०|४.३.१२० तस्येदम्
After a word in the Genitive -6th-Case in construction an affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ comes in the sense of 'this is his',<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

4.3.121|4.3.121 rathaadyat‌|rathaadyat‌|rathaadyat‌ 4.3.121|रथाद्यत्‌|रथाद्यत्‌ ४.३.१२१|४.३.१२१|४.३.१२१ रथाद्यत्‌
The affix यत् comes after रथ in the sense of 'this is his'.<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.3.122|4.3.122 pattrapuurvaadaNJ|pattrapuurvaadaNJ|pattrapuurvaadaNJ 4.3.122|पत्त्रपूर्वादञ्|पत्त्रपूर्वादञ् ४.३.१२२|४.३.१२२|४.३.१२२ पत्त्रपूर्वादञ्
When preceded by a word denoting 'a draught animal', रथ takes the affix अञ् in the sense of 'this is his'.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.123|4.3.123 pattraadhvaryupariShadashcha|pattraadhvaryupariShadashcha|pattraadhvaryupariShadashcha 4.3.123|पत्त्राध्वर्युपरिषदश्च|पत्त्राध्वर्युपरिषदश्च ४.३.१२३|४.३.१२३|४.३.१२३ पत्त्राध्वर्युपरिषदश्च
After a word denoting a draught-animal and after the words 1. अध्वर्यु and 2. परिषद् the affix अञ् is added.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.124|4.3.124 halasiiraaTThak|halasiiraaTThak|halasiiraaTThak 4.3.124|हलसीराट्ठक्|हलसीराट्ठक् ४.३.१२४|४.३.१२४|४.३.१२४ हलसीराट्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes in the sense of 'this is his' after the words 1. हल and 2. सीर।<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.3.125|4.3.125 dvaMdvaadvun vairamaithunikayoH|dvaMdvaadvun vairamaithunikayoH|dvaMdvaadvun vairamaithunikayoH 4.3.125|द्वंद्वाद्वुन् वैरमैथुनिकयोः|द्वंद्वाद्वुन् वैरमैथुनिकयोः ४.३.१२५|४.३.१२५|४.३.१२५ द्वंद्वाद्वुन् वैरमैथुनिकयोः
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'this is his' after द्वन्द compound of words denoting 'mutual enmity' or 'matrimonial relationship'.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.126|4.3.126 gotracharaNaadvuNJ|gotracharaNaadvuNJ|gotracharaNaadvuNJ 4.3.126|गोत्रचरणाद्वुञ्|गोत्रचरणाद्वुञ् ४.३.१२६|४.३.१२६|४.३.१२६ गोत्रचरणाद्वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'this is his' after the words denoting गोत्र (Patronymic/Family-names) of Vedic schools.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.127|4.3.127 saMghaankalaxaNeShvaNJyaNJiNJaamaN|saMghaankalaxaNeShvaNJyaNJiNJaamaN|saMghaankalaxaNeShvaNJyaNJiNJaamaN 4.3.127|संघाङ्कलक्षणेष्वञ्यञिञामण्|संघाङ्कलक्षणेष्वञ्यञिञामण् ४.३.१२७|४.३.१२७|४.३.१२७ संघाङ्कलक्षणेष्वञ्यञिञामण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'this is his' after a गोत्र (Patronymic) word ending with the affix अञ् or यञ् or इञ् , the words so formed expressing a multitude, a mark or a sign. <br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.128|4.3.128 shaakalaadvaa|shaakalaadvaa|shaakalaadvaa 4.3.128|शाकलाद्वा|शाकलाद्वा ४.३.१२८|४.३.१२८|४.३.१२८ शाकलाद्वा
The affix अण् optionally comes in the sense of 'this is his congregation, mark, sign or hamlet' after the word शाकल।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.129|4.3.129 ChandogaukthikayaaJNikabahvRchanaTaaNJNJyaH|ChandogaukthikayaaJNikabahvRchanaTaaNJNJyaH|ChandogaukthikayaaJNikabahvRchanaTaaNJNJyaH 4.3.129|छन्दोगौक्थिकयाज्ञिकबह्वृचनटाञ्ञ्यः|छन्दोगौक्थिकयाज्ञिकबह्वृचनटाञ्ञ्यः ४.३.१२९|४.३.१२९|४.३.१२९ छन्दोगौक्थिकयाज्ञिकबह्वृचनटाञ्ञ्यः
The affix ञ्य comes in the sense of 'this is his Law or Tradition' after the words 1. छान्दोग 2. औक्थिक 3. याज्ञिक 4. बह्वृच and 5. नट।<br><br>Terms: ञ्य

4.3.130|4.3.130 na daNDamaaNavaantevaasiShu|na daNDamaaNavaantevaasiShu|na daNDamaaNavaantevaasiShu 4.3.130|न दण्डमाणवान्तेवासिषु|न दण्डमाणवान्तेवासिषु ४.३.१३०|४.३.१३०|४.३.१३० न दण्डमाणवान्तेवासिषु
The affix वुञ् is not used after a Family-name when it denotes 'a beginner pupil' and 'a boarder pupil'.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.131|4.3.131 raivatikaadibhyashChaH|raivatikaadibhyashChaH|raivatikaadibhyashChaH 4.3.131|रैवतिकादिभ्यश्छः|रैवतिकादिभ्यश्छः ४.३.१३१|४.३.१३१|४.३.१३१ रैवतिकादिभ्यश्छः
The affix छ comes in the sense of 'this is his' after the words रैवतिक etc.<br><br>Terms: छ

4.3.132|4.3.132 kaupinjalahaastipadaadaN|kaupinjalahaastipadaadaN|kaupinjalahaastipadaadaN 4.3.132|कौपिञ्जलहास्तिपदादण्|कौपिञ्जलहास्तिपदादण् ४.३.१३२|४.३.१३२|४.३.१३२ कौपिञ्जलहास्तिपदादण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'this is his' after the words 1. कौपिञ्जल 2. हास्तिपद।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.133|4.3.133 aatharvaNikasyekalopashcha|aatharvaNikasyekalopashcha|aatharvaNikasyekalopashcha 4.3.133|आथर्वणिकस्येकलोपश्च|आथर्वणिकस्येकलोपश्च ४.३.१३३|४.३.१३३|४.३.१३३ आथर्वणिकस्येकलोपश्च
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'this is his' after the word आथर्वणिक and the penultimate इक् is elided.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.134|4.3.134 tasya vikaaraH|tasya vikaaraH|tasya vikaaraH 4.3.134|तस्य विकारः|तस्य विकारः ४.३.१३४|४.३.१३४|४.३.१३४ तस्य विकारः
An affix -- प्राग्दीव्यतोऽण् ४.१.८३ etc., comes after a word in the Genitive -6th-Case in construction in the sense of 'a modification thereof'.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

4.3.135|4.3.135 avayave cha praaNyoShadhivRxebhyaH|avayave cha praaNyoShadhivRxebhyaH|avayave cha praaNyoShadhivRxebhyaH 4.3.135|अवयवे च प्राण्योषधिवृक्षेभ्यः|अवयवे च प्राण्योषधिवृक्षेभ्यः ४.३.१३५|४.३.१३५|४.३.१३५ अवयवे च प्राण्योषधिवृक्षेभ्यः
An affix comes after a word denoting an animal, a herb and a tree in Genitive -6th-Case in construction in the sense 'this is its part' (as well as 'this is its modification').<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-6

4.3.136|4.3.136 bilvaadibhyo.aN|bilvaadibhyo.aN|bilvaadibhyo.aN 4.3.136|बिल्वादिभ्योऽण्|बिल्वादिभ्योऽण् ४.३.१३६|४.३.१३६|४.३.१३६ बिल्वादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'its modification or its part' after the words बिल्व etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.137|4.3.137 kopadhaachcha|kopadhaachcha|kopadhaachcha 4.3.137|कोपधाच्च|कोपधाच्च ४.३.१३७|४.३.१३७|४.३.१३७ कोपधाच्च
After a word having क् as its penultimate, the affix अण् comes in the sense of modification or a part or both, as appropriate.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.138|4.3.138 trapujatunoH Shuk|trapujatunoH Shuk|trapujatunoH Shuk 4.3.138|त्रपुजतुनोः षुक्|त्रपुजतुनोः षुक् ४.३.१३८|४.३.१३८|४.३.१३८ त्रपुजतुनोः षुक्
The affix अण् with the augment षुक् comes in the sense of 'its modification' after the words त्रपुन् and जतुन्।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.139|4.3.139 oraNJ|oraNJ|oraNJ 4.3.139|ओरञ्|ओरञ् ४.३.१३९|४.३.१३९|४.३.१३९ ओरञ्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'modification or part' (provided that the word has not the अनुदात्त - grave accent on the first syllable).<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.140|4.3.140 anudaattaadeshcha|anudaattaadeshcha|anudaattaadeshcha 4.3.140|अनुदात्तादेश्च|अनुदात्तादेश्च ४.३.१४०|४.३.१४०|४.३.१४० अनुदात्तादेश्च
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of 'modification or part' after a word having अनुदात्त - grave accent on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.141|4.3.141 palaashaadibhyo vaa|palaashaadibhyo vaa|palaashaadibhyo vaa 4.3.141|पलाशादिभ्यो वा|पलाशादिभ्यो वा ४.३.१४१|४.३.१४१|४.३.१४१ पलाशादिभ्यो वा
The affix अञ् comes optionally in the sense of 'modification or part' after the words पलाश etc.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.142|4.3.142 shamyaaShTlaNJ|shamyaaShTlaNJ|shamyaaShTlaNJ 4.3.142|शम्याष्ट्लञ्|शम्याष्ट्लञ् ४.३.१४२|४.३.१४२|४.३.१४२ शम्याष्ट्लञ्
The affix ट्लञ् comes in the sense of 'modification or part' after the word शमी।<br><br>Terms: ट्लञ्

4.3.143|4.3.143 mayaDvaitayorbhaaShaayaamabhaxyaachChaadanayoH|mayaDvaitayorbhaaShaayaamabhaxyaachChaadanayoH|mayaDvaitayorbhaaShaayaamabhaxyaachChaadanayoH 4.3.143|मयड्वैतयोर्भाषायामभक्ष्याच्छादनयोः|मयड्वैतयोर्भाषायामभक्ष्याच्छादनयोः ४.३.१४३|४.३.१४३|४.३.१४३ मयड्वैतयोर्भाषायामभक्ष्याच्छादनयोः
The affix मयट् comes optionally after any base, in these two meanings of 'product' and 'part' in secular language when neither food nor clothing is spoken of.<br><br>Terms: मयट्

4.3.144|4.3.144 nityaM vRddhasharaadibhyaH|nityaM vRddhasharaadibhyaH|nityaM vRddhasharaadibhyaH 4.3.144|नित्यं वृद्धशरादिभ्यः|नित्यं वृद्धशरादिभ्यः ४.३.१४४|४.३.१४४|४.३.१४४ नित्यं वृद्धशरादिभ्यः
The affix मयट् comes in the sense of 'product' and 'part' when neither food nor clothing is spoken of, invariably after वृद्ध words and शर etc.<br><br>Terms: मयट्

4.3.145|4.3.145 goshcha puriiShe|goshcha puriiShe|goshcha puriiShe 4.3.145|गोश्च पुरीषे|गोश्च पुरीषे ४.३.१४५|४.३.१४५|४.३.१४५ गोश्च पुरीषे
The affix मयट् comes after the word गो in the sense of 'its dung'.<br><br>Terms: मयट्

4.3.146|4.3.146 piShTaachcha|piShTaachcha|piShTaachcha 4.3.146|पिष्टाच्च|पिष्टाच्च ४.३.१४६|४.३.१४६|४.३.१४६ पिष्टाच्च
The affix मयट् invariably comes in the sense of 'its product or part' after the word पिष्ट।<br><br>Terms: मयट्

4.3.147|4.3.147 saMJNaayaaM kan|saMJNaayaaM kan|saMJNaayaaM kan 4.3.147|संज्ञायां कन्|संज्ञायां कन् ४.३.१४७|४.३.१४७|४.३.१४७ संज्ञायां कन्
The affix कन् comes in the sense of 'product' after the word पिष्ट , the whole word being a Name.<br><br>Terms: कन्

4.3.148|4.3.148 vriiheH puroDaashe|vriiheH puroDaashe|vriiheH puroDaashe 4.3.148|व्रीहेः पुरोडाशे|व्रीहेः पुरोडाशे ४.३.१४८|४.३.१४८|४.३.१४८ व्रीहेः पुरोडाशे
The affix मयट् comes after the word व्रीहि in the sense of a पुरोडाश।<br><br>Terms: मयट्

4.3.149|4.3.149 asaMJNaayaaM tilayavaabhyaam‌|asaMJNaayaaM tilayavaabhyaam‌|asaMJNaayaaM tilayavaabhyaam‌ 4.3.149|असंज्ञायां तिलयवाभ्याम्‌|असंज्ञायां तिलयवाभ्याम्‌ ४.३.१४९|४.३.१४९|४.३.१४९ असंज्ञायां तिलयवाभ्याम्‌
The affix मयट् comes in the sense of 'product' after the words तिल and यवा - the whole not being a name.<br><br>Terms: मयट्

4.3.150|4.3.150 dvyachashChandasi|dvyachashChandasi|dvyachashChandasi 4.3.150|द्व्यचश्छन्दसि|द्व्यचश्छन्दसि ४.३.१५०|४.३.१५०|४.३.१५० द्व्यचश्छन्दसि
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) after a dissyllabic word the affix मयट् comes in the sense of 'product or part'.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-मयट्

4.3.151|4.3.151 notvadvardhrabilvaat‌|notvadvardhrabilvaat‌|notvadvardhrabilvaat‌ 4.3.151|नोत्वद्वर्ध्रबिल्वात्‌|नोत्वद्वर्ध्रबिल्वात्‌ ४.३.१५१|४.३.१५१|४.३.१५१ नोत्वद्वर्ध्रबिल्वात्‌
The affix मयट् does not come in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after the dissyllabic words having a short vowel उ in them, nor after the words 1. वर्ध्र and 2. बिल्वा।<br><br>Terms: छन्दस्-मयट्

4.3.152|4.3.152 taalaadibhyo.aN|taalaadibhyo.aN|taalaadibhyo.aN 4.3.152|तालादिभ्योऽण्|तालादिभ्योऽण् ४.३.१५२|४.३.१५२|४.३.१५२ तालादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'its product or part' after the words ताला etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.153|4.3.153 jaataruupebhyaH parimaaNe|jaataruupebhyaH parimaaNe|jaataruupebhyaH parimaaNe 4.3.153|जातरूपेभ्यः परिमाणे|जातरूपेभ्यः परिमाणे ४.३.१५३|४.३.१५३|४.३.१५३ जातरूपेभ्यः परिमाणे
The affix अण् comes after a word denoting 'gold' when the sense is a weight or measure.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.154|4.3.154 praaNirajataadibhyo.aNJ|praaNirajataadibhyo.aNJ|praaNirajataadibhyo.aNJ 4.3.154|प्राणिरजतादिभ्योऽञ्|प्राणिरजतादिभ्योऽञ् ४.३.१५४|४.३.१५४|४.३.१५४ प्राणिरजतादिभ्योऽञ्
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of 'product or part' after the words expressing living beings and after रजत etc.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.155|4.3.155 NJitashcha tatpratyayaat‌|NJitashcha tatpratyayaat‌|NJitashcha tatpratyayaat‌ 4.3.155|ञितश्च तत्प्रत्ययात्‌|ञितश्च तत्प्रत्ययात्‌ ४.३.१५५|४.३.१५५|४.३.१५५ ञितश्च तत्प्रत्ययात्‌
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of 'product or part' after a word which ends in an affix having an indicatory ञ् , such affix denoting 'its product or part'.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.156|4.3.156 kriitavat‌ parimaaNaat‌|kriitavat‌ parimaaNaat‌|kriitavat‌ parimaaNaat‌ 4.3.156|क्रीतवत्‌ परिमाणात्‌|क्रीतवत्‌ परिमाणात्‌ ४.३.१५६|४.३.१५६|४.३.१५६ क्रीतवत्‌ परिमाणात्‌
After a word denoting 'a measure' the affix expressing 'its product or part' is the same as the affix having the sense of 'purchased'.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

4.3.157|4.3.157 uShTraadvuNJ|uShTraadvuNJ|uShTraadvuNJ 4.3.157|उष्ट्राद्वुञ्|उष्ट्राद्वुञ् ४.३.१५७|४.३.१५७|४.३.१५७ उष्ट्राद्वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'product or part' after the word उष्ट्र।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.158|4.3.158 umorNayorvaa|umorNayorvaa|umorNayorvaa 4.3.158|उमोर्णयोर्वा|उमोर्णयोर्वा ४.३.१५८|४.३.१५८|४.३.१५८ उमोर्णयोर्वा
The affix वुञ् comes optionally in the sense of 'product or part' after the words 1. उमा and 2. ऊर्णा।<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

4.3.159|4.3.159 eNyaa DhaNJ|eNyaa DhaNJ|eNyaa DhaNJ 4.3.159|एण्या ढञ्|एण्या ढञ् ४.३.१५९|४.३.१५९|४.३.१५९ एण्या ढञ्
The affix ढञ् comes optionally in the sense of 'product or part' after the feminine word एणी।<br><br>Terms: ढञ्

4.3.160|4.3.160 gopayasoryat‌|gopayasoryat‌|gopayasoryat‌ 4.3.160|गोपयसोर्यत्‌|गोपयसोर्यत्‌ ४.३.१६०|४.३.१६०|४.३.१६० गोपयसोर्यत्‌
The affix यत् comes in the sense of 'product or part' after the words 1. गो and 2. पयस्।<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.3.161|4.3.161 droshcha|droshcha|droshcha 4.3.161|द्रोश्च|द्रोश्च ४.३.१६१|४.३.१६१|४.३.१६१ द्रोश्च
The affix यत् comes in the sense of 'product or part' after the word द्रु।<br><br>Terms: यत्

4.3.162|4.3.162 maane vayaH|maane vayaH|maane vayaH 4.3.162|माने वयः|माने वयः ४.३.१६२|४.३.१६२|४.३.१६२ माने वयः
The affix वय comes in the sense of 'product' after the word द्रु , the word meaning 'a measure'.<br><br>Terms: वय

4.3.163|4.3.163 phale luk|phale luk|phale luk 4.3.163|फले लुक्|फले लुक् ४.३.१६३|४.३.१६३|४.३.१६३ फले लुक्
The affix denoting 'product or part' is लुक् elided when such a product or part is 'a fruit'.<br><br>Terms: लुक्

4.3.164|4.3.164 plaxaadibhyo.aN|plaxaadibhyo.aN|plaxaadibhyo.aN 4.3.164|प्लक्षादिभ्योऽण्|प्लक्षादिभ्योऽण् ४.३.१६४|४.३.१६४|४.३.१६४ प्लक्षादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'product or part, it being a fruit' after the words प्लक्ष etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.165|4.3.165 jambvaa vaa|jambvaa vaa|jambvaa vaa 4.3.165|जम्ब्वा वा|जम्ब्वा वा ४.३.१६५|४.३.१६५|४.३.१६५ जम्ब्वा वा
The affix अण् optionally comes in denoting a fruit after the word जम्बु।<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.3.166|4.3.166 lup cha|lup cha|lup cha 4.3.166|लुप् च|लुप् च ४.३.१६६|४.३.१६६|४.३.१६६ लुप् च
The affix denoting 'fruit' is optionally elided by लुप् after the word जम्बु।<br><br>Terms: लुप्

4.3.167|4.3.167 hariitakyaadibhyashcha|hariitakyaadibhyashcha|hariitakyaadibhyashcha 4.3.167|हरीतक्यादिभ्यश्च|हरीतक्यादिभ्यश्च ४.३.१६७|४.३.१६७|४.३.१६७ हरीतक्यादिभ्यश्च
The affix denoting 'fruit' is elided by लुप् after the words हरीतकी etc.<br><br>Terms: लुप्

4.3.168|4.3.168 kaMsiiyaparashavyayoryaNJaNJau luk cha|kaMsiiyaparashavyayoryaNJaNJau luk cha|kaMsiiyaparashavyayoryaNJaNJau luk cha 4.3.168|कंसीयपरशव्ययोर्यञञौ लुक् च|कंसीयपरशव्ययोर्यञञौ लुक् च ४.३.१६८|४.३.१६८|४.३.१६८ कंसीयपरशव्ययोर्यञञौ लुक् च
The affixes यञ् and अञ् come respectively in the sense of 'its product' after the words 1. कंसीय and 2. परशव्य and there is लुक् elision (of the छ and यत् affixes of those words).<br><br>Terms: यञ् and अञ्

4.4.1|4.4.1 praagvahateShThak|praagvahateShThak|praagvahateShThak 4.4.1|प्राग्वहतेष्ठक्|प्राग्वहतेष्ठक् ४.४.१|४.४.१|४.४.१ प्राग्वहतेष्ठक्
The affix ठक् comes as a governing affix in the senses enumerated hereafter up to sūtra ४.४.७६.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.4.2|4.4.2 tena diivyati khanati jayati jitam|tena diivyati khanati jayati jitam|tena diivyati khanati jayati jitam 4.4.2|तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम्|तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम् ४.४.२|४.४.२|४.४.२ तेन दीव्यति खनति जयति जितम्
The affix ठक् comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense of 'he plays', 'he digs', 'he conquers' or 'he is conquered'.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.4.3|4.4.3 saMskRtam|saMskRtam|saMskRtam 4.4.3|संस्कृतम्|संस्कृतम् ४.४.३|४.४.३|४.४.३ संस्कृतम्
The affix ठक् comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction, in the sense of 'refined thereby'.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.4.4|4.4.4 kulatthakopadhaadaN|kulatthakopadhaadaN|kulatthakopadhaadaN 4.4.4|कुलत्थकोपधादण्|कुलत्थकोपधादण् ४.४.४|४.४.४|४.४.४ कुलत्थकोपधादण्
After the word कुलत्थ and after the words having a penultimate क् , the affix अण् is added in the sense of 'refined or prepared therewith'.<br><br>Terms: अण्

4.4.5|4.4.5 tarati|tarati|tarati 4.4.5|तरति|तरति ४.४.५|४.४.५|४.४.५ तरति
The affix ठक् comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction, in the sense of 'he crosses thereby over the waters'.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.4.6|4.4.6 gopuchChaaTThaNJ|gopuchChaaTThaNJ|gopuchChaaTThaNJ 4.4.6|गोपुच्छाट्ठञ्|गोपुच्छाट्ठञ् ४.४.६|४.४.६|४.४.६ गोपुच्छाट्ठञ्
The affix ठञ् comes after the word गोपुच्छ in the sense of 'he crosses thereby'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.4.7|4.4.7 naudvyachaShThan|naudvyachaShThan|naudvyachaShThan 4.4.7|नौद्व्यचष्ठन्|नौद्व्यचष्ठन् ४.४.७|४.४.७|४.४.७ नौद्व्यचष्ठन्
The affix ठञ् comes after the word नौ and after bases having two syllables in the sense of 'he crosses therewith'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

4.4.8|4.4.8 charati|charati|charati 4.4.8|चरति|चरति ४.४.८|४.४.८|४.४.८ चरति
After a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction comes the affix ठक् in the sense of 'he goes on by means thereof'.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.4.9|4.4.9 aakarShaat ShThal|aakarShaat ShThal|aakarShaat ShThal 4.4.9|आकर्षात् ष्ठल्|आकर्षात् ष्ठल् ४.४.९|४.४.९|४.४.९ आकर्षात् ष्ठल्
The affix ष्ठल् comes in the sense of 'he goes on by means thereof' after the word आकर्ष।<br><br>Terms: ष्ठल्

4.4.10|4.4.10 parpaadibhyaH ShThan|parpaadibhyaH ShThan|parpaadibhyaH ShThan 4.4.10|पर्पादिभ्यः ष्ठन्|पर्पादिभ्यः ष्ठन् ४.४.१०|४.४.१०|४.४.१० पर्पादिभ्यः ष्ठन्
The affix ष्ठन् comes in the sense of 'he goes on, by means thereof' after the words पर्प etc.<br><br>Terms: ष्ठन्

4.4.11|4.4.11 shvagaNaaTThanca|shvagaNaaTThanca|shvagaNaaTThanca 4.4.11|श्वगणाट्ठञ्च|श्वगणाट्ठञ्च ४.४.११|४.४.११|४.४.११ श्वगणाट्ठञ्च
The affixes ठञ् and ष्ठन् , come after the word श्वगण , in the sense of 'he goes by means thereof'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ् and ष्ठन्

4.4.12|4.4.12 vetanaadibhyo jiivati|vetanaadibhyo jiivati|vetanaadibhyo jiivati 4.4.12|वेतनादिभ्यो जीवति|वेतनादिभ्यो जीवति ४.४.१२|४.४.१२|४.४.१२ वेतनादिभ्यो जीवति
The affix ठक् comes in the sense of 'he lives thereby' after the words वेतन etc. being in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction.<br><br>Terms: ठक्

4.4.13|4.4.13 vasnakrayavikrayaaTThan|vasnakrayavikrayaaTThan|vasnakrayavikrayaaTThan 4.4.13|वस्नक्रयविक्रयाट्ठन्|वस्नक्रयविक्रयाट्ठन् ४.४.१३|४.४.१३|४.४.१३ वस्नक्रयविक्रयाट्ठन्
The affix ठन् comes in the sense of 'he lives thereby' after the words 1. वस्न 2. क्रय and 3. विक्रय being in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction.<br><br>Terms: ठन्

4.4.14|4.4.14 aayudhaachCha cha|aayudhaachCha cha|aayudhaachCha cha 4.4.14|आयुधाच्छ च|आयुधाच्छ च ४.४.१४|४.४.१४|४.४.१४ आयुधाच्छ च
The affixes छ and ठन् come in the sense of 'he conveys thereby' after the word आयुध।<br><br>Terms: छ and ठन्

4.4.15|4.4.15 haratyutsangaadibhyaH|haratyutsangaadibhyaH|haratyutsangaadibhyaH 4.4.15|हरत्युत्सङ्गादिभ्यः|हरत्युत्सङ्गादिभ्यः ४.४.१५|४.४.१५|४.४.१५ हरत्युत्सङ्गादिभ्यः
