5.1.16|5.1.16 tadasya tadasmin syaaditi|tadasya tadasmin syaaditi|tadasya tadasmin syaaditi 5.1.16|तदस्य तदस्मिन् स्यादिति|तदस्य तदस्मिन् स्यादिति ५.१.१६|५.१.१६|५.१.१६ तदस्य तदस्मिन् स्यादिति
The above mentioned affixes come after a word in the first case in construction, with the force of a genitive or locative, when the word in the first case is agent of the verb स्यत् ; in other words - the above-mentioned affixes have also the senses of 'very well sufficient there to' and 'very well sufficient to be made therein'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.17|5.1.17 parikhaayaa DhaNJ|parikhaayaa DhaNJ|parikhaayaa DhaNJ 5.1.17|परिखाया ढञ्|परिखाया ढञ् ५.१.१७|५.१.१७|५.१.१७ परिखाया ढञ्
The affix ढञ् (+/- एय) comes after the word परिखा in the above senses of 'this is sufficient for that' and 'this is sufficient therein'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.18|5.1.18 praagvateShThaNJ|praagvateShThaNJ|praagvateShThaNJ 5.1.18|प्राग्वतेष्ठञ्|प्राग्वतेष्ठञ् ५.१.१८|५.१.१८|५.१.१८ प्राग्वतेष्ठञ्
Up to sutra ५.१.११५ (excluding that) the affix ठञ् (+/- इक or +/- क) bears rule.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.19|5.1.19 aarhaadagopuchChasaMkhyaaparimaaNaaTThak|aarhaadagopuchChasaMkhyaaparimaaNaaTThak|aarhaadagopuchChasaMkhyaaparimaaNaaTThak 5.1.19|आर्हादगोपुच्छसंख्यापरिमाणाट्ठक्|आर्हादगोपुच्छसंख्यापरिमाणाट्ठक् ५.१.१९|५.१.१९|५.१.१९ आर्हादगोपुच्छसंख्यापरिमाणाट्ठक्
Up to sutra ५.१.६३, inclusive, the affix ठक् (+/- इक or +/- क)<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.20|5.1.20 asamaase niShkaadibhyaH|asamaase niShkaadibhyaH|asamaase niShkaadibhyaH 5.1.20|असमासे निष्कादिभ्यः|असमासे निष्कादिभ्यः ५.१.२०|५.१.२०|५.१.२० असमासे निष्कादिभ्यः
The affix ठक् comes after the words निष्क etc., when they are not parts of a compound, the sense of the affix being that taught in the subsequent sutras up to ५.१.६३.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.21|5.1.21 shataachcha Thanyataavashate|shataachcha Thanyataavashate|shataachcha Thanyataavashate 5.1.21|शताच्च ठन्यतावशते|शताच्च ठन्यतावशते ५.१.२१|५.१.२१|५.१.२१ शताच्च ठन्यतावशते
The affixes ठन् (-/- इक) and यत् (-/य) come in the senses taught up to ५.१.६३ after the word शत् , when it is not part of a compound and when it does not mean merely 'hundred'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.22|5.1.22 saMkhyaayaa atishadantaayaaH kan|saMkhyaayaa atishadantaayaaH kan|saMkhyaayaa atishadantaayaaH kan 5.1.22|संख्याया अतिशदन्तायाः कन्|संख्याया अतिशदन्तायाः कन् ५.१.२२|५.१.२२|५.१.२२ संख्याया अतिशदन्तायाः कन्
The affix (-/- -क) comes after a Numeral, when it does not end with ति or शत् , in the sense of the affix being that taught hereafter up to ५.१.६३<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.23|5.1.23 vatoriDvaa|vatoriDvaa|vatoriDvaa 5.1.23|वतोरिड्वा|वतोरिड्वा ५.१.२३|५.१.२३|५.१.२३ वतोरिड्वा
The affix कन् coming after a Numeral ending with वत्, takes optionally the augment इद् , the sense of the affix being those given up to ५.१.६३<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.24|5.1.24 viMshatitriMshadbhyaaM DvunnasaMJNaayaam‌|viMshatitriMshadbhyaaM DvunnasaMJNaayaam‌|viMshatitriMshadbhyaaM DvunnasaMJNaayaam‌ 5.1.24|विंशतित्रिंशद्भ्यां ड्वुन्नसंज्ञायाम्‌|विंशतित्रिंशद्भ्यां ड्वुन्नसंज्ञायाम्‌ ५.१.२४|५.१.२४|५.१.२४ विंशतित्रिंशद्भ्यां ड्वुन्नसंज्ञायाम्‌
The affix डुवन् (-/- -अक) comes in the senses taught up to ५.१.६३ after the words विंशति and त्रिंशत् , when it does not denote a Name: the ति and अत् of the base being dropped before this affix.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.25|5.1.25 kaMsaaTTiThan|kaMsaaTTiThan|kaMsaaTTiThan 5.1.25|कंसाट्टिठन्|कंसाट्टिठन् ५.१.२५|५.१.२५|५.१.२५ कंसाट्टिठन्
