5.1.28|5.1.28 adhyardhapuurvadvigorlugasaMJNaayaam|adhyardhapuurvadvigorlugasaMJNaayaam|adhyardhapuurvadvigorlugasaMJNaayaam 5.1.28|अध्यर्धपूर्वद्विगोर्लुगसंज्ञायाम्|अध्यर्धपूर्वद्विगोर्लुगसंज्ञायाम् ५.१.२८|५.१.२८|५.१.२८ अध्यर्धपूर्वद्विगोर्लुगसंज्ञायाम्
The affix having the senses taught up to ५.१.६३, is elided by लुक् after a stem beginning with the word अध्यर्ध , and after a द्विगु compound, when it is not in a name.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.29|5.1.29 vibhaaShaa kaarShaapaNasahasraabhyaam|vibhaaShaa kaarShaapaNasahasraabhyaam|vibhaaShaa kaarShaapaNasahasraabhyaam 5.1.29|विभाषा कार्षापणसहस्राभ्याम्|विभाषा कार्षापणसहस्राभ्याम् ५.१.२९|५.१.२९|५.१.२९ विभाषा कार्षापणसहस्राभ्याम्
The affix having the senses taught up to ५.१.६३, is not always संख्या। Thus for the purpose of application of the affix कृत्वसूच् ५.४.१७, this word is not a संख्या।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.30|5.1.30 dvitripuurvaanniShkaat‌|dvitripuurvaanniShkaat‌|dvitripuurvaanniShkaat‌ 5.1.30|द्वित्रिपूर्वान्निष्कात्‌|द्वित्रिपूर्वान्निष्कात्‌ ५.१.३०|५.१.३०|५.१.३० द्वित्रिपूर्वान्निष्कात्‌
The आर्हीय affix ५.१.६३ is optionally elided after a द्विगु occasioning compound, of the word निष्क preceded by द्वि and त्रि।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.31|5.1.31 bistaachcha|bistaachcha|bistaachcha 5.1.31|बिस्ताच्च|बिस्ताच्च ५.१.३१|५.१.३१|५.१.३१ बिस्ताच्च
The आर्हीय affix ५.१.३७-63 occasioning a द्विगु compound, is optionally elided after the word बिस्त preceded by द्वि and त्रि।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.32|5.1.32 viMshatikaat‌ khaH|viMshatikaat‌ khaH|viMshatikaat‌ khaH 5.1.32|विंशतिकात्‌ खः|विंशतिकात्‌ खः ५.१.३२|५.१.३२|५.१.३२ विंशतिकात्‌ खः
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the आर्हीय senses ५.१.३७-63 after the word विंशतिक , when preceded by the word अध्यर्द्ध or a Numeral, occasioning a द्विगु।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.33|5.1.33 khaaryaa iikan|khaaryaa iikan|khaaryaa iikan 5.1.33|खार्या ईकन्|खार्या ईकन् ५.१.३३|५.१.३३|५.१.३३ खार्या ईकन्
The affix ईकन् (-/- -ईक) comes in the आर्हीय senses ५.१.३७-63 after the word खारी , when preceded by the word अध्यर्ध or a Numeral occasioning a द्विगु।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.34|5.1.34 paNapaadamaaShashataadat‌|paNapaadamaaShashataadat‌|paNapaadamaaShashataadat‌ 5.1.34|पणपादमाषशतादत्‌|पणपादमाषशतादत्‌ ५.१.३४|५.१.३४|५.१.३४ पणपादमाषशतादत्‌
The affix यत् (य) comes in the आर्हीय senses ५.१.३७-63 after the words पण, माष and शत , when preceded by the word अध्यर्ध or a Numeral occasioning a द्विगु।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.35|5.1.35 shaaNaadvaa|shaaNaadvaa|shaaNaadvaa 5.1.35|शाणाद्वा|शाणाद्वा ५.१.३५|५.१.३५|५.१.३५ शाणाद्वा
The affix यत् comes optionally after the word शन, in the आर्हीय-senses ५.१.६३, when it is preceded by the word अध्यर्ध or a Numeral occasioning a द्विगु।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.36|5.1.36 dvitripuurvaadaN cha|dvitripuurvaadaN cha|dvitripuurvaadaN cha 5.1.36|द्वित्रिपूर्वादण् च|द्वित्रिपूर्वादण् च ५.१.३६|५.१.३६|५.१.३६ द्वित्रिपूर्वादण् च
The affix अण् (-/- -अ) as well as यत् optionally also comes after the word शाण , in the आर्हीय-senses ५.१.३७-63, when preced by the words द्वि and त्रि।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.37|5.1.37 tena kriitam|tena kriitam|tena kriitam 5.1.37|तेन क्रीतम्|तेन क्रीतम् ५.१.३७|५.१.३७|५.१.३७ तेन क्रीतम्
The thirteen affixes taught in ५.१.१८-36 have the sense of 'purchased with this price' and are added to a word in the third case in construction.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.38|5.1.38 tasya nimittaM saMyogotpaatau|tasya nimittaM saMyogotpaatau|tasya nimittaM saMyogotpaatau 5.1.38|तस्य निमित्तं संयोगोत्पातौ|तस्य निमित्तं संयोगोत्पातौ ५.१.३८|५.१.३८|५.१.३८ तस्य निमित्तं संयोगोत्पातौ
The above affixes have further the sense of 'for its sake', when the meaning is a relation or an unwanted appearance.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.39|5.1.39 godvyachorasaMkhyaaparimaaNaashvaaderyat‌|godvyachorasaMkhyaaparimaaNaashvaaderyat‌|godvyachorasaMkhyaaparimaaNaashvaaderyat‌ 5.1.39|गोद्व्यचोरसंख्यापरिमाणाश्वादेर्यत्‌|गोद्व्यचोरसंख्यापरिमाणाश्वादेर्यत्‌ ५.१.३९|५.१.३९|५.१.३९ गोद्व्यचोरसंख्यापरिमाणाश्वादेर्यत्‌
After the word गो and after a word having two syllables, with the exception of a Numeral, or a Measure of capacity or अश्व etc., the affix यत् (य) is added, in the above sense of 'a relation or a portent for the purpose of that'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.40|5.1.40 putraachCha cha|putraachCha cha|putraachCha cha 5.1.40|पुत्राच्छ च|पुत्राच्छ च ५.१.४०|५.१.४०|५.१.४० पुत्राच्छ च
After the word पुत्र the affix छ (ईय) also comes, as well as यत् (य), in the above sense of 'a relation or a portent for the purpose of that'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.41|5.1.41 sarvabhuumipRthiviibhyaamaNaNJau|sarvabhuumipRthiviibhyaamaNaNJau|sarvabhuumipRthiviibhyaamaNaNJau 5.1.41|सर्वभूमिपृथिवीभ्यामणञौ|सर्वभूमिपृथिवीभ्यामणञौ ५.१.४१|५.१.४१|५.१.४१ सर्वभूमिपृथिवीभ्यामणञौ
The affixes अण् (+/- -अ) and अञ् (+/- -अ) are respectively added to the words सार्वभूमि and पृथ्वी , in the above mentioned sense of 'a connection or a portent for its purpose'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.42|5.1.42 tasyeshvaraH|tasyeshvaraH|tasyeshvaraH 5.1.42|तस्येश्वरः|तस्येश्वरः ५.१.४२|५.१.४२|५.१.४२ तस्येश्वरः
To the same bases सार्वभूमि and पृथ्वी , are added the same affixes अण् and अञ् respectively, in the sense of 'lord thereof'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.43|5.1.43 tatra vidita iti cha|tatra vidita iti cha|tatra vidita iti cha 5.1.43|तत्र विदित इति च|तत्र विदित इति च ५.१.४३|५.१.४३|५.१.४३ तत्र विदित इति च
To the same bases सार्वभूमि and पृथ्वी , being in the 7th case in construction, are added the same affixes अण् and अञ् respectively, in the sense that of 'known therein'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.44|5.1.44 lokasarvalokaaTThaNJ|lokasarvalokaaTThaNJ|lokasarvalokaaTThaNJ 5.1.44|लोकसर्वलोकाट्ठञ्|लोकसर्वलोकाट्ठञ् ५.१.४४|५.१.४४|५.१.४४ लोकसर्वलोकाट्ठञ्
The affix ठञ् (+/- इक) comes in the sense of 'known therein' after the words लोक and सर्वलोक , in the 7th case in construction.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.45|5.1.45 tasya vaapaH|tasya vaapaH|tasya vaapaH 5.1.45|तस्य वापः|तस्य वापः ५.१.४५|५.१.४५|५.१.४५ तस्य वापः
The above mentioned affixes ५.१.१८ etc. come after a word in the 6th-Case in construction, in the sense of 'sown with so much'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.46|5.1.46 paatraat ShThan|paatraat ShThan|paatraat ShThan 5.1.46|पात्रात् ष्ठन्|पात्रात् ष्ठन् ५.१.४६|५.१.४६|५.१.४६ पात्रात् ष्ठन्
The affix ष्ठान् (-/- इक) comes in the sense of 'sown with so much' after the word पात्र।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.47|5.1.47 tadasmin vRddhyaayalaabhashulkopadaa diiyate|tadasmin vRddhyaayalaabhashulkopadaa diiyate|tadasmin vRddhyaayalaabhashulkopadaa diiyate 5.1.47|तदस्मिन् वृद्ध्यायलाभशुल्कोपदा दीयते|तदस्मिन् वृद्ध्यायलाभशुल्कोपदा दीयते ५.१.४७|५.१.४७|५.१.४७ तदस्मिन् वृद्ध्यायलाभशुल्कोपदा दीयते
The above mentioned affixes have also the sense of 'an interest, or a rent, or a profit, or a tax,or a bribe given thereby or in that'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.48|5.1.48 puuraNaardhaaTThan|puuraNaardhaaTThan|puuraNaardhaaTThan 5.1.48|पूरणार्धाट्ठन्|पूरणार्धाट्ठन् ५.१.४८|५.१.४८|५.१.४८ पूरणार्धाट्ठन्
The affix ठञ् (+/- इक) comes in the same sense of 'an interest, or a rent, or a profit, or a tax,or a bribe given thereby or therein' after a word denoting an ordinal and after the word अर्ध।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.49|5.1.49 bhaagaadyachcha|bhaagaadyachcha|bhaagaadyachcha 5.1.49|भागाद्यच्च|भागाद्यच्च ५.१.४९|५.१.४९|५.१.४९ भागाद्यच्च
The affix यत् (य) comes after the word भाग in the sense of 'an interest, or a rent, or a profit, or a tax,or a bribe given thereby or therein'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.50|5.1.50 taddharati vahatyaavahati bhaaraadvaMshaadibhyaH|taddharati vahatyaavahati bhaaraadvaMshaadibhyaH|taddharati vahatyaavahati bhaaraadvaMshaadibhyaH 5.1.50|तद्धरति वहत्यावहति भाराद्वंशादिभ्यः|तद्धरति वहत्यावहति भाराद्वंशादिभ्यः ५.१.५०|५.१.५०|५.१.५० तद्धरति वहत्यावहति भाराद्वंशादिभ्यः
The above mentioned affixes after the word भार preceded by the word वंश etc., have the sense of 'who carries away, or conveys or brings that'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.51|5.1.51 vasnadravyaabhyaaM Thankanau|vasnadravyaabhyaaM Thankanau|vasnadravyaabhyaaM Thankanau 5.1.51|वस्नद्रव्याभ्यां ठन्कनौ|वस्नद्रव्याभ्यां ठन्कनौ ५.१.५१|५.१.५१|५.१.५१ वस्नद्रव्याभ्यां ठन्कनौ
The affix ठन् (-/- -इक्) and कन् (-/- क) come respectively after the words वसन and द्रव्य , in the 2nd case in construction, in the same sense of 'who carries etc.'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.52|5.1.52 sambhavatyavaharati pachati|sambhavatyavaharati pachati|sambhavatyavaharati pachati 5.1.52|सम्भवत्यवहरति पचति|सम्भवत्यवहरति पचति ५.१.५२|५.१.५२|५.१.५२ सम्भवत्यवहरति पचति
The above mentioned affixes have also the sense of 'what is capable of holding that, or takes away that, or cooks that'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.53|5.1.53 aaDhakaachitapaatraat‌ kho.anyatarayaam|aaDhakaachitapaatraat‌ kho.anyatarayaam|aaDhakaachitapaatraat‌ kho.anyatarayaam 5.1.53|आढकाचितपात्रात्‌ खोऽन्यतरयाम्|आढकाचितपात्रात्‌ खोऽन्यतरयाम् ५.१.५३|५.१.५३|५.१.५३ आढकाचितपात्रात्‌ खोऽन्यतरयाम्
The affix ख (ईन) may optionally be added in the above sense of 'being capable of holding etc.' after the words आढक, आचित and पात्र।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.54|5.1.54 dvigoShThaMshcha|dvigoShThaMshcha|dvigoShThaMshcha 5.1.54|द्विगोष्ठंश्च|द्विगोष्ठंश्च ५.१.५४|५.१.५४|५.१.५४ द्विगोष्ठंश्च
The affix ष्ठान् (-/- इक) as well as the affix affix ख (ईन) may optionally come after the same words आढक, आचित and पात्र being final of a द्विगु compound, the sense being that of 'what can hold etc.'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.55|5.1.55 kulijaallukkhau cha|kulijaallukkhau cha|kulijaallukkhau cha 5.1.55|कुलिजाल्लुक्खौ च|कुलिजाल्लुक्खौ च ५.१.५५|५.१.५५|५.१.५५ कुलिजाल्लुक्खौ च
After the word कुलिज , being final of a द्विगु , there is optionally the elision of the above affixes, or the adding of the affix ख (इन), in the sense of 'what can hold that etc.'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.56|5.1.56 so.asyaaMshavasnabhRtayaH|so.asyaaMshavasnabhRtayaH|so.asyaaMshavasnabhRtayaH 5.1.56|सोऽस्यांशवस्नभृतयः|सोऽस्यांशवस्नभृतयः ५.१.५६|५.१.५६|५.१.५६ सोऽस्यांशवस्नभृतयः
The affixes taught in प्राग्वतेष्ठञ् ५.१.१८ etc. have also the sense of 'this is his portion, price or pay'.<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.57|5.1.57 tadasya parimaaNam|tadasya parimaaNam|tadasya parimaaNam 5.1.57|तदस्य परिमाणम्|तदस्य परिमाणम् ५.१.५७|५.१.५७|५.१.५७ तदस्य परिमाणम्
The affixes taught in प्राग्वतेष्ठञ् ५.१.१८ etc. have the sense of 'this is its measure'.<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.58|5.1.58 saMkhyaayaaH saMJNaasaMghasuutraadhyayaneShu|saMkhyaayaaH saMJNaasaMghasuutraadhyayaneShu|saMkhyaayaaH saMJNaasaMghasuutraadhyayaneShu 5.1.58|संख्यायाः संज्ञासंघसूत्राध्ययनेषु|संख्यायाः संज्ञासंघसूत्राध्ययनेषु ५.१.५८|५.१.५८|५.१.५८ संख्यायाः संज्ञासंघसूत्राध्ययनेषु
The affixes प्राग्वतेष्ठञ् ५.१.१८ etc. come after a word denoting a numeral in the sense of 'this is its measure when the word so formed means a Name, a Multitude, a Book or a fixed way and mode of study.<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.59|5.1.59 panktiviMshatitriMshatchatvaariMshatpancaashatShaShTisaptatyashiitinavatishatam|panktiviMshatitriMshatchatvaariMshatpancaashatShaShTisaptatyashiitinavatishatam|panktiviMshatitriMshatchatvaariMshatpancaashatShaShTisaptatyashiitinavatishatam 5.1.59|पङ्क्तिविंशतित्रिंशत्चत्वारिंशत्पञ्चाशत्षष्टिसप्तत्यशीतिनवतिशतम्|पङ्क्तिविंशतित्रिंशत्चत्वारिंशत्पञ्चाशत्षष्टिसप्तत्यशीतिनवतिशतम् ५.१.५९|५.१.५९|५.१.५९ पङ्क्तिविंशतित्रिंशत्चत्वारिंशत्पञ्चाशत्षष्टिसप्तत्यशीतिनवतिशतम्
The following words are anomalous - 1. पङ्क्ति 'a verse' 2. विंशति 'twenty' 3. त्रिंशत् 'thirty' 4.चत्वारिंशत् 'forty' 5. पञ्चाशत् 'fifty' 6. षष्टि 'sixty' 7. सप्तति 'seventy' 8. अशीति 'eighty' 9. नवति 'ninety' 10. शतम् 'hundred'.<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.60|5.1.60 pancaddashatau varge vaa|pancaddashatau varge vaa|pancaddashatau varge vaa 5.1.60|पञ्चद्दशतौ वर्गे वा|पञ्चद्दशतौ वर्गे वा ५.१.६०|५.१.६०|५.१.६० पञ्चद्दशतौ वर्गे वा
The words 1. पञ्चत् and 2. दशत् in combination with वर्ग may be anomalously so formed, in the sense of 'this is its measure'.<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.61|5.1.61 saptano.aNJ Chandasi|saptano.aNJ Chandasi|saptano.aNJ Chandasi 5.1.61|सप्तनोऽञ् छन्दसि|सप्तनोऽञ् छन्दसि ५.१.६१|५.१.६१|५.१.६१ सप्तनोऽञ् छन्दसि
The affix अञ् (+/- अ) comes after the word सप्तन् in the छन्दस् (Vedas) when the meaning is that of a वर्ग।<br><br>Terms: अञ्

5.1.62|5.1.62 triMshachchatvaariMshatorbraahmaNe saMJNaayaaM DaN|triMshachchatvaariMshatorbraahmaNe saMJNaayaaM DaN|triMshachchatvaariMshatorbraahmaNe saMJNaayaaM DaN 5.1.62|त्रिंशच्चत्वारिंशतोर्ब्राह्मणे संज्ञायां डण्|त्रिंशच्चत्वारिंशतोर्ब्राह्मणे संज्ञायां डण् ५.१.६२|५.१.६२|५.१.६२ त्रिंशच्चत्वारिंशतोर्ब्राह्मणे संज्ञायां डण्
The affix अञ् (+/- अ) comes in the sense of 'this is its measure' after the words 1. त्रिंशत् and 2. चत्वारिशत् when it is a Name denoting a ब्राहमण-book.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

5.1.63|5.1.63 tad arhati|tad arhati|tad arhati 5.1.63|तद् अर्हति|तद् अर्हति ५.१.६३|५.१.६३|५.१.६३ तद् अर्हति
