5.1.76|5.1.76 pantho Na nityam|pantho Na nityam|pantho Na nityam 5.1.76|पन्थो ण नित्यम्|पन्थो ण नित्यम् ५.१.७६|५.१.७६|५.१.७६ पन्थो ण नित्यम्
The affix ण comes after the word पन्थ which becomes the substitute of पथिन्, the sense of the affix being 'who always goes'.<br><br>Terms: ण

5.1.77|5.1.77 uttarapathenaahRtaM cha|uttarapathenaahRtaM cha|uttarapathenaahRtaM cha 5.1.77|उत्तरपथेनाहृतं च|उत्तरपथेनाहृतं च ५.१.७७|५.१.७७|५.१.७७ उत्तरपथेनाहृतं च
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'who passes by that way' and 'what is conveyed by that way' after the word उत्तरपथ in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.78|5.1.78 kaalaat‌|kaalaat‌|kaalaat‌ 5.1.78|कालात्‌|कालात्‌ ५.१.७८|५.१.७८|५.१.७८ कालात्‌
In the following sūtras the phrase 'after a word denoting time' should be supplied to complete the sense.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.79|5.1.79 tena nirvRttam|tena nirvRttam|tena nirvRttam 5.1.79|तेन निर्वृत्तम्|तेन निर्वृत्तम् ५.१.७९|५.१.७९|५.१.७९ तेन निर्वृत्तम्
The affix ठञ् comes after a word denoting time in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense of 'to be accomplished by that time'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.80|5.1.80 tamadhiiShTo bhRto bhuuto bhaavii|tamadhiiShTo bhRto bhuuto bhaavii|tamadhiiShTo bhRto bhuuto bhaavii 5.1.80|तमधीष्टो भृतो भूतो भावी|तमधीष्टो भृतो भूतो भावी ५.१.८०|५.१.८०|५.१.८० तमधीष्टो भृतो भूतो भावी
The above affixes come after a word expressing time in the Accusative -2nd case in construction in the senses of 'solicited to instruct for such a period or which will last so long'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.81|5.1.81 maasaadvayasi yatkhaNJau|maasaadvayasi yatkhaNJau|maasaadvayasi yatkhaNJau 5.1.81|मासाद्वयसि यत्खञौ|मासाद्वयसि यत्खञौ ५.१.८१|५.१.८१|५.१.८१ मासाद्वयसि यत्खञौ
The affixes यत् and खञ् come after the word मास in denoting 'age'.<br><br>Terms: यत् and खञ्

5.1.82|5.1.82 dvigoryap‌|dvigoryap‌|dvigoryap‌ 5.1.82|द्विगोर्यप्‌|द्विगोर्यप्‌ ५.१.८२|५.१.८२|५.१.८२ द्विगोर्यप्‌
The affix यप् comes after the word मास when forming a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) and meaning 'age'.<br><br>Terms: यप्

5.1.83|5.1.83 ShaNmaasaaNNyachcha|ShaNmaasaaNNyachcha|ShaNmaasaaNNyachcha 5.1.83|षण्मासाण्ण्यच्च|षण्मासाण्ण्यच्च ५.१.८३|५.१.८३|५.१.८३ षण्मासाण्ण्यच्च
The affixes ण्त् , यप् and ठञ् comes in the sense of 'age' after the word षण्मास।<br><br>Terms: ण्त् , यप् and ठञ्

5.1.84|5.1.84 avayasi ThaMshcha|avayasi ThaMshcha|avayasi ThaMshcha 5.1.84|अवयसि ठंश्च|अवयसि ठंश्च ५.१.८४|५.१.८४|५.१.८४ अवयसि ठंश्च
The affix ठन् comes after the word षण्मास when 'age' is Not meant.<br><br>Terms: ठन्

5.1.85|5.1.85 samaayaaH khaH|samaayaaH khaH|samaayaaH khaH 5.1.85|समायाः खः|समायाः खः ५.१.८५|५.१.८५|५.१.८५ समायाः खः
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the four-fold senses of 'solicited', 'hired', 'lasted' and 'will last', after the word समा।<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.86|5.1.86 dvigorvaa|dvigorvaa|dvigorvaa 5.1.86|द्विगोर्वा|द्विगोर्वा ५.१.८६|५.१.८६|५.१.८६ द्विगोर्वा
The affix ख (ईन) comes optionally in the senses taught in पन्थो ण नित्यम् ५.१.७६, तमधीष्टो भृतो भूतो भावी ५.१.८० after the word समा , forming a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound).<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.87|5.1.87 raatryahassaMvatsaraachcha|raatryahassaMvatsaraachcha|raatryahassaMvatsaraachcha 5.1.87|रात्र्यहस्संवत्सराच्च|रात्र्यहस्संवत्सराच्च ५.१.८७|५.१.८७|५.१.८७ रात्र्यहस्संवत्सराच्च
The affix ख optionally in the senses taught in तेन निर्वृत्तम् ५.१.७९, द्विगोर्यप्‌ ५.१.८२, after the words 1. रात्री 2. अहन् and 3. सम्वत्सर , occasioning a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound).<br><br>Terms: ख

5.1.88|5.1.88 varShaalluk cha|varShaalluk cha|varShaalluk cha 5.1.88|वर्षाल्लुक् च|वर्षाल्लुक् च ५.१.८८|५.१.८८|५.१.८८ वर्षाल्लुक् च
The above affixes and ख and ठिञ् may also be elided after a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) ending in वर्षा।<br><br>Terms: ख and ठिञ्

5.1.89|5.1.89 chittavati nityam|chittavati nityam|chittavati nityam 5.1.89|चित्तवति नित्यम्|चित्तवति नित्यम् ५.१.८९|५.१.८९|५.१.८९ चित्तवति नित्यम्
The affixes meaning 'accomplished' etc. पन्थो ण नित्यम् ५.१.७६, तमधीष्टो भृतो भूतो भावी ५.१.८० are necessarily elided after the word वर्षा forming a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) when it refers to being endowed with reason.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.90|5.1.90 ShaShTikaaH ShaShTiraatreNa pachyante|ShaShTikaaH ShaShTiraatreNa pachyante|ShaShTikaaH ShaShTiraatreNa pachyante 5.1.90|षष्टिकाः षष्टिरात्रेण पच्यन्ते|षष्टिकाः षष्टिरात्रेण पच्यन्ते ५.१.९०|५.१.९०|५.१.९० षष्टिकाः षष्टिरात्रेण पच्यन्ते
The anomalously formed word षष्टिकाः has the meaning of 'what are matured in six nights'.<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.91|5.1.91 vatsaraantaachChashChandasi|vatsaraantaachChashChandasi|vatsaraantaachChashChandasi 5.1.91|वत्सरान्ताच्छश्छन्दसि|वत्सरान्ताच्छश्छन्दसि ५.१.९१|५.१.९१|५.१.९१ वत्सरान्ताच्छश्छन्दसि
The affix छ comes in the छन्दस् (Vedas) in the five-fold senses taught in पन्थो ण नित्यम् ५.१.७६, तमधीष्टो भृतो भूतो भावी ५.१.८०, after a stem ending in वत्सर।<br><br>Terms: छ

5.1.92|5.1.92 samparipuurvaat‌ kha cha|samparipuurvaat‌ kha cha|samparipuurvaat‌ kha cha 5.1.92|सम्परिपूर्वात्‌ ख च|सम्परिपूर्वात्‌ ख च ५.१.९२|५.१.९२|५.१.९२ सम्परिपूर्वात्‌ ख च
When the affixes ख (ईन) and छ (ईय) coem in the छन्दस् (Vedas) in the five-fold senses taught in पन्थो ण नित्यम् ५.१.७६, तमधीष्टो भृतो भूतो भावी ५.१.८०, after the word वत्सर , when preceded by सम् and परि।<br><br>Terms: ख and छ

5.1.93|5.1.93 tena parijayyalabhyakaaryasukaram|tena parijayyalabhyakaaryasukaram|tena parijayyalabhyakaaryasukaram 5.1.93|तेन परिजय्यलभ्यकार्यसुकरम्|तेन परिजय्यलभ्यकार्यसुकरम् ५.१.९३|५.१.९३|५.१.९३ तेन परिजय्यलभ्यकार्यसुकरम्
The affix ठञ् comes after a word denoting time in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction in the sense 'to be subdued, to be gained or attained, to be completed and to be easily completed in that time'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.94|5.1.94 tadasya brahmacharyam|tadasya brahmacharyam|tadasya brahmacharyam 5.1.94|तदस्य ब्रह्मचर्यम्|तदस्य ब्रह्मचर्यम् ५.१.९४|५.१.९४|५.१.९४ तदस्य ब्रह्मचर्यम्
The affix ठञ् comes after a word of time in the sense of 'an abstinence that lasts so long' or 'who practises abstinence so long'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.95|5.1.95 tasya cha daxiNaa yaJNaakhyebhyaH|tasya cha daxiNaa yaJNaakhyebhyaH|tasya cha daxiNaa yaJNaakhyebhyaH 5.1.95|तस्य च दक्षिणा यज्ञाख्येभ्यः|तस्य च दक्षिणा यज्ञाख्येभ्यः ५.१.९५|५.१.९५|५.१.९५ तस्य च दक्षिणा यज्ञाख्येभ्यः
The affix ठञ् comes after a word being the name of sacrifice, in the sense of 'the fee thereof'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.96|5.1.96 tatra cha diiyate kaaryaM bhavavat‌|tatra cha diiyate kaaryaM bhavavat‌|tatra cha diiyate kaaryaM bhavavat‌ 5.1.96|तत्र च दीयते कार्यं भववत्‌|तत्र च दीयते कार्यं भववत्‌ ५.१.९६|५.१.९६|५.१.९६ तत्र च दीयते कार्यं भववत्‌
The affixes having the sense of भव तत्र भवः ४.३.५३ , कालाट्ठञ् ४.३.११ , come after a time-denoting word in the sense of 'what is given in that, and what is done in that'.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.97|5.1.97 vyuShTaadibhyo.aN|vyuShTaadibhyo.aN|vyuShTaadibhyo.aN 5.1.97|व्युष्टादिभ्योऽण्|व्युष्टादिभ्योऽण् ५.१.९७|५.१.९७|५.१.९७ व्युष्टादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes after the words व्युष्ट etc. in the Locative -7th case in construction, the sense of 'being given therein or done therein'.<br><br>Terms: अण्

5.1.98|5.1.98 tena yathaakathaachahastaabhyaaM Nayatau|tena yathaakathaachahastaabhyaaM Nayatau|tena yathaakathaachahastaabhyaaM Nayatau 5.1.98|तेन यथाकथाचहस्ताभ्यां णयतौ|तेन यथाकथाचहस्ताभ्यां णयतौ ५.१.९८|५.१.९८|५.१.९८ तेन यथाकथाचहस्ताभ्यां णयतौ
The affixes ण and यत् come respectively after the words यथा-कथा-च and हस्त being in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction having the sense of what is 'given or is done in this way'.<br><br>Terms: ण and यत्

5.1.99|5.1.99 sampaadini|sampaadini|sampaadini 5.1.99|सम्पादिनि|सम्पादिनि ५.१.९९|५.१.९९|५.१.९९ सम्पादिनि
