5.1.108|5.1.108 prakRShTe ThaNJ|prakRShTe ThaNJ|prakRShTe ThaNJ 5.1.108|प्रकृष्टे ठञ्|प्रकृष्टे ठञ् ५.१.१०८|५.१.१०८|५.१.१०८ प्रकृष्टे ठञ्
The affix यत् (यं) comes in the sense of 'long standing' after the word काल being the Nominative 1st-Case in construction.<br><br>Terms: यत् (यं)

5.1.109|5.1.109 prayojanam|prayojanam|prayojanam 5.1.109|प्रयोजनम्|प्रयोजनम् ५.१.१०९|५.१.१०९|५.१.१०९ प्रयोजनम्
The affix ठञ् comes in the sense of 'that whose occasion or purpose is this' after a word in the Nominative 1st-Case in construction.<br><br>Terms: ठञ्

5.1.110|5.1.110 vishaakhaa.a.aShaaDhaadaN manthadaNDayoH|vishaakhaa.a.aShaaDhaadaN manthadaNDayoH|vishaakhaa.a.aShaaDhaadaN manthadaNDayoH 5.1.110|विशाखाऽऽषाढादण् मन्थदण्डयोः|विशाखाऽऽषाढादण् मन्थदण्डयोः ५.१.११०|५.१.११०|५.१.११० विशाखाऽऽषाढादण् मन्थदण्डयोः
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'that whose purpose is this' after the words 1. विशाखा and 2. आषाढ when the derivative of the first is combined with मन्य and that of the second with दण्ड।<br><br>Terms: अण्

5.1.111|5.1.111 anupravachanaadibhyashChaH|anupravachanaadibhyashChaH|anupravachanaadibhyashChaH 5.1.111|अनुप्रवचनादिभ्यश्छः|अनुप्रवचनादिभ्यश्छः ५.१.१११|५.१.१११|५.१.१११ अनुप्रवचनादिभ्यश्छः
The affix छ (ईय) comes in the same sense of 'that whose purpose is this' after The affix words अनुप्रवचन etc.<br><br>Terms: छ (ईय)

5.1.112|5.1.112 samaapanaat‌ sapuurvapadaat‌|samaapanaat‌ sapuurvapadaat‌|samaapanaat‌ sapuurvapadaat‌ 5.1.112|समापनात्‌ सपूर्वपदात्‌|समापनात्‌ सपूर्वपदात्‌ ५.१.११२|५.१.११२|५.१.११२ समापनात्‌ सपूर्वपदात्‌
The affix छ (ईय) comes in the same sense of 'that whose purpose is this' after the word समापन when it has a word in composition preceding it.<br><br>Terms: छ (ईय)

5.1.113|5.1.113 aikaagaarikaT chaure|aikaagaarikaT chaure|aikaagaarikaT chaure 5.1.113|ऐकागारिकट् चौरे|ऐकागारिकट् चौरे ५.१.११३|५.१.११३|५.१.११३ ऐकागारिकट् चौरे
The word ऐकागारिकट् is irregularly formed in the sense of 'thief'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

5.1.114|5.1.114 aakaalikaDaadyantavachane|aakaalikaDaadyantavachane|aakaalikaDaadyantavachane 5.1.114|आकालिकडाद्यन्तवचने|आकालिकडाद्यन्तवचने ५.१.११४|५.१.११४|५.१.११४ आकालिकडाद्यन्तवचने
The word आकालिकट् is irregularly formed in the sense of 'what coincides with the beginning and the end i.e. what lasts only an instant'.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

5.1.115|5.1.115 tena tulyaM kriyaa chedvatiH|tena tulyaM kriyaa chedvatiH|tena tulyaM kriyaa chedvatiH 5.1.115|तेन तुल्यं क्रिया चेद्वतिः|तेन तुल्यं क्रिया चेद्वतिः ५.१.११५|५.१.११५|५.१.११५ तेन तुल्यं क्रिया चेद्वतिः
The affix वति (वत्) comes after a word in the Instrumental -3rd case in construction, in the sense of 'like that' when the meaning is 'similarity of action'.<br><br>Terms: वति

5.1.116|5.1.116 tatra tasyeva|tatra tasyeva|tatra tasyeva 5.1.116|तत्र तस्येव|तत्र तस्येव ५.१.११६|५.१.११६|५.१.११६ तत्र तस्येव
The affix वति (वत्) also comes in the sense of 'like what is therein or thereof'.<br><br>Terms: वति

5.1.117|5.1.117 tadarham|tadarham|tadarham 5.1.117|तदर्हम्|तदर्हम् ५.१.११७|५.१.११७|५.१.११७ तदर्हम्
The affix वति (वत्) comes after a word in the Accusative -2nd case in construction in the sense of 'befitting that or suited to that'.<br><br>Terms: वति

5.1.118|5.1.118 upasargaachChandasi dhaatvarthe|upasargaachChandasi dhaatvarthe|upasargaachChandasi dhaatvarthe 5.1.118|उपसर्गाच्छन्दसि धात्वर्थे|उपसर्गाच्छन्दसि धात्वर्थे ५.१.११८|५.१.११८|५.१.११८ उपसर्गाच्छन्दसि धात्वर्थे
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the affix वति (वत्) is added to an उपसर्ग (Preposition) in the sense of a verbal root.<br><br>Terms: छन्दस् - वति

5.1.119|5.1.119 tasya bhaavastvatalau|tasya bhaavastvatalau|tasya bhaavastvatalau 5.1.119|तस्य भावस्त्वतलौ|तस्य भावस्त्वतलौ ५.१.११९|५.१.११९|५.१.११९ तस्य भावस्त्वतलौ
The affixes त्व and तल् come in the sense of 'the nature thereof' after a word in the Genitive 6th-Case.<br><br>Terms: त्व and तल्

5.1.120|5.1.120 aa cha tvaat‌|aa cha tvaat‌|aa cha tvaat‌ 5.1.120|आ च त्वात्‌|आ च त्वात्‌ ५.१.१२०|५.१.१२०|५.१.१२० आ च त्वात्‌
From this forward as far as the sūtra ब्रह्मणस्त्वः ५.१.१३६, the affixes त्व and तल् bear the rule.<br><br>Terms: त्व and तल्

5.1.121|5.1.121 na naNJpuurvaattatpuruShaadachaturasaMgatalavaNavaTayudhakatarasalasebhyaH|na naNJpuurvaattatpuruShaadachaturasaMgatalavaNavaTayudhakatarasalasebhyaH|na naNJpuurvaattatpuruShaadachaturasaMgatalavaNavaTayudhakatarasalasebhyaH 5.1.121|न नञ्पूर्वात्तत्पुरुषादचतुरसंगतलवणवटयुधकतरसलसेभ्यः|न नञ्पूर्वात्तत्पुरुषादचतुरसंगतलवणवटयुधकतरसलसेभ्यः ५.१.१२१|५.१.१२१|५.१.१२१ न नञ्पूर्वात्तत्पुरुषादचतुरसंगतलवणवटयुधकतरसलसेभ्यः
The affixes denoting 'nature' taught hereafter do not come after a तत्-पुरुष compound formed by the negative particle नञ् with the exception of the the following - 1. चतुर 2. संगत 3. लवण 4. वट 5. बुध 6. कत 7. रस and 8. लस ।<br><br>Terms: 

5.1.122|5.1.122 pRthvaadibhya imanijvaa|pRthvaadibhya imanijvaa|pRthvaadibhya imanijvaa 5.1.122|पृथ्वादिभ्य इमनिज्वा|पृथ्वादिभ्य इमनिज्वा ५.१.१२२|५.१.१२२|५.१.१२२ पृथ्वादिभ्य इमनिज्वा
The affix इमनिच् (इमन्) comes optionally in the sense of 'nature thereof' after the words पृथु etc.<br><br>Terms: इमनिच् (इमन्)

5.1.123|5.1.123 varNadRDhaadibhyaH ShyaNJ cha|varNadRDhaadibhyaH ShyaNJ cha|varNadRDhaadibhyaH ShyaNJ cha 5.1.123|वर्णदृढादिभ्यः ष्यञ् च|वर्णदृढादिभ्यः ष्यञ् च ५.१.१२३|५.१.१२३|५.१.१२३ वर्णदृढादिभ्यः ष्यञ् च
The affixes ष्यञ् and इमनिच् come in the sense of 'nature thereof' after a word denoting colour and after the words दृढ etc.<br><br>Terms: ष्यञ् and इमनिच्

5.1.124|5.1.124 guNavachanabraahmaNaadibhyaH karmaNi cha|guNavachanabraahmaNaadibhyaH karmaNi cha|guNavachanabraahmaNaadibhyaH karmaNi cha 5.1.124|गुणवचनब्राह्मणादिभ्यः कर्मणि च|गुणवचनब्राह्मणादिभ्यः कर्मणि च ५.१.१२४|५.१.१२४|५.१.१२४ गुणवचनब्राह्मणादिभ्यः कर्मणि च
The affix ष्यञ् has after a word expressive of quality and after ब्राह्मण etc., the sense of the activity or occupation or something or someone.<br><br>Terms: ष्यञ्

5.1.125|5.1.125 stenaadyannalopashcha|stenaadyannalopashcha|stenaadyannalopashcha 5.1.125|स्तेनाद्यन्नलोपश्च|स्तेनाद्यन्नलोपश्च ५.१.१२५|५.१.१२५|५.१.१२५ स्तेनाद्यन्नलोपश्च
The affix यत् (यं) comes in the sense of 'nature thereof or action thereof' after the word स्तेन in the Genitive 6th-Case and न is elided before this affix.<br><br>Terms: यत् (यं)

5.1.126|5.1.126 sakhyuryaH|sakhyuryaH|sakhyuryaH 5.1.126|सख्युर्यः|सख्युर्यः ५.१.१२६|५.१.१२६|५.१.१२६ सख्युर्यः
The affix य comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after the word सखि।<br><br>Terms: य

5.1.127|5.1.127 kapiJNaatyorDhak|kapiJNaatyorDhak|kapiJNaatyorDhak 5.1.127|कपिज्ञात्योर्ढक्|कपिज्ञात्योर्ढक् ५.१.१२७|५.१.१२७|५.१.१२७ कपिज्ञात्योर्ढक्
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after the words 1. कपि and 2. ज्ञाति।<br><br>Terms: ढक्

5.1.128|5.1.128 patyantapurohitaadibhyo yak|patyantapurohitaadibhyo yak|patyantapurohitaadibhyo yak 5.1.128|पत्यन्तपुरोहितादिभ्यो यक्|पत्यन्तपुरोहितादिभ्यो यक् ५.१.१२८|५.१.१२८|५.१.१२८ पत्यन्तपुरोहितादिभ्यो यक्
The affix यक् comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after a compound ending with पति and after पुरोहित etc.<br><br>Terms: यक्

5.1.129|5.1.129 praaNabhRjjaativayovachanodgaatraadibhyo.aNJ|praaNabhRjjaativayovachanodgaatraadibhyo.aNJ|praaNabhRjjaativayovachanodgaatraadibhyo.aNJ 5.1.129|प्राणभृज्जातिवयोवचनोद्गात्रादिभ्योऽञ्|प्राणभृज्जातिवयोवचनोद्गात्रादिभ्योऽञ् ५.१.१२९|५.१.१२९|५.१.१२९ प्राणभृज्जातिवयोवचनोद्गात्रादिभ्योऽञ्
The affix अञ् comes in the sense of 'nature or action or thereof' after class names of animals and words expressing age as well as after उद्गात्रि etc.<br><br>Terms: अञ्

5.1.130|5.1.130 haayanaantayuvaadibhyo.aN|haayanaantayuvaadibhyo.aN|haayanaantayuvaadibhyo.aN 5.1.130|हायनान्तयुवादिभ्योऽण्|हायनान्तयुवादिभ्योऽण् ५.१.१३०|५.१.१३०|५.१.१३० हायनान्तयुवादिभ्योऽण्
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after compounds ending in हायन and after युवन etc.<br><br>Terms: अण्

5.1.131|5.1.131 igantaachcha laghupuurvaat‌|igantaachcha laghupuurvaat‌|igantaachcha laghupuurvaat‌ 5.1.131|इगन्ताच्च लघुपूर्वात्‌|इगन्ताच्च लघुपूर्वात्‌ ५.१.१३१|५.१.१३१|५.१.१३१ इगन्ताच्च लघुपूर्वात्‌
The affix अण् comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after a stem ending in इक् (इ ई उ ऊ ऋ or ऌ) when the preceding syllable is prosodially light.<br><br>Terms: अण्

5.1.132|5.1.132 yopadhaadguruupottamaadvuNJ|yopadhaadguruupottamaadvuNJ|yopadhaadguruupottamaadvuNJ 5.1.132|योपधाद्गुरूपोत्तमाद्वुञ्|योपधाद्गुरूपोत्तमाद्वुञ् ५.१.१३२|५.१.१३२|५.१.१३२ योपधाद्गुरूपोत्तमाद्वुञ्
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after a polysyllabic stem whose penultimate letter is य् and whose penultimate syllable is prosodially heavy.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

5.1.133|5.1.133 dvaMdvamanoJNaadibhyashcha|dvaMdvamanoJNaadibhyashcha|dvaMdvamanoJNaadibhyashcha 5.1.133|द्वंद्वमनोज्ञादिभ्यश्च|द्वंद्वमनोज्ञादिभ्यश्च ५.१.१३३|५.१.१३३|५.१.१३३ द्वंद्वमनोज्ञादिभ्यश्च
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after a द्वन्द समास and after the words मनोज्ञ etc.<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

5.1.134|5.1.134 gotracharaNaachshlaaghaa.atyaakaaratadaveteShu|gotracharaNaachshlaaghaa.atyaakaaratadaveteShu|gotracharaNaachshlaaghaa.atyaakaaratadaveteShu 5.1.134|गोत्रचरणाच्श्लाघाऽत्याकारतदवेतेषु|गोत्रचरणाच्श्लाघाऽत्याकारतदवेतेषु ५.१.१३४|५.१.१३४|५.१.१३४ गोत्रचरणाच्श्लाघाऽत्याकारतदवेतेषु
The affix वुञ् comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after a गोत्र (Patronymic/Family-name) and after the Name of a Vedic School when one boasts thereby or manifests his contempt thereby or when it means one who has attainted that (or has come for an inspection or inquiring thereof).<br><br>Terms: वुञ्

5.1.135|5.1.135 hotraabhyashChaH|hotraabhyashChaH|hotraabhyashChaH 5.1.135|होत्राभ्यश्छः|होत्राभ्यश्छः ५.१.१३५|५.१.१३५|५.१.१३५ होत्राभ्यश्छः
The affix छ (ईय) comes in the sense of 'nature or action thereof' after words expressing होत्रा priests.<br><br>Terms: छ (ईय)

5.1.136|5.1.136 brahmaNastvaH|brahmaNastvaH|brahmaNastvaH 5.1.136|ब्रह्मणस्त्वः|ब्रह्मणस्त्वः ५.१.१३६|५.१.१३६|५.१.१३६ ब्रह्मणस्त्वः
The affix त्व comes in the sense of of 'nature or action thereof' after the word ब्रह्मण denoting a kind of होत्रा priest.<br><br>Terms: त्व

5.2.1|5.2.1 dhaanyaanaaM bhavane xetre khaNJ|dhaanyaanaaM bhavane xetre khaNJ|dhaanyaanaaM bhavane xetre khaNJ 5.2.1|धान्यानां भवने क्षेत्रे खञ्|धान्यानां भवने क्षेत्रे खञ् ५.२.१|५.२.१|५.२.१ धान्यानां भवने क्षेत्रे खञ्
The affix खञ् comes in the sense of 'a place of growing when that place is a field' after the name of any particular corn being in the Genitive 6th-Case.<br><br>Terms: खञ्

5.2.2|5.2.2 vriihishaalyorDhak|vriihishaalyorDhak|vriihishaalyorDhak 5.2.2|व्रीहिशाल्योर्ढक्|व्रीहिशाल्योर्ढक् ५.२.२|५.२.२|५.२.२ व्रीहिशाल्योर्ढक्
The affix ढक् comes in the sense of 'a place of growing, when it is a field' after the words 1. व्रीहि and 2. शालि।<br><br>Terms: ढक्

5.2.3|5.2.3 yavayavakaShaShTikaadat‌|yavayavakaShaShTikaadat‌|yavayavakaShaShTikaadat‌ 5.2.3|यवयवकषष्टिकादत्‌|यवयवकषष्टिकादत्‌ ५.२.३|५.२.३|५.२.३ यवयवकषष्टिकादत्‌
The affix यत् comes in the sense of 'a place of growing, when it is a field' after the words 1. यव 2. यवक and 3. षष्टिक।<br><br>Terms: यत्

5.2.4|5.2.4 vibhaaShaa tilamaaShomaabhangaa.aNubhyaH|vibhaaShaa tilamaaShomaabhangaa.aNubhyaH|vibhaaShaa tilamaaShomaabhangaa.aNubhyaH 5.2.4|विभाषा तिलमाषोमाभङ्गाऽणुभ्यः|विभाषा तिलमाषोमाभङ्गाऽणुभ्यः ५.२.४|५.२.४|५.२.४ विभाषा तिलमाषोमाभङ्गाऽणुभ्यः
The affix यत् comes in the sense of 'a place of growing, when it is a field' optionally after the words 1. तिल 2. माष3. उमा 4. भङ्गा and 5. अणु।<br><br>Terms: यत्

5.2.5|5.2.5 sarvacharmaNaH kRtaH khakhaNJau|sarvacharmaNaH kRtaH khakhaNJau|sarvacharmaNaH kRtaH khakhaNJau 5.2.5|सर्वचर्मणः कृतः खखञौ|सर्वचर्मणः कृतः खखञौ ५.२.५|५.२.५|५.२.५ सर्वचर्मणः कृतः खखञौ
The affix ख (ईन) and खञ् comes in the sense of 'wholly made thereof' after the word सर्वचर्मन्।<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन) and खञ्

5.2.6|5.2.6 yathaamukhasaMmukhasya darshanaH khaH|yathaamukhasaMmukhasya darshanaH khaH|yathaamukhasaMmukhasya darshanaH khaH 5.2.6|यथामुखसंमुखस्य दर्शनः खः|यथामुखसंमुखस्य दर्शनः खः ५.२.६|५.२.६|५.२.६ यथामुखसंमुखस्य दर्शनः खः
The affix ख (ईन) and खञ् comes in the sense of 'a mirror' after the words 1. यथामुख and 2. संमुख being in Genitive 6th-Case in construction.<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन) and खञ्

5.2.7|5.2.7 tatsarvaadeH pathyangakarmapatrapaatraM vyaapnoti|tatsarvaadeH pathyangakarmapatrapaatraM vyaapnoti|tatsarvaadeH pathyangakarmapatrapaatraM vyaapnoti 5.2.7|तत्सर्वादेः पथ्यङ्गकर्मपत्रपात्रं व्याप्नोति|तत्सर्वादेः पथ्यङ्गकर्मपत्रपात्रं व्याप्नोति ५.२.७|५.२.७|५.२.७ तत्सर्वादेः पथ्यङ्गकर्मपत्रपात्रं व्याप्नोति
After the words 1. पथि 2. अङ्ग 3. कर्मन् 4. पत्र or 5. पात्र , preceded by सर्व being in the Accusative -2nd case in construction, the affix ख (ईन) comes in the sense of 'what pervades or fills the whole of that'.<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन)

5.2.8|5.2.8 aaprapadaM praapnoti|aaprapadaM praapnoti|aaprapadaM praapnoti 5.2.8|आप्रपदं प्राप्नोति|आप्रपदं प्राप्नोति ५.२.८|५.२.८|५.२.८ आप्रपदं प्राप्नोति
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the sense of 'reaching thereto' after the word आप्रपद।<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन)

5.2.9|5.2.9 anupadasarvaannaayaanayaM baddhaabhaxayatineyeShu|anupadasarvaannaayaanayaM baddhaabhaxayatineyeShu|anupadasarvaannaayaanayaM baddhaabhaxayatineyeShu 5.2.9|अनुपदसर्वान्नायानयं बद्धाभक्षयतिनेयेषु|अनुपदसर्वान्नायानयं बद्धाभक्षयतिनेयेषु ५.२.९|५.२.९|५.२.९ अनुपदसर्वान्नायानयं बद्धाभक्षयतिनेयेषु
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the senses of 'so bound', 'eating that' and 'to carry thereto' after the words 1. अनुपद 2. सर्वान्न and 3. आयन।<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन)

5.2.10|5.2.10 parovaraparamparaputrapautramanubhavati|parovaraparamparaputrapautramanubhavati|parovaraparamparaputrapautramanubhavati 5.2.10|परोवरपरम्परपुत्रपौत्रमनुभवति|परोवरपरम्परपुत्रपौत्रमनुभवति ५.२.१०|५.२.१०|५.२.१० परोवरपरम्परपुत्रपौत्रमनुभवति
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the sense of 'who witnesses or experiences that' after the words 1. परोवर 2. परम्पर and 3. पुत्रपौत्र , in the Accusative -2nd case in construction.<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन)

5.2.11|5.2.11 avaarapaaraatyantaanukaamaM gaamii|avaarapaaraatyantaanukaamaM gaamii|avaarapaaraatyantaanukaamaM gaamii 5.2.11|अवारपारात्यन्तानुकामं गामी|अवारपारात्यन्तानुकामं गामी ५.२.११|५.२.११|५.२.११ अवारपारात्यन्तानुकामं गामी
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the sense of 'who purposes to go' after the words 1. अवारपार 2. अत्यन्त and 3. अनुकाम being in the Accusative -2nd case in construction.<br><br>Terms: 

5.2.12|5.2.12 samaaMsamaaM vijaayate|samaaMsamaaM vijaayate|samaaMsamaaM vijaayate 5.2.12|समांसमां विजायते|समांसमां विजायते ५.२.१२|५.२.१२|५.२.१२ समांसमां विजायते
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the sense of 'who bears in the womb' after the word समांसमाम्।<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन)

5.2.13|5.2.13 adyashviinaa.avaShTabdhe|adyashviinaa.avaShTabdhe|adyashviinaa.avaShTabdhe 5.2.13|अद्यश्वीनाऽवष्टब्धे|अद्यश्वीनाऽवष्टब्धे ५.२.१३|५.२.१३|५.२.१३ अद्यश्वीनाऽवष्टब्धे
The word अद्यश्वीन is anomalous meaning 'a female near delivery'.<br><br>Terms: Anomalous

5.2.14|5.2.14 aagaviinaH|aagaviinaH|aagaviinaH 5.2.14|आगवीनः|आगवीनः ५.२.१४|५.२.१४|५.२.१४ आगवीनः
The word आगवीन is irregularly formed.<br><br>Terms: Irregular

5.2.15|5.2.15 anugvalaMgaamii|anugvalaMgaamii|anugvalaMgaamii 5.2.15|अनुग्वलंगामी|अनुग्वलंगामी ५.२.१५|५.२.१५|५.२.१५ अनुग्वलंगामी
The affix ख (ईन) comes in the sense of 'who is fit to follow' after the word अनुगु।<br><br>Terms: ख (ईन)

5.2.16|5.2.16 adhvano yatkhau|adhvano yatkhau|adhvano yatkhau 5.2.16|अध्वनो यत्खौ|अध्वनो यत्खौ ५.२.१६|५.२.१६|५.२.१६ अध्वनो यत्खौ
The affixes यत् (यं) and ख (ईन) come in the sense of 'who is fit or able to follow' after the word अध्वन्।<br><br>Terms: यत् (यं) and ख (ईन)

5.2.17|5.2.17 abhyamitraachCha cha|abhyamitraachCha cha|abhyamitraachCha cha 5.2.17|अभ्यमित्राच्छ च|अभ्यमित्राच्छ च ५.२.१७|५.२.१७|५.२.१७ अभ्यमित्राच्छ च
The affixes छ (ईय), यत् (यं) and ख (ईन) come in the sense of 'who is able to go' after the word अभ्यमित्र।<br><br>Terms: छ (ईय), यत् (यं) and ख (ईन)

5.2.18|5.2.18 goShThaat‌ khaNJ bhuutapuurve|goShThaat‌ khaNJ bhuutapuurve|goShThaat‌ khaNJ bhuutapuurve 5.2.18|गोष्ठात्‌ खञ् भूतपूर्वे|गोष्ठात्‌ खञ् भूतपूर्वे ५.२.१८|५.२.१८|५.२.१८ गोष्ठात्‌ खञ् भूतपूर्वे
The affix खञ् comes in the sense of 'it formerly had been' after the word गोष्ठ।<br><br>Terms: खञ्

5.2.19|5.2.19 ashvasyaikaahagamaH|ashvasyaikaahagamaH|ashvasyaikaahagamaH 5.2.19|अश्वस्यैकाहगमः|अश्वस्यैकाहगमः ५.२.१९|५.२.१९|५.२.१९ अश्वस्यैकाहगमः
The affix खञ् comes in the sense of 'what is travelled over or traversed in one day' after the word अश्व being in the Genitive 6th-Case in construction.<br><br>Terms: खञ्

