6.1.54|6.1.54 chisphurorNau|chisphurorNau|chisphurorNau 6.1.54|चिस्फुरोर्णौ|चिस्फुरोर्णौ ६.१.५४|६.१.५४|६.१.५४ चिस्फुरोर्णौ
There is optionally the substitution of आ in the room of the dipthong of the roots चि and स्फुर् when in the Causative.<br><br>Terms: धातु-गुर्-प्रत्यय-णमुल्

6.1.55|6.1.55 prajane viiyateH|prajane viiyateH|prajane viiyateH 6.1.55|प्रजने वीयतेः|प्रजने वीयतेः ६.१.५५|६.१.५५|६.१.५५ प्रजने वीयतेः
There is optionally the substitution of आ in the room of the dipthong of the root वी in the causative, when meaning 'to conceive an embryo'.<br><br>Terms: धातु-चि-स्फुर्

6.1.56|6.1.56 bibheterhetubhaye|bibheterhetubhaye|bibheterhetubhaye 6.1.56|बिभेतेर्हेतुभये|बिभेतेर्हेतुभये ६.१.५६|६.१.५६|६.१.५६ बिभेतेर्हेतुभये
There is optionally the substitution of आ in the room of the dipthong of the root भी 'to fear' in the causative, when the fear is produced directly through the agent of the causative.<br><br>Terms: धातु-वी

6.1.57|6.1.57 nityaM smayateH|nityaM smayateH|nityaM smayateH 6.1.57|नित्यं स्मयतेः|नित्यं स्मयतेः ६.१.५७|६.१.५७|६.१.५७ नित्यं स्मयतेः
There is invariably the substitution of आ for the dipthong of the root स्मि 'to smile' in the causative, when the astonishment is produced directly through the agent of the causative.<br><br>Terms: धातु-भी

6.1.58|6.1.58 sRjidRshorjhalyamakiti|sRjidRshorjhalyamakiti|sRjidRshorjhalyamakiti 6.1.58|सृजिदृशोर्झल्यमकिति|सृजिदृशोर्झल्यमकिति ६.१.५८|६.१.५८|६.१.५८ सृजिदृशोर्झल्यमकिति
The augment अम् (अ) comes after the ऋ or सृज् 'to create' and दृश् 'to see', when an affix beginning with a झल् letter (the Mute and the Sibilant) follows: provided that it has no indicatory क।<br><br>Terms: धातु-स्मि

6.1.59|6.1.59 anudaattasya chardupadhasyaanyatarasyaam|anudaattasya chardupadhasyaanyatarasyaam|anudaattasya chardupadhasyaanyatarasyaam 6.1.59|अनुदात्तस्य चर्दुपधस्यान्यतरस्याम्|अनुदात्तस्य चर्दुपधस्यान्यतरस्याम् ६.१.५९|६.१.५९|६.१.५९ अनुदात्तस्य चर्दुपधस्यान्यतरस्याम्
The augment अम् (अ) augment comes optionally after the ऋ of those roots which are exhibited in the धातुपाठ as अनुदात्त , when such roots end in a consonant having a ऋ has penultimate and are followed by an affix beginning with a mute or sibilant and not having an indicatory क।<br><br>Terms: 

6.1.60|6.1.60 shiirShaMshChandasi|shiirShaMshChandasi|shiirShaMshChandasi 6.1.60|शीर्षंश्छन्दसि|शीर्षंश्छन्दसि ६.१.६०|६.१.६०|६.१.६० शीर्षंश्छन्दसि
The word शीर्षन् 'head', is found in छन्दस्।<br><br>Terms: 

6.1.61|6.1.61 ye cha taddhite|ye cha taddhite|ye cha taddhite 6.1.61|ये च तद्धिते|ये च तद्धिते ६.१.६१|६.१.६१|६.१.६१ ये च तद्धिते
There is the substitution of this stem शीर्षन् for शिरस् when a तद्धित-affix beginning with य follows.<br><br>Terms: 

6.1.62|6.1.62 achi shiirShaH|achi shiirShaH|achi shiirShaH 6.1.62|अचि शीर्षः|अचि शीर्षः ६.१.६२|६.१.६२|६.१.६२ अचि शीर्षः
There is the substitution of शीर्ष for शीरस् when a तद्धित-affix beginning with a vowel follows.<br><br>Terms: तद्धित

6.1.63|6.1.63 paddannomaashRnnishasanyuuShandoShanyakanChakannudannaasanChasprabhRtiShu|paddannomaashRnnishasanyuuShandoShanyakanChakannudannaasanChasprabhRtiShu|paddannomaashRnnishasanyuuShandoShanyakanChakannudannaasanChasprabhRtiShu 6.1.63|पद्दन्नोमास्हृन्निशसन्यूषन्दोषन्यकञ्छकन्नुदन्नासञ्छस्प्रभृतिषु|पद्दन्नोमास्हृन्निशसन्यूषन्दोषन्यकञ्छकन्नुदन्नासञ्छस्प्रभृतिषु ६.१.६३|६.१.६३|६.१.६३ पद्दन्नोमास्हृन्निशसन्यूषन्दोषन्यकञ्छकन्नुदन्नासञ्छस्प्रभृतिषु
In the weak cases (beginning with the accusative plural) the following stems are substituted: पद for पाद , दत् for दन्त , नस् for नासिका , मास् for मास , हृद् for हृदय , निश for निशा , असन् for असृज् , यूषन् for यूष , दोषन् for दास् , यकन् for यकृत् , शकन् for शकृत् , उदन् for उदक and आसन् for आस्य।<br><br>Terms: 

6.1.64|6.1.64 dhaatvaadeH ShaH saH|dhaatvaadeH ShaH saH|dhaatvaadeH ShaH saH 6.1.64|धात्वादेः षः सः|धात्वादेः षः सः ६.१.६४|६.१.६४|६.१.६४ धात्वादेः षः सः
There is the substitution of स in the room of the ष् being the initial of a verbal root as enunciated in the धातुपाठ।<br><br>Terms: 

6.1.65|6.1.65 No naH|No naH|No naH 6.1.65|णो नः|णो नः ६.१.६५|६.१.६५|६.१.६५ णो नः
There is the substitution of न् for the initial ण् of the root in the धातुपाठ।<br><br>Terms: धातुपाठ

6.1.66|6.1.66 lopo vyorvali|lopo vyorvali|lopo vyorvali 6.1.66|लोपो व्योर्वलि|लोपो व्योर्वलि ६.१.६६|६.१.६६|६.१.६६ लोपो व्योर्वलि
There is लोप-substitution (elision) of the व् and य् when followed by any consonant except य्।<br><br>Terms: धातुपाठ

6.1.67|6.1.67 verapRktasya|verapRktasya|verapRktasya 6.1.67|वेरपृक्तस्य|वेरपृक्तस्य ६.१.६७|६.१.६७|६.१.६७ वेरपृक्तस्य
There is the elision of the affix वि when reduced to the single letter व्।<br><br>Terms: धातुपाठ

6.1.68|6.1.68 halNGyaabbhyo diirghaat‌ sutisyapRktaM hal|halNGyaabbhyo diirghaat‌ sutisyapRktaM hal|halNGyaabbhyo diirghaat‌ sutisyapRktaM hal 6.1.68|हल्ङ्याब्भ्यो दीर्घात्‌ सुतिस्यपृक्तं हल्|हल्ङ्याब्भ्यो दीर्घात्‌ सुतिस्यपृक्तं हल् ६.१.६८|६.१.६८|६.१.६८ हल्ङ्याब्भ्यो दीर्घात्‌ सुतिस्यपृक्तं हल्
After a consonant there is the elision of the nominative affix स् and the tense-affix ति and सि (when reduced to the form of त् and स् ) being consonants; and so also after the long vowels ई and आ of the feminine (affix ङी and आप् ), there is the elision of the nominative affix स्।<br><br>Terms: 

6.1.69|6.1.69 eNGhrasvaat‌ sambuddheH|eNGhrasvaat‌ sambuddheH|eNGhrasvaat‌ sambuddheH 6.1.69|एङ्ह्रस्वात्‌ सम्बुद्धेः|एङ्ह्रस्वात्‌ सम्बुद्धेः ६.१.६९|६.१.६९|६.१.६९ एङ्ह्रस्वात्‌ सम्बुद्धेः
The consonant of the nominative-affix (सु and its substitute अम् ) is elided in the Vocative singular after a nominal-stem ending in ए or ओ or a short vowel.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-F-तिङ्

6.1.70|6.1.70 sheshChandasi bahulam|sheshChandasi bahulam|sheshChandasi bahulam 6.1.70|शेश्छन्दसि बहुलम्|शेश्छन्दसि बहुलम् ६.१.७०|६.१.७०|६.१.७० शेश्छन्दसि बहुलम्
In the छन्दस् , the elision of the case-ending इ (शि) of the nominative and accusative plural neuter, is optional.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-8

6.1.71|6.1.71 hrasvasya piti kRti tuk|hrasvasya piti kRti tuk|hrasvasya piti kRti tuk 6.1.71|ह्रस्वस्य पिति कृति तुक्|ह्रस्वस्य पिति कृति तुक् ६.१.७१|६.१.७१|६.१.७१ ह्रस्वस्य पिति कृति तुक्
To a root ending in a short vowel is added the augment त् (तुक्) when a कृत्-affix having an indicatory ए follows.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-छन्दस्

6.1.72|6.1.72 saMhitaayaam|saMhitaayaam|saMhitaayaam 6.1.72|संहितायाम्|संहितायाम् ६.१.७२|६.१.७२|६.१.७२ संहितायाम्
In the following sutras up to ६.१.१५७ inclusive, the words संहितायाम् 'in an unbroken flow of speech', should be supplied.<br><br>Terms: धातु-कृत्

6.1.73|6.1.73 Che cha|Che cha|Che cha 6.1.73|छे च|छे च ६.१.७३|६.१.७३|६.१.७३ छे च
The augment त् is added to a preceding short vowel also when छ follows an in an uninterrupted speech.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.74|6.1.74 aaNGmaaNGoshcha|aaNGmaaNGoshcha|aaNGmaaNGoshcha 6.1.74|आङ्माङोश्च|आङ्माङोश्च ६.१.७४|६.१.७४|६.१.७४ आङ्माङोश्च
The augment त् is added to the parcticle आ and the prohibitive particle मा , when छ follows an in a continous text.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.75|6.1.75 diirghaat‌|diirghaat‌|diirghaat‌ 6.1.75|दीर्घात्‌|दीर्घात्‌ ६.१.७५|६.१.७५|६.१.७५ दीर्घात्‌
The augment त् is added to a long vowel, when followed by छ in a continous text.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.76|6.1.76 padaantaadvaa|padaantaadvaa|padaantaadvaa 6.1.76|पदान्ताद्वा|पदान्ताद्वा ६.१.७६|६.१.७६|६.१.७६ पदान्ताद्वा
The augment त् is added optionally to a long vowel final in a full word (पद) when followed by छ।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.77|6.1.77 iko yaNachi|iko yaNachi|iko yaNachi 6.1.77|इको यणचि|इको यणचि ६.१.७७|६.१.७७|६.१.७७ इको यणचि
The semi-vowels य् व् र् ल् are the substitutes of the corresponding vowels इ उ ऋ and ऌ (long and short), when followed by a vowel.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.78|6.1.78 echo.ayavaayaavaH|echo.ayavaayaavaH|echo.ayavaayaavaH 6.1.78|एचोऽयवायावः|एचोऽयवायावः ६.१.७८|६.१.७८|६.१.७८ एचोऽयवायावः
For the vowels ए ऐ ओ and औ are respectively substituted अय् आय् अव् and आव् when a vowel follows.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.79|6.1.79 vaanto yi pratyaye|vaanto yi pratyaye|vaanto yi pratyaye 6.1.79|वान्तो यि प्रत्यये|वान्तो यि प्रत्यये ६.१.७९|६.१.७९|६.१.७९ वान्तो यि प्रत्यये
The substitution of अव् and आव् for ओ and औ also takes place before an affix beginning with य।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.80|6.1.80 dhaatostannimittasyaiva|dhaatostannimittasyaiva|dhaatostannimittasyaiva 6.1.80|धातोस्तन्निमित्तस्यैव|धातोस्तन्निमित्तस्यैव ६.१.८०|६.१.८०|६.१.८० धातोस्तन्निमित्तस्यैव
For the final dipthongs ओ and औ of a root, are substituted अव् and आव् respectively, before an affix beginning with य् , then only when such dipthong has been itself first evolved by that affix.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.81|6.1.81 xayyajayyau shakyaarthe|xayyajayyau shakyaarthe|xayyajayyau shakyaarthe 6.1.81|क्षय्यजय्यौ शक्यार्थे|क्षय्यजय्यौ शक्यार्थे ६.१.८१|६.१.८१|६.१.८१ क्षय्यजय्यौ शक्यार्थे
In क्षय्य and जय्य there is substitution of अय् for ए only then when the sense is that of 'to be possible to do'.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.82|6.1.82 krayyastadarthe|krayyastadarthe|krayyastadarthe 6.1.82|क्रय्यस्तदर्थे|क्रय्यस्तदर्थे ६.१.८२|६.१.८२|६.१.८२ क्रय्यस्तदर्थे
In the क्रय्य there is substitution of अय् for ए when the sense is that of 'exposed or put out for sale, saleable'.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.83|6.1.83 bhayyapravayye cha chChandasi|bhayyapravayye cha chChandasi|bhayyapravayye cha chChandasi 6.1.83|भय्यप्रवय्ये च च्छन्दसि|भय्यप्रवय्ये च च्छन्दसि ६.१.८३|६.१.८३|६.१.८३ भय्यप्रवय्ये च च्छन्दसि
The forms भय्य and प्रवय्य are found in the छन्दस<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.84|6.1.84 ekaH puurvaparayoH|ekaH puurvaparayoH|ekaH puurvaparayoH 6.1.84|एकः पूर्वपरयोः|एकः पूर्वपरयोः ६.१.८४|६.१.८४|६.१.८४ एकः पूर्वपरयोः
From here up to ६.१.१११ inclusive is always to be supplied the phrase 'for the preceding and the following is substituted'.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.85|6.1.85 antaadivachcha|antaadivachcha|antaadivachcha 6.1.85|अन्तादिवच्च|अन्तादिवच्च ६.१.८५|६.१.८५|६.१.८५ अन्तादिवच्च
And this single susbtitute is considered as the final of the preceding (form) and the initial of the succeeding (form).<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.86|6.1.86 ShatvatukorasiddhaH|ShatvatukorasiddhaH|ShatvatukorasiddhaH 6.1.86|षत्वतुकोरसिद्धः|षत्वतुकोरसिद्धः ६.१.८६|६.१.८६|६.१.८६ षत्वतुकोरसिद्धः
The substitution of the final आदेश is to be considered as to have not taken effect, when otherwise स would have changed to ष , or when the augment त् (तुक्) is to be added.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.87|6.1.87 aadguNaH|aadguNaH|aadguNaH 6.1.87|आद्गुणः|आद्गुणः ६.१.८७|६.१.८७|६.१.८७ आद्गुणः
The गुण is the single substitute of the final अ or आ of a preceding word and the simple vowel of the succeeding (अ or आ + a vowel = गुण)।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.88|6.1.88 vRddhirechi|vRddhirechi|vRddhirechi 6.1.88|वृद्धिरेचि|वृद्धिरेचि ६.१.८८|६.१.८८|६.१.८८ वृद्धिरेचि
The वृद्धि is the single substitute of अ or आ of a preceding word and the initial dipthong of the succeeding (अ or आ + dipthong = वृद्धि)।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.89|6.1.89 etyedhatyuuThsu|etyedhatyuuThsu|etyedhatyuuThsu 6.1.89|एत्येधत्यूठ्सु|एत्येधत्यूठ्सु ६.१.८९|६.१.८९|६.१.८९ एत्येधत्यूठ्सु
The वृद्धि is the single substitute of अ or आ + ए of एति (root इ) and एधति (root एध), and for अ or आ + ऊ of उठ (the substitute of वा in वाह by ६.४.१३२).<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.90|6.1.90 aaTashcha|aaTashcha|aaTashcha 6.1.90|आटश्च|आटश्च ६.१.९०|६.१.९०|६.१.९० आटश्च
The वृद्धि is the single substitute when the augment आट् is followed by any vowel.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.91|6.1.91 upasargaadRti dhaatau|upasargaadRti dhaatau|upasargaadRti dhaatau 6.1.91|उपसर्गादृति धातौ|उपसर्गादृति धातौ ६.१.९१|६.१.९१|६.१.९१ उपसर्गादृति धातौ
The वृद्धि is the single substitute when the अ or आ of a preposition (उपसर्ग) is followed by the short ऋ of a verb.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.92|6.1.92 vaa supyaapishaleH|vaa supyaapishaleH|vaa supyaapishaleH 6.1.92|वा सुप्यापिशलेः|वा सुप्यापिशलेः ६.१.९२|६.१.९२|६.१.९२ वा सुप्यापिशलेः
According to the opinion of आपिशलि, the वृद्धि is optionally the single substitute, when the अ or आ of a preposition is followed by a Demoninative Verb beginning with ऋ।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.93|6.1.93 auto.amshasoH|auto.amshasoH|auto.amshasoH 6.1.93|औतोऽम्शसोः|औतोऽम्शसोः ६.१.९३|६.१.९३|६.१.९३ औतोऽम्शसोः
For the ओ of a nominal stem + अ of the Accusative case-ending अम् and अस् the single substitute is आ।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.94|6.1.94 eNGi pararuupam|eNGi pararuupam|eNGi pararuupam 6.1.94|एङि पररूपम्|एङि पररूपम् ६.१.९४|६.१.९४|६.१.९४ एङि पररूपम्
For the अ or आ of the Preposition + ए or ओ of a verbal root, the second vowel is the single substitute.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.95|6.1.95 omaaNGoshcha|omaaNGoshcha|omaaNGoshcha 6.1.95|ओमाङोश्च|ओमाङोश्च ६.१.९५|६.१.९५|६.१.९५ ओमाङोश्च
For the अ or आ of ओम् or + the vowel of the Preposition आङ् , the second vowel is the single substitute.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.96|6.1.96 usyapadaantaat‌|usyapadaantaat‌|usyapadaantaat‌ 6.1.96|उस्यपदान्तात्‌|उस्यपदान्तात्‌ ६.१.९६|६.१.९६|६.१.९६ उस्यपदान्तात्‌
For the अ or आ (not standing at the end of a पद or full word) + उ of उस the Tense-affix, the second vowel is the single substitute.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.97|6.1.97 ato guNe|ato guNe|ato guNe 6.1.97|अतो गुणे|अतो गुणे ६.१.९७|६.१.९७|६.१.९७ अतो गुणे
Also when the short अ , not being final in a पद , is followed by a गुण letter, then in the room of both the precedent and the subsequent - the single substitute is the form of the subsequent i.e. the गुण।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.98|6.1.98 avyaktaanukaraNasyaata itau|avyaktaanukaraNasyaata itau|avyaktaanukaraNasyaata itau 6.1.98|अव्यक्तानुकरणस्यात इतौ|अव्यक्तानुकरणस्यात इतौ ६.१.९८|६.१.९८|६.१.९८ अव्यक्तानुकरणस्यात इतौ
The इ of इति is the single substitute for the अत् (of a word denoting imitation of an inarticulate sound) + इति।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.99|6.1.99 naamreDitasyaantyasya tu vaa|naamreDitasyaantyasya tu vaa|naamreDitasyaantyasya tu vaa 6.1.99|नाम्रेडितस्यान्त्यस्य तु वा|नाम्रेडितस्यान्त्यस्य तु वा ६.१.९९|६.१.९९|६.१.९९ नाम्रेडितस्यान्त्यस्य तु वा
This substitution does not take place when a sound-imitation word is doubled, here, however, for the final त् + इ , the single substitute is optionally इ (the second vowel).<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.100|6.1.100 nityamaamreDite Daachi|nityamaamreDite Daachi|nityamaamreDite Daachi 6.1.100|नित्यमाम्रेडिते डाचि|नित्यमाम्रेडिते डाचि ६.१.१००|६.१.१००|६.१.१०० नित्यमाम्रेडिते डाचि
Of such a doubled sound-imitation word, to which the affix आ is added which causes elision of the final अत् , for the final त् of the first member and the initial consonant of the second member, such subsequent consonant is always the single substitute.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.101|6.1.101 akaH savarNe diirghaH|akaH savarNe diirghaH|akaH savarNe diirghaH 6.1.101|अकः सवर्णे दीर्घः|अकः सवर्णे दीर्घः ६.१.१०१|६.१.१०१|६.१.१०१ अकः सवर्णे दीर्घः
When a single vowel is followed by a homogenous vowel, the corresponding long vowel is the single substitute for both the precedent and the subsequent vowels.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.102|6.1.102 prathamayoH puurvasavarNaH|prathamayoH puurvasavarNaH|prathamayoH puurvasavarNaH 6.1.102|प्रथमयोः पूर्वसवर्णः|प्रथमयोः पूर्वसवर्णः ६.१.१०२|६.१.१०२|६.१.१०२ प्रथमयोः पूर्वसवर्णः
For the simple vowel of a nominal-stem and for the vowel of the case-affixes of the Nominative and the Accusative in all numbers, there is the single substitution of a long vowel corresponding to the first vowel.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.103|6.1.103 tasmaachChaso naH puMsi|tasmaachChaso naH puMsi|tasmaachChaso naH puMsi 6.1.103|तस्माच्छसो नः पुंसि|तस्माच्छसो नः पुंसि ६.१.१०३|६.१.१०३|६.१.१०३ तस्माच्छसो नः पुंसि
After such a long vowel homogenous with the first, न् is substituted for the स् of the Acccusative case affix शस् in the masculine.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.104|6.1.104 naadichi|naadichi|naadichi 6.1.104|नादिचि|नादिचि ६.१.१०४|६.१.१०४|६.१.१०४ नादिचि
The substitution of a long vowel homogenous with the first, does not take place when अ or आ is followed by a vowel (other than अ) of the case-affixes of the Nominative and the Accusative.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.105|6.1.105 diirghaajjasi cha|diirghaajjasi cha|diirghaajjasi cha 6.1.105|दीर्घाज्जसि च|दीर्घाज्जसि च ६.१.१०५|६.१.१०५|६.१.१०५ दीर्घाज्जसि च
The substitution of a long vowel homogenous with the first, does not take place whena long vowel is followed by a nominative or accusative case-affix beginning with a vowel (other than अ) or by the Nominative Plural affix अस्।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.106|6.1.106 vaa Chandasi|vaa Chandasi|vaa Chandasi 6.1.106|वा छन्दसि|वा छन्दसि ६.१.१०६|६.१.१०६|६.१.१०६ वा छन्दसि
In the Vedas, the long vowel may optionally be the single substitute of both vowels in these cases last mentioned.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.107|6.1.107 ami puurvaH|ami puurvaH|ami puurvaH 6.1.107|अमि पूर्वः|अमि पूर्वः ६.१.१०७|६.१.१०७|६.१.१०७ अमि पूर्वः
There is the single substitution of the first vowel, when a simple vowel is followed by the अ of the case ending अम्।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.108|6.1.108 samprasaaraNaachcha|samprasaaraNaachcha|samprasaaraNaachcha 6.1.108|सम्प्रसारणाच्च|सम्प्रसारणाच्च ६.१.१०८|६.१.१०८|६.१.१०८ सम्प्रसारणाच्च
There is the single substitution of the first vowel for the vocalised semi-vowel and the subequent vowel.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.109|6.1.109 eNGaH padaantaadati|eNGaH padaantaadati|eNGaH padaantaadati 6.1.109|एङः पदान्तादति|एङः पदान्तादति ६.१.१०९|६.१.१०९|६.१.१०९ एङः पदान्तादति
In the room of ए or ओ final in a पद , and the short अ , which follows it, is substituted the single vowel of the form of the first (ए or ओ)।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.110|6.1.110 NGasiNGasoshcha|NGasiNGasoshcha|NGasiNGasoshcha 6.1.110|ङसिङसोश्च|ङसिङसोश्च ६.१.११०|६.१.११०|६.१.११० ङसिङसोश्च
In the room of ए or ओ (in the body of a word), + अ of the case-affix अस् of the Ablative and Genitive Singular, the single substitute is the form of the precedent.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.111|6.1.111 Rta ut‌|Rta ut‌|Rta ut‌ 6.1.111|ऋत उत्‌|ऋत उत्‌ ६.१.१११|६.१.१११|६.१.१११ ऋत उत्‌
In the room of ऋ + अ of the case-affix अस् of the Ablative and Genitive singular, the single substitute is the letter short उ।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.112|6.1.112 khyatyaat‌ parasya|khyatyaat‌ parasya|khyatyaat‌ parasya 6.1.112|ख्यत्यात्‌ परस्य|ख्यत्यात्‌ परस्य ६.१.११२|६.१.११२|६.१.११२ ख्यत्यात्‌ परस्य
There is the substitution of उ for the अ of अस् of the Ablative and Genitive Singular after सखि and पति , when for the इ of those two stems य् is substituted.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.113|6.1.113 ato roraplutaadaplute|ato roraplutaadaplute|ato roraplutaadaplute 6.1.113|अतो रोरप्लुतादप्लुते|अतो रोरप्लुतादप्लुते ६.१.११३|६.१.११३|६.१.११३ अतो रोरप्लुतादप्लुते
The उ is the substitute of रु (the र् substitute of a final स् ८.२.६६) when an अ , which is not a प्लुत, both precedes and follows it.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.114|6.1.114 hashi cha|hashi cha|hashi cha 6.1.114|हशि च|हशि च ६.१.११४|६.१.११४|६.१.११४ हशि च
The उ is the substitute of रु (the र् substitute of a final स् ८.२.६६) when it is followed by a soft consonant and preceded by an अप्लुत short अ।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.115|6.1.115 prakRtyaa.antaHpaadamavyapare|prakRtyaa.antaHpaadamavyapare|prakRtyaa.antaHpaadamavyapare 6.1.115|प्रकृत्याऽन्तःपादमव्यपरे|प्रकृत्याऽन्तःपादमव्यपरे ६.१.११५|६.१.११५|६.१.११५ प्रकृत्याऽन्तःपादमव्यपरे
The final ए or ओ and the following अ when occuring in the middle half of a foot of a Vedic verse, retain their original forms, except when the अ is followed by ख् or य्।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.116|6.1.116 avyaadavadyaadavakramuravrataayamavantvavasyuShu cha|avyaadavadyaadavakramuravrataayamavantvavasyuShu cha|avyaadavadyaadavakramuravrataayamavantvavasyuShu cha 6.1.116|अव्यादवद्यादवक्रमुरव्रतायमवन्त्ववस्युषु च|अव्यादवद्यादवक्रमुरव्रतायमवन्त्ववस्युषु च ६.१.११६|६.१.११६|६.१.११६ अव्यादवद्यादवक्रमुरव्रतायमवन्त्ववस्युषु च
The ए or ओ retain their original form in the middle of a Vedic verse, when the following words come after them (though the अ in these has a व् and य् following it) - अव्यात् , अवद्यात् , अवक्रमुः , अव्रत , अवन्तु , अवस्यु।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.117|6.1.117 yajuShyuraH|yajuShyuraH|yajuShyuraH 6.1.117|यजुष्युरः|यजुष्युरः ६.१.११७|६.१.११७|६.१.११७ यजुष्युरः
In the यजुर्वेद , the word उरस् when changed to उरो , retains it original form when followed by a short अ which is also retained.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.118|6.1.118 aapojuShaaNovRShNovarShiShThe.ambe.ambaale.ambikepuurve|aapojuShaaNovRShNovarShiShThe.ambe.ambaale.ambikepuurve|aapojuShaaNovRShNovarShiShThe.ambe.ambaale.ambikepuurve 6.1.118|आपोजुषाणोवृष्णोवर्षिष्ठेऽम्बेऽम्बालेऽम्बिकेपूर्वे|आपोजुषाणोवृष्णोवर्षिष्ठेऽम्बेऽम्बालेऽम्बिकेपूर्वे ६.१.११८|६.१.११८|६.१.११८ आपोजुषाणोवृष्णोवर्षिष्ठेऽम्बेऽम्बालेऽम्बिकेपूर्वे
In the यजुर्वेद , the short अ is retained after आपो , जुषनो , वृष्णो , वर्षिष्ठे and also in and after अम्बे or अम्बाले when they stand before अम्बिके।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.119|6.1.119 anga ityaadau cha|anga ityaadau cha|anga ityaadau cha 6.1.119|अङ्ग इत्यादौ च|अङ्ग इत्यादौ च ६.१.११९|६.१.११९|६.१.११९ अङ्ग इत्यादौ च
In the यजुर्वेद , when the word अङ्गे is followed by अङ्गे , the subsequent short अ is retained, as well as the preceding ए or ओ।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.120|6.1.120 anudaatte cha kudhapare|anudaatte cha kudhapare|anudaatte cha kudhapare 6.1.120|अनुदात्ते च कुधपरे|अनुदात्ते च कुधपरे ६.१.१२०|६.१.१२०|६.१.१२० अनुदात्ते च कुधपरे
In the यजुर्वेद , when an अनुदात्त अ is followed by a Guttural or a ध, the antecedent ए or ओ retains it s form, as well as this subsequent अ।<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.121|6.1.121 avapathaasi cha|avapathaasi cha|avapathaasi cha 6.1.121|अवपथासि च|अवपथासि च ६.१.१२१|६.१.१२१|६.१.१२१ अवपथासि च
In the यजुर्वेद , when the gravely accented अ of अवपथास् follows ए or ओ , the vowels retain their original form.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.122|6.1.122 sarvatra vibhaaShaa goH|sarvatra vibhaaShaa goH|sarvatra vibhaaShaa goH 6.1.122|सर्वत्र विभाषा गोः|सर्वत्र विभाषा गोः ६.१.१२२|६.१.१२२|६.१.१२२ सर्वत्र विभाषा गोः
After गो the subsequent अ may optionally be retained everywhere, in the Vedas as well as in the secular literature.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.123|6.1.123 avaNG sphoTaayanasya|avaNG sphoTaayanasya|avaNG sphoTaayanasya 6.1.123|अवङ् स्फोटायनस्य|अवङ् स्फोटायनस्य ६.१.१२३|६.१.१२३|६.१.१२३ अवङ् स्फोटायनस्य
According to the opinion of स्फोटायन , there is the substitution of अवङ् for the ओ of गो when it is followed by any vowel.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.124|6.1.124 indre cha (nityam)|indre cha (nityam)|indre cha (nityam) 6.1.124|इन्द्रे च (नित्यम्)|इन्द्रे च (नित्यम्) ६.१.१२४|६.१.१२४|६.१.१२४ इन्द्रे च (नित्यम्)
The substitution of अव for the ओ of गो is compulsory when a vowel to be found in the word इन्द्र follows it.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.125|6.1.125 plutapragRhyaa achi nityam|plutapragRhyaa achi nityam|plutapragRhyaa achi nityam 6.1.125|प्लुतप्रगृह्या अचि नित्यम्|प्लुतप्रगृह्या अचि नित्यम् ६.१.१२५|६.१.१२५|६.१.१२५ प्लुतप्रगृह्या अचि नित्यम्
The प्लुत (८.२.८२ etc.) and प्रगृह्य (१.१.११ etc.) vowels remain unaltered when followed by a vowel (so far as the operation of that vowel is concerned).<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.126|6.1.126 aaNGo.anunaasikashChandasi|aaNGo.anunaasikashChandasi|aaNGo.anunaasikashChandasi 6.1.126|आङोऽनुनासिकश्छन्दसि|आङोऽनुनासिकश्छन्दसि ६.१.१२६|६.१.१२६|६.१.१२६ आङोऽनुनासिकश्छन्दसि
For the adverb आ , is substituted in the छन्दस् the nasalised आँ , when a vowel follows it, and it retains its original form.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.127|6.1.127 iko.asavarNe shaakalyasya hrasvashcha|iko.asavarNe shaakalyasya hrasvashcha|iko.asavarNe shaakalyasya hrasvashcha 6.1.127|इकोऽसवर्णे शाकल्यस्य ह्रस्वश्च|इकोऽसवर्णे शाकल्यस्य ह्रस्वश्च ६.१.१२७|६.१.१२७|६.१.१२७ इकोऽसवर्णे शाकल्यस्य ह्रस्वश्च
According to the opinion of शाकल्य , the simple vowels with the exception of अ , when followed by a non-homogenous vowel, retain their original forms; and if the vowel is long, it is shortened.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.128|6.1.128 RtyakaH|RtyakaH|RtyakaH 6.1.128|ऋत्यकः|ऋत्यकः ६.१.१२८|६.१.१२८|६.१.१२८ ऋत्यकः
According to the opinion of शाकल्य , the simple vowel followed by ऋ retains its original form, and if the vowel is long, it is shortened.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.129|6.1.129 aplutavadupasthite|aplutavadupasthite|aplutavadupasthite 6.1.129|अप्लुतवदुपस्थिते|अप्लुतवदुपस्थिते ६.१.१२९|६.१.१२९|६.१.१२९ अप्लुतवदुपस्थिते
Before the word इति in the पदपाठ , a प्लुत vowel is treated like an ordinary अप्लुत vowel.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.130|6.1.130 ii3 chaakravarmaNasya|ii3 chaakravarmaNasya|ii3 chaakravarmaNasya 6.1.130|ई३ चाक्रवर्मणस्य|ई३ चाक्रवर्मणस्य ६.१.१३०|६.१.१३०|६.१.१३० ई३ चाक्रवर्मणस्य
According to the opinion of चाक्रवर्मण , the प्लुत ई3 followed by a vowel is treated like an ordinary vowel.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.131|6.1.131 diva ut‌|diva ut‌|diva ut‌ 6.1.131|दिव उत्‌|दिव उत्‌ ६.१.१३१|६.१.१३१|६.१.१३१ दिव उत्‌
For the final of the nominal-stem दिव् , there is the substitution of उ , when it is a पद (१.४.१४ etc.).<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.132|6.1.132 etattadoH sulopo.akoranaNJsamaase hali|etattadoH sulopo.akoranaNJsamaase hali|etattadoH sulopo.akoranaNJsamaase hali 6.1.132|एतत्तदोः सुलोपोऽकोरनञ्समासे हलि|एतत्तदोः सुलोपोऽकोरनञ्समासे हलि ६.१.१३२|६.१.१३२|६.१.१३२ एतत्तदोः सुलोपोऽकोरनञ्समासे हलि
After एतद् and तद् there is elision of the case-affix स् (of the Nominative Singular), when a consonant follows it, when these words are not combined with क (५.३.७१) and have not the Negative Particle in composition.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.133|6.1.133 syashChandasi bahulam|syashChandasi bahulam|syashChandasi bahulam 6.1.133|स्यश्छन्दसि बहुलम्|स्यश्छन्दसि बहुलम् ६.१.१३३|६.१.१३३|६.१.१३३ स्यश्छन्दसि बहुलम्
In the छन्दस् , the case-affix of the nominative singular is diversely elided after स्य , when a consonant follows it.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.134|6.1.134 so.achi lope chet‌ paadapuuraNam|so.achi lope chet‌ paadapuuraNam|so.achi lope chet‌ paadapuuraNam 6.1.134|सोऽचि लोपे चेत्‌ पादपूरणम्|सोऽचि लोपे चेत्‌ पादपूरणम् ६.१.१३४|६.१.१३४|६.१.१३४ सोऽचि लोपे चेत्‌ पादपूरणम्
The case affix of सस् 'he', is elided before a vowel, if by such elision the meter of the foot becomes complete.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.135|6.1.135 suT kaat‌ puurvaH|suT kaat‌ puurvaH|suT kaat‌ puurvaH 6.1.135|सुट् कात्‌ पूर्वः|सुट् कात्‌ पूर्वः ६.१.१३५|६.१.१३५|६.१.१३५ सुट् कात्‌ पूर्वः
Up to ६.१.१५७ inclusive, the following sentence is to be supplied in every aphorism - 'before क is added स्'.<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.136|6.1.136 aDabhyaasavyavaaye.api|aDabhyaasavyavaaye.api|aDabhyaasavyavaaye.api 6.1.136|अडभ्यासव्यवायेऽपि|अडभ्यासव्यवायेऽपि ६.१.१३६|६.१.१३६|६.१.१३६ अडभ्यासव्यवायेऽपि
The augment सुट् is placed before क even when the augment अट् ६.४.७१ or the Reduplicate intervenes (between the preposition and the verb).<br><br>Terms: संहितायाम्

6.1.137|6.1.137 samparyupebhyaH karotau bhuuShaNe|samparyupebhyaH karotau bhuuShaNe|samparyupebhyaH karotau bhuuShaNe 6.1.137|सम्पर्युपेभ्यः करोतौ भूषणे|सम्पर्युपेभ्यः करोतौ भूषणे ६.१.१३७|६.१.१३७|६.१.१३७ सम्पर्युपेभ्यः करोतौ भूषणे
The augment सुट् is placed before क when सम् , परि , and उप are followed by the verb कृ and the sense is that of ornamenting.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.138|6.1.138 samavaaye cha|samavaaye cha|samavaaye cha 6.1.138|समवाये च|समवाये च ६.१.१३८|६.१.१३८|६.१.१३८ समवाये च
The augment सुट् is placed before क even when सम् , परि , and उप are followed by the verb कृ and the sense being that of combining.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.139|6.1.139 upaat‌ pratiyatnavaikRtavaakyaadhyaahaareShu|upaat‌ pratiyatnavaikRtavaakyaadhyaahaareShu|upaat‌ pratiyatnavaikRtavaakyaadhyaahaareShu 6.1.139|उपात्‌ प्रतियत्नवैकृतवाक्याध्याहारेषु|उपात्‌ प्रतियत्नवैकृतवाक्याध्याहारेषु ६.१.१३९|६.१.१३९|६.१.१३९ उपात्‌ प्रतियत्नवैकृतवाक्याध्याहारेषु
The augment सुट् is placed before क , when the verb कृ comes after उप , and the sense is that of 'to take pains for something, to prepare, and to supply and ellipses in a discourse'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.140|6.1.140 kiratau lavane|kiratau lavane|kiratau lavane 6.1.140|किरतौ लवने|किरतौ लवने ६.१.१४०|६.१.१४०|६.१.१४० किरतौ लवने
The augment सुट् is placed before क , when the verb कृ comes after उप , and the sense is that of 'to cut or to split'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.141|6.1.141 hiMsaayaaM prateshcha|hiMsaayaaM prateshcha|hiMsaayaaM prateshcha 6.1.141|हिंसायां प्रतेश्च|हिंसायां प्रतेश्च ६.१.१४१|६.१.१४१|६.१.१४१ हिंसायां प्रतेश्च
The augment सुट् is placed before क , when the verb कृ comes after उप and प्रति and the sense 'to cause suffering'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.142|6.1.142 apaachchatuShpaachChakuniShvaalekhane|apaachchatuShpaachChakuniShvaalekhane|apaachchatuShpaachChakuniShvaalekhane 6.1.142|अपाच्चतुष्पाच्छकुनिष्वालेखने|अपाच्चतुष्पाच्छकुनिष्वालेखने ६.१.१४२|६.१.१४२|६.१.१४२ अपाच्चतुष्पाच्छकुनिष्वालेखने
The augment सुट् is placed before क , when the verb कृ comes after अप and the sense is 'the scraping of earth by four-footed animals or birds'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.143|6.1.143 kustumburuuNi jaatiH|kustumburuuNi jaatiH|kustumburuuNi jaatiH 6.1.143|कुस्तुम्बुरूणि जातिः|कुस्तुम्बुरूणि जातिः ६.१.१४३|६.१.१४३|६.१.१४३ कुस्तुम्बुरूणि जातिः
The word कुस्तुम्बुरु is irregularly, formed with the augment सुट् and means 'a species of herb'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.144|6.1.144 aparasparaaH kriyaasaatatye|aparasparaaH kriyaasaatatye|aparasparaaH kriyaasaatatye 6.1.144|अपरस्पराः क्रियासातत्ये|अपरस्पराः क्रियासातत्ये ६.१.१४४|६.१.१४४|६.१.१४४ अपरस्पराः क्रियासातत्ये
The word अपस्पराः is formed by the augment सुट् when the sense is that of 'uninterrupted action'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.145|6.1.145 goShpadaM sevitaasevitapramaaNeShu|goShpadaM sevitaasevitapramaaNeShu|goShpadaM sevitaasevitapramaaNeShu 6.1.145|गोष्पदं सेवितासेवितप्रमाणेषु|गोष्पदं सेवितासेवितप्रमाणेषु ६.१.१४५|६.१.१४५|६.१.१४५ गोष्पदं सेवितासेवितप्रमाणेषु
The word गोष्पद is formed by सुट् , when meaning a locality visited or not visited by cows, or when it means quantity.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.146|6.1.146 aaspadaM pratiShThaayaam‌|aaspadaM pratiShThaayaam‌|aaspadaM pratiShThaayaam‌ 6.1.146|आस्पदं प्रतिष्ठायाम्‌|आस्पदं प्रतिष्ठायाम्‌ ६.१.१४६|६.१.१४६|६.१.१४६ आस्पदं प्रतिष्ठायाम्‌
The word आस्पद is formed by सुट् when meaning 'a place or position'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.147|6.1.147 aashcharyamanitye|aashcharyamanitye|aashcharyamanitye 6.1.147|आश्चर्यमनित्ये|आश्चर्यमनित्ये ६.१.१४७|६.१.१४७|६.१.१४७ आश्चर्यमनित्ये
