6.1.150|6.1.150 viShkiraH shakunirvikaro vaa|viShkiraH shakunirvikaro vaa|viShkiraH shakunirvikaro vaa 6.1.150|विष्किरः शकुनिर्विकरो वा|विष्किरः शकुनिर्विकरो वा ६.१.१५०|६.१.१५०|६.१.१५० विष्किरः शकुनिर्विकरो वा
The word विषिकर is formed with सुट् optionally when denoting a kind of bird, the other form being विकार।<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.151|6.1.151 hrasvaachchandrottarapade mantre|hrasvaachchandrottarapade mantre|hrasvaachchandrottarapade mantre 6.1.151|ह्रस्वाच्चन्द्रोत्तरपदे मन्त्रे|ह्रस्वाच्चन्द्रोत्तरपदे मन्त्रे ६.१.१५१|६.१.१५१|६.१.१५१ ह्रस्वाच्चन्द्रोत्तरपदे मन्त्रे
In a मन्त्र , the सुट् is added to चन्द्र when it is second member in a compound and is preceded by a short vowel.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.152|6.1.152 pratiShkashashcha kasheH|pratiShkashashcha kasheH|pratiShkashashcha kasheH 6.1.152|प्रतिष्कशश्च कशेः|प्रतिष्कशश्च कशेः ६.१.१५२|६.१.१५२|६.१.१५२ प्रतिष्कशश्च कशेः
To the root कश् 'to go, to punish', is added the augment सुट् , when preceded by the preposition प्रति , the form being प्रतिष्कशः।<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.153|6.1.153 praskaNvaharishchandraavRShii|praskaNvaharishchandraavRShii|praskaNvaharishchandraavRShii 6.1.153|प्रस्कण्वहरिश्चन्द्रावृषी|प्रस्कण्वहरिश्चन्द्रावृषी ६.१.१५३|६.१.१५३|६.१.१५३ प्रस्कण्वहरिश्चन्द्रावृषी
The words प्रस्कण्व and हरिश्चन्द्र are formed by सुट् meaning the two Rishis of that name.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.154|6.1.154 maskaramaskariNau veNuparivraajakayoH|maskaramaskariNau veNuparivraajakayoH|maskaramaskariNau veNuparivraajakayoH 6.1.154|मस्करमस्करिणौ वेणुपरिव्राजकयोः|मस्करमस्करिणौ वेणुपरिव्राजकयोः ६.१.१५४|६.१.१५४|६.१.१५४ मस्करमस्करिणौ वेणुपरिव्राजकयोः
The word मस्कर means 'a bamboo', and मस्करिन् means 'a medicant monk'.<br><br>Terms: सुट् augment

6.1.155|6.1.155 kaastiiraajastunde nagare|kaastiiraajastunde nagare|kaastiiraajastunde nagare 6.1.155|कास्तीराजस्तुन्दे नगरे|कास्तीराजस्तुन्दे नगरे ६.१.१५५|६.१.१५५|६.१.१५५ कास्तीराजस्तुन्दे नगरे
The words कास्तर and अजस्तुन्द are names of cities.<br><br>Terms: word meaning

