The word कारस्कर means 'a tree'.<br><br>Terms: word meaning

6.1.157|6.1.157 paaraskaraprabhRtiini cha saMJNaayaam|paaraskaraprabhRtiini cha saMJNaayaam|paaraskaraprabhRtiini cha saMJNaayaam 6.1.157|पारस्करप्रभृतीनि च संज्ञायाम्|पारस्करप्रभृतीनि च संज्ञायाम् ६.१.१५७|६.१.१५७|६.१.१५७ पारस्करप्रभृतीनि च संज्ञायाम्
The words पारस्कर etc. are Names.<br><br>Terms: word meaning

6.1.158|6.1.158 anudaattaM padamekavarjam‌|anudaattaM padamekavarjam‌|anudaattaM padamekavarjam‌ 6.1.158|अनुदात्तं पदमेकवर्जम्‌|अनुदात्तं पदमेकवर्जम्‌ ६.१.१५८|६.१.१५८|६.१.१५८ अनुदात्तं पदमेकवर्जम्‌
A word is, with the exception of one syllable, unaccented.<br><br>Terms: word meaning

6.1.159|6.1.159 karShaatvato ghaNJo.anta udaattaH|karShaatvato ghaNJo.anta udaattaH|karShaatvato ghaNJo.anta udaattaH 6.1.159|कर्षात्वतो घञोऽन्त उदात्तः|कर्षात्वतो घञोऽन्त उदात्तः ६.१.१५९|६.१.१५९|६.१.१५९ कर्षात्वतो घञोऽन्त उदात्तः
A stem formed with the कृत-affix घञ् has the acute accent on the end-syllable, if it is formed from the root कृष् (कर्षति) or has a long आ in it.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.160|6.1.160 unChaadiinaaM cha|unChaadiinaaM cha|unChaadiinaaM cha 6.1.160|उञ्छादीनां च|उञ्छादीनां च ६.१.१६०|६.१.१६०|६.१.१६० उञ्छादीनां च
The words उच्छ etc. have acute accent on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.161|6.1.161 anudaattasya cha yatrodaattalopaH|anudaattasya cha yatrodaattalopaH|anudaattasya cha yatrodaattalopaH 6.1.161|अनुदात्तस्य च यत्रोदात्तलोपः|अनुदात्तस्य च यत्रोदात्तलोपः ६.१.१६१|६.१.१६१|६.१.१६१ अनुदात्तस्य च यत्रोदात्तलोपः
An unaccented vowel gets also the acute accent, when on account of it preceding acute is elided.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.162|6.1.162 dhaatoH|dhaatoH|dhaatoH 6.1.162|धातोः|धातोः ६.१.१६२|६.१.१६२|६.१.१६२ धातोः
A root has the acute on the end syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.163|6.1.163 chitaH|chitaH|chitaH 6.1.163|चितः|चितः ६.१.१६३|६.१.१६३|६.१.१६३ चितः
A stem (formed by an affix or an augment or substitute) having an indicatory च् gets acute on the end syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.164|6.1.164 taddhitasya|taddhitasya|taddhitasya 6.1.164|तद्धितस्य|तद्धितस्य ६.१.१६४|६.१.१६४|६.१.१६४ तद्धितस्य
A stem formed with a तद्धित-affix having an indicatory च् , has acute on the end syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.165|6.1.165 kitaH|kitaH|kitaH 6.1.165|कितः|कितः ६.१.१६५|६.१.१६५|६.१.१६५ कितः
A stem formed by a तद्धित-affix having an indicatory क , has acute accent on the end syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-तद्धित

6.1.166|6.1.166 tisRbhyo jasaH|tisRbhyo jasaH|tisRbhyo jasaH 6.1.166|तिसृभ्यो जसः|तिसृभ्यो जसः ६.१.१६६|६.१.१६६|६.१.१६६ तिसृभ्यो जसः
The Nominative Plural (जस्) of तिस् has acute accent on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-तद्धित

6.1.167|6.1.167 chaturaH shasi|chaturaH shasi|chaturaH shasi 6.1.167|चतुरः शसि|चतुरः शसि ६.१.१६७|६.१.१६७|६.१.१६७ चतुरः शसि
The word चतुर् , followed by the Accusative Plural, has acute accent on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.168|6.1.168 saavekaachastRtiiyaa.a.adivibhaktiH|saavekaachastRtiiyaa.a.adivibhaktiH|saavekaachastRtiiyaa.a.adivibhaktiH 6.1.168|सावेकाचस्तृतीयाऽऽदिविभक्तिः|सावेकाचस्तृतीयाऽऽदिविभक्तिः ६.१.१६८|६.१.१६८|६.१.१६८ सावेकाचस्तृतीयाऽऽदिविभक्तिः
The case affixes of the Instrumental and of the cases that follow it have the acute accent, if the stem in the Locative Plural is monosyllablic.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.169|6.1.169 antodattaaduttarapadaadanyatarasyaamanityasamaase|antodattaaduttarapadaadanyatarasyaamanityasamaase|antodattaaduttarapadaadanyatarasyaamanityasamaase 6.1.169|अन्तोदत्तादुत्तरपदादन्यतरस्यामनित्यसमासे|अन्तोदत्तादुत्तरपदादन्यतरस्यामनित्यसमासे ६.१.१६९|६.१.१६९|६.१.१६९ अन्तोदत्तादुत्तरपदादन्यतरस्यामनित्यसमासे
The same case endings may optionally have the acute accent, if the monosyllabic word stands at the end of a compound, and has acute accent on the final, when the compound can be easily unloosened.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.170|6.1.170 anceshChandasyasarvanaamasthaanam|anceshChandasyasarvanaamasthaanam|anceshChandasyasarvanaamasthaanam 6.1.170|अञ्चेश्छन्दस्यसर्वनामस्थानम्|अञ्चेश्छन्दस्यसर्वनामस्थानम् ६.१.१७०|६.१.१७०|६.१.१७० अञ्चेश्छन्दस्यसर्वनामस्थानम्
In the छन्दस् , the case-endings other than the सर्वनामस्थान , get the acute accent when coming after अञ्चि।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति-समास

6.1.171|6.1.171 UDidampadaadyappumraidyubhyaH|UDidampadaadyappumraidyubhyaH|UDidampadaadyappumraidyubhyaH 6.1.171|ऊडिदम्पदाद्यप्पुम्रैद्युभ्यः|ऊडिदम्पदाद्यप्पुम्रैद्युभ्यः ६.१.१७१|६.१.१७१|६.१.१७१ ऊडिदम्पदाद्यप्पुम्रैद्युभ्यः
The same (असर्वनामस्थान) case-endings have the acute accent, when the stem ends in वाह् , also after इदम् after पद् etc. (upto ६.१.६३) after अप , पुंस् , रै and दिव्।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति-समास-छन्दस

6.1.172|6.1.172 aShTano diirghaat‌|aShTano diirghaat‌|aShTano diirghaat‌ 6.1.172|अष्टनो दीर्घात्‌|अष्टनो दीर्घात्‌ ६.१.१७२|६.१.१७२|६.१.१७२ अष्टनो दीर्घात्‌
The असर्वनामस्थान case-endings after अष्टन् 'eight', have acute accent, when it gets the form अष्टा।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.173|6.1.173 shaturanumo nadyajaadii|shaturanumo nadyajaadii|shaturanumo nadyajaadii 6.1.173|शतुरनुमो नद्यजादी|शतुरनुमो नद्यजादी ६.१.१७३|६.१.१७३|६.१.१७३ शतुरनुमो नद्यजादी
After an oxytone Particle in अत् the feminine suffix ई , (नदि) and the case endings beginning with vowels (with the exception of strong cases) have acute accent, when the participial affix has not the augment न् (i.e. is not अन्त).<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.174|6.1.174 udaattayaNo halpuurvaat‌|udaattayaNo halpuurvaat‌|udaattayaNo halpuurvaat‌ 6.1.174|उदात्तयणो हल्पूर्वात्‌|उदात्तयणो हल्पूर्वात्‌ ६.१.१७४|६.१.१७४|६.१.१७४ उदात्तयणो हल्पूर्वात्‌
The same endings have the acute accent, when for the acutely accented final vowel of the stem, a semi-vowel is substituted, and which is preceded by a consonant.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.175|6.1.175 noNGdhaatvoH|noNGdhaatvoH|noNGdhaatvoH 6.1.175|नोङ्धात्वोः|नोङ्धात्वोः ६.१.१७५|६.१.१७५|६.१.१७५ नोङ्धात्वोः
But not so, when the vowel is of the feminine affix ऊ ४.१.६६, or the final of a root.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.176|6.1.176 hrasvanuDbhyaaM matup‌|hrasvanuDbhyaaM matup‌|hrasvanuDbhyaaM matup‌ 6.1.176|ह्रस्वनुड्भ्यां मतुप्‌|ह्रस्वनुड्भ्यां मतुप्‌ ६.१.१७६|६.१.१७६|६.१.१७६ ह्रस्वनुड्भ्यां मतुप्‌
The otherwise unaccented मत् (वत्) takes the acute accent, when an oxytoned stem ends in a light vowel, or the affix has before it the augment न् ८.२.१६.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.177|6.1.177 naamanyatarasyaam‌|naamanyatarasyaam‌|naamanyatarasyaam‌ 6.1.177|नामन्यतरस्याम्‌|नामन्यतरस्याम्‌ ६.१.१७७|६.१.१७७|६.१.१७७ नामन्यतरस्याम्‌
After an oxytoned stem which ends in a light vowel, the genitive ending नाम् has optionally the acute accent.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.178|6.1.178 NGyaashChandasi bahulam|NGyaashChandasi bahulam|NGyaashChandasi bahulam 6.1.178|ङ्याश्छन्दसि बहुलम्|ङ्याश्छन्दसि बहुलम् ६.१.१७८|६.१.१७८|६.१.१७८ ङ्याश्छन्दसि बहुलम्
In the छन्दस , the ending नाम् has diversely the acute accent after the feminine affix ई।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.179|6.1.179 ShaTtrichaturbhyo halaadiH|ShaTtrichaturbhyo halaadiH|ShaTtrichaturbhyo halaadiH 6.1.179|षट्त्रिचतुर्भ्यो हलादिः|षट्त्रिचतुर्भ्यो हलादिः ६.१.१७९|६.१.१७९|६.१.१७९ षट्त्रिचतुर्भ्यो हलादिः
The case-endings beginning with a consonant, have the acute accent after the Numerals called षट् १.१.२४, as well as after त्रि and चतुर् ।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.180|6.1.180 jhalyupottamam|jhalyupottamam|jhalyupottamam 6.1.180|झल्युपोत्तमम्|झल्युपोत्तमम् ६.१.१८०|६.१.१८०|६.१.१८० झल्युपोत्तमम्
The above numerals, when taking a case-affix beginning with a भस् or स् , get the acute accent on the penultimate syllable, when the said numerals assume a form consisting of three or more syllables.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.181|6.1.181 vibhaaShaa bhaaShaayaam|vibhaaShaa bhaaShaayaam|vibhaaShaa bhaaShaayaam 6.1.181|विभाषा भाषायाम्|विभाषा भाषायाम् ६.१.१८१|६.१.१८१|६.१.१८१ विभाषा भाषायाम्
In the Secular language this is optional.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.182|6.1.182 na goshvantsaavavarNaraaDankrunkRdbhyaH|na goshvantsaavavarNaraaDankrunkRdbhyaH|na goshvantsaavavarNaraaDankrunkRdbhyaH 6.1.182|न गोश्वन्त्साववर्णराडङ्क्रुङ्कृद्भ्यः|न गोश्वन्त्साववर्णराडङ्क्रुङ्कृद्भ्यः ६.१.१८२|६.१.१८२|६.१.१८२ न गोश्वन्त्साववर्णराडङ्क्रुङ्कृद्भ्यः
The foregoing rules from ६.१.१६८ downwards have no applicability after गो , and श्वन् and words ending in them; nor after a stem which before the case ending of the Nominative Singular has अ or आ , nor after रज् , or after a stem ending in अञ्च् , nor as well as after कुञ्च् and कृत्।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.183|6.1.183 divo jhal|divo jhal|divo jhal 6.1.183|दिवो झल्|दिवो झल् ६.१.१८३|६.१.१८३|६.१.१८३ दिवो झल्
After दिव् a case-ending beginning with भ or स is unaccented.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.184|6.1.184 nR chaanyatarasyaam|nR chaanyatarasyaam|nR chaanyatarasyaam 6.1.184|नृ चान्यतरस्याम्|नृ चान्यतरस्याम् ६.१.१८४|६.१.१८४|६.१.१८४ नृ चान्यतरस्याम्
After नृ , a case-ending beginning with भ or स is optionally unaccented.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.185|6.1.185 titsvaritam|titsvaritam|titsvaritam 6.1.185|तित्स्वरितम्|तित्स्वरितम् ६.१.१८५|६.१.१८५|६.१.१८५ तित्स्वरितम्
An affix having an indicatory त् , is स्वरित i.e. has circumflex accent.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.186|6.1.186 taasyanudaattenNGidadupadeshaallasaarvadhaatukamanudaattamahanviNGoH|taasyanudaattenNGidadupadeshaallasaarvadhaatukamanudaattamahanviNGoH|taasyanudaattenNGidadupadeshaallasaarvadhaatukamanudaattamahanviNGoH 6.1.186|तास्यनुदात्तेन्ङिददुपदेशाल्लसार्वधातुकमनुदात्तमहन्विङोः|तास्यनुदात्तेन्ङिददुपदेशाल्लसार्वधातुकमनुदात्तमहन्विङोः ६.१.१८६|६.१.१८६|६.१.१८६ तास्यनुदात्तेन्ङिददुपदेशाल्लसार्वधातुकमनुदात्तमहन्विङोः
The Personal-endings and their substitutes ३.२.१२४-126 are, when they are सार्वधातुक ३.४.११३ etc., unaccented after the charactertistic of the Periphrastic Future (तासि) after a root which in the धातुपाठ has an unaccented vowel or a ङ् (with the exception of ह्नुङ् and इङ्) as indicatory letter, as well as after what has a final अ in the Grammatical System of Instruction (उपदेश)।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.187|6.1.187 aadiH sicho.anyatarasyaam|aadiH sicho.anyatarasyaam|aadiH sicho.anyatarasyaam 6.1.187|आदिः सिचोऽन्यतरस्याम्|आदिः सिचोऽन्यतरस्याम् ६.१.१८७|६.१.१८७|६.१.१८७ आदिः सिचोऽन्यतरस्याम्
The सिच् Aorist, the first syllable may optionally have the acute accent.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्-प्रत्यय

6.1.188|6.1.188 svapaadirhiMsaamachyaniTi|svapaadirhiMsaamachyaniTi|svapaadirhiMsaamachyaniTi 6.1.188|स्वपादिर्हिंसामच्यनिटि|स्वपादिर्हिंसामच्यनिटि ६.१.१८८|६.१.१८८|६.१.१८८ स्वपादिर्हिंसामच्यनिटि
The acute accent is optionally on the first syllable when a Personal-ending, being सार्वधातुक tense affix beginning with a vowel, provided that the vowel is not the augment इट् , follows after स्वप् etc., or after हिंस्।<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.189|6.1.189 abhyastaanaamaadiH|abhyastaanaamaadiH|abhyastaanaamaadiH 6.1.189|अभ्यस्तानामादिः|अभ्यस्तानामादिः ६.१.१८९|६.१.१८९|६.१.१८९ अभ्यस्तानामादिः
The acute accent falls on the first syllable of the reduplicate verbs when followed by an affix beginning with a vowel (the vowel being not नुट्) and being a सार्वधातुक Personal-ending.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.190|6.1.190 anudaatte cha|anudaatte cha|anudaatte cha 6.1.190|अनुदात्ते च|अनुदात्ते च ६.१.१९०|६.१.१९०|६.१.१९० अनुदात्ते च
Also when the unaccented endings of the three persons in the singular follow, the first syllable of the reduplicate has the acute.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.191|6.1.191 sarvasya supi|sarvasya supi|sarvasya supi 6.1.191|सर्वस्य सुपि|सर्वस्य सुपि ६.१.१९१|६.१.१९१|६.१.१९१ सर्वस्य सुपि
The acute is on the first syllable of सर्व when the case-endings follow.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.192|6.1.192 bhiihriibhRhumadajanadhanadaridraajaagaraaM pratyayaat puurvam piti|bhiihriibhRhumadajanadhanadaridraajaagaraaM pratyayaat puurvam piti|bhiihriibhRhumadajanadhanadaridraajaagaraaM pratyayaat puurvam piti 6.1.192|भीह्रीभृहुमदजनधनदरिद्राजागरां प्रत्ययात् पूर्वम् पिति|भीह्रीभृहुमदजनधनदरिद्राजागरां प्रत्ययात् पूर्वम् पिति ६.१.१९२|६.१.१९२|६.१.१९२ भीह्रीभृहुमदजनधनदरिद्राजागरां प्रत्ययात् पूर्वम् पिति
In भी , ह्री , भृ , हु , मद् , जन् , धन् , दरिद्रा and जागृ , and in their reduplicates, the acute accent is, before the सार्वधातुक unaccented endings of the three persons in singular, (पित्), on the syllable which precedes the affix.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.193|6.1.193 liti|liti|liti 6.1.193|लिति|लिति ६.१.१९३|६.१.१९३|६.१.१९३ लिति
The acute accent falls on the syllable immediately preceding the affix that has an indicatory ल्।<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.194|6.1.194 aadirNamulyanyatarasyaam|aadirNamulyanyatarasyaam|aadirNamulyanyatarasyaam 6.1.194|आदिर्णमुल्यन्यतरस्याम्|आदिर्णमुल्यन्यतरस्याम् ६.१.१९४|६.१.१९४|६.१.१९४ आदिर्णमुल्यन्यतरस्याम्
The first syllable may be optionally acute when the absolutive affix णमुल् follows.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.195|6.1.195 achaH kartRyaki|achaH kartRyaki|achaH kartRyaki 6.1.195|अचः कर्तृयकि|अचः कर्तृयकि ६.१.१९५|६.१.१९५|६.१.१९५ अचः कर्तृयकि
The roots which are exhibited in धातुपाठ with a final vowel, may be optionally have the acute on the first syllable, before the affixes of the Passive (यक्), when the sense of the verb is Reflexive.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.196|6.1.196 thali cha seTiiDanto vaa|thali cha seTiiDanto vaa|thali cha seTiiDanto vaa 6.1.196|थलि च सेटीडन्तो वा|थलि च सेटीडन्तो वा ६.१.१९६|६.१.१९६|६.१.१९६ थलि च सेटीडन्तो वा
Before the ending थ of the Perfect, Second Person Singular, when this ending takes the augment इ ; the acute accent falls either on the first syllable, or on this इ , or on the personal ending.<br><br>Terms: accent-धातु

6.1.197|6.1.197 NJnityaadirnityam|NJnityaadirnityam|NJnityaadirnityam 6.1.197|ञ्नित्यादिर्नित्यम्|ञ्नित्यादिर्नित्यम् ६.१.१९७|६.१.१९७|६.१.१९७ ञ्नित्यादिर्नित्यम्
Whatever is derived with an affix having an indicatory ञ् or न् , has the acute accent invariably on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.198|6.1.198 aamantritasya cha|aamantritasya cha|aamantritasya cha 6.1.198|आमन्त्रितस्य च|आमन्त्रितस्य च ६.१.१९८|६.१.१९८|६.१.१९८ आमन्त्रितस्य च
The first syllable of a Vocative gets the acute accent.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.199|6.1.199 pathimathoH sarvanaamasthaane|pathimathoH sarvanaamasthaane|pathimathoH sarvanaamasthaane 6.1.199|पथिमथोः सर्वनामस्थाने|पथिमथोः सर्वनामस्थाने ६.१.१९९|६.१.१९९|६.१.१९९ पथिमथोः सर्वनामस्थाने
The acute accent is on the first syllable of पथिन् and मथिन् when followed by a strong case-ending.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

6.1.200|6.1.200 antashcha tavai yugapat‌|antashcha tavai yugapat‌|antashcha tavai yugapat‌ 6.1.200|अन्तश्च तवै युगपत्‌|अन्तश्च तवै युगपत्‌ ६.१.२००|६.१.२००|६.१.२०० अन्तश्च तवै युगपत्‌
The Infinitive in तवै has the acute on the first syllable and on the last syllable at one and the same time.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति-words

6.1.201|6.1.201 xayo nivaase|xayo nivaase|xayo nivaase 6.1.201|क्षयो निवासे|क्षयो निवासे ६.१.२०१|६.१.२०१|६.१.२०१ क्षयो निवासे
The word क्षय has the acute on the first syllable and on the last syllable at one and the same time.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.202|6.1.202 jayaH karaNam|jayaH karaNam|jayaH karaNam 6.1.202|जयः करणम्|जयः करणम् ६.१.२०२|६.१.२०२|६.१.२०२ जयः करणम्
The acute accent falls on the first syllable of जय , in the sense of 'whereby one attains victory'.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.203|6.1.203 vRShaadiinaaM cha|vRShaadiinaaM cha|vRShaadiinaaM cha 6.1.203|वृषादीनां च|वृषादीनां च ६.१.२०३|६.१.२०३|६.१.२०३ वृषादीनां च
The words वृष etc. have the acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.204|6.1.204 saMJNaayaamupamaanam‌|saMJNaayaamupamaanam‌|saMJNaayaamupamaanam‌ 6.1.204|संज्ञायामुपमानम्‌|संज्ञायामुपमानम्‌ ६.१.२०४|६.१.२०४|६.१.२०४ संज्ञायामुपमानम्‌
The acute accent falls on the first syllable of that word with which something is likened, provided that it is a name.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.205|6.1.205 niShThaa cha dvyajanaat‌|niShThaa cha dvyajanaat‌|niShThaa cha dvyajanaat‌ 6.1.205|निष्ठा च द्व्यजनात्‌|निष्ठा च द्व्यजनात्‌ ६.१.२०५|६.१.२०५|६.१.२०५ निष्ठा च द्व्यजनात्‌
A disyllabic Participle in त (निष्ठा) when a Name has the acute on the first syllable, but not if the first syllable has an आ।<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.206|6.1.206 shuShkadhRShTau|shuShkadhRShTau|shuShkadhRShTau 6.1.206|शुष्कधृष्टौ|शुष्कधृष्टौ ६.१.२०६|६.१.२०६|६.१.२०६ शुष्कधृष्टौ
Also शुष्क and धृष्ट have acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.207|6.1.207 aashitaH kartaa|aashitaH kartaa|aashitaH kartaa 6.1.207|आशितः कर्ता|आशितः कर्ता ६.१.२०७|६.१.२०७|६.१.२०७ आशितः कर्ता
The word आशित meaning 'having eaten' has acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.208|6.1.208 rikte vibhaaShaa|rikte vibhaaShaa|rikte vibhaaShaa 6.1.208|रिक्ते विभाषा|रिक्ते विभाषा ६.१.२०८|६.१.२०८|६.१.२०८ रिक्ते विभाषा
The word रिक्त may have optionally the acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.209|6.1.209 juShTaarpite cha Chandasi|juShTaarpite cha Chandasi|juShTaarpite cha Chandasi 6.1.209|जुष्टार्पिते च छन्दसि|जुष्टार्पिते च छन्दसि ६.१.२०९|६.१.२०९|६.१.२०९ जुष्टार्पिते च छन्दसि
In the छन्दस , the words जुष्ट and अर्पित have optionally the acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent

6.1.210|6.1.210 nityaM mantre|nityaM mantre|nityaM mantre 6.1.210|नित्यं मन्त्रे|नित्यं मन्त्रे ६.१.२१०|६.१.२१०|६.१.२१० नित्यं मन्त्रे
In the मन्त्राः , these words जुष्ट and अर्पित have always the acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-छन्दस

6.1.211|6.1.211 yuShmadasmadorNGasi|yuShmadasmadorNGasi|yuShmadasmadorNGasi 6.1.211|युष्मदस्मदोर्ङसि|युष्मदस्मदोर्ङसि ६.१.२११|६.१.२११|६.१.२११ युष्मदस्मदोर्ङसि
The acute accent is on the first syllable of युष्मद् and अस्मद् in the Genitive Singular.<br><br>Terms: accent-छन्दस

6.1.212|6.1.212 NGayi cha|NGayi cha|NGayi cha 6.1.212|ङयि च|ङयि च ६.१.२१२|६.१.२१२|६.१.२१२ ङयि च
The acute accent is on the first syllable of युष्मद् and अस्मद् in the Dative Singular.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति-pronouns

6.1.213|6.1.213 yato.anaavaH|yato.anaavaH|yato.anaavaH 6.1.213|यतोऽनावः|यतोऽनावः ६.१.२१३|६.१.२१३|६.१.२१३ यतोऽनावः
Whatever is formed by the affix यत् , has, if it is a disyllabic word, the acute on the first syllable, with the exception of नाव्यः from नौ।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति-pronouns

6.1.214|6.1.214 iiDavandavRshaMsaduhaaM NyataH|iiDavandavRshaMsaduhaaM NyataH|iiDavandavRshaMsaduhaaM NyataH 6.1.214|ईडवन्दवृशंसदुहां ण्यतः|ईडवन्दवृशंसदुहां ण्यतः ६.१.२१४|६.१.२१४|६.१.२१४ ईडवन्दवृशंसदुहां ण्यतः
The acute accent is on the first syllable of ईड् , वन्द , वृ , शंस् and दुह् , when they are followed by the affix ण्यत्।<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति-pronouns

6.1.215|6.1.215 vibhaaShaa veNvindhaanayoH|vibhaaShaa veNvindhaanayoH|vibhaaShaa veNvindhaanayoH 6.1.215|विभाषा वेण्विन्धानयोः|विभाषा वेण्विन्धानयोः ६.१.२१५|६.१.२१५|६.१.२१५ विभाषा वेण्विन्धानयोः
The acute accent is optionally on the first syllable of वेणु and इन्धान।<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.216|6.1.216 tyaagaraagahaasakuhashvaThakrathaanaam|tyaagaraagahaasakuhashvaThakrathaanaam|tyaagaraagahaasakuhashvaThakrathaanaam 6.1.216|त्यागरागहासकुहश्वठक्रथानाम्|त्यागरागहासकुहश्वठक्रथानाम् ६.१.२१६|६.१.२१६|६.१.२१६ त्यागरागहासकुहश्वठक्रथानाम्
The acute accent is optionally on the first syllables of त्याग , राग , हास , कुह , श्वठ , and क्रथ।<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.217|6.1.217 upottamaM riti|upottamaM riti|upottamaM riti 6.1.217|उपोत्तमं रिति|उपोत्तमं रिति ६.१.२१७|६.१.२१७|६.१.२१७ उपोत्तमं रिति
What is formed by an affix having an indicatory र , has acute on the penultimate syllable, the full word consisting of more than two syllables.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.218|6.1.218 chaNGyanyatarasyaam|chaNGyanyatarasyaam|chaNGyanyatarasyaam 6.1.218|चङ्यन्यतरस्याम्|चङ्यन्यतरस्याम् ६.१.२१८|६.१.२१८|६.१.२१८ चङ्यन्यतरस्याम्
The acute accent may be optionally on the penultimate syllable of the reduplicated Aorist in चङ् , the word consisting of more than two syllables.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.219|6.1.219 matoH puurvamaat‌ saMJNaayaaM striyaam‌|matoH puurvamaat‌ saMJNaayaaM striyaam‌|matoH puurvamaat‌ saMJNaayaaM striyaam‌ 6.1.219|मतोः पूर्वमात्‌ संज्ञायां स्त्रियाम्‌|मतोः पूर्वमात्‌ संज्ञायां स्त्रियाम्‌ ६.१.२१९|६.१.२१९|६.१.२१९ मतोः पूर्वमात्‌ संज्ञायां स्त्रियाम्‌
The आ before the affix मत् has the acute accent, when the word is a name in the Feminine Gender.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.220|6.1.220 anto.avatyaaH|anto.avatyaaH|anto.avatyaaH 6.1.220|अन्तोऽवत्याः|अन्तोऽवत्याः ६.१.२२०|६.१.२२०|६.१.२२० अन्तोऽवत्याः
The Names ending in अवति have the acute accent on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-word-Feminine

6.1.221|6.1.221 iivatyaaH|iivatyaaH|iivatyaaH 6.1.221|ईवत्याः|ईवत्याः ६.१.२२१|६.१.२२१|६.१.२२१ ईवत्याः
The Names ending in ईवति have the acute on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

6.1.222|6.1.222 chau|chau|chau 6.1.222|चौ|चौ ६.१.२२२|६.१.२२२|६.१.२२२ चौ
In compound words ending in अञ्च् , the final vowel of the preceding word has the acute accent in the weak cases in which only च् of अञ्च् remains.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

6.1.223|6.1.223 samaasasya|samaasasya|samaasasya 6.1.223|समासस्य|समासस्य ६.१.२२३|६.१.२२३|६.१.२२३ समासस्य
A compound word has the acute on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-समास

6.2.1|6.2.1 bahuvriihau prakRtyaa puurvapadam|bahuvriihau prakRtyaa puurvapadam|bahuvriihau prakRtyaa puurvapadam 6.2.1|बहुव्रीहौ प्रकृत्या पूर्वपदम्|बहुव्रीहौ प्रकृत्या पूर्वपदम् ६.२.१|६.२.१|६.२.१ बहुव्रीहौ प्रकृत्या पूर्वपदम्
In a बहुव्रीहि समास the first member preserves its own original accent.<br><br>Terms: बहुव्रीहि समास

6.2.2|6.2.2 tatpuruShe tulyaarthatRtiiyaasaptamyupamaanaavyayadvitiiyaakRtyaaH|tatpuruShe tulyaarthatRtiiyaasaptamyupamaanaavyayadvitiiyaakRtyaaH|tatpuruShe tulyaarthatRtiiyaasaptamyupamaanaavyayadvitiiyaakRtyaaH 6.2.2|तत्पुरुषे तुल्यार्थतृतीयासप्तम्युपमानाव्ययद्वितीयाकृत्याः|तत्पुरुषे तुल्यार्थतृतीयासप्तम्युपमानाव्ययद्वितीयाकृत्याः ६.२.२|६.२.२|६.२.२ तत्पुरुषे तुल्यार्थतृतीयासप्तम्युपमानाव्ययद्वितीयाकृत्याः
In a तत्-पुरुष समास the first member preserves its original accent when it is a word - 1. meaning 'a resemblance' or 2. an Instrumental or 3. a Locative or 4. a word with which the second member is compared or 5. an indeclinable or 6. an Accusative or 7. a Future Passive Participle<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास the

6.2.3|6.2.3 varNaH varNeShvanete|varNaH varNeShvanete|varNaH varNeShvanete 6.2.3|वर्णः वर्णेष्वनेते|वर्णः वर्णेष्वनेते ६.२.३|६.२.३|६.२.३ वर्णः वर्णेष्वनेते
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when a word denoting colour is compounded with another colour denoting word but not so when it is the word एत।<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.4|6.2.4 gaadhalavaNayoH pramaaNe|gaadhalavaNayoH pramaaNe|gaadhalavaNayoH pramaaNe 6.2.4|गाधलवणयोः प्रमाणे|गाधलवणयोः प्रमाणे ६.२.४|६.२.४|६.२.४ गाधलवणयोः प्रमाणे
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second term is गाध or लवण and the compound expresses 'a measure or mass'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.5|6.2.5 daayaadyaM daayaade|daayaadyaM daayaade|daayaadyaM daayaade 6.2.5|दायाद्यं दायादे|दायाद्यं दायादे ६.२.५|६.२.५|६.२.५ दायाद्यं दायादे
In a तत्-पुरुष समास having the word दायद् as its second member, the first member denoting inheritance preserves its original accent.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.6|6.2.6 pratibandhi chirakRchChrayoH|pratibandhi chirakRchChrayoH|pratibandhi chirakRchChrayoH 6.2.6|प्रतिबन्धि चिरकृच्छ्रयोः|प्रतिबन्धि चिरकृच्छ्रयोः ६.२.६|६.२.६|६.२.६ प्रतिबन्धि चिरकृच्छ्रयोः
In a तत्-पुरुष समास having the words चिर or कृच्छ्र as its second member, the first member, when it denotes that which experiences an obstacle, preserves its original accent.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.7|6.2.7 pade.apadeshe|pade.apadeshe|pade.apadeshe 6.2.7|पदेऽपदेशे|पदेऽपदेशे ६.२.७|६.२.७|६.२.७ पदेऽपदेशे
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is the word पद denoting 'a pretext'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.8|6.2.8 nivaate vaatatraaNe|nivaate vaatatraaNe|nivaate vaatatraaNe 6.2.8|निवाते वातत्राणे|निवाते वातत्राणे ६.२.८|६.२.८|६.२.८ निवाते वातत्राणे
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is the word निवात in the sense of 'a protection from wind'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.9|6.2.9 shaaradeanaartave|shaaradeanaartave|shaaradeanaartave 6.2.9|शारदेअनार्तवे|शारदेअनार्तवे ६.२.९|६.२.९|६.२.९ शारदेअनार्तवे
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is the word शारद having any other sense than that of 'autumnal'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.10|6.2.10 adhvaryukaShaayayorjaatau|adhvaryukaShaayayorjaatau|adhvaryukaShaayayorjaatau 6.2.10|अध्वर्युकषाययोर्जातौ|अध्वर्युकषाययोर्जातौ ६.२.१०|६.२.१०|६.२.१० अध्वर्युकषाययोर्जातौ
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is the word अध्वर्यु or कषाय denoting a genus.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.11|6.2.11 sadRshapratiruupayoH saadRshye|sadRshapratiruupayoH saadRshye|sadRshapratiruupayoH saadRshye 6.2.11|सदृशप्रतिरूपयोः सादृश्ये|सदृशप्रतिरूपयोः सादृश्ये ६.२.११|६.२.११|६.२.११ सदृशप्रतिरूपयोः सादृश्ये
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is the word सदृश or प्रतिरूप expressing resemblance with someone or something.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.12|6.2.12 dvigau pramaaNe|dvigau pramaaNe|dvigau pramaaNe 6.2.12|द्विगौ प्रमाणे|द्विगौ प्रमाणे ६.२.१२|६.२.१२|६.२.१२ द्विगौ प्रमाणे
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) denoting 'measure or quantity'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.13|6.2.13 gantavyapaNyaM vaaNije|gantavyapaNyaM vaaNije|gantavyapaNyaM vaaNije 6.2.13|गन्तव्यपण्यं वाणिजे|गन्तव्यपण्यं वाणिजे ६.२.१३|६.२.१३|६.२.१३ गन्तव्यपण्यं वाणिजे
Before the word वाणिज 'a trader' the first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its accent when it is a word specifying the place wither one has to go or the ware in which one deals.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.14|6.2.14 maatropaJNopakramachChaaye napuMsake|maatropaJNopakramachChaaye napuMsake|maatropaJNopakramachChaaye napuMsake 6.2.14|मात्रोपज्ञोपक्रमच्छाये नपुंसके|मात्रोपज्ञोपक्रमच्छाये नपुंसके ६.२.१४|६.२.१४|६.२.१४ मात्रोपज्ञोपक्रमच्छाये नपुंसके
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the words 1. मात्रा 2. उपज्ञा 3. उपक्रम and 4. छाया when these words appear as neuter.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.15|6.2.15 sukhapriyayorhite|sukhapriyayorhite|sukhapriyayorhite 6.2.15|सुखप्रिययोर्हिते|सुखप्रिययोर्हिते ६.२.१५|६.२.१५|६.२.१५ सुखप्रिययोर्हिते
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when its second term is सुख or प्रिय and the sense is 'to feel delight' or 'is good'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.16|6.2.16 priitau cha|priitau cha|priitau cha 6.2.16|प्रीतौ च|प्रीतौ च ६.२.१६|६.२.१६|६.२.१६ प्रीतौ च
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when its second term is सुख or प्रिय and the sense is 'agreeable to one' or 'desired'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.17|6.2.17 svaM svaamini|svaM svaamini|svaM svaamini 6.2.17|स्वं स्वामिनि|स्वं स्वामिनि ६.२.१७|६.२.१७|६.२.१७ स्वं स्वामिनि
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when it denotes a thing possessed and when its second term is स्वामिन्।<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.18|6.2.18 patyaavaishvarye|patyaavaishvarye|patyaavaishvarye 6.2.18|पत्यावैश्वर्ये|पत्यावैश्वर्ये ६.२.१८|६.२.१८|६.२.१८ पत्यावैश्वर्ये
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when it ends in पति and means 'master' or 'lord'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.19|6.2.19 na bhuuvaakchiddidhiShu|na bhuuvaakchiddidhiShu|na bhuuvaakchiddidhiShu 6.2.19|न भूवाक्चिद्दिधिषु|न भूवाक्चिद्दिधिषु ६.२.१९|६.२.१९|६.२.१९ न भूवाक्चिद्दिधिषु
The words भू , वाक् , चित् and दिधिषू however do not preserve their original accent in तत्-पुरुष समास when coming before the word पति denoting 'master' or 'lord'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.20|6.2.20 vaa bhuvanam|vaa bhuvanam|vaa bhuvanam 6.2.20|वा भुवनम्|वा भुवनम् ६.२.२०|६.२.२०|६.२.२० वा भुवनम्
The word भुवन may optionally keep its accent in a तत्-पुरुष समास before the word पति denoting 'master' or 'lord'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.21|6.2.21 aashankaabaadhanediiyassu saMbhaavane|aashankaabaadhanediiyassu saMbhaavane|aashankaabaadhanediiyassu saMbhaavane 6.2.21|आशङ्काबाधनेदीयस्सु संभावने|आशङ्काबाधनेदीयस्सु संभावने ६.२.२१|६.२.२१|६.२.२१ आशङ्काबाधनेदीयस्सु संभावने
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent before words आशङ्क , आबाध and नेदीयस् , when it treats about a supposition.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.22|6.2.22 puurve bhuutapuurve|puurve bhuutapuurve|puurve bhuutapuurve 6.2.22|पूर्वे भूतपूर्वे|पूर्वे भूतपूर्वे ६.२.२२|६.२.२२|६.२.२२ पूर्वे भूतपूर्वे
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is the word पूर्व and the sense is 'this had been lately…'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.23|6.2.23 savidhasaniiDasamaryaadasaveshasadesheShu saamiipye|savidhasaniiDasamaryaadasaveshasadesheShu saamiipye|savidhasaniiDasamaryaadasaveshasadesheShu saamiipye 6.2.23|सविधसनीडसमर्यादसवेशसदेशेषु सामीप्ये|सविधसनीडसमर्यादसवेशसदेशेषु सामीप्ये ६.२.२३|६.२.२३|६.२.२३ सविधसनीडसमर्यादसवेशसदेशेषु सामीप्ये
The first member of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent when the second member is 1. सविध 2. सनीड 3. समर्याद 4. सवेश and 5. सदेश in the sense of 'what can be found in the vicinity thereof'.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.24|6.2.24 vispaShTaadiini guNavachaneShu|vispaShTaadiini guNavachaneShu|vispaShTaadiini guNavachaneShu 6.2.24|विस्पष्टादीनि गुणवचनेषु|विस्पष्टादीनि गुणवचनेषु ६.२.२४|६.२.२४|६.२.२४ विस्पष्टादीनि गुणवचनेषु
The words विस्पष्ट etc. preserve their accent when followed by an adjective word in a compound.<br><br>Terms: तत्-पुरुष समास

6.2.25|6.2.25 shrajyaa.avamakanpaapavatsu bhaave karmadhaaraye|shrajyaa.avamakanpaapavatsu bhaave karmadhaaraye|shrajyaa.avamakanpaapavatsu bhaave karmadhaaraye 6.2.25|श्रज्याऽवमकन्पापवत्सु भावे कर्मधारये|श्रज्याऽवमकन्पापवत्सु भावे कर्मधारये ६.२.२५|६.२.२५|६.२.२५ श्रज्याऽवमकन्पापवत्सु भावे कर्मधारये
In a कर्मधारय समास the first member consisting of a भाव (verbal noun) preserves its original accent before the adjective forms built from श्र -- प्रशस्यस्य श्रः ५.३.६०, ज्य -- ज्य च ५.३.६१, अवम and कन् -- युवाल्पयोः कनन्यतरस्याम् ५.३.६४, and before a form built from the word पाप।<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.26|6.2.26 kumaarashcha|kumaarashcha|kumaarashcha 6.2.26|कुमारश्च|कुमारश्च ६.२.२६|६.२.२६|६.२.२६ कुमारश्च
In a कर्मधारय समास the first member consisting of the word कुमार preserves it original accent.<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.27|6.2.27 aadiH pratyenasi|aadiH pratyenasi|aadiH pratyenasi 6.2.27|आदिः प्रत्येनसि|आदिः प्रत्येनसि ६.२.२७|६.२.२७|६.२.२७ आदिः प्रत्येनसि
In a कर्मधारय समास of कुमार followed by प्रत्येनस् the acutely accented (उदात्त) falls on the first syllable of कुमार।<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.28|6.2.28 puugeShvanyatarasyaam|puugeShvanyatarasyaam|puugeShvanyatarasyaam 6.2.28|पूगेष्वन्यतरस्याम्|पूगेष्वन्यतरस्याम् ६.२.२८|६.२.२८|६.२.२८ पूगेष्वन्यतरस्याम्
The first syllable of कुमार is optionally acutely accented (उदात्त) when the second member is a word denoting 'the name of a horde'.<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.29|6.2.29 igantakaalakapaalabhagaalasharaaveShu dvigau|igantakaalakapaalabhagaalasharaaveShu dvigau|igantakaalakapaalabhagaalasharaaveShu dvigau 6.2.29|इगन्तकालकपालभगालशरावेषु द्विगौ|इगन्तकालकपालभगालशरावेषु द्विगौ ६.२.२९|६.२.२९|६.२.२९ इगन्तकालकपालभगालशरावेषु द्विगौ
In a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) the first member preserves its original accent before a stem ending in a simple vowel with the exception of अ (इक्) before a word denoting time, as well as before 1. कपाल 2. भगाल and 3. शराव।<br><br>Terms: द्विगु समास

6.2.30|6.2.30 bahvanyatarasyaam|bahvanyatarasyaam|bahvanyatarasyaam 6.2.30|बह्वन्यतरस्याम्|बह्वन्यतरस्याम् ६.२.३०|६.२.३०|६.२.३० बह्वन्यतरस्याम्
In a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) the word बहु may optionally preserve its accent when followed by an इक्-ending stem or by a time-word or by 1. कपाल 2. भगाल and 3. शराव।<br><br>Terms: द्विगु समास

6.2.31|6.2.31 diShTivitastyoshcha|diShTivitastyoshcha|diShTivitastyoshcha 6.2.31|दिष्टिवितस्त्योश्च|दिष्टिवितस्त्योश्च ६.२.३१|६.२.३१|६.२.३१ दिष्टिवितस्त्योश्च
In a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) the first member may optionally preserve its accent when followed by the words दिष्टि and वितस्ति।as its second members.<br><br>Terms: द्विगु समास

6.2.32|6.2.32 saptamii siddhashuShkapakvabandheShvakaalaat‌|saptamii siddhashuShkapakvabandheShvakaalaat‌|saptamii siddhashuShkapakvabandheShvakaalaat‌ 6.2.32|सप्तमी सिद्धशुष्कपक्वबन्धेष्वकालात्‌|सप्तमी सिद्धशुष्कपक्वबन्धेष्वकालात्‌ ६.२.३२|६.२.३२|६.२.३२ सप्तमी सिद्धशुष्कपक्वबन्धेष्वकालात्‌
When a word ending in the Locative -7th case does not denote time preserves its original accent when followed by 1. सिद्ध 2. शुष्क 3. पक्व and 4. बन्ध in a compound.<br><br>Terms: द्विगु समास

6.2.33|6.2.33 paripratyupaapaa varjyamaanaahoraatraavayaveShu|paripratyupaapaa varjyamaanaahoraatraavayaveShu|paripratyupaapaa varjyamaanaahoraatraavayaveShu 6.2.33|परिप्रत्युपापा वर्ज्यमानाहोरात्रावयवेषु|परिप्रत्युपापा वर्ज्यमानाहोरात्रावयवेषु ६.२.३३|६.२.३३|६.२.३३ परिप्रत्युपापा वर्ज्यमानाहोरात्रावयवेषु
The particles 1. परि 2. प्रति 3. उप and 4. अप preserve their accent before that word which specifies an exclusion or a portion of day and night (in an अव्ययीभाव समास also).<br><br>Terms: द्विगु and अव्ययीभाव समास

6.2.34|6.2.34 raajanyabahuvachanadvaMdve.andhakavRShNiShu|raajanyabahuvachanadvaMdve.andhakavRShNiShu|raajanyabahuvachanadvaMdve.andhakavRShNiShu 6.2.34|राजन्यबहुवचनद्वंद्वेऽन्धकवृष्णिषु|राजन्यबहुवचनद्वंद्वेऽन्धकवृष्णिषु ६.२.३४|६.२.३४|६.२.३४ राजन्यबहुवचनद्वंद्वेऽन्धकवृष्णिषु
The first member of a द्वन्द समास formed of names denoting the क्षत्रिय (warrior) clans in the plural number retains its original accent when the warrior belongs to the clan of अन्धक or वृष्णि।<br><br>Terms: द्वन्द समास

6.2.35|6.2.35 saMkhyaa|saMkhyaa|saMkhyaa 6.2.35|संख्या|संख्या ६.२.३५|६.२.३५|६.२.३५ संख्या
The numeral word standing as the first member of a द्वन्द समास , preserves its accent.<br><br>Terms: द्वन्द समास

6.2.36|6.2.36 aachaaryopasarjanashchaantevaasii|aachaaryopasarjanashchaantevaasii|aachaaryopasarjanashchaantevaasii 6.2.36|आचार्योपसर्जनश्चान्तेवासी|आचार्योपसर्जनश्चान्तेवासी ६.२.३६|६.२.३६|६.२.३६ आचार्योपसर्जनश्चान्तेवासी
When words denoting scholars are named after their teachers and are compounded into a द्वन्द समास the first member retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: द्वन्द समास

6.2.37|6.2.37 kaartakaujapaadayashcha|kaartakaujapaadayashcha|kaartakaujapaadayashcha 6.2.37|कार्तकौजपादयश्च|कार्तकौजपादयश्च ६.२.३७|६.२.३७|६.२.३७ कार्तकौजपादयश्च
Also in the द्वन्द समास-s कार्तकौजप etc. the first members retain their accent.<br><br>Terms: द्वन्द समास

6.2.38|6.2.38 mahaan vriihyaparaahNagRShTiiShvaasajaabaalabhaarabhaaratahailihilarauravapravRddheShu|mahaan vriihyaparaahNagRShTiiShvaasajaabaalabhaarabhaaratahailihilarauravapravRddheShu|mahaan vriihyaparaahNagRShTiiShvaasajaabaalabhaarabhaaratahailihilarauravapravRddheShu 6.2.38|महान् व्रीह्यपराह्णगृष्टीष्वासजाबालभारभारतहैलिहिलरौरवप्रवृद्धेषु|महान् व्रीह्यपराह्णगृष्टीष्वासजाबालभारभारतहैलिहिलरौरवप्रवृद्धेषु ६.२.३८|६.२.३८|६.२.३८ महान् व्रीह्यपराह्णगृष्टीष्वासजाबालभारभारतहैलिहिलरौरवप्रवृद्धेषु
The word महत् (महा) retains its accent before the following - 1. व्रीहि 2. अपराह्ण 3. गृष्टि 4. इष्वास 5. जाबाल 6. भार 7. भारत 8. हैलिहिल 9. रौरव and 10. प्रवृद्धे।<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.39|6.2.39 xullakashcha vaishvadeve|xullakashcha vaishvadeve|xullakashcha vaishvadeve 6.2.39|क्षुल्लकश्च वैश्वदेवे|क्षुल्लकश्च वैश्वदेवे ६.२.३९|६.२.३९|६.२.३९ क्षुल्लकश्च वैश्वदेवे
The words महत् and क्षुल्लक retain their accent before the word वैश्वदेव।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.40|6.2.40 uShTraH saadivaamyoH|uShTraH saadivaamyoH|uShTraH saadivaamyoH 6.2.40|उष्ट्रः सादिवाम्योः|उष्ट्रः सादिवाम्योः ६.२.४०|६.२.४०|६.२.४० उष्ट्रः सादिवाम्योः
The word उष्ट्र retains its accent before सादि and वामि।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.41|6.2.41 gauH saadasaadisaarathiShu|gauH saadasaadisaarathiShu|gauH saadasaadisaarathiShu 6.2.41|गौः सादसादिसारथिषु|गौः सादसादिसारथिषु ६.२.४१|६.२.४१|६.२.४१ गौः सादसादिसारथिषु
The word गो retains its accent before 1. साद 2. सादि and 3. सारथि।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.42|6.2.42 kurugaarhapatariktagurvasuutajaratyashliiladRDharuupaapaarevaDavaataitilakadruuHpaNyakambalo daasiibhaaraaNaaM cha|kurugaarhapatariktagurvasuutajaratyashliiladRDharuupaapaarevaDavaataitilakadruuHpaNyakambalo daasiibhaaraaNaaM cha|kurugaarhapatariktagurvasuutajaratyashliiladRDharuupaapaarevaDavaataitilakadruuHpaNyakambalo daasiibhaaraaNaaM cha 6.2.42|कुरुगार्हपतरिक्तगुर्वसूतजरत्यश्लीलदृढरूपापारेवडवातैतिलकद्रूःपण्यकम्बलो दासीभाराणां च|कुरुगार्हपतरिक्तगुर्वसूतजरत्यश्लीलदृढरूपापारेवडवातैतिलकद्रूःपण्यकम्बलो दासीभाराणां च ६.२.४२|६.२.४२|६.२.४२ कुरुगार्हपतरिक्तगुर्वसूतजरत्यश्लीलदृढरूपापारेवडवातैतिलकद्रूःपण्यकम्बलो दासीभाराणां च
The first member retains its accent in the following - 1. कुरु-गार्हपत 2. रिक्त-गुरु 3. असूत-जरती 4. अश्लील-दृढ-रूपा 5. पारे-वडवा 6. तैतिल-कद्रूः 7. पण्य-कम्बलः and 8. दासीभार etc.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.43|6.2.43 chaturthii tadarthe|chaturthii tadarthe|chaturthii tadarthe 6.2.43|चतुर्थी तदर्थे|चतुर्थी तदर्थे ६.२.४३|६.२.४३|६.२.४३ चतुर्थी तदर्थे
A word in the Dative -4th Case as the first member retains its accent when the second member expresses that which is suited to become the former.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.44|6.2.44 arthe|arthe|arthe 6.2.44|अर्थे|अर्थे ६.२.४४|६.२.४४|६.२.४४ अर्थे
Before the word अर्थ the first member in the Dative -4th Case retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.45|6.2.45 kte cha|kte cha|kte cha 6.2.45|क्ते च|क्ते च ६.२.४५|६.२.४५|६.२.४५ क्ते च
The first member in the Dative -4th Case retains its accent before a Past Participle in क्त।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.46|6.2.46 karmadhaaraye.aniShThaa|karmadhaaraye.aniShThaa|karmadhaaraye.aniShThaa 6.2.46|कर्मधारयेऽनिष्ठा|कर्मधारयेऽनिष्ठा ६.२.४६|६.२.४६|६.२.४६ कर्मधारयेऽनिष्ठा
Before the Past Participle in क्त the first member when it itself is not a Past Participle, retains its original accent in a कर्मधारय समास ।<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.47|6.2.47 ahiine dvitiiyaa|ahiine dvitiiyaa|ahiine dvitiiyaa 6.2.47|अहीने द्वितीया|अहीने द्वितीया ६.२.४७|६.२.४७|६.२.४७ अहीने द्वितीया
Before the Past Participle in क्त , a word ending in the Accusative -2nd case retains its accent when it does not mean a separation.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.48|6.2.48 tRtiiyaa karmaNi|tRtiiyaa karmaNi|tRtiiyaa karmaNi 6.2.48|तृतीया कर्मणि|तृतीया कर्मणि ६.२.४८|६.२.४८|६.२.४८ तृतीया कर्मणि
A word ending in the Instrumental -3rd case retains its accent before the Past Participle in क्त when it has a Passive meaning.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.49|6.2.49 gatiranantaraH|gatiranantaraH|gatiranantaraH 6.2.49|गतिरनन्तरः|गतिरनन्तरः ६.२.४९|६.२.४९|६.२.४९ गतिरनन्तरः
A word called गति -- गतिश्च १.४.६०, when standing immediately before a Participle in क्त having a Passive significance, retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.50|6.2.50 taadau cha niti kRtyatau|taadau cha niti kRtyatau|taadau cha niti kRtyatau 6.2.50|तादौ च निति कृत्यतौ|तादौ च निति कृत्यतौ ६.२.५०|६.२.५०|६.२.५० तादौ च निति कृत्यतौ
An immediately preceding गति -- गतिश्च १.४.६०, retains its original accent before (a word formed by) a कृत्-affix beginning with त् which as an indicatory न् but before तु।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.51|6.2.51 tavai chaantashcha yugapat‌|tavai chaantashcha yugapat‌|tavai chaantashcha yugapat‌ 6.2.51|तवै चान्तश्च युगपत्‌|तवै चान्तश्च युगपत्‌ ६.२.५१|६.२.५१|६.२.५१ तवै चान्तश्च युगपत्‌
An immediately preceding गति -- गतिश्च १.४.६०, retains its original accent before an Infinitive in तवै -- कृत्यार्थे तवैकेन्केन्यत्वनः ३.४.१४, but whereby simultaneously the final has the acute as well.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.52|6.2.52 aniganto.ancatau vapratyaye|aniganto.ancatau vapratyaye|aniganto.ancatau vapratyaye 6.2.52|अनिगन्तोऽञ्चतौ वप्रत्यये|अनिगन्तोऽञ्चतौ वप्रत्यये ६.२.५२|६.२.५२|६.२.५२ अनिगन्तोऽञ्चतौ वप्रत्यये
An immediately preceding गति -- गतिश्च १.४.६०, not ending in इ or उ retains its accent before an affix having a व् follows.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.53|6.2.53 nyadhii cha|nyadhii cha|nyadhii cha 6.2.53|न्यधी च|न्यधी च ६.२.५३|६.२.५३|६.२.५३ न्यधी च
The गति-s नि and अधि however retain their original accent before अञ्च् when the affix व् follows.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.54|6.2.54 iiShadanyatarasyaam|iiShadanyatarasyaam|iiShadanyatarasyaam 6.2.54|ईषदन्यतरस्याम्|ईषदन्यतरस्याम् ६.२.५४|६.२.५४|६.२.५४ ईषदन्यतरस्याम्
The word ईषत् when the first member of a compound may optionally preserve its original accent.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.55|6.2.55 hiraNyaparimaaNaM dhane|hiraNyaparimaaNaM dhane|hiraNyaparimaaNaM dhane 6.2.55|हिरण्यपरिमाणं धने|हिरण्यपरिमाणं धने ६.२.५५|६.२.५५|६.२.५५ हिरण्यपरिमाणं धने
The first member denoting the quantity of gold retains optionally its original accent before the word धन।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.56|6.2.56 prathamo.achiropasampattau|prathamo.achiropasampattau|prathamo.achiropasampattau 6.2.56|प्रथमोऽचिरोपसम्पत्तौ|प्रथमोऽचिरोपसम्पत्तौ ६.२.५६|६.२.५६|६.२.५६ प्रथमोऽचिरोपसम्पत्तौ
The word प्रथम when first in a compound optionally retains its original accent when meaning 'a novice'.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.57|6.2.57 katarakatamau karmadhaaraye|katarakatamau karmadhaaraye|katarakatamau karmadhaaraye 6.2.57|कतरकतमौ कर्मधारये|कतरकतमौ कर्मधारये ६.२.५७|६.२.५७|६.२.५७ कतरकतमौ कर्मधारये
The words कतर and कतम when as first member of a compound optionally retain their original accent in a कर्मधारय समास।<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.58|6.2.58 aaryo braahmaNakumaarayoH|aaryo braahmaNakumaarayoH|aaryo braahmaNakumaarayoH 6.2.58|आर्यो ब्राह्मणकुमारयोः|आर्यो ब्राह्मणकुमारयोः ६.२.५८|६.२.५८|६.२.५८ आर्यो ब्राह्मणकुमारयोः
The word आर्य optionally retains its original accent in a कर्मधारय समास before the words ब्राह्मण and कुमार।<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.59|6.2.59 raajaa cha|raajaa cha|raajaa cha 6.2.59|राजा च|राजा च ६.२.५९|६.२.५९|६.२.५९ राजा च
The word राजन् optionally retains its original accent in a कर्मधारय समास before the words ब्राह्मण and कुमार।<br><br>Terms: कर्मधारय समास

6.2.60|6.2.60 ShaShThii pratyenasi|ShaShThii pratyenasi|ShaShThii pratyenasi 6.2.60|षष्ठी प्रत्येनसि|षष्ठी प्रत्येनसि ६.२.६०|६.२.६०|६.२.६० षष्ठी प्रत्येनसि
The word राजन् ending in Genitive 6th-Case optionally retains its original accent before the word प्रत्येनस्।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.61|6.2.61 kte nityaarthe|kte nityaarthe|kte nityaarthe 6.2.61|क्ते नित्यार्थे|क्ते नित्यार्थे ६.२.६१|६.२.६१|६.२.६१ क्ते नित्यार्थे
A word having the sense of 'always' optionally retains its original accent before a Past Participle in क्त ।<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.62|6.2.62 graamaH shilpini|graamaH shilpini|graamaH shilpini 6.2.62|ग्रामः शिल्पिनि|ग्रामः शिल्पिनि ६.२.६२|६.२.६२|६.२.६२ ग्रामः शिल्पिनि
The word ग्राम when first member of a compound optionally retains its original accent before a word denoting 'a professional man or artisan'.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.63|6.2.63 raajaa cha prashaMsaayaam|raajaa cha prashaMsaayaam|raajaa cha prashaMsaayaam 6.2.63|राजा च प्रशंसायाम्|राजा च प्रशंसायाम् ६.२.६३|६.२.६३|६.२.६३ राजा च प्रशंसायाम्
The word राजन् optionally retains its original accent after a profession-denoting noun when praise is expressed.<br><br>Terms: समास accent

6.2.64|6.2.64 aadirudaattaH|aadirudaattaH|aadirudaattaH 6.2.64|आदिरुदात्तः|आदिरुदात्तः ६.२.६४|६.२.६४|६.२.६४ आदिरुदात्तः
In the following up to -- न भूताधिकसंजीवमद्राश्मकज्जलम् ६.२.९१, inclusive, the phrase 'the first syllable in -(the word standing in the Nominative 1st-Case) has the acute accent (उदात्त)' is always to be supplied.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.65|6.2.65 saptamiihaariNau dharmye.aharaNe|saptamiihaariNau dharmye.aharaNe|saptamiihaariNau dharmye.aharaNe 6.2.65|सप्तमीहारिणौ धर्म्येऽहरणे|सप्तमीहारिणौ धर्म्येऽहरणे ६.२.६५|६.२.६५|६.२.६५ सप्तमीहारिणौ धर्म्येऽहरणे
If the first member of a compound is in the Locative -7th case or denoting the name of the Receiver of Tax, has acutely accented (उदात्त) first syllable, when the second member is a word denoting 'what is lawful', but not when it is हरण।<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.66|6.2.66 yukte cha|yukte cha|yukte cha 6.2.66|युक्ते च|युक्ते च ६.२.६६|६.२.६६|६.२.६६ युक्ते च
The first member of a compound has acute on the first syllable when the second member denotes that by whom the things denoted by the first are regulated or kept in order.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.67|6.2.67 vibhaaShaa.adhyaxe|vibhaaShaa.adhyaxe|vibhaaShaa.adhyaxe 6.2.67|विभाषाऽध्यक्षे|विभाषाऽध्यक्षे ६.२.६७|६.२.६७|६.२.६७ विभाषाऽध्यक्षे
The acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable is optional when the word अध्यक्ष follows.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.68|6.2.68 paapaM cha shilpini|paapaM cha shilpini|paapaM cha shilpini 6.2.68|पापं च शिल्पिनि|पापं च शिल्पिनि ६.२.६८|६.२.६८|६.२.६८ पापं च शिल्पिनि
The word पाप is optionally acutely accented (उदात्त) on the first syllable when followed by a word denoting a professional man.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.69|6.2.69 gotraantevaasimaaNavabraahmaNeShu xepe|gotraantevaasimaaNavabraahmaNeShu xepe|gotraantevaasimaaNavabraahmaNeShu xepe 6.2.69|गोत्रान्तेवासिमाणवब्राह्मणेषु क्षेपे|गोत्रान्तेवासिमाणवब्राह्मणेषु क्षेपे ६.२.६९|६.२.६९|६.२.६९ गोत्रान्तेवासिमाणवब्राह्मणेषु क्षेपे
The first syllable of the first member of a compound is acutely accented (उदात्त) before a गोत्र (Patronymic) name or a Scholar-name and also before माणव and ब्राह्मण when a reproach is meant.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.70|6.2.70 angaani maireye|angaani maireye|angaani maireye 6.2.70|अङ्गानि मैरेये|अङ्गानि मैरेये ६.२.७०|६.२.७०|६.२.७० अङ्गानि मैरेये
The first syllable of the word preceding मैरेय gets the acute accent (उदात्त) when it denotes the ingredient of the same.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.71|6.2.71 bhaktaakhyaastadartheShu|bhaktaakhyaastadartheShu|bhaktaakhyaastadartheShu 6.2.71|भक्ताख्यास्तदर्थेषु|भक्ताख्यास्तदर्थेषु ६.२.७१|६.२.७१|६.२.७१ भक्ताख्यास्तदर्थेषु
A word denoting food gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when before a word which denotes a repository suited to contain that.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.72|6.2.72 gobiDaalasiMhasaindhaveShuupamaane|gobiDaalasiMhasaindhaveShuupamaane|gobiDaalasiMhasaindhaveShuupamaane 6.2.72|गोबिडालसिंहसैन्धवेषूपमाने|गोबिडालसिंहसैन्धवेषूपमाने ६.२.७२|६.२.७२|६.२.७२ गोबिडालसिंहसैन्धवेषूपमाने
A word denoting the object of comparison gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when standing before गो , बिडाल , सिंह and सैन्धव।<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.73|6.2.73 ake jiivikaa.arthe|ake jiivikaa.arthe|ake jiivikaa.arthe 6.2.73|अके जीविकाऽर्थे|अके जीविकाऽर्थे ६.२.७३|६.२.७३|६.२.७३ अके जीविकाऽर्थे
A word denoting the object of comparison gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when the second member is a word ending in the affix अक and the compound expresses a calling by which one gets his living.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.74|6.2.74 praachaaM kriiDaayaam|praachaaM kriiDaayaam|praachaaM kriiDaayaam 6.2.74|प्राचां क्रीडायाम्|प्राचां क्रीडायाम् ६.२.७४|६.२.७४|६.२.७४ प्राचां क्रीडायाम्
A compound, the second member of which is a word ending in affix अक and which denotes the sport of the Eastern people, gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.75|6.2.75 aNi niyukte|aNi niyukte|aNi niyukte 6.2.75|अणि नियुक्ते|अणि नियुक्ते ६.२.७५|६.२.७५|६.२.७५ अणि नियुक्ते
A compound, the second member of which is a word ending in the कृत् -affix अण् and which denotes a functionary, gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.76|6.2.76 shilpini chaakRNJaH|shilpini chaakRNJaH|shilpini chaakRNJaH 6.2.76|शिल्पिनि चाकृञः|शिल्पिनि चाकृञः ६.२.७६|६.२.७६|६.२.७६ शिल्पिनि चाकृञः
And when such a compound ending in अण् -affix denotes the name of a professional man, but not when the second term कार(derived from कृञ्), the acute accent (उदात्त) is on the first syllable of the first word.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.77|6.2.77 saMJNaayaaM cha|saMJNaayaaM cha|saMJNaayaaM cha 6.2.77|संज्ञायां च|संज्ञायां च ६.२.७७|६.२.७७|६.२.७७ संज्ञायां च
Also when such an उपपद compound ending in अण् -affix denotes a Name, the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the first syllable but not when the second term is कार।<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.78|6.2.78 gotantiyavaM paale|gotantiyavaM paale|gotantiyavaM paale 6.2.78|गोतन्तियवं पाले|गोतन्तियवं पाले ६.२.७८|६.२.७८|६.२.७८ गोतन्तियवं पाले
The words 1. गो 2. तन्ति and 3. यव get the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when followed by पाल।<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.79|6.2.79 Nini|Nini|Nini 6.2.79|णिनि|णिनि ६.२.७९|६.२.७९|६.२.७९ णिनि
A compound ending in कृत् -affix णिनि (इन्) has the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable of the first member.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.80|6.2.80 upamaanaM shabdaarthaprakRtaaveva|upamaanaM shabdaarthaprakRtaaveva|upamaanaM shabdaarthaprakRtaaveva 6.2.80|उपमानं शब्दार्थप्रकृतावेव|उपमानं शब्दार्थप्रकृतावेव ६.२.८०|६.२.८०|६.२.८० उपमानं शब्दार्थप्रकृतावेव
When the first member of a compound expresses that with which resemblance is denoted then it has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable before a word formed by णिनि (इन्) affix, only then, when such latter word is radical without any preposition and means 'giving out a definite sound like so and so'.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.81|6.2.81 yuktaarohyaadayashcha|yuktaarohyaadayashcha|yuktaarohyaadayashcha 6.2.81|युक्तारोह्यादयश्च|युक्तारोह्यादयश्च ६.२.८१|६.२.८१|६.२.८१ युक्तारोह्यादयश्च
The compounds युक्तारोहिन् etc. have acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.82|6.2.82 diirghakaashatuShabhraaShTravaTaM je|diirghakaashatuShabhraaShTravaTaM je|diirghakaashatuShabhraaShTravaTaM je 6.2.82|दीर्घकाशतुषभ्राष्ट्रवटं जे|दीर्घकाशतुषभ्राष्ट्रवटं जे ६.२.८२|६.२.८२|६.२.८२ दीर्घकाशतुषभ्राष्ट्रवटं जे
When the first member is a word ending in a long vowel or is 1. काश 2. तुष 3. भ्राष्ट्र 4. वट and is followed by ज , the acutely accented (उदात्त) falls on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.83|6.2.83 antyaat‌ puurvaM bahvachaH|antyaat‌ puurvaM bahvachaH|antyaat‌ puurvaM bahvachaH 6.2.83|अन्त्यात्‌ पूर्वं बह्वचः|अन्त्यात्‌ पूर्वं बह्वचः ६.२.८३|६.२.८३|६.२.८३ अन्त्यात्‌ पूर्वं बह्वचः
In a word consisting of more than two syllables followed by ज , the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the syllable before the last.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.84|6.2.84 graame.anivasantaH|graame.anivasantaH|graame.anivasantaH 6.2.84|ग्रामेऽनिवसन्तः|ग्रामेऽनिवसन्तः ६.२.८४|६.२.८४|६.२.८४ ग्रामेऽनिवसन्तः
Before ग्राम the first syllable of the first member as acute accent (उदात्त) when thereby inhabitants are not meant.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.85|6.2.85 ghoShaadiShu|ghoShaadiShu|ghoShaadiShu 6.2.85|घोषादिषु|घोषादिषु ६.२.८५|६.२.८५|६.२.८५ घोषादिषु
The first member has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when followed by घोषा etc.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.86|6.2.86 ChaatryaadayaH shaalaayaam|ChaatryaadayaH shaalaayaam|ChaatryaadayaH shaalaayaam 6.2.86|छात्र्यादयः शालायाम्|छात्र्यादयः शालायाम् ६.२.८६|६.२.८६|६.२.८६ छात्र्यादयः शालायाम्
The words छात्रि etc. get acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when followed by the word शाला।<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.87|6.2.87 prasthe.avRddhamakarkyaadiinaam‌|prasthe.avRddhamakarkyaadiinaam‌|prasthe.avRddhamakarkyaadiinaam‌ 6.2.87|प्रस्थेऽवृद्धमकर्क्यादीनाम्‌|प्रस्थेऽवृद्धमकर्क्यादीनाम्‌ ६.२.८७|६.२.८७|६.२.८७ प्रस्थेऽवृद्धमकर्क्यादीनाम्‌
The first member which has not a वृद्धि in the first syllable or which is not कर्की etc. gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable before प्रस्थ।<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.88|6.2.88 maalaa.a.adiinaaM cha|maalaa.a.adiinaaM cha|maalaa.a.adiinaaM cha 6.2.88|मालाऽऽदीनां च|मालाऽऽदीनां च ६.२.८८|६.२.८८|६.२.८८ मालाऽऽदीनां च
The first syllable of माला etc. gets the acute accent (उदात्त) when प्रस्थ follows.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.89|6.2.89 amahannavaM nagare.anudiichaam|amahannavaM nagare.anudiichaam|amahannavaM nagare.anudiichaam 6.2.89|अमहन्नवं नगरेऽनुदीचाम्|अमहन्नवं नगरेऽनुदीचाम् ६.२.८९|६.२.८९|६.२.८९ अमहन्नवं नगरेऽनुदीचाम्
The first member has an acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable before the word नगर but not when it is the word महत् or नव , nor when it refers to a city in the lands of the Northern People.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.90|6.2.90 arme chaavarNaM dvyachtryach|arme chaavarNaM dvyachtryach|arme chaavarNaM dvyachtryach 6.2.90|अर्मे चावर्णं द्व्यच्त्र्यच्|अर्मे चावर्णं द्व्यच्त्र्यच् ६.२.९०|६.२.९०|६.२.९० अर्मे चावर्णं द्व्यच्त्र्यच्
A word of two or three syllables ending in a अ or आ (with the exception of महा and नव) standing before the word अर्म has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.91|6.2.91 na bhuutaadhikasaMjiivamadraashmakajjalam|na bhuutaadhikasaMjiivamadraashmakajjalam|na bhuutaadhikasaMjiivamadraashmakajjalam 6.2.91|न भूताधिकसंजीवमद्राश्मकज्जलम्|न भूताधिकसंजीवमद्राश्मकज्जलम् ६.२.९१|६.२.९१|६.२.९१ न भूताधिकसंजीवमद्राश्मकज्जलम्
The following words do not get acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when standing before अर्म etc. - 1. भूत 2. अधिक 3. संजीव 4. मद्र 5. अश्मन् and 6. कञ्जल।<br><br>Terms: समास 1st-acute

6.2.92|6.2.92 antaH|antaH|antaH 6.2.92|अन्तः|अन्तः ६.२.९२|६.२.९२|६.२.९२ अन्तः
In the following sūtras up to निष्ठोपसर्गपूर्वमन्यतरस्याम्‌ ६.२.११०, inclusive, is to be supplied the phrase 'the last syllable in a word standing in the Nominative 1st-Case has the acute accent (उदात्त)'.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.93|6.2.93 sarvaM guNakaartsnye|sarvaM guNakaartsnye|sarvaM guNakaartsnye 6.2.93|सर्वं गुणकार्त्स्न्ये|सर्वं गुणकार्त्स्न्ये ६.२.९३|६.२.९३|६.२.९३ सर्वं गुणकार्त्स्न्ये
The acute accent (उदात्त) is on the final of the word सर्व standing as the first member before an attributive word in the sense 'whole, through and through'.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.94|6.2.94 saMJNaayaaM girinikaayayoH|saMJNaayaaM girinikaayayoH|saMJNaayaaM girinikaayayoH 6.2.94|संज्ञायां गिरिनिकाययोः|संज्ञायां गिरिनिकाययोः ६.२.९४|६.२.९४|६.२.९४ संज्ञायां गिरिनिकाययोः
The last syllable of the first member before गिरि and निकाय has the acute accent (उदात्त) when the compound is a Name.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.95|6.2.95 kumaaryaaM vayasi|kumaaryaaM vayasi|kumaaryaaM vayasi 6.2.95|कुमार्यां वयसि|कुमार्यां वयसि ६.२.९५|६.२.९५|६.२.९५ कुमार्यां वयसि
The last syllable of the first member get the acute accent (उदात्त) when the word कुमारी follows, the compound denoting age.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.96|6.2.96 udake.akevale|udake.akevale|udake.akevale 6.2.96|उदकेऽकेवले|उदकेऽकेवले ६.२.९६|६.२.९६|६.२.९६ उदकेऽकेवले
Before the word उदक when the compound denotes a mixture, the last syllable of the first member has the acute accent (उदात्त).<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.97|6.2.97 dvigau kratau|dvigau kratau|dvigau kratau 6.2.97|द्विगौ क्रतौ|द्विगौ क्रतौ ६.२.९७|६.२.९७|६.२.९७ द्विगौ क्रतौ
Before a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound), when the compound denotes a sacrifice, the last syllable of the first member has the acute accent (उदात्त).<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.98|6.2.98 sabhaayaaM napuMsake|sabhaayaaM napuMsake|sabhaayaaM napuMsake 6.2.98|सभायां नपुंसके|सभायां नपुंसके ६.२.९८|६.२.९८|६.२.९८ सभायां नपुंसके
Before the word सभा when it is exhibited as Neuter, the first member of the compound gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.99|6.2.99 pure praachaam|pure praachaam|pure praachaam 6.2.99|पुरे प्राचाम्|पुरे प्राचाम् ६.२.९९|६.२.९९|६.२.९९ पुरे प्राचाम्
Before the word पुर , when the compound denotes a city of the Eastern People, the final of the final of the first member as the acute accent (उदात्त).<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.100|6.2.100 ariShTagauDapuurve cha|ariShTagauDapuurve cha|ariShTagauDapuurve cha 6.2.100|अरिष्टगौडपूर्वे च|अरिष्टगौडपूर्वे च ६.२.१००|६.२.१००|६.२.१०० अरिष्टगौडपूर्वे च
When the words अरिष्ट and गौड stand first, the first member has the acute accent (उदात्त) on the final before the word पुर।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.101|6.2.101 na haastinaphalakamaardeyaaH|na haastinaphalakamaardeyaaH|na haastinaphalakamaardeyaaH 6.2.101|न हास्तिनफलकमार्देयाः|न हास्तिनफलकमार्देयाः ६.२.१०१|६.२.१०१|६.२.१०१ न हास्तिनफलकमार्देयाः
But when the words 1. हास्तिन 2. फलक and 3. मार्देय precede पुर , the acute accent (उदात्त) does not fall on their final.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.102|6.2.102 kusuulakuupakumbhashaalaM bile|kusuulakuupakumbhashaalaM bile|kusuulakuupakumbhashaalaM bile 6.2.102|कुसूलकूपकुम्भशालं बिले|कुसूलकूपकुम्भशालं बिले ६.२.१०२|६.२.१०२|६.२.१०२ कुसूलकूपकुम्भशालं बिले
The words 1. कुसूल 2. कूप 3. कुम्भ and 4. शाला have the acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable before the word बिल।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.103|6.2.103 dik‌shabdaa graamajanapadaakhyaanachaanaraaTeShu|dik‌shabdaa graamajanapadaakhyaanachaanaraaTeShu|dik‌shabdaa graamajanapadaakhyaanachaanaraaTeShu 6.2.103|दिक्‌शब्दा ग्रामजनपदाख्यानचानराटेषु|दिक्‌शब्दा ग्रामजनपदाख्यानचानराटेषु ६.२.१०३|६.२.१०३|६.२.१०३ दिक्‌शब्दा ग्रामजनपदाख्यानचानराटेषु
Words expressing (in space of time) have acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable when followed by a word denoting a village or a country or a narrative before the word चानराट।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.104|6.2.104 aachaaryopasarjanashchaantevaasini|aachaaryopasarjanashchaantevaasini|aachaaryopasarjanashchaantevaasini 6.2.104|आचार्योपसर्जनश्चान्तेवासिनि|आचार्योपसर्जनश्चान्तेवासिनि ६.२.१०४|६.२.१०४|६.२.१०४ आचार्योपसर्जनश्चान्तेवासिनि
The direction denoting words have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final, before the names of scholars when such names derived from those of their teachers.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.105|6.2.105 uttarapadavRddhau sarvaM cha|uttarapadavRddhau sarvaM cha|uttarapadavRddhau sarvaM cha 6.2.105|उत्तरपदवृद्धौ सर्वं च|उत्तरपदवृद्धौ सर्वं च ६.२.१०५|६.२.१०५|६.२.१०५ उत्तरपदवृद्धौ सर्वं च
Words denoting direction and the word सर्व have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final before a word which takes वृद्धि in the first syllable of the second term by सुसर्वार्धाज्जनपदस्य ७.३.१२.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.106|6.2.106 bahuvriihau vishvaM saMJNayaam|bahuvriihau vishvaM saMJNayaam|bahuvriihau vishvaM saMJNayaam 6.2.106|बहुव्रीहौ विश्वं संज्ञयाम्|बहुव्रीहौ विश्वं संज्ञयाम् ६.२.१०६|६.२.१०६|६.२.१०६ बहुव्रीहौ विश्वं संज्ञयाम्
The word विश्व has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final, being first member in a बहुव्रीहि समास , when it is a Name.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.107|6.2.107 udaraashveShuShu|udaraashveShuShu|udaraashveShuShu 6.2.107|उदराश्वेषुषु|उदराश्वेषुषु ६.२.१०७|६.२.१०७|६.२.१०७ उदराश्वेषुषु
The first member in a बहुव्रीहि समास , before the words 1. उदर 2. अश्व and 3. इषु , gets acute accent (उदात्त) on the final syllable when the compound denotes a Name.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.108|6.2.108 xepe|xepe|xepe 6.2.108|क्षेपे|क्षेपे ६.२.१०८|६.२.१०८|६.२.१०८ क्षेपे
A word before 1. उदर 2. अश्व and 3. इषु in a बहुव्रीहि समास gets the acute accent (उदात्त) on the final, when reproach is meant.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.109|6.2.109 nadii bandhuni|nadii bandhuni|nadii bandhuni 6.2.109|नदी बन्धुनि|नदी बन्धुनि ६.२.१०९|६.२.१०९|६.२.१०९ नदी बन्धुनि
In a बहुव्रीहि समास having the word बन्धु as its second member, the first member ending in the feminine affix ई (नदी word) has the ac on its final syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.110|6.2.110 niShThopasargapuurvamanyatarasyaam‌|niShThopasargapuurvamanyatarasyaam‌|niShThopasargapuurvamanyatarasyaam‌ 6.2.110|निष्ठोपसर्गपूर्वमन्यतरस्याम्‌|निष्ठोपसर्गपूर्वमन्यतरस्याम्‌ ६.२.११०|६.२.११०|६.२.११० निष्ठोपसर्गपूर्वमन्यतरस्याम्‌
In a बहुव्रीहि समास a Participle in a क्त preceded by a preposition, standing as the first member of the compound has optionally acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.111|6.2.111 uttarapadaadiH|uttarapadaadiH|uttarapadaadiH 6.2.111|उत्तरपदादिः|उत्तरपदादिः ६.२.१११|६.२.१११|६.२.१११ उत्तरपदादिः
In the following sūtras up to कुण्डं वनम् ६.२.१३६, inclusive, should always be supplied the phrase 'the first syllable of the second member has the acute accent (उदात्त)'.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.112|6.2.112 karNo varNalaxaNaat‌|karNo varNalaxaNaat‌|karNo varNalaxaNaat‌ 6.2.112|कर्णो वर्णलक्षणात्‌|कर्णो वर्णलक्षणात्‌ ६.२.११२|६.२.११२|६.२.११२ कर्णो वर्णलक्षणात्‌
In a बहुव्रीहि समास the word कर्ण standing as second member has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when it is preceded by a word denoting colour or mark.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.113|6.2.113 saMJNaupamyayoshcha|saMJNaupamyayoshcha|saMJNaupamyayoshcha 6.2.113|संज्ञौपम्ययोश्च|संज्ञौपम्ययोश्च ६.२.११३|६.२.११३|६.२.११३ संज्ञौपम्ययोश्च
In a बहुव्रीहि समास the second member कर्ण has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when the compound denotes a Name or Resemblance.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.114|6.2.114 kaNThapRShThagriivaajaMghaM cha|kaNThapRShThagriivaajaMghaM cha|kaNThapRShThagriivaajaMghaM cha 6.2.114|कण्ठपृष्ठग्रीवाजंघं च|कण्ठपृष्ठग्रीवाजंघं च ६.२.११४|६.२.११४|६.२.११४ कण्ठपृष्ठग्रीवाजंघं च
In a बहुव्रीहि समास expressing a Name or comparison the second members 1. कण्ठ 2. पृष्ठ 3. ग्रीवा and 4. जङ्घा have acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.115|6.2.115 shRngamavasthaayaaM cha|shRngamavasthaayaaM cha|shRngamavasthaayaaM cha 6.2.115|शृङ्गमवस्थायां च|शृङ्गमवस्थायां च ६.२.११५|६.२.११५|६.२.११५ शृङ्गमवस्थायां च
In a बहुव्रीहि समास denoting age (as well as a Name or a Resemblance), the second member शृङ्ग gets acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.116|6.2.116 naNJo jaramaramitramRtaaH|naNJo jaramaramitramRtaaH|naNJo jaramaramitramRtaaH 6.2.116|नञो जरमरमित्रमृताः|नञो जरमरमित्रमृताः ६.२.११६|६.२.११६|६.२.११६ नञो जरमरमित्रमृताः
After a Negative Particle, in a बहुव्रीहि समास the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the first syllable of 1. जर 2. मर 3. मित्र and 4. मृत।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.117|6.2.117 sormanasii alomoShasii|sormanasii alomoShasii|sormanasii alomoShasii 6.2.117|सोर्मनसी अलोमोषसी|सोर्मनसी अलोमोषसी ६.२.११७|६.२.११७|६.२.११७ सोर्मनसी अलोमोषसी
After the adjective सु in a बहुव्रीहि समास a stem ending in मन् and अस् with the exception of लोमन् and उषस् has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.118|6.2.118 kratvaadayashcha|kratvaadayashcha|kratvaadayashcha 6.2.118|क्रत्वादयश्च|क्रत्वादयश्च ६.२.११८|६.२.११८|६.२.११८ क्रत्वादयश्च
After the adjective सु in a बहुव्रीहि समास the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the first syllable of क्रतु etc.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.119|6.2.119 aadyudaattaM dvyach Chandasi|aadyudaattaM dvyach Chandasi|aadyudaattaM dvyach Chandasi 6.2.119|आद्युदात्तं द्व्यच् छन्दसि|आद्युदात्तं द्व्यच् छन्दसि ६.२.११९|६.२.११९|६.२.११९ आद्युदात्तं द्व्यच् छन्दसि
In a बहुव्रीहि समास in the छन्दस् (Vedas) a word of two syllables with acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when preceded by सु gets acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.120|6.2.120 viiraviiryau cha|viiraviiryau cha|viiraviiryau cha 6.2.120|वीरवीर्यौ च|वीरवीर्यौ च ६.२.१२०|६.२.१२०|६.२.१२० वीरवीर्यौ च
In a बहुव्रीहि समास in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after सु the words वीर and वीर्य have acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-1st-term

6.2.121|6.2.121 kuulatiiratuulamuulashaalaa.axasamamavyayiibhaave|kuulatiiratuulamuulashaalaa.axasamamavyayiibhaave|kuulatiiratuulamuulashaalaa.axasamamavyayiibhaave 6.2.121|कूलतीरतूलमूलशालाऽक्षसममव्ययीभावे|कूलतीरतूलमूलशालाऽक्षसममव्ययीभावे ६.२.१२१|६.२.१२१|६.२.१२१ कूलतीरतूलमूलशालाऽक्षसममव्ययीभावे
In an अव्ययीभाव समास the following second terms have acute accent (उदात्त) on their first syllable - 1. कूल 2. तीर 3. तूल 4. मूल 5. शाला 6. अक्ष and 7. सम।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.122|6.2.122 kaMsamanthashuurpapaayyakaaNDaM dvigau|kaMsamanthashuurpapaayyakaaNDaM dvigau|kaMsamanthashuurpapaayyakaaNDaM dvigau 6.2.122|कंसमन्थशूर्पपाय्यकाण्डं द्विगौ|कंसमन्थशूर्पपाय्यकाण्डं द्विगौ ६.२.१२२|६.२.१२२|६.२.१२२ कंसमन्थशूर्पपाय्यकाण्डं द्विगौ
In a द्विगु समास (Numeral Determinative Compound) the following second members get acute accent (उदात्त) on their first syllable - 1. कंस 2. मन्थ 3. शूर्प 3. पाय्य and 4. काण्ड।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.123|6.2.123 tatpuruShe shaalaayaaM napuMsake|tatpuruShe shaalaayaaM napuMsake|tatpuruShe shaalaayaaM napuMsake 6.2.123|तत्पुरुषे शालायां नपुंसके|तत्पुरुषे शालायां नपुंसके ६.२.१२३|६.२.१२३|६.२.१२३ तत्पुरुषे शालायां नपुंसके
The word शाला at the end of a तत्-पुरुष समास when exhibited in the Neuter has acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.124|6.2.124 kanthaa cha|kanthaa cha|kanthaa cha 6.2.124|कन्था च|कन्था च ६.२.१२४|६.२.१२४|६.२.१२४ कन्था च
In a Neuter तत्-पुरुष समास ending in कन्था the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the first syllable of the second member.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.125|6.2.125 aadishchihaNaadiinaam|aadishchihaNaadiinaam|aadishchihaNaadiinaam 6.2.125|आदिश्चिहणादीनाम्|आदिश्चिहणादीनाम् ६.२.१२५|६.२.१२५|६.२.१२५ आदिश्चिहणादीनाम्
In a Neuter तत्-पुरुष समास ending in कन्था the first syllable of चिहण etc. have the acute accent (उदात्त).<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.126|6.2.126 chelakheTakaTukakaaNDaM garhaayaam|chelakheTakaTukakaaNDaM garhaayaam|chelakheTakaTukakaaNDaM garhaayaam 6.2.126|चेलखेटकटुककाण्डं गर्हायाम्|चेलखेटकटुककाण्डं गर्हायाम् ६.२.१२६|६.२.१२६|६.२.१२६ चेलखेटकटुककाण्डं गर्हायाम्
The words 1. चेल 2. खेट 3. कटुक and 4. काण्ड at the end of a तत्-पुरुष समास have acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when a reproach is meant.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.127|6.2.127 chiiramupamaanam‌|chiiramupamaanam‌|chiiramupamaanam‌ 6.2.127|चीरमुपमानम्‌|चीरमुपमानम्‌ ६.२.१२७|६.२.१२७|६.२.१२७ चीरमुपमानम्‌
The word चीर at the end of a तत्-पुरुष समास has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when something is compared with it.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.128|6.2.128 palalasuupashaakaM mishre|palalasuupashaakaM mishre|palalasuupashaakaM mishre 6.2.128|पललसूपशाकं मिश्रे|पललसूपशाकं मिश्रे ६.२.१२८|६.२.१२८|६.२.१२८ पललसूपशाकं मिश्रे
In a तत्-पुरुष समास ending in 1. पलल 2. सूप and 3. शाक the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the first syllable of these when the compound denotes a food mixed or seasoned with something.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.129|6.2.129 kuulasuudasthalakarShaaH saMJNaayaam|kuulasuudasthalakarShaaH saMJNaayaam|kuulasuudasthalakarShaaH saMJNaayaam 6.2.129|कूलसूदस्थलकर्षाः संज्ञायाम्|कूलसूदस्थलकर्षाः संज्ञायाम् ६.२.१२९|६.२.१२९|६.२.१२९ कूलसूदस्थलकर्षाः संज्ञायाम्
The words 1. कूल 2. सूद 3. स्थल and 4. कर्ष have acute accent (उदात्त) on their first syllable when at the end of a तत्-पुरुष समास denoting a Name.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.130|6.2.130 akarmadhaaraye raajyam|akarmadhaaraye raajyam|akarmadhaaraye raajyam 6.2.130|अकर्मधारये राज्यम्|अकर्मधारये राज्यम् ६.२.१३०|६.२.१३०|६.२.१३० अकर्मधारये राज्यम्
The word राज्यम् has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when at the end of a तत्-पुरुष समास which is not a कर्मधारय समास ।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.131|6.2.131 vargyaadayashcha|vargyaadayashcha|vargyaadayashcha 6.2.131|वर्ग्यादयश्च|वर्ग्यादयश्च ६.२.१३१|६.२.१३१|६.२.१३१ वर्ग्यादयश्च
At the end of a non-कर्मधारय तत्-पुरुष समास the words वर्ग्य etc. have acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.132|6.2.132 putraH puMbhyaH|putraH puMbhyaH|putraH puMbhyaH 6.2.132|पुत्रः पुंभ्यः|पुत्रः पुंभ्यः ६.२.१३२|६.२.१३२|६.२.१३२ पुत्रः पुंभ्यः
The word पुत्र coming after a Masculine noun in a तत्-पुरुष समास has a acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.133|6.2.133 naachaaryaraajartviksaMyuktaJNaatyaakhyebhyaH|naachaaryaraajartviksaMyuktaJNaatyaakhyebhyaH|naachaaryaraajartviksaMyuktaJNaatyaakhyebhyaH 6.2.133|नाचार्यराजर्त्विक्संयुक्तज्ञात्याख्येभ्यः|नाचार्यराजर्त्विक्संयुक्तज्ञात्याख्येभ्यः ६.२.१३३|६.२.१३३|६.२.१३३ नाचार्यराजर्त्विक्संयुक्तज्ञात्याख्येभ्यः
The word पुत्र does not have an acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when preceded by a word which falls under the category of teachers, kings, priests, wife's relations and agnates and cognates.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.134|6.2.134 chuurNaadiinyapraaNiShaShThyaaH|chuurNaadiinyapraaNiShaShThyaaH|chuurNaadiinyapraaNiShaShThyaaH 6.2.134|चूर्णादीन्यप्राणिषष्ठ्याः|चूर्णादीन्यप्राणिषष्ठ्याः ६.२.१३४|६.२.१३४|६.२.१३४ चूर्णादीन्यप्राणिषष्ठ्याः
The words चूर्ण etc. in a तत्-पुरुष समास have acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable when preceding word ends in a Genitive 6th-Case and does not denote a living being.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.135|6.2.135 ShaT cha kaaNDaadiini|ShaT cha kaaNDaadiini|ShaT cha kaaNDaadiini 6.2.135|षट् च काण्डादीनि|षट् च काण्डादीनि ६.२.१३५|६.२.१३५|६.२.१३५ षट् च काण्डादीनि
The six words - 1. काण्ड 2. चीर 3. पलल 4. सूप 5. शाक and 6. कूल of sūtras ६.२.१२६-129 preceded by a non-living Genitive 6th-Case word have acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.136|6.2.136 kuNDaM vanam|kuNDaM vanam|kuNDaM vanam 6.2.136|कुण्डं वनम्|कुण्डं वनम् ६.२.१३६|६.२.१३६|६.२.१३६ कुण्डं वनम्
The word कुण्ड at the end of a तत्-पुरुष समास denoting 'a wood or forest' has acute accent (उदात्त) on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.137|6.2.137 prakRtyaa bhagaalam|prakRtyaa bhagaalam|prakRtyaa bhagaalam 6.2.137|प्रकृत्या भगालम्|प्रकृत्या भगालम् ६.२.१३७|६.२.१३७|६.२.१३७ प्रकृत्या भगालम्
The word भगाल at the end of a तत्-पुरुष समास preserves its original accent.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.138|6.2.138 shiternityaabahvajbahuvriihaavabhasat‌|shiternityaabahvajbahuvriihaavabhasat‌|shiternityaabahvajbahuvriihaavabhasat‌ 6.2.138|शितेर्नित्याबह्वज्बहुव्रीहावभसत्‌|शितेर्नित्याबह्वज्बहुव्रीहावभसत्‌ ६.२.१३८|६.२.१३८|६.२.१३८ शितेर्नित्याबह्वज्बहुव्रीहावभसत्‌
After शिति , a word retains in a बहुव्रीहि समास its original accent when it is always of not more than two syllables with the exception of भसद्.।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.139|6.2.139 gatikaarakopapadaat‌ kRt‌|gatikaarakopapadaat‌ kRt‌|gatikaarakopapadaat‌ kRt‌ 6.2.139|गतिकारकोपपदात्‌ कृत्‌|गतिकारकोपपदात्‌ कृत्‌ ६.२.१३९|६.२.१३९|६.२.१३९ गतिकारकोपपदात्‌ कृत्‌
In a तत्-पुरुष समास a word ending in a कृत् affix preserves its original accent when preceded by an indeclinable called गति -- गतिश्च १.४.६०, or a noun standing in intimate relation to a verb (कारक) or any word which gives occasion for compounding (उपपद -- तत्रोपपदं सप्तमीस्थम्‌ ३.१.९२)<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.140|6.2.140 ubhe vanaspatyaadiShu yugapat‌|ubhe vanaspatyaadiShu yugapat‌|ubhe vanaspatyaadiShu yugapat‌ 6.2.140|उभे वनस्पत्यादिषु युगपत्‌|उभे वनस्पत्यादिषु युगपत्‌ ६.२.१४०|६.२.१४०|६.२.१४० उभे वनस्पत्यादिषु युगपत्‌
In वनस्पति etc. both members of the compound preserve their original accent simultaneously.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.141|6.2.141 devataadvaMdve cha|devataadvaMdve cha|devataadvaMdve cha 6.2.141|देवताद्वंद्वे च|देवताद्वंद्वे च ६.२.१४१|६.२.१४१|६.२.१४१ देवताद्वंद्वे च
In a द्वन्द compound of the Names of Divinities, both the members retain their original accent.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.142|6.2.142 nottarapade.anudaattaadaavapRthiviirudrapuuShamanthiShu|nottarapade.anudaattaadaavapRthiviirudrapuuShamanthiShu|nottarapade.anudaattaadaavapRthiviirudrapuuShamanthiShu 6.2.142|नोत्तरपदेऽनुदात्तादावपृथिवीरुद्रपूषमन्थिषु|नोत्तरपदेऽनुदात्तादावपृथिवीरुद्रपूषमन्थिषु ६.२.१४२|६.२.१४२|६.२.१४२ नोत्तरपदेऽनुदात्तादावपृथिवीरुद्रपूषमन्थिषु
In a द्वन्द compound of the Names of Divinities, both members of the compound simultaneously do not retain their accent when the first syllable of the second word is अनुदात्त with the exception of 1.पृथिवी 2. रुद्र 3. पूष and 4. मन्थिन्।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.143|6.2.143 antaH|antaH|antaH 6.2.143|अन्तः|अन्तः ६.२.१४३|६.२.१४३|६.२.१४३ अन्तः
In the following sūtras up to the end of this chapter should always be supplied the phrase 'the last syllable of the second member has the acute accent (उदात्त)'.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.144|6.2.144 thaathaghaNJktaajabitrakaaNaam|thaathaghaNJktaajabitrakaaNaam|thaathaghaNJktaajabitrakaaNaam 6.2.144|थाथघञ्क्ताजबित्रकाणाम्|थाथघञ्क्ताजबित्रकाणाम् ६.२.१४४|६.२.१४४|६.२.१४४ थाथघञ्क्ताजबित्रकाणाम्
The last syllable of the second member has the acute accent (उदात्त) in the verbal nouns ending in 1. थ 2. अथ 3. घञ् 4. क्त 5. अच् 6. अप् 7. इत्र and 8. क when preceded by a गति , a कारक or an उपपद -- गतिकारकोपपदात्‌ कृत्‌ ६.२.१३९<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.145|6.2.145 suupamaanaat‌ ktaH|suupamaanaat‌ ktaH|suupamaanaat‌ ktaH 6.2.145|सूपमानात्‌ क्तः|सूपमानात्‌ क्तः ६.२.१४५|६.२.१४५|६.२.१४५ सूपमानात्‌ क्तः
The Participle in क्त has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when it is preceded by सु or by a word with which the second member is compared.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.146|6.2.146 saMJNaayaamanaachitaadiinaam‌|saMJNaayaamanaachitaadiinaam‌|saMJNaayaamanaachitaadiinaam‌ 6.2.146|संज्ञायामनाचितादीनाम्‌|संज्ञायामनाचितादीनाम्‌ ६.२.१४६|६.२.१४६|६.२.१४६ संज्ञायामनाचितादीनाम्‌
The Participle in क्त has acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable when preceded by a गति or a कारक or an उपपद if the compound denotes a Name, but not in आचित etc.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.147|6.2.147 pravRddhaadiinaaM cha|pravRddhaadiinaaM cha|pravRddhaadiinaaM cha 6.2.147|प्रवृद्धादीनां च|प्रवृद्धादीनां च ६.२.१४७|६.२.१४७|६.२.१४७ प्रवृद्धादीनां च
The word प्रवृद्ध etc. ending in क्त have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.148|6.2.148 kaarakaaddattashrutayorevaashiShi|kaarakaaddattashrutayorevaashiShi|kaarakaaddattashrutayorevaashiShi 6.2.148|कारकाद्दत्तश्रुतयोरेवाशिषि|कारकाद्दत्तश्रुतयोरेवाशिषि ६.२.१४८|६.२.१४८|६.२.१४८ कारकाद्दत्तश्रुतयोरेवाशिषि
The final of Part Participles दत्त and श्रुत alone have the acute accent (उदात्त) in a compound denoting a Name and a Benediction, the preceding word being a word standing in close relation to an action (कारक)।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.149|6.2.149 itthambhuutena kRtamiti cha|itthambhuutena kRtamiti cha|itthambhuutena kRtamiti cha 6.2.149|इत्थम्भूतेन कृतमिति च|इत्थम्भूतेन कृतमिति च ६.२.१४९|६.२.१४९|६.२.१४९ इत्थम्भूतेन कृतमिति च
The Participle in क्त has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when the compound denotes 'done by one in such a condition'.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.150|6.2.150 ano bhaavakarmavachanaH|ano bhaavakarmavachanaH|ano bhaavakarmavachanaH 6.2.150|अनो भावकर्मवचनः|अनो भावकर्मवचनः ६.२.१५०|६.२.१५०|६.२.१५० अनो भावकर्मवचनः
After a कारक as mentioned in कारकाद्दत्तश्रुतयोरेवाशिषि ६.२.१४८, the second member ending in the affix अन and denoting an action in the Abstract or the object (i.e. having the senses of Passive Adjective), has the acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.151|6.2.151 manktinvyaakhyaanashayanaasanasthaanayaajakaadikriitaaH|manktinvyaakhyaanashayanaasanasthaanayaajakaadikriitaaH|manktinvyaakhyaanashayanaasanasthaanayaajakaadikriitaaH 6.2.151|मन्क्तिन्व्याख्यानशयनासनस्थानयाजकादिक्रीताः|मन्क्तिन्व्याख्यानशयनासनस्थानयाजकादिक्रीताः ६.२.१५१|६.२.१५१|६.२.१५१ मन्क्तिन्व्याख्यानशयनासनस्थानयाजकादिक्रीताः
The words ending in मन् or क्तिन् affixes and the words 1. व्याख्यान 2. शयन 3. आसन 4. स्थान and 5. क्रीत as well as याजक etc. have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when at the end of a compound preceded by कारक word.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.152|6.2.152 saptamyaaH puNyam|saptamyaaH puNyam|saptamyaaH puNyam 6.2.152|सप्तम्याः पुण्यम्|सप्तम्याः पुण्यम् ६.२.१५२|६.२.१५२|६.२.१५२ सप्तम्याः पुण्यम्
The word पुण्य has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when preceded by a Noun in the Locative -7th case.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.153|6.2.153 UnaarthakalahaM tRtiiyaayaaH|UnaarthakalahaM tRtiiyaayaaH|UnaarthakalahaM tRtiiyaayaaH 6.2.153|ऊनार्थकलहं तृतीयायाः|ऊनार्थकलहं तृतीयायाः ६.२.१५३|६.२.१५३|६.२.१५३ ऊनार्थकलहं तृतीयायाः
The acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the final of words having the sense of ऊन and of कलह when they are second members in a compound, preceded by a term in the Instrumental -3rd case.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.154|6.2.154 mishraM chaanupasargamasaMdhau|mishraM chaanupasargamasaMdhau|mishraM chaanupasargamasaMdhau 6.2.154|मिश्रं चानुपसर्गमसंधौ|मिश्रं चानुपसर्गमसंधौ ६.२.१५४|६.२.१५४|६.२.१५४ मिश्रं चानुपसर्गमसंधौ
The word मिश्र has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final after an Instrumental -3rd case when it is not joined with any Preposition and does not mean a 'compact or alliance'.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.155|6.2.155 naNJo guNapratiShedhe sampaadyarhahitaalamarthaastaddhitaaH|naNJo guNapratiShedhe sampaadyarhahitaalamarthaastaddhitaaH|naNJo guNapratiShedhe sampaadyarhahitaalamarthaastaddhitaaH 6.2.155|नञो गुणप्रतिषेधे सम्पाद्यर्हहितालमर्थास्तद्धिताः|नञो गुणप्रतिषेधे सम्पाद्यर्हहितालमर्थास्तद्धिताः ६.२.१५५|६.२.१५५|६.२.१५५ नञो गुणप्रतिषेधे सम्पाद्यर्हहितालमर्थास्तद्धिताः
The words formed with the तद्धित affixes denoting 'fitted for that' -- सम्पादिनि ५.१.९९, 'deserving that' -- तद् अर्हति ५.१.६३, 'good for that' -- तस्मै हितम् ५.१.५, 'capable to effect that' -- तस्मै प्रभवति संतापादिभ्यः ५.१.१०१, have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when preceded by the Negative Particle नञ् , when it makes a negation with regard to the above mentioned attributes.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.156|6.2.156 yayatoshchaatadarthe|yayatoshchaatadarthe|yayatoshchaatadarthe 6.2.156|ययतोश्चातदर्थे|ययतोश्चातदर्थे ६.२.१५६|६.२.१५६|६.२.१५६ ययतोश्चातदर्थे
The words formed with the तद्धित affixes य and यत् when not denoting 'useful for that' have acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable after the particle नञ् negating the attribute.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.157|6.2.157 achkaavashaktau|achkaavashaktau|achkaavashaktau 6.2.157|अच्कावशक्तौ|अच्कावशक्तौ ६.२.१५७|६.२.१५७|६.२.१५७ अच्कावशक्तौ
A word formed with the कृत् affixes अच् and क preceded by the particle नञ् has the acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when the meaning is 'not capable'.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.158|6.2.158 aakroshe cha|aakroshe cha|aakroshe cha 6.2.158|आक्रोशे च|आक्रोशे च ६.२.१५८|६.२.१५८|६.२.१५८ आक्रोशे च
A word formed by the कृत् affixes अच् and क preceded by a Negative Particle have an acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when one abuses somebody by that word.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.159|6.2.159 saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam|saMJNaayaam 6.2.159|संज्ञायाम्|संज्ञायाम् ६.२.१५९|६.२.१५९|६.२.१५९ संज्ञायाम्
When abuse is meant, a word preceded by नञ् has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final in denoting a Name.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.160|6.2.160 kRtyokeShNuchchaarvaadayashcha|kRtyokeShNuchchaarvaadayashcha|kRtyokeShNuchchaarvaadayashcha 6.2.160|कृत्योकेष्णुच्चार्वादयश्च|कृत्योकेष्णुच्चार्वादयश्च ६.२.१६०|६.२.१६०|६.२.१६० कृत्योकेष्णुच्चार्वादयश्च
After the Negative Particle, the words formed by the कृत्य affixes -- कृत्याः प्राङ् ण्वुलः ३.१.९५, by उक and इष्णुच् and the words चारु etc. have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.161|6.2.161 vibhaaShaa tRnnannatiixNashuchiShu|vibhaaShaa tRnnannatiixNashuchiShu|vibhaaShaa tRnnannatiixNashuchiShu 6.2.161|विभाषा तृन्नन्नतीक्ष्णशुचिषु|विभाषा तृन्नन्नतीक्ष्णशुचिषु ६.२.१६१|६.२.१६१|६.२.१६१ विभाषा तृन्नन्नतीक्ष्णशुचिषु
After the negative particle, the final of the following is optionally acute accent (उदात्त) - a word formed with the affix तृन् and the words 1. अन्न 2. तीक्ष्ण and 3. शुचि।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.162|6.2.162 bahuvriihaavidametattadbhyaH prathamapuuraNayoH kriyaagaNane|bahuvriihaavidametattadbhyaH prathamapuuraNayoH kriyaagaNane|bahuvriihaavidametattadbhyaH prathamapuuraNayoH kriyaagaNane 6.2.162|बहुव्रीहाविदमेतत्तद्भ्यः प्रथमपूरणयोः क्रियागणने|बहुव्रीहाविदमेतत्तद्भ्यः प्रथमपूरणयोः क्रियागणने ६.२.१६२|६.२.१६२|६.२.१६२ बहुव्रीहाविदमेतत्तद्भ्यः प्रथमपूरणयोः क्रियागणने
In a बहुव्रीहि समास , after the words इदम् , एतद् and तद् the last syllable of प्रथम and of a proper ordinal numeral as the acute accent (उदात्त) when the number of times of an action is meant.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.163|6.2.163 saMkhyaayaaH stanaH|saMkhyaayaaH stanaH|saMkhyaayaaH stanaH 6.2.163|संख्यायाः स्तनः|संख्यायाः स्तनः ६.२.१६३|६.२.१६३|६.२.१६३ संख्यायाः स्तनः
In a बहुव्रीहि समास , after a numeral the word स्तन has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.164|6.2.164 vibhaaShaa Chandasi|vibhaaShaa Chandasi|vibhaaShaa Chandasi 6.2.164|विभाषा छन्दसि|विभाषा छन्दसि ६.२.१६४|६.२.१६४|६.२.१६४ विभाषा छन्दसि
Optionally so, in the छन्दस् (Vedas), the स्तन after a numeral has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.165|6.2.165 saMJNaayaaM mitraajinayoH|saMJNaayaaM mitraajinayoH|saMJNaayaaM mitraajinayoH 6.2.165|संज्ञायां मित्राजिनयोः|संज्ञायां मित्राजिनयोः ६.२.१६५|६.२.१६५|६.२.१६५ संज्ञायां मित्राजिनयोः
In a बहुव्रीहि समास ending in मित्र and अजिन the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the last syllable when the compound denotes a Name.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.166|6.2.166 vyavaayino.antaram|vyavaayino.antaram|vyavaayino.antaram 6.2.166|व्यवायिनोऽन्तरम्|व्यवायिनोऽन्तरम् ६.२.१६६|६.२.१६६|६.२.१६६ व्यवायिनोऽन्तरम्
In a बहुव्रीहि समास ending in अन्तर the acute accent (उदात्त) is on the final after a word which denotes 'that which lies between'.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.167|6.2.167 mukhaM svaangam|mukhaM svaangam|mukhaM svaangam 6.2.167|मुखं स्वाङ्गम्|मुखं स्वाङ्गम् ६.२.१६७|६.२.१६७|६.२.१६७ मुखं स्वाङ्गम्
In a बहुव्रीहि समास the acute accent (उदात्त) is on the final when the second member is मुख 'mouth' i.e. the actual bodily part of an animal and not used metaphorically.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.168|6.2.168 naavyayadik‌shabdagomahatsthuulamuShTipRthuvatsebhyaH|naavyayadik‌shabdagomahatsthuulamuShTipRthuvatsebhyaH|naavyayadik‌shabdagomahatsthuulamuShTipRthuvatsebhyaH 6.2.168|नाव्ययदिक्‌शब्दगोमहत्स्थूलमुष्टिपृथुवत्सेभ्यः|नाव्ययदिक्‌शब्दगोमहत्स्थूलमुष्टिपृथुवत्सेभ्यः ६.२.१६८|६.२.१६८|६.२.१६८ नाव्ययदिक्‌शब्दगोमहत्स्थूलमुष्टिपृथुवत्सेभ्यः
In a बहुव्रीहि समास the acute accent (उदात्त) does not fall on such मुख 'mouth' denoting a real mouth when it comes after an indeclinable and a name of a direction or after 1. गो 2. महत् 3. स्थूल 4. मुष्टि 5. पृथु and 6. वत्स।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.169|6.2.169 niShThopamaanaadanyatarasyaam|niShThopamaanaadanyatarasyaam|niShThopamaanaadanyatarasyaam 6.2.169|निष्ठोपमानादन्यतरस्याम्|निष्ठोपमानादन्यतरस्याम् ६.२.१६९|६.२.१६९|६.२.१६९ निष्ठोपमानादन्यतरस्याम्
In a बहुव्रीहि समास the word मुख denoting 'an actual mouth' has optionally the acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when preceded by a participle in त or by that wherewith something is compared.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.170|6.2.170 jaatikaalasukhaadibhyo.anaachChaadanaat‌ kto.akRtamitapratipannaaH|jaatikaalasukhaadibhyo.anaachChaadanaat‌ kto.akRtamitapratipannaaH|jaatikaalasukhaadibhyo.anaachChaadanaat‌ kto.akRtamitapratipannaaH 6.2.170|जातिकालसुखादिभ्योऽनाच्छादनात्‌ क्तोऽकृतमितप्रतिपन्नाः|जातिकालसुखादिभ्योऽनाच्छादनात्‌ क्तोऽकृतमितप्रतिपन्नाः ६.२.१७०|६.२.१७०|६.२.१७० जातिकालसुखादिभ्योऽनाच्छादनात्‌ क्तोऽकृतमितप्रतिपन्नाः
After a word denoting a species (with the exception of a word for 'garment or covering') and after a time-denoting word as well as after सुख etc. the Participle in the क्त has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final in a बहुव्रीहि समास but not so when the participles are 1. कृत 2. मित 3. प्रतिपन्न।<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.171|6.2.171 vaa jaate|vaa jaate|vaa jaate 6.2.171|वा जाते|वा जाते ६.२.१७१|६.२.१७१|६.२.१७१ वा जाते
After a species (with the exception of a word for 'garment or covering') or a time-denoting word or after सुख etc. in a बहुव्रीहि समास the word जात has optionally acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.172|6.2.172 naNJsubhyaam|naNJsubhyaam|naNJsubhyaam 6.2.172|नञ्सुभ्याम्|नञ्सुभ्याम् ६.२.१७२|६.२.१७२|६.२.१७२ नञ्सुभ्याम्
In a बहुव्रीहि समास formed by the negative particle नञ् or by सु has the acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable of the compound.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.173|6.2.173 kapi puurvam|kapi puurvam|kapi puurvam 6.2.173|कपि पूर्वम्|कपि पूर्वम् ६.२.१७३|६.२.१७३|६.२.१७३ कपि पूर्वम्
In a बहुव्रीहि समास formed by the negative particle नञ् or by सु and ending in the affix कप् -- नद्यृतश्च ५.४.१५३, has acute accent (उदात्त) on the syllable preceding the affix.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.174|6.2.174 hrasvaante.antyaat‌ puurvam|hrasvaante.antyaat‌ puurvam|hrasvaante.antyaat‌ puurvam 6.2.174|ह्रस्वान्तेऽन्त्यात्‌ पूर्वम्|ह्रस्वान्तेऽन्त्यात्‌ पूर्वम् ६.२.१७४|६.२.१७४|६.२.१७४ ह्रस्वान्तेऽन्त्यात्‌ पूर्वम्
When the compound ends in a light vowel the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the syllable before such last, in a बहुव्रीहि समास preceded by नञ् and सु to which the affix कप् -- नद्यृतश्च ५.४.१५३, is added.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.175|6.2.175 bahornaNJvaduttarapadabhuumni|bahornaNJvaduttarapadabhuumni|bahornaNJvaduttarapadabhuumni 6.2.175|बहोर्नञ्वदुत्तरपदभूम्नि|बहोर्नञ्वदुत्तरपदभूम्नि ६.२.१७५|६.२.१७५|६.२.१७५ बहोर्नञ्वदुत्तरपदभूम्नि
A बहुव्रीहि समास with बहु has the same accent as नञ् when it denotes muchness of the object expressed by the second member.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.176|6.2.176 na guNaadayo.avayavaaH|na guNaadayo.avayavaaH|na guNaadayo.avayavaaH 6.2.176|न गुणादयोऽवयवाः|न गुणादयोऽवयवाः ६.२.१७६|६.२.१७६|६.२.१७६ न गुणादयोऽवयवाः
In a बहुव्रीहि समास , after बहु the acute accent (उदात्त) does not fall on the final of गुण etc. when they appear in the compound as ingredient of something else.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.177|6.2.177 upasargaat‌ svaangaM dhruvamaparshu|upasargaat‌ svaangaM dhruvamaparshu|upasargaat‌ svaangaM dhruvamaparshu 6.2.177|उपसर्गात्‌ स्वाङ्गं ध्रुवमपर्शु|उपसर्गात्‌ स्वाङ्गं ध्रुवमपर्शु ६.२.१७७|६.२.१७७|६.२.१७७ उपसर्गात्‌ स्वाङ्गं ध्रुवमपर्शु
A word denoting a part of the body which is constant (and indispensable) with the exception of पर्शु has after a preposition in a बहुव्रीहि समास the acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: समास end acute-2nd-term

6.2.178|6.2.178 vanaM samaase|vanaM samaase|vanaM samaase 6.2.178|वनं समासे|वनं समासे ६.२.१७८|६.२.१७८|६.२.१७८ वनं समासे
After a preposition वन has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final in compounds of every kind.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.179|6.2.179 antaH|antaH|antaH 6.2.179|अन्तः|अन्तः ६.२.१७९|६.२.१७९|६.२.१७९ अन्तः
After अन्तर् the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the final of वन।<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.180|6.2.180 antashcha|antashcha|antashcha 6.2.180|अन्तश्च|अन्तश्च ६.२.१८०|६.२.१८०|६.२.१८० अन्तश्च
The word अन्तर् has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when preceded by a preposition.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.181|6.2.181 na nivibhyaam|na nivibhyaam|na nivibhyaam 6.2.181|न निविभ्याम्|न निविभ्याम् ६.२.१८१|६.२.१८१|६.२.१८१ न निविभ्याम्
The word अन्तर् does not have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final after the prepositions नि and वि।<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.182|6.2.182 parerabhitobhaavimaNDalam|parerabhitobhaavimaNDalam|parerabhitobhaavimaNDalam 6.2.182|परेरभितोभाविमण्डलम्|परेरभितोभाविमण्डलम् ६.२.१८२|६.२.१८२|६.२.१८२ परेरभितोभाविमण्डलम्
After परि a word which expresses something which has both this side and that side, as well as the word मण्डल has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.183|6.2.183 praadasvaangaM saMJNaayaam|praadasvaangaM saMJNaayaam|praadasvaangaM saMJNaayaam 6.2.183|प्रादस्वाङ्गं संज्ञायाम्|प्रादस्वाङ्गं संज्ञायाम् ६.२.१८३|६.२.१८३|६.२.१८३ प्रादस्वाङ्गं संज्ञायाम्
After प्र a, a word which does not denote a part of the body has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when the compound is a name.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.184|6.2.184 nirudakaadiini cha|nirudakaadiini cha|nirudakaadiini cha 6.2.184|निरुदकादीनि च|निरुदकादीनि च ६.२.१८४|६.२.१८४|६.२.१८४ निरुदकादीनि च
The words निरुदकetc. Have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.185|6.2.185 abhermukham|abhermukham|abhermukham 6.2.185|अभेर्मुखम्|अभेर्मुखम् ६.२.१८५|६.२.१८५|६.२.१८५ अभेर्मुखम्
The word मुख has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when preceded by अभि।<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.186|6.2.186 apaachcha|apaachcha|apaachcha 6.2.186|अपाच्च|अपाच्च ६.२.१८६|६.२.१८६|६.२.१८६ अपाच्च
The word मुख has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final after the preposition अप्।<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.187|6.2.187 sphigapuutaviiNaa.anjo.adhvakuxisiiranaamanaama cha|sphigapuutaviiNaa.anjo.adhvakuxisiiranaamanaama cha|sphigapuutaviiNaa.anjo.adhvakuxisiiranaamanaama cha 6.2.187|स्फिगपूतवीणाऽञ्जोऽध्वकुक्षिसीरनामनाम च|स्फिगपूतवीणाऽञ्जोऽध्वकुक्षिसीरनामनाम च ६.२.१८७|६.२.१८७|६.२.१८७ स्फिगपूतवीणाऽञ्जोऽध्वकुक्षिसीरनामनाम च
The words 1. स्फिग 2. पूत 3. वीणा 4. अञ्जस् 5. अध्वम् 6. कुक्षि 6. नामन् and a word denoting 'a plough' have acute accent (उदात्त) on the final when preceded by the preposition अप्।<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.188|6.2.188 adheruparistham|adheruparistham|adheruparistham 6.2.188|अधेरुपरिस्थम्|अधेरुपरिस्थम् ६.२.१८८|६.२.१८८|६.२.१८८ अधेरुपरिस्थम्
After अधि that word which denotes that thing which overlaps or stands upon has the acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.189|6.2.189 anorapradhaanakaniiyasii|anorapradhaanakaniiyasii|anorapradhaanakaniiyasii 6.2.189|अनोरप्रधानकनीयसी|अनोरप्रधानकनीयसी ६.२.१८९|६.२.१८९|६.२.१८९ अनोरप्रधानकनीयसी
After अनु a word which is not the Principal as well as कनीयस् has acute accent (उदात्त) on the final.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.190|6.2.190 puruShashchaanvaadiShTaH|puruShashchaanvaadiShTaH|puruShashchaanvaadiShTaH 6.2.190|पुरुषश्चान्वादिष्टः|पुरुषश्चान्वादिष्टः ६.२.१९०|६.२.१९०|६.२.१९० पुरुषश्चान्वादिष्टः
After अनु the acute accent (उदात्त) falls on the final of पुरुष when it means a man of whom mention was already made.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.191|6.2.191 aterakRtpade|aterakRtpade|aterakRtpade 6.2.191|अतेरकृत्पदे|अतेरकृत्पदे ६.२.१९१|६.२.१९१|६.२.१९१ अतेरकृत्पदे
After अति , a word not formed by a कृत् affix and the word पद have acute accent (उदात्त) on the last syllable.<br><br>Terms: 

6.2.192|6.2.192 neranidhaane|neranidhaane|neranidhaane 6.2.192|नेरनिधाने|नेरनिधाने ६.२.१९२|६.२.१९२|६.२.१९२ नेरनिधाने
