6.2.199|6.2.199 paraadishChandasi bahulam|paraadishChandasi bahulam|paraadishChandasi bahulam 6.2.199|परादिश्छन्दसि बहुलम्|परादिश्छन्दसि बहुलम् ६.२.१९९|६.२.१९९|६.२.१९९ परादिश्छन्दसि बहुलम्
The first syllable of the second member is diversely acutely accented (उदात्त) in the छन्दस् (Vedas).<br><br>Terms: 

6.3.1|6.3.1 aluguttarapade|aluguttarapade|aluguttarapade 6.3.1|अलुगुत्तरपदे|अलुगुत्तरपदे ६.३.१|६.३.१|६.३.१ अलुगुत्तरपदे
In the following sūtras up to विभाषा स्वसृपत्योः ६.३.२४, inclusive, is always to be supplied the phrase 'the elision does not take place before the second member of the compound'.<br><br>Terms: 

6.3.2|6.3.2 pancamyaaH stokaadibhyaH|pancamyaaH stokaadibhyaH|pancamyaaH stokaadibhyaH 6.3.2|पञ्चम्याः स्तोकादिभ्यः|पञ्चम्याः स्तोकादिभ्यः ६.३.२|६.३.२|६.३.२ पञ्चम्याः स्तोकादिभ्यः
The Ablative -5th case-ending after स्तोक etc. is not elided before the second member of a compound.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-Non-elision

6.3.3|6.3.3 ojaHsaho.ambhastamasaH tRtiiyaayaaH|ojaHsaho.ambhastamasaH tRtiiyaayaaH|ojaHsaho.ambhastamasaH tRtiiyaayaaH 6.3.3|ओजःसहोऽम्भस्तमसः तृतीयायाः|ओजःसहोऽम्भस्तमसः तृतीयायाः ६.३.३|६.३.३|६.३.३ ओजःसहोऽम्भस्तमसः तृतीयायाः
The Instrumental -3rd case endings after 1. ओजस् 2. सहस् 3. अम्भस् and 4. तमस् are not elided before the second member of a compound.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-Non-elision

6.3.4|6.3.4 manasaH saMJNaayaam|manasaH saMJNaayaam|manasaH saMJNaayaam 6.3.4|मनसः संज्ञायाम्|मनसः संज्ञायाम् ६.३.४|६.३.४|६.३.४ मनसः संज्ञायाम्
After मनस् when the compound is a Name, the Instrumental -3rd case endings are not elided before the second member.<br><br>Terms: विभक्ति-Non-elision

