7.1.88|7.1.88 bhasya TerlopaH|bhasya TerlopaH|bhasya TerlopaH 7.1.88|भस्य टेर्लोपः|भस्य टेर्लोपः ७.१.८८|७.१.८८|७.१.८८ भस्य टेर्लोपः
The last vowel, with the consonant that follows it, is dropped in . पथिन् 2. मथिन् and 3. ऋभुक्षिन् before a weak case-ending beginning with a vowel (before which the अङ्ग (stem) is called भ -- यचि भम् १.४.१८.<br><br>Terms: Some substitution

