7.1.94|7.1.94 RdushanaspurudaMso.anehasaaM cha|RdushanaspurudaMso.anehasaaM cha|RdushanaspurudaMso.anehasaaM cha 7.1.94|ऋदुशनस्पुरुदंसोऽनेहसां च|ऋदुशनस्पुरुदंसोऽनेहसां च ७.१.९४|७.१.९४|७.१.९४ ऋदुशनस्पुरुदंसोऽनेहसां च
अनङ् (अन्) is substituted for the final of the अङ्ग (stems) ending in ऋ as well as for the final of 1. उशनस् 2. पुरुदंशस् and 3. अनेहस् in the Nominative 1st-Case singular (but not in the Vocative Case singular).<br><br>Terms: अनङ् substitution

7.1.95|7.1.95 tRjvat‌ kroShTuH|tRjvat‌ kroShTuH|tRjvat‌ kroShTuH 7.1.95|तृज्वत्‌ क्रोष्टुः|तृज्वत्‌ क्रोष्टुः ७.१.९५|७.१.९५|७.१.९५ तृज्वत्‌ क्रोष्टुः
The word क्रोष्टु 'a jackal' is treated in the strong cases (with the exception of Vocative Case singular) as if it ended in तृच् (तृ).<br><br>Terms: Some substitution

